window.LYRIAN_DATA = {"version":"0.12.5","races":[{"id":"chimera","name":"Chimera","attributes":"You gain +1 in toughness and +1 in awareness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in either Magic, Survival, Animal Husbandry, Perception, Insight, Linguistics or Artifice.","proficiencies":"You can speak, read and write Common as well as the special dialect of your sub-race.","description":"Chimera are creatures that have been mutated due to magic and have gained sentience. Almost all Chimera can be traced back to areas of high magical concentration and a lifeform that was mutated. Despite being quite varied in physical characteristics, all Chimera are effectively the same race at their core. It is unknown how arcane magic was able to pattern itself in such a way&\n\nFrom Slime Chimera to the more common Feline Chimeras, there are varied sub-races that can be found throughout the world. And those sub-races can vary widely, even within the same phenotypes. Coloration, ear and tail shapes, and even number of physical characteristics. These widely varying phenotypes are broadly categorized in two ways: kanolith and zoalith.\n\nKanolith chimera have limited physical characteristics. Most kanoliths will have ears, tails, or both corresponding to their sub-race. Kanoliths are the most common type of chimera overall and what most will think of when imagining a chimera of any sub-race.\n\nZoalith chimera have exaggerated or prevalent physical characteristics. Fur, scales, replaced or altered limbs, and animalistic face shapes are all examples of zoalith features. This often leads to zoalith chimera having a far more \"bestial\" appearance which can sometimes bring social challenges. While zoalith chimera are overall rarer than kanolith, there are some sub-races that this trend is reversed. Centaurs, harpies, lamiafolk, and slimefolk are all examples of sub-races which trend toward zoalith.","abilities":["Fight or Flight"]},{"id":"demon","name":"Demon","attributes":"You gain +1 in Power and +1 in Reason.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in either Common Knowledge, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice.","proficiencies":"You can speak, read, write Common and Sorthen. You also gain proficiency in one common weapon or +5 skill points in a skill relating to your demon clan.","description":"In Demon lore, they were the descendants of Angels who had rebelled against providence. Losing their angelic wings and methods to absorb the Divine might of Light, they've adapted techniques to burn their own life force to temporarily tap into their powers. The dangerous technique called Divine Release, is highly praised as the pinnacle of a demon's powers.\n\nWhile originally slandered as \"demons\" by humans and the angels of old, the demons have embraced the name as proof of their rebellion.\n\nDemons appear as humanoids, and but have varying secondary characteristics. Some have tiny wings that are devoid of the providence absorbing \"feathers\", while some have various kinds of horns or eye patterns. Some even have pointed ears like the fae.\n\nThe Demon city of Sorthen exists as an aristocratic meritocracy, where the power balance shifts, houses die and new ones are born based on their contribution to society. These Demon houses all grant their offspring a middle name, this name referencing their roles in society from servants to soldiers to scholars. Each family passes down the techniques of their role, specializing for the greatest efficiency. None of these roles are looked down upon, and it is considered an honor to fulfill your purpose to the highest capability. While the tradition of adhering to house societal roles, they are not inflexible. It is not unusual for an individual to carve out a new life path if they demonstrate exceptional merit, and straying from that assigned family role would then not be viewed negatively.\n\nSize: Medium","abilities":["Divine Release","Demonblood Regeneration"]},{"id":"fae","name":"Fae","attributes":"You gain +1 in Agility and +1 in Cunning.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in either Magic, Medicine, Negotiation, Intimidation, Insight.","proficiencies":"You can speak, read and write Sylvan, as well as Common.","description":"The Fae are widely considered the first people that populated Lyra. They are beings that were born from the will of nature and the world itself. Faeries can be quite varied in culture and demeanor, some using their age immortality to achieve great wisdom-- while others might use it to laze about and be merry.\n\nThe most common type of Fae are the High Fae which appear as youthful humanoids with pointed ears and eyes that come in various colors and patterns","abilities":["Faerie Flash"]},{"id":"human","name":"Human","attributes":"You gain +1 in the main stat of your choice and +1 in the substat of your choice.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in any non-crafting or gathering skill of your choice.","proficiencies":"You can speak, read and write Common, as well as another Language of your choice. You also gain proficiency in one common weapon group.","description":"The origin of humans is not quite clear-- a race of generally homogenous characteristics in comparison to the other races. Despite their similarity, humans are varied in nature and have adapted to many different environments. Humans are quick learners and quick to adapt, a haste that is unseen in some of the other races, a byproduct of their generally shorter lifespans.\n\nFor a reason still unknown, the humans are blessed by providence-- the great power of divine light and are born with a special attunement for it regardless of their religion.\n\nSize: Medium","abilities":["Divine Providence","Human Adaptability"]},{"id":"youkai","name":"Youkai","attributes":"You gain +1 in Focus and +1 in Presence.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in either Insight, Intimidation, Magic, Medicine, Negotiation","proficiencies":"You can speak, read and write Kiraran, as well as Common.","description":"Contrary to popular belief, Youkai are not the same as Chimera. Rather than being lifeforms that have attained sentience through magical mutations, Youkai were once ambient magic that binded together to form lifeforms. Hailing from the misty isle of Kirara, the Youkai are the rarest race amongst the population of Lyr.\n\nLike Chimera, the Youkai lineages are divided into Sub-Races.","abilities":["Spiritual Sync"]}],"ancestries":[{"id":"ancient-marionette","name":"Ancient Marionette","description":"Ancient Marionettes: Lost to time and sea, the Ancient Marionettes stand as enigmatic remnants of a past long forgotten. Once components of the colossal arcane superweapon known as a \"Divine Arms\", these constructs now serve as hosts to sentient magic, giving life and consciousness to their once dormant forms. Rescued from the wreckage of a bygone vessel that met its fate in the waters surrounding the Isle of Kirara, these inert marionettes were left on the enchanted shore, their purpose and power seemingly lost to the ages. However, the island's potent, ambient magic, a phenomenon that gives birth to the unique entities known as youkai, saw in these Ancient Marionettes an opportunity - bodies ready to house their formless essence. As the island's pervasive magic seeped into the marionettes, they awoke from their lifeless slumber. The youkai spirits, now housed in these ancient bodies, began to stir, imbuing them with a consciousness that mirrored their own. Thus, the Ancient Marionettes were reborn, not as weapons of war but as sentient beings in their own right, the symbiosis of ancient technology and living magic. Physically, Ancient Marionettes resemble their former selves - intricate, humanoid forms, wrought from an alloy seemingly immune to the ravages of time and sea. Strange, arcane symbols adorn their bodies, pulsating with a soft, ethereal glow that intensifies when they harness their magical abilities. Their eyes, once empty and hollow, now shine with the vibrant spark of sentient life. Despite their imposing exterior, these reborn constructs possess an inherent gentleness, a testament to the youkai spirit within them. They are beings of thought and contemplation, bound by a curiosity of their new existence, their strange past, and the world they find themselves in. The Ancient Marionettes stand as a testament to the transformative power of magic, a symbol of a union between the ancient and the new, and a unique addition to the diverse inhabitants of the Isle of Kirara.\n\nSize: Medium\n\nWinner of the 2023 Alpha Race Creation Contest (Constructs) by PurpleXCompleX."},{"id":"anubis","name":"Anubis","description":"The Anubis are a unique race of Fae from the southwestern region of Telsin, known for their deep respect for life, death, and the natural order. With dark hair, bronze skin, and their unique Jackal-like ears, the Anubis see themselves as guardians of the living and the dead alike. While their own lifespans are exceptionally long, they hold a profound reverence for the brief lives of other beings, viewing them as precious gifts to be treasured even beyond death. This belief extends to the Anubis’ role in mediating spiritual affairs and protecting the deceased from desecration.\n\nRenowned for their honesty and strong sense of karma, the Anubis possess an almost supernatural ability to discern lies, making them respected yet sometimes avoided as arbiters. Their ceremonial attire includes light-colored clothing, adorned with golden jewelry and polished river stones—symbols of lineage often passed down or given as offerings to the deceased.\n\nSkilled at laying disturbed spirits to rest, they hold a complex relationship with necromancy, respecting it when practiced with reverence. Anubis Necromancers act as graveyard caretakers and conduct important funerary rites, roles woven into their cultural fabric and essential to their purpose across the region, which has garnered respect in spiritual circles even as far as Northi.\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"bearfolk","name":"Bearfolk","description":"Bearfolk are a proud and enduring branch of the Chimera, towering humanoids with dense fur, heavy frames, and deep, resonant voices. Most stand a head taller than the average human and carry the strength to match it, yet behind their massive build lies a quiet and thoughtful nature. Bearfolk are often the last to speak up and do so in short sentences, not speaking any more words than are necessary.\n\nTheir culture prizes food, patience, community, and comfort. To a bearfolk, food shared is a sacred bond. Most live in small family holds scattered through the colder reaches of Northi. Their settlements, half-buried in snow and stone, are renowned for their hospitality.\n\nDespite their imposing nature, bearfolk often display surprising cunning. They are famous, perhaps infamous, for their uncanny ability to blend into society. Through sheer confidence or a kind of cosmic absurdity, a bearfolk in a robe and hat can convince entire villages that they are \"definitely not a bear.\" Scholars call this phenomenon Bear Shock, and no one has yet figured out how or why it works.\n\nBearfolk have an uncomplicated and big love for food. To them, a good meal is one of life's purest pleasures and a sign of prosperity hard-earned through long winters and heavy labor. They'll eat nearly anything that fills the belly, but they have an undeniable fondness for sweets: honey, candied fruits, and rare confections that melt on the tongue. Many bearfolk adventurers quietly hoard local delicacies from the regions they visit, trading stories and bites of food with the same enthusiasm others reserve for treasure.\n\nBearfolk adventurers are often wanderers who leave their homes to test their might or seek rare foods from distant lands. Some serve as guardians and caravan escorts, others simply follow their instincts wherever they lead. Their role in parties is usually that of a frontliner, delivering heavy blows with their paws.\n\n\"Full belly, calm heart.\"\n\nSize: M"},{"id":"bullfolk","name":"Bullfolk","description":"Bullfolk are a sub-race of Chimera, native to the rolling foothills around the northern mountains of Northi. Technically the same sub-race as Cowfolk, the extreme sexual dimorphism between Bullfolk and Cowfolk make them physically and visibly distinct. While Cowfolk possess short and curvy figures, Bullfolk tower over those around them with muscular builds. However, it is only the foolish that believe the hulking stature of Bullfolk is a sign of brutish agility and intelligence, as they are quite nimble and some of the most clever architects.\n\nBullfolk culture prizes bonds more than any one thing. Bonds between friends, family, and partners. If a Bullfolk offers you their honest friendship, it is a friendship they will maintain and protect fiercely. If they offer you their partnership, they will never stray. This level of devotion can be off putting to some as it is often devoid of any need or requirement for reciprocation. Sometimes, especially for those used to betrayal in their lives, it feels \"too good to be true\". And many don't get the full extent of their devotion until their Bullfolk friend follows them on a harrowing journey or stands defiantly in front of a monster to protect them. But beware betraying a Bullfolk that has formed that bond with you. Because it is not your friend you will have to worry about, but their family should they ever learn about it.\n\nBullfolk are often craftsmen of some kind and it is common for Bullfolk in a community to be the go-to for any construction needs. Even Bullfolk that never take up the professions of hammer, saw, and forge often have hobbies in whittling, weaving, or even painting. The most untrained Bullfolk will still have a knack for the lay of a foundation, the set of a roof, or the plane of a chair. Handmade and personal gifts are common to receive from a Bullfolk during birthdays, holidays, or special occasions.\n\nBullfolk adventurers are almost always a friend joining someone they care for on a journey, although some simply travel from their homes for the sheer novelty of seeing the rest of the world. They are at home in the frontline, using their size and stature to guard and protect their allies with sheer mass and devastating blows.\n\nAnd importantly: headbutt a Bullfolk at your own risk.\n\nMale only.\n\nSize: M"},{"id":"cait-sith","name":"Cait Sith","description":"Cait Sith are a rare subrace of the fae, distinguished by their dual forms and elusive nature within the realm of Lyr. Originating from the lands of Avalon, Cait Sith often appear as enchanting Fae adorned with delicate cat ears atop their heads, leading many to mistake them for the more common Catfolk. However, their true versatility is revealed in their ability to assume the form of an actual cat, a transformation that many Cait Sith embrace and many stay in for most of their lives. This shapeshifting capability allows them to seamlessly integrate into various environments, particularly human dwellings, where they often masquerade as beloved house cats. Their preference for a relaxed and lounging lifestyle reflects the tranquil culture of Avalon, where comfort and leisure are highly valued. In their feline guise, Cait Sith seek out the warmth and attention of humans, enjoying the care and adoration bestowed upon them. Cait Sith are known to become irked when they do not receive the expected adoration, such as being left milk, leading them to orchestrate mischievous pranks on those who neglect their whims.\n\nDespite their seemingly benign and playful demeanor, Cait Sith harbor a deep-seated animosity towards their mortal enemies, the Black Dogs, also known as Cu Sith. These shapeshifting dog Fae from Sylvan share an intense mutual detest, often culminating in deadly duels that underscore the severity of their rivalry. Beyond their playful tricks, Cait Sith possess a formidable and sinister ability to manipulate the life force of weakened enemies, using this dark magic as a potent weapon to eliminate threats. This unique combination of charm and lethal power makes Cait Sith both captivating and dangerous. Players who choose Cait Sith characters have the possibility of living double lives as they pretend to be normal cats, using trickery and haunting forces to their means. Their intense rivalry with the Black Dogs can also make for some interesting and fun roleplaying moments.\n\nSize: Medium (when not in cat form)"},{"id":"catfolk","name":"Catfolk","description":"The Catfolk, a subrace of the Chimera, are the most populous inhabitants of the world, surpassing even Humans in numbers. Predominantly hailing from the nation of Northi, their agile and instinctual nature once allowed them to dominate vast continents through swift and strategic warfare. Today, their presence is found everywhere, thriving from the enchanted Fae forests of Easter to the tranquil Kiraran Islands. This widespread distribution showcases their remarkable adaptability and resilience, enabling them to flourish in diverse environments and integrate seamlessly with various cultures.\n\nPlaying a Catfolk means embodying grace, agility, and a keen survival instinct. Their heritage as former rulers and fierce warriors grants them a natural prowess in both combat and leadership, making them ideal for roles that require quick thinking and dexterity. Catfolk are fiercely independent yet deeply communal, valuing both personal achievement and the strength of their kin. Whether navigating the political landscapes of Northi’s cities or exploring uncharted wilds, Catfolk characters bring a dynamic blend of tradition and innovation, resilience and adaptability, to any adventuring party\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"centaur","name":"Centaur","description":"Centaurs, a proud subrace of the Chimera, predominantly inhabit the expansive great plains of Northi and extend into the rugged Nuren territories of Axias. Renowned for their formidable size and unmatched speed, Centaurs thrive in open landscapes where they can harness their natural agility to navigate the vast expanses effortlessly. Their preference for the untamed wilderness often keeps them apart from bustling city life, though resilient individuals can be found adapting to urban environments despite the challenges their stature presents. Centaurs live in tight-knit tribal villages, valuing strong familial bonds within their specific tribes over a unified racial identity. This tribal allegiance fosters a deep sense of loyalty and reliability, making each Centaur a steadfast ally and a formidable presence on the battlefield.\n\nHistorically, Centaurs played a crucial role during the Great Divine War by joining the Susururu Rebellion, where their strength and speed were indispensable in both medical evacuation and logistical support. Their legacy as dependable warriors and medics underscores their reputation for being strong, fast, and reliable. However, a dark chapter in their history—enslavement by the Catfolk as mounts—has left lingering distrust towards the Catfolk, shaping their interactions and alliances in the present day. Playing a Centaur means embodying resilience and independence, drawing upon their tribal heritage to navigate both the challenges of the wild and the complexities of a world still healing from past conflicts. Centaur characters bring a unique blend of physical prowess and unwavering loyalty, making them ideal for roles that require both strength and strategic support within any adventuring party.\n\nSize: Large"},{"id":"cowfolk","name":"Cowfolk","description":"Cowfolk are a sub-race of Chimera, native to the rolling foothills around the northern mountains of Northi. Technically the same sub-race as Bullfolk, the extreme sexual dimorphism between Cowfolk and Bullfolk make them physically and visibly distinct. While Bullfolk tower over those around them with muscular builds, Cowfolk possess short and curvy figures. However, it is only the foolish that believe the dainty stature of Cowfolk is a vulnerability, as they are deceptively resilient and strong for their size.\n\nCowfolk culture prizes bonds more than any one thing. Bonds between friends, family, and partners. If a Cowfolk offers you their honest friendship, it is a friendship they will maintain and protect fiercely. If they offer you their partnership, they will never stray. This level of devotion can be off putting to some as it is often devoid of any need or requirement for reciprocation. Sometimes, especially for those used to betrayal in their lives, it feels \"too good to be true\". And many don't get the full extent of their devotion until their Cowfolk friend follows them on a harrowing journey or stands defiantly in front of a monster to protect them. But beware betraying a Cowfolk that has formed that bond with you. Because it is not your friend you will have to worry about, but their family should they ever learn about it.\n\nWhen they settle in one place for long enough, Cowfolk often get incredibly domestic and there has never been an account of an uncomfortable or unwelcoming Cowfolk home. It doesn't matter if it's a home, an inn room, or a long term camp site, leave a Cowfolk in one place for long enough and you'll begin to find trinkets, warm blankets, hand made cushions, and well stocked food supplies building up over time. However, they are rarely tied down to any location and will cheerfully pack everything up or even leave things behind to continue traveling.\n\nCowfolk adventurers are almost always a friend joining someone they care for on a journey, although some simply travel from their homes for the sheer novelty of seeing the rest of the world. They often take up frontline roles to directly support or protect their friends as a sturdy foundation of any party's composition.\n\nAnd most importantly: never, ever ask a Cowfolk for her milk unless you share a very, very close bond with her.\n\nFemale only\n\nSize: M"},{"id":"cu-sith","name":"Cu Sith","description":"Cu Sith are a rare subrace of Fae, distinguished by their dual forms and steadfast nature. They originated from the lands of Sylvan within Easter and appear as enchanting, dogfolk-like Fae with dog ears atop their heads and emotive tails. Their true forms, however, are that of a small or medium sized dog, indistinguishable from any normal dog. This shapeshifting allows them to blend into most environments, especially areas with other races, where they sometimes take on the role of beloved pet or guardian. They can form strong bonds with others in this guise and history is full of stories of mysteriously intelligent dogs caring for their owners, rescuing children, or driving off attackers from families and villages.\n\nOne particularly strange series of events in history involved the royal family pet of the Kingdom of Sayce. Located on the eastern edge of Northi on the shores of Sayce Lake, the small kingdom held a double dominating trade position of controlling lake and river travel in eastern Northi and also airship travel as they benefited from a major leyline running through the kingdom. Shortly before King Leonard Rune Leon of Northi began his push for unifying the entire country, the Trehaerne family colluded with the neighboring Kingdom of Eynion in an attempt to overthrow the Sayce’s and take control of the Kingdom by allowing assassins to stage in their estate. If things had gone to plan, the entire Sayce family would have been wiped out and the Trehaerne’s would have inherited the throne. However, in a series of unbelievable events, the Sayce family dog tripped up, foiled, uncovered, and in one account, even took up a sword in his jaws and fought off an assassin when he went directly after Princess Lowri in a furious duel. The machinations of the Trehaerne family and the Kingdom of Eynion was presented to King Leonard and justice was seen to, the Kingdom of Sayce was one of the first to join the growing movement of unification. After that event, regardless of the truth behind the more exaggerated stories, the Sayce Royal Flag has included the silhouette of that dog.\n\nBecause of their loyal and dedicated nature, Cu Sith have a deep hatred toward the flighty and cruel Cait Sith. The shapeshifting cats from Avalon share this mutual detestment and this often leads to deadly duels. It is speculated that Cu Sith began to venture out into the wider world beyond Easter as a direct opposition to the Cait Sith and to protect others from being taken advantage of. The Cu Sith’s haunting bark is one of their most useful tools in driving off or defeating Cait Sith and also reinforces the perception of the deep animosity between cats and dogs.\n\nSize: M"},{"id":"dogfolk","name":"Dogfolk","description":"Dogfolk are renowned for their unwavering culture of loyalty and honor, embodying the virtues that make them esteemed allies and steadfast companions within the realm of Lyr. Their deep-seated sense of duty often leads them to trust and support those to whom they have sworn allegiance, even in the face of betrayal. This inherent trustworthiness has, unfortunately, made Dogfolk susceptible to exploitation throughout history. Prior to the reign of King Leo of Northi, the fragmented kingdoms and city-states of the Catfolk frequently abused the Dogfolk’s loyalty, coercing them into servitude and neglecting their rightful honor. King Leo's ascension marked a pivotal shift, as he championed the protection of Dogfolk rights and endeavored to eradicate the oppressive practices that had long plagued them. While Queen Renia has largely upheld King Leo’s reforms, some remnants of the old abuses linger, maintaining a delicate balance of power and respect.\n\nDue to their intense culture of loyalty and honor, Dogfolk are celebrated as the finest bodyguards in all of Lyr, their dedication making them virtually impervious to bribery or betrayal. This steadfastness ensures that they remain reliable protectors, whether guarding noble estates or adventuring parties traversing treacherous landscapes. Those Dogfolk who do commit betrayal, are properly dealt with by their own—bearing the mark of a torn or cropped ears. Players who choose to embody a Dogfolk character can expect to play roles that emphasize loyalty, protection, and honor, making them ideal for those who wish to portray loyal retainers or powerful guardians.\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"dryad","name":"Dryad","description":"Dryads, an enchanting subrace of the Fae, are deeply intertwined with the natural world, making them rare visitors beyond the verdant expanses of their forest homes. Predominantly hailing from the enchanted woods of Easter, a select few have established their presence in the forest territories of Susururu in Northi. While urban environments are seldom their preference, some Dryads venture into cities driven by necessity or purpose, often finding solace only in their work as they navigate the concrete jungles far from their beloved woodlands. Their existence is a harmonious blend of isolation and duty, maintaining a delicate balance between their innate connection to nature and the demands of the wider world.\n\nCentral to Dryad culture is the sacred tradition of planting a new tree with each birth, symbolizing a celebration of life and the enduring bond within their communities. These family groves serve as living testaments to their heritage, meticulously tended by each generation to honor their lineage and the cycle of life. Regardless of where their paths may lead, Dryads are bound by an unwavering commitment to return and pay respects to their families, reinforcing the importance of kinship and continuity. Visually, Dryads are a breathtaking embodiment of nature's diversity, adorned with green or leafy hair, plant-like or wooden skin, and an array of natural features that reflect their individual connection to the flora around them. Playing a Dryad allows one to channel the grace and resilience of the forest, bringing a profound sense of harmony and natural beauty to any adventuring party.\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"dullahan","name":"Dullahan","description":"The Dullahan are a subspecies of Fae that are often shunned even from Fae society due to their association with death. Dullahan are able to subconsciously feel death and are in some way pulled towards it. For this reason, most Dullahan end up leaving the Fae society of Easter. The long lifespans of the Fae and the relative stability of their lands make deaths a rarity. Dullahan have little concept of family, and a child Dullahan matures within a year. In non-fae society, Dullahan are unjustly feared and reviled as the harbingers of death as it follows either shortly after a Dullahan appears or it appears right before a Dullahan does. Because of this, it is rare for a Dullahan to ever truly settle down in a place and even most travelling Dullahan have a way to hide their appearance. Male Dullahan often have to resort to magic, while female ones can get away with a hooded cloak and good head placement.\n\nDullahan have two distinctively different appearances, similar to the Kanolith and Zoalith variants of Chimera's. Regardless of the variant, they share that the Dullahan is a humanoid figure that is clad almost entirely in armor. The male version of a Dullahan is commonly found without a head all together, where as the female Dullahan tends to carry a Fae head with her oftentimes carrying it in her arms. Curiously enough, this armor is normally entirely decorative and offers no more protection than normal flesh would. It is only when a Dullahan picks up a suit of armor and merges it with themselves that their armor becomes resilient.\n\nDullahan adventurers are rare and viewed with mixed opinions. Some believe in the superstition that they cause death and treat it with caution. Others view their attraction to death as either a free warning sign or a hint as to where money could be found. Personality wise, Dullahans often have a rather morbid sense of humor and a nihilistic outlook on the world. They struggle to make meaningful connections but value the ones that they do.\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"gnome","name":"Gnome","description":"Gnomes, often referred to as \"mine faeries,\" are a reclusive subrace of the Fae known for their curiosity and mastery of the earth's hidden treasures. Preferring the solitude of subterranean environments, Gnomes are predominantly found throughout the foothills of Easter's Mountains, with a resilient few making their homes in the depths of Mt. Merlin in Northi. Their affinity for hunting and uncovering buried riches drives them to explore the intricate network of tunnels and caverns, where their adept burrowing skills and knowledge of the terrain set them apart from other Fae. This solitary nature fosters a culture of independence and self-reliance, as many Gnomes choose to embark on treasure hunts alone, guided by their own instincts and expertise.\n\nEquipped with the unique ability to shape their mana into formidable claws, Gnomes effortlessly carve through earth and stone, creating intricate tunnels or devising cunning pitfalls to outwit their adversaries. This magical prowess not only enhances their efficiency in excavation and exploration but also serves as a strategic advantage in defending their hard-earned treasures. Playing a Gnome means embracing a life of exploration and discovery, leveraging their resourcefulness and dexterity to navigate both the physical and magical challenges of the world. Gnome characters bring a blend of resilience, surprise, and unwavering determination to any adventuring party, making them great teammates who can create unique tactical advantages.\n\nSize: Small"},{"id":"harpy","name":"Harpy","description":"Harpies are a prideful race of Chimera, originally inhabiting the foothills of Mt. Merlin, where their natural command over the skies first took flight. Renowed for their aerial prowess, every Harpy child is given a swallow to raise as a pet, carefully studying the birds' unpredictable aerial acrobatics to hone their own flying skills. This early training instills young Harpies with a fierce pride and confidence in their wings, reinforcing the significance of flight to their cultural identity. As they mature, they become adept aerial hunters, using their keen perception and swift reflexes to hunt various hard to reach game on the sheer cliffs.\n\nIn the lower elevations of their homes, the Harpy clans maintain a steady relationship with the Tengu, who dwell in the colder, snowier peaks of Mt. Merlin. Both groups gather periodically to train together, testing their skills in friendly competitions and forging bonds through trade. Because Harpies reside closer to the more accessible areas of Lyr, they are often the more visible face of this winged alliance, facilitating most interactions between the Tengu and the main population.\n\nPlayers that want to express skyborne freedom will find Harpies to be an ideal choice.\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"high-fae","name":"High Fae","description":"The High Fae, the most populous subrace among the Fae, are the heart of Easter's capitals. Dominating the grand cities of Avalon and Sylvan, these urban strongholds have grown into the largest metropolises in the region, attracting Fae from all corners of the world. Unlike their more reclusive kin, High Fae embrace innovation and possess an insatiable wanderlust, driving their rapid expansion and fostering a dynamic society where tradition meets progress. Despite their affinity for forming a great society, High Fae remain deeply connected to nature, seamlessly blending architectural marvels with the natural landscapes that surround them.\n\nPossessing eyes imbued with powerful arcane circuits, all Fae can create minor distortions in the minds of others, but the High Fae have honed this ability to extraordinary levels. They can manipulate the fabric of space with precision, allowing them to teleport at will, a skill that grants them unparalleled agility and strategic advantage both in daily life and in the heat of conflict. Playing a High Fae means embodying a blend of grace, ingenuity, and magical prowess, making them ideal for roles that require both creativity and tactical finesse. Their unique abilities and forward-thinking mindset enable High Fae characters to navigate complex social structures and adapt swiftly to ever-changing circumstances.\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"horse-folk","name":"Horse-Folk","description":"Horse-folk are Kanolith versions of Centaurs. (Placeholder)"},{"id":"jiangshi","name":"Jiangshi","description":"Jiangshi, a subrace of Youkai, are beings that inhabit and reanimate dead bodies. When a Jiangshi is born from a Youkai parent, a mitama—the undeveloped Youkai spirit—is inserted into the corpse of a physical being, such as a Human or Chimera. A distinctive talisman is affixed to their head, signifying their status and anchoring their existence within the host body. This bond prevents the corpse from decaying and grants the Jiangshi the ability to restore the dead body and benefit from healing, making them resilient on the battlefield. Predominantly found within the confines of Kirara, Jiangshi are rare and often face discrimination in other nations due to their unsettling forms and their relentless ferocity in combat, where they operate without experiencing pain or fatigue.\n\nPlaying a Jiangshi involves embodying both strength and vulnerability. The unbreakable bond between the Jiangshi and their host body means that any severe damage to the corpse results in the Jiangshi's demise, introducing a critical vulnerability despite their formidable nature. In regions outside of Kirara, Jiangshi often encounter mistrust and prejudice. Additionally, a rising trend sees non-Youkai individuals traveling to Kirara to offer the corpses of their loved ones as hosts, driven by a deep desire to reconnect with those who have passed. This dynamic adds layers of emotional complexity and narrative tension for Jiangshi characters, who must navigate their powerful abilities alongside societal challenges. Jiangshi bring a unique combination of endurance, and a rich backstory to any adventuring party, making them compelling choices for players seeking depth and roleplaying potential.\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"kitsune","name":"Kitsune","description":"Kitsune are the most prevalent subrace of Youkai, enchanting the world with their graceful presence. Manifesting as graceful fox spirits adorned with multiple tails, each tail symbolizes their age, wisdom, and magical prowess. Renowned for their mastery of illusions and arcane arts, Kitsune seamlessly blend deception and enchantment, making them formidable sorcerers and cunning tricksters. As the first Youkai to unite and establish a cohesive society, Kitsune laid the foundational stone for Youkai civilization on the mist-shrouded Kiraran Isles, a region rich in magical energy that perfectly complements their innate abilities. The capital city of Al Hazard, founded by the enigmatic Kitsune Grandmaster Zathegi—whose true form and gender remain shrouded in mystery—stands as a testament to their ingenuity and enigma. Al Hazard, one of the oldest surviving cities in all of Lyr, continues to thrive as a beacon of Kitsune culture and magical excellence.\n\nPlaying a Kitsune means embracing a character steeped in tradition, mystique, and an unwavering appreciation for beauty and art. With a natural affinity for illusion and magic that can shape both perception and reality, Kitsune seamlessly integrate their artistic talents into their magical practices, making them exceptional artisans. In Kitsune society, those who create or embody beauty are held in the highest reverence, fostering a culture that celebrates artistic expression and craftsmanship. Kitsune characters excel in roles that require a flair for the dramatic, whether as spellcasters, diplomats, spies, or master artisans. Their rich cultural heritage offers deep narrative potential, allowing players to explore themes of identity, legacy, and creativeness. Despite their magical and artistic talents, Kitsune are often viewed with suspicion by others, remnants of which persist in societal prejudices and mistrust outside Kirara. This dynamic provides ample opportunities for character development, as Kitsune navigate their place in a world that both reveres and fears their magical and artistic heritage. Kitsune bring a unique blend of charm, intelligence, magical versatility, and artistic prowess to an adventuring party, making them captivating and influential allies.\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"lamiafolk","name":"Lamiafolk","description":"Lamia are a subrace of the Chimera, native to the expansive great plains of Northi, though some communities have also established themselves within the dense forests. These graceful beings are characterized by their serpentine lower bodies, which, while imposing, present challenges in mobility within urban settings. To overcome this, many Lamia adventurers master transformative spells that allow them to adopt a more humanoid form, enhancing their versatility and adaptability in urban environments. Lamia society places immense value on family, with large family units sharing expansive homes that serve as both living spaces and communal hubs. This strong emphasis on familial bonds fosters a deep sense of loyalty and cooperation within their tribes, making Lamia individuals steadfast allies and dedicated protectors of their kin.\n\nHistorically, the Lamia have forged strong alliances with Centaur tribes, cohabiting in harmonious co-species settlements such as the renowned city of Nuren in Dacquoise, Axia. During the Great Divine War, Lamia phalanxes, in tandem with Centaur flanking tactics, played a pivotal role in stalling Northi's conquest of Nuren, showcasing their exceptional prowess in melee combat. Lamia excel in close-quarters battle, utilizing their powerful tails to grapple and constrict enemies with lethal efficiency. Additionally, their coiling tactics have been employed defensively, allowing them to coil around allies in peril to shield them with their armored scales. Playing a Lamia means embracing a character of formidable strength, strategic combat skills, and unwavering dedication to family and tribe. Their unique blend of melee expertise and defensive adaptability offers players the opportunity to craft characters who are both resilient warriors and compassionate protectors, enriching any adventuring party with their dual heritage of strength and unity.\n\nSize: Large"},{"id":"lizardfolk","name":"Lizardfolk","description":"Lizardfolk are a subspecies of Chimera native to the marshes and wetlands west of Sorthen. Their settlements are built with elegant hydromantic engineering, blending magic and design to rise above the flooded terrain—floating walkways, moisture-shielded libraries, and algae-filtered alchemical workshops are common. Though geographically remote, Lizardfolk settlements are self-sufficient and technologically sophisticated, designed for longevity in a land where the air hums with decay.\n\nThey are visually distinct with scaled limbs, slit-pupil eyes, and long muscular tails. This has led them to claim they descend from dragons. Kobolds, who claim the same origin, often reject these assertions outright, calling them fakers, pretenders and other more hostile insults. While there are some disputes regarding their heritage, these conflicts rarely lead to anything more than name calling from both sides.\n\nBy nature and culture, Lizardfolk are calm, deliberate, and slow to anger. Their society values stability, precision, and patience. Qualities that serve them well in a landscape where impulsiveness leads quickly to sinking mud or venomous fangs. Leadership is typically granted to those who demonstrate long-term vision rather than charisma, and decisions are often made after exhaustive study and debate. Artisans, scholars, and hydromancers hold great respect in their society, particularly those who contribute to the subtle shaping of their ever-changing environment.\n\nLizardfolk adventurers are uncommon but unmistakable. Those who leave the swamps often do so with deliberate purpose, seeking knowledge, reclaiming lost relics, or testing themselves against the wider world to affirm their strength and legacy. Unlike the boastful or glory-driven, Lizardfolk adventurers tend to approach danger with methodical caution and a long-term mindset, favoring preparation over bravado. Many act as medics, scouts, or tacticians within mixed parties, relying on their natural resilience, amphibious mobility, and calm under pressure. While some companions find them difficult to read, those who earn a Lizardfolk’s trust often find themselves with an unwavering ally—patient, perceptive, and quietly formidable.\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"mothfolk","name":"Mothfolk","description":"Mothfolk are a rarely seen subspecies of Chimera marked by their gossamer wings, feathery antennae, and luminous red eyes with black sclera.\n\nUnlike most Chimera, Mothfolk live startlingly brief lives. They mature within a few years and rarely live past forty. As a result, their society is built not on permanence, but on beauty, memory, and motion. Each generation considers itself a brief candle that is meant to burn brightly, not last forever. While they are generally gentle and introspective, their views on mortality make them eerily calm or even reckless in the face of death.\n\nMothfolk are nomadic, traveling in small groups as they follow seasonal shifts, changes in ambient magic or other signs. They rarely construct permanent dwellings, preferring temporary silk-covered domes or high-hanging cocoons spun between old trees or ruin pillars.\n\nDespite their gentle demeanor, Mothfolk face distinct challenges. Their alien appearance, especially the more bestial Zoalith mothfolk, evokes unease in most people. There are many negative rumors and myths surrounding the mothfolk and thus the elusive mothfolk avoid interacting with others unless absolutely necessary.\n\nMothfolk adventurers often embrace the path of a frontliner or scout. Their short lives push them to live boldly, though not always recklessly. They approach danger like a moth approaches flame: fully aware of the risk, but compelled nonetheless. Those who party with a mothfolk should restrain their impulses, or they might find themselves caught in the same inferno.\n\n\"Better to burn with brilliance for a moment, than fade forgotten in stillness.\"\n\nSize: Small"},{"id":"nekomata","name":"Nekomata","description":"Nekomata are a rare and often misunderstood sub-race of Youkai. They are deeply associated with death in most Youkai cultures and folklore ties them to first developing the methods and talismans needed to birth Jiangshi. In more recent times, with increasing trade and travel between Kirara and Lyr, Nekomata are often mistaken for Catfolk by Lyrian natives, with their primary distinguishing feature being their twin cat tails.\n\nNekomata are most often solitary wanderers with only the rare villages to be found hidden in dense mountain forests. In fact, most people in Kirara will go their entire long lives without ever seeing a Nekomata. Unfortunately, this elusiveness makes any stories or tales involving a Nekomata stand out all the more and the most memorable are almost always those that are shocking. This has given Nekomata an undeserved reputation of hostility and maliciousness in Youkai society due to the actions of cruel pranksters, arsonists, and serial killers throughout history. A Nekomata traveling through Kirara will often find their actions and steps watched carefully by suspicious townsfolk and guards, although this reputation hasn't spread well into Lyr.\n\nBeyond their ability to puppet the recently deceased and their close connection with death, Nekomata are most known for their grudges. They do not forget an insult, a thrown stone, or a slight nor the faces and voices of the ones that said the words or threw the stones. It is likely that many of the cruel pranks, burned buildings, and slaughtered families are from a Nekomata settling their grudge decades later.\n\nNekomata adventurers are often cautious to trust their companions but will form deep bonds if their trust isn't betrayed. In fact, adventuring parties that have a long standing Nekomata member would be wise to keep an eye on their twin-tailed friend, especially when insults begin to fly. Because a Nekomata holding a grudge for themselves is dangerous, but a Nekomata that is holding a grudge in defense of a friend is something lethal.\n\nAnd a Nekomata using the corpses of their recently defeated enemies to help in looting is a perfectly normal cultural quirk.\n\n\"I remember the stone you threw twenty winters ago. Do you?\"\n\nSize: M"},{"id":"nio","name":"Nio","description":"The Nio are ancient stone guardians. sentient statues who once stood vigil over sacred temples, hidden groves, and ancestral shrines across the lands of Kirara and beyond. Sometimes confused with gargoyles, the Nio possess intelligence and empathy whereas gargoyles typically attack anyone that comes close.\n\nThe Nio have little in terms of a society or community. They often spend most of their life in a sacred sleep. While resting in this form they do not eat and they do not age making them the perfect guards. It is not uncommon for a Nio to spend decades in this form until their services are required again and a Nio usually serves alone, or with just one other Nio.\n\nMost Nio speak little, and when they do, it is with a slow, resonant cadence. They are not heartless, but they value purpose above sentiment. Their sense of duty is absolute, and many of them refuse to step away from their warded locations, even when the world has long forgotten them.\n\nSome Nio now wander, their temples lost to time or desecrated by war. These unbounded Nio seek new causes or companions to protect, and may imprint upon individuals they deem righteous. Others serve monasteries or empires as living monuments, standing sentinel in gardens, courtyards, and graveyards alike.\n\nNio adventurers lean towards frontline roles, many of them relying on their hardened skin to absorb blows. By nature, most of them are also more accustomed to using melee weapons or unarmed combat as statues with other weapons are simply less common.\n\nThose traveling with an Nio will find a reliable and loyal ally. Just don't expect great conversations.\n\n\"The world may forget. But I remain.\"\n\nSize: M"},{"id":"oni","name":"Oni","description":"Their magical power is focused toward power and male Oni are generally large, strong, and sometimes brutish. Contrarily, female Oni are often very beautiful, by human standards. However, an Oni's appearance has little in common with their physical strength and despite their appearance, Oni are often calm and introspective. Oni are sometimes mistaken for Demons due to their horns. Most Oni also enjoy alcohol, which makes even the calmest incredibly rowdy. They tend to have incredibly powerful Ki, and even without training they tend to be able to affect the Ki of others.\n\nSize: Medium\n\nWinner of the 2023 Alpha Race Creation Contest by AShyMoth."},{"id":"phoenix","name":"Phoenix","description":"Phoenix Chimera are a rare subrace of Chimera, with only a few families known to exist within Lyr. Most of these families reside in the solitary heights of Mt. Merlin, where their isolation is not driven by culture or pride, but by a constant threat of danger. Legends speak of the miraculous healing power held within Phoenix feathers—the ability to cure all sickness, including death—which has made these unfortunate Chimera the prime targets for bounty hunters.\n\nThe pursuit of esoteric medicine pushed the Phoenixfolk into hiding, making them mysterious beings when they do venture away from home. To keep themselves safe from exploitation and to increase their chances of survival, Phoenix Chimera often disguise themselves as other avianfolk Chimera, blending into different communities to avoid detection.\n\nIn some of the darker corners of the world, Phoenixfolk have been kidnapped and forced into cages, their plumes and tears harvested for monetary gain. Taking advantage of their Fiery Rebirth, some of these captured Phoenixfolk are taken to the brink of death repeatedly to have their ashes harvested.\n\nPlayers who decide to play Phoenixfolk should be prepared to engage in themes of concealment and mystery, where the threat of kidnapping could be around any corner.\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"pixie","name":"Pixie","description":"Pixies are the diminutive subrace of the Fae, known for their delicate wings and vibrant presence within the forest canopies of Lyr. These tiny flying beings craft their homes in hollowed-out sections of ancient trees, seamlessly blending with the natural environment to remain elusive and hard to spot. Despite their small stature and physical fragility, Pixies possess incredible agility, allowing them to dart through the air with unparalleled grace. Their ability to soar above the battlefield provides them with strategic advantages, enabling them to outmaneuver larger foes and support their allies from above. Pixies embody a carefree spirit, often approaching life with a playful and lighthearted demeanor, taking challenges as they come without the weight of undue seriousness.\n\nLiving primarily within Fae communities and scattered throughout the vast forests of Lyr, Pixies maintain an aloof and independent nature, preferring solitude or the company of their kin over the complexities of larger societies. However, their significance transcends their playful exterior, as evidenced by the legendary Pixie Leaflit, a member of the Hero Signum's party that triumphed over the Goddess of Evil, Heira. This historic alliance is immortalized by a statue of the party, the oldest known monument in Lyr, nestled deep within Mt. Merlin. Playing a Pixie means embracing a character that combines agility, and a spirited approach to life. They are perfect for players that enjoy tactical thinking and nimble movements, as they bring unwavering optimism to their allies.\n\nSize: Tiny"},{"id":"rabbitfolk","name":"Rabbitfolk","description":"Rabbitfolk are a resilient subrace of the Chimera, predominantly hailing from the slums of Northi and Westria. Historically looked down on by the Catfolk, they continue to face prejudice from some older-minded individuals who view them as inferior. Rabbitfolk often have incredibly large families and very deep ties to community and to support themselves, they tend to take on less desirable jobs throughout the city. It is not uncommon for entire businesses to be run by extended families of Rabbitfolk or by joint community ventures. Due to this focus on family and community, Rabbitfolk tend to create very strong bonds with any companions they spend long periods of time with. It is not unheard of for long-time coworkers, school friends, or adventuring companions to suddenly find themselves as \"part of the family\" and inducted into an expansive extended family. However, despite their industrious nature, persistent social stigma has driven many Rabbitfolk to seek alternative means of livelihood, sometimes turning to crime as a desperate measure to ensure their families' well-being.\n\nAt the helm of Mothergreen's infamous Lorenz Mafia is Fiona MacCocairy, a determined Rabbitfolk girl who strives to bring honor to the underworld. Fiona has initiated a battle of optics, working tirelessly to clean up the Mafia and institute strict codes of honor, thereby bringing a semblance of respect and legitimacy to even their criminal trade. Her efforts highlight the tragic reality that many Rabbitfolk's involvement in crime stems from a profound desire to provide for their loved ones at any cost. Playing a Rabbitfolk is ideal for players who wish to embody characters with large, extended families, expansive communities, and explore the underworld and adverse conditions.\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"raijin","name":"Raijin","description":"Raijin are an exceptionally rare subrace of Youkai, embodying the very essence of lightning crystallized into sentient form. Their bodies are conduits of electrical energy, with vibrant arcs of lightning coursing through and emanating around them, granting them an electrifying presence that is both mesmerizing and formidable. Possessing incredible speed and agility, Raijin can catch and consume lightning, harnessing its raw power to fuel their abilities and enhance their combat prowess. This mastery over electrical energy not only makes them swift and lethal on the battlefield but also allows them to manipulate their surroundings with bursts of lightning-infused magic. Due to the intense energy that flows through and around them, Raijin often feel uncomfortable amidst the energetic fields of their own kind, which compels them to lead solitary lives.\n\nHistorically, Raijin have traversed the farthest and most remote reaches of Lyr, their nomadic lifestyles a testament to their independence and relentless pursuit of personal goals. On the battlefield, Raijin excel as lone warriors or as leaders of small, focused units, utilizing their incredible energy to wipe out enemies in single combat. Their unique abilities allow them to absorb lightning, rendering them impervious to such assaults, and to imbue their weapons with crackling electricity, transforming them into fearsome instruments of battle. This dual mastery not only enhances their offensive capabilities but also instills fear in their adversaries. While typically solitary, Raijin can bring tactical advantages to an adventuring party, wreathing their weapons in electricity for a powerful frontal assault. Players who thrive as lone wolves and enjoy infusing weapons with power, will find playing a Raijin immensely rewarding. Additionally, those who aspire to lead or prefer to follow their own desires without hesitation will resonate with the Raijin's independent and dynamic nature, making them captivating and influential allies.\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"ratfolk","name":"Ratfolk","description":"Ratfolk are a versatile subrace of the Chimera, seamlessly integrated into all walks of life throughout the vast lands of Lyr. Found all over from the bustling cities like Westria to the expansive plains of Axias, Ratfolk are renowned for their exceptional adaptability and resourcefulness. Their prehensile tails grant them unparalleled dexterity, making them adept laborers and specialists in performing a wide array of odd jobs. Whether working as carpenters in the city, or tracking down dungeons as adventurers, they can be found living their day to day lives with a sense of purpose, taking it one day at a time. Ratfolk are agile experts being incredibly hard to catch. Despite their presence in diverse environments, Ratfolk maintain a strong sense of community through large family units, though they often venture out to pursue individual endeavors, returning periodically to reunite with their kin.\n\nPlaying a Ratfolk means embodying a character that excels in versatility and everyday practicality. Ideal for players who enjoy characters skilled in various tasks and adept at handling diverse challenges, Ratfolk bring a unique blend of hardworking efficiency and laid-back charm to any adventuring party. Their ability to perform multiple roles with ease makes them invaluable in both combat and non-combat scenarios, while their relaxed demeanor fosters a harmonious and approachable presence within the group. Whether taking on the role of a diligent craftsman, a cunning scout, or a dependable support character, Ratfolk offer players the opportunity to create relatable and multifaceted personas. For those seeking to portray a character that balances productivity with a relaxed, everyday person feel, Ratfolk are the perfect choice, adding practicality to an adventuring party.\n\nSize: Small"},{"id":"red-pandafolk","name":"Red Pandafolk","description":"Red Pandas are a solitary subrace of Chimera, renowned for their ability to seamlessly integrate into diverse cultures across the expansive realm of Lyr. Unlike other races that form tight-knit communities, Red Pandas prefer to forge individual paths, often immersing themselves in the societies they inhabit rather than clustering with their kin. Their aloof and relaxed demeanor masks a deep-seated competence, as they approach every task with a lightheartedness that not only enhances their own resilience but also uplifts the morale of those around them. This carefree attitude does not diminish their effectiveness; rather, it complements their exceptional agility and acrobatic prowess, making them elusive and unpredictable in both social interactions and combat scenarios.\n\nDespite their easygoing nature, Red Pandas are inherently cautious and can be easily spooked, a trait that paradoxically transforms them into formidable fighters. Their heightened awareness and instinctual fear responses enable them to navigate and survive even the most perilous situations with remarkable dexterity and strategic finesse. Those who underestimate the Red Panda's seemingly detached attitude often find themselves outmaneuvered and defeated by these slippery warriors. In gameplay, Red Pandas are ideal for players who wish to embody characters that have a \"my pace\" attitude, utilizing their acrobatic skills and evasive techniques to outsmart opponents. Embracing a Red Panda character offers a unique blend of aloof charm and combat versatility, providing both strategic advantages and a dynamic presence.\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"ryujin","name":"Ryujin","description":"Ryujin are a rare and prideful sub-race of Youkai with distinctive draconic features. Claiming to be the only true direct descendants of mythical dragons, Ryujin are often at odds with Lizardfolk and Kobolds, who both claim the same - though Ryujin don't give the opinions of \"lesser races\" much thought in that regard. Overall, Ryujin are regal and intimidating with a presence that commands a room and a glare that can silence a crowd.\n\nCulturally, Ryujin live together and apart from the rest of Kiraran society. They don't tend to form Ryujin villages but instead take on leadership roles in other Youkai communities as exclusive merchants, mayors, governors, or just wealthy nobles leveraging their wealth and power. They demand a level of excellence from those around them that causes communities they're in to both be free of corruption and require full, constant effort of improvement that can drive people away in search for an easier, simpler life.\n\nBut what Ryujin demand of others, they demand of themselves even more intensely. Ryujin craftsmen will spend decades perfecting a single work to be worthy of their effort and lineage. Warriors will master techniques passed down from master to student for hundreds of years and often fight with an elegance that would be more at home on a stage than a battlefield. Scholars and mages dissect and understand their chosen fields to degrees of minutia reserved for specialist universities. Striking up a conversation about a Ryujin's interest will be a sure method of being regaled with the proper impact angles for hammering the shape of a katana, an arcane breakdown of individual elements of the Glittershard spell, or a detailed retelling down to individual combatants of an ancient, obscure battle.\n\nBut most mysterious of all are Ryujin adventurers. Often young and still in training (for a Ryujin), their drive to seek out the wonders of the world is second to none. The pride and drive for excellence is still present but there is often an underlying goal or purpose in their traveling the world. Ryujin adventurers are often knowledgeable in history and lost knowledge and they always seem to be searching for something, an ancient item or manuscript or tome. Unless you are extremely close to a Ryujin, it is not recommended to press them on the details of their search.\n\n\"You are ignorant of what stands before you.\"\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"salamander","name":"Salamander","description":"Salamanders are a proud, fiercely independent race, valuing personal strength and mastery over their innate fire magic. They are artisans at heart, channeling their elemental gifts into crafts that demand intense heat and fine control, such as metalwork, glassblowing, and the forging of enchanted items. In Sorthen, where these arts are highly respected, Salamanders have carved out a niche for themselves as master crafters, known for producing items of rare beauty and resilience.\n\nWhile they have a somewhat insular culture, valuing Salamander kinship and traditions, they are not unwelcoming to outsiders. In Glassteps, their primary settlement, Salamanders coexist harmoniously with Demons and other races.\n\nSalamander society places a strong emphasis on self-expression through craft. Each Salamander seeks to leave a mark on the world through their creations, which often hold personal or spiritual significance. Their apprenticeships are long and arduous, as young Salamanders must learn to temper their fiery nature and master their powers before they are considered full artisans. This mastery is symbolized by the ritual creation of a \"Soulforge,\" a unique piece of art that captures the essence of the Salamander's inner fire and serves as a testament to their skill and control.\n\nSize: Medium\n\nWinner of the 2023 Alpha Race Creation Contest (Elementals) by Sabbrewolf."},{"id":"selkie","name":"Selkie","description":"Selkies are mesmerizing Aquatic Fae primarily found off the tranquil shores of Houkaina, where their presence enriches the vibrant merfolk society. Although relatively rare, many Selkies have become prominent members of Houkaina, contributing significantly to its cultural and magical tapestry. While a majority of Selkies cherish their seaside abodes, a notable number venture beyond the coast, establishing homes near rivers or lakes to remain close to their beloved water sources. This preference for aquatic environments underscores their deep connection to water, allowing them to seamlessly integrate into various aquatic communities and adapt to both marine and freshwater realms. Central to Selkie identity is the magic seal cloak, a precious item bestowed upon them at birth, much like the Tengu. This cloak grants Selkies the ability to transform into their elusive Seal Form, a transformation shrouded in mystery as it remains unclear whether the seal form or their humanoid appearance came first. In their Seal Form, Selkies exhibit extraordinary speed and agility underwater, making them nearly impossible to capture and allowing them to navigate the depths with unparalleled grace.\n\nA defining cultural aspect of the Selkies is the profound significance of their seal cloaks. According to longstanding oral traditions, if a person were to steal a Selkie's cloak, the Selkie is culturally obligated to marry them. Although this obligation is not enforced by law, many Selkies take this tradition seriously, fiercely protecting their sealskin cloaks from theft—with many learning magic methods at an early age to summon and protect this cloak. Additionally, Selkies possess the innate ability to infuse water with their own mana, enabling them to manipulate it for various magical applications, which makes them exceptional Hydromancers and Cryomancers. Their early mastery of spells related to hiding and summoning their magic items further enhances their mystical prowess. Players who choose to play a Selkie character will appreciate the blend of aquatic grace and magical versatility, making Selkies ideal for those who wish to explore the freedom of the ocean and mystery of an aquatic Fae society.\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"sheepfolk","name":"Sheepfolk","description":"Sheepfolk are a sub-race of Chimera, native to the plains and lake coastline of what is now southern Axias, most sheepfolk now live in the plains area within Northi between Axias and Eisenstadt. Born with a natural sensitivity to magic, Sheepfolk have historically built settlements and migrated along major leylines. They were of critical help to sages in mapping and studying these invisible rivers of magical energy and many airship captains today feel it is good luck to have a sheepfolk on board. This deep sensitivity to magic comes from unique spirit circuits linked to their hair follicles, allowing unprecedented detection ability to magical energies and signals. Additionally, this sensitivity (and the natural talent to send magical signals as well) allows a sheepfolk to sense and smooth away the chaotic magical rhythm of physical exhaustion and mental fatigue. It’s said that the best night sleep a person can get is in the arms of or resting on the lap of a sheepfolk.\n\nHowever, this magical sensitivity made sheepfolk uniquely useful in one very critical field: communications. With their innate ability to sense and send magical signals, they are commonly hired, trained, or conscripted into militaries. Historically, the use of sheepfolk and advancing artifice communication technology allowed Northi to dominate conflicts with accurate maneuver warfare. Only the overwhelming might of Westrian paladins and the scouting and aerial advantages of the demon aerial mages prevented Northi domination of the peninsula in full. This paradigm nearly changed radically during the Four Swords War. Sheepfolk communication specialists began utilizing new jamming artifices. Not only were these specialists key in continuing Northi’s domination of communication range and quality, but they were also able to use these new tools to isolate Sorthen communication signals and adaptively jam them. This removal of critical communication ability combined with the joint strike with Westrian forces and newly implemented aeromancers finally allowed the demons to be pushed back.\n\nA major setback in the conflict drew the attention of sheepfolk after the war’s conclusion. Somehow, someway, the demons had briefly established completely untraceable and secure communications between their command posts in the south and their last general in the field. This limited communication allowed the demons to organize a blocking action at the Battle of Three Passes where General Ar’Golan’s battalion was able to hold back the invasion for weeks, allowing the evacuation of the remaining demon forces to Marlone Bay. This feat, which suddenly failed at the end of the battle, was investigated and the work of Aetherie Lu’Pana was discovered. Since the end of the war, the techniques and technology of the Aetherie has spread like a blaze through the sheepfolk communities, building on and allowing them to improve their own innate abilities to levels they’d never gone before. It is commonly thought among the sheepfolk that the late Aetherie Lu’Pana must have had sheepfolk help or had studied sheepfolk extensively to develop what she had.\n\nSheepfolk adventurers are often quiet, having grown up where needing to speak up to be heard was unnecessary, and they tend to shy away from those who are loud (both in actual volume and in showing off their magical energy). They will also think it is quite normal for groups to request them to act as a communication hub, even among new parties or strangers. But their comforting embrace and comfortable dreams are only for friends."},{"id":"slimefolk","name":"Slimefolk","description":"Slimefolk are a rare subrace of Chimera, tracing their lineage back to slime creatures that inhabit every corner of Lyr. Despite their gelatinous origins, Slimefolk possess a humanoid form that mirrors their unique personalities, and while this can change over time, it cannot be willingly altered without great strain and training. To better integrate into diverse societies and mitigate the unsettling responses to the nature of their true forms, many Slimefolk's first exposure to magic is a basic glamour spell, allowing them to seamlessly blend in and navigate social landscapes with ease.\n\nHighly independent by nature, Slimefolk typically do not form tight-knit communities with other Slimefolk, largely due to their rarity and solitary tendencies. While they do not possess an inherent sex, Slimefolk have developed the ability to emulate sexual characteristics to facilitate social interactions and relationships. Their exceptional ability to blend into any society means that others often perceive them as members of different, more humanoid races, unaware of their true slimy heritage. This chameleon-like quality makes Slimefolk ideal for players who wish to navigate complex social environments undetected, while also having access to unique techniques that can surprise and outmaneuver others when needed. Embracing a Slimefolk character means valuing independence and adaptability, offering both strategic advantages and a versatile role.\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"spiderfolk","name":"Spiderfolk","description":"Spiderfolk are a unique and industrious subrace of the Chimera, descended from ground spiders that mutated into a more humanoid direction. Their multiple arms enhance their dexterity, making them exceptional at multitasking and performing a wide array of tasks simultaneously. While they do not naturally use webs beyond utility purposes, a few Spiderfolk have trained to imbue their webs with mana, transforming them into incredibly durable tools for combat and defense.\n\nIn the heart of Northi City, Spiderfolk often purchase small, seemingly uninhabitable plots of land and build their homes vertically, creating spider houses that are architectural marvels with furniture often bolted sideways into the walls. Many Spiderfolk are renowned as masterful chefs, such as Master Chef Vinia Lalune, who runs Northi's most luxurious restaurant, \"Silk And Kettle.\" Her culinary creations have earned her widespread acclaim, showcasing the Spiderfolk's exceptional multitasking abilities in the kitchen. Players who wish to embody characters skilled in object interaction and vertical gameplay, will find Spiderfolk to be an ideal choice.\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"suryan","name":"Suryan","description":"Suryan are a secluded sub-race of Youkai. Often described as \"light given form\", the radiance that surrounds them is unmistakable and they are a spectacle for those who have never seen a Suryan before. Most Suryan are deeply spiritual and hold a reverence for light and its nurturing properties.\n\nSuryan villages and towns tend to be located in high mountain valleys, as close to the sun as can be managed while still able to support crops. The warm light each Suryan gives off makes their villages pleasantly welcoming and even the most inhospitable seeming locations team with trees, farms, and wildlife due to their influence. It is not uncommon to scale a frigid mountain pass only to descend into a shallow valley full of warm sunlight and green nature fully at odds with the surrounding mountains.\n\nThese villages and towns often support mountaintop monasteries where Suryan monks learn and meditate on the Five Harmonies, with the first and oldest, Divyajyoti% \u0000laya%, being located in a secluded section of the N\u0001gan[tya Parvata% placed upon the highest peak, N+l\u0001mbara[ikhara%. Five Harmonies monasteries produce revered wisdoms and graceful healers and are common pilgrimages for the wealthy and destitute alike.\n\nSuryan adventurers carry that spirituality and sense of community with them on their journeys. While not all will be mystical monks capable of weaving light into healing threads, their willingness to help even in small ways is a common behavior. A Suryan adventurer is just as comfortable clearing the wilderness of dangerous monsters as they are cheerfully helping a farmer harvest their crops. Many Suryan have been taught from a young age the basic mysticism of Five Harmonies as a guiding principle, although those born and raised outside of those mountain communities may lack that connection.\n\nExpect Suryan companions to be spiritual and compassionate to those around them.\n\n\"J+vana% jyotibhi% j\u0001yate. All life springs from light.\"\n\nTL Notes:\n\nN\u0001gan[tya Parvata% - The Mountains of the Dragon Dance\n\nN+l\u0001mbara[ikhara% - The Blue-Robed Peak, in this case blue-robed is a poetic epithet for the sky.\n\nDivyajyoti% \u0000laya% - The Sanctuary of Divine Light\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"tengu","name":"Tengu","description":"Tengu are a distinguished subrace of Youkai, recognizable as humanoids adorned with majestic wings that grant them the ability to soar through the skies of Lyr. Originating from the rugged mountains of Mt. Merlin, Tengu reside alongside the dangerous Astra Line, a region teeming with chaotic astra energy and perilous creatures known as Fiends. Each Tengu possesses the unique ability to summon a supernatural mask, meticulously crafted to reflect their individual essence. When donned, these masks suppress their innate aura and presence, rendering them nearly invisible to magical detection. This ability is crucial for their survival, as it allows them to navigate the treacherous landscapes at the border of the Astra Line undetected by the ever-present threat of Fiends. Renowned as fierce warriors and specialist Fiend hunters, they have developed the technique of bathing their weapons in their own aura. This specialty technique creating properties similar to silver weapons to shatter Fiendish defenses. Tengu play a pivotal role in safeguarding their homeland and by proxy the homelands of others, maintaining the delicate balance between order and chaos.\n\nDespite many Tengu villages falling under the jurisdiction of Northi, the kingdom respects their autonomy, recognizing the invaluable protection Tengu provide by keeping Fiends at bay. This mutual respect fosters a harmonious relationship, with the citizens of Northi viewing the presence of Tengu as a blessing rather than a burden. Tengu society is built on principles of strength, honor, and resilience, making them ideal companions for those who seek to embody the spirit of a fierce slayer. Players who are drawn to characters that harness the power of flight, excel in combat, and specialize in hunting formidable monsters will find the Tengu subrace exceptionally rewarding. Embracing a Tengu character means stepping into the role of a vigilant protector, capable of swift aerial maneuvers and specialist knowledge of Fiends, guiding the party's path against the most evil of creatures.\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"unseelie","name":"Unseelie","description":"The Unseelie are a feared and infamous branch of the Fae, marked by their dark complexions, dagger-thin features, and eyes that shimmer like oil in moonlight. The Unseelie dwell in eternal gloom, deep in the heart of the Eastern Forests where sunlight never reaches, and where even other Fae dare not tread.\n\nUnseelie society is one of discipline, cruelty, and control. Though they rarely harm each other, their reputation for depravity is well-earned. They take great pride in the art of suffering, perfecting pain as both punishment and expression. Captives brought into the dark woods are not killed quickly, if at all. They are kept, their torment prolonged by methods that are as surgical as they are sadistic. To the Unseelie, mercy is wasteful, and empathy is an affliction to be corrected.\n\nDespite this darkness, or perhaps because of it, Unseelie adventurers are not rare. They often leave the forest not out of exile, but ambition. In the wider world, their talents for interrogation, infiltration, and assassination find both fear and value. While some become little more than thugs or enforcers, others integrate into adventuring parties, happy to do the \"dirty work\" others shy from.\n\nUnseelie adventurers gravitate toward melee combat, preferring to witness an enemy's suffering from up close, though many also learn some form of healing. They typically excel at sabotage, torture, and covert operations. Unseelie also generally have no moral restrictions and will use whatever tactic ensures victory.\n\nWhile some Unseelie may suppress their darker instincts, most do not apologize for what they are. Those who travel with an Unseelie should always keep that in mind, lest they find themselves with a dagger in the back.\n\n\"Death is not punishment. It is a mercy.\"\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"willo-wisp","name":"Willo Wisp","description":"Willo Wisps are mischievous faeries of light, known for their playful nature and enchanting presence within the forests of Lyr. Primarily nocturnal, these elusive beings possess the innate ability to emit and manipulate light, creating mesmerizing displays that captivate all who witness them. While most Willo Wisps thrive under the cover of darkness, a select few have adapted to living during the daytime, blending their luminous abilities with the natural light to remain hidden yet active. Their strong connection with Faerie Light Eyes grants them the power to weave intricate illusions, allowing them to strike at the minds of their targets and manipulate perceptions with ease. Historically, before relations between the Fae and other races improved, many adventurers who dared to explore the Eastern forests were lured to their doom by Willo Wisps. Those unfortunate souls whose eyes met the fiery blue glow of activated Faerie Light Eyes were ensnared in illusions, guiding them toward their deaths to never be seen again.\n\nDespite the legends and cautionary tales passed down through generations, Willo Wisps themselves harbor no ill will toward these prejudices; in fact, many revel in the fear and mystery surrounding them. Stories among Human and Chimera alike continue to warn children against venturing into the woods at night, lest a Willo Wisp lead them to an early demise. This enigmatic behavior adds a layer of allure and intrigue to the Willo Wisps, making them a compelling choice for players who wish to embody a race with inherent magical eye powers or embody the classic mischievous fae who delight in the fearful tales spun about them.\n\nSize: Small"},{"id":"wolf-folk","name":"Wolf-folk","description":"Wolf-folk are a distinguished subrace of Chimera, inhabiting the rugged snowy peaks of Mt. Merlin and extending their presence to the vast expanses of Susururu Forest, where the largest populations thrive. These resilient beings have developed a predatory instinct that enables them to meticulously hone in on and swiftly eliminate their prey, striking decisively when they detect any sign of weakness. Renowned as some of the finest hunters in the realm, Wolf-folk sustain themselves by thriving on nature's bounty, establishing and maintaining small, tightly-knit villages among their own kind. Their exceptional hunting prowess is complemented by their remarkable teamwork; Wolf-folk excel in collaborating with trusted allies, skillfully exploiting any openings their companions create to maximize their effectiveness in both combat and survival scenarios.\n\nThe hunting skill of Wolf-folk is highly esteemed, particularly their animal furs, which are considered the best in the realm. These furs are meticulously prepared and sought after by merchants who journey to the remote, forested, and mountainous villages where Wolf-folk reside. The quality and durability of their furs make them invaluable commodities, enhancing the reputation of Wolf-folk artisans across Lyr. Despite their isolated habitats, the Wolf-folk maintain a robust network of trade and interaction with outside merchants, ensuring that their villages remain prosperous and their skills highly regarded. Players that want to play keen hunters who work well with others would enjoy what Wolf-folk have to offer.\n\nSize: Medium"},{"id":"yuki-onna","name":"Yuki-Onna","description":"Yuki-Onna are an rare subrace of Youkai, exclusively female snow spirits who embody the serene yet formidable essence of winter. Primarily inhabiting the frigid regions around Mt. Merlin, the eastern fringes of Easter's forest, and the vast expanses of the Mirane Tundra, Yuki-Onna live in tightly-knit tribes that reflect their deep connection to their icy environments. These Youkai are incredibly rare outside their snowy homelands, with only those possessing powerful soul cores daring to traverse into warmer climates. In the magical sanctuary of Kirara, a sizeable population of Yuki-Onna thrives, thanks to the strong ambient magic that allows them to withstand the heat. Their presence in Kirara not only highlights their resilience but also their drive to adapt to different climates.\n\nYuki-Onna are renowned for their mastery of cryomancy, a powerful form of magic that allows them to control and manipulate ice and snow. This mastery was exemplified by the legendary cryomancer, Mirane, who was mentored by the Tsurara tribe of Yuki-Onna in the creation of the Eternal Mirane Cage—a legendary-class spell. Following the sealing of a dangerous Fiend by Mirane, Yuki-Onna played a crucial role in the subsequent expedition to eliminate the threat, showcasing their prowess as fierce warriors and reliable allies. Playing a Yuki-Onna is ideal for players who relish the roles of outsiders and travelers, embracing characters who navigate the world with grace despite its hostility. Their unique abilities and tribal heritage offer a rich narrative experience, perfect for those seeking to portray resilient and independent spirits who are unafraid to journey far from home in pursuit of their goals.\n\nSize: Medium"}],"classes":[{"id":"abjurer","name":"Abjurer","tier":2,"role1":"Defender","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Arcane Barrier learned, must possess at least 1 spell that deals damage.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Reason or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Athletics, Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Every initiate mage learns early on that the first fundamental of magic is defense. But for Abjurers, this lesson became their mantra. These Mages took their masters' teachings to heart and mastered the art of defensive magic.\n\nAbjurers are incredibly durable, and they don't just keep that strength to themselves—they can extend it to their allies, making everyone around them tougher in battle. Their focus is unmatched, allowing them to control space and protect others, even without relying on weapons.\n\nDespite their power, Abjurers are often underestimated. But when the heat of battle comes, they prove their worth, showing remarkable resilience under fire. It's this unshakeable defense that makes them indispensable in the chaos of war.","guide":"Abjurer's are frontline spellcasters that oftentimes don't wear armor. To help with the durability, you have Mana Shield. Mana Shield gives you a small amount of temporary HP every turn. It's good for reducing a small amount of damage every turn, but will not protect from a large burst turn.\n\nMana Shield also lets you cast spells while engaged by enemies if they are challenged by you, which can be accomplished by the Spell Challenge key ability. AoE spells can be used to inflict Challenge on many enemies, though they won't apply it if they miss or are fully blocked as many of them do not target the enemy, but an area. Single target spells will always apply it however.\n\nYour best tool for doing so when engaged by an enemy is Abjurer's Blast, which is a short range spell that can be used multiple times per turn, but doesn't provoke. This lets you set up challenge safely on enemies even if you lost the initiative.\n\nTo protect your allies and disrupt enemies that go for them, you have Arcane Pull. Arcane Pull is effective in keeping your backline safe from melee enemies, but it can be useless if there's not enough distance between you and your allies.\n\nFinally, Arcane Barrier II is a simple upgrade on the normal arcane barrier, letting you add your guard to the guard of the barrier.","keyAbility":"Spell Challenge","abilities":["Abjurer's Blast","Mana Shield","Arcane Barrier II","Arcane Pull"]},{"id":"acolyte","name":"Acolyte","tier":1,"role1":"Healer","role2":"Support","difficulty":3,"requirements":"None.","heart":"You gain +1 to Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to either Power or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Appraise, Medicine, Religion, Magic, History, Insight, Negotiation, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Acolytes are practitioners of the mysterious power known as Faith, which is believed to be the oldest form of magic. In a world where The Church of Kari reigns as the most dominant religion, most Acolytes, about 95%, are Human, and nearly all of them, around 99%, belong to the Church.\n\nAcolytes are people with a special calling, blessed with the power to perform miracles thanks to their deep faith. They're part of a bigger community that includes other Acolytes, priests, and sometimes even Paladins. Because of this, they can usually find a safe place to rest and get help in churches and temples wherever they go.\n\nWith their healing and protective abilities, Acolytes are essential members of any party, making sure their friends stay safe and well during tough battles.","guide":"Acolytes are the main healers of groups of new adventurers, being the only tier 1 class with the capability to heal others.\n\nTheir primary tool for this is Cure Touch. The mana cost is high, but it is still more efficient (and cheaper) than drinking a potion. Keep in mind that it does provoke attacks of opportunity, so position yourself behind the ally you're healing if they are in melee combat.\n\nLight's Care is some efficient after combat healing. It heals for the same amount as Cure Touch for a fraction of the mana cost. It also has the benefit of allowing the target to prevent an injury to themselves if they went down in combat.\n\nWhat makes an acolyte truly valuable for a newbie group is Angel's Embrace. It has no mana cost and reduces the damage an ally takes by a large amount. The range is short, so most acolyte's prefer a melee weapon. Since you are using your RP to help others, be wary that you don't put yourself in a position where the enemy can focus you as your RP dwindles.\n\nMiracle: Sanctuary creates a small but durable barrier that can be used both offensively and defensively. When used defensively, it can give your allies a moment of reprieve, letting them drink a potion before going for a round two. It can also be used to trap an enemy inside the barrier, isolating it from its allies while your own allies wail on it.","keyAbility":"Acolyte's Journey","abilities":["Cure Touch","Light's Care","Angel's Embrace","Miracle: Sanctuary"]},{"id":"adventurer","name":"Adventurer","tier":1,"role1":"Utility","role2":"Striker","difficulty":1,"requirements":"None","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning, Reason, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on any non crafting skill. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Legends have it that Fayto Zhelti was the first true adventurer, a spirited young girl from a humble town in the Kingdom of Alpinum. Her Father was an explorer and Fayto dreamed of following in his footsteps.\n\nYet, as childhood began to fade away, a painful realization crawled within her heart: the incredibly physical feats of strength her father effortlessly performed always lay just beyond grasp. No amount of blood, sweat or tears could overcome the anguish of her physical reality. She watched her younger brothers surpass her in strength, joining their father on this expeditions she yearned for. Loneliness began to infect her heart that ached for adventure, but fate had cruelly denied her that path.\n\nStill she persisted, even in her pain... tirelessly striking the same tree day after day for years.\n\nHumans barely had the lifespan to master the arcane arts—which at the time were incredibly complex without shortcuts. Her Mother, an arcane practitioner, taught her daughter the methods of utilizing magic for mundane tasks: heating water kettles and stirring up a gentle whirlpool to do laundry. While practicing these humble homecrafts, Fayto remembered that feeling, the tingling surge that ran through her limbs.\n\nOne day, as she swung her dulled blade against that ancient tree, she poured every ounce of her yearning and willpower into her strike. The familiar surge ran through her as the explosive energy flooded her body, exactly as it had done alongside her Mother. In a thunderous crash, the mighty tree toppled.\n\nFrom that day forward, she pursued that elusive feeling. She trained relentlessly until she mastered the art of \"internal magic\" which would be known later as ki. Soon after that she joined her father's adventures at last, growing and developing until she embarked on her own journeys, making a name for herself wherever she went \"Fayto, the female adventurer.\"\n\nTo this day, adventurers still practice the skills Fayto Zhelti perfected long ago—a martial art born of determination and control of ones self, leveling the playing field for all who practice it. Following Fayto's example, Adventurers continue to train—leaping to extraordinary heights, molding mana to extend their reach, projecting their aura like iron... all while maintaining perfect composure. Although the ancient martial art remains nameless, its teaches are diligently passed down to every aspiring adventurer, serving as a solid foundation for future development.","guide":"The adventurer is a generalist class that has a bit of everything. One of the main draws of the adventurer is their options in picking their proficiencies, being the only tier 1 class that can choose a specialized weapon and heavy armor.\n\nPower Jump is an anti-air tool that lets you hit enemies in the air even if you only have melee weapons. It is even better if you can fly, as you can use power jump as a cheap way to gain altitude.\n\nMana Razor gives you increased range on your attacks. If you're using a melee weapon with this, you'll need to be aware that turning your attacks into ranged attacks does mean you'll provoke attacks of opportunity. It only affects your basic melee attacks, but you can still use your abilities on enemies within your normal range.\n\nSteel Aura is a defensive tool that can be very powerful when attacked by a large group of grunts. With 3 additional guard, you will most likely take only 1 damage from light attacks from those enemies, though you'll still need to be wary of heavy attacks.\n\nYour Secret Art: Efficient Spirit Control is a simple mana reduction ability. If you do not have any other secret arts yet, then don't be afraid to use this whenever you would spend 2 or more mana on something.","keyAbility":"Adventurer Essentials","abilities":["Power Jump","Mana Razor","Steel Aura","Secret Art: Efficient Spirit Control"]},{"id":"aeromancer","name":"Aeromancer","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Controller","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Any class mastered or Wind mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Reason or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The first Aeromancer corps were born in Northi, created as a direct response to Sorthen's formidable Ace Aerial Mage squads. While the Catfolk had a stronghold on the ground with their incredible speed, the Fae and Sorthen flyers posed a constant threat from above. That is, until a cunning Catfolk mage named Nicole Mimi changed the game.\n\nMimi took a magical art that was once considered weak, Aeromancy, and turned it into a force to be reckoned with. By destabilizing the air itself, she crafted powerful gales and sudden downbursts, effectively disrupting air superiority. What was once seen as a lesser magic became a devastating weapon under her mastery.\n\nTo this day, Aeromancers from all corners of the world study Mimi's tomes, learning to command the sky just as she did. They've turned Aeromancy into an art of its own, capable of twisting the winds and reshaping the battlefield.","guide":"Aeromancers take on a more controllery striker role, displacing enemies while attacking them. They are very dangerous when near cliffs or other hazards. Their difficulty lies in the importance of their positioning. Knockbacks do damage if the target can not be moved the full distance, so knocking enemies into walls can add a decent amount of damage.\n\nWind Blast is a low investment ability that provides significant displacement. While using it near hazards is the obvious choice, it can also be used to free up space for allies or to push the enemy closer to your allies so they can spend more AP on attacking instead of moving.\n\nWind Scatter is an almost pure disruption tool. It makes further AoE's impossible, so careful use is required to not disrupt your allies. A good Wind Scatter however, can put significant distance between the front most and backmost enemy of a formation, which allows for targets to be isolated and picked off.\n\nWind Buffet is a more defensive knockback, forcing enemies away from you. Be careful, as it provokes attacks of opportunities and can hit allies.\n\nDownburst is a simple, but extremely powerful anti-air tool. With high range and lock-on, an aeromancer is a aerial mage or flying monster's worst nightmare.","keyAbility":"Wind Master","abilities":["Wind Blast","Downburst","Wind Scatter","Wind Buffet"]},{"id":"aeromaster","name":"Aeromaster","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Controller","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Aeromancer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The Aeromaster has taken their abilities to the next level, becoming a master of air magic. They are able to wield powerful and destructive spells, using their control over the air to unleash devastating storms and gales upon their enemies.","guide":"The Aeromaster gains increased control over their displacements ability through their key ability. This helps them position the enemies they push to set them up for their allies.\n\nWind Blast II is a more versatile version of Wind Blast, most importantly letting you do a precise attack for an almost guaranteed knockback.\n\nDownburst II allows the aeromaster to punish flying enemies even when its not their turn. It has the same properties as the normal downburst otherwise.\n\nCyclone is primarily a control tool used for knocking enemies prone that does a slight amount of damage. It can also be combo'd into Downburst II, though the RP cost may be too high to do it a lot.\n\nTheir Secret Art: Razor Hurricane is another mix of control and damage. The large size of it makes it good for locking down areas. It also cannot be destroyed like wall type blockades and even if they can take the damage, the knockback is still a problem. If you don't need to seal off an area, you can move it into enemies for some extra damage.","keyAbility":"Controlled Wind","abilities":["Wind Blast II","Cyclone","Downburst II","Secret Art: Razor Hurricane"]},{"id":"aetherie","name":"Aetherie","tier":2,"role1":"Utility","role2":"Support","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Appraise, Magic, Artifice, Perception, Insight, Stealth or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The Four Swords War pushed the boundaries of artifice and magic in the way only a continent spanning conflict can. Entire schools of magic were created and artifice technology raced forward at breakneck speed. The Aetherie were but one of those desperate developments. Founded from the study of the genius work of a Lu Clan demon by Axian and Sorthen researchers, the brief life of the namesake of the magical discipline is inescapably entwined with the art of Mind Connection.\n\nAetherie Lu'Pana earned her right as a master of magic in the middle of her own apprenticeship as the war with Westria and Northi pushed into Sorthen's borders. After reading through the requests passed to her master for a method to counter or break through Northi artifice communications jamming, Aetherie offered up her own research project: a mind/mana connection technique. It didn't take long after successfully demonstrating the new magic that her preliminary plans for an amplifying artifice was put into the prototype stage. She and the prototype were rushed toward the rapidly collapsing front where she was able to establish communications between General Ar'Golan and his battalion commanders, using herself as a conduit. This ability to coordinate in real time using the eyes of his own commanders allowed the Sorthen Rear Guard to briefly hold the invading armies at the Battle of Three Passes for the critical weeks needed for their remaining forces and critical civilians to be evacuated to Marlone.\n\nUnfortunately, the defense collapsed when Aetherie Lu'Pana, pushed beyond her limits by the strain of upkeeping her Mind Connection using the prototype sensory station, died from the strain. Her notes and the testimony of the one surviving commander from Three Passes that had been Mind Connected was studied carefully and the \"Aetherie Mind Connect\" school of magic was codified shortly after the war.\n\nAetherie are a rare breed of mage. The mental fortitude required to process multiple viewpoints and even spread their influence out from those they're connected with does not come easily and there are whispered stories of would-be Aetherie losing their minds in the ebb and flow of magic. But a well practiced Aetherie, with proper support and equipment, can bring unprecedented support and coordination to any group.","guide":"The Aetherie is a long range utility and support class.\n\nWhile it can function at close range, the main draw is to use Mind Connection to set up a telepathic link and work off your allies while you remain somewhere else. This range is further boosted if you can afford the sensory mage suit, so you should invest in that if you plan to play this way.\n\nPsychometry is a free or almost free scouting ability that is very valuable in dungeons or other indoor explorations. It can let your party properly prepare before entering dangerous room.\n\nConduit is what lets you use abilities from other classes while playing from long range. There are still some restrictions on what you can do, so picking classes that synergize well with this ability is important.\n\nTap Cracker lets you open doors from a distance, which can be useful in avoiding traps. You can also unlock doors, allowing you to fulfill a niche without having to invest many skill points into it.\n\nSpirit Circuit Crash is a powerful ability that removes a targets ability to use mana without any roll or save. Because it doesn't have a mana cost, you can effectively keep a target from using a mana ability the entire fight unless they choose to take the damage. But be aware that not every enemy will have or use mana.","keyAbility":"Mission Control","abilities":["Psychometry","Conduit","Tap Cracker","Spirit Circuit Crash"]},{"id":"agrarian","name":"Agrarian","tier":2,"role1":"Artisan","role2":"Controller","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Farmer mastered","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Farming.","description":"\"Thank you, Sister Yselwen. We thank Kari's Light for guiding you to us in our hour of need.\"\n\nYselwen gave the Elder a smile and a bow, resisting the urge to correct him. She wasn't a Sister of his faith. But she held her tongue and turned away from the gathered villagers and the settlement. Once over the hill and fully out of sight, her shoulders drooped and her smile dropped. Rubbing a few frustrated circles on her forehead in an attempt to dispel the headache of dealing with the religiously righteous and ignorant, she turned from the packed dirt path and out into the wild fields. She took deep breaths as the scents of nature washed away the cloying dregs of the human settlement that seemed determined to cling to her.\n\n\"Yggdrasil nerth iy thoir,\" she prayed, fingers brushing against the stalks of wild wheat as she passed. She needed all the strength Yggdrasil could grant her after dealing with the Karites. At least the farmers had taken her teachings and blessings to heart. Not parroted like so many in recent days, but an actual understanding of the connection they were calling upon. It wasn't enough to bring Yggdrasil to prominence, even if she could spread that same message to a thousand farmers across Westria, but it did sustain Her.\n\nNormally, she didn't stray far from the borders of Easter, content to spread the Blessings of Yggdrasil where it was more accepted. But with a famine tearing its way across Lyr, she felt it was a ripe opportunity to help some people and spread Yggdrasil's teachings a little wider. With a huff, she spun back toward her next destination, having not noticed she'd stopped to stare toward that stupid village with its stupid elder. They wouldn't starve come winter and that was more important than a silly man pushing his faith on her.\n\nAnd so it went, village after village, town after town. Meetings with priests, elders, mayors, and farmers. Dealing with the initial distrust of her skin, the color of oak leaves in the autumn, or the claims of heresy at her words. But they all wanted to live, wanted to eat. So she taught and blessed and spoke to those that would listen.\n\n\"Bennachd na Yggdrasil ar talah se,\" would be repeated in broken, Westrian accents with earnest intent.\n\n\"Gabthasinn a toirt Yggdrasil don tiodlac seo,\" some would say on her departure, clutching at crudely woven tree effigies.\n\nFor decades, Priestess Yselwen wandered the lands of Axia, Westria, and Northi. Where she tred, the famine faded. Her blessings and the teachings of Yggdrasil took root in small villages and in farmers' hearts. The Dryad of the Fall became a myth and a legend, invoked in the same blessings she once taught. Some say that she still wanders the fields near Easter to this day, blessing those in need.","guide":"The Agrarian uses their scythe more in combat compared to the farmer, though they retain their controller nature.\n\nSeparate wheat from chaff is a large AoE attack with a knockback attached to it. Great for when you're surrounded and want to force grunts to spend more AP on movement. If you land a kill with this ability, then it becomes even more potent and could potentially deny a grunt of being able to do anything for a turn.\n\nTerracing is a reverse hole creation. You raise up the ground around yourself to force enemies to make athletics checks to get up to you. At 10ft high, you may be unable to strike back against an enemy unless you bring a range weapon, but it can still help in separating enemy formations.\n\nHarvest Moon is a powerful effect that costs a bit of mana to activate. The healing effect on it isn't very mana efficient, effectively just a healing potion, but it is free action wise. The slowing effect is large control effect that remains active, but upkeep cost can add up over time. If none of your allies need the healing, it may be smart end it early with the free heavy attack and look to regain some of the mana spent on it.\n\nOn the crafting side, Four Field System is an ability you want to use at the start of your crafting basically every time. With Four Field System, even actions like Steady Craft become better than just doing a basic craft and it becomes better the more other crafting abilities you have.","keyAbility":"Expert Farmer","abilities":["Separate wheat from chaff","Terracing","Four Field System","Harvest Moon"]},{"id":"alchemeister","name":"Alchemeister","tier":2,"role1":"Artisan","role2":"Healer","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Alchemist mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Alchemy.","description":"Researchers who have come to understand the nature of objects and energy.","guide":"The Alchemeister is an alchemist that is more skilled at crafting and using the items they craft. Detailed Finish is a good final action when crafting, giving you a higher average at no cost.\n\nWith Infuse Potion you are able to heal with potions without requiring your allies to drain their own mana, making you a lot more effective as a healer. You don't have to use it every time either, allowing you to make others pay with their mana when yours is running low.\n\nWith Counter-Potion you are able to use an alchemy item as a reaction, allowing you to do a variety of powerful things. You can toss a flashbang to interrupt an action by lowering their AP, toss a slowing flask when an enemy is about to approach your ally or toss a molly when they've finished moving to make them take guaranteed damage. Combine this with Quickdraw Alchemy from alchemist and you don't even need to prepare this action in advance. At any point you can quickdraw what you need and toss it.\n\nSecret Art: All of Creation is a situational ability. Changing the damage type will not always be useful, but it can really help amplify damage dealt when against an enemy with a vulnerability or weakness. It is also completely free, apart from taking up your one secret art per encounter. Special Mention goes to Alchemist belonging to a race that can absorb a certain elemental damage, such as Salamander. A Salamander alchemist can force any big attack about to hit them to be fire damage, which they can easily absorb and turn into healing for themselves.","keyAbility":"Expert Alchemist","abilities":["Combat Chemistry","Counter-Potion","Detailed Finish","Secret Art: All of Creation"]},{"id":"alchemist","name":"Alchemist","tier":1,"role1":"Artisan","role2":"Healer","difficulty":2,"requirements":"None.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Alchemy. You also gain 5 skill points to spend in Medicine, Magic or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Researchers and chemists who try to understand what composes the world.","guide":"Alchemist is a crafting class that can use the consumables they craft to great effect. With Light Work you can craft tons of items at the same time, though you still have to pay material costs as normal. As you go through a lot of items, being able to double what you craft in 1 point is still valuable.\n\nThrow Potion lets you function as a healer for a party. Your healing will be fairly AP efficient, but it can be dangerous to rely on an alchemist healer as the person receiving the potion has to pay the mana cost. In a party where other people may want to use their mana for their own abilities, it may be impossible to heal as the fight drags on.\n\nDoctor Jekyll lets you or an ally drink a potion or elixir when the combat start. In most cases this will be an elixir, allowing you to get a boost without having to spend an action on it.\n\nQuickdraw Alchemy lets you take out an alchemy item at any time, even when it's not your turn. Most of the time this property will not come into play, as you can't use it when it's not your turn yet, but you could prepare a flask that an ally can take off your hands when it is their turn. Of course, you will most likely just want to use it to not have to spend your AP to draw them before using them yourself.","keyAbility":"The Alchemist","abilities":["Throw Potion","Doctor Jekyll","Light Work","Quickdraw Alchemy"]},{"id":"alkahest","name":"Alkahest","tier":2,"role1":"Artisan","role2":"Utility","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Transmuter mastered","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain 10 Transmuter points. Pick one of the crafting disciplines, such as blacksmithing or alchemy. Whenever you use your Transmuter abilities in a craft of that discipline, you may add your transmuter points as bonus to that ability (even if it's not a roll). You must pick a different discipline than one you picked in Transmuter, but you gain an additional 5 points in your original discipline for free.","description":"While Transmuters provide foundations for everyday life and artisan work, Alkahests are those who are obsessed with the subtleties of matter and creation. Alkahests are the experts in the fields of Transmutational Alchemy, quickly altering reality with precision and artistic flair. They're able to immediately concept and transmute just the right tool for any situation.\n\nHistorically, one Alkahest above all others was a pioneer in her field. She remains celebrated across Lyr to this day—Etoile Dacquoise. While her best friend and rival, Riannon Aquanas, focused on the art of core Alchemy, Etoile dedicated her life to mastering the complexities of Transmutation. In the atelier together, these pioneers had opened an often historically referenced shop in the Kingdom of Mothergreen—and became the foundation of innovation during Lyr's darkest hours.\n\nHistorical word of mouth speaks of Etoile's contributions from behind the scenes in the battle against Heira, the Goddess of Evil. Although she never wielded a sword on the front lines, her mastery of transmutation alongside Riannon's expertise in alchemical creations created the tools and solutions needed by their friends that did. The members of those legendary heroes helped create that shop themselves, as the procurement arm of the business. Etoile's legacy is still immortalized to this day behind the statues of Riannon and the other heroes:\n\nElly, The Hero\nUruka, The Sylph\nSignum, The Heretic\nLeaflit, The Pixie\nBrynhildr, The Dragon\nBasalt, The Dwarf\n\nToday's Alkahests follow in Etoile's footsteps and in her teachings, fulfilling their roles as vital supporters and adventurers, heroes and innovators alike. They sometimes provide assistance from the sidelines, demonstrating that heroism is not only about direct confrontation but also wits, innovation and dedication to a future victory.","guide":"The Alkahest is a crafter and utility class with very limited combat potential.\n\nYour best combat ability is your Secret Art: Transmute Proto Armatae. While it costs a fair bit of mana, you can view the armatae's HP as getting a ton of bonus HP that stacks with temporary HP. In addition, you get to make a free attack each turn. It doesn't increase your damage output much (or at all), but it's good defensively. You can use it defensively by spending RP and absorb a hit with the free 20 HP shield it comes with.\n\nAlchemical Detonation is your other ability that can be used in combat, although it is situational. Strong when you're against enemies that use wall creation. It also has strong out of combat benefits, allowing you enter virtually any building at little cost.\n\nTransmute Effective Implement is another out of combat tool that can grant you a massive bonus to a skill check. If you're willing to spend enough mana, you can succeed at almost any check if you want to.\n\nSiphon Materials costs an interlude point, but it lets you extract valuable materials that might otherwise be wasted in an item you can't use. You could extract the silver from a katana to have a blacksmith make it into a dagger for example.\n\nFinally, stabilize matter is another co crafting ability. It statistically beats out the other options, though you do have to precast it instead of using it after you see the roll. A small bit of creation lets you convert a herb to one of a different element at the cost of reducing the rarity. Using this reduces the value of herb, so it should only be done if you desperately need the herb.","keyAbility":"Transmutation Tricks","abilities":["Transmute Effective Implement","Alchemical Detonation","Siphon Material","Secret Art: Transmute Proto Armatae"]},{"id":"amanita","name":"Amanita","tier":3,"role1":"Healer","role2":"Striker","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Mycomancer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Awareness or Cunning.","soul":"You gain +1 to Power or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Medicine, Magic or Survival. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Amanita’s are expert Mycomancer’s that weave life and death hand in hand. Blessed healers to their allies and terrifying killers to their enemies, they were feared ever since the first Fae Amanita’s appeared amongst the ranks of Sylvan’s army. Amanita’s often wear mushroom caps on their head with spotted designs to signify their rank. The spores that reside within all Amanita’s blood also grants them considerable resilience against poison.","guide":"Amanita’s expand on the Healer and Striker hybrid of the Mycomancer, specializing in supporting tanks while busting enemy tanks. Vital Drain and Hyphal Force are excellent tools for overcoming armor, while also keeping allies healthy. Spore burst is useful in a pinch when caught out of position. The Amanita also has the terrifying ability of keeping allies up while downed, giving them the ability to continue fighting. However, make sure to remind your allies that they are in risk of dying due to being able to fight at negative HP, as reaching negative maximum HP can kill a character.","keyAbility":"Fungal Metabolite","abilities":["Vital Drain","Hyphal Force","Spore Burst","Secret Art: Mushroomize"]},{"id":"angelblooded","name":"Angelblooded","tier":2,"role1":"Utility","role2":"","difficulty":1,"requirements":"Must have the Angelblooded breakthrough.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness, Cunning, Reason, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on any non crafting or gathering skill. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Angelblooded are humans with angelic heritage that can transform into semi-divine beings.","guide":"The main appeal of the angelblooded is the True Divine Release. Not only does it give flight and extra movement speed, it is also a requirement to use the other two abilities of the class. Unfortunately, the upkeep and cost make it hard to use until you obtain God's Blessing, which reduces both to 0.\n\nOnce this class is mastered, it becomes very powerful. On top of the benefits mentioned above, you get to make a free light attack every round. You also get to do a stronger block every round, making blocking an option even if your toughness is low and you're not wearing armor.\n\nEven after mastering it, it is still a once per arc ability. Make sure you don't use it too early.","keyAbility":"Angelic Presence","abilities":["True Divine Release","Divine Guard","Divine Might","God's Blessing"]},{"id":"animal-summoner","name":"Animal Summoner","tier":2,"role1":"Specialist","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Any class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning, Reason, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Animal Husbandry. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"A summoning class that specializes in animals.","guide":"The animal summoner is a summoning class that summons a variety of animals to harrass their enemies. Your animals are chosen randomly with Giant Spider being the best overall option and boar being a close second. Wolf has some mana less control and damage options, but is weaker stat wise.\n\nSummon Animal is the ability the rest of your class functions around. It lets you summon one of the animals mentioned above. How it functions depends on whether you use independent action or not. If you choose not to use Independent Action, you can summon two animals at the same time and you can use them to control space or act as living obstacles without requiring much investment if you don't want to. If you activate independent action, you get a rather cheap extra unit that can just add free damage in combat.\n\nBecause summon animal becomes disabled if your animal dies, you'll want to use Emergency Recall to remove it before it can die. It is very unlikely for your animal to die with the high damage reduction it gives, so you shouldn't be using other RP on your summoned animal in most cases.\n\nBestial Command lets you effectively trade 2 mana for 2 AP worth of actions on your pet. More importantly, it also lets you trade 2 of your own AP for 2 AP of your summoned animal. While it's a questionable trade now, when you get access to buffs to your animal it can be very worthwhile to do so.\n\nHalf Restore is a heal and shielding tool for your animal. The mana cost is lower than normal healing abilities and it converts overheal into shielding, so it may be worth casting at the start if you spawn your animal next to you.","keyAbility":"Summon Animal","abilities":["Emergency Recall","Half Restore","Independent Action","Bestial Command"]},{"id":"anti-mage","name":"Anti-Mage","tier":2,"role1":"Support","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Anti-mage is a discipline often pursued by those who don't practice magic themselves. With Mages playing such a critical role in boosting military power, it's often a top priority to neutralize them first. That’s where Anti-Mages come in. They dedicate their studies to finding the cracks in all forms of magic, learning how to disrupt and cancel its effects.\n\nAnti-Mages have a deep understanding of magic, perhaps even more so than some Mages themselves. They don't just know how magic works, they know how to break it.\n\nA prime example of their power was seen during the 2nd Battle of Jav. A Demon Anti-Mage singlehandedly turned the tide at the east gate, neutralizing a line of magical smoke deployed by the Westrians. This critical move helped maintain the stalemate that Jav held for years, showcasing just how formidable Anti-Mages can be on the battlefield.","guide":"Anti-mages do well against mages as the name suggests. Dispel magic is a guaranteed removal of a magical effect that has many possible uses. Whether its buffs, control spells or debuffs, dispel magic can remove it all.\n\nIf you know you're up against a mage that can shield themselves or allies, you can cast Anti-Shield on them. For many mages, shields are an important defense and Anti-Shield can be safely re-applied to them every turn to deny them this.\n\nIf your allies are under fire by enemy mages, you can use Anti-Magic Shield on them. It gives them 1 RP and reduces the damage they take on top of that.\n\nCounterspell can be gamechanging if used to counter an important spell. Though it has high potential, it also has a high RP cost. If you try to counterspell simple damage spells, you'll quickly find yourself running out. Save your RP and only use it to deny a spell the opposing mage absolutely needs to cast.","keyAbility":"Magic Resistance","abilities":["Dispel Magic","Anti-Shield","Anti-Magic Shield","Counterspell"]},{"id":"arcanist","name":"Arcanist","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Mage or Sorcerer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Appraise, Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"While many Mages focus on transforming mana into different elements, Arcanists take a different path. They dedicate themselves to mastering its purest form—the raw, unaltered magic known as Arcane. It might not be as flashy as other types of magic, but when it comes to sheer power, nothing else comes close.\n\nArcane magic is notoriously difficult to defend against. However, it demands a lot from the caster, drawing heavily on their personal mana reserves. That's why Arcanists spend so much time meditating and training—to build up their mana and ensure they can wield this potent force.\n\nThese Mages are the masters of fundamental attack magic, capable of delivering devastating blows of pure magical energy. When it's raw power you need, an Arcanist is the one you want on your side.","guide":"Arcanists have relatively high mana costs, but their expanded circuits key ability gives them a bit extra to work with. Arcane Buster is a tool for dealing with opposing spellcasters due to its shieldbreaker property.\n\nArcane Explosion is a simple AoE spell that forces you to get close to the action. In exchange, it does not provoke attacks of opportunity and has the rapid keyword. If you're swarmed by grunts, two arcane explosions can go a long way to clearing them out.\n\nTo help with this, Arcane Power exists. It has a steep mana cost, but costs no action and all spells in this class do arcane damage.\n\nFinally, they have Magic Missile II which is a spammable version of Magic Missile. This is also powerful when used in conjunction with Arcane Power, especially against enemies that rely on dodge. 4 Arcane Power'd Magic Missiles are a serious threat against them.","keyAbility":"Expanded Circuits","abilities":["Arcane Buster","Arcane Explosion","Arcane Power","Magic Missile II"]},{"id":"archer","name":"Archer","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Ranger mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness,or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain 5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Stealth, Medicine, Perception, Survival, Animal Husbandry or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Archers are the masters of ranged combat, commanding the battlements during times of war. Skilled squads of Archers were feared for their ability to deliver devastating volleys of missiles at high speed, effectively keeping infantry advances at bay. Their keen eyes and sharp intuition allowed them to choose the most effective ammunition for maximum impact.\n\nThe title \"Archer\" originally referred to those who wielded bows, but as technology evolved, so did the term. With the invention of crossbows and firearms, those who demonstrated exceptional skill with these new weapons still proudly took on the title. Today, \"Archer\" represents anyone with a remarkable talent for ranged prowess, regardless of the weapon they use.","guide":"Archers build on the ranger with a heavier focus on ranged attacks. They gain Status Assessment II, which in addition to showing HP also informs you of damage type strengths and weaknesses. Knowledge on what to use against enemies can be very important and this should be used frequently.\n\nFor single target attacks, they gain Snap Shot II. It allows the archer to make a light attack at a mana cost. While it competes against the normal snap shot, it has no AP cost. It is best used when an enemy is low on hit points and you lack AP to finish it before it can take a turn.\n\nThe archer is strong against small groups and big groups. Against big groups, a volley covers a very large area. Against smaller groups, multishot can target multiple enemies with a heavy attack doing serious damage or burning RP. The mana cost for overcharging it isn't too high either, so you could feasibly attack several enemies at the same time.\n\nFinally, for the creative archers out there there is Unerring Aim. While it has a less immediately clear combat purpose, targeting things such as a rope holding a chandelier or a potion an enemy is holding in their hands can still prove useful.","keyAbility":"Status Assessment II","abilities":["Unerring Aim","Volley","Snap Shot II","Multishot"]},{"id":"archsage","name":"Archsage","tier":3,"role1":"Utility","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Sage mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Appraise, Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The Sage is a class that specializes in augmenting the magical abilities of themselves. They are highly skilled in the use of magic enhancement spells and techniques, able to boost the power and effectiveness of other magic used by themselves.","guide":"The archsage brings more utility to the table, further augmenting spells they might have from other classes.\n\nPersistent spell adds another turn to the duration of a buff or debuff. Most of these have a short duration to begin with, so this can double the duration in a lot of cases.\n\nBattle Cast can be used when pressured by a melee enemy to cast spells without the risk of being attacked. It has a mana cost, so sometimes it may be better to simply retreat.\n\nIf the archsage has mana, they can have powerful turns with the use of Presence of Mind. Reducing the ap cost by 2 is effectively the same as getting 2 AP, allowing for a potential 6 AP turn as long as mana lasts.\n\nTo help with their mana issues, they have clearcasting. It is hard to find a better use of your encounter start ability than reducing the mana cost by 2.\n\nFinally, they have their Secret Art: Ultimate Spell. It works on AoE spells as well as single target ones and by turning it into true damage you ignore guard as well as damage resistances.","keyAbility":"Augmented Casting - Persistent Spell","abilities":["Battle Cast","Clearcasting","Presence of Mind","Secret Art: Ultimate Spell"]},{"id":"armiger","name":"Armiger","tier":2,"role1":"Utility","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Any class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning, Reason, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Appraise, Artifice, Magic, Stealth, Athletics or Art. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Armigers are those who follow a lesser-known path of the Wandering Witch, Chroma-Daria Lichtvog—a discipline cloaked in the folds of space rather than time. They are said to draw upon hidden realms between the mortal world and the heavens, forging tiny pockets of reality where their relics lie waiting. While others try to replicate this inter-dimensional craft through mere artificing, the mimicry cannot begin to understand the true nature of the world beyond the veil.\n\nStories speak of Armigers phantom thieves, making valuables disappear in the blink of an eye with sleight of hand. But in reality they carve out their vault in the emptiness between planes, shaping that space with will and technique. To the untrained eye, an Armiger seems to summon weapons out of thin air—one moment, their hands are empty; the next, they brandish whatever blade suits the situation. Scholars debate whether these conjurations come from raw sorcery or from the Witch’s ancient teachings, locked away in scrolls that vanish just as quickly as the vaults themselves.\n\nFacing an Armiger in combat can be jarring, for they never truly run out of options. One weapon broken, another materializes. An opponent thinks them cornered—yet the Armiger draws forth an entire arsenal from nowhere, their weapons gleaming in starlight and swirling dust. In a single, fluid motion, they swap armaments as easily as drawing a breath. An attack with a mace to break armor could suddenly become the pointed tip of a spear—a confusing dance that keeps opponents constantly on the defensive.\n\nThe best among them often walk unarmed with a calm confidence, knowing that whatever threat appears, they carry an arsenal in the blink of an eye. And though some see the Armigers’ ability as merely convenient, rumors persist of deeper secrets hidden in those dimensional pockets. For Armigers, it’s not just about storing trinkets—it’s about understanding the distance between worlds, that tenuous thread of reality and emptiness. No Armiger is ever truly disarmed—and perhaps thats what makes them fearsome.","guide":"An armiger's primary strength in combat lies in their versatility through the items stored in their Dimensional Armory. As such, the most difficult part of being an Armiger comes before the battle starts in how you fill it up.\n\nThe dimensional armory gives a lot of extra burden you can work with, allowing you to retrieve them quickly through Fast Dimensional Equip. This does cost either mana or RP, both valuable combat resources. Using it with RP allows you to change the weapon midattack, giving you options such as changing to a different damage type or swapping to a katana for the extra crit. The 0 AP swap can also be helpful in letting you alternate between melee and ranged combat without losing any AP.\n\nWith Full Dimensional Equip, you can change your armor easily alongside your weapon. This gives an Armiger an unusual advantage in being able to swap their armor to fit the situation, where normal people are stuck with their choice even if it's less optimal.\n\nArmiger's out of combat utility comes from Send To Armory. The armory can hold any sort of item, allowing you to steal or hide things with no risk of what you took ever being found. It has little use in combat, though if an enemy ever drops a weapon to switch to a different one, you can ensure they can't pick it back up.","keyAbility":"Dimensional Armory","abilities":["Send To Armory","Fast Dimensional Equip","Dimensional Armory Expansion","Full Dimensional Equip"]},{"id":"armorsmith","name":"Armorsmith","tier":1,"role1":"Artisan","role2":"Defender","difficulty":2,"requirements":"None","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness. You also gain proficiency in Heavy Armor or Greatshields.","soul":"You gain +1 to Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Armorsmithing. You also gain 5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Riding or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Chainmail, gambeson, lamellar, plate. Protection came in an uncountable variety throughout the ages, evolving to greater heights in direct competition with weapons as the years marched on. A race between offense and defense that would carry on into the future, unending.\n\nBut unlike a weapon, a well made suit of armor was not just a representation of craftsmanship, of the materials forged and riveted and sewn, but of design. Of careful planning, measurement, and even artistry. While weapons were held up in the romantic eye of forging, it was armor that pushed a smith to their limits. Consideration of the intended wearer, of the amount of flexibility in the design if it was intended to be more generic, and the limitations and strengths of various materials were all factors that had to be accounted for before the first ingot entered the forge.\n\nAn armorsmith had to not just be a master of metals but of linens, silks, leathers, wools, and hides of an uncountable number of beasts. They had to have an eye for form and function. A learned or inherent understanding of the physics of the body and movement. Intuit the forces of imagined impacts, weak points, and failures. They needed to have a fundamental understanding of how to break things, all in the effort to prevent their work from being broken.","guide":"The armorsmith is a crafter that takes on the role of a defender when in combat. They prefer to wear armor and shield that they crafted themselves and should be expected to wear at least medium armor.\n\nYour armor choice is very important, as it affects multiple of your abilities. With share armor, you can temporarily give the guard bonus and block bonus of your armor over to an ally. This ability won't do much if you're using light armor, but if you're using a well crafted heavy armor you can increase an ally's guard by up to 4 allowing them to shrug off most light attacks. Very powerful against large groups of grunts, as it will work against all of them.\n\nReinforce Armor is another ability that changes greatly based on your armor. The doubled guard can be useful when you're being light attack spammed, but the extra block can also be used when you're facing an enemy that does high heavy damage to allow you to still fully block it.\n\nFor crafting, thermal quench is best used as your last action to gain the maximum possible benefit from it and repair armor is just a simple repair ability.\n\nFAQ:\n\nQ: Does Westrian Style tool apply to Thermal Quench?\nA: Yes, every 5 that is ‘rolled’ because of the Westrian Style tool counts as a 5 for Thermal Quench.","keyAbility":"Armorsmith Basics","abilities":["Repair Armor","Share Armor","Thermal Quench","Reinforce Armor"]},{"id":"artificer","name":"Artificer","tier":1,"role1":"Artisan","role2":"Utility","difficulty":2,"requirements":"None","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Artificing. You also gain 5 skill points to spend in Artifice, Magic, Linguistics, History or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Artificers were the great equalizers of the world. In a land where magic was steeped into the fiber of every being, those who failed to understand its mysteries suffered a steep disadvantage. During the Great Divine War where magic razed the land and powerful Divine Arms leveled cities, the desperation of the weak created the first artifices—artificial spirit circuits that used magical fuel to function. This allowed even the magically inept, but studied warriors to brave the battlefield against the hellscape of fireballs and magic missiles. Contained in compact shells, magical fuel was compressed into an easy to use form and inserted into the artifice which allowed devastating spell effects to ignite at the press of a button.\n\nAfter the war, Artificers brought comfort and convenience to the world... filling the night streets with an easy to maintain source of light that didn't rely on dangerous gasses or fuels. Their devices fed the world through agricultural technology and brought nations together with fleets of wondrous airships that brought trade and culture from far away lands.\n\nTo this day, Artificers are a staple in society... and some still take on the pioneering spirit of their ancestors, creating new wondrous tools for the future of the realm.","guide":"The artificer is an artisan class that functions as a utility class outside of crafting.\n\nYour Blackbird is a very powerful scouting device, able to scout long distances at little cost. Unlike most other forms of scouting, the blackbird carries little risk even if its discovered only requiring an errand action to repair. Another errand action you have is repair artifice, which can be more useful than other repair skills thanks to Overclock. Overclock might give you that little bit of crafting boost that you need, at the cost of making the item start broken. It doesn't cost a crafting dice, you so don't need to use it unless the craft would otherwise fail.\n\nYour final ability is Quick Artifice Reload. While weak when you start out, the more artifices you get the more use you'll get out of this as it allows you to use powerful artifices more than once per combat without having to spend a lot of AP reloading.","keyAbility":"Artificer Basics","abilities":["Repair Artifice","Blackbird","Overclock","Quick Artifice Reload"]},{"id":"assassin","name":"Assassin","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Rogue or Culinarian mastered, any tier 2 class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness, Cunning or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 Focus, Power or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Stealth, Deception, Roguecraft, Perception, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Assassins trace their origins back to the lawless city of Telsin, deep in the Southern Desert. With little military power of their own and relying mostly on the harsh desert environment for protection, the people of Telsin developed less conventional methods of defense. Assassins emerged from this need, honing their skills in reconnaissance and studying their targets with meticulous care, mentally preparing themselves before executing the perfect kill.\n\nTheir reputation for precision and effectiveness quickly spread, becoming so legendary that other nations started to take notice. Before long, these nations began hiring assassins of their own, both to eliminate key targets and to counter the deadly expertise of other assassins.","guide":"The assassin functions best when they get the jump on the enemy. Their Inconspicuous key ability is key for this, as it lets them get a surprise attack even if the rest of the party isn't quite as sneaky.\n\nWhen they get the surprise, they can use their Death Mark ability. It gives them a small benefit on killing the target, but the real use is opening up the target to their other abilities.\n\nDevastating Strike III is the first of those abilities. Similar to the normal devastating strike, but it does guaranteed maximum damage.\n\nTheir Secret Art: Assassinate is the second of those abilities. While a sure-hit and full pierce heavy attack is already strong by itself, it shows its true potential against enemies who are unaware of you. Due to this nature, it is a rare secret art ability that must be activated in the first round or lose power.\n\nStudy Target has minor issues in a direct fight, though getting a lock-on heavy attack for 4 combined AP is not bad against dodgy enemies. When there's a temporary lull in the action, for example through an acolyte sanctuary barrier, setting up a study target before hand will give you an edge when the fighting resumes. It can also be used to force a Death Mark onto an enemy if you were unable to get the surprise round before. However, this is very AP inefficient so it should most likely be avoided in most cases.","keyAbility":"Inconspicuous","abilities":["Death Mark","Study Target","Devastating Strike III","Secret Art: Assassinate"]},{"id":"aurora-blade-style","name":"Aurora Blade Style","tier":2,"role1":"Controller","role2":"Striker","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any class mastered. Proficiency in at least one of light swords, longsword, katana or dueling weapon.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning, Reason, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Athletics, Intimidation, Magic, History, Flight, Survival or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Idris deflected a spine with a grunt, the undulating limb that had lashed out at him retracting in a jittering pattern as the fiend wound up for another attack. A fiend off to the side shrieked as half its body froze suddenly and shattered. A flurry of icy blasts and arcane bolts checked the advance of a group of lesser fiends, allowing him to focus on the big one trying to skewer him. He ducked a sweeping attack and drifted out of the way of a slam with a gentle tap of his foot against the frozen ground. He hovered for a moment before his feet touched down again as he brought his sword around, the frost infused blade biting deeply into the side of the fiend, sending it staggering away. He lifted off into the air with the recoil of the blow, grimacing at the feel of chilly dampness on his feet.\n\n\"Aaah, this is so dumb! Why isn't Illyana here?! Getting married isn't as important as exploring somewhere new!\"\n\nHe looked over and saw his two companions huddling behind a deteriorating wall of ice as a group of fiends was barraging them with energy blasts. Mirane peaked out from cover to throw some icicles the size of trees at the fiends before the combined fire forced her back behind cover.\n\n\"Idris!\"\n\n\"I'm busy!\" he called back, parrying another attack and using the momentum to drift up and over a second attack. He twisted in mid air as some of the fiends with the ranged attacks focused on him, his sword sparking as he was forced to block one of the dark bolts that he couldn't avoid.\n\n\"Agh! This is dumb! Chroma, time out!\"\n\n\"Stop.\"\n\nIt was a simple command but the world obeyed. Bolts of energy were stopped mid flight, the fiends suddenly as still as statues. Even the snow had stopped falling, snowflakes stationary in the air.\n\n\"Can't you do anything about these guys over here, Idris? We can't do anything \u0018cause they keep shooting at us!\"\n\n\"If I do, the big one will rush you. You want to deal with those tentacles?\" He drifted slowly toward the ground, crossing his legs like he was sitting on the ground even as he hovered in place.\n\nMirane shivered and shook her head. \"No no, I'm good.\"\n\n\"We're too used to Illyana taking up a frontliner role,\" Chroma said. \"If she were here, this fight would be over already.\"\n\nIdris sighed. \"Okay&I can give you some cover so we can focus on the big one. We should be able to bring it down with combined fire, it's not very tough. It's just really grabby.\"\n\n\"We can do that. We can do that, right, Chroma?\"\n\nThe chronomancer sighed and rubbed her forehead, disguising the fond smile from Mirane. \"We can do that, yes.\"\n\n\"Great! Good plan! Time in!\"\n\nWith a snap of her fingers, Chroma let time resume. Without missing a moment, Idris rushed across the field. Whisps of aurora trailed his sword as he swung it in a vertical arc. A prismatic wall of shifting auroras stretched into the sky and completely blocked the sight of the group of ranged fiends. Then, in a flash of frost and ice, he was back in the face of the disconcertingly tentacled fiend, his sword coming down like a glacier turned into a guillotine. Ice magic and arcane blasts slammed into the suddenly frozen fiend.\n\n\"Haha! This is more like it! Great work, Idris!\"\n\nIt was a little awkward and they still made a few mistakes on their travels through the mountains and tundra, but they eventually began to develop new tactics to cover their missing member. Now, if only they could develop new tactics for dealing with Mirane insisting the legendary paradise that was supposed to exist in these mountains was \"Just over the next ridge, I can feel it!\"\n\nStill&every new day seeing a new sight was worth it just to see her smile. Mirane's wonder at every new vista filled his heart with warmth and he always caught Chroma smiling behind her hand as they watched Mirane scramble to be the first over the next rise.","guide":"The Aurora Blade Style is a controller and striker melee class.\n\nWinter's Edge is your standard opener, giving you a precise attack that slows on hit rather than on damage. This makes it very reliable to apply slow with if you have a decent amount of focus.\n\nAurora Slash is a long range slowing attack that also slows on hit, but it's only a light attack. This makes it less reliable for applying slow, but it has a powerful added benefit of adding a line of sight blocking wall. You will likely have to move to gain benefit from it, but luckily you have Rimestep.\n\nRimetep is an ability you can only use after an enemy is slowed by a Frost keyword ability. This means it does not work with attacks such as Crippling Attack, but does work with Cryomancer stuff. Notably, it doesn't have to be YOUR slow that triggers Rimestep. If your ally applies a slow as a Cryomancer, you can activate Rimestep of it. Because it's 0 RP to use, you can also use it after Winter's Edge as a free reposition around the target.\n\nFinally, your secret art Permafrost Guillotine is a heavily discounted attack that can only be used after Rimestep. It's a rare low AP cost attack that does not cost mana itself, but the Rimestep requirement makes it more limited for a pure DPS character as you'll be forced to use precise and light attacks that do cost mana to trigger it. Though if you can get an ally to trigger Rimestep on your turn, it can be very powerful.","keyAbility":"Frost Weapon","abilities":["Aurora Blade Style: Winter's Edge","Aurora Blade Style: Aurora Slash","Aurora Blade Style: Rimestep","Aurora Blade Style Secret Art: Permafrost Guilotine"]},{"id":"bajiquan-style","name":"Bajiquan Style","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Cultivator or Martial Artist mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Perception, Insight, Medicine, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Bajiquan is a martial art crafted by the Wolffolk of the Susururu Woods, building on the ancient techniques of Kiraran martial arts. This discipline is all about focusing and compacting one's own mana, over and over, until it can be unleashed in a single, explosive strike. The practitioners of Bajiquan move with a fluid grace, seamlessly blending flowing movements with sudden, devastating bursts of power. It's a style that turns the battlefield into a dance, a ballet of destruction with the Bajiquan fighter at its center.","guide":"Masters of the Bajiquan Style use their Zhen Jiao to take small movements across the battlefield and deal bonus damage. It only applies when moving directly towards an enemy, just dancing around them isn't what Bajiquan is about. Before they can make use of this, they must first enter the Tempestuous Fire Stance. This stance limits what you can do and most notably disables moving without canceling the stance, but it does work even non-bajiquan unarmed strikes.\n\nOnce in their stance, Double Palm Strike is the main opening move of a Bajiquan user. It pushes the target back up to 15ft, which sets it up for a follow up movement from fire stance and gives the bonus damage from Zhen Jiao.\n\nThe highest value that can be obtained from the Zhen Jiao is a follow up with Tetsuzanko. With a 3 AP cost, you are able to move 15ft before using it when in your stance which perfectly matches the maximum pushback distance from Double Palm Strike. Tetsuzanko also pushes the target back again, which may lead to another follow up if using an ability such as fight or flight.\n\nThe other follow up option is Elbow Uppercut. Double Palm Strike is also an unarmed attack, so it matches the combo requirements to let Elbow Uppercut deal its full pierce damage.","keyAbility":"Fire Stance","abilities":["Double Palm Strike","Zhen Jiao","Elbow Uppercut","Tetsuzanko"]},{"id":"bard","name":"Bard","tier":2,"role1":"Support","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Idol mastered. Alternatively, have at least 5 skill points in the Art (Singing) expertise, Art (Idol) expertise or at least 5 points in an Art expertise of an instrument.","heart":"You gain +1 to Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Appraise, Art, Negotiation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Bards are the storytellers, entertainers, and actors of the world, hailing from all sorts of disciplines. Whether they're performing in a bustling tavern for a handful of tips or captivating a crowd in the town square, Bards bring life and joy wherever they go. They're the ones who immortalize the tales of adventuring parties, ensuring that no deed, whether noble or notorious, goes unheard.\n\nIn a party, Bards play a crucial role by inspiring their allies to achieve greatness. With their music, they can lift spirits and hype up their companions, turning the tide of battle with a well-timed tune.","guide":"The bard is a support class primarily focused around their Inspiring Song and Dirge of Despair. Inspiring Song gives every ally a 1d4 bonus to a roll once per round. It may not seem much, but it can be used to push a barely missed attack into hitting. Dirge of Despair is the opposite, affecting enemies instead. Due to allowing a save, it's a bit less reliable but a lot of fights may have more enemies than allies on the battlefield. Because both of these are songs and cannot be used at the same time, the bard has to choose which one they want to use. In general, Inspiring Song is more offensive while Dirge of Despair is a more defensive song.\n\nTheir other support ability is Siren Song. It also cannot be used with the other two songs, but it can be a powerful CC against grunts. Because they spend the AP on their turn, their movement provokes attacks of opportunities and even if they are broken free, their spent AP remains lost.\n\nTheir last combat ability is Shatter, which is a good follow up after luring enemies closer with Siren Song. The AP cost makes it usable even when keeping up Inspiring Song or Dirge of Despair as well.","keyAbility":"Toss a coin","abilities":["Inspiring Song","Dirge of Despair","Shatter","Siren Song"]},{"id":"battle-mage","name":"Battle Mage","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Have at least 1 spell, Be proficient in at least 1 melee weapon.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness or Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 Focus, Power or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Athletics, Intimidation, Magic, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"There was once a time when pure, unbridled magic was the most powerful force in the land. A single mage could hold off entire enemy battalions with ease. But that changed with the invention of Artificing. Suddenly, battles began to shift, with more and more fighters targeting mages directly, exploiting their difficulty in close combat. As the martial world integrated rapid uses of internal mana and artifices, mages found themselves on the defensive, facing enemies up close like never before.\n\nIn response to this new threat, the first Battle Mages emerged from Northi. These warriors developed a unique spell weave, while incredibly mana-intensive, it allowed them to cast spells rapidly, even in the heat of close-range combat. This innovation took full advantage of their physical prowess as Chimera, turning them into formidable opponents both near and far.\n\nThe invention of the \"Shooting Form\" further enhanced their capabilities. This technique allowed Battle Mages to imbue their melee weapons with the properties of staves, enabling a seamless transition between long-range spellcasting and close-quarters combat. With this versatility, Battle Mages became a force to be reckoned with, combining the raw power of magic with the physicality of martial arts.","guide":"The battlemage is a competent switch striker, being able to swap between melee and ranged combat instantly. Weapon Swap has no cost and can be used even on an enemies turn, allowing you to swap to melee form if an enemy thinks he can just walk away.\n\nMage Armor gives a lot of flexibility which is normally unavailable. When fighting a horde of weak monsters, you can start in heavy armor and watch their attacks bounce off almost harmlessly. Against a hard hiting boss, starting in light for maximum evasion might be better. If you made a mistake or the situation changes, a 2 AP cost is an acceptable price to pay for a change. Your RP changes as well, so starting in heavy armor and then moving to lighter armor as the fight progresses is a valid strategy.\n\nDragon Breaks The Ranks is a long range gap closer that moves you forward with devastating force. The high AP cost may make it hard to use, but don't overlook the AoE damage part of the charge. It can also be used to escape from a tough situation as it gives flight, lots of movement and you don't provoke, provided you have a target you can charge to.\n\nBecause the battle mage wants to spend time in melee combat, battle cast is a necessity to be able to cast spells without putting yourself at risk.\n\nCircle Swing is their main melee attack. It allows you to create space and follow up with a cheaper spell or ranged attack. Be aware that you may still provoke attacks from other enemies you are engaged with, even if you main target is now unable to.\n\nThe most common weapon for a battle mage is a polearm. The extra range on attacks makes it easier for it to weave melee and spells without provoking.","keyAbility":"Mage Armor","abilities":["Dragon Breaks The Ranks","Battle Cast","Shooting Form","Circle Swing"]},{"id":"battlemaster","name":"Battlemaster","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Adventurer or Fighter mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning, Reason, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Appraise, Athletics, Riding, Deception, Medicine, History, Perception, Insight, Survival, Negotiation, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"A versatile fighter that can use any weapon.","guide":"The battlemaster is an expert in all weapons. If you find a good weapon, whether its an artifice, relic or even a divine arms, you will be able to use it to its maximum effect.\n\nYou also don't need to worry about being unable to use certains attack with your new weapon due to the Unconventional Weapon ability. It has the potential for silly combos, such as using Iai while a greataxe.\n\nBeing a master of battle, they posses ways to punish both Dodge and Guard focused characters. Skillful blow has lock-on to make it good against high agility where as Mordschlag's guard crush allows it to punish heavily armored enemies.\n\nDisarming Attack is their last ability and it can give them the edge in a duel against most martial enemies. If they forgot to bring a spare weapon, the disarm all but disables them for a turn.","keyAbility":"Arms Mastery","abilities":["Mordschlag","Skillfull Blow","Unconventional Weapon","Disarming Attack"]},{"id":"berserker","name":"Berserker","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 Power or Focus.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Athletics, Perception, Survival, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Berserkers are aggressive fighters that almost completely ignore defense in exchange for more offense.","guide":"Berserkers are highly aggresive fighters that rely on allies to keep them alive. They are centered around their rage stance, which gives them 2 bonus AP in exchange for disabling RP abilities. A person without RP is extremely vulnerable, so you will need allies to cast thing like the acolyte's Angel's Embrace on you for protection. Alternatively, you can wait with using it until you are have burned through some RP already. You will lose out on some power, but it may be better than going down.\n\nBoth Break Free and Fallen Friend fit the playstyle of waiting with Rage Stance instead of using it immediately. Break Free especially is powerful against enemies with heavy CC effects.\n\nInto the fray is a gap closer that lets you approach an enemy without spending AP, allowing for a maximum amount of attacks after. The RP cost makes it so its best used when already in rage stance where your RP is less useful.\n\nThe same applies to Reckless Strike. Normally trading 1 RP for 1 AP is not worth it, but when you can't use your RP anyway, it is a good way to get some extra damage in.","keyAbility":"Fallen Friend","abilities":["Rage Stance","Into the Fray","Break Free","Reckless Strike"]},{"id":"biochemist","name":"Biochemist","tier":2,"role1":"Specialist","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Alchemist mastered or Transmutered mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning, Reason, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Riding, Appraise, Medicine, Magic, History, Animal Husbandry, Art or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Yanyan stood in front of the mirror. Her cat ears twitched nervously as she inspected herself. \"Not good enough.\" She murmured to herself. Camielelileananu would never notice her looking like that.\n\nWith a sigh she stepped away, the cat ears and tail disappearing as if they were never there. She laid down on the bed and began to browse through her large collection of information on her idol. Articles Camielelileananu had written, interviews with her and even just a map of where she traveled.\n\n\"She showed great loyalty and courage.\" Yanyan read a comment from her about a dogfolk guard that saved a child. That was just praising an individual person, nothing to do with the race. Camielelileananu spent a lot of time around some slimes, but that was to be expected. One of the greatest minds in her field was a slimegirl after all.\n\nYanyan had studied this over a dozen times already, trying to figure just WHAT type of chimera her love was into. Her eyes fell onto the map again and landed on Houkaina. It was a country of Merfolk, relatively small. However, Camielelileananu had been there multiple times already for book signings. Could it be?&\n\nShe wasted no time. Yanyan immediately got up from her bed and began to pack her stuff. She couldn't yet transform into a merfolk, but she knew where to get the samples required for that.","guide":"The biochemist class is a specialist class that is very dependent on having the correct gene.\n\nYou can collect samples through… various methods and use them with Biohacking to temporarily have access to the gene. You will really want the increased gene limit from mastering the class to give yourself more options.\n\nYou activate these samples through Gene Activation, which gives you a temporary bonus. Your usefulness heavily depends on what genes you decided to bring with you.\n\nHelix Siphon lets you work around the usual limit on genes, as long as you're fighting chimera's or are partied with some. Your power as biochemist greatly increases if you have allies with you that give you useful genes.\n\nG. Shift is an encounter start that lets you mimic the effects of an elixir, at the cost of 1 extra AP or RP. It also still costs HP, so not necessarily what you'd want to use every fight but free elixirs are good.\n\nAnima Synthesis Form is your secret art and it gives you the entire subrace for the whole encounter. Like with gene activation, it heavily depends on what gene you decided to bring. Some races are always good though, such as horse for horse step accel or harpy for flight.","keyAbility":"Transmuter of Life","abilities":["Gene Activation","Helix Siphon","G. Shift","Secret Art: Anima Synthesis Form"]},{"id":"black-oath-style","name":"Black Oath Style","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Cultivator or Martial Artist mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 Focus, Power or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Deception, Intimidation, Insight, Medicine or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Fordu D' Nali stood, centered in the middle of the rough road. Behind her, a village was evacuating in the face of the incoming armies of Northi and Westria. Before her, a scouting party of Westrian Crusaders were dismounting, all shining silver armor and shields. At their head, a hulking brute of a man stomped forward, a massive greatsword already licking with holy light.\n\n\"I am Ser Kael, Paladin of the Church of Light. In Kari's name, surrender so that you may be granted a peaceful end,\" the man boomed.\n\nFordu scoffed and took a heavy stance, her fists clenched. \"You want to get past me? You don't have enough blood to pay that toll.\"\n\nThe men behind Ser Kael shifted as if they could feel the weight of power gathering around her. The paladin leveled his sword at her, golden fire ripping down its length, casting an incandescent glow across the shadows of the canyon wall. He took first one step, the ground cracking slightly underneath his might, then another. Then he was running, his sword pointed to skewer her.\n\nShe took a slow, deep breath and released the power singing in her blood. Shadowy wings burst from her back and time seemed to slow. The onrushing paladin no longer barreled down at her like a charging horse. The pain and ache of her Divine Release was captured, channeled, stored. Licks of dark fire flickered around her fists as she waited and watched. Ser Kael closed the distance and she did nothing to stop him from plunging his sword directly through her chest. She barely felt the massive sword, but the holy light ate at her like acid. Even with every bit of her training, she couldn't hold in the scream that ripped from her throat.\n\nBut she didn't fall. Her wings stabilized her, her stance grounded her, and the pain was only fuel. Gathered, condensed, mixed, converted into a dark fire. As close as they were, she could see Ser Kael's eyes widen in shock through the gap in his helmet. Then she struck back. Shadow Counter. Taking the pain of her Divine Release, the agony of being stabbed and burned by holy fire. Her mana flooded with the growing counter, empowering and bringing the potential to its height. Even the impact of her attack she reflected upon herself, amplified, and unleashed to join the rush of force and shadow.\n\nSer Kael ceased to exist from the waist up. Fordu stumbled forward a step without his weight holding her up and she pulled the sword still impaling her painfully out of her chest. It clattered loudly against the canyon floor. She took another step forward and the crusaders Ser Kael brought with him took a step back. She grinned and wiped the blood dripping from her mouth away. Her wings flexed, the Divinity of her blood sustaining her even through a devastating wound.\n\n\"You're not getting away!\" She rushed forward, dark fire gathering around her fists and the screams of the crusaders echoed off the walls.","guide":"The Black Oath style is an unarmed fighting style that sacrifices its own health for extra damage.\n\nYour main tool for this class is the Inexorable Shadow Stance. It lets you deal damage to yourself to boost your damage to enemies by the same amount. Enemies CAN still dodge attacks after you declare your HP loss, but because it would make your action invalid your HP would get refunded. It has some strong uses in overwhelming enemies with light attacks that can suddenly hit extremely hard or punching through his guard and block enemies with overwhelming force. And with Focused Power, you simply guarantee that you deal max extra damage. Dark Surge also synergizes with this, simply giving you a nice small accuracy bonus for using your stance.\n\nEclipse Breaker is a setup move that can deny an area from an enemy. It has no mana cost and and you can start charging it with 1 AP, simply canceling it if nobody is in it.\n\nShadow Counter is another setup move with multiple uses. As you get lower on HP, the damage of this ability increases drastically. This forces an enemy into uncomfortable choices of potentially spending a lot of actions to escape from your attack or risk taking a hard hitting move. You do become weaker defensively due to attacks getting trick attack against you, but if you survive your damage goes up even more.\n\nOverall, the black oath style is a high risk/reward playstyle. Deciding on when to take your damage is key to staying alive.\n\nFAQ:\n\nQ: What happens when an enemy reacts to my attack after I use Inexorable Shadow Stance?\nA: If an enemy decides to Dodge or take a similar sort of action to make your attack miss, that attack would no longer fulfill the ‘on hit’ condition and your HP would be refunded. If any enemy decides to Block however, you would still have spent your HP.","keyAbility":"Dark Surge","abilities":["Inexorable Shadow Stance","Eclipse Breaker","Focused Power","Shadow Counter"]},{"id":"blacksmith","name":"Blacksmith","tier":1,"role1":"Artisan","role2":"Support","difficulty":2,"requirements":"None.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness or Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Power, Focus or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Blacksmithing. You also gain 5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Riding or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Forgers of Lyr's weapons.","guide":"Blacksmith is a crafting class that creates weapons. A lot of your abilities and use will come during interlude phases where you can craft your weapons.\n\nOutside of crafting, you can use Forged Knowledge to boost the damage of an attack you made. It requires you to use a weapon you crafted yourself and you only maximize one dice, so use it when you are a few points of damage of from killing an enemy or to turn a 1 into a 6 or 8.\n\nWith Weapon Maintenance, you give a weapon a +1 bonus to damage or accuracy. It only costs an encounter start action, so there's no reason not to do it if you aren't using it for anything else.\n\nWhen crafting, Steady Craft II is better than rolling on average. You can delay using it to see if you need a higher number at the end before using it, but it will be better most of the time.","keyAbility":"Craft Weapons","abilities":["Repair Weapon","Forged Knowledge","Steady Craft II","Weapon Maintenance"]},{"id":"bloodbinder","name":"Bloodbinder","tier":2,"role1":"Healer","role2":"","difficulty":4,"requirements":"At least 1 class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness or Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Medicine, Magic or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Healers that use their own lifeforce.","guide":"As a Bloodbinder, you’ll want to hover around 50% HP to get the most out of Crimson Enmity. It’s a bit of a balancing act, but the extra healing boost is worth it.\n\nYour bread-and-butter combo is Transfusion followed by Blood Drain. Start by healing your allies with Transfusion, then use Blood Drain to top up your own HP. It’s a great way to keep both you and your team in the fight without leaving yourself too vulnerable.\n\nBlood Shield is super effective when you cast it on someone with high guard. It’s a two for one—blocking damage while also healing them up, so it’s a great move when you need to protect and patch up a teammate at the same time.\n\nLife Sacrifice takes you down to just 1 HP, but all that lost health goes directly into healing an ally, which can be a real game-changer when things get rough. If you pair it with Crimson Enmity, you can really boost its impact and turn the tide when your team needs it most.\n\nFAQ:\n\nQ: Does my healing get increased if using the ability lowers my HP below Crimson Enmity threshold as part of the ability? IE: Through Life Sacrifice\nA: No, the increased healing threshold is determined at the point the ability is used.","keyAbility":"Transfusion","abilities":["Crimson Enmity","Blood Drain","Blood Shield","Secret Art: Life Sacrifice"]},{"id":"bodyguard","name":"Bodyguard","tier":2,"role1":"Defender","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Fighter, Maid or Armorsmith mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Riding, Intimidation, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Bodyguards specialize in protecting a single person.","guide":"The bodyguard is focused around protecting a single target. You can choose who this target is with VIP Protection. They are well-suited to escort and protection missions, but even in normal ones they synergize well with squishy melee allies. Since they automatically get hit and can't react when using the redirect part of VIP Protection, having high Toughness and wearing armor is recommended.\n\nWith Temporary Protection, the bodyguard can pay a heavy mana cost to protect another ally. It should only be used in emergencies, but using it on a low health ally can keep them in the fight without them having to play super defensive.\n\nShelter is a more limited, but powerful version of the re-direct of the key ability. Heavy Attacks will do a lot of damage if you take them without reacting, so Shelter is best saved for those attacks.\n\nAt your side helps you with positioning. It can save your VIP target when they do something stupid or if they get forcefully moved, but it can also be used offensively to teleport next to them when they charge ahead.\n\nVengeance is a cheaper heavy attack that can be used if your VIP target was attacked. If the condition is met, there's rarely a reason not to use it. It becomes even more powerful if your VIP target is below 0 HP, though you obviously do not want that situation to happen to begin with.","keyAbility":"VIP Protection","abilities":["Shelter","Temporary Protection","Vengeance","At your side"]},{"id":"botanist","name":"Botanist","tier":2,"role1":"Gatherer","role2":"Utility","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Forager mastered","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Reason or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Toughness or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Foraging.","description":"The frigid passes surrounding Mt. Merlin were inhospitable places. Cutting winds, icy ground, and regular blizzards made them nearly impassable during the winter months, not that dangerous conditions stopped the adventurous from making the trek into the mountains. Small villages populated by hardy men and women were scattered through the passes and valleys. And each had their share of myths and legends passed down through the years. For the village of Cartrmyn, the Princess of the Mountain was theirs.\n\nAs the story was told, the Princess of the Mountain influenced the chill, the snow, and the storms of the little valley Cartrmyn was nestled in. Said to have the form of a \"woman made of ice\", offerings were left regularly at the beginning and end of winter. A common game among the children of the village was to stay up into the deep night in an attempt to catch a glimpse of the Princess as she collected the offerings. Gifts of wild berries, mosses, lichens, mushrooms of all kinds, stacks of wood from unknown trees, and unheard of herbs would be given by the Princess in thanks. And the types of gifts exchanged would tell the villagers how the winter would go or&as an apology for a harsh season. When piles of berries and nuts and extra firewood was left, the village knew they were in for a dangerous winter; but gifts of wild flowers and herbs told of a mild winter approaching. By heeding the signs left by the Princess, Cartrmyn was able to thrive in even the most extreme seasons.\n\nHowever, it wasn't long before word spread about their guardian Princess and those seeking riches and knowledge would come in search of her. For those who were respectful of the village and of the mountain, they would leave with wisdom and the grace of the Princess and would forever find safe passage in the winter chill. But for those with greed in eyes and evil in their hearts, the Princess was as unforgiving as a sudden winter storm. The unearthly shrieks of those that crossed her echoed across the mountain side like the roars of a hundred mountain lions and the gnashing of a thousand teeth, a dire warning to all that would cross--\n\nMiyu closed the book with a sharp snap and sighed. \"It was just a chainsaw,\" she complained to no one. \"And why do they make it sound like I'm hundreds of years old?!\" Grudgingly, she tucked the book back into the pack that had been prepared by the villagers. Dried meats and fish, metal tools and knives, and a small collection of glowing crystals that she could use to produce more magical fuels. In return, she had laid out hand woven baskets of whatever she'd been able to find over the last week that she wasn't keeping for herself. Berries, tubers, and bundles of medicinal flowers.\n\n\"Why is it so hard to get people to leave me alone?\"","guide":"The botanist, like the forager, is a gathering and utility class. Their only in combat ability is Felling Strike. At first glance it may look like a normal knockback move, but you get to move before doing the knockback, which lets you more easily do things like push enemies of ledges or knock an enemy back into your team.\n\nCraft Pemmican lets you convert food units into rations without the cost of any actions. These rations are easier to carry, don't require a kit to prepare and less likely to be ruined. It's a nice little bonus and there's little reason not to do it whenever you can.\n\nDuring gathering, Memory of the Grove synergizes with the forager abilities as well as the other botanist ability, Stalks of Comparison. Memory can be used in several ways, you can reroll a very low dice to get a better roll, but you can also use it on a higher value one to store it for later use with Stalks or Divining Petalfall.\n\nFor stalks of comparison, it's always a good ability since it can apply to either Node points or Lucky points. Getting the bonus for it can be made easier or even guaranteed with the use of other abilities. Using the stored value of memory along with the pre-determined rolls of Verdant Instinct can get you that bonus.","keyAbility":"Botany Study","abilities":["Memory of the Grove","Trail Mix","Stalks of Comparison","Forager's Eye"]},{"id":"brawler","name":"Brawler","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Martial Artist mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 Power or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Perception, Insight, Survival, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Scrappy fighters that are willing to get into the fray and trade blows.","guide":"A brawler is a scrappy fighter that takes hits to dish them out.\n\nCounter Stance is a risky stance in which you cannot react to attacks through normal means, but you get to make a counter attack afterwards. A brawler has to carefully weigh his options before entering the stance, as he cannot end it until his next turn starts. One option is to only use it when you are already low on RP, as being unable to Dodge or Block has little effect when you lack the RP to do so to begin with.\n\nTo help survive while countering, a brawler has access to Vital Drive II. While the healing itself isn't the most efficient, being able to use it as reaction allows you to stay standing after attacks that should have knocked you out.\n\nSuckerpunch is an amazing opening move, if you can land it. It can only be used when already in melee range of an enemy at the start of the encounter, so getting up in someone's face before you fight them is a good move.\n\nKnockout Punch instantly takes out grunt level enemies and leaves them alive, which sets it apart from similar abilities. Useful for when you need to interrogate them after. The 4 AP cost for a heavy attack makes it risky to use against enemies who still have RP left, so ideally you let your allies set you up before using it.\n\nWind-up punch is an attack meant to punch through tough guards. While it lacks the full pierce or guard crush properties, by adding all the damage together into 1 big attack, the guard is less valuable than what is it applied multiple times.","keyAbility":"Shrug it off","abilities":["Counter Stance","Wind-up Punch","Suckerpunch","Knockout Punch"]},{"id":"carpenter","name":"Carpenter","tier":1,"role1":"Artisan","role2":"Striker","difficulty":2,"requirements":"None","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness or Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Power, Focus or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Carpentry. You also gain 5 skill points to spend in Athletics, History or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"On Sorthen's Marlone coast, where Lizardfolk pilehouses rise above the crashing waves, to the spires of Merlin's Academy of magic in Northi—wherever Carpenters go, civilization follows.\n\nSince the first dawn of Lyr, these artisans were the backbone of civilization. Between their awl, saw and hammer they built up military camps into fortresses and small villages into thriving metropolises.\n\nCarpenters are far from just competent in their art and tools, they also understand that cooperation is necessary for great works. It doesn't matter if its to erect a guildhall estate or to confront the threat of a siege of hobgoblin raiders—Carpenters always work together with their allies like hammer and nail.\n\nCrafting far more than just still buildings, their carvings can be seen in hand and belt for many denizens of the realm. From the first wooden tools, to finely tuned bows from the finest Yew—their equipment are trusted by all professions. Expert carpenters also have the understanding of specialized oil coatings, imbuing their creations with special material qualities.\n\nIn every community, these artisans are known to be indispensable building blocks of society who work tirelessly to push civilization forward, one nail at a time.","guide":"The carpenter is a crafting class that performs like a striker in combat. With Hammer and Nail, you get the option to do guaranteed damage at the cost of some RP and mana pretty frequently. Useful for ensuring you can finish of weakened enemies.\n\nFelling Strike may look like a normal knockback move, but you get to move before doing the knockback, which lets you more easily do things like push enemies of ledges or knock an enemy back into your team.\n\nRepair Wood Weapon is a simple repair ability. In the zone is a crafting ability that you want to use as late as possible. If you're not using another finishing move such as Standard Finish, it's best to always save it for the last dice. Gains more value the higher quality materials you use, as each extra dice you add to the total gives a +1.","keyAbility":"Carpenter Basics","abilities":["Repair Wood Weapon","Hammer and Nail","In The Zone","Felling Strike"]},{"id":"cavalier","name":"Cavalier","tier":1,"role1":"Utility","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"None","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Animal Husbandry, Riding, Intimidation, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The origin of mounted combat and cavalry specifically has been debated among historians since nomadic riders hunted game across the Axian Plains. Cavalry, as it’s recognizably known in a more modern sense, was first organized by humans, utilizing their more advanced techniques of animal husbandry to domesticate and breed horses into mounts and beasts of burden. With their reliance on various animals for labor, humanity had a head start and also had a distinct need for increased mobility on the battlefield. With open plains and rolling hills making up a generous portion of their homeland, humans were at a distinct disadvantage in mobility to the Chimera of Northi.\n\nIn the long conflicts before the advent of Paladins, Westrian cavalry stood as the only near parity force humans could deploy against Northi and Sorthen. Light scouts and mounted archers were the primary uses of cavalry at the time to both maximize the strengths of mounted soldiers and to preserve both the precious skills of the riders and their trained mounts. While there have been many techniques surrounding cavalry over the centuries, modern understanding has codified the most basic of elements into the art of the Cavalier.\n\nToday, the use of cavalry has spread to every corner of Lyr. No matter the type of mount, be it horse, wyvern, or even the humble dragonfly, the Cavalier lays the foundation for all cavalry techniques.","guide":"The cavalier is a mounted combatant that excels in wide open plains. Being a tier 1 class, you get some proficiencies with Lance being the stand out one. It's a speciality weapon that can only be used while mounted, but it's effectively a polearm with a potential for increased damage. Make sure you always carry a backup weapon in case you are forced to fight dismounted.\n\nBecause mounts are such an important part of the cavalier, your mount choice will matter a lot. A horse is the most common choice (or a pony for smaller races). It is the fastest land mount, but it can only move in a straight line and has little other special qualities. The boar is the optimal choice for smaller races, as it will buff their trample and make it work against medium creatures. Wolf is the slowest of the three, but it is not restricted to line movement and has a special attack it can use. For most cavaliers, the horse is the best choice as it will make it easier to activate your Trample.\n\nThe core ability of the cavalier is Trample. It requires you to build up some speed by moving, but once you do you can trample a large amount of enemies in a single movement. It's a sure hit attack that knocks enemies prone, making it extremely punishing if it lands. It does however have some counters to be aware of. First being that you can't trample enemies that are the same size as you, so large enemies are unaffected. Secondly that the enemy can block your attack to stop it. Attempting a direct charge through the enemy tank may not work out very well.\n\nTo help with hit and run attacks, you get Canter. It must be used immediately after attacking, but it lets you sidestep 10ft which can let you move out of range of the enemy. After your out of range, you can then reposition and prepare for another charge.\n\nRider & Mount as one is a passive ability that lets you re-direct attacks to you instead of your mount. Mounts are not as durable as you are, so you will want to almost always use this. AoE attacks cannot be re-directed with this, so be careful of those. It also doesn't work if you're using a flying mount, so you'll want to stick with land based ones.\n\nHorse Whistle is what you can use to get your mount back to you after you're dismounted. This lets you use other abilities such as Faerie Flash or abilities from other classes to temporarily get off your mount without having to walk back to it.\n\nSpirit Jump can be used as an anti-air tool, but it can also be used to help your mount maneuver across difficult terrain such as cliffs or wide pits.","keyAbility":"Mounted Basics","abilities":["Canter","Horse Whistle","Rider & Mount As One","Trample"]},{"id":"chronofighter","name":"Chronofighter","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":4,"requirements":"Any class mastered, proficient in any melee weapon.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning, Reason or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Riding, Intimidation, Perception, Magic or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Chronofighter is a melee-focused class that uses time power to enhance their attacks.","guide":"Chronofighter is a complex class that relies in setting up future turns to take advantage of attacks from the past.\n\nAttacks from the past is a difficult ability to use. Because everything is exactly mirrored based of the position of your previous turn and you cannot move before using it, it comes down to planning and a bit of luck to make good use of. However, when it does, the result is amazing. Being able to double your attacks are almost no cost is incredibly powerful.\n\nAccelerating Strike is a tool that should be combined with the Delay encounter start action, which is free for a Chronofighter. This lets you loop enemies at a crucial point, letting you take two turns in a row before they can respond.\n\nDelayed Hit is a good tool getting around temporary guard buffs. The target can still Block the damage when it hits the turn later, but less intelligent creatures may get faked out by the weird nature of the attack and try to react to it from the start.\n\nButterfly Effect is a ramping ability. The initial mana cost is extremely high and it is not until the third use that it becomes a good use. The total mana cost before it becomes free is 9 mana and it takes at least 3 turns of stacking. Keep this in mind before using it, as it is a heavy commitment and a big waste of mana if you can't get max value out of it. When a fight does last long though and you get to keep stacking it, it is one of the most powerful abilities that exists.","keyAbility":"Past Self","abilities":["Accelerating Strike","Delayed Hit","Attacks from the Past","Secret Art: Everything, Everywhere, All At Once"]},{"id":"chronomancer","name":"Chronomancer","tier":2,"role1":"Support","role2":"Controller","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Mage or Sorcerer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason or Cunning.","soul":"You gain +1 Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Magic or History. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Chronomancers are rare mages who wield the mysterious power of time itself. They can slow down moments, speed them up, or even rewind them, turning the tide of battle in ways that few can predict or understand. In a world where such magic is almost unheard of, Chronomancers stand out as an often feared force.\n\nTheir magic traces back to one source: Chroma-Daria Lichtvog, a wandering Witch and Thaumaturge who’s been around for over a thousand years—at least, that’s what the stories say. Daria teaches her craft on a whim, picking students when it suits her. Most Chronomancers have either learned directly from her or stumbled across her ancient writings, devoting their lives to uncovering the secrets within.\n\nRunning into a Chronomancer means you’re up against someone who can twist the flow of time itself. Whether they’ve been taught by the Witch herself or have painstakingly studied her elusive texts, their powers are as astonishing as they are unsettling.","guide":"Chronomancers are all about controlling the battlefield, and their abilities make them a vital part of any team. When you’re not sure what move to make, use Store Time to bank it for later. Having one extra action the next turn can open up powerful combinations, or help to strike during a more opportune time.\n\nSlow is a go-to for dealing with those quick and slippery foes. It never misses, so you can lock them down or force them to waste their precious resources on defense. Accelerando is a lifesaver for a teammate who got a bad roll on initiative or just needs a speed boost to make an important move.\n\nThe heart of a Chronomancer’s toolkit is Haste. This ability lets your ally get the most out of their buffs or strike during a crucial moment. In a pinch, Galaxy Stop is your trump card. It time stops all the grunt enemies on the battlefield, giving your party the breathing room to either regroup or take out a few foes while they’re defenseless.\n\nWhile a Chronomancer is great at supporting and controlling the flow of battle, they don’t do so well on their own. They shine best when they’re working in tandem with their allies in nearly any party setup, using their versatile abilities to keep momentum.","keyAbility":"Store Time","abilities":["Slow","Accelerando","Haste","Secret Art: Galaxy Stop"]},{"id":"colossus","name":"Colossus","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Controller","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any tier 2 class mastered. Adventurer or Fighter mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Riding, Intimidation, Perception. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"A warrior that fights with two heavy weapons to crush their enemies.","guide":"A colossus wants to use heavy weapons and Titan's Grip means that there is very little reason not to do so. They can use Mighty Leap get into range of an enemy and disrupt all enemies around the target, allowing the Colossus to engage into groups of enemies without severe risk. You can also jump to an empty spot if your goal is just to land an AoE unbalanced debuff.\n\nDouble Slam is two hit combo of which every hit can inflict a debuff on the enemy. You can combo it after apply Unbalanced with mighty leap for a double chance to knock someone prone.\n\nTwo Sword Crush is a powerful ability that lets you push past the guard of an enemy. Slam and Double Slam both only apply their effects on damage and are light attack, making an enemy likely to Block against it. If their guard isn't super high, you can then use Two Sword Crush to do more damage than their Block and apply the effect.\n\nClimax Art: Titan's Blade is a powerful AoE attack that will annihilate people that cannot avoid the initial strike. Can be used as a finisher, but also an opening move to immediately burn some RP from enemies if they line up for you.","keyAbility":"Titan's Grip","abilities":["Mighty Leap","Double Slam","Two Sword Crush","Secret Art: Titan Blade"]},{"id":"cryomancer","name":"Cryomancer","tier":2,"role1":"Controller","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any class mastered or Frost mastery.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to your Focus, Power or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Masters of frost, the Cryomancers weave the raw, chilling power of ice into an art form. Theirs is a domain of control, using their wintry gifts not for sheer damage, but to manipulate the battlefield and dictate the flow of combat.\n\nCryomancers thrive in battlefield control where their icy enchantments can wreak the most havoc. With a wave of their hand, they can transform the ground to ice, halting an enemy advane, or encase foes in blocks of solid frost, taking them out of the fight completely. Their chilling spells can slow even the most agile opponent, leaving them vulnerable to attacks.\n\nDon't let their cold demeanor fool you - beneath the icy exterior lies a burning resolve. To be a Cryomancer is to understand that the battlefield is a canvas, and with the power of frost at their fingertips, they are the artists, painting a portrait of control and chaos in equal measure.","guide":"The combination of Icicle Nail, Sheet Ice and Glacial wall are a hat-trick of battlefield control, both creating cover, halting enemy advances and slowing front line enemy units. As a pure controller, Sheet Ice can be used freely and at minimal cost to block chokepoints or to funnel enemies. It can also be used to hinder the movement of units by casting it into an enemy.\n\nGlacial wall can create cover from nothing, quickly subverting a strategic advantage the enemy might have or bolstering your own.\n\nLastly in a pinch, the Cyromancer can devastate low level enemies with Frost Coffin, immediately eliminating a threat from the battlefield and also creating cover for your team.","keyAbility":"Ice Cold","abilities":["Icicle Nail","Sheet Ice","Glacial Wall","Frost Coffin"]},{"id":"culinarian","name":"Culinarian","tier":1,"role1":"Artisan","role2":"Controller","difficulty":2,"requirements":"None","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Culinary. You also gain 5 skill points to spend in Art, Medicine, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The clamour of half a dozen meals cooking at once, pots and skillets sizzling along with the clank of utensils frantically flipping or stirring. A chaotic dance of food preparation found in the busiest cities in Lyr.\n\nThe quiet crackle of a campfire under the stars, a small pot bubbling gently, wafting steam to mix with the smoke of the fire above. A simple stew nearly ready to be served to friends resting from a day of adventure.\n\nTense concentration as an exotic dish was prepared with an eye for presentation. A drizzle of sauce here, an edible garnish there. The stark white of the plate a spotlight of contrast to draw attention to the artful arrangement fit for a king.\n\nCulinarians came from all walks of life and could be found preparing meals from the austere kitchens of Northi royalty to a simple farming cottage in Sorthen. They shouldn’t be mistaken for anyone able to light a fire and char a slab of meat on a stick. Cooking was their passion and their art. Ingredients simple and elegant, mixed with skill and care, could become soul warming meals. After a day of hiking up a mountain pass, sailing through a storm, or even completing a day of schooling, the comfort of a well cooked meal was bliss beyond words.","guide":"The culinarian is a crafter and controller hybrid that uses various cooking tools to annoy its enemies.\n\nOil Slick is an incredibly powerful zone control tool. It forces an enemy to move only 5ft per action or fall prone, effectively working as a double difficult terrain. By tossing it directly on someone, if they want to move towards you they have to spend at least 2 AP to leave the oil making it a pretty AP efficient trade. It does fail against enemies who can teleport or fly though.\n\nPepper Spray is another powerful tool, giving a guaranteed blind that can be used defensively as well. Blind makes an attack a lot more likely to miss, making up for RP you would have spent on dodging an attack. It can also be used on your turn for no mana cost. It also hits your allies though, so be wary of that.\n\nOn the crafting side, Perfect Seasoning is just a free bonus you can use whenever you add in an ingredient. You're always going to be adding at least 1 and may even get multiple uses out of it when using Stir Layered Flavors.\n\nCraft Pemmican lets you convert food units into rations without the cost of any actions. These rations are easier to carry, don't require a kit to prepare and less likely to be ruined. It's a nice little bonus and there's little reason not to do it whenever you can.","keyAbility":"Culinary Basics","abilities":["Perfect Seasoning","Oil Slick","Craft Pemmican","Pepper Spray"]},{"id":"cultivator","name":"Cultivator","tier":1,"role1":"Utility","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"None","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning, Reason, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Appraise, Athletics, Deception, Perception, Insight, Medicine, Intimidation, Stealth or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"To cultivate is not merely to gather power, but to decide how one will exist within it. While Ki can be sensed and refined by many, a cultivator distinguishes themselves by the principles they choose to shape that power around.\n\nEvery cultivator begins by learning to draw Ki inward and circulate it through the body, but this practice alone does not define the path. What matters is the intent behind it. Some cultivate to stand firm, others to strike decisively, and others still to remain unbound. Over time, these choices influence not only a cultivator’s techniques, but the way they move, react, and behave.\n\nCultivation places constant pressure on belief. Power responds more readily to consistency than contradiction, and cultivators who act against their own principles often find their progress stalling or their techniques failing at critical moments. As a result, most adopt a guiding philosophy early on, refining their practice around it as they grow.\n\nBecause of this, cultivation traditions vary widely. One sect may prize endurance and rootedness, teaching its disciples to weather any storm. Another may emphasize adaptability or freedom, encouraging practitioners to preserve choice and avoid being fixed in place. These differences are not merely cosmetic. They shape how Ki is circulated, how arts are used, and how conflict is approached.\n\nA cultivator’s strength is therefore not measured solely by the amount of power they possess, but by how well their actions align with the path they have chosen. Those who cultivate without direction may achieve temporary gains, but rarely endure. Those who commit to a philosophy, however subtle, find their Ki responding with greater clarity and reliability over time.","guide":"The cultivator class is a utility class with several useful abilities.\n\nKi Circulation lets you remove a variety of debuffs from yourself. You'll most likely use it to remove poisons or unbalanced, as Bleeding and Shaken will likely already have taken effect before you can use it.\n\nKi Sense is a simple tool that lets you know where to search for stealthed targets when they are in range.\n\nKi Recovery is an upgrade from the basic Draw Mana encounter conclusion action and is very useful for anyone that uses a lot of mana.\n\nThe Sword Riding Art is a way of flying that's both better and worse than other ways of flight. You gain some weaknesses to pushbacks and aren't as good in aerial combat, but the upside is that you never get rooted even if you're lowered to the ground level by normal attacks. It does require you to bring a spare weapon that you can't use for combat, so keep that in mind.","keyAbility":"Cultivator's Journey","abilities":["Ki Circulation","Ki Sense","Ki Recovery","Sword Riding Art"]},{"id":"curse-knight","name":"Curse Knight","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Appraise, Athletics, Deception, Perception, Insight, Negotiation, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"A name given to warriors who suffer from a terrible curse. Their frequent misfortune is well known with even their weapons often managing to strike themselves instead of their enemies. However, there are some who manage to channel this misfortune and use its power against their enemies.","guide":"The Curse Knight is a class that can deal a high amount of damage at the cost of their own health.\n\nBacklash is guaranteed damage on an enemy that they almost cannot stop, but you also take some damage yourself. It's good for finishing off low health targets or in fights where you feel the HP loss won't matter.\n\nDevil's Blow is another good damage dealing ability that comes with a risk of potentially hitting yourself. The mana cost is low, so the attack can be spammed as long as you feel lucky. If you have an oracle in your party, then this attack is almost always safe to use.\n\nDevi's Curse relies on the enemy missing to deal damage to them. Best used on their heavy attacks, as the mana cost may not be worth it to reflect a light one.\n\nThe Secret Art: Life Bet lets you do one massive hit, but the damage is based on how much HP you lose from it. Finding an optimal timing may be difficult, as you don't want to use it while an enemy still has reactions left but as the fight drags on, your HP will most likely be lower. Having support from your allies or your other abilities will be key in using this secret art.\n\nFinally, the key ability On my terms allows you to continue using your abilities even as your HP gets lower. You won't need to worry about accidentally killing yourself. You can also use it to effectively ignore enemy attacks of opportunity while you're at low HP, since they will never kill you anyway or stand in effects that trigger at the start of your turn such as a fire.","keyAbility":"On my terms","abilities":["Backlash","Devil's Curse","Devil's Blow","Secret Art: Life Bet"]},{"id":"cutthroat","name":"Cutthroat","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Culinarian or Rogue mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Stealth, Deception, Roguecraft, Perception, Insight, Negotiation, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"-","guide":"-","keyAbility":"Surgical Precision","abilities":["Exposing Stab","Feinting Stab","Devastating Strike II","Artery Cut"]},{"id":"daionmyoji","name":"Daionmyoji","tier":3,"role1":"Specialist","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Onmyoji mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Appraise, Medicine, Religion, Magic Perception, Insight, Art or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Paper scattered away from him in a gust of unnatural wind, talismans shredding even as he was blown off his feet from the attack. Mamouru landed hard and rolled a few times before sliding to his feet. His opponent in the massive melee was grinning, wind magic whipping around her and causing her clothes to snap sharply. The catfolk girl was one of the many aeromancers that had devastated his unit's aerial mages and while the enemy mages hadn't gotten out of the fight unscathed, there were enough of them to drop into the demon backlines. Which was why he was dealing with the psycho catgirl instead of supporting the frontline troops.\n\n\"Oh nyo, all of your little spells just fluttered away! Whatever will the big bad demon do?\"\n\nShe wasn't wrong. He had lost a bulk of his talismans and while he did have his wand and could cast spells himself without those talismans, the windy barrier around her would make actually hitting her incredibly difficult. Still, he leveled his wand at her with grim determination, his divine blood itching underneath his skin, begging for release.\n\n\"Surrender!\" he called out over the wind. \"And I promise you'll be treated fairly!\"\n\nThe girl laughed and took a step forward, foot crunching on a talisman that was doggedly stuck to the ground.\n\n\"Oh, you're funny! You've already lost, idiot!\"\n\n\"I may be an idiot, but I'm not the one that just stepped on a trap.\" The girl's eyes darted down to the talisman now stuck to her foot and then back up at him. With a showy move, he snapped his fingers and a pulse of magic surged out for more than a hundred feet in every direction.\n\nSpells fizzled and died as the mana interference of his dispel disrupted their delicate matrices. Half a dozen aeromancers feel screaming to their deaths as the wind keeping them aloft stripped away from them. But importantly, the windy barrier around the catgirl in front of him died down. In an instant, he drew a very special talisman and held it between his fingers as his hands formed the required seal to unlock it.\n\n\"Ultimate Spell: Divine Disjunction!\"\n\nThe talisman dissolved in a rush of energy as a series of magical circles unfolded before him. The augmented magic missiles flashed away from him in a swarm, trails of magical energy marking their travel. The girl tried to dodge but the missiles were relentless in their homing and their empowered nature slashed through her light armor with no resistance. She had just enough time to look up from where she landed, clutching her bleeding shoulder, to see the second wave of missiles launch from the echo of the first magical circle. By the time the dust settled, there was one less aeromancer to deal with.","guide":"The Daionmyoji is a class that is heavily dependant on the types of talismans you bring.\n\nWith Spell Transfer, you will have more flexibility in that as long as you can find an ally willing to help you.\n\nPrepared Talisman has a lot of possible applications primarily being used as a sort of prepare action that can be held for longer. You could put a cure touch talisman on an ally at the start of combat and only pop it when they get injured allowing you to stay at range. Place a fissure talisman down on the ground in front of you and if an enemy ever tries to approach you, you send them into the pit. It does consume the talisman when used in this way though, so be aware of that.\n\nWith Talisman Recursion you are able to get more use out of the unique talismans from spell transfer, allowing you to for example double fireball even though you only have 1 fireball talisman and you're not a pyromancer yourself.\n\nSpiritual Reading is a mostly utility ability that is a more effective version of several abilities such as aurasense and sense magic at the cost of 1 mana. It has situational use, but if you need to figure out magic in the middle of combat or want to figure out how strong this NPC is, it's good.\n\nThe secret art is the ultimate versatility option. While it does cost you your secret art, you get to replicate any basic spell in the game as you need it. Need to get rid of a magic effect? Get dispel magic. A flier giving you trouble you want to get rid of instantly? Downburst II. Entire team is injured and needs healing? Radiant Halo.","keyAbility":"Spell Transfer","abilities":["Prepared Talisman","Spiritual Reading","Talisman Recursion","Secret Art: Within This Ink, The Perfect Answer"]},{"id":"dark-priest","name":"Dark Priest","tier":2,"role1":"Healer","role2":"Support","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Acolyte, Mage or Sorcerer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason or Cunning.","soul":"You gain +1 to Power or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Religion, Magic, History, Appraise, Deception, Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"By CCeles.","guide":"-","keyAbility":"Soul Absorption","abilities":["Gloom Infusion","Dark Healing","Dark Barrier","Stygian Screen"]},{"id":"deadeye","name":"Deadeye","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Marksman, Gunslinger, Scout or Archer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness, Cunning or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain 5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Stealth, Medicine, Perception, Survival, Animal Husbandry or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"An expert marksman or archer whose unmatched aim allows them to perform incredible feats.","guide":"The deadeye is a ranged striker with some minor control and utility. Status Assessment III is similar to the previous version, but it no longer has the quick keyword meaning it can be used without worrying that it increases the cost of other abilities.\n\nAimed Shot is a simple attack meant to punish enemies that rely on dodge.\n\nDisarming Shot is a powerful tool that can be used to disarm enemies for a long range. Disarming melee enemies may seem like the obvious choice, but many ranged enemies will not carry a spare ranged weapon. Disarming them will most likely lead to them being unable to act for the turn.\n\nCountershot is another tool the Deadeye has to show it is the superior ranged attacker. It is not guaranteed, but it can assist allies and defend yourself against opposing ranged attacks.\n\nSecret Art: Perfect Repetition is not the easiest secret art to use. It has the upside of having no mana cost and relatively low AP cost, but if you roll badly the attack is wasted. On the other hand, a good roll almost ensures a guaranteed hit every round unless the target takes cover. It is more reliable when the enemy has no RP, but don't be afraid to throw it out early and go for a gamble. It's worth the risk.","keyAbility":"Superior Assessment","abilities":["Disarming Shot","Countershot","Aimed Shot","Secret Art: Perfect Repetition"]},{"id":"death-knight","name":"Death Knight","tier":3,"role1":"Defender","role2":"Striker","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Armorsmith or Fighter mastered and any tier 2 class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Power or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Athletics, Religion, Survival, Intimidation, Perception, Insight or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"By Sabbrewolf.","guide":"The Death Knight's versatility comes from their ability to switch between dealing damage and using defensive options depending on the needs of the encounter. They thrive when they have a steady supply of corpses to convert to Bone armor to protect or sustain themselves. As such, timing and resource management are crucial for a Death Knight player.\n\nBone Armor is a core defensive tool that enables you to mitigate a powerful incoming attack.\nUnholy Pact serves as a potent self-heal and buff, converting your Bone Armor into a substantial amount of health. Making the right choice between the defensive boost of Bone Armor or using your resources to heal and focus more on offense will be crucial.\n\nCall of the Grave allows you to force enemies into close-quarters combat, where Death Knights excel, but will have difficulty landing on evasive targets. It's a great opener to control the battlefield and ensure enemies are where you want them while applying pressure with Can’t Escape Death. Just be wary when using that ability lest you find yourself isolated from your allies.\n\nUnholy Strength is a powerful self buff but it requires careful management of your resources so be mindful of your mana.","keyAbility":"Bone Armor","abilities":["Unholy Pact","Call of the Grave","Can't Escape Death","Secret Art: Unholy Strength"]},{"id":"dragoon","name":"Dragoon","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Lancer mastered. 10 Points in the Athletics (Jumping) expertise skill or be a Jiangshi.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Riding, Intimidation, Perception, Common Knowledge or a relevant Expert Knowledge skill (By DM Approval). You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Dragoons are a high mobility class that can fight at great heights without risk.","guide":"Dragoons excel at fighting at heights. They do not need to worry about fall damage when using their dragoon abilities and can turn it into damage for them by using Skydive. When not fighting on an airship or something else that flies, Dragoons can use buildings or trees to gain the height advantage.\n\nIf there is nothing else around, Jump can be used. It is a decent initiation option, though Jump is often better used to reposition or escape from a bad situation than pure initiation.\n\nDragonfire Dive is a powerful AoE tool that puts you in range to follow up with more attacks right after.\n\nJump Back is an ability that allows the dragoon to perform hit and run attacks. You can engage, then jump back to force enemies to waste their movement in coming to you. When fighting in the air, you can jump on an enemy, kill it, then jump back to your airship. There's a lot of possibilities, just keep in mind that it has to be used directly after a Jump ability. Don't stick around for too long, or you aren't able to get back.\n\nTheir Secret Art: Dragonslaying Jump is what makes them masters of aerial combat. It is effectively a guaranteed heavy hit on a flying target that forces them to the ground. Against a target that is flying high above the ground, this last part can easily be fatal.","keyAbility":"Jump","abilities":["Skydive","Dragonfire Dive","Jump Back","Secret Art: Dragonslaying Jump"]},{"id":"duelist","name":"Duelist","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Defender","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Fencer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness, Cunning or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Deception, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The Duelist is a highly skilled fighter who excels in one-on-one combat. They are agile and quick on their feet, using their speed and finesse to outmaneuver their opponents and deliver precise, deadly strikes.","guide":"The duelist, like the fencer it builds on, is a 1v1 expert and off-tank on the battlefield. With deflect missiles, they gain some defense against ranged attacks.\n\nRiposte II is a more defensive version of the original riposte. Where the fencer traded the RP they saved from the Parry ability into damage, with Riposte II the duelist can dish out heavy attacks while sitting on all their RP still. It does cost mana, so it's nothing something that should be used after every Parry.\n\nDuelist Blow is a powerful tool in 1v1s, but since the benefit disappears when forced to use RP against other targets it may be hard to use in fights against multiple enemies unless you can find isolated those 1v1s.\n\nForward Momentum is a simple and cheap ability that helps with that. It's best used with light attacks if the target still has RP remaining. A few attacks and the duelist can fight the target without interruptions.\n\nThe Climax Art: Endless Waltz has the potential for a ton of attacks. It's especially strong against enemies out of RP, against who it may repeat until they are dead. Against grunts, it can still be powerful although less consistent. The first attack would remove their RP, while the second would deal damage. Of course, bad rolls can happen and the ability may end early.","keyAbility":"Deflect Everything","abilities":["Forward Momentum","Riposte II","Duelist Blow","Secret Art: Endless Waltz"]},{"id":"earthcleaving-style","name":"Earthcleaving Style","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any class mastered. Proficiency in any two-handed melee weapon.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Magic, Survival, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"A crowd of warriors was a uniquely noisy experience. Armor clanking and rattling, leather creaking, weapons ringing. There were all types of Youkai at the festival from hulking Oni men with bulging muscles to elegant Kitsune with armor that looked like they cost multiple seasons worth of work to afford. A serene faced Ryujin was just stepping up to the head of the crowd, his horns gleaming in the sun and his scaled armor a masterwork.\n\n\"The Stone Splitting Festival shall now begin. There are boulders from all corners of the world and the prize for splitting each will go to the one who makes the final, splitting stroke. Rewards are, obviously, determined by the quality of the stone.\" He gestured toward the field behind him at the decorated areas containing various sized boulders of different materials. \"Our centerpiece is a ShMki infused basalt from beyond Ezochi, sourced from the depths of the Kita no ShMheki.\"\n\nLeft unsaid was that something like that would be nearly impossible to crack, let alone split. Even still, a significant chunk of the largest and most confident of the crowd immediately went toward the basalt boulder to prove their worth. Yuzu followed behind that group, the wooden carapace covering the mysterious metals of her limbs was hand carved by her grandmother, replacing the cracked, porcelain-like covering she used to have. Her fingers clacked against the handle of her greatsword, tilting it slightly to prevent the tip from dragging on the ground. A Raijin scoffed next to her as he adjusted the katana at his waist.\n\n\"This isn't a game for a doll,\" he sneered. \"You need real muscle for this.\"\n\nYuzu was tempted to flip her hair and walk by him but she didn't want to antagonize people if she didn't have to. They'd be upset enough as it was when she split that boulder. His sentiment was common, especially among warriors, when it came to Marionettes like her or even Jiangshi in small bodies. Her form was static, she couldn't build muscle like an Oni or Kitsune or Raijin. But she could focus more mana into her metal limbs, her wooden skin, and her joints to increase her strength and durability. In fact, she could feel she was only tapping the barest potential of what her body was capable of even now.\n\nBy the time she reached the end of the line, there was already a cacophony of shouts and weapon impacts against stones intermingled with distant cheers as weaker stones were split. But at the basalt boulder, the only sounds were roars of effort and the ring of ineffectual impacts. A cheer went up when she was just about to get her turn when the Raijin that had mocked her used his lightning infused katana to break a finger sized chip off the boulder, marking the most significant damage so far.\n\nFinally it was Yuzu's turn and laughter followed her as she swung her sword off her shoulder to land heavily point down in the ground, balanced by her grip on the crossguard that was just about at eye level with her. Calls to \"get the doll out of here\" rang out but she ignored them. With a shout that drowned them out, she slammed her sword straight down into the earth until it stopped with a tremor at the guard, making those around her wobble. She pulled it out with a slight hop, her sword now coated in jagged stone. She stepped up to the basalt boulder, the shMki of it a palpable aura. She lifted her sword easily above her head.\n\n\"Keisoku HMkai!\"\n\nHer sword came down with a resonating crack, the earth and air vibrating with the force of it. With a groan of protest, the basalt boulder slowly split apart to the stunned silence of the crowd.\n\n--\nTranslator's Note:\n\nShMki - Miasma\n\nKita no ShMheki - Northern Barrier\n\nKeisoku HMkai - Measured Collapse\n\nEzochi - The center northern island of Kirara","guide":"The Earthcleaving style is a class that's focused on busting through heavily armored and low evasion targets. It lets you use your potentially high focus and transfer that into hitting enemies against which you'd normally struggle.\n\nYour basic combo starts with Tectonic Overhead, which is a heavy attack that has a high chance to miss against enemies without low evasion. Only use it against enemies with heavy armor or similar lowered evasion. This combo's into Strata Cut, which is effectively guaranteed half pierce damage. Finally, measured collapse is a full pierce heavy of which you can know in advance whether it will hit or not. If it does, it is one of the best abilities you can use.\n\nWeight of the Mountain is a simple ability that lets you convert focus into damage when you're hitting something that has low enough evasion that you don't need your focus to hit it.","keyAbility":"Earth Weapon","abilities":["Strata Cut","Tectonic Overhead","Weight of the Mountain","Measured Collapse"]},{"id":"electromancer","name":"Electromancer","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Controller","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any class mastered or have Lightning element mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 Focus, Power or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Spellcasters that cast lightning spells.","guide":"Electromancers excel in fighting against enemies in water. Their superconductor ability applies two powerful keywords all lightning attacks for free. This applies even to attacks made with channeling weapons, not just the Electromancer abilities.\n\nZap is an ability with a high chance to apply static. Static is the main debuff of the electromancer and what gives them the controller status. It does not damage the person who has it, but it forces them to position carefully to not hit their allies with it. Your allies are immune to the effect, so you don't need to worry about the enemies hitting them with your static. Static is most effective if combined with roots, such as a netting flask or against enemies already engaged in melee combat, where moving to an isolated spot becomes more difficult.\n\nBolting is a long range strike with a small benefit of potentially ignoring cover. The nature of the attack means it cannot be used indoors however. When not using it as a snipe attack, it's most useful for being a Heavy attack that also applies Static.\n\nForked Lightning is their only way to apply static without using mana. It requires there to be two targets, but static is useless without at least two targets anyway. The static value is lower than on the other attacks is lower to compensate for this lack of mana cost.\n\nChain Lightning can decimate entire groups, provided that their RP has been burned beforehand and you don't get unlucky with rolls. Only use it when at least two people have 0 RP or otherwise cannot react to your attack, otherwise it's not worth the cost.","keyAbility":"Superconductor","abilities":["Zap","Bolting","Forked Lightning","Chain Lightning"]},{"id":"electromaster","name":"Electromaster","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Controller","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Electromancer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Magic, Flight, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Masters of lightning.","guide":"Electromaster builds on the Electromancer, focusing around dealing damage and controlling the battlefield with their static.\n\nLightning Strikes Twice punishes enemies who don’t position themselves properly by transferring any static to the targets they hit. Against clusters of enemies, this can chain into many applications.\n\nWith Static Discharge, they can force this chain reaction even easier. Applying static on an enemy and then instantly discharging it gets the ball rolling quickly.\n\nOnce the static is properly applied, they can begin to do AoE damage through thunderstorm. The damage is not particularly high, but it can hit many enemies. Note that it cannot be used indoors, making Electromasters more suited for outside combat.\n\nAgainst bosses or other scenarios where single target damage is required, they can use Static Overload. It requires static to be applied, but it does decent damage and dazes the target.\n\nWhen they activate their secret art Lightning Field, they become almost unapproachable for grunt level enemies. The constant unavoidable damage will shred through them in only a couple of turns.","keyAbility":"Lightning Strikes Twice","abilities":["Thunderstorm","Static Overload","Static Discharge","Secret Art: Lightning Field"]},{"id":"elementalist","name":"Elementalist","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Controller","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Mage or Sorcerer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Magic, Artifice, Perception, Linguistics or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The sounds of fighting and dying were getting closer and closer. Naori rushed into the throne room, her regal dress replaced with enchanted robes and sturdy boots. Her Queensguard hurried beside her, the clank of their armor and weapons not nearly enough to drown out the sounds of war that were far too close. A harried Captain was just sending off a runner at the foot of the thrones as she came to a stop.\n\n\"What is the situation now, Captain?\"\n\n\"Your Highness,\" he said with a quick bow. \"The King is organizing the defense at the gates and the rest of the keep walls are holding, for now. But we're outnumbered by these vile cats and General Kytur is still days away with the main body of our forces.\"\n\nNaori closed her eyes and took a steadying breath. That her husband was out on the front was not the news she wanted to hear. She knew he'd been when she didn't see him on the throne, but it was still like a fist tightened around her heart at the confirmation. He was a great warrior, one of the finest in Ithelia, but even someone as mighty as he was could be brought down by numbers.\n\n\"Be honest with me, Captain. Will we hold?\"\n\nHer Queensguard shifted in shock and the Captain hesitated before lowering his gaze and shaking his head. \"No, my Queen. It's a miracle we haven't had any breakthroughs already. Our garrison just isn't large enough to repel this kind of attack.\"\n\n\"I see.\" She turned to her most trusted personal guard. \"Amelia.\"\n\n\"Yes, Your Highness.\"\n\n\"You will get my daughter and get her out. These cats mean to destroy us and I will not let them have Kori.\"\n\nThere was reluctance in Amelia's gaze before she nodded and brought her arm up in a salute. \"Marnol, Surie, with me. We'll get the Princess out, Your Highness. We have allies in Susururu that will shelter us.\"\n\n\"Thank you, Amelia. All of you. May the Light of Kari watch over you.\"\n\nIt was only minutes after half her Queensguard had left the throne room before assassins broke through the lines. The Captain and her guards fought to keep them away but it was her magic that was the true threat. Elemental blasts flew from her hands like rain. Fire, ice, lightning, earth, wind&even holy and dark magic cut down catfolk soldiers. It was the very nature of the world fighting against their invasion, buying time for Amelia to get out with Kori. To get to safety.\n\n\"The annexation of Ithelia and the rabbitfolk will be the source of the greatest breakthroughs in magical understanding in the last five hundred years. It's still a shame that we had to wipe out the Itia family, but any survivors would have been a rallying point for rebellion. We're lucky that the young King and Queen hadn't yet produced an heir.\" - General Purin Haearn in a letter back to Northi about the successful campaign against the rabbitfolk of Ithelia","guide":"The elementalist, a very offensive focus based class with the added options of choosing what element to use in any combat using Elemental Convergence.\n\nMagic Blast II is just a superior version to the first one having access to 120ft spell is nothing to scoff at, it can also be figure out elemental weaknesses by frequently swapping between elements before using your more dangerous abilities.\n\nElemental Bolt is your go to spell for elementalists, hosting several debuffs to send at the enemies using the right element for the right target whether it's burning or slowing them, sundering them for your stronger melee attackers to take advantage for it, using the right element at the right time will prove fruitful.\n\nWhile Bolt is your go to now Elemental Burst is the most scary of the abilities being that you can at any point increase the damage your spells cause for 1RP cost makes elementalist a powerhouse if no enemies are making effort to focus them as you will quickly whittle them down if they choose to take your attacks freely but do remember that every Elemental Burst is 1 less RP for your defenses.\n\nThe Secret Art, Surge of Elements can be used against anyone you'd fancy as it is a raw amount of attacks coming towards them, if you plan to remove their RP fast or simply finding a gassed target to unleash the full wrath of an elementalist barrage of spells on them, and for the cheap price of 1 mana you can overcharge it to give yourself two additional elements to give yourself nine light attacks to barrage someone. A gassed Target fears this secret art or finding a target not willing to lose a ton of health or rp early in a combat will also prove great.\n\nBy Buntaoo.","keyAbility":"Elemental Convergence","abilities":["Magic Blast II","Elemental Bolt","Elemental Burst","Secret Art: Surge of Elements"]},{"id":"eremancer","name":"Eremancer","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Any class mastered or Dark Mastery.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason or Cunning.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power or Toughness","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Religion, Magic, History, Appraise, Deception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Wisps of dark smoke seeped from the wound in the human's chest as the man slowly collapsed to the ground. The alley was suffocatingly silent, the sounds of nightlife muted by an unseasonable blanket of fog. Golan watched with a twist in his stomach as the human coughed weakly, blood dribbling from his lips.\n\n\"This pain is nothing compared to what they've done to me.\"\n\nHe grit his teeth and touched the spot on his head where his second horn should have been, long ago broken off, the phantom pain fading. Humans had done that to him. He didn't like hurting people, it made him sick to his stomach.\n\n\"But they never learn. I have to stop them.\"\n\n\"Demon--\"\n\nA flare of hatred rushed through him as he stared down at the human. It turned cold as he channeled that rage, dark miasma gathering in his hand like freezing night. Slowly, he pressed his hand into the man's throat, cutting off the scream that nearly ripped through the night, the dark energy suffocating and tearing. He watched as the man choked on nothing but darkness and blood until his eyes faded and he slumped fully to the ground.\n\nIt was sinful, what he was doing. Golan's mother would be horrified with him. She'd had such high hopes, high beliefs. Named him after some famous general, went to the Church of Light every week even though they all but spat on her. She'd tell him over and over that their ancient rebellion had been a mistake, had been demon-kind's greatest sin. That they just needed to trust in Kari and Her Providence. But that didn't keep her, his family, his friends safe. So he'd sin and sin and sin. For them. And in the quiet times, the dark moments, it was as if he could hear approval.\n\n\"I'm the only one who loves your sin.\"\n\nWith a grimace, he poured dark magic at the corpse, scouring it from existence. Only a stain on the paving stones would mark it and that evidence would be gone with the next rain.","guide":"-","keyAbility":"Stygian Comprehension","abilities":["Malevolent Phantasm","Energy Drain","Schadenfreude","Secret Art: Spirit Stigma"]},{"id":"evil-eye","name":"Evil Eye","tier":2,"role1":"Controller","role2":"Striker","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any class mastered. Must have at least 1 mystic eye slot open.","heart":"You gain +1 to Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain 5 skill points to spend on Perception. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"There was a loud banging on the door. The spiderfolk sitting at the table inside the little house placed her pen on the table with a sigh. She made her way to the door and opened it, being greeted to the sight of several dozen people standing outside her place brandishing torches and makeshift weapons.\n\n\"Monster! Murderer! You'll pay for what you did!\"\n\nCame the cries from the crowd of villagers, emboldened by the presence of a small group of better armed and armored people in front. \"You can't hide your crimes any longer, Dulcinea. Come with us, and we'll ensure you get a fair trial.\" Said the young man in front with a confident smile, clearly the leader of the small adventurer group.\n\nThe spider woman looked over the assembled group of people with annoyance rather than fear. She blinked once and one of her eight eyes began to glow in an eerie golden glow.\n\nAll in her gaze began to feel a sense of dread creeping over them, as if they suddenly realized they were trying to mess with someone far beyond their powers. A person turned around to run, and more began to follow.\n\nThey were too late.\n\nDulcinea blinked once more and two more of her eyes began to glow. The people felt their energy being sapped from them. Worse, they felt their very soul was being attacked by some dark magic. The screaming started.\n\nThe leader, now having realized what was happening, drew his sword and prepared to charge at the spider woman. He only made it a single step before his companions watched him slump to the floor, his sword falling from his grip. Beyond the body of their friend stood Dulcinea, with one of her main eyes now glowing a bright blue.\n\nTwo of the companions ran, fleeing into the sea of corpses from the villagers that lay there without any visible wounds. They made it further, but not far enough as they left the acolyte of Kari the only one alive of the group. She stood there, frozen in fear, as the spider approached her prey.\n\n\"Look into my eyes, it's the last thing you'll ever see.\"","guide":"Soon","keyAbility":"Evil Eye","abilities":["Cursed Evil Eye","Evil Eye of Lethargy","Evil Eye of Fear","Evil Eye of Death"]},{"id":"exalted-blade","name":"Exalted Blade","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Sword Paladin mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on any non crafting or gathering skill. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"\"...and like the Sun rising at the Dawn, Saint Rebekah held aloft her golden blade in defiance of the King of Fiends. To this day, no one knows the details of the final moments of the Battle of Fort Ende, but the fiend army never crossed the border, destroyed in place by the holy might of Kari.\" - The Final Stand of Saint Rebekah; Holy Record of the Church of Kari\n\n\"Fort Dinaich, or Fort Ende as the Westrians call it, located north of Eisenstadt along the border of the Astra Line, has been rebuilt countless times throughout history. But only once was it completely destroyed; in the creatively named Battle of Fort Dinaich. Historical records differ in details but there were luckily a plethora of eyewitness accounts for nearly the entire battle and it is one of the most studied in relation to massed fiend attacks. It was undoubtable that Saint Rebekah was key to the final defense of the Fort and for the escape of so many survivors but any accounts of her defeating the Principality King of Fiends in single combat are unconfirmed at best and mythological at worst.\" - Analysing the Battle of Fort Dinaich by Alejandro Ar Murin\n\n--\n\n\"Hold them!\" Rebekah shouted, her voice raw from overuse. She ducked away from the sweeping attacks of a multi-armed Exousia before bringing her sword up to bash aside its attacks. It staggered and that was all the time she needed to slash down, sword gleaming with holy magic, severing what counted as a head for the fiend. It collapsed and began dissolving into wisps of Astra but she didn't take a moment to rest. Holy light flared along her body and down her arms as she swung her sword in a horizontal arc, releasing the built up energy in a scything ray into the advancing Kratos and Exousia. That bought her the time to take stock of the battle for a brief, critical moment.\n\nFort Ende was burning, the walls were breached, and she could just make out the distant figures of wounded being evacuated south. But more importantly, her left flank was buckling under a focused Exousia attack.\n\n\"CORIN! Hit the left flank now! Now! NOW!\"\n\nThe speck that was Corin in the sky eviscerated the flying fiends harrying her with a wash of magical bullets. The air was still thick with fiends but she had enough space to begin gathering magic in earnest, magical arrays splaying out around her. Blue light began to wash out every color across the battlefield and the world seemed to hold its breath. Then a roar, so powerful that it shook the ground beneath her feet, and a flare of nearly blinding blue light. When Rebekah finally blinked away the spots in her eyes, the push on the left had been replaced by a seething cloud of smoke and dust.\n\n--\n\n\"The attrition of a battle like this, against this many fiends, is inevitable. Even for Skybound or Gem ranked warriors. Even with feats of prowess that seemed more out of myths from the Divine War than something that happened nearly two hundred years ago. It's almost hard to believe people like Corin Airheart or Malkor the Mountain Crusher could ever fall but that is just the reality of engaging a Principality. And while the truth of the account of the one survivor of Saint Rebekah's party is oft debated, the truth of the matter is that whatever did happen at the end of the battle, it was visible for miles and no fiends survived it to pursue the survivors\" - The Saint's Party by Helga von Lurgen\n\n--\n\nCorin was down. She had cleared the skies, swept aside dozens of Exousia. And the Principality had swatted her from the air like an annoying insect. Malkor was down, buried somewhere under a pile of fiends that was so large that their dissolving mists had still yet to clear. At least Amelia had made it out, her healing working miracles even if her prayers went to that heretical tree goddess. She would make sure the survivors made it home.\n\nRebekah gingerly lowered herself down to one knee, sword point digging into the blood soaked ground to keep her balance. With the braying of fiends too fearful to come near her echoing around her, she prayed. The rote prayers that she'd scoffed at as an initiate gave her comfort&like the soothing embrace of a mother. And for a brief, eternal moment, it was like she was floating amidst the heavens, golden sunlight beckoning her to paradise.\n\nAn earth shuddering stomp snapped her back to reality, to the smoke clogged air and the King of Fiends staring down at her. But even with her serene focus shattered, she continued to pray.\n\n\"You fought well,\" it said in a soothing, deep voice. \"Surrender to me and become my Queen.\"\n\nRebekah stood and pulled her sword from the mud.\n\n\"...and I shall hold my blade on high to bask in Your radiance,\" she said as she raised her sword, golden light flickering along the blade. The Principality took a massive step forward to stop her.\n\n\"Grant me Your Guidance to see through falsehoods and banish the corruption,\" she continued, her voice rising. Her left hand rose to join her right on the grip of her sword and she set her feet in a steady stance.\n\n\"You FOOL! You throw away all I can offer you for your witch of a goddess?!\"\n\nThe King of Fiends was moments away from reaching her, the miasmatic axe in his hands raised to swing.\n\n\"And I shall render Your DIVINE JUDGEMENT!\"\n\nRebekah's sword fell and the world turned golden.","guide":"-","keyAbility":"Execute the Heretic","abilities":["Undying Justice","Divine Storm","Crusader's Advance","Secret Art: Divine Judgement"]},{"id":"exalted-shield","name":"Exalted Shield","tier":3,"role1":"Defender","role2":"Support","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Shield Paladin mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on any non crafting or gathering skill. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Susana stood upon the parapet, facing the storm choked chaotic mess that was the Astra Line. Miasma had been gathering along the border all day, twisting and warping and occasionally revealing a glimpse of a grotesque fiend. Attacks on Fort Ende were not uncommon, the fiends tested their defences regularly. But for the sickening miasma to concentrate so heavily required an unheard of gathering of fiends. An unnatural gathering.\n\n\"Unnatural,\" she scoffed to herself. As if fiends could be anything but unnatural. Fiends would take any opportunity to attack the peoples of Lyr but they were fickle abominations. Greedy. Prideful. It took great power to bind them together for a single purpose. A walking calamity. A Principality. Rebekah and her party had left earlier that week on a hunt for what she had described as a \"King of Fiends\" in an effort to prevent such a gathering of evil.\n\n\"I'm leaving Ende in your care, Susana. If the worst comes, you must hold them. Bleed them. If this abomination makes it past us, the northlands will burn before it can be stopped.\"\n\nSeeing the spreading miasma crawling slowly toward the walls of Fort Ende, Susana wondered if her friend had failed or was simply too late. She shook that thought away, basking in the golden light of the sun falling on her shoulders. It wouldn't be long until the storm clouds spread and cast them all in gloom, so she would take the comfort of Kari's Light while she could.\n\n\"High Priestess? The division commanders are assembled.\"\n\nSusana took a fortifying breath and cast out her worries in a short prayer. \"Your Radiance guides my hand as a Bulwark for all. Enai.\"\n\n\"Enai,\" the courier said quietly.\n\n--\n\n\"Fort Ende withstood the King of Fiends and his army for six days. Six times, the Principality was turned back by the walls and by the High Priestess of the Bulwark, Lady Susana. The Divine Providence of Kari filled the air around her, held her aloft in defiance of the King of Fiends, and uplifted the defenders of Fort Ende. With her holy defenses they were able to reap righteous retribution of the fiends ranks. To all at Fort Ende, it was as if a miracle had descended from the heavens.\n\nAnd on the seventh day, that miracle fell. Some say it was exhaustion, some a foul trick by the Principality, and yet others claimed treachery. But when Lady Susana fell, the walls of Fort Ende fell with her. But the walls had held long enough. For Saint Rebekah, her return from glorious crusade was greeted by bearing witness to the fall of a dear friend. But that only fueled her fury as she brought an end to the King of Fiends and his army.\" - The Lost of Ende, an Anthology of Testimony by Urik Fispline","guide":"-","keyAbility":"Shield the Fallen","abilities":["Undying Justice","Aura of Resistance","Holy Declaration","Secret Art: Divine Shield"]},{"id":"excavator","name":"Excavator","tier":2,"role1":"Gatherer","role2":"Striker","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Miner mastered","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Mining.","description":"From a collection of well preserved and maintained Recorder Orbs in the mining town of Caernelli, located at the base of the Tuagledd Mountains and south east of Mt. Merlin itself.\n\nAn image wavered to life, revealing a pair of rugged boots scuffing into the ground. Sound, slightly distorted, played of the dirt crunching and loud cloth rustling before the image swung wildly in a blur. When it steadied, the freckled face of a young ratfolk girl smiled and a hand came up to ruffle her windblown hair into some semblance of order.\n\n\"Oh, it's working now! Uh&uh&right! Hi! I'm Dina Awbrey, senior apprentice to Master Oric Carew of the Caernelli Mining Institute.\" The view suddenly panned to show a sweeping image of a distant town and quarry nestled against the base of the mountains. By the angle, Dina was hundreds of feet up the mountain above the town. A gloved hand came into view, pointing at one of the distant buildings. \"Right down there.\"\n\nThe image panned again with the sound of rustling cloth and the slight creak of well worn leather. By the time the view settled, Dina was making final adjustments of the straps of a bulky pack. A compact shovel, a pickaxe, spare boots, some metal contraptions, and a significant amount of rope were all easily visible. She clapped her hands together and gave the recorder orb a thumbs up.\n\n\"Ready to go! I'll prove to old dog Carew that there's more to this mountain than the stone and iron in the quarry!\" She pointed dramatically up at the mountain peaks just as the orb gave an alarming warble. \"Oops, time's u--\" The recording cut off suddenly.\n\nSeveral following recordings chronicled Dina's journey up the mountain and some of her&interesting attempts at cooking while camping. The next interesting recording was much more harrowing.\n\n\"Woooah! O-ooooh! Uh--okay! I'm OKAY!\" Wind hissed across the sheer cliff face and snapped at loose clothing. The image wobbled for a moment before it stabilized, showing an impossible angle of Dina clinging to the cliff with both hands and her boots sporting attached climbing cleats. She was holding the recorder orb with her tail. Rope dangled beneath her down a hundred foot drop, secured in place by the occasional piton.\n\n\"Almost fell there!\" Dina shouted over the wind with a laugh. \"UH&I'm about halfway up this cliff now and my boots are working GREAT! Really gonna need to thank Patrick for them. And these new pitons! They don't budge at all!\" She demonstrated by leaning back and tugging aggressively at the rope securing her to the cliff face.\n\n\"Anyway! Right up there is the cave I spotted yesterday. The one with that glint.\" Still leaning out, Dina pointed above her and stretched her tail out for a better angle. The very faintest impression of a shadowed outcropping could be seen. \"I should be up there in time for lunch--\" A gust of wind swung Dina and she scrambled for a good hold on the cliff. \"If this wind doesn't knock me down first!\" The orb's view swung and then suddenly darkened with a cacophony of rustling before the recording stopped.\n\nThe next recording began with Dina grinning and tapping a vein of metal glistening in the sunlight. \"I knew it. Orichalcum, it has to be.\" There was a snap and hum of an artifice device activating and a bright light shone down into the cave. More lines of mineral gleamed. The light shifted sharply as Dina moved the source into view. It was a leather cap with what looked like the barest bones of a Northi Lantern attached to it. She tapped the top and the dull sound of metal covered in leather echoed.\n\n\"Patrick called this a \u0018hard hat'. He's thinking of trying to get all the miners to wear them, but it's not really working out. He did manage to fit a lantern on it though, kinda heavy, but being able to see with hands and tail free is great! Anyway, I'm gonna get a couple samples of this near the entrance and see what else I can find deeper in!\" The image cut off.\n\nThere were no further recordings but there was a collection of custom made tools and various samples displayed. A folding shovel, a reinforced pickaxe, the climbing spike attachments for her boots, the self expanding pitons, and the hard hat with the mounted lamp. Refined versions of them could be purchased at the Institute to support more Excavator activity in the mountains, led and taught by Master Dina Awbrey.","guide":"The excavator is the continuation of miner and is also a striker role in combat. Mountain Slayer has a limited use case, only being usable against shielded targets, but becomes very powerful when you get to use it doing almost Heavy attack level damage with full pierce on it.\n\nCave Raider is another ability with situational use, but it can be useful in caves where you can now easily move around.\n\nFor gathering, Focused Detonation is great against both node points and lucky points. Either way you use it, Lucky Strike can help you top off afterwards. Take it easy is not an ability you want to use against every node, but if you're doing easier nodes that you can clear even with limited dice, take it easy is a great way to get some additional materials.","keyAbility":"Ore Hunter","abilities":["Focused Detonation","Mountain Slayer","Cave Raider","Take it easy"]},{"id":"executor","name":"Executor","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any mastered class + Any points in Acolyte.","heart":"You gain +1 to Cunning or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Power or Focus.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Roguecraft, Religion, Magic, History, Insight, Stealth, Perception or Expert Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Agents of the Church's justice.","guide":"Executors are good against mages. Holy Orders gives them sticking power to a single target that is almost impossible to escape from. Because they can only attack a single target, it does mean they cannot threaten multiple backline threats by themselves. Sometimes, it may be worth foregoing the holy orders until later.\n\nDeus Vult can only be used against people who have Holy Orders on them. It allos the executor to trade an RP for an offensive boost, making for an attack that is hard to dodge. It also gains the shieldbreaker property, which can heavily punish mages.\n\nIt is best used in combination with Ave Maria. It has a higher AP cost, so missing it is particularly bad which deus vult helps prevent. It can be worth tossing out against a target that has no RP left, especially if they have higher guard. It also does Holy damage, which may be relevant against some enemies.\n\nEagle Hunt is what Executors use to get in range of their targets. They can leap over the frontline and land in the back. It may also be used as an escape tool or it can be seen as a cheap movement option if you are already planning to use Silentium, which gets a 1 AP discount when used during Eagle Hunt. Silentium is primarily used against mages, against who disabling their concentration can be devastating. It also disables their spells until they remove it, which can be seen as effectively lowering their RP or AP for the next turn. Use with Deus Vult when you absolutely need to cancel an ongoing spell they are concentrating on.","keyAbility":"Holy Orders","abilities":["Silentium","Eagle Hunt","Deus Vult","Ave María"]},{"id":"faerie-light-eyes","name":"Faerie Light Eyes","tier":2,"role1":"Controller","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Must have the \"Mystic Eyes of Faerie Light\" breakthrough. Must have at least 1 mystic eye slot open.","heart":"You gain +1 to Awareness or Cunning.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Insight, Stealth or Perception. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The Fae have natural abilities to twist reality into wild illusions. All Fae have their eyes naturally linked to their Spirit Circuits, allowing them to peer through natural veils that cause other beings to become lost in deep forests. A few Fae have trained these connections further, causing them to unleash reality-warping abilities that affect the minds of their opponents. Faerie Light Eyes also increases kinetic perception, allowing the user to more easily dodge attacks from enemies.","guide":"Users are of the Faerie Light eyes are masters of illusion and deadly against those without an heroic aura. Hold Person instantly reduces their AP and RP to 0, at the cost of one of your own RP. Because it's an RP ability, it can be used as reaction to what a grunt is doing. Save it for one that is doing something important, such as tossing a flask or trying to escape and alert others. There's not much reason to use this on your own turn, unless you want to follow it up with Empty.\n\nEmpty renders a person under the effects of Hold Person insane, which may not always be a desirable outcome. Even disregarding interrogations, an insane person could run further into a dungeon and alert others. Even when not used for this purpose, Empty can be a powerful ability. Many monsters do not have many abilities and losing a core ability permanently for the rest of the fight can be crippling.\n\nIf you manage to seal away a powerful ability, you can use it yourself with Golden Illusion. Copying the ability is free, so there is little reason not to do it. You can simply replace it if you get a better ability later in the fight. How to use the golden illusion the best is hard to say, it all depends on what you copy after all.\n\nTime Dilation is an improved dodge. The mana cost is a bit steep, but you can use it after you see the roll and thus perfectly determine how much mana you need to use to dodge the attack.","keyAbility":"Faerie Light Eyes","abilities":["Faerie Light Eyes: Hold Person","Faerie Light Eyes: Time Dilation","Faerie Light Eyes:  Empty","Faerie Light Eyes: Golden Illusion"]},{"id":"farmer","name":"Farmer","tier":1,"role1":"Artisan","role2":"Controller","difficulty":2,"requirements":"None","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Farming. You also gain 5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Survival, Animal Husbandry or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"\"Bennachd na Yggdrasil ar talah se.\" The Blessing of Yggdrasil upon this land. The traditional words spoken over a Farmer's field before any work is done for the season. Passed down through the generations, most modern Farmers have no knowledge of its origin or the significance it holds in prayer to an old god. Attempts by the Church of Light to coin their own blessing by Kari has had mixed results throughout history, with the traditional appeal seeming to always be measurably more effective. The prayer was ultimately, and grudgingly, accepted by the Church but there were still occasional movements and studies made to replace it with something \"more holy\".\n\nFrom the expansive wheat fields of Dacquoise to the carefully tended orchards of Sylvan, the ancient words of blessing were spoken and passed down from father to son, mother to daughter, master to apprentice. While every farmer may know the words, may know the varying rituals, it was the head Farmer of the village that would lead each blessing. Often thought of as the wizened elder (to the annoyance of those much younger that have learned the ways of the blessing), it was common for the head Farmer to bless a towns' fields in a rotation. While it wasn't as glamorous as becoming a mage or a knight or an adventurer, there was always a steady apprenticeship across Lyr, of families and communities teaching and training the next generation.\n\nTo the Farmer, the connection to the land was a palpable thing, the energy flowing from them and into them in equal measure. While this gave Farmers a tendency to plant roots of their own and remain in one place, some took their brief connection to the natural world as a call. To discover and see as much of the world they could connect to as possible. But most importantly of all, no farmer or Farmer would ever forget the benediction of the harvest: \"Gabthasinn a toirt Yggdrasil don tiodlac seo.\" We thank Yggdrasil for this gift.","guide":"The farmer is a crafting class that functions as a controller when in combat.\n\nScarecrow's Gaze is your most important tool in fights against groups of enemies. The most common use for this will be to stand together with your backline, then use it to prevent enemies from easily targeting your vulnerable targets in the back. You could also go on the offensive yourself and use it to ensure that you or an ally can't be threatened while going for an enemy spellcaster. The core of this ability is to ensure the enemies have little choice but to attack your tank.\n\nPlow the fields is a cheap AoE attack that also creates difficult terrain for 1 turn. Can be used pre-emptively to make an enemies advance more difficult.\n\nWither the stalk is a strong debuff against a single enemy. Denying the use of Power will remove a lot of damage from an attack and this is especially powerful against less intelligent enemies with set patterns that use their strong attacks at the start of their turn.\n\nOn the crafting side, farmers are IP intensive compared to other crafters. While they can make a lot of goods (and profit), you are forcing yourself to commit to 2 IP to get any benefit out of it. Pull the weeds should be seen as an emergency tool to get a sudden 5 crafting points at the cost of losing some profit. If you're only a few points off a big upgrade such as infuse Qi, then it's probably worth using.","keyAbility":"Farming Basics","abilities":["Plow the fields","Wither the Stalk","Pull the weeds","Scarecrow's Gaze"]},{"id":"fencer","name":"Fencer","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Defender","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness, Cunning or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 Focus.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Deception, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"A nimble fighter that likes to duel.","guide":"The fencer is a highly mobile 1v1 specialist. Their fancy footwork allows them to reposition on the battlefield and away from other attackers, keeping them focused on their target.\n\nParry is their most important ability. It costs 1 mana, but the RP cost is easily refunded if you use it against light attacks or against someone weaker than you. Because it effectively is a damage check with your focus instead of power, you should be careful in using it against high power enemies, especially if they use a heavy weapon. A heavy attack from those is likely to break through your parry and a dodge might be the better option.\n\nRiposte is the follow up to a parry. It costs 1 RP, so it does eat into your defenses but it is an otherwise free Heavy attack. Just keep your RP in mind before using it.\n\nLunge helps fencer on fighting multiple enemies a bit. If an enemy is barely out of range, you can use your Lunge for extra range than fancy footwork to get in range. It can also be useful against rogueish characters who think they are safe after an evasive maneuver. Simply activate lunge and hit them from 10ft away.\n\nPrecise Thrust is an attack that's best used against heavily armored targets. Dodging is usually the preferred answer to a Heavy attack, so this may not see much use except against the most armored of enemies.\n\nFAQ:\n\nQ: Does Parry still apply guard after?\nA: No, Parry is treated as a Block, so it does not add guard afterwards. It would also block crits, and does not work against Full Pierce attacks.","keyAbility":"Fancy Footwork","abilities":["Parry","Lunge","Riposte","Precise Thrust"]},{"id":"fighter","name":"Fighter","tier":1,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Defender","difficulty":2,"requirements":"None.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Power, Focus, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Riding, Intimidation, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Fighters come from many backgrounds. They can be adventurers, soldiers or even just travelers who've decided to master the arts of combat. They wield weapons with expert skill, making them the backbone of any adventuring party.\n\nWhat sets them apart from ordinary soldiers is their ability to perceive and control mana within their bodies. This keen understanding gives them an edge—allowing them to move at high speeds and deliver powerful blows. Fighters are a force to be reckoned with on the battlefield and welcome allies.","guide":"Fighters are versatile front liners that are able to defend against attacks effectively while also exerting pressure on the enemy. A good fighter is expected to draw the enemy to them and to create space for the rest of their allies to unleash their full potential.\n\nCharge can be used to gain position in a fight without sacrificing attack. When moving in in the first round of a combat, you normally have to sacrifice attacks for the movement. Charge helps mitigate this, allowing the fighter to take point and still do damage.\n\nSlam is only a small knockback, but the AP cost of the attack is low and it has no other cost. It can be used to create space for an ally to safely escape, but a fighter can also use it at the end of their attack sequence. This way the target will need to spend 1 AP on movement again to get in range, lowering their attacks.\n\nDefensive Flexibility gives high RP economy, but it requires a bit of thinking ahead. It has to be used after you take one of the two basic reactions, and youll have to predict what your opponent will do next or force them to do suboptimal attacks. In long fights, consider what attacks you can safely tank without the use of RP to allow for more defensive flexibility uses in the future. Every RP you can spend that leads into defensive flexibility is effectively doubled.\n\nPower Strike is an attack that can deal a lot of damage, but is not very mana-efficient. It should almost always only be used against a target with no RP left. Fighters themselves don't have anything else that uses mana, so it's worth using for new characters. As you unlock more classes and get other abilities that use mana, Power Strike will probably not see much use anymore.","keyAbility":"Fighter's Journey","abilities":["Charge","Power Strike","Slam","Defensive Flexibility"]},{"id":"five-harmonies-style","name":"Five Harmonies Style","tier":2,"role1":"Healer","role2":"Striker","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Cultivator or Martial Artist mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Reason or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Perception, Insight, Medicine, Negotiation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The first Suryan monastery was built on the highest mountaintops in Kirara, the ones closest to the sun. There the monks sought its guidance and found enlightenment through the 5 core tenets that they called the harmonies.\n\nThe Harmony of Form teaches that the body is a vessel of light. The body must remain clear and disciplined for radiance to pass through it. Through mastery of the body, the first harmony is achieved. Perfect form, movement without wasted motions.\n\nThe Harmony of Intention transforms will into compassion. True strength is not to destroy, but the choice to preserve. It is the power to channel your inner radiance into healing energy to aid those in need around you.\n\nThe Harmony of Sensation awakens sensation through contact. Every touch becomes a dialogue in the world. Once a person feels without judgement, they experience the world honestly and begin to awaken to truth.\n\nThe Harmony of Perception refines this awareness into clarity. Once mastered, this perception blooms into pure intuition and a fighter is able to extend their influence on the world.\n\nThe final teaching is the Harmony of Consciousness. It only can be understood once the other harmonies become one. It is the dissolution of separation. The body, thought, senses and motions all become a single blooming sun of radiance. A single moment of temporary enlightenment.\n\nWhile the teachings were philosophical in nature at the start, masters of the Five Harmonies have converted these teachings into a formidable fighting style.\n\n\"Move with clarity, Choose without hesitation, Feel without fear, See without illusion, Become without self.\"","guide":"The 5 harmonies style is a healing class with low range and mobility on their heals, but high versatility in how they use them.\n\nThe core part of the class is the Luminous Form Stance. It is required to use all the other abilities in the class and gives you extra range to help with the fact that you can't willingly move. Leaving the stance means you lose all stacks, so consider very carefully if you have to leave it or not. The stance does not end if you make ranged attacks, so that may be a better option and you can wait for your allies to move to you for healing. You also only build stacks with abilities, so abilities like Leg Sweep should be considered for stack building.\n\nPure Intentions is your primary healing ability. It has relatively short range, but it is low AP cost and very versatile in how much you heal. If an ally needs only a small amount of healing you could spend only 1 or 2 stacks, while for an ally that is near death you could choose t o spend all 5 stacks for a big burst heal.\n\nFirst Sensation is a simple ability that helps you stack faster. Noteworthy is that the first stack it gives is on hit, not on damage. It also has a combo effect, so stance into first sensation is a good way to instantly gain some stacks.\n\nFlowing Perception is your one mobility tool that lets you move while remaining in stance. Useful for both repositioning to heal and for moving around the fight.\n\nBlooming Consciousness is your secret art. It heals for a large amount in an aoe around you being both relatively mana efficient for the healing done and not costing too much AP for an AoE heal. It's only weakness is its limited range combined with the unmoving nature of your stance and relying on getting max stacks. If your team is grouped up, you can Flowing Perception to someone for a stack and positioning before you use it.","keyAbility":"Five Harmonies","abilities":["Mantra: Pure Intentions","Mudra: First Sensation","Mantra: Flowing Perception","Dharani: Blooming Conciousness"]},{"id":"flame-sentinel","name":"Flame Sentinel","tier":2,"role1":"Support","role2":"Controller","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Mage mastered or Fire mastery.","heart":"You gain +1 Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 Power or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"A supportive fire magic user that can buff their allies and zone away enemies.","guide":"Flame Sentinels support their allies primarily through offense. Flame Weapon grants a small power boost to a weapon of an ally and lets them deal fire damage, which may be important against some enemies. Controlled Blaze will not prevent your allies from setting things on fire, so be careful when giving it out when flameable material is around.\n\nFlame Shield allows you to do damage after an ally takes damage. It costs 1 RP, but its fully unavoidable and full pierce damage. If you hang out in the back and don't have much use for your RP, this can be an excellent way to spend it.\n\nFlame Infusion is a situational ability. Against certain enemies it's extremely powerful and against others, its a detriment.\n\nFlame Wall is a strong zoning tool, able to cut off a large portion of a fight. You can also use it as a damage tool, dropping it right on top of enemies to force them to use an RP. If they choose not to do so, or if they have no more RP to spent, then it is effectively a Sure Hit attack once their turn starts.","keyAbility":"Controlled Blaze","abilities":["Flame Infusion","Flame Shield","Flame Weapon","Flame Wall"]},{"id":"flash-star-blade-style-","name":"Flash Star Blade Style","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Any class mastered. Proficiency in one of light swords, longsword, katana or dueling weapon.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Athletics, Intimidation, Magic, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"A blade style originating from Raijin swordmasters. A notable practicioner of Flash Star Blade Style is Rin Tatsugami of Madeline.","guide":"The Flash Star Style is a sword style originating from the Raijin that requires precise positioning. Photon Line moves you exactly 25ft, not up to 25ft. This can make it difficult to use against a single target, since you'll often dash past the target and be unable to attack them without moving. Using it as a retreating option is a valid choice as you force the enemy to move to attack you.\n\nIf you do manage to line up the perfect Photon Line on the offense, you can combo it into Thunderbolt Slash. Thunderbolt Slash is 3 light attacks for the cost of 2 AP. With its mana cost reduced by the combo effect, it lines up perfectly for a 4 AP turn that doesn't cost any mana.\n\nStarlight Crescent Reversal is a safe mana dump each turn, allowing for a cheap Light attack.\n\nThe Secret Art: Twin Nova Pursuit is an engagement and isolation tool. You are able to move a target 25ft or 50ft, depending on how they react, which can let you get a 1v1 when you remove an enemy from a melee brawl. It can also be used to engage and knock an enemy into your own allies, allowing them to pile on without having to move and most likely dragging that enemy out of range of any support abilities.","keyAbility":"Lightning Weapon","abilities":["Flash Star Style: Photon Line","Flash Star Style: Thunderbolt Slash","Flash Star Style: Starlight Crescent Reversal","Flash Star Style Secret Art: Twin Nova Pursuit"]},{"id":"flowing-wind-style","name":"Flowing Wind Style","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Utility","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Forager, Fighter, Rogue, Martial Artist, Cultivator or Adventurer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Perception, Insight, Medicine, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The Flowing Wind Style was founded by Yun Fei of the Azure Cloud Sect, a cultivator and the first leader of the sect. She taught that freedom without motion is illusion, and motion without freedom is merely compulsion. To cultivate the wind is to accept that remaining unchanged is itself a form of confinement. These teachings shape the core beliefs behind the style and likewise the style encourages its students to accept those tenets.\n\nMotion is continuity. A flowing thing may be slowed, turned aside or dispersed but it does not stop unless forced. Students are taught that every movement is an act of cultivation. To move is to remain free.\n\nFreedom is choice and choice is power. Without the strength to resist being forced into an action, a person can never be truly free. Those that follow the Flowing Wind Style seek strength for that reason, to remain free until the very end.","guide":"The Flowing Wind Style is a damage dealing class with some focus on mobility.\n\nCloudstep is your initial ability and it lets you move a short distance without provoking. While the distance is very short at the start, it's good for repositioning in melee and it gets buffed when combined with the Plume-Treading Art passive, which boosts your movement speed. When you get enough extra movement, the halved movement speed from Cloudstep matters less. It also lets you walk on air to reach flying targets without needing to fly yourself.\n\nAll this movement lets you build up stacks you can then proc with Flowing Wind Strike, which can deal up to +10 extra damage based off your stacks.\n\nYou can also use your stacks to gain a bonus to your Dodge with Driftwind Evasion, which may let you avoid an attack you couldn't normally dodge at the cost of giving up damage.\n\nYour Secret Art: Vanishing Thousand Steps lets you move freely across the battlefield for 1 turn. It can be great for both starting a fight by instantly reaching their backline or for catching runners towards the end of a fight.","keyAbility":"Cloudstep","abilities":["Plume-Treading Art","Flowing Wind Strike","Driftwind Evasion","Secret Art: Vanishing Thousand Steps"]},{"id":"forager","name":"Forager","tier":1,"role1":"Gatherer","role2":"Utility","difficulty":2,"requirements":"None","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Reason or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Toughness or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Foraging. You also gain 5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Medicine, Survival or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"From the lively activity of the deep forest to the serene stillness of the snowy tundra, a Forager was most at home wandering places no one has traveled through in decades (if ever). To take only what was needed, to preserve the beauty of what was; that was the motto of many Foragers. An ideal that caused natural tension between Foragers and Farmers but even the most steadfast Forager would admit that their ways wouldn’t be able to support the growing population of Lyr.\n\nA true Forager could be recognized by their unique gathering tool: giant scissors. Named so due to their general construction of two handles with paired blades connected to a pivot point, the giant scissors were reinforced survival multi-tools. Designed for the specific needs of each Forager, the scissors often had blades large enough to cut a tree in half (or a man) and most came with sharpened tips that could be used like a spear when the tool was closed. Serrated or sharpened outer edges could allow for sawing and chopping wood, while the handles would sometimes have hooks to aid in pulling things down into easy reach. A difficult tool to master just for harvesting, those Foragers that trained to fight with them were unpredictable dervishes that utilized their unconventional weapon’s quirks to their advantage.\n\nWith a deep connection to the natural world around them and experience born from time in the wilderness, Foragers were never truly in danger of running out of even the most basic of supplies. Be it food and water or torches, ropes, and even shelters, a Forager could often find or fashion some manner of natural replacement. With a sharp eye for details honed by spotting tiny gatherable herbs and mushrooms (and identifying their properties at a glance), their versatility in supplies, and even their strange combat style, any adventure or expedition would do well to consider bringing a Forager along.","guide":"The forager is a gatherer and utility class. Their primary use in combat is to use Lifebeat Sense to gather information on the HP status of enemies, as well as making them easier to be critically hit. This does cost mana, so be careful about overusing this.\n\nTheir second combat ability is vivisect, which is an instakill ability with severeal requirements to it. While it may look hard to use because of that, in practice you can get this off pretty reliably. Simply use Lifebeat Sense on a grunt you know is RP exhausted, and you can immediately Vivisect them after. The combo isn't cheap action or mana wise, but it cannot miss which is nice.\n\nFor gathering, you have Verdant Instinct and Divining Petalfall. These are best used together. An early Verdant Instinct can give you the information you need, then you can replace one with a 5 if needed which allows you to guarantee a Divining Petalfall for Lucky Points.","keyAbility":"Forager's Path","abilities":["Verdant Instinct","Lifebeat Sense","Divining Petalfall","Vivisect"]},{"id":"forgemaster","name":"Forgemaster","tier":2,"role1":"Artisan","role2":"Support","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Blacksmith mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness or Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Power, Focus or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Blacksmithing.","description":"Crafters who supply the world's weapons.","guide":"The forgemaster retains their crafting focus and is able to craft higher quality items. With Inspired Finish you can add a large boost to your craft at the very end. However, you can't do anything else after that so you might have to take a risk and apply the bonuses early, then hope you roll high enough.\n\nForged Knowledge II now work on the weapons of allies as well, though you still need to have made their weapon. it also maximizes all the damage dice, which can create a sizeable damage increase on a bad damage roll.\n\nSecret Art: Shatter is either a Sure Hit heavy attack that deals good damage, or if they block it you destroy their weapon. Powerful against enemies that uses weapons, but it won't have much use against non-humanoids.\n\nFAQ:\n\nQ: How does inspired finish interact with a Westrian Style tool?\nA: All 3 dice become a 5.","keyAbility":"Focused Weapons","abilities":["Inspired Finish","Forged Knowledge II","Expertise Study (Blacksmithing)","Secret Art: Shatter"]},{"id":"geomancer","name":"Geomancer","tier":2,"role1":"Controller","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Any class mastered or Earth mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"A magic user that focuses on manipulating the earth around them.","guide":"A Geomancer is a controller that uses shapes the battlefield to their benefit. Fissure is their main control spell that creates a large hole in the ground that enemies will have to get out of. This can be powerful when combined with other tools such as a Flame Oil Flask. People at the edges may step out of the fissure by spending an RP, but then you have the option of hitting them with a Seismic Shove.\n\nSeismic Shove is a unique forced movement ability in that it lets you push an enemy in any direction, instead of only backwards. If you hit an enemy with it, you can toss them into the Fissure they just avoided.\n\nMud Wall is another area control spell that you can use. You can spend AP on it to either build cover for yourself and your allies, or create a small patch of difficult terrain for the enemies. When used a reaction, you can use the cover creating part of it to turn a potential hit into a miss or use it to make an enemy be unable to reach your allies. You can also use it in combination with the Fissure ability to create a sudden wall for when an enemy attempts to jump out of the hole.\n\nSecret Art: Earthquake is a wide hitting spell that does low damage, but knocks enemies prone. Its main strength is the extremely long range on it and the bonus damage it does against magically created objects. The last part may not come up often, but it will be devastating when it does. Be aware that it will also destroy your own mud walls.\n\nFinally, Tremorsense is a simple spell that lets you temporarily become aware of creatures. Useful for spotting out potential assassins, but it can also let you do things like position a fissure through a wall.","keyAbility":"Tremorsense","abilities":["Mud Wall","Fissure","Seismic Shove","Secret Art: Earthquake"]},{"id":"geomaster","name":"Geomaster","tier":3,"role1":"Controller","role2":"Striker","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Geomancer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The caravan is stopped. The bridge over the ravine is gone, scrap and splinter of it remaining on either side of the more than one hundred twenty foot gap in the earth. Did it collapse from the weather or an earthquake? Or was it deliberately destroyed by Northi sappers, flaunting their new air superiority of Sorthen's logistical lines? It didn't matter, the bridge was gone and the evacuation toward Marlone was stopped dead in its tracks. Teyo Lu'Solana scowled at the gap, the earth shivering with each impatient tap of her foot.\n\nThe leaders of the caravan were arguing over alternative routes or taking the time to rebuild the bridge. They were assuming General Ar'Golan would be able to hold off the might of the combined Northi-Westria forces. That they had time for \"alternative routes\" or \"bridge building\". Teyo knew if they stayed here, they would be caught against this ravine and slaughtered. And she had been tasked by the General to get this caravan safely to Marlone.\n\n\"We're crossing,\" she declared loudly, interrupting the debate.\n\nOne of the men nervously looked at his compatriots and then reluctantly stepped forward. \"With all due respect, Lady Lu'Solana, the decision hasn't been made yet. We'll take your input into consideration as a vote for a bridge, but--\"\n\nTeyo scoffed and turned away, walking toward the edge of the ravine. \"No, we're crossing now. We've wasted enough time.\"\n\nShe ignored the indignant officials shouting at her as she plants her feet at the point where stone meets open air. Mana surged through her body, her blood singing, begging to release its shackles. She held that urge back and crossed her arms imperiously. Then, with a stomp of her foot, the earth heaved beneath her and she rode a bridge of earth across the ravine where it anchored solidly with the opposite wall as if it had always been.\n\nThe new stone bridge is twenty feet wide and gently arched for support. With a few twists of her feet and guidance from her hands, support pillars rose from the ravine floor to shore up the structure of the bridge and ensure it wouldn't buckle under the load. Finally, Teyo let a shuddering breath escape her lips but didn't let the exhaustion of shaping that much earth show. She just stands to the side of the new bridge as the awestruck evacuees trundle past her in wagons and carts. She only followed once the last of the refugees were across and with a violent twist of her feet, the entire bridge collapsed in a roar of falling stone.\n\nThey were safe, for now, and free to get to the ships that would take them to Marlone in the Bay.","guide":"Geomaster is primarily a controller class like the geomancer.\n\nEarthen Divide lets you split up the battlefield by just creating a massive wall. Powerful even outdoors to block ranged attacks, but especially if inside a cave or dungeon of some sort where there might not be a way to get around the wall and enemies have to force their way through.\n\nWall Ride is a simple mobility tool that lets you reposition after using Mud Wall or Earthen Divide. If you do a very long Earthen Divide, Wall Ride can let you move a super long distance for free.\n\nPillar of Earth is a manaless construction tool with the limit of having to place it below someone. Apart from creating cover, you can use it to either push up an enemy or an ally to get them out of attack of opportunity range.\n\nSpike Field is a nasty field hazard that will quickly chew through the HP of any grunt or even heroic enemy that simply goes through it at full speed. Be aware that it does affect allies as well.\n\nFinally, Second Tremor gives you increased controlling power against heroics. The only downside of it is that you may struggle to reliably activate it often without the support of allies, but it can be devastating if combined with reliable sources of prone such as leg sweep or wire sweep. As a pure geomancer, you'll most likely activate this purely off earthquake and fissures by yourself.","keyAbility":"Wall Ride","abilities":["Earthen Divide","Pillar of Earth","Spike Field","Second Tremor"]},{"id":"grandmaster","name":"Grandmaster","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":4,"requirements":"Any class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +1 to Deception, Linguistics, Magic, Appraise, History, Artifice, Insight, Art, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Isabelle Un Lavi scowled when her healed boots crunched against the wooden debris of the front door as she stepped outside. The big bruiser of a bandit lay sprawled where she'd tossed him through the door. Well, she hadn't. Stone grinding against wood announced the arrival of her very effective bodyguard. The intricately carved visage of a Westrian Knight came to a rest at the foot of the stairs, the sunlight gleaming off the white marble stone. She took the time to straighten her sleeves and brush her hair back with a flick of her wrist.\n\n\"Gentlemen, this is the single most foolish attempt at robbery I have ever seen,\" she said to the half dozen other bandits watching her warily (one was trying to wake up the big bruiser of a leader without much luck). \"And normally, I would be delighted to entertain you until the sheriff arrives to collect you.\" Her tail flicked in irritation. \"But unfortunately, you've gone and destroyed a perfectly wonderful door on my master's house and that I cannot abide. No, you'll just have to pay for that.\"\n\n\"This is stupid! It's just the maid and an enchanted statue!\" one of the bandits shouted, either the second in command or the loudmouth that wished he was. Whoever he was, he was inspiring enough to get them motivated to commit to the robbery again and the new leader was charging right at her, spear held like a lance.\n\n\"Pawn to E4,\" she said. The sound of stone grinding was all the warning the loudmouth had before a stone statue of a Westrian Squire grew from the ground in front of him. His spear chipped a chunk off the pawn's shoulder but the pawn buried its stone sword through the bandit's torso. It carelessly dropped the corpse and took a step forward, visibly morphing into a regal Westrian Priest, white stone robes pristine and an ornate, heavy stone mace in its hands.\n\nFaced with two enchanted statues, one unconscious leader, and one dead loudmouth, the remaining bandits seemed to think it was time to make a run for it.\n\n\"I don't think so,\" Isabelle said, gesturing for her Bishop and Knight to move. The sounds of stone slamming against flesh and the screams of their fellows drove the bandits that had slipped by her creations to make a full sprint for the gates. With a twist of her wrist and a snap of her fingers, stone rose up out of the ground between them and safety. The stone face of Saint Rebekah stared down at them as they stumbled to a halt.\n\n\"I'm afraid this is Checkmate, gentlemen.\"","guide":"The grandmaster is ranged striker that builds up their collection of pieces over the course of the battle that they use to attack enemies.\n\nSummon Piece is your first ability and the only way to generate the pieces you need for your other ability. A pawn is the least versatile, but the only piece that doesn't require mana. What you summon will depend on what you are facing, as it may be easier to promote your pieces against heavy tank enemies or bosses who are more likely to just tank a heavy. If you need to set up a piece to swap to with castling, then you have no choice but to summon a rook.\n\nThe most important ability for dealing damage is Move Piece, which moves a piece you control as if it was a chess piece. At 1 AP 1 mana for heavy, it's quite good at dealing damage though it comes with the condition that your pieces must be in position to make use of it.\n\nCastling is a simple swap ability. You can use it to both get yourself out of danger or to position a rook into a spot it can attack from.\n\nCheck can be used to force an enemy to move or accept taking an additional heavy attack. Against enemies that can't move for free, you're at worst trading 1 AP for 1 AP. Even if an enemy moves out of your check, the free move piece lets you set up for a real Move Piece right after.\n\nCheckmate is your secret art and an ability that gains more value the longer a fight goes. Every piece that's in position is 1 heavy attack, so the maximum amount of heavy attacks is equal to the amount of turns in the battle assuming you've spent every turn using one.","keyAbility":"Puppet Grandmaster","abilities":["Move Piece","Castling","Check","Secret Art: Checkmate"]},{"id":"granite-warden","name":"Granite Warden","tier":2,"role1":"Support","role2":"Defender","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Mage mastered or Earth mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness or Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Survival or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The whistle of the cannonball-like projectile shrieked through the air only to be intercepted by a slab of stone erupting from the ground. The projectile and wall shattered and Taran burst through the debris and dust, his massive form like a wall in its own right as he brought his axe down in a devastating strike against one of the many Kratos swarming toward them, the shockwave shattering more than the one he'd directly struck.\n\n\"Keep those walls coming, Bethan! We're almost there!\"\n\nBethan barely had the breath to sprint to keep up with her husband, each of her steps bringing an echo of the battlefield and everything touching the ground. The large Fiend behind the small army of lesser Fiends sucked up another one of its minions, the creature screaming as it was chewed and molded into another projectile. It fired again at Taran but she didn't have to intervene as he deflected the cannonball with a fist infused with stone.\n\nA stomp of her dainty foot caused a fissure to spring open along Taran's flank, swallowing a couple Kratos but mostly preventing the large group from jumping him right as he finally reached the Fiend that was spawning them. She slid her foot, scraping against the rock and she lifted her hand. Another wall shot up between Taran and the Fiend, catching a heavy claw blow that would have caught her husband full in the side. That left him with every opportunity to bring his axe down in a mana fueled blow.\n\nTen minutes later, they were standing among the evaporating remains of the Fiends and the rubble of her protective walls, cracks in the earth, and stone projectiles she'd created during the fight.\n\n\"That was closer than I like,\" Taran said tiredly as she tied a bandage around his arm.\n\n\"We handled it,\" she said, reaching out to take his face in her small hands. \"No one in the village was hurt, no homes were damaged.\"\n\n\"I know. But this is the third attack this month. There must be a Dungeon nearby, somewhere.\"\n\n\"That's a problem for adventurers,\" she insisted. \"You're not dragging me off to clear a Dungeon. We have kids, Taran.\"\n\n\"I know&but&\"\n\n\"Twenty years ago, we wouldn't have hesitated, I know.\" Bethan shifted his face until he was looking directly at her. \"But we have something more important than our old glory days, now. We'll send a message to Mothergreen and Northi to get some help with this when we get back home.\"\n\nTaran smiled and scooped her up into his arms and stood, drawing a laugh out of her. \"What did I ever do to deserve such a wonderful wife?\"\n\n\"Because you're a wonderful husband. Also, the muscles didn't hurt.\"","guide":"Granite Warden is a support class that excels in buffing the defense on your allies.\n\nEarth Armor increases the guard of an ally's armor, effectively making it 1 tier higher than it is. Note that you can't cast it on yourself.\n\nEarth Infusion is a situational spell like all infusions. It reduces the damage from Lightning and Earth, which are both decent damage types to mitigate if you face an enemy that uses them.\n\nSteady Ground is primarily a reaction tool to prevent an ally from getting knocked prone or if they would be pushed out of position. It does cost an RP, so it may not be worth usign every time.\n\nEarth Shield is your primary tool in combat allowing you to exchange your RP to give someone else an RP against the most common attacks. It also gives a sizeable amount of Block if you have high focus, which can help low guard allies against attacks they can't dodge.","keyAbility":"Tremorsense","abilities":["Steady Ground","Earth Armor","Earth Infusion","Earth Shield"]},{"id":"gravitect","name":"Gravitect","tier":3,"role1":"Controller","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Mage mastered and one tier 2 class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Appraise, Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Storm clouds swirled unnaturally overhead as if drawn to a singular point directly over the ruins of the temple. Seren waited, her robes and tail tugging in the swirling winds. The adventurers finally stepped out of the intact section of the temple, a ramshackle group that proudly displayed the colors of the Dragon Claw Alliance in some way or another: a scarf, a patch, a tunic, an armband. They were a standard seeming group with a heavy frontline and ranged support, well suited for the variety of dangers found when traveling within the Holy Astra Line.\n\n\"It's over, Seren! Your reign of terror ends today!\" the leader shouted, a rabbitfolk man in heavy plate.\n\n\"All of your followers are dead, there's nowhere to run!\" growled the hulking bulk of a bearfolk as he flexed his clawed fists.\n\nThe other two, a rogue and a priestess, stayed silent, watching her warily.\n\n\"That is quite the thing to say in such a holy place,\" she said calmly. \"Here I am, attempting to restore the world to its proper balance, righting the wrongs placed at the feet of the Holy Mother, Heira. And you can only scream and shout and kill. Ungrateful. Unacceptable.\"\n\nShe raised her hand. \"You are in the presence of a High Priestess of Heira! I am Seren Rhys and you! Will! KNEEL!\"\n\nHer hand dropped and the world dropped with it. Cracks spread across the worn stone beneath the DCA party's feet and they each fell to their knees at the sheer weight crushing them down, even the mighty bearfolk.\n\n\"You have spat on Her Grace for the last time!\"\n\nWith a roar, the adventurers pushed themselves to their feet and charged at her. Gravity shifted and warped at her command, stone flew and shattered, and spells flew. The sanctity of the ancient temple was disgraced by purified and unpurified blood alike. And she would make them pay for every transgression!","guide":"The Gravitect is a controller class with a large focus on moving allies and enemies.\n\nGravitational Push is your basic tool for this working on both allies and enemies and not allowing for a save of any kind. You can pull an ally out of danger or push an enemy away from them, pull an enemy closer to your allies to gang up on them.\n\nSingularity Collapse is an AoE pull that helps you set up for future AoE attacks such as Fireball, Fissure etc.\n\nWeight of the World is a power anti-air and anti-jump tool that cancels movement and punishes something for trying to leave the ground in your range.\n\nBlack Hole is a relatively cheap Secret Art that will likely affect most of the map and be a constant annoyance. It may also cause problems for your own allies by moving them out of range, so be aware of that.\n\nGravity Master key ability primary use is to let you work around sources of immovable. Since most of your stuff revolves around forcefully moving people, it lets you spend a mana to still be able to affect targets that go temporarily immune to it.","keyAbility":"Gravity Master","abilities":["Gravitational Push","Singularity Collapse","Weight of the World","Secret Art: Black Hole"]},{"id":"graviturge","name":"Graviturge","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Mage or Sorcerer mastered and one tier 2 class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Appraise, Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The sound of combat was all around her but seemed muted and distant. Kumiko pushed herself painfully to her feet, one arm hanging limp at her side and dripping blood steadily onto the stone beneath her feet. The blade of her katana shook slightly as she brought it up into a poor reflection of a proper stance. Opposite her, staring at her without emotion and unblinking eyes, was the Jiangshi cultist leader. Kumiko grit her teeth just looking at the cultist that was wearing her mother's face.\n\n\"I expected more out of your Team,\" the cultist said flatly, stepping forward in the slow, deliberate advance she'd used the entire fight. Her giant axe dragged along behind her, carving a furrow in the stone with its sheer weight.\n\nKumiko's Team was still fighting, engaging the other cultists and akuma they had summoned. All of them were Ascendant rank and they were being pushed back by the sheer weight of numbers in this attack. They were one of the fifty Teams spread across Ezochi to contain any akuma incursions. She had already signaled to them that they had a major incursion and the lack of any response likely meant there were similar attacks happening elsewhere. Hopefully, none as strong as what was hitting Team 44.\n\n\"You think you're winning here?\" Kumiko demanded with more bravado than she felt.\n\n\"No, I've won here.\"\n\nThat was the only warning before the cultist leader rushed forward, axe swinging from on high in a crushing blow that she knew she couldn't avoid or block. Kumiko stared defiantly, unwilling to blink or look away from her end.\n\nWhich is why she caught the air bend like a distorted mirror so much so that for a moment, she could see the cultist's back reflected above her. Then the air cracked and the leader was crushed into the stone. A second, louder crack slammed into the ground next to her and a petite, dark haired Oni stood calmly with her hands pressed together like she was holding a trapped bug.\n\n\"Well done holding the line,\" she said. The earth shook and the horrifying sound of dozens of bones snapping at once filled the air. The Oni, the Dark Radiance Natsuki herself, clapped her hands and then swept them out toward the others fighting, hurling cultists and akuma away like play things. Of the cultist leader, only a crumpled mess of an axe and blood stained stone remained. \"Pull Team 44 back, I'll handle this incursion from here.\"","guide":"The Graviturge is a straightforward striker class that excels vs larger targets.\n\nMass Index gives you a small damage boost against large and huge creatures. Gravity Crush is a short range spell of which the main goal is to let you activate this damage boost as basic attack replacements.\n\nCompression is a simple 1 AP heavy attack that gets a small discount against large targets.\n\nDensity Break is your 1 AP filler move for the average rotation of 2 AP heavy, compression, 1 AP spare. It benefits from Mass Index as well and will likely outperform a light against boss type enemies.\n\nLocalized Collapse is technically an AoE, but is more effective when used against single targets assuming you have decent Focus and won't do much against smaller ones. Because it's not a spell, it cannot benefit from Mass Index.\n\nAbsolute Compression is your secret art and one you can kind of toss out whenever. Heroics will likely dodge this and spend the extra RP from trick attack and while bosses can tank it, double heavy full pierce will be good damage regardless.","keyAbility":"Mass Index","abilities":["Compression","Density Break","Localized Collapse","Secret Art: Absolute Compression"]},{"id":"great-berserker","name":"Great Berserker","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Berserker mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Athletics, Perception, Survival, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Offensive powerhouses that overwhelm enemies with sheer force.","guide":"Great Berserker are high risk, offensive powerhouses.\n\nSingle-Minded Fury makes them focus on that 1 person, gaining a ton of bonuses and immunities, but being effectively useless against other enemies until that target is dead. Using it early or against the wrong target can make you ineffective in the fight. For example, a flying enemy may be unreachable for several turns in which you'd be able to do little.\n\nSimply running away is not much of an option however. Unrelenting assault prevents them from escaping through any means other than teleporting.\n\nSmash through the pain gives great berserkers a bit of survivability, though at the cost of using that RP to do more damage. It's pretty efficient and it stacks with your normal guard bonus.\n\nVictory or Death is a double-edged sword. Doing maximum damage is obviously good, but if you fail to finish off the enemy or enemies, then you will take a ton of damage on the turn after. It is best used when needing to finish off a high priority target or near the end of a fight. Because of the difference in damage rolls sizes, it is best used solely with heavy attacks. There's little benefit to maximum damage light attacks in most cases.","keyAbility":"Giant Strength","abilities":["Unrelenting Assault","Single-Minded Fury","Smash through the pain","Victory or Death"]},{"id":"great-knight","name":"Great Knight","tier":2,"role1":"Defender","role2":"Support","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Cavalier mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Animal Husbandry, Riding, Intimidation, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"First fielded by Northi not long after Hussars were becoming common on the battlefield, the Great Knight represented the quintessential heavy cavalry. With knight and mount both clad in heavy armor, the Great Knight was made to be a mobile barrier. Able to interpose their armored bulk for their allies and even project that protection into an aura around them, Great Knights were able to push through even the most heavily contested battlefields for their allies. And while there were countless stories throughout the ages of heavily armored knights turning the tides of battle, there were none as debated as the story of Sir Owain Morgan and Dame Madeline Benoit.\n\nAs told and accepted by Northi historians, Sir Owain Morgan was a dogfolk Great Knight without peer. Honorable beyond reproach and an unstoppable juggernaut on the battlefield, he had a list of successful battles attributed to him that stretched the imagination. In fact, detractors of Sir Owain’s tale would often point out that he must have surely known teleportation and time travel magics to be at so many battles at once. What could not be disputed was that Sir Owain certainly existed, his name recorded in the annals of the Bastion Knights. But his most debated feat was one that involved a Westrian knight, Dame Madeline Benoit, and the proliferation of Mage Knights into Northi’s military.\n\nWhile there were many versions of the tale, the most accepted one in Northi followed a series of reasonably set in stone facts. During one of the many border skirmishes common between Northi and Westria as they vied for control over the Nuren Plains, it was said that Sir Owain led a counter attack against a Westrian skirmishing force. He led his men to victory and successfully captured many knights to ransom back to Westria, including Dame Madeline Benoit. While most of the knights and men at arms were released back to their homes, Dame Madeline was kept for one very important reason: to teach Northi the art of the Mage Knight. Historians for the Era of Knights could often be incited into argument around the idea as there were as many accounts for how Northi gained access to the skills of Westria’s holy knights as there were historians to argue about them.\n\nBut what was almost universally accepted as the truth was that Sir Owain, disgusted with his peers and superiors' lack of any decency to release Dame Madeline back to her family, took it upon himself to free the woman. There was little historical accounting of where they went or what they did but there were legends of a pair of knights wandering Lyr and helping those in need. And while those actions had never definitively been attributed to Sir Owain and Dame Madeline, what couldn’t be denied was when they both turned back up in solid historical record.\n\nThey would found Morgan Ranch in what would later become Dacquoise, near the future site of the city of Madeline. It was there that the retired knights, happily married for an unclear amount of time, had begun taking on students and ranch hands to teach the art of horsemanship, knighthood, and magic. While the ranch itself did not last into modern times, the house itself was maintained and the legacy of chivalry was upheld by the descendants of those students. Collectively, and informally, they called themselves the Knights of Morgan and dedicated themselves to helping those in need whenever and wherever they were found.","guide":"The great knight is a mounted tank class that excels in fights with many different engagements.\n\nIntercept is your main tool in getting around the battlefield, allowing you to ride to an allies aid. If you move to an ally far away enough, you can even use Trample and do some damage with it. Note that your movement is not a sidestep, you do provoke attacks of opportunity with it.\n\nRescue & Drop lets you save an ally from a bad situation and ride them out to safety. You can also drop them immediately to another square nearby to break them free from being surrounded or to let them move away without provoking.\n\nYour Secret Art: Moving Castle is an aura that reduces damage by 3 in a small aura around you. This can be massive when fighting against a group of non-heroic enemies, reducing the damage your allies take by a large amount. You can also move for free once per turn to reposition and potentially help allies in two completely different positions at the same time.\n\nShared Defense is a simple tool that helps you protect your mount from AoE attacks.","keyAbility":"Heavy Cavalry","abilities":["Rescue & Drop","Intercept","Shared Defense","Secret Art: Moving Castle"]},{"id":"guardian","name":"Guardian","tier":2,"role1":"Defender","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Fighter or Armorsmith mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Riding, Intimidation, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Guardians are heavily armored fighters that specialize in defense for both themselves and their allies.","guide":"The guardian is a defender that wants to reduce damage through high toughness and heavy armor. They get access to this heavy armor, though the drawbacks of it are noticeable too. Too much guard may be overkill and it may be better to stick to medium or light armor in some cases.\n\nThey control what the enemy can do by using Provoke and Threatening Aura. Provoke is a 1 turn Challenge for no AP cost, while threatening aura does cost 2 AP, but you automatically challenge everything around you. Challenge makes enemies provoke attacks of opportunity when they hit anybody except you, so you do need to keep in melee range of the enemies. Challenging Aura is especially good when you have other melee fighters that are squishy next to you. A berserker will greatly appreciate being hard to target.\n\nTo help with being a threat with your attacks of opportunity, the controlled opportunities key ability gives you a small bonus to them. Thanks to it, guardians are more free to ignore focus and power and focus on defensive stats.\n\nHold the line lets a guardian convert AP to RP at a good rate, at the cost of some mana. In a long fight, frequent use of this will let you keep your RP until you really need it.\n\nLast Stand is an ability that should only be used when you know you're going to face many attacks during the upcoming round. The RP cost is heavy, but it can easily be RP efficient. You don't need to use mana on this for it to be worth it, but it's worth considering if you are likely to face a bunch of heavy attacks.","keyAbility":"Controlled Opportunities","abilities":["Provoke","Hold the line","Threatening Aura","Last Stand"]},{"id":"gun-paladin","name":"Gun Paladin","tier":2,"role1":"Support","role2":"Striker","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Human. Ranger mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on any non crafting or gathering skill. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"John was a paladin who loved guns. Like his fellow paladins, he had been trained in the ways of sword and shield.\n\nOne day, he and his friends were forced to gather at a border village where a fiend had reportedly appeared. The reports were true. In front of them stood a towering mass of shadows and tentacles that had already murdered the entire population. But of course, they could not simply retreat or it may attack other villages.\n\nHis commander gave the order and dozens of paladins charged forward to subdue the creature. But not John. He looked towards the men and women who were running to their death, then towards the pistols he carried at his side. They were expected to fight in melee, but why would Kari's light discriminate against a weapon?\n\nHe sheathed his sword and shield and drew his pistol. He ignored his commander's shouting and aimed the weapon at the monster. Brilliant holy light fired from the barrel and as it struck the monster, his allies' attacks became empowered. Without hesitation, he threw his spare pistol to other paladins nearby. Together, their shots annihilated the creature and he became known as the first gun paladin.","guide":"The gun paladin is a support striker class that lets your allies attack for you.\n\nJudgement Shot is a light attack that allows an ally to spend their extra RP on making a heavy attack. Even them making a light attack can be better if your offensive stats are worse.\n\nTwin Verdict lets you convert your extra RP into extra offensive power. It combo's decently well with snap shot in giving you access to another heavy in a turn.\n\nDivine Barrage lets you and several allies all light up a single target. While it costs a bit of mana, it can do a lot of damage to a squishy target.\n\nSanctity Aura is a situational aura effect. It may let your allies do extra damage or bypass resistances when you let them make attacks.","keyAbility":"Holy Weapon","abilities":["Judgement Shot","Twin Verdict","Sanctity Aura","Divine Barrage"]},{"id":"gunfu","name":"Gunfu","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Cultivator or Martial Artist mastered. Gunslinger mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness Cunning, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Perception, Deception, Insight, Survival or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"A skilled gunner and martial artist that combines guns and martial arts into a deadly mix.","guide":"Those who practice Gunfu are able to fight well from both range as well as in melee due to not suffering any penalties when firing in melee combat. They are able to weaken the enemy from range, then go in for the kill once they’ve come closer.\n\nSlide & Shoot is their gap closer that can be used to slip past the frontline to target the backline. It also starts their combo and should always be followed up with an unarmed attack for maximum value.\n\nPistol Whip is counted as an unarmed attack and is thus a natural follow up that now costs 0 AP. The debuff it applies will help reduce the amount of attacks you face.\n\nAfter that, you can finish it up with a Point Blank Shot. It is not particularly effective against heavy armor, but it punishes dodgy characters extremely hard.\n\nTheir Secret Art Whirling Death is an excellent clean up tool for grunt type enemies. Ideally it should be used when multiple enemies are already weakened. This will allow for multiple activations of its Killing Blow mechanic when you finish off the weak enemies and can keep shooting.","keyAbility":"Gun Martial Arts","abilities":["Slide & Shoot","Point Blank Shot","Pistol Whip","Secret Art: Whirling Death"]},{"id":"gunslinger","name":"Gunslinger","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Stealth, Perception, Insight, Survival, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The Gunslinger is a ranged combat specialist who excels in the use of firearms, particularly pistols. They are skilled marksmen, able to hit their targets with deadly accuracy and speed.","guide":"The gunslinger takes control of the fight from the start with their Quickdraw ability. It's only a light attack, but it's a free attack that can't be reacted to, so it's free early damage. Because it's an encounter start ability, it is one of the few things that lets you act before enemy with ‘First Shot’ initiative bonus can take their action.\n\nRicochet is a simple attack that can be used to bypass light cover. If an enemy is using light cover, there's little reason not to use it.\n\nWarning Shot costs a fair bit of mana, but gaining Trick Attack can help you secure hits. Grunts are unable to react to them, so you can snipe one hiding behind cover with a warning shot + ricochet combo.\n\nFor their Secret Art: Fan the hammer you'll probably want to bring a spare pistol. It is a relatively close range ability and the high AP cost makes it hard to move and shoot if you don't get extra AP from somewhere, but it can do a large amount of damage. A single reaction will affect all 4 shots, so its something only to be used against a target that has exhausted their RP.","keyAbility":"Gunslinger's Agility","abilities":["Ricochet","Warning Shot","Quickdraw","Secret Art: Fan the hammer"]},{"id":"harrier","name":"Harrier","tier":2,"role1":"Controller","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Ranger mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus.","skills":"You gain 5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Stealth, Medicine, Perception, Survival, Animal Husbandry or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Eirlys Saoirsen crouched low, fingers brushing against a crushed leaf. A single discrepancy in a literal forest of leaves. A single mistake by her prey. She stood and continued following the trail, ghosting through the brush and vines without a trace or hindrance. It was an eternal job to patrol the border of the Great Forest, the boundary of Easter. Normally, the magic of the Fae prevented intruders from making it more than half a mile into the Forest before they became so confused that they wandered back out. But sometimes, poachers would hire an unscrupulous Fae (there were more of those than she liked) to guide them through the country wide bounded field.\n\nEirlys had been tracking this group for three days, her anger growing at each sign of a hunted glitter stag or crudely harvested glow moss. But she was close, finally, and she could put an end to this. She froze as a branch snapped in the near distance ahead of her and she could just make out brash voices and the sounds of a camp being prepared. She paused, pulling out her crossbow and silently readying it with a bolt. Then she stalked forward, silent and leaving no trail to tack her by.\n\nThe poachers were gathering fallen branches for a fire, two catfolk chimera and a human. Their guide, a stuffy looking high fae, was leaning against a tree, radiating barely disguised disgust. Eirlys stalked closer slowly as the camp came together until she was only twenty feet away from the guide. Once in position, she didn’t hesitate and the snap of her crossbow firing put everyone on alert. Well, so did the cry of agony from the guide as her bolt punched through his left calf, pinning it to the tree. She thrust out her hand, vines flying from her outstretched arm and wrapping the surprised Fae to the tree, pinning his arms. Then she sprinted from cover, to slap a piece of sticky bark over his eyes to prevent him from teleporting free of his bindings.\n\nThe poachers were scrambling for their weapons, swords and axes. They had already unstrung their bows for the night so she had the advantage in range. And her crossbow had already reset itself, waiting for a bolt, the partially living weapon her steady companion for longer than most civilizations had lasted. Her second shot of the night pinned one of the catfolk to the ground by his boot, her third knocking another head over heels as he tried to close the distance through the rough terrain of the brush.\n\nShe faded in and out of visibility, moving impossibly quickly through the surrounding forest, bolts picking away at them from safety. The sun was just setting by the time the last poacher fell still and she was finally able to relax. Well…Eirlys looked at the struggling, screaming Fae guide and walked over to him. She stuck another sticky bark over his mouth, careful to keep his nose free for breathing. With his screaming muffled, she would really be able to relax. She could turn him in to the Council in Sylvan later.","guide":"The harrier is a ranged controller class that prefers using a crossbow.\n\nPinning Shot will be your most powerful control option, allowing you to potentially root a target which is a powerful debuff. The target can spend 2 AP to break free, but this is still an AP win for you and you and your allies will benefit from its reduced dodge until it does.\n\nTo setup for your pinning shot, you have Knockback Shot allowing you to knock an enemy close to or into a wall.\n\nTo help with reliability, you have Rapid Correction which not only allows you to turn a miss against the base evasion into a potential hit, it can also allow you to react after a target dodges the attack to turn it into an attack that goes past their dodge.\n\nFlushing Shot is naturally used against enemies in cover to bait them out of it. Even if they choose not to move, you just get a Sure Hit attack against them which is just good.\n\nFinally, Discern Immunities is a simple ability that will prevent you from using abilities that won't work against an enemy. It does share the Quick keyword with Status Assessment, so be aware you can't use both in the same turn without spending an extra PA.","keyAbility":"Discern Immunities","abilities":["Knockback Shot","Pinning Shot","Rapid Correction","Flushing Shot"]},{"id":"high-priest","name":"High Priest","tier":3,"role1":"Healer","role2":"","difficulty":1,"requirements":"Priest mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to either Power or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Medicine, Religion, Magic, History, Insight, Negotiation, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Powerful divine agents who bring peace and comfort to their allies.","guide":"The high priest has strong out of combat healing thanks to their Tranquil Prayers. If possible, you will want to delay healing near the end of a fight and save your mana to use it after combat ends.\n\nCure Touch II is a massive heal with an equally big mana cost. It's very powerful when an ally is low on hit points, but it may leave you out of options in the future.\n\nPurification Circle is an AoE debuff removal. It is relatively cheap AP and Mana cost wise if you're hitting more than 1 person and it can remove different debuffs from different people.\n\nRadiant Halo is another spell with a high mana cost. It heals all allies, but the range may be limiting if the party is split up in a fight. You can also cast it by using RP, which can be a lifesaver when you need to top of your allies after a powerful AoE attack.\n\nFinally, Walking Church is a secret art that effectively makes a target immune to damage for one turn. There will always be a use for this ability in a fight, so save a mana and RP for it until you need it.","keyAbility":"Tranquil Prayers","abilities":["Cure Touch II","Purification Circle","Radiant Halo","Secret Art: Walking Church"]},{"id":"highlander","name":"Highlander","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Adventurer, Fighter, Farmer, Blacksmith or Miner mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Riding, Intimidation, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"A fighter that uses heavy weapons to land powerful blows.","guide":"The highlander is a reliable combatant that uses heavy melee weapons. Their aftershocks ability ensures that even if they miss their heavy attacks, they still deal some damage to the target and enemies around them.\n\nSteady Stance is cheap to activate and protects against most knockbacks and prone knocking abilities, assuming you've leveled Power a good amount. It can be used as a reaction, so you don't need to activate it until you are hit by one of those types of abilities.\n\nCleave is an AP efficient attack, provided you hit the first attack on the enemy. Best used if the first target has no AP remaining, but even on a miss you can do good damage with aftershocks.\n\nKnockdown Swing a simple ability that knocks people prone. It can be used to open up enemies for your allies or to make the enemy more vulnerable to your Overpower.\n\nOverpower can demolish enemies with much lower power than you, but it may not do much if their power is similar to yours. Evaluate how much power your opponent has before using it. Against prone enemies, the benefit is doubled making it almost always worth using.","keyAbility":"Aftershocks","abilities":["Steady Stance","Knockdown Swing","Cleave","Overpower"]},{"id":"hoarfrost","name":"Hoarfrost","tier":3,"role1":"Controller","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Cryomancer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Toughness","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Magic or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The Hoarfrosts are Cryomancers who’ve mastered the chilling power of ice, tracing their origins back to a legendary mage named Mirane. She was the first to truly perfect the art of Cryomancy during her journey through the eastern Tundra. Her story took a dramatic turn when she faced off against a powerful Fiend. In that intense battle, Mirane developed her ultimate spell, the Eternal Mirane Cage. This incredible spell froze the Fiend in place for ten long years, giving an army of adventurers the time they needed to arrive and finally take it down.\n\nMirane’s magic didn’t just fade into history—it’s been passed down through the generations to future Hoarfrosts. Those who follow in her footsteps wear a snowflake emblem, just like Mirane did, and many of them embark on their own journeys to the Tundra that now bears her name.","guide":"Eternal Mirane Cage is a legendary ability, but it’s not something you’ll use all the time. It’s perfect for when you need to subdue enemies who just won’t give up, making Hoarfrosts a great choice for missions where taking down targets alive is the goal.\n\nFrost Driver is an excellent follow-up move that turns a slow into a full-on root, setting up your team for devastating AoE attacks and utility plays. Just be aware of its limitation against flying enemies—it won’t be as effective there.\n\nWhite Thunder is a clever setup move that transforms your Glacial Walls into potential bombs. It forces enemies to think twice before getting too close, giving you control over the battlefield.\n\nWhen things get dicey, Glacial Bastion is your panic button, but it’s not something to use without thought. While it shields you, it can also give enemies the chance to position themselves around you, potentially trapping you. If you see them making a move for a big strike, use White Thunder while encased, since you can’t defend yourself while you’re in the ice.\n\nLastly, the Hoarfrost’s Secret Art, Whiteout, is a powerful tool that reduces accuracy for everyone on the battlefield and can be activated right at the start of an encounter. It’s especially useful if you’re ambushed or under heavy pressure, buying your team some defensive turns to regroup and reposition. Just keep in mind that enemies with Frost Immunity or Ice Cold are unaffected by it, just like you.","keyAbility":"Eternal Mirane Cage","abilities":["Frost Driver","White Thunder","Glacial Bastion","Secret Art: Whiteout"]},{"id":"hussar","name":"Hussar","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Cavalier mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Animal Husbandry, Riding, Intimidation, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The romantic image of cavalry often brought to mind knights in gleaming plate armor, resplendent in heraldry, astride a powerful steed. Lances, spears, and longswords held aloft, ready to ride nobly into the fray. Ready to rescue princesses, slay dragons, and dispatch dishonorable knaves. While many knights struggle to live up to that image, the origin of those lofty traits could be found in the Hussars.\n\nNamed after the light cavalry unit raised from the nobles and knights of Macaron in Dacquoise, the Macaron Hussars set a standard for both chivalry and battlefield prowess that has remained largely unchallenged even into the modern day. While the individual knights may have their betters in swordsmanship or as riders, the combined unit has been considered the premier elite light cavalry force since its creation across all of Lyr. Sworn directly to the King of Dacquoise, the honor within the ranks of the Macaron Hussars is such that there has never been a recorded or rumored instance of betrayal of their oaths, even during the rare instances of attempted usurpation of the Line of the King. They have never failed to follow the rightful King or Heir of Dacquoise.\n\nTheir metal was tested in recent memory at the Battle of Nuren Crossing where the combined forces of the Nuren Guard and a small adventuring party held a critical bridge crossing against Northi invasion during the Four Swords War. The Northi commanders, intent to utilize Dacquoise’s roads to move rapidly into a flanking position against Mothergreen, attempted to take the northernmost bridge crossing of the Nuren river. When they were unable to capture the bridge with their scouts, the Northi force was pinned against the river by Lamian elements of the Nuren Guard. Before they were able to withdraw and regroup, the hammer of the Macaron Hussars smashed them against the Lamian anvil, having used a risky ford miles downstream. With their support elements gutted, supplies captured, and further Dacquoise reinforcements incoming, the invading force surrendered and were permitted to withdraw back to Northi.\n\nHussars around the world have strived to live up to the gallantry and reputation of their namesakes, always chasing that seemingly distant goal. And while more renegade knights have taken up the skills of mobility and devastatingly powerful charges that the Hussars are known for, many still believe that the embodiment of the knight as demonstrated by the Macaron Hussars was a goal worth striving for.","guide":"The hussar is a mounted class that overwhelms the enemy with devastating charges.\n\nCavalry charge is a movement ability that boosts your trample. It has no additional cost over normal movement, so you should always use this if you're planning to trample enemies over moving normally. Any non-heroic enemy with your trample also becomes Shaken, which basically makes them useless on their next turn.\n\nMomentum is an ability that you can use after you've moved in range of the enemy with your charging attack, as it can gain a large damage boost. Another option is to strike at a non-heroic enemy that used their RP to dodge your trample. They'll now have no RP left and your momentum boosted attack is likely to one shot them, especially if using a lance.\n\nBreak Away is the ability you use to move away from the enemy to prepare for another trampling charge attack. The mana cost is relatively high, so ideally you don't want to be in a position where you have to use it.\n\nSecret Art: Override is a powerful secret art that relies heavily on enemies being in a line to get maximum value out of. Be careful when using this against rogues, their evasive maneuvers ability can force you to end your override early by creating an empty space.","keyAbility":"Terrifying Charge","abilities":["Cavalry Charge","Break Away","Momentum","Secret Art: Override"]},{"id":"hydromancer","name":"Hydromancer","tier":2,"role1":"Specialist","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Any class mastered or Water mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason, Presence or Awareness","soul":"You gain +1 to Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in any Reason, Awareness or Presence category skill.","description":"Hydromancers are specialist water mages who can fit into almost any party. They're ‘fluid’ if you will. (Placeholder)","guide":"Hydromancers are versatile specialist mages who can do a little bit of everything. They are reliant on their ability key ability Blue Tide to create domains of water from which they can cast spells from. This poses a challenge, as you must set up preparations in advance in order be effective. In exchange for this limitation, Hydromancers are incredibly versatile and can deal damage, support, control and even heal. Their ultimate ability, Refreshing Stream, is a rare ability that allows you to heal RP, a critical defensive resource. In addition, Hydromancers can use RP to cast many of their abilities, giving them the ability to turn the tides mid turn.\n\nSetting up Blue Tide early is critical to take early space. You’ll want to move with your team and continue to use Blue Tide to create more zones that you can fight and cast from. If you find yourself in a battle near or on top of water, you’re in luck as you won’t need to cast Blue Tide as often. Aqua Drill can be used as a normal heavy attack, but also has the additional purpose of spreading water into areas that do not have any. You can use Aqua Drill as a combo with other abilities to increase your casting range of water spells.\n\nCrashing Foam Wave is a versatile ability that can be used to push enemies away, as well as set up allies for more powerful attacks, or to pull enemies away from danger. Since forced movement doesn’t trigger attacks of opportunity, you can bounce allies away with it.\n\nCure Water is a basic healing spell but its quite strong. Its mana cost is quite high, so use caution with casting it often.\n\nAgility builds favor Hydromancers, as having high RP for your abilities is recommended.","keyAbility":"Mage of the Tides","abilities":["Aqua Drill","Crashing Foam Wave","Cure Water","Refreshing Stream"]},{"id":"iai-style","name":"Iai Style","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any class mastered. Proficient with Katana.","heart":"You gain +1 to Awareness or Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Intimidation, History, Insight, Art, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The art of Iai came from the Island of Kirara, a sword style utilizing Kiraran blades. The Youkai were known for their highly lethal speed and technique in preference over raw power. Iaidoka are quite rare, students of elusive Kiraran Masters who only train two students at a time.","guide":"Masters of the Iaido style typically start the battle in one of two ways: They open with an Iai strike or wait for the enemy to strike, then counter with Uke Nagashi. Iaido centers around Iaijutsu and the sheathed state. Their most important abilities are locked behind this sheathed state and unless you fulfill conditions, its a once per battle thing.\n\nIai Strike is a powerful attack that not only has lock-on, it's also only 1 AP. Unless you are using a weapon other than a katana and mixing weapon fighting styles, this will most likely be your first action in combat. Because using it loses the sheathed state, it can not be used again unless you use Kiri-tsuke.\n\nKiri-tsuke is a heavy attack with the benefit of resetting your sheathed state when you score a kill with it. Depending on the battle, this may be an easy or hard thing to do, but you should always look for the opportunity for the reset.\n\nChiburi Noto is used at the end of the encounter and buffs you for your next one by maximizing your Iai strike damage. The benefit of this can be good, but if you are low on HP or mana it may be wise to use one of the basic options instead.\n\nUke Nagashi is a powerful counter move that has the condition that you must still be in the sheathed state. Because making any attack with a katana removes the sheathed state, this means you can not attack before using Uke Nagashi, unless you use a different type of weapon. This is a valid option. You can choose to attack with a normal sword, then drop it and prepare for your counter. If you'd rather only use a katana and still want to use this, then you can instead play very aggressive with your positioning. Use all your AP to move up, then when the enemy wants to attack you, unleash the counter. You can also choose to delay and hope the enemy moves up and attacks you.","keyAbility":"Iaijutsu","abilities":["Iai Strike","Kiri-tsuke","Chiburi Noto","Uke Nagashi"]},{"id":"idol","name":"Idol","tier":1,"role1":"Support","role2":"Healer","difficulty":1,"requirements":"None","heart":"You gain +1 to Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Stealth, Deception, Linguistics, Insight, Art, Negotiation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Kyouko took a deep breath to settle her nerves and had to stop her hands from smoothing her skirt down again. Her boots crunched softly against the frosted moss, the heels sinking in a bit before she adjusted her stride.\n\n\"Don't worry, Kyouko-chan, we won't let any harm come to you,\" Nalin said, his voice a deep rumble as he held out her wand. It looked like a tiny toy in his huge, bullfolk hands and she gave him a bright smile, her twin tails curling. He patted her gently on the head and then hefted his heavy shield and mace.\n\n\"I know. You all have protected me for so long, now I can help you!\" she said earnestly.\n\nHenry flashed her a peace sign with a grin and Marco looked away to fiddle with his staff. Marco always got embarrassed so easily but Kyouko knew he loved listening to her practicing her songs every night. Seren pushed her way through the brush ahead of them, her face brightening as she jogged over to the group, her cat ears perked up happily and her tail twitching back and forth. She leaned in for a quick hug before getting down business.\n\n\"It's definitely an enemy group,\" she said. \"Five members with a full mix of front liners, mid range, and supporters. They'll be tricky to beat but they don't have Kyouko.\"\n\n\"True!\" Henry agreed. \"C'mon, let's teach these guys that they can't just do what they want here.\"\n\nThe point of intercept Seren had scouted was just ahead, a nice clearing that would give them plenty of area to move in. Kyouko took her position behind her friends and waited. It wasn't long until an eclectic group stumbled into the clearing with none of the matching uniforms her friends had. The newcomers noticed them instantly and they immediately pulled out weapons.\n\n\"Why do we always run into cultists?\" one of them complained. \"And why do they always have hostages?!\"\n\nHostages? Kyouko looked around. Her group hadn't taken any hostages. And she resented being called a cultist!\n\nStill, just like she had practiced, she began the first steps of her performance, her mana spreading across the clearing in sparkles and phantom music.\n\n\"In the shadow of the world I play~\"","guide":"The idol class is one of the easiest classes in the game.\n\nYou have 3 buffing songs, one that boosts accuracy, one that boosts damage and one that boosts evasion. Simply use the song that your party needs you to use based on the enemy you're fighting. In most cases, you'll likely up using This is our moment!\n\nStay here with me is an AoE healing song that can keep your party up over a long fight with decent efficiency if you're healing multiple people.\n\nMashup is the one way to get more songs active as an Idol without going into other classes. Due to the way songs work, you can only have 1 of them active normally but Mashup lets you ignore this and get your songs up faster for a small mana cost.","keyAbility":"Idol's Journey","abilities":["This is our moment!","Twinkle Step","Stay Here With Me!","Mashup"]},{"id":"jonin","name":"Jonin","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Support","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Ninja mastered","heart":"You gain +1 to Cunning.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Stealth, Deception, Roguecraft, Perception, Insight, Negotiation, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"-","guide":"-","keyAbility":"Ninja Techniques","abilities":["Kugeki-zan","En-dama","Kage Bunshin: Kyomei","Ougi: Taju Bunshin no Jutsu"]},{"id":"knight-paramount","name":"Knight-Paramount","tier":3,"role1":"Defender","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Great Knight mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Animal Husbandry, Riding, Intimidation, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Jasmine Fontaine, Knight-Paramount of Westria, wheeled Dauntless around to avoid a spear that would have cut under her mount's armored side. She barely paid attention to the offending spearman falling to the ground with a choked cry as her warhorse's kick sent him tumbling. She was focused more on the echoing sound of a horn in the distance, strident and urgent. A call to return, an attack. She had specifically left the rest of her unit with the Baroness in the case that parts of the ambushing force attempted to break away but the bandits had been fully focused on engaging her. The ambush she had disrupted had been a decoy to draw away defenders from Baroness Durand's carriage.\n\nA crossbow bolt hissed through the air as she stood fully in her stirrups and she let it glance uselessly off her pauldron, adding another scratch to her new armor. The road took a bend through the forest so she couldn't see the carriage and her men but she could just make out the sounds of distant clashing. Dauntless suddenly jerked as a particularly foolish bandit grabbed the slack in the reins in some attempt to wrest control of her mount from her. Her clever warhorse bit the idiot and bodily lifted him briefly before tossing his head, sending the man flying. She swept her lance around to bash another of the bandits away and then spurred Dauntless forward.\n\n\"Stop her! Spears!\" someone called out and a few men rushed to block her path but she was already on them. They very much underestimated Dauntless's speed due to his heavy armor but that just meant he was an unstoppable avalanche.\n\n\"Out of my WAY!\" Only one had the presence of mind to dive out of her path, the rest trampled mercilessly into the ground.\n\n And she was away, thundering down the road. In only minutes, the carriage was in sight and the situation was not in her men's favor. Two of the cavaliers had been pulled from their horses and were fighting on foot, backs nearly against the carriage itself. The other cavalier, his young face a mask of panic, was frantically fending off bandits attempting to get hold of him. And the man she left in charge, a veteran Hussar, was being held at bay by a wall of spearmen. None of her men were down but it was only a matter of time if she didn't break the attack.\n\nShe urged Dauntless on faster, the thunder of his hooves drawing the attention of everyone around the carriage. She could see the leader of the bandits recoil, looking desperately back toward the spears already fully occupied. He knew what was coming and there was nothing he could do to stop it. Mana flowed through her and Dauntless as echoes of a full cavalry charge began to form around her, the manifestation of a Knight-Paramount's Unstoppable Onslaught.\n\nThey tried to run, tried to jump out of the way, but the wake of her charge swept them all away. The full force of her charge slammed into the spear line, the dust from her phantom charge billowing forward. Jasmine spun Dauntless around and leveled her lance toward the bandit leader who was staring in horror at the ruined remnants of his forces.\n\n\"Surrender!\" she commanded. \"And your lives will be spared!\" For the time being. Most bandits ended their careers with the noose.\n\nWeapons clattered to the ground but it was only to allow the bandits to run away faster. She didn't have to command her cavaliers to chase them down, with the two dismounted delayed only long enough to call their horses.\n\n\"Keep them safe, Paul, I didn't finish off the other force,\" she said to the Hussar as he came alongside her. \"I'll watch over the Baroness for now.\"","guide":"The Knight-Paramount is the continuation of the Great Knight and likewise focuses on mounted defense.\n\nWith Living Cover, other allies can use you as cover. This is especially useful against light attacks, as you'll most likely be able to reduce their damage to almost nothing where your unarmored allies may take a lot of damage. Against some heavy attacks, you may wish to not grant the cover and save your own RP.\n\nBlocking Move is your tool to prevent enemies from walking past you. You opportunity attack them, then interrupt their movement. After this they must choose to either attack you, while you get a free block against them essentially refunding your RP or they continue to walk away which now costs them another AP of movement and you get to make a sure hit attack against them, which is essentially a better heavy opportunity attack.\n\nHeavy Trample is a simple passive ability that lets you scale better, as even grunts may begin to start blocking your trample at some point.\n\nArmored Blow is an attack to use after engaging, giving you a free improved block against the target. It's probably not worth forcing this ability to be used after the initial charge in.\n\nYour Secret Art: Unstoppable Onslaught is an alternative to the more defensive and mana hungry moving castle. You simply just use it at the start of the fight and weaken all enemies in a large area for no mana cost. Whether you use this ability or your Great Knight secret art will depend on what you're facing and how much mana you like to use on other stuff such as Spirit Jump.","keyAbility":"Living Cover","abilities":["Blocking Move","Heavy Trample","Armored Blow","Secret Art: Unstoppable Onslaught"]},{"id":"lancer","name":"Lancer","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Cavalier, Adventurer or Fighter mastered, Proficient in polearms or lances.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Riding, Intimidation, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Lancers are a class that specializes in using polearms.","guide":"Lancers prefer to let the enemy come to them. The full pierce effect gained from their Brace key ability makes even a readied light attack do good damage.\n\nExtending Spear allows the lancer to attack from long range and hit a lot of enemies if they line up. Extending Spear followed by a readied attack is a good way to start fights and wait for the enemy to get closer.\n\nOnce they are close, a crescent sweep can knock them all off their feet and set them up for the rest of the team.\n\nWhen there is only a few enemies, look for a position to use Piercing Stab in. 2 AP for 2 heavy attacks is very cost efficient, even if you have to move for 1 AP to position for it.\n\nFinally, lunge with a polearm gives you a 20ft attack range. This is long enough to hit basically every enemy in the front line and may be enough range to even hit a backline target that moved up too far.","keyAbility":"Brace","abilities":["Lunge","Piercing Stab","Extending Spear","Crescent Sweep"]},{"id":"mage","name":"Mage","tier":1,"role1":"Utility","role2":"Controller","difficulty":2,"requirements":"None.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason","soul":"You gain +1 to either Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Appraise, Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Mages are initiates of the arcane, who’ve mastered the basics and proven their skill in both control and power. By drawing in ambient mana and blending it with their own, they can cast devastating spells of all kinds. The path of a Mage is as varied as the Mages themselves.\n\nSome might start off their journey at the Merlin's Academy of Magic, while others are self taught or might become the pupil of a wandering teacher.\n\nWhile still considered beginners in the journey of Magic, Mages are quite powerful on their own with many considering a skilled mage to be worth the equivalent of an entire squad of infantry.","guide":"Mages offer supportive control to the party, out of combat utility and a barrage of long range spells to wither down the most evasive of targets.\n\nSense Magic and Decipher Magic both serve as out of combat investigation tools. Sense Magic gives information, while Decipher Magic actively lets you disable magical fields.\n\nArcane Barrier is a defensive tool that lets mages effectively block without having a high guard. If an attack did a low amount of damage, you may be able to use the Block reaction afterwards with the barrier still up and still get some value out of it.\n\nGlittershards is their control ability. It covers a 15x15ft area which is a decent area and be can be used primarily to block enemy ranged attackers from shooting you. The mana cost on it is low, so you can feel free to drop it and recast it in a better position if the need arises.\n\nMagic Missile is light attack that should be used against dodge heavy characters. If you know the enemy is not going to die from 1 missile, you can overcharge it and fire a second one for the same cost again. The target has to react to both of them with separate reactions, so you'll be doing some good damage or burning reactions with it.","keyAbility":"Mage's Journey","abilities":["Decipher Magic","Arcane Barrier","Glittershards","Magic Missile"]},{"id":"mage-knight","name":"Mage Knight","tier":2,"role1":"Healer","role2":"Support","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Cavalier mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Awareness, Reason or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Animal Husbandry, Magic, Riding, Intimidation, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"First fielded by Westria during the growing advent of the Church of Light and cavalry’s importance on the battlefield, the Mage Knight brought both magical support and healing to the highly mobile battlefront. While originally simply an order of priest-knights, Mage Knights would eventually grow to encompass all forms of magical casting. Whether it was raining down spells or utilizing their unique training to heal mount and rider both, the Mage Knight could turn the tide of a battle with their mere presence. And while there were countless stories throughout the ages of holy knights bringing men back from the brink of death, there were none as debated as the story of Dame Madeline Benoit and Sir Owain Morgan.\n\nAs told and accepted by Westrian historians, Dame Madeline Benoit was a human Mage Knight without equal. Gentle and nurturing to her allies and able to bring her enemies low with figurative hellfire, she held a near saintly presence in the Church of Light. Debates would still sometimes crop up among the clergy as to her suitability as a Saint but her history was both ill documented and controversial, depending on who was asked. There was no dispute of her actual existence as her name was recorded as a Holy Knight of Kari, but there was a much debated feat in her history: Sir Owain Morgan and the proliferation of Great Knights into Westria’s military.\n\nWhile there were many versions of the tale, the most accepted one in Westria followed a series of reasonably set in stone facts. During the many border incursions from Northi as it tried to wrest control of the Nuren Plains from their ancestral owners, it was said that Dame Madeline Benoit helped devastate a Northi skirmishing force. Not only was she instrumental in capturing many of the Northi knights, she graciously tended to their wounds with a special focus on Sir Owain Morgan. The dogfolk Great Knight had taken the brunt of the Westrian counterattack as he shielded his men and required significantly more care than the others. In fact, he traveled back to Westria for further treatment while his men were released back to Northi. It was said that, in his gratitude, he volunteered the skills of the Great Knight and allowed Westrian artisans to study his and his mount’s armor. And while there was debate on the validity of that tale for the origin of the proliferation of Great Knights into the Westrian military, they paled in comparison to the vicious arguments that revolved around the love story between Dame Madeline and Sir Owain.\n\nThe most commonly accepted telling of the great love between Madeline and Owain was that of star crossed lovers fighting destiny and the world to be together. What started as simple care for a wounded knight became tender affection as the months of Owain’s recovery ran on. Some accounts painted a picture of desperate, forbidden love with various forces working to keep them apart. Secret marriages, hidden lineages, and fantastical courtly intrigue plagued the romance novel market with few authors making any attempts to disguise their protagonists. The reality of it was much simpler and all the sweeter for it.\n\nNeither Madeline or Owain had the heart to return to the constant fighting between their two countries and retired from their respective militaries. The legend among the Benoit household was that the pair had a private wedding in the garden of Madeline’s childhood home and then departed for destinations unknown. The rumor was that they spent time as traveling knights, wandering Lyr and helping those in need. And while those actions had never definitively been attributed to Dame Madeline and Sir Owain, what couldn’t be denied was when they both turned back up in solid historical record.\n\nThey would found Morgan Ranch in what would later become Dacquoise, near the future site of the city of Madeline. It was there that the retired knights, happily married for an unclear amount of time, had begun taking on students and ranch hands to teach the art of horsemanship, knighthood, and magic. While the ranch itself did not last into modern times, the house itself was maintained and the legacy of chivalry was upheld by the descendants of those students. Collectively, and informally, they called themselves the Knights of Morgan and dedicated themselves to helping those in need whenever and wherever they were found.","guide":"The mage knight is a mounted healer that specializes in aiding other mounted combatants.\n\nCavalry heal is a heal that heals both the rider and mount for a mana cost that is only slightly higher than a normal heal, making is pretty efficient. It is important to note that unlike a lot of other of the mounted class abilities, both spells of the mage knight can be used while dismounted.\n\nThe other heal in question is Rescue, which is a mid range teleport spells that pulls an ally next to you. This immediately puts them in range for a healing ability. Unlike most teleport abilities, this pulls both mount and rider. Can also be used offensively to pull a slower ally closer to the enemy.\n\nAnother way the mage knight can heal allies is by using Mounted Casting. You can ride past an ally and use Mounted Casting to heal them, then keep riding on to safety. If your way is blocked, you can also use Canter thanks to your key ability.\n\nFinally, your Secret Art: Ride of the Valkyrie requires some setup and positioning from your allies but it's an efficient heal if you can hit your entire party with it. Can also be combined with trample, but be careful as your trample getting blocked may prevent further movement and healing.","keyAbility":"Mage Knight","abilities":["Cavalry Heal","Mounted Casting","Rescue","Secret Art: Ride of the Valkyrie"]},{"id":"magitechnician-","name":"Magitechnician","tier":2,"role1":"Artisan","role2":"Utility","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Artificer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Artificing.","description":"Expert Magitechnicans are the true pioneers of artificing, creating new inventions out of piles of metal parts and magical fuel. The most famous of which is the world renown artificer only known as \"Angel\". During the annual Magitechnician Fair held by the Riannon Institute of Alchemy in Mothergreen, a mysterious artifice arrived as an entry. It was a common Buster Weapon, but it was the intense modifications made to its efficiency that were the awe of all adventurers that laid eyes upon it. Despite winning the 1st prize at the fair, no one came to claim the prize... and had become known as the \"Angel-Type\" Buster Artifice—named after the pseudonym used by the crafter.\n\nOnce an artifice only used by fighters, the Angel-Type Buster Artifice started to spread amongst more defensively oriented users—often placed on daggers for quick, practical deployment. Despite the speculations as to Angel's identity, few suspected the creator was a local from their own town. Their inability to discover Angel's true identity was due to preconceived notions of who or what a renowned artificer should look like.\n\nIn reality, \"Angel\" was one of the early members of the Angel's Sword Guild—a notorious Adventurer's guild that created trouble wherever they went. But quietly hidden away in her workshop, surrounded by plush toys and scattered mechanical parts, Ayrara Ravness—a young Fae who appears no older than a ten-year old human crafts some of the most innovative artifices in Axia. She rarely takes commissions from outsiders, instead preferring to work exclusively with those whom her whims favor. In truth, more often than not, her workshop finds itself closed due to the insistence of her half-sister Elly, who continually drags her away on yet another adventure.","guide":"The magitechnician is an artisan class like the artificer.\n\nYour first ability and one of your main tools is the artificer's glove. From these options, sigma glove is the most commonly useful one in combat allowing you to use an artifice more than once per turn which can be powerful when combined with buster artifices. Gamma glove is a specialized glove that's good against other artifice users while Delta glove is a specialized, but big boost in a skill of your choosing. Because it's easy to swap, you could use it to give yourself a +10 bonus to stealth before a stealth mission.\n\nYour combat ability is your Secret Art: Entropic Magic Pulse. This EMP disables most temporary magic effects on top of disabling artifices. The disabling magic part is the main use of it, allowing you to remove effects like glittershards of walls whenever you want and make enemies vulnerable to your allies.\n\nOn the crafting side, expertise study is a simple 4 expertise points. Reverse Polarity reverses the roll, allowing you to turn a bad roll into a good one. If you save it for when you roll a 1 or a 2, it can give a massive boost to your crafting compared to keeping the roll.","keyAbility":"Advanced Artificing","abilities":["Craft Artificer's Glove","Reverse Polarity","Expertise Study (Artificing)","Secret Art: Entropic Magic Pulse"]},{"id":"maid","name":"Maid","tier":1,"role1":"Support","role2":"Utility","difficulty":1,"requirements":"None","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness, Cunning, Reason, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain 5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Stealth, Roguecraft, Medicine, Common Knowledge, Linguistics, Appraise, History, Perception, Insight, Survival or Intimidation. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The din of battle had finally faded, replaced with a sudden uneasy silence. Ronan wasted no time in rushing through the line of jagged thorns that had appeared at the beginning of the ambush, his sword arm heavy as he hacked his way through. Milla! He was too breathless to shout. I can't believe we left her like that!\n\nShe was just a maid they were escorting along a quiet route toward Mothergreen. No one could have predicted a fiend attack! The unsettling stillness made his blood chill, thinking of the polite girl mutilated in their absence. He finally punched through the thorn wall and stumbled to a stop. Balro stumbled as he bumped into him from behind, the salamander lancer equally stunned by the scene in front of him.\n\nAoife pushed him forward, her hands already pulling a faintly glowing healing potion from her pouch. \"What are you standing here for--\" The elf dropped the potion in shock.\n\nIn the clearing behind the thorn wall was Milla, her maid outfit pristine from her frilly hat to her \"it's shortened for mobility\" skirt. Whisps of Astra were fading from the remnants of three kratos corpses. She was quietly sweeping around one of the kratos, the Astra dissipating with each pass of her broom. But the most jarring image was the full tea set sitting on a moss covered stump. It was pristine, the small porcelain kettle steaming gently and was flanked by crisp, freshly made cookies. The tainted smell of Astra was rapidly being replaced by warm butterscotch and soothing tea. There was a small plate and teacup arrayed round the stump for each of them.\n\n\"I apologize for the delay in refreshments,\" Milla said with a small bow and a professional smile. Her eyes slid from the fully evaporating kratos corpse to the tea set and a blush started to fade into visibility on her cheeks. \"I&did have to use some of the fine silver. But you can be assured, I've thoroughly cleaned them!\"\n\nShe took a breath and her smile returned, the practiced nature of it softened by her blush. \"Take a moment to enjoy, the tea is at the perfect temperature. I'll be handling the clean up. Please, do not hesitate to call on me.\"\n\nRonan and the others found themselves enjoying tasty, freshly made cookies and tea while watching on with astonishment as Milla \"cleaned\" the battlefield. That included somehow sweeping the entire wall of thorns away with her broom and a feather duster.\n\nJust what was this maid?!","guide":"The maid is a support class that helps allies in and out of combat.\n\nYour primary tool for supporting in combat is Please Hold Still, which simply gives an ally a massive boost to their hit roll. Can also be prepared to be used before important attacks, though this leaves you vulnerable to RP movement actions or the target simply moving away.\n\nSnacks Time is your other tool that will likely see use in combat. In longer fights, giving all your allies a mana back can be valuable plus it's effectively free health potions for your party.\n\nAllow me to clean that is mostly for cleaning the floor and allowing your allies to move up safely. The movement is not a sidestep, so be aware of that. It can also be used to dust off allies to remove their negative effects.\n\nOvertime again lets you do certain IP actions more than once. If there's nothing to do with the IP, you can Rest and help your allies by giving them a bonus.","keyAbility":"Maid Training","abilities":["Allow me to clean that~","Please Hold Still~","Overtime again?","Snack Time Everyone!~"]},{"id":"marksman","name":"Marksman","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Ranger mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Power or Focus.","skills":"You gain 5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Stealth, Medicine, Perception, Survival, Animal Husbandry or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Marksman is a single-target ranged powerhouse. They rain heavy damage onto the enemy from afar and can be devastating if not stopped.","guide":"Marksman gain Status Assessment II, which in addition to showing HP also informs you of damage type strengths and weaknesses. Knowledge on what to use against enemies can be very important and this should be used frequently.\n\nBlast Away is a self peeling tool that knocks the enemy back on a failed save, letting you safely move away from the target afterwards.\n\nProne Cover is another form of defense that lets you drop prone as a reaction. It gives the prone keyword to your ranged attacks and basic reactions, so you aren't left completely vulnerable while on the floor. You will have to spend AP to stand up again if you need to move, so it's not something you want to always immediately use.\n\nConsistent Shot combined the accuracy of a precise attack with the damage of a heavy attack. Primarily used when you want a high chance of dealing good damage against a target that still has RP remaining.\n\nPerfect Shot can do a lot of damage, but is reliant on your teammates to keep enemies within your line of sight for long enough. If your target breaks line of sight, the ability is wasted. To keep your options the most open, it is best to start your perfect shot by spending 2 AP as the last action on your turn. Now if you can't finish it, you will have only wasted 2 AP instead of 4.","keyAbility":"Status Assessment II","abilities":["Blast Away","Prone Cover","Consistent Shot","Perfect Shot"]},{"id":"martial-artist","name":"Martial Artist","tier":1,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":1,"requirements":"None.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Perception, Insight, Medicine, Intimidation, Common Knowledge or a relevant Expert Knowledge skill (By DM approval). You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Martial Artists are fighters who’ve turned their bodies into finely tuned weapons. All across the world of Lyr, you can find them practicing different arts and styles. The true might of the Martial Artist is their mastery of Zaipher, the skill of tapping into their internal mana to heal themselves and deal devastating magic-enhanced blows.\n\nZaipher doesn't have the raw power of Arcane magic, but what it lacks in volume, it makes up for in blazing speed. Martial Artists utilize quick, sudden bursts of energy that can take an enemy by surprise.","guide":"Martial Artists are strikers with a simple standard combo. Leg Sweep is the combo starter. Being knocked prone is already bad normally, but especially so against a martial artist. You should expect most enemies to attempt to react to a leg sweep. If they don't, or if you hit anyway, you can follow up with a Rushing Knee Drop.\n\nRushing Knee Drop is guaranteed to hit and can be used with both AP and RP. The RP version is less efficient, but it can allow for a higher damage turn. Rushing Knee Drop can also be used when its not your turn, if an ally is able to render an opponent Prone. Because this is not on your turn, this version always costs an RP and can't be used with just an AP.\n\nThe final part of the combo is Double Punch. It is effectively a dual wield attack for unarmed users.\n\nTheir single non-damaging combat ability is Vital Drive. Vital Drive isn't very mana efficient, but it takes no action and you can potentially spend a lot of mana on it to heal for a large amount.\n\nUnarmed abilities only require a single free hand, so keeping an utility item in your offhand for quick use is possible.","keyAbility":"Martial Artist's Journey","abilities":["Leg Sweep","Vital Drive","Rushing Knee Drop","Double Punch"]},{"id":"master-armorer","name":"Master Armorer","tier":2,"role1":"Artisan","role2":"Defender","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Armorsmith mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Armorsmithing","description":"The sign hanging above the smithy's door was marked in the nonsensical scratchings that the Kiraran's called writing. Thankfully, a smaller sign hanging from the first displayed a carving of eastern armor set beside a hammer. There were no special adornments to the signs nor any of the colorful standing banners that stood outside the more famous guild shops. Charles was here chasing a rumor and had had to shake his guides to pursue. A non-affiliated armorsmith, almost unheard of in the cultural ethos of Kirara. With a last glance at the humble, undecorated exterior (sturdy construction, he grudgingly admitted), he slid open the door.\n\nA bell knocked gently against the top of the door as he pushed it along its runner, tinkling awkwardly. It wasn't at all like a more practical swinging door that would send a bell ringing clearly, the timbre just a little off. Heat washed over him as he stepped inside, flowing from a doorway only half covered in a split cloth screen. A large desk occupied a significant portion of the floor next to what he could only assume was the entrance to the attached forge, its proportions just a little too large to be comfortable for him to work at. Delicate etching tools, magical crystals, and large grinding bowls covered most of the desk with reams of paper taking up a tiny sliver of one side and the front half of a strangely shaped breastplate taking up the remaining space. Armor stands displayed stunning examples of the lamellar armor favored by Kiraran warriors, each a masterpiece in their own right (although he doubted their protective capabilities when compared to good, Westrian plate).\n\nCharles stepped fully into the shop and slid the door closed behind him, enduring that awkward bell jingle again. With the sound of the busy street muted, he could make out a low conversation drifting in from the forge over the quiet roar of a stoked fire. He waited a moment more before he determined the owner wouldn't have heard the bell and he'd have to wait for him to come back out to the front desk. But that would let him get a good look at the craftsmanship of the armor without bias.\n\nTwenty minutes later, he carefully set the elaborate helmet he'd been turning over back on its stand, irritation at being ignored for so long rising. He was half tempted to leave but he didn't know when else he'd be able to be free of his minders to visit again. He took several steps toward the fabric barrier of the forge door when a shadow loomed behind it. A hulking hand, grey as stone, parted the curtain and a massive&creature ducked through the doorway. A hand that could close into a fist the size of a cannon ball, arms as thick around as he was at the waist. Leg muscles straining against silk trousers with every movement, and a heavy, many pocketed leather apron to cover the wide expanse of chest. Charles had seen Oni before, but the one before him was the largest he'd ever even heard of.\n\nThe huge Oni blinked in surprise and said something in Kiraran back through the forge door, his voice like the rumble of a rockslide. A cheerful, high and clear voice called back, a woman's voice. Then a feminine roar of effort followed by the crash of a hammer on metal. The giant rumbled a chuckle and said something to him.\n\n\"Uh&sorry. I don't&\" A series of furious hammer impacts punctuated by more cute roars interrupted him.\n\n\"Ah. No problem,\" the huge Oni said, his accent heavy. He gestured toward the cluttered desk, which Charles obligingly moved to stand in front of. The Oni did something and suddenly the deafening sound of the crashing hammer vanished. The huge man then settled behind the desk and somehow made it look tiny and cramped.\n\n\"Welcome Mako Forge! What do for you?\"\n\nCharles cleared his throat and pulled out a small bundle of paper from inside his coat. \"Well, Mako, I have a requ--\"\n\n\"Ha! Me? Not Mako! Tate,\" the Oni pointed to himself with his thumb. \"Tate.\"\n\n\"Tate then,\" Charles returned. He almost wished he had his translators with him. \"I have a request and I heard your forge might be able to handle it.\" He held out the plans (well, more like rough ideas) for Tate and watched, fascinated, as the giant deftly flipped through them. He almost didn't notice that Tate had pulled on a pair of spectacles, making the giant of a man even more incongruous sitting behind the desk.\n\n\"Hmm.\" Charles could almost feel that hum through his feet, like a mountain was thinking. \"You want stop tepo. Yes?\"\n\n\"Uh&tehpuh?\"\n\nTate stared at him and then turned the plans around to tap a massive finger on the drawing of a musket.\n\n\"Tepo.\"\n\n\"Oh, a gun! Yes. I want the armor to stop&tehpuh.\"\n\n\"Hmm. Hmm.\" Tate flipped the pages pack to the first and set them down on top of a spread of tools. \"Can make. For you?\"\n\n\"Yes, for me. For proof, too.\"\n\n\"You want mahu?\" Tate preempted Charles's question by tapping a glass vial full of faintly glowing crystal shards. He wanted to know if he wanted the armor enchanted. \"No mahu more hard.\"\n\n\"Uh, no. No mah-hoo.\"\n\n\"Good. Good. Can make.\" Tate raised a massive fist and banged it on the wall behind him. He shouted something in Kiraran and it only took moments before the curtain parted again from the forge. Charles felt his mouth go dry and he tried not to stare. Never before had he seen a woman so&so proportioned! Her every boisterous movement as she nearly skipped to Tate seemed to be a test of her scant clothing to contain her and sent her braided red hair dancing. Her skin glistened with sweat from the forge, that perfect cream color that some Kiraran's seemed to possess naturally and would send women back home into conniptions of envy. His mind stalled and stuttered when Tate handed the voluptuous beauty his plans. If Tate was a giant then the woman before him was a pixie. If she was more than five feet tall, he'd eat his hat. And she looked even smaller contrasted to Tate's bulk even sitting at the desk.\n\nHe caught Tate's grin even as the man pulled the startled woman against him, bringing her to giggling. \"This Mako-chan, my wife,\" he said proudly. \"Best forge in Kirara.\"\n\nThe woman, Mako, chattered something scolding at Tate and peeled his grip off her like he had all the strength of a toddler. She flipped through the plans more slowly than her husband, shifting side to side as she made interested noises.\n\n\"Mahu nai-no?\" she asked.\n\n\"Hah,\" was Tate's reply.\n\nThat answer seemed to excite the woman and she turned to look up at Charles, eyes gleaming with anticipation. She gave him a thumbs up and tossed the plans back to Tate with an excited chatter of orders. Tate laughed and shooed her back to the forge. Charles stood in stunned silence with the laughing Oni for a long moment before the huge man said anything.\n\n\"Mako-chan very excited,\" he explained needlessly.\n\nCharles left Mako's Forge in a slight daze, light a good amount of gold, but with the promise of a set of non-magical nor artifice plate armor that could stop bullets. He was to pick it up in a week. But as strange as the couple was, he was certain the quality of the armor would be beyond reproach. Maybe they'd consider moving to Westria? They obviously didn't play Kiraran political games&","guide":"The master armorer is the continuation of the armorsmith that continues its role as a defender in combat. Like the armorsmith, you want to use as heavy armor as possible without compromising on your RP.\n\nArmor Up is an ability that gives temporary HP to yourself based on the block of your armor and shield. If you're using high block armor and shields, it becomes a very mana and AP efficient ability.\n\nSpiked Armor is an ability that lets you deal damage to your attacker, but it only works if enemies actually attack. It's best used when combined with a Challenge ability from another class, or if you're the only target someone can attack without moving. In that case, they have to choose between attacking you and dealing damage or wasting their turn.\n\nFor crafting, Grindstone Echo lets you copy a previous result. This makes it better the later you use, as you have more results to choose from. Even in a worst case scenario, you can steady craft and then copy the steady craft dice for a guaranteed number.","keyAbility":"Armorsmithing Expert","abilities":["Grindstone Echo","Armor Up","Expertise Study (Armorsmithing)","Spiked Armor"]},{"id":"mime","name":"Mime","tier":1,"role1":"Utility","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"None","heart":"You gain +1 to Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Art. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in this skill.","description":"Mary couldn't quite understand what she was seeing. Their caravan had been attacked by hobgoblins, which their guards had dutifully moved to engage. They were fighting among the trees, working together to root out the hobs and unfortunately fully engaged and unable to respond to the second group of hobs that had been waiting. Merchants and fathers had picked up brooms, rakes, and shovels. Anything to defend themselves with as they ushered the women and children behind them.\n\nBut it was the young man that had silently been riding along with them that stepped forward to confront the small group of hobs on his own. He gestured with a smile that he'd be perfectly okay and that everyone should stay back. Mary thought he must be a mage or a martial artist of some kind. And she was kind of right. Instead of calling down sparkling magic and fire or punching and kicking his way through the hobs he just&acted like he was pulling out&something. A gun? He behaved like he had a real gun in his hands, dramatically loading it. But&he didn't have anything in his hands.\n\nWas he crazy? Was it actually magic?\n\nEveryone was surprised when there was the loud crack of a gun going off and one of the hobs tumbled to the ground. The&mage -- he had to be a mage -- twirled his invisible gun and blew silently like he was blowing away smoke from the barrel of a real gun. He dramatically fell into a showy stance and three more gunshots rang out, dropping just as many hobs. The last one seemed to get over whatever strange magic this was and charged at the man.\n\nAgain, he reacted dramatically and silently, acting out dropping his invisible gun and putting his hands out in some attempt to stop the enraged hob. Everyone was as shocked as the hob was when it slammed into an invisible wall inches from the man's outstretched hands. Stunned by the sudden impact, the hob staggered backwards, giving the man time to do&what was he doing?\n\nHe was reaching over his shoulder like he was gripping the handle of something slung over his back. He hefted whatever it was like it weighed a lot and dramatically tilted as it dragged him sideways. A puff of dirt appeared as an indent was carved out of the ground by whatever it was. Acting like he was lifting something massive, the man silently wound up with a dramatic stance, one leg lifted. Then he brought his invisible weapon down, smashing the hob into the road in a sickening crack.\n\nWas that&a giant hammer? An invisible giant hammer?\n\nThe man rocked on his feet to regain his balance and made a show of wiping his brow and heaving a relieved sigh. Then he turned back to all of them and gave a cheerful thumbs up.\n\n\"What&the hell was that?\" Mary heard her dad mutter. She wanted to know too. She'd never heard of invisible magic like this!","guide":"The mime is a silly class that prevents you from speaking while using it. Making gestures is still fine!\n\nMost Mime abilities are Illusion abilities, which means you'll be weak to people with the Faerie Light Eyes. Your imaginary weapon just lets you quickly draw any weapon you want. Powerful early, though it remains a basic version with no mods or upgrades. Imaginary consumables is a similar ability that mimics a real thing, allowing you to spend a fair bit of mana for a powerful consumable effect. Things like flashbangs and smokeflasks are always good to mimic, though you'll still have to spend the AP to toss it as well.\n\nInvisible Wall is a small wall that gives a temporary big bonus. The size is small, but it's low AP cost and it costs no mana.\n\nFinally Dramatic Death is a way to get an enemy group to stop focusing you. If you use it while low on HP, you can also simply choose to remain playing dead and be safer.","keyAbility":"Mime's Journey","abilities":["Imaginary Weapon","Invisible Wall","Dramatic Death","Imaginary Consumables"]},{"id":"miner","name":"Miner","tier":1,"role1":"Gatherer","role2":"Striker","difficulty":2,"requirements":"None","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power or Toughness. In addition your Pickaxe proficiency gains: Superior Armor Pierce: Treats the enemy’s Guard as if it was 1 lower.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Mining. You also gain 5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Appraise or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The advent of the Adventurer and the use of internal magic began an age of heroes. Of feats great and small immortalized in legends and small tavern tales. But quietly, beyond the glory of heroes, the same power that let them set their names ablaze in history gave rise to something more modest. The crunch of a shovel slicing into the ground or the ring of the pickaxe against stone were not the sounds of heroes, but to the humble Miner, they represented greatness.\n\nUtilizing their own internal mana to augment their strength and precision, individual Miners were able to gather on a scale that used to take teams of a dozen or more to match. Be it stone for roads and castle walls or rare metals to be forged into legendary weapons, Miners represented the bedrock of architects and smiths the world over. While Mining Guilds obviously emerged to organize and regulate rich mining opportunities, solitary Miners were still common in villages and the frontiers of society. A single Miner with an abundant area to gather from could easily support an entire town’s needs for stone and metal.\n\nAnd while it was common for Miners to have hired protectors, especially within the guilds, it was a foolish attacker that believed them to be easy targets. That same power and precision that allowed a Miner to shatter rock with ease and peel raw ore from the earth was just as easily turned toward their defense. It was a foolish bandit or adventurer that underestimated the rending power of a Miner’s pickaxe.","guide":"Miner is a gatherer and striker class that functions like an anti-tank character in combat. Rock Fang reduces the target's guard by 2, which can be massive boost in damage even against non-tanks. Especially if you have allies that are dual wielding. It's best used against elites, as grunts will most likely die too fast for the debuff to matter.\n\nExcavation Crash is best used when an enemy is surrounded by your allies. The enemy may choose to move to avoid your Heavy attack, but doing so DOES provoke attacks of opportunity from your allies which might result in it taking even more damage.\n\nFor gathering, Power Rock Strike is a great opener especially once you get more points in mining. Efficient strike can be to ensure you don't waste any points on your node point total and can get the maximum lucky value. It's best to use this as late as possible, in case you still need to use abilities that may drain your node points.","keyAbility":"Rock and Stone","abilities":["Power Rock Strike","Excavation Crash","Efficient Strike","Rock Fang"]},{"id":"mist-veil-elegy","name":"Mist Veil Elegy","tier":2,"role1":"Controller","role2":"Striker","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Idol or Bard mastered or 10 points in Art (Flute) expertise and any class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Art. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The vale stretched far below, a green hollow wrapped in morning fog. From the ridge, the Songstress raised her flute and pressed her lips to the reed. A single note slipped into the air and the mist stirred in answer.\n\nIt flowed like a tide, rolling down the slope until the travelers below found themselves swallowed by a pale shroud. At first they moved with confidence, torches and laughter breaking the veil, but soon their steps slowed. Their voices faltered. The mist thickened around them, drinking their warmth, their strength, their very breath.\n\nA dissonant chord thrummed through the haze, and the travelers stumbled as one. The mist struck in unison with the note, and bodies crumpled soundlessly into the grass. The fog grew denser, heavier, a chorus swelling unseen within its folds.\n\n\"Why do you play?\" A familiar voice whispered in the wind.\n\nThe flute rose again. A mournful melody spilled into the air: A pair of shackles hanging from the wall / A candle guttering in the dark, its flame shrinking / a lone tree shedding its last leaves / a vast tide rising, unstoppable / The endless horizon and silence beyond it.\n\nThat was her answer.","guide":"-","keyAbility":"Song without Song","abilities":["Mist of the Vale","Phantoms of the Mist","Despair of Isolation","Traveler's End"]},{"id":"monk","name":"Monk","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Cultivator or Martial Artist mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 Focus, Power or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Perception, Insight, Medicine, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Monks are graceful fighters in tune with their inner self.","guide":"Monks are dodge experts with some access to ranged attacks. Ki Blast is a simple ranged attack, being notable for its ability to be used without a weapon and for dealing arcane damage. Many martial artists lack ways to deal non-physical damage and Ki Blast is a good option against enemies that are strong against physical damage.\n\nFlowing Kick becomes an AP efficient move if used after an attack misses. If you missed an attack previously, there's little reason not to follow it with a Flowing Kick.\n\nSerene Water Stance is the core of the monk. Entering it isn't very hard, but making full use of it isn't easy. It gives you some extra evasion, but you cannot move normally while in this stance. This means you have little to catch up to an enemy and forced to spam Ki Blast instead. Because of the mana cost, you also have to make a conscious choice whether to enter it or not.\n\nIf you do enter the stance and are able to stay in range of the enemy, you can use Strike of Still Water. With a Sure Hit and Full pierce attack for just 1 mana, it is incredibly powerful. If you are able to use it, do so.","keyAbility":"Empty Body","abilities":["Ki Blast","Flowing Kick","Serene Water Stance","Strike of Still Water"]},{"id":"mycomancer","name":"Mycomancer","tier":2,"role1":"Healer","role2":"Striker","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Mage mastered or Earth Mastery","heart":"You gain +1 to Awareness or Cunning.","soul":"You gain +1 to Power or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Medicine, Magic or Survival. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Mycomancers are powerful mages that harness the power of fungi to heal allies and destroy enemies. They try to understand death through mycology.","guide":"Mycomancers are a unique healer that relies on dealing damage to heal their allies. The only target they can heal is their Spore Symbiote.\n\nOnce it is placed, you can use Saprophytic Bolt to heal your target. Grunts may react to it even if its a light attack, so burning their RP first may be advised so you don't waste it.\n\nDestroying Angel is a bigger heal and also comes with the benefit of instantly killing the target when used against grunts. It is not worth using against non-grunts however.\n\nPoison Spore is the last ability that can center around the spore symbiote. It can be used as a zoning tool of sorts, but be aware that your allies are not immune to the poison. One of the better uses is placing it around yourself or the symbiote if they are a more vulnerable target and using the spore as a deterrent to any assassin type enemies that might threaten the backline.\n\nAmoxicillin is a simple disease removal spell. The cast time makes it unusable in battle and you are required to identify the disease first, but it's a free removal once you do.\n\nAs a mycomancer, it is recommended you heal early rather than late. Your healing can be unreliable and you don't want your allies to drop low, only for you to miss a crucial a heal and watch them go down.","keyAbility":"Spore Symbiote","abilities":["Saprophytic Bolt","Poison Spore","Amoxicillin","Destroying Angel"]},{"id":"mystic-eyes-of-destruction","name":"Mystic Eyes of Destruction","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Evil Eye mastered or Oni plus any tier 2 mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Appraise, Perception, Insight, Medicine, Magic or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The deck rocked beneath me and storm clouds writhed above. Rain splattered against my skin as I lay on my back, limbs tingling with phantom shocks of pain dancing through me. Memories of a similar moment came over me, of me looking up in confusion at my parents for the first time, their huge blue faces alight with wonder. Papa and Tousan. Ostracized by the village for loving each other, for bringing life to a doll like me. Like everyone in the village, they were meant to take on Oni wives so they could have more Oni children that would continue the lineage of mystic eyes our village was known for. To keep the supply of warriors coming, to feed the constant wars between other lords that used our warriors as mercenaries.\n\nA muffled roar cut through the crashing waves and rain. Briefly, the rain stopped as a shadow flew overhead, then it returned in a deluge. The ship shuddered and people cried out in panic. I pushed myself to my feet with the help of a railing, the sea alarmingly close as the ship plunged down the back of a wave.\n\n\"Honoka!\" An Oni woman stumbled toward me, holding a bow with a snapped string. \"Thank the gods you weren't thrown over!\"\n\nI gripped the woman's shoulder to steady her. \"I'm okay! How's the rest of the fleet?\"\n\nShe shook her head, tears mingling with the rain running down her face. \"They're gone, Honoka! That damned dragon sank them all! We're only still here because of Masahiro's barrier and it's failing!\"\n\nGone. Papa. Tousan. Everyone left from our village that had managed to escape the forces that wanted to wipe us out. My grip on the railing tightened, my delicate looking, porcelain skin splintering the wood with frightening ease. And with the failing barrier, we would be next. How was it possible the Ryujin had something this powerful? Dragons were a myth, a legend. There shouldn't be one crushing our armies or sinking our fleet. It didn't matter, it was here and it was killing us. Killing my family. My eyes burned, the technique that I had painstakingly learned flaring to life. The pride of our village.\n\nEyes of Destruction.\n\nOur warriors were infamous for being able to cut down men from dozens of paces with just a glare or destroy anything we settled our gaze on. It was why we were in demand. And it was why we were being destroyed.\n\nThe dragon descended, a flying mountain of scales and rage. A flare of light erupted from its maw and shattered our barrier and it dove toward our helpless ship, to crush us. Then something impossible happened. We weren't crushed and thrown into the sea at the mercy of the storm. The dragon shrank, collapsing into a man, a Ryujin in pristine armor. He started speaking, denouncing our family. Our clan. That our destruction was the will of the Emperor.\n\nHe was good with a sword, his katana flashing as he cut down the battered crew and disoriented fighters. He gleamed, honey gold light flaring around him like a sunrise. I met him in the middle of the ship and his surprise let me deflect away the killing blow on a young boy, not even an apprentice.\n\n\"A doll?\"\n\n\"I am a Tokiha warrior.\"\n\nHe seemed startled to see the gleaming crimson of my eyes. He took a step back, suddenly less confident in his reduced state. He seemed to be regretting not just destroying the ship while he was a dragon. The golden light around him flared brighter and I could see the shadow of a dragon looming behind him. My eyes shone and then the world briefly lost all color. And Void claimed his transformation. He staggered in shock and barely deflected away my sword. But he couldn't deflect my gaze. My eyes shone and he choked, his throat cut by an invisible blade. I cut his head off, just to be sure, and kicked his body overboard.\n\nBut the damage was done. With so little crew left, with so much damage, we couldn't weather the storm. We fought just as hard against any enemy, but it was futile. And I had to watch as my friends, my family, sank and drowned. And as I stared up at the swirling storm clouds, I let myself sink beneath the waves, hoping that the crushing depths would let me join my family in death.","guide":"Perish is a simple attacking ability that lets you make basic attacks with your eyes.\n\nDestroy forces the target to make a save or take heavy damage. It is powerful against enemies with low toughness, functioning similar to how a Sure Hit attack might. Doom may amplify this damage further, adding another Light damage on top of the damage with another failed save.\n\nUnmake is situational, but it's a powerful tool for destroying walls or even dropped items.\n\nYour secret art: Void, is a one time removal of basically any effect on a target. Notable uses can be removing temporary HP from an enemy, removing elemental strengths or temporary damage reductions.","keyAbility":"Look of Death","abilities":["Destroy","Unmake","Doom","Secret Art: Void"]},{"id":"mystic-eyes-of-domination","name":"Mystic Eyes of Domination","tier":3,"role1":"Controller","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Evil Eye mastered or Demon plus any tier 2 mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Perception, Insight, Magic, Negotiation, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"\"Send the next one in, please.\"\n\nArrio Wi Vanian looked down and checked the profile pinned to his clipboard as the insensate volunteer was carried out by a pair of stoic nurses. He marked the check boxes appropriately for a full circuit collapse and spirit core regression and then signed it. Another failure. Catastrophic, this time. He hesitated a moment and then also checked the box for supplementary aid to be given to the boy's family. It would probably take him decades to recover the use of his circuits and become a productive member of society again.\n\nHe moved over to the small desk and began organizing his paperwork like he did after every new volunteer left the testing room. He found his gaze lingering on a frustrating report, eyes scanning over the most important parts.\n\n&discovered in a low Lu clan, it appears to be a spontaneous manifestation of similar progress to our own efforts&\n\n&fully stable and functioning. It's clear it does not match the Lir Aseria in potency or breadth but it demonstrates that the bloodline that housed such a potent Eye still lingers in the population, if diluted. Code Name: Domination.\n\n&could not secure the cooperation of Cora Lu Milinen as she has relocated to Axias. Please authorize an Acquisition.\n\nOf course, no Acquisition was authorized. The heads of Wi Vanian did not want to aggravate any adventuring guilds based out of Mothergreen, even one as small and new as the Silver Wings. They were barely even monitoring the girl, for Kari's sake. And of course, none of the girl's family showed any signs of manifesting an Eye or even matching circuit or spirit core readings to indicate they ever would. Frustrating.\n\nThe door to the room opened quietly on smooth hinges and a nurse shuffled in, more paperwork in her hands. \"Doctor, your next patient,\" she said, hands steady as a member of Un ought to be. He took them with a nod and clipped them to his board, eyes already scanning them.\n\n\"Thank you, send them in.\"\n\nTwo more nurses and a nervous young woman entered the room. The nurses directed her to sit on the examination bed and then waited patiently off to the side. If the initial exam went well, they would be the test targets of this girl's Eye.\n\n\"Miss&\" Arrio checked the paperwork, a slight frown touching the corner of his lips. Not a member of a high Family. \"Miss Cutilia, thank you for participating in this study. Please follow my instructions to the best of your ability.\"\n\nThe girl nodded and he began his examination with careful study of her circuits, her spirit core, and her eyes. She did possess these new \"Eyes of Domination\", as evidence of the swirling sigils that snapped into existence when she channeled mana to her eyes. But it was a far cry from the sheer presence of Lir Aseria. It had been over thirty years since those fools and those greater fools that had followed them had tried their rebellion. Thirty years since the last holder of the Eyes of Command had been killed -- by the clan head Endo himself no less! The fool! And he'd lost control of his daughter as well! The last dregs of Lir Aseria blood they'd had control over and he'd let her fall in with those thrice damned adventurers!\n\nAnd now&now they couldn't touch her. The Angel's Sword Guild may be young but they had gathered power to themselves in amounts that couldn't be easily countered. One day, they'd make a mistake and Wi Vanian would be ready.\n\nBut for now&he forced a friendly, professional smile to his face.\n\n\"Well done, Miss Cutilia. You've taken the treatment well and your circuits are stable. Next, we'll run some tests of your capabilities. The nurses will assist you with that.\"\n\nAs Miss Cutilia began to express her power, tentatively calling out commands to the nurses in turn, he dutifully recorded the results. They were well within the standards of Domination, only a handful of seconds or a few minutes of influence before the mana unravelled. If only they hadn't lost their one success. What they'd done back then was impossible now, the recovered Lir Aseria Eyes from the rebellion were too far degraded for implantation. They still had use for making the infusions that helped their test subjects develop Domination, but&he could still remember the subtle shiver of power from that girl, one eye gleaming with that Lir Aseria golden glow. But they'd lost her, too.\n\nShe'd just vanished in the night from a secure room in the most secure facility Wi Vanian operated. No guards could remember anything, no sensors were tripped, and the recording orbs just showed one moment where their pride and joy was safe in bed and the next an empty, otherwise undisturbed room. Records of her spirit core readings, the successful implantation reports, the unique alchemical mixtures used&all of it was gone. Erased from secure rooms and artifice recorders like they'd never been. Only their memories of what they'd had remained.\n\nHe shook himself from his sour thoughts and offered Miss Cutilia a smile, the girl gasping in air and sweating from the amount of mana she'd had to channel. \"Thank you for your assistance, Miss Cutilia. Please follow the nurses back to your room.\"\n\nHe turned his attention to the nurses. \"And send in the next, please.\"","guide":"The mystic eyes of domination are a powerful controller class.\n\nAuthority is a simple key ability that boosts your ability to influence people using your negotiation and intimidation skills.\n\nCharm just charms a single enemy. Useful if you don't want to be the one targeted by a boss.\n\nKneel is a 1 for 1 AP trade, assuming they fail the save. Good against single enemies or heroics with low toughness. Decree can force an enemy either closer to put them out of position for the rest of your team, or you can force an enemy off you without moving yourself.\n\nForbid is a secret art that is quite costly mana wise, but can force bad actions on an enemy for 1 round. Bosses are the easiest to predict, though the damage on them maybe less significant. Against heroic enemies, you'll want a good read on their abilities before you use it. Though even denying abilities for a turn on a support or healer (by making them take a lot of damage) can be quite valuable.","keyAbility":"Authority","abilities":["Charm","Kneel","Decree","Secret Art: Forbid"]},{"id":"necromancer","name":"Necromancer","tier":2,"role1":"Specialist","role2":"Striker","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Any class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning, Reason or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Necromancers manipulate the dead. Feared and hated by most people, and often justifiably so.","guide":"Necromancers are a special class that has a focus on raising undead to fight for them. These undead, zombies or skeletons, are not strong by themselves but can be a threat once they gather. The undead they raise do not stay after an arc is finished. This means that necromancer starts an arc of weak until they find an opportunity to raise some.\n\nThe undead group themselves can be used in multiple ways. They add free damage while they are alive, so keeping them that way is good. At the same time, they can also be used as disposable creatures that can be used to hold off a powerful enemy to buy yourself team to heal or retreat. They are also pretty hard to fully kill off, but keep them away from multi-hit attacks and AoE holy damage.\n\nRaise Undead can be used either during combat to get a group going, or you can chain cast it once a combat is over. Soulreap combines the raising of the undead with a heavy attack, allowing you to build up your forces without wasting AP or letting you get two active in 1 turn, provided there's already a corpse somewhere.\n\nCorpse Explosion uses your raised undead as a resource. It is a powerful aoe for the cost which can be further empowered by using more corpses. This trades long term fight potential for a quick gain and it may not be worth blowing too many zombies on if you can't restock afterwards.\n\nCorpse Domination lets you raise an enemy you killed to help you in the fight. It's not worth using unless it's on a heroic target, but adding another body to the battlefield on your side can swing the battle in your favor. It's powerful in fights against multiple heroic enemies.\n\nSpeak with dead is an out of combat utility ability. The usefulness on it depends heavily on the situation, as well as the GM.\n\nOne last thing to keep in mind as a necromancer player is that most people are not fond of zombies and skeletons. If you stroll into town with a small undead army behind you, don't expect a warm welcome in most places.","keyAbility":"Raise Undead","abilities":["Soulreap","Speak with dead","Corpse Explosion","Bring out your dead"]},{"id":"necromaster","name":"Necromaster","tier":3,"role1":"Specialist","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Necromancer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning, Reason or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"\"And then the Headmaster -- wait&wasn't it Headmistress? No no, that stinky old man was definitely the Headmaster! He had that huge beard&yeah! -- where was I? Oh yeah, then the Headmaster showed up and my beloved Jean Claude--\"\n\nEleri pricked her finger with her needle as she jumped in surprise (she did not let out a surprised \"Nya!\" and no one would be able to prove it!). A skeleton with a permanent skewed grin had dropped a random assortment of old, mostly ruined clothing next to her. It clattered away and Eleri let out a sigh of relief, absently smoothing her poofed up tail while absently sucking on the finger she'd accidentally stabbed. With her focus striped from her frantic sewing, she took the time to take stock of the others.\n\nYuzuki was off to one side going through choreography with a skeleton dressed in a tattered wizard's robe complete with glued on white beard and a huge, wide brimmed conical hat. Her katana was still sheathed at her side as she made exaggerated practice swings at the skeleton with a vaguely sword shaped stick. Her puffy tanuki tail was stiff with her concentration and worry and her cute little round ears were focused forward.\n\nCelyn was nervously looking around as she scribbled in her journal. As she watched, Celyn scribbled out whatever it was she was writing and started again. The lyrics to the song that was demanded didn't seem to be going well. Eleri wanted to get up and comfort the poor girl&and not just because Celyn had the softest, fluffiest hugs that Eleri absolutely did not fake twisted ankles to get bed time cuddles with.\n\nKatsuro was currently the focus of their host's ire. Kathelyne the Necromancer, stomping her feet like the child she looked like, was berating him about&a tree?\n\n\"It's supposed to be a cherry tree! With the pink flowers! Not a sad willow! PAY ATTENTION NEXT TIME!\"\n\nThe kitsune was apologizing about the mistake before he darted away, looking for anything that might let him make pink cherry blossoms. That wasn't the first time Kathelyne had gotten on them about details. Details she hadn't included in her story at all! Eleri hadn't deserved to have that freaky giant skeleton monster looming over her while the necromancer berated her about getting the Riannon Institute uniforms wrong! How was she supposed to know what some Mothergreen school uniform looked like?!\n\nHer gaze finally drifted over to Laurent and she couldn't help but let her eyes linger. He'd taken off his shirt and armor sometime while she had been sewing and the dappled sunlight coming through the canopy above was making him practically glisten. He was using Katsuro's axes and hatchets to roughly build out the stage and he'd been doing a lot of heavy lifting. Technically, he was supposed to be in the big fight at the end of the play too, but their paladin was the only one strong enough to lift those heavy logs and boards.\n\nAnother pile of discarded clothes (she didn't want to think too hard about it, but they were probably from adventurers who had died to this maniac!) landed next to her as another skeleton clattered up to her. This one&gave her the shivers as the thing turned around, as the tail of what once was a lamia moved in a slithering motion&but the rib bones acted like little millipede legs. With one last shiver, Eleri got back to work. She had to finish the uniforms so they could get out of here. And the only way out was to perform Kathlyne's very creatively titled: \"The Stupid Riannon Institute Expelled Me For Making Cute Friends And I Hate Them!\"","guide":"The necromaster continues from the necromancer and sorta does what necromancer already does, but better.\n\nUndead mastery just lets you control more zombies, allowing for scaling as you grow in power.\n\nRaise Undead II is a longer range and cheaper version of Raise Undead making it more usable in combat. It also lets you build up zombies even when not fighting humanoids at the cost of (a lot of) mana.\n\nThanergetic Bloom is a mostly free zombie per turn, allowing you to always have at least 1 of them out for your other abilities such as corpse explosion or command undead.\n\nCommand Undead is a simple 1 AP transfer to your summon. Very useful when you have to move your zombies and still want them to spend 2 AP to attack.\n\nSecret Art: Skeletal Champion lets you summon a big summon that will likely hit harder than you or your zombies. It does remove all your zombies due to the summon limit and while it gets some temporary HP for it, it may be worth not using it if you have a large stack built up. The overcharge is expensive, but it may be worth it if you don't spend a lot of mana.","keyAbility":"Undead Mastery","abilities":["Raise Undead II","Thanergetic Bloom","Command Undead","Secret Art: Skeletal Champion"]},{"id":"ninja","name":"Ninja","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Rogue mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Cunning.","soul":"You gain +1 Focus or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Stealth, Deception, Roguecraft, Perception, Insight, Negotiation, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Kiraran rogues who use a mix of physical prowess and magical arts to slay their enemies in the darkness.","guide":"The ninja is a slippery ranged class that uses throwing weapons.\n\nTheir first ranged option is the Kibaku Fuda Shuriken. It's a fairly AP efficient attack, even if used against just a single target, but it is of course ideally tossed into a group of enemies.\n\nThe Kage Shuriken no Jutsu is used against single targets. Unless they target chooses to block the first one, you are guaranteed that at least one of the attacks hits, making it good against dodgy targets.\n\nA lot of power of the ninja comes from their Bunshin Tai no Jutsu. It creates a copy that shares everything with the original body. It can be used in many different ways. For example, you can use the body double to threaten enemy ranged attackers. You don't need to worry about overextending too much. If the enemy decides to retreat and collapse on you, you can simply dismiss the copy and escape from harm. You can also use it to flank enemies and hit them from where cover won't protect them. The important here to keep in mind that is that you are never overextended with a clone. If you feel you are in danger, simply dismiss it.\n\nAnother powerful defensive tool Ninjas have is Kawarimi no Jutsu. The RP cost is higher than normal, but it protects even against sure hit attacks and because you can hide and move, you are also safe from any future follow up attacks.","keyAbility":"Ninja Style","abilities":["Kibaku Fuda Shuriken","Kawarimi no Jutsu","Bunshin Tai no Jutsu","Kage Shuriken no Jutsu"]},{"id":"nomad","name":"Nomad","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Support","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Cavalier mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Animal Husbandry, Riding, Flight, Intimidation, Perception, Insight or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"It was difficult to pin down the origins of anything throughout history. Plenty of ideas and methods were known to crop up simultaneously among completely isolated groups by simple happenstance. However, it was largely accepted that the idea of modern cavalry began with the arrival of nomadic human tribes from the north east of Lyr. Masters of their stocky, resilient horses, they migrated south west out of the tundra and steppe due to extremely harsh seasons and famine. Forced to avoid the forests of Easter to the south and pushed away from the budding kingdoms in Northi to the west, the nomadic humans settled in the lush plains of Axia and Nuren. Their art of mounted archery gave them unparalleled hunting abilities and made them maddeningly difficult to chase down, even from the fleet footed catfolk and rabbitfolk.\n\nFor a time, the Nomads roamed plains, breeding ever stronger horses and leading a relatively simple life. They didn’t know that their presence forced the kingdoms of Northi to push their influence west into Susururu Forest, displacing wolf-folk and lamiafolk, and to the selkies of Houkaina on the coast. But eventually, with nowhere to continue expanding aside from the frigid north, Northi returned its attention to the plains. Utilizing enslaved centaurs as mounts, the catfolk hoped to narrow the mobility gap and to be able to finally hunt down the annoying humans. But without any static settlements and their mastery of the plains, the Nomads were still able to control the pace of any battles or hunts.\n\nSimultaneous to the more concentrated efforts from Northi, humans from Westria began to treat with the nomadic tribes of the Nuren Plains. They traded for horses, for trainers, and offered riches beyond the nomadic tribes’ wildest dreams for empty land. Northi wasn’t alone in dreaming of securing the plains for their potential wealth of farmland, but the humans from the south recognized that the Nomads had completely stalled chimeran expansion with their mastery of horses and Westria had long been praying for something that would let them protect themselves from the chimera and fae. Humans had a long history of domesticating animals to help balance the strengths of their neighbors: dogs for hunting, oxen for burden…the introduction of horses was simply another method to overcome their weaknesses.\n\nWith a combination of various deals with the nomads and utilizing their own methods against them, Westria was finally able to push its borders to the edge of the forest and the Nuren River. Their actions unfortunately displaced or eradicated tribes of nomads that resisted the territorial grab. Some historians believe that ancient, bad blood was one of the larger factors for the rise of independent nations along Westria’s north eastern border. Many humans from the plains regions could still claim ancestors from those nomadic tribes and while there was no official animosity, some were convinced there was an overarching reason they had carved out their independence from both Northi and Westria.","guide":"The nomad is a ranged cavalry class that can be nearly impossible to catch.\n\nAs a nomad, you excel in fights where you have a lot of space to run around it. Your light cavalry key ability makes you able to fight at maximum potential even in terrain that would normally be unfavorable for you, allowing you to keep your full mobility.\n\nHit & Run is an ability that can either be used with a melee or ranged weapon. With a melee weapon, it does provoke an attack but it lets you move away from the enemy while dealing damage. With a ranged weapon it allows an essentialy free reposition and enables you to keep your distance from the enemy. It also allows you to use Running Shot.\n\nRuning Shot is a 1 RP cost ability that lets you make a Heavy attack. It does require you to move before you can use it, but Nomad has several ways of doing that. The RP cost is normally a big risk for a character to spend on offensive abilities, but as a nomad you have enough mobility and range that you can afford to spend some of it on doing more damage.\n\nTrailblazer is an utility ability that helps your allies get across difficult terrain. It can also be used to help them get into the fray faster, though it does cost them some RP.\n\nYour Secret Art: Chase the Horizon is the ultimate kiting tool against a single enemy. It has a steep mana cost for the duration, but it ensures the target you pick cannot catch you while its active and you can punish them if they do move. It's best used when kiting a boss or when a melee enemy is far away from anything to attack. If they are forced to spend 4 AP on movement to do anything, then you get 4 attacks which is not bad for the cost.","keyAbility":"Light Cavalry","abilities":["Hit & Run","Running Shot","Trailblazer","Secret Art: Chase the Horizon"]},{"id":"onmyoji-","name":"Onmyoji","tier":2,"role1":"Specialist","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Any class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Appraise, Medicine, Religion, Magic Perception, Insight, Art or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Scribes who use magic paper and ink to create magic talismans imbued with spells.","guide":"The Onmyoji is a utility class that focuses on using talismans, scrolls or similar items. They can either create their own or use those created by others. Buying talismans from others is an excellent way to increase your versatility in combat or plug the gaps in your party composition.\n\nCreate Talisman lets you make your own talismans. This lets you potentially cast a spell twice per turn and the key ability lets you use your talisman at a -1 AP cost. You can also trade these talismans to other players, allowing them to benefit for spells they would normally be unable to use.\n\nSecret Talisman is an ability that just lets you use a Secret Art that's on a talisman. Secret Arts are normally limited to once per encounter, so being able to use two can be quite the power boost.\n\nSealing Talisman is a powerful CC, but it comes at the cost of having to prepare the talisman beforehand. Grunts have little counterplay against it, but even against heroics you can force them to waste quite a bit of AP for no AP cost of your own.\n\nPreparedness gives you a bit more flexibility and options in what you can bring. Overall, Onmyoji is very reliant on either outside sources of talismans or in having strong classes to complement it to really shine. It is not recommended to take the class without taking some other classes beforehand or having a clear goal in mind.","keyAbility":"Expert Scribe","abilities":["Create Talisman","Preparedness","Sealing Talisman","Secret Talisman"]},{"id":"oracle","name":"Oracle","tier":2,"role1":"Support","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Appraise, History, Magic, Insight, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Mysterious people that work on the edge of Magic and Divinity, utilizing enigmatic powers to see the future whether by instinct or divine intervention.","guide":"-","keyAbility":"Receive Oracle","abilities":["Scry","Foretell","Prediction","Secret Art: Gate of Fate"]},{"id":"peltast","name":"Peltast","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any class mastered. Proficiency in throwing weapons.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Riding, Intimidation, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"A specialist in using throwing weapons.","guide":"The peltast makes throwing weapons a valid choice for a main weapon. The boomerang key ability makes it so you no longer have to keep paying AP to draw more weapons. The peltast ideally wants to play close to the enemy and isn't afraid of melee combat.\n\nLong Toss gives you a long range option. The range of throwing weapons is normally a bit low, so this can be used when you would be out of range to attack normally.\n\nRappelling Dagger is a movement option that can also deal damage. Useful when you have to engage an enemy that's not too far away and it can be used to obtain high ground by rappelling into a tree or on top of a building.\n\nFan of Knives is a point blank AoE that can be used even when engaged in melee. It will require you to get close to the enemy before you can use it.\n\nStab & Throw is an AP efficient attack that requires you to be in melee, plus to have another enemy nearby.","keyAbility":"Boomerang","abilities":["Long Toss","Fan of Knives","Rappelling Dagger","Stab & Throw"]},{"id":"phantom-thief","name":"Phantom Thief","tier":3,"role1":"Utility","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Thief mastered and mage mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness or Cunning.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Appraise, Athletics, Stealth, Deception, Roguecraft, Perception, Insight, Negotiation, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"\"Why is the hardest part of the heist always climbing?\" Jack grumbled as he pulled himself up another few feet, fingers finding the barest of purchase in the seams between the stones that made up the wall he was climbing. He paused, head tilting and then shaking with an exasperated sigh. Another detection field. The TENTH ONE. With little effort, he reached out with one hand and flicked his fingers against the magical threads of the bounded field, his own magical energy seeping seamlessly into the web of detection. Moments later, he passed right through it like a ghost, just like all of the others.\n\n\"I knew Merlin Academy was said to be well protected but this is just ridiculous.\" He swung himself up to a closed window, high up the tower he'd been scaling. If his intel was right, he just needed to unlock this window, bypass the detection ward, and he'd be just down the hall from his target. Neither the ward or lock gave him much trouble and he was inside a well kept classroom. Stadium seating style with large desks and benches running the length of each level. Nice open space front and center for whatever magic practice they did in this particular class.\n\nJack gave an impressed whistle as he crossed the room. No wonder Northi mages trained at Merlin were so annoying; they were well trained AND snobby aristocrats. He'd never had a classroom half as good during his studies.\n\nStill shaking his head at it all, he slipped into the hall. Look left, look right, look left again because that always bit him in the ass if he didn't and he was clear. He took a right from the classroom and was slipping into the target room within a minute. Still no alarms, guards, or inconveniently appearing students. Just him and the manuscript perched oh so nicely on a stand in the middle of the room.\n\nJack rolled his eyes to the mage hiding under an invisibility spell to his left. \"Man, that's a pretty obvious trap you know?\" he told the man. The mage startled in surprise and his spell shattered, motes of magic dripping off him like rain.\n\n\"What--how did--\" the mage cleared his throat and straightened his shoulders before marching resolutely between Jack and his prize. \"You certainly live up to your reputation, Mister Harlequin.\"\n\nJack smiled but obviously the man couldn't see that through his mask. \"Please, call me Diamond. Harlequin makes me feel like my old man.\"\n\nThe mage scoffed, his little kitty ears flatting with his irritation, and raised his hands, fingers splayed and magic gathering. \"It doesn't matter what you call yourself, you're not leaving here and you're certainly not touching that manuscript. The alarm is already sounded, you'll not be escaping the entirety of Merlin Academy's staff.\"\n\nJack didn't have the heart to tell him the alarm had, in fact, not sounded. He was holding the activation thread coiled around his pinky, after all.\n\n\"Look, you don't have to go through all this trouble. Just let me have that bit of paper and I won't have to embarrass you. Okay?\"\n\nThe mage flicked his fingers and in a sharp voice said, \"Cyrin!\"\n\nAn anemic yellow bolt of magic crossed the distance between them in an eyeblink&and splattered against the door behind him ineffectually. With a smirk tugging his lips, he ran his hand through the wake of the spell, gathering the echo of it and reconstructing it in the space of a breath.\n\n\"Cyrin!\" he echoed mockingly. His copied spell hit the mage dead in the chest and expanded, wrapping around him like magical ropes. It even made a magical blindfold and gag. Nasty spell for a mage to get hit by. Jack gingerly stepped over the bound and struggling mage, hands snagging and redirecting the threads of even more barriers and wards around the manuscript. With a final snipping motion for the sticking ward on the bundle of papers itself, he plucked it from its stand. A brief flip through revealed a dizzying array of mechanical and magical information and the confusing combination of it all to make some sort of armatae.\n\nExactly like the customer said. Perfect. He was about to make his client in Dacquoise very happy. As he stepped back over the mage, he dropped his marker. At first glance, it looked like a playing card but the white face of it only had a depiction of his mask.\n\n\"Well, it was fun, but I won't be seeing you. But feel free to tell everyone about Diamond Harlequin, would you?\"","guide":"Soon.","keyAbility":"Phantom Thief","abilities":["Stolen Power","Duplicate","Grand Theft Horse","Steal Heart"]},{"id":"phosphomancer","name":"Phosphomancer","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Support","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any class mastered or Holy mastery.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Religion, Art Magic, History, Appraise, Negotiation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"By CCeles.","guide":"-","keyAbility":"Benevolence","abilities":["Brilliance","Gleaming Cut","Illuminating Flash","Crucified by Radiance"]},{"id":"pierrot","name":"Pierrot","tier":1,"role1":"Controller","role2":"Support","difficulty":2,"requirements":"None","heart":"You gain +1 to Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Agility or Toughness","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Art. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in this skill.","description":"Laughter and cheers filled the air. Animals roared to the delight of a crowd under a massive tent, likely prancing in a circle with mock fierceness. His family was in one of those tents, enjoying the entertainment of the circus. Owen had only left to find a snack, to replace the one someone had accidentally knocked out of his hands. He had a pocket full of clim that clinked as he walked and that had drawn attention.\n\nSo now he was cornered in a dark alley between tents by a trio of tall, rabbitfolk boys. His tail flicked in agitation as he backed away. The gleam of the knife held by the leader caught the light with a sinister shine.\n\n\"Look, kid, just give us the money, yeah?\" the leader rabbitfolk said, gesturing with his knife. \"We're not gonna hurt you, we're just hungry, see?\"\n\n\"O-okay,\" he agreed, trembling hands fumbling into his pocket. In his nerves, he dropped the money at his feet. The three rabbitfolk scowled at him.\n\n\"Tch. Typical useless cat. What the hell are you doing, huh?\"\n\n\"S-sorry! I-I didn't mean--\"\n\nSplat!\n\nThe rabbitfolk on the right staggered sideways as a pie, of all things, smacked him in the side of the head. He shook his head, dazed and surprised by the sudden pie.\n\n\"What the hell? Who the hell are you?!\"\n\nOwen turned to look and was just as confused as the three muggers. It was a clown. White outfit, white face painted with dramatic tears, a flower pin, and massive red shoes.\n\n\"Gentlemen, this is a place of laughter and fun. Why don't you just forget about all of this and enjoy the circus?\"\n\n\"Look buddy,\" the leader said, taking stomping steps toward the clown until he loomed right over him. \"This isn't any of your business, yeah? Just walk away.\"\n\nHonk!\n\nQuick as a flash, the clown reached up and stuck a large, circular red nose on the rabbitfolk leader's face and squeezed it.\n\n\"You--!\" his shout was interrupted with a startled gurgling as the flower on the clown's chest sprayed water into his face.\n\nThe non-pied member of the group shouted and stepped forward only for his feet to flip out from underneath him, a banana peel flying into the air comically. He hit the ground with a thud and then a surprised squawk as another pie slapped into his face.\n\n\"Maybe you boys should leave, you're pretty accident prone,\" the clown said nonchalantly, twirling yet another pie on the tip of his finger. Unwilling to face more pies, banana peels, and humiliation, the rabbitfolk fled.\n\n\"Well, good riddance to sour souls. You okay, kid?\"\n\n\"Y-yeah. Thank you!\"\n\n\"Don't mention it. Why don't you get back to your family?\" And before Owen could complain that he was out here to find something to eat, the clown held out a steaming fresh corndog and the coins he'd dropped.\n\n\"Enjoy the circus!\"","guide":"The Pierrot is a clown class with some silly abilities.\n\nYour main ability is the ability to toss pie's, at essentially any time. It's just 2 damage, but it's effectively unavoidable.\n\nFlower squirt is a simple attack ability that applies Soaked to the enemy. HONK! is a 0 AP challenge, but it relies on the enemy passing a save. Still if you want to be tanking and you have no other quick actions, it's free to use.\n\nFinally, banana peel is a powerful movement interrupt. Because they fall prone, the rest of their movement is canceled.","keyAbility":"Pierrot's Journey","abilities":["Pie Toss","Flower Squirt","HONK!","Banana Peel"]},{"id":"priest","name":"Priest","tier":2,"role1":"Healer","role2":"Support","difficulty":1,"requirements":"Acolyte mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to either Power or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Medicine, Religion, Magic, History, Insight, Negotiation, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Priests belong to a religion and utilize the mystery of divine power to protect and heal allies.","guide":"The priest has access to several healing and support abilities.\n\nHoly Light is a heal that doesn't heal as much as Cure Touch does, but it costs less AP and most importantly, has greatly increased range. Where the acolyte has to play close to their allies and is at risk of provoking attacks of opportunity to heal, the priest doesn't have that issue. Out of combat, Cure Touch is still better for healing.\n\nThe Secret Art: Resurrect is an emergency heal that can only be used when an ally has already gone down. Note how it sets the targets HP to 0 before healing. This makes it have great synergy with demons or other abilities that allow a person to fight at full strength when below 0 HP. They can keep going until they reach heavy negative HP before they go down, after which you can bring them back up.\n\nSacrament is a free buff that you will most likely want to apply to your strongest physical striker at the start of combat. Turning the weapon into holy damage can also be very helpful against certain enemies.\n\nPurify is a simple cleansing tool that can remove basically any debuff from an ally. Even using it to remove something like Daze can be worth it to let a DPS get more actions in.","keyAbility":"Studied Healer","abilities":["Sacrament","Purify","Holy Light","Secret Art:  Revitalize"]},{"id":"protector","name":"Protector","tier":3,"role1":"Defender","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Guardian mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Riding, Intimidation, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Heavily armored warriors with large shields that protect their allies.","guide":"The protector gains access to greatshield to help in their tanking. Like heavy armor, equipping a greatshield may be overkill on the defensive front. However, it comes with the benefit of letting your allies use you as cover, so greatshield + medium armor is better than normal shield + heavy armor if you have to choose between them.\n\nWith no getting past!, ignoring the protector's attacks of opportunities is basically impossible. It has sure hit and applies a slow at the minimum, so unless the target has high block there's little chance they can move at full speed away from a protector. The option to use a heavy attack exists as well. While a sure hit heavy attack is normally really strong, due to your heavy armor you probably do not have the RP to spare on it.\n\nProvoke II is a fire and forget challenge ability that keeps an enemy taunted for the entire fight. You don't want to keep switching this around since the AP cost is too high for it, so just put it on the most dangerous enemy and leave it there.\n\nBullet Magnet is a tool for protecting your allies from ranged attacks. You have to use it on your turn, so you have to be aware of when enemy archers are in position to shoot your allies. It is a great ability to help win ranged battles, especially if you can find low or even high cover to hide behind.\n\nThe Secret Art: Shield Wall is effectively a party wide invulnerability against a single ability. The mana cost is very high, but this can save everyone's life when used against a powerful AoE attack.","keyAbility":"Greatshield Master","abilities":["No getting past!","Provoke II","Bullet Magnet","Secret Art: Shield Wall"]},{"id":"pyromancer","name":"Pyromancer","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any class mastered or Fire mastery.","heart":"You gain +1 Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Mages the specialize in fire magic.","guide":"Pyromancer specialize in dealing fire damage and setting things on fire.\n\nFireball is one of their signature abilities, dealing damage in a small AoE. It has decent range making it good for dealing with packs of enemies before they can get close.\n\nIncendiary Ray is strong when used in a choke point. If the enemies all line up through a single corridor, one ray can hit many enemies at the same time. It can hit allies as well however, so make sure they're okay with it before you start blasting.\n\nAfter dealing Fire damage, you can spend an RP to set people on fire. While using it against a single enemy may not seem like a worthwhile trade, as RP is generally more valuable, disrupting the actions of a boss type enemy by lowering their AP by 1 can still be valuable. When using mana to use it against multiple enemies, it becomes a more appealing choice. Especially since grunts lack AP to begin with, meaning they will spend half their AP on removing the burn. If they choose not to remove it, the burn is likely to kill them after their turn ends.\n\nThe Secret Art: Pyroblast is a heavy nuke. Where most of these types of hard-hitting abilities basically require the target to be out of RP, pyroblast has a second use condition if an enemy decided not to remove the burn you put on it. If neither of the conditions are met, it's probably best to wait.","keyAbility":"Controlled Blaze","abilities":["Fireball","Incendiary Ray","Ignite","Secret Art: Pyroblast"]},{"id":"pyromaster","name":"Pyromaster","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Pyromancer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason","soul":"You gain +1 to Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Fire mages who have reached the pinnacle of fire control.","guide":"The Pyromaster is AoE striker that deals fire damage. Their Eternal Flames ability heavily punishes people who don't immediately remove the burns they inflict, all but ensuring they will die eventually. They rely on the pyromancer's ignite for many of their burning needs.\n\nFireball II is their one ability that inflicts Burning without the need of ignite. This makes it more mana and action efficient than a normal fireball. If needed, the size of it can also be increased by spending more mana. Good for those situations where a few enemies are barely out of range.\n\nBlast Wave is a self peel tool. It also knocks back allies, so be mindful of your positioning.\n\nFireball Barrage lets you pelt an entire battlefield with fireballs. Very likely to be useful at the start of a fight where enemies are not yet clustered into one position.\n\nThe Climax Art: Meteor is a sure hit attack that can only be avoided by walking out of the area before it lands. The damage potential of this ability when overcharged to the maximum is insane, though you are unlikely to be able to do so. Even when used at just 4 AP, the damage is high. You will need to rely on your teammates or terrain to keep enemies inside the strike radius however.","keyAbility":"Eternal Flames","abilities":["Blast Wave","Fireball II","Fireball Barrage","Secret Art: Meteor"]},{"id":"ranger","name":"Ranger","tier":1,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Utility","difficulty":1,"requirements":"None.","heart":"You gain +1 to Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Toughness.","skills":"You gain 5 skill points to spend on Appraise, Athletics, Stealth, Medicine, Perception, Survival, Animal Husbandry or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Rangers hail from the ranks of expert hunters and skilled military marksmen. Their senses and instincts are keen—taking down targets from incredible distances. Whether wielding bows, crossbows, or rifles, Rangers are always ready with an oppressive rain of missiles.\n\nAn expert ranger has the ability to pick out targets of opportunity. They quickly zero in on the most vulnerable enemies, picking them off with precision. It’s this talent for oppressively breaking down the opposition that makes Rangers so effective in battle.\n\nRangers have trained the ability to flood mana into their optical magic circuits—granting them the ability to see further and more sharply. They spot threats from great distances and then strike them with pinpoint accuracy.\n\nThey're a welcome addition to any adventuring party. With sharp focus and deadly accuracy that makes them fearsome opponents.","guide":"Rangers are versatile strikers that can excel at ranged combat, but can also fight in melee if required.\n\nTrack is a pure out of combat utility tool that ensures the ranger can always follow tracks without rolling.\n\nStatus Assessment is a support tool that lets your party know how injured a target is. Knowing the rough HP % of an enemy is important in making correct tactical decisions, whether it's who to focus fire or whether to retreat all together.\n\nCrippling attack can be used with both a melee and ranged weapon, but applying it from range is a lot more useful. Landing a slow on a melee enemy can allow you to kite it or seriously delay it from being able to attack.\n\nSnap Shot is an 1 AP heavy attack, but the chance to hit on it isn't going to be great. Rangers focused on power over focus may see some good use out of this ability. Even normal rangers should consider using this over a light attack when forced to choose between the two, especially against enemies with high guard against who a light attack would do very little even if it hits.\n\nGuided Aim is what rangers can spend a lot of mana on. It will remain a powerful ability especially as you go into later classes. Adding a bonus to your accuracy roll, even if the mana cost is higher for the benefit, can help make important abilities more reliable. With guided aim, you need to worry less about future secret art attacks barely missing.","keyAbility":"Ranger's Journey","abilities":["Track","Guided Aim","Crippling Attack","Snap Shot"]},{"id":"reaver","name":"Reaver","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Highlander mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Riding, Intimidation, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Marcus stared at his \u0018mentor' with exasperation as the zoalith catfolk demonstrated a series of strikes against a reinforced training dummy. Captain Kreman was undeniably skilled and had raw power behind his strikes to boot. However&\n\n\"UuuuooohRAH!\" the catfolk exclaimed, bringing his greatsword down in a heavy, two handed strike with a crash. Dirt and dust exploded around him, obscuring everything from view. A stiff breeze rushed through the training area revealing Captain Kreman in a dramatic pose and Marcus could see him looking out of the corner of his eye to make sure he was seen.\n\nWith a self satisfied smile, Captain Kreman stood up and stabbed his sword down into the dirt. Marcus could practically feel Vice-Captain Aislyn's glare at the Captain's actions from somewhere in the growing camp and the amount of extra maintenance his sword would need.\n\n\"See? That's how it's done! You do it.\"\n\nMacrus had not, in fact, seen how it was done. Captain Kreman had attacked the training dummy at full speed and had only shouted at the top of his lungs in various strange ways instead of explaining the technique Marcus was learning. Still, trying to point that out to the Captain would only get him confused so Marcus just resigned himself into being chastised mid technique and finally being taught properly. He stepped up and settled into a stance that was meant to build and maintain momentum in his blade so he could strike with little warning on anyone approaching him.\n\n\"You're standing wrong,\" Captain Kreman said.\n\nMarcus waited for some sort of correction for a long moment before he adjusted his footing and lifted his sword again.\n\n\"Wrong!\" A light kick hit him in the side of the foot and he nearly staggered. \"Like that!\"\n\nHe checked his footing and tried to memorize how it felt and then began to spin his sword around him, the tip whistling as he built up speed.\n\n\"Huh&not bad.\" And with no further warning, Captain Kreman stepped into the sweeping area of his sword. He couldn't have stopped his blade if he wanted to and he was very grateful when the Captain deflected his unintentional blow with apparent ease. The catfolk man nodded with a frown. \"Good power but&\"\n\n\"But?\" Marcus asked, ready for any sort of criticism that would help him improve.\n\n\"Where is your warcry?!\"\n\nMarcus stared at the Captain. \"What?\"\n\n\"How can you expect to put full power into your strikes if you're not putting full power through yourself?!\" Captain Kreman brushed him aside with the flat of his sword and took up a stance.\n\n\"Like this!\" He swung down. \"URAH!\"\n\nHe cut to the side in a leg level strike. \"OOUUAH!\"\n\nHe leapt into the air with a flip, his sword leading the way down \"SHUWAH!\"\n\nThe air became heavy with magic and then Captain Kreman began to spin. \"UUOOH-RAH-RAH-RAH-RAH-RAH-RAH!\" Every strike of his spin on the dummy was punctuated by an increasingly louder \u0018warcry'.\n\nMarcus stared, taking it all in, watching his mentor's feet, his stance, the angle of his sword, and even the rush of magic as it spun through the air. This, at least, was something he could learn from.\n\nHe'd leave out the warcry, though.","guide":"Soon.","keyAbility":"Overwhelming Critical","abilities":["Sweeping Stance","Full Power Swing","Shieldcrusher","Secret Art: Bladestorm"]},{"id":"rogue","name":"Rogue","tier":1,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"None.","heart":"You gain +1 to Cunning.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Appraise, Athletics, Stealth, Deception, Roguecraft, Perception, Insight, Negotiation, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Rogues are the shadowy denizens of the underworld, using subterfuge and cunning to outsmart their enemies. They know how to create confusion and chaos, slipping in for the perfect strike when the moment is just right. A Rogue’s greatest strength lies in understanding their own weaknesses. They never fight fair, always looking to tip the scales in their favor.\n\nYou’ll find Rogues lurking in the dark corners of Lyr’s cities, where they navigate the underbelly with ease. But they’re not just criminals or street-level operatives. Many are recruited by official agencies, prized for their abilities in gathering information and conducting espionage. Their unique skill set also makes them invaluable members of adventuring parties, where their knack for stealth and strategy can turn the tide in any situation.\n\nRogues thrive in the shadows, always one step ahead, always ready to seize the advantage.","guide":"Rogues are high-mobility Strikers that specialize in weaving through the enemy lines, finding opportune targets and attacking them for high damage. Feint, Evasive Maneuver and Movement Burst allow Rogues to take advantage of battlefield positioning without putting themselves into too much risk.\n\nFeint is a cheaper disengage that only works against a single target. It competes with evasive maneuver for escaping an enemy's attack range, but it has another upside to it. Because the target cannot make any attacks of opportunity against you, you could fire a ranged weapon in someone's face without risk.\n\nEvasive Maneuver is both an offensive and defensive tool. It can be used as a reaction to an enemy attacking you in melee, which forces them to move up if they wish to keep attacking you. This takes an AP and may provoke attacks of opportunity from your allies. The AP they were about to spend on the initial attack is refunded however and they may choose to swap targets. As a rogue, keep this is in mind if you don't have a dedicated tank in your party. It can also be used to position more aggressively to do a full attack turn. When used on your own turn, you don't even need to spend RP for it and can just use mana instead.\n\nMovement burst is their last mobility tool. The mana cost is high for what it gives, but the ability to move 100ft in 1 AP should not be underestimated. Whether it's for chasing someone or escaping, a rogue with movement burst is almost impossible to keep up with.\n\nFor offense, they have Sneak Attack. It has a noticeable mana cost, but trick attacks cost double the RP to react to. This means that grunts generally cannot react to it and even heroic creatures have to make a serious decision whether it's worth spending 2 RP against 1 attack.\n\nFinally, devastating strike is the attack that shines when someone's RP has been exhausted. Easy to use against grunts, but it will take some time for it to be usable against heroic enemies. Still, once you can use it it's just guaranteed, pure damage.","keyAbility":"Rogue's Journey","abilities":["Evasive Maneuver","Movement Burst","Sneak Attack","Devastating Strike"]},{"id":"saboteur","name":"Saboteur","tier":2,"role1":"Controller","role2":"Utility","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Rogue mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill in Stealth or Stealth Expertise","description":"Rogues that create opportunities for their teammates, breaking through and creating their own entrances while hindering the enemy.","guide":"Saboteurs combine scouting tools with some gadgets and explosives they can use in combat.\n\nPresence Concealment protects you from certain magical tracking tools. Scouting Ahead is useful when sneakily trying to move through a dungeon or other dangerous place, allowing your group to move stealthily even when not everyone in the group has put points into stealth.\n\nChemical Explosive is a bomb that can be used to blow up many different things. Blowing a hole through a wall, or just blowing up a house straight up are both possible. You can only use it once per arc, so you do need to put in a bit of thought before committing to it. It can deal a lot of damage if it hits a person, but the detonation time is too long for it to see use in combat.\n\nFlash Bomb is effectively a free flashbang flask that allows a save. Daze is pretty powerful when you can inflict it on multiple people, tossing a flash bomb every turn can be worth it, even against just a single enemy.\n\nWire Sweep is another potentially powerful CC tool. Because it is a save instead of an attack, enemies with low toughness may find it hard to defend against.","keyAbility":"Saboteur","abilities":["Flash Bomb","Scouting Ahead","Wire Sweep","Chemical Explosive"]},{"id":"sage","name":"Sage","tier":2,"role1":"Utility","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Mage, Sorcerer or Mage Knight mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Appraise, Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Sages are spellcasters that excel in augmenting spells.","guide":"Sage is an utility class that amplifies other spells you already know. Thus, it is best to only take sage if you already have some spells from other classes.\n\nIncreased Reach is a situational, but useful tool to make those spells that have a low range easier to use.\n\nWith selective casting, AoE abilities that can also hit allies before a lot easier to use. Even something like a meteor is now perfectly safe to stand in for your allies.\n\nLengthened Incantation can be used to increase the damage your spells deal. It is most effective when used with AoE attacks, as the damage bonus would be effective against all enemies hit. You can also use it to gather damage for 1 big attack when dealing with high guard enemies.\n\nDualcast effectively allows you to give a spell the rapid keyword for a turn, though with some more restrictions. There are many potential ways to use it. The low mana cost makes it easy to use it even for things like tossing two fireballs. Lengthened Incantation can provide a similar amount of damage, but dualcast has the advantage of being able to see the results of your action before you commit to casting it again.\n\nSecret Art: Overcharge can be seen as a free 3 mana once per encounter, at the cost of using your secret art. It does require a high mana spell to get maximum use out of, but unless you have another secret art it competes with, it's worth using every fight.","keyAbility":"Augmented Casting - Increased Reach","abilities":["Lengthened Incantation","Selective Casting","Dualcast","Secret Art: Overcharge"]},{"id":"scout","name":"Scout","tier":2,"role1":"Utility","role2":"Striker","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Rogue or Ranger mastered","heart":"You gain +1 to Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Agility.","skills":"You gain 5 skill points to spend on Appraise, Athletics, Stealth, Medicine, Perception, Survival, Animal Husbandry, Art or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"In the frostbitten silence at the edge of the Astra Lands, survival doesn’t just come from strength, it comes from knowing where not to step. The first to cross the threshold past Mirane were not conquerors or scholars, but a scattered few with sharpened senses and silent tread.\n\nIt was the scouts, led by Elyne Ravas, that laid the first trail into the Astra Lands. Long, long before the existence of the Dragon Claw Alliance or the Mirane Expeditioner's Alliance, they were the ones that cleared the path, placed the first markers and discovered how vast the lands truly were. The things learned during that time were passed on and are still shared to this day.\n\nThe scout’s role is not simply to guide, but to witness. To thread through impossible terrain, observe the unspeakable, and return with clarity while others return with nothing at all. Whether alone or among allies, they mark the path. Not for glory, but so others may live long enough to see it.\n\n\"Eyes sharp, steps light. Leave no echo but the truth.\" -Ravas","guide":"The scout is a class that allows for more solo play than would normally be possible. With the high bonuses given from Independant Actor and the scout's retreat ability, a scout operating alone is unlikely to be caught out and trapped before they can escape.\n\nWhen you are forced to work in a team, you can take point with their Pathfinder ability and allow allies to move up unimpeded. With squadsight, you can spot out hidden enemies for your allies as well as increase the range of their ranged attacks. This can be very useful to allow allies that only have a light ranged weapon to fire at enemies further away.\n\nTo move up in a fight without getting focused, you have Hide in bush. It won't work in every environment, but it allows you to remain hidden even if the terrain would normally be too open or there would be too many sight lines from different angles.\n\nFinally, your secret art is a powerful opening move that does require you to start the battle in stealth. It also requires you to use it as your first attack, but it's an auto hit attack that deals maximum damage and allows you to remain stealthed as a bonus.","keyAbility":"Independent Actor","abilities":["Squadsight","Pathfinder","Hide in bush","Secret Art: Ambush Shot"]},{"id":"searing-lotus-style","name":"Searing Lotus Style","tier":2,"role1":"Defender","role2":"Striker","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Reason or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Magic, Perception, Intimidation, Survival, Art or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Aine watched as injured soldiers ran past her through a narrow pass. She hadn't expected things to be easy when she set out with her comrades from Glassworks, answering the surprising call for help from the Demons, but the sheer weight of numbers the combined Northi-Westrian forces brought to bear was mind boggling. They had lost the battle, that was clear and obvious, but her unit's objective had been complete. The relic was safely smuggled out of the now burning city while they had held the rear guard.\n\nShe didn't know what the relic was, she didn't know why it was so important, she didn't know why half her comrades were dead and the rest injured, but she had to hope that it was something that would turn the tide of the war.\n\n\"Keep going!\" she shouted after the few remaining Salamanders and Demons that had hesitated when she hadn't followed them. She turned fully toward the approaching humans and brought her longsword down with a sharp motion. Fire bloomed along the blade, so hot that it began to sear the grass nearby and caused the humans to come to a wary halt at the sheer heat of it. The tip of her blade scratched a molten line in the stone between her and the enemy.\n\n\"If you cross that, I'll be forced to kill you,\" she warned, her voice holding an echo of a wildfire.\n\nTheir response was just laughter and a cautious approach, swordsmen fanning out and a pair of riflemen hurrying to load their weapons. She let out a scorching breath and let Fire become a reality in the world around her. The air shimmered and the stone slagged into molten puddles around her. Scorching wind flew around her, the sudden heat displacing air aggressively and sending her hair dancing. She took a defensive stance and waited for the first man to gain his nerve. Their courage was bolstered by more men coming up the pass, ready to push the chase for her withdrawing men.\n\nThe first man to cross into her domain barely had time to scream before he was scorched to ash and bone. Those that tried to bypass her found that she had placed herself too neatly in the pass opening and they had to dance back with severe burns. Rifles range out and she was forced to deflect away one shot with her sword while the others were wildly off target, the heat haze throwing off their aim.\n\nShe couldn't hold them forever and she knew she would die here. But she would burn as much time and as many men as she could, the flame of hope in her heart that the artifact would all be worth it, that it would bring an end to the war.\n\n\"Come, then! I'll burn you all to ash!\"","guide":"The Searing Lotus Style is a striker and tank hybrid class.\n\nTrial by Fire is a simple attack that applies Challenged to the target, but it punishes you if you miss. If you have other ways of applying challenge to the target and need to land it, you might not want to take the risk.\n\nScorching Reprisal is a heavy attack of opportunity that just gives you another free one after. Naturally it's only worth using if you think an enemy will provoke another AoO.\n\nMolten Domain is a tanking domain that forces enemies around you to stand and fight you or catch on fire. Against multiple enemies, this can rack up a lot of burning quickly.\n\nInfernal Bastion is a block that can force the attacker to waste an AP or do some damage to them. If you time it at their last attack of a turn, they'll likely be unable to remove the burn.","keyAbility":"Fire Weapon","abilities":["Trial By Fire","Scorching Reprisal","Molten Domain","Infernal Bastion"]},{"id":"shadow-thief","name":"Shadow Thief","tier":2,"role1":"Utility","role2":"Support","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Rogue mastered or Dark mastery.","heart":"You gain +1 to Cunning.","soul":"You gain +1 to Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Stealth, Deception, Roguecraft, Perception, Insight, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The Shadow Thief is a stealthy and cunning character, specializing in thievery, deception, and infiltration. They excel at slipping into enemy territory undetected and stealing valuable items or information, using their quick reflexes and agility to escape undetected.","guide":"The shadow thief is a utility class that works best during the night. Every single ability they have has higher than normal mana costs during the day, but lower than average during the night. Ideally, you only want to fight during the night though of course this isn't always an option.\n\nShadowstep at night is better than normal movement. Not only do you move further or the AP cost, with it being a teleport you ignore attacks of opportunity, difficult terrain and other hassles. During the day, it's a worse Fae Flash. Still usable if you need to teleport, but not worth the mana cost in a lot of cases.\n\nVanish during the night is a 1 RP hide action. This has some use cases, allowing you to make more attack while taking advantage of the stealth bonus. The use case by itself doesn't change much during the day, as the RP cost is a bigger limiting factor than the mana cost in most cases.\n\nShadow Cloak not only gives you a stealth bonus, it also lets you stealth even when you don't have cover or concealment. This makes the Vanish ability a lot more useful, allowing you to stealth in the middle of nowhere, although it requires a high stealth skill bonus. It's a one time cost that lasts until the end of the encounter, so it's still usable even during the day. It's also just good for sneaking into places, especially when combined with Shade Form.\n\nShade Form is a primarily out of combat exploration tool, though it has some use in combat too by being able to move through enemy spaces. It is almost unusable during the day due to its upkeep cost though.","keyAbility":"Nightstalker","abilities":["Shadow Step","Shade Form","Vanish","Shadow Cloak"]},{"id":"shadowbringer","name":"Shadowbringer","tier":3,"role1":"Support","role2":"Utility","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Shadow Thief mastered","heart":"You gain +1 to Cunning.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Stealth, Deception, Roguecraft, Perception, Insight, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"-","guide":"-","keyAbility":"Shared Darkness","abilities":["Hide in Shadows","Darkness","Sable Grace","Secret Art: Nightcaller"]},{"id":"shield-paladin","name":"Shield Paladin","tier":2,"role1":"Defender","role2":"Support","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Human, proficient with shields and medium armor.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on any non crafting or gathering skill. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Paladins are powerful warriors who receive their powers from their god. Shield paladins are frontline defenders and healers who can keep their weaker allies safe.","guide":"The shield paladin is a tank that focuses on blocking and temporary HP.\n\nThrough their Aura of Protection, they allow their allies to block against attacks even if their Block is normally too low to be usable. This does cost mana and it requires your ally to block, so communication with your allies is key.\n\nWith Holy Shield, you can convert AP into defense, gaining both a high Block potentially allowing you to block even heavy attacks and a decent check of temporary HP. You do give up damage by using too much AP on this, so it is not always the best option to dump all your AP into it.\n\nDivine Smite is a more offensive way to gain temporary hit points. It does require landing the heavy attack, but it can be used both on yourself or an ally.\n\nShield paladins can also heal themselves or ally through their Lay on Hands ability. It's efficient both mana and AP wise, with the only drawback being that it only has a touch range. It does not provoke attacks of opportunity however, so you don't need to worry about disengaging from the fight before healing.","keyAbility":"Holy Weapon","abilities":["Holy Shield","Aura of Protection","Divine Smite II","Lay on Hands"]},{"id":"shield-saint","name":"Shield Saint","tier":3,"role1":"Defender","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Bodyguard mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Riding, Intimidation, Perception, Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The sworn shieldbrother or sister of a Sword Saint. Like its twin saint, the Shield Saint originally hails from Kirara where it fights together with their chosen partner.\n\nThe Shield Saint is trained in defensive techniques whose purpose is to allow for their partner to focus purely on offense while the Shield Saint absorbs the hits. At first these techniques were merely physical, but over time the nature has evolved into a more spiritual connection. The bond between a Shield Saint and their partner links their very souls together and neither can be bonded again until one of them passes away. Because of this, the partner a Shield Saint chooses is very important and in Kirara most pairs are selected based on compatibility at an early age. It is not uncommon for a Sword Saint and Shield Saint pair to be romantically involved with each other.","guide":"As a Shield Saint, your primary goal is to protect your soulmate from harm.\n\nYour main tool for doing so is Faithful Shield, which lets you turn AP into free RP for the purpose of keeping your soulmate safe. Shelter still has a range restriction, so this works best if your soulmate is also a melee character.\n\nQuick Assist combines several feature of Bodyguard into one and adds some offense on top of it. Keep in mind the range is rather short and like with Faithful Shield, your life is easier with a melee soulmate as you are more likely to get the mana cost reduction.\n\nThe secret art Dynamic Duo combines defense with offense. You Challenge all enemies and can use the bodyguard's At your side to teleport across the battlefield to threaten enemies you didn't before. Where normally your attacks might be a bit weak, because your soulmate is making them it will punish enemies ignoring your Challenge that much harder. It also has a low mana and AP cost, so you can use it pretty much every fight.\n\nFinally, Lifesense is a utility tool that can be used to keep track of the status of your soulmate should you split up. It has no mana cost, so you can keep it up indefinitely if you want to.","keyAbility":"Soul Bond","abilities":["Lifesense","Faithful Shield","Quick Assist","Secret Art: Dynamic Duo"]},{"id":"shieldwarden","name":"Shieldwarden","tier":2,"role1":"Healer","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Acolyte, Mage or Mage Knight mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Power or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Magic, Religion, Medicine, Perception, Negotiation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Shielding mages","guide":"Shieldwardens are a healing class that walk a tight line between being too cautious and being too confident. Those too cautious will burn through their mana quickly, while those who wait too long before shielding may find their allies already on the floor where their shields will do little to get them back up. They lack traditional combat healing, but make up for it with superior numbers on their shields.\n\nPower Word: Shield is their standard protection spell. You’ll want to cast it on your tank or the target most likely to get hit in the early rounds of combat.\n\nPower Word: Barrier is also an option for an early cast, but the mana cost may feel high if the temporary HP doesn’t get used. Since it can be cast while using RP, it may be better to wait until the party is targeted by AoE attacks before using it.\n\nPower Word: Reinforce is a manaless way to give your allies more shields, with the condition that you probably already placed shields on them beforehand. It also works with temporary HP not applied by you, so there’s some possible powerful synergies there.\n\nSecret Art: Lifesaver is something you’ll only use as a last resort. Unless someone is low on hit points, it will not provide great value for its mana cost. But if you combine it with the above mentioned reinforce, an ally can fight at near death for a long period of time.\n\nRecover Power makes it less likely you waste your mana by shielding yourself near the end of the combat, but it only works on yourself.","keyAbility":"Recover Power","abilities":["Power Word: Shield","Power Word: Barrier","Power Word: Reinforce","Secret Art: Lifesaver"]},{"id":"shinigami-eyes","name":"Shinigami Eyes","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Any class mastered, must have the Touched by Death breakthrough. Must have at least 1 mystic eye slot open.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Stealth, Medicine, Perception, Insight or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Shinigami Eyes are mystic eyes that allow the user to perceive the death of things. This manifests in the shape of lines and points on a creature’s body, which can be cut or stabbed.","guide":"The Shinigami Eyes are a mystic eye ability. When you activate your death perception, you immediately see the HP % of all enemies within sight. It may cost a mana, but it gives information a lot faster than relying on Status Assessment skills.\n\nWith the True Death passive ability, you immediately become a counter to any sort of healer. There's nothing to heal when their maximum HP is reduced by the same amount as their HP.\n\nLine of Death is a light attack that punishes armored targets that think they can ignore light attacks. It won't do much extra against targets without a high guard.\n\nPoint of Death does consistent damage against enemies below half HP. Even against targets without high guard, it may still be worth using sometimes for its maximum damage property when you need to secure a kill and can't risk rolling low on damage.\n\nSecret Art: Seventeen Dissection is a secret art that does not cost any mana, making it usable in every fight. Against heroic enemies, it is just a guaranteed 17 damage. It can be useful if they are still sitting on RP but are low on HP. If they are out of RP, then just attacking normally may do more damage. Against any type of grunt, it is just an instant kill no matter. Useful against grunts that have a lot of hit points.","keyAbility":"Death Perception","abilities":["True Death","Line of Death","Point of Death","Secret Art: Seventeen Dissection"]},{"id":"sky-knight","name":"Sky Knight","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Utility","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Cavalier mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Animal Husbandry, Riding, Flight, Intimidation, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"As was common with most innovations that made radical leaps, the history of the Sky Knights was steeped in warfare. Like the development of the Cavalier, learning to take to the sky on the backs of winged mounts stemmed from a need to counter a threat. Aerial Mages from Sorthen had long since, and in some cases continue, dominated the skies as scouts, couriers, and as untouchable bombardment specialists. With no modern airships to deter them and no Aeromancers to threaten them, both Northi and Westria searched for a solution. Nearly simultaneously, the two countries developed their own methods.\n\nFrom the mountains and hills near Mount Merlin, Northi tamed the wild pegasi. Harpy hunters were the first to capture and tame the wild flying horses and harpy run ranches continue to produce the highest quality mounts with specialized breeds tailored for various tasks. A pegasus’s agility and speed in the air let the chimeran knights of Northi put up a challenge to Sorthen aerial units in terms of scouting, but their limited endurance and fragile wings made them less suited as couriers and frontline combatants.\n\nWestria took a nuisance that plagued their southeastern border along the mountains near Jav and turned it into a solution. Wyverns roosting in the mountains and forests were regularly dealt with by adventurers and knights but some enterprising (and foolhardy) beast tamers decided to attempt to tame newly hatched wyverns as companions. With some false starts, they succeeded and it wasn’t long before an interest in training them as mounts emerged. Slower and less nimble in the air than their pegasi counterparts, a wyvern’s thick scales and devastating Reginleiv made them much more suitable as flying heavy cavalry.\n\nTo this day, there is little overlap in the Sky Knight forces of Northi and Westria. While each side failed to deploy units that could directly counter Aerial Mages, their arrival on the battlefield removed Sorthen’s complete dominance of the air. Modern Sky Knight adventurers utilize whatever type of mount that suits their style (or that they can afford) and continue to fill their historical roles as scouts, couriers, and aerial cavalry.","guide":"The sky knight is a class that focuses on flying mounts. It is vulnerable to ranged attacks, but it has excellent target access. Despite being a tier 2 class, it may not be accessible for everyone due to the high cost of pegasi and wyverns. A pegasus is faster, but wyverns are a lot more durable and with some offensive power.\n\nAir Stability helps manage the durability issues of the pegasus, allowing you to re-direct attacks like normal. The flight rules of you losing altitude still apply though. Aerial Loop can also help with this. It can be used if either you or your mount become the target and it affects both of you, useful for avoiding AoE attacks.\n\nAerial Crashdown is your main tool of attacking the backline, moving you to the target and allowing your mount to make a heavy attack for just 2 AP. Be careful of getting stuck on the ground against melee enemies however, as you can't canter of your mounts attack.\n\nIf you don't want to commit to an engagement, you can use Flyby attack. This, like Aerial Crashdown, also works with Trample, though getting trample value is harder with a flying mount.\n\nYour Secret Art: Mythical Awakening varies based on the type of flying mount you use. The pegasus one can be used both offensively to just deal damage, but also defensively if you're scared of being forced to the ground by arrows. You can just bellorophon to attack and move low enough that you won't get shot down. The wyvern's reginliev is best used on the same elevation as the enemy, as it will be hard to hit many targets with the line attack otherwise.","keyAbility":"Air Stability","abilities":["Aerial Crashdown","Aerial Loop","Flyby Attack","Secret Art: Mythical Awakening"]},{"id":"sky-talon-style","name":"Sky Talon Style","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Controller","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Cultivator or Martial Artist mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Flight, Perception, Intimidation, Survival or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The various clans of Harpies and Tengu's live in harmony together on Mt Merlin. This was not always the case.\n\nA long time ago, the two races were in a violent territorial dispute over the mountain. The tengu held control over it when the harpies moved in. The tengu were worried about the threat of these sudden newcomers, while the harpies considered Mt Merlin part of Northi's territory and thus their land by right.\n\nThe tengu had both the numbers and defender's advantage and quickly moved to forcefully expel the invaders after the brief set of negotiations broke down. However, they had lacked knowledge of the Harpy's innate mastery of the wind. Their downbursts would snipe tengu's out of the sky without any recourse and the first battle ended in a crushing defeat for the crows.\n\nSeizing the momentum, the harpies pushed forward and suppressed the tengu's, who were unable to use their usual flying combat strategies. Hope seemed lost. Until, Dawn Waits Above stepped out of her solitary training from the highest peaks of the mountains.\n\nDawn gifted onto her fellow tengu's a martial arts style that let them harness the power of the wind themselves. They managed to fly faster and land extremely quickly to avoid the dangerous blasts of wind coming from the sky. Once they closed the gap, their wind-infused fists knocked the harpies out of the sky themselves where they were beaten into submission.\n\nWith the new techniques, the tides of the battle shifted into a stalemate. With neither side having an advantage and enough blood already spilled, the two races agreed to stop fighting. The tengu's settled on the higher peaks, always being able to look down on the harpies and keep watch over them.\n\nEven after that short war, the Sky Talon Style remains a commonly used martial arts style to this day. The tengu's of Mt Merlin will never forget how vulnerable they were, while other aspiring martial artists see the style as a way to mimic the strength of the flying races.\n\n\"Fall not like a bird losing flight, but like a blade from heaven.\" Dawn Waits Above, 3rd scroll of the Sky Talon Style.","guide":"Soon","keyAbility":"Boundless Wind","abilities":["Master of the Empty Sky","Heavenfall Descent","Swift Wind Palm","Cloud Piercing Claw"]},{"id":"sniper","name":"Sniper","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Marksman or Scout mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Cunning or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain 5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Stealth, Medicine, Perception, Survival, Animal Husbandry or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Snipers are expert marksmen that use sniper rifles to devastating effect.","guide":"The sniper uses sniper rifles to fire at enemies from far beyond a range in which they can counter. It will be rare to get these extreme range fight, but you should always look to play as far back as possible.\n\nIdeally, you want to move as little as possible to get the accuracy bonus from Snipe. Positioning well early in the fight will keep paying off as it goes on.\n\nPenetrating Shot allows you to remain stationary without having to care about the cover the enemy has. Check with the GM if their cover can be penetrated before using it.\n\nWith Concealed Shot, you are able to keep entering stealth after firing make your attacks impossible to react to. The RP cost may not be an issue either as long as you can stay far enough away from the fighting that you do not take counterattacks.\n\nAimed Shot is a lock-on Heavy attack that can punish dodge users. Stealthed attacks can do the same, but you won't alway have that option.\n\nKillshot is the opening move of the sniper, provided you are able to remain hidden from the enemies before the fight starts. Normally high AP abilities do not gain the benefit of being a hidden attacker, but Killshot is an exception to this if used in the first round. This lets a sniper do huge damage right from the start. You can combine it with the ranger's guided aim ability for an almost certain hit that cannot be reacted to in any way.","keyAbility":"Snipe","abilities":["Penetrating Shot","Concealed Shot","Aimed Shot","Killshot"]},{"id":"sorcerer","name":"Sorcerer","tier":1,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"None","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Deception, Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Negotiation, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"\"Why can't I just use a wand? This is hard!\"\n\nKori flexed her fingers as the magic she was trying to channel into a magical blast fizzled underneath her skin. Her tutor, Mister Corwin, tutted as he watched her stoically. But most importantly, he didn't hand her her wand. Her long ears twitched and flattened back, mirroring the annoyance on her face.\n\n\"Mister Corwin!\"\n\n\"You are the Crown Princess of Ithelia, Princess Itia. The magical traditions and strengths of your family run in your blood. This power and these spells are your heritage and the source of pride and defense of the kingdom.\"\n\nKori continued to pout. Mister Corwin sighed lightly.\n\n\"If you can channel this magic without a focus today, I'll inform the Queen of how well you're doing in your studies. I'm sure she'll reward you for your diligence.\"\n\nKori's pout vanished in an instant, thoughts of treats and sweets swirling through her mind. With a shake of her head that caused her ears to flop about, she turned her attention back to the target dummy a few paces away.\n\n\"Remember, focus not just on your own magic, but the magic in the air and the stone beneath your feet. Open yourself up to the flow of worldy magic and become a conduit&\"\n\nShe tuned out Mister Corwin's lecture, taking a breath as she reached out with the part of her that was real but unreal at the same time. She breathed in, a phantom breath mirroring her, filling her with an energy that made her blood feel fizzy. She brought her hand up and breathed out steadily, picturing the magic pulling in from the air and floor beneath her feet, into her core, and up her arm.\n\n\"Taro!\"\n\nHer skin tingled and a prismatic sheen covered her arm for a moment before it leapt from her outstretched hand in a bolt, hitting the target dummy with a resounding crash that knocked it over and left a scorched divot on the shoulder.\n\n\"I did it!\" Kori spun around with a wide grin, her dress fluttering around her ankles.\n\n\"You did, Princess. Well done. Now, do it again, faster.\"","guide":"The sorcerer is a simple spellcasting striker class.\n\nYour magic blast is a close range spell. It's not really more effective than using a wand, but it can be used by other abilities that use spells for elemental damage access.\n\nArcane Rapidfire is a spell that gives you some extra light attacks in exchange for mana. At circuit costs, it's pretty efficient damage but the ability shares the circuit with Arcane Blast which may be the superior damage option. Arcane Blast is a 1 AP heavy with a big mana cost. It's useful when you don't have the full AP to fire a heavy.\n\nFinally, Circuit Reset lets you spend 1 AP to reduce the mana cost of an ability by 1 in the future. It's not really worth using circuit reset just for the reduced mana cost if you have other options, but if you have a spare AP it may be more worth it than making a light.","keyAbility":"Sorcerer's Journey","abilities":["Magic Blast","Arcane Rapidfire","Arcane Blast","Circuit Reset"]},{"id":"spearmaster","name":"Spearmaster","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Controller","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Lancer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Riding, Intimidation, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"An expert spear fighter.","guide":"The spearmaster combines the damage dealing capabilities of the lancer and improves on them, adding some controlling power to the mix.\n\nVersatile range allows you to manipulate your own threatened range. This is useful in spread out melee fights where enemies may have too much freedom to move away from you otherwise.\n\nDraw-In can either be used as a tool to help position enemies for your allies or it can be combined with Lunge to draw an enemy far away into the range of your polearm.\n\nSpear Charge is effectively an upgraded version of the basic Charge that the fighter class has. It gives you a small damage bonus, but you are limited to a single attack even if you spend 4 AP. You can also combine it with Wild Thrusts. Wild Thrusts is an AoE attack that leads into a zone denial. The box it strikes in is fairly small, so it is most powerful in tight spaces. It disables your other attacks of opportunity, but you may cancel it when an enemy is about to provoke to attack them.\n\nThe secret art Gae Bolg is a fairly simple move. With a relatively low cost for a secret art, it's a guaranteed hit with a heavy attack unless fate decides otherwise. It doesn't add any extra damage, so against Block type defenders it may not be worth the mana cost.","keyAbility":"Versatile Range","abilities":["Draw-In","Wild Thrusts","Spear Charge","Secret Art: Gae Bolg"]},{"id":"spell-blademaster","name":"Spell Blademaster","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Spellblade mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness or Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Athletics, Intimidation, Magic, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Spellblades that have mastered their art.","guide":"-","keyAbility":"Draw Elements II","abilities":["Spellblade's Preparation","Elemental Sweep","Double Elements","Secret Art: Spectrum Blade"]},{"id":"spellblade","name":"Spellblade","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Have at least 1 spell, Have one element mastered, Be proficient in 1 weapon.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness or Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Athletics, Intimidation, Magic, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Spellblades are melee fighters that enchant their weapons with magic.","guide":"The spellblade is a melee class that relies on its versatility of its weapon enchantments to gain an edge in battle.\n\nImbue Weapon allows you to always do damage that an enemy is weak to if you're aware of it. Greater Imbue Weapon is similar, paying 1 mana cost for +1 power bonus. Most of the time, if you are planning to stick with 1 enchantment, you will want to use the Greater version. In fights where you are constantly swapping your enchantment, it may be more worth to stick with the normal version.\n\nDraw Elements is what allows the spellblade to pick whatever element they want. Outside of elemental damage bonuses, this is mostly relevant for Elemental Strike.\n\nElemental Strike is a light attack that can apply a whole variety of effects, based on what your weapon is currently enchanted with. Which one of these is the most effective depends heavily on the situation.\n\nSpellstrike lets you use attack magic despite being in melee combat. It is effectively the same as casting a spell without provoking attacks of opportunity, but since it is applied through your weapon it does benefit from Greater Imbue Weapon or similar weapon related buffs.","keyAbility":"Draw Elements","abilities":["Imbue Weapon","Elemental Strike","Spellstrike","Greater Imbue Weapon"]},{"id":"starcaller","name":"Starcaller","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Controller","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Mage or Sorcerer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Appraise, Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Astrea Lu Novar stood on a cliff overlooking the plains in the distance. Already she could see the Westrian forces approach in a tight combat formation towards the severely outnumbered Sorthen forces that hugged the edge of the forest. They were weakened and the Westrian had brought many paladins for this fight. However, the Westrians probably weren't expecting her.\n\nShe looked at her younger brother and nodded. He shouted commands and all around her she could feel their subordinates set up their defensive barrier of stars. Sorthen saboteurs could probably sneak through it, but Westrians? They would kill themselves trying to break through.\n\nAs this happened, the Westrians had begun to engage the forces below. Astra raised her hand to the sky and dozens followed after her. \"Target the healers.\" She gave a simple command and uncountable stars began to form above the heads of the humans. Their panic and attempts to flee and find cover did little to save them from the magical energy that exploded onto the battlefield.\n\nWith the healers weakened or killed, she directed her attention to the paladins still cutting through her fellow demons in the frontline. A point of white-gold light ignited in the air above their leader. The air tightened around it, distorting faintly like a heat haze with a ring of plasma forming around it. And then it ruptures, exploding outwards in a violent flare leaving nothing but a crater where the man once was.\n\nThe rest scramble for a counteroffensive, but that too would be pointless. After all, how could one fight the sky itself?\n\n\"When you see a falling star, do not wish. Run.\"","guide":"The starcaller is a long range DPS mage class.\n\nYour key ability Celestial Artillery lets you ignore cover when attacking from long range with the spells from this class. Comet is a simple long range spell to let you do this reliably without spending mana.\n\nStarfall is a zone denial tool that's interesting in that it punishes whoever doesn't move out more due to suddenly taking all the hits. It's only light attacks though, so it won't do much vs tanks.\n\nCorona Burst is a simple Heavy attack with added damage on top.\n\nStarlance is a precise attack that lets you ignore a good portion of the target's guard. This makes it effective against high agility targets who generally have low guard to begin with, while still letting you do acceptable damage to people with medium guard levels too.\n\nFinally, Stardust Reverie is another zone control tool that helps you prevent enemies from rushing your position and denying your long range passive. You can use it early in a fight and keep adjusting the range as enemies approach you.","keyAbility":"Celestial Artillery","abilities":["Starfall","Corona Burst","Stardust Reverie","Starlance"]},{"id":"still-stone-style","name":"Still Stone Style","tier":2,"role1":"Defender","role2":"Striker","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Cultivator or Martial Artist mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Perception, Insight, Medicine, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The Nio have stood at the gates of shrines, temples, and holy places for centuries, carved in stone yet bound in spirit. Many of them never stir, sleeping away decades in statue form. But history remembers the few who did awaken when their sacred grounds were threatened.\n\nThe most famous account comes from the fall of the Twin Gate of Renkoji, The temple,one of the oldest temples that existed in Kirara, was guarded by two great Nio known as Agyo and Ungyo\n\nWhen an enemy force descended upon the shrine, the monks inside knew that they would not be able to hold it. But the wardens stepped down from their pedestals for the first time in living memory. They fought without weapons, their arms and fists breaking spears like kindling, their bodies weathering blows that would have felled a dozen warriors. When enemies slipped past, the guardians leapt to intercept, placing themselves between blade and priest.\n\nThe monks of RenkMji observed their movements in awe. After the battle, when the twin wardens finally fell and their bodies shattered at the temple threshold, the surviving disciples etched every move into scrolls. They called it the Still Stone Style, named so out of respect for the guardians who gave their life to protect them.\n\nTo this day, Nio and other devoted martial artists practice the style, its philosophy unchanged: To become the wall between your enemies and your friends.\n\n\"Let your body be like jade, unyielding and pure.\" -Still Stone Style 5th scroll.","guide":"-","keyAbility":"Shielding Fist","abilities":["Steadfast Earth Stance","Hardening Fist","Earthen Guardian","Secret Art: Jade Skin"]},{"id":"strategist","name":"Strategist","tier":3,"role1":"Support","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Tactician mastered","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason, Awareness or Cunning.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Deception, Stealth, Appraise, History, Magic, Perception, Intimidation, Negotiation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Shannon studied the field as she idly leaned to avoid a bolt of magical fire. Kane and Mara were making a fighting retreat not too far away, the burly guardian ensuring the much smaller demon woman was safe while providing her the openings to harass the three enemies pressuring them. Behind the line of melee, Kaede was darting around a frustrated pyromancer, most of her attacks deflecting off hasty arcane barriers as she disrupted his attempts to bring his firepower to bear. Shannon's own pistol weighed heavily in her hand but the enemy mage was out of range and she didn't want to risk hitting her team by firing into the melee. And besides, her best contribution wasn't necessarily to provide ranged fire support, but to be slightly removed from the battle to help guide it.\n\nAnd suddenly, a moment. The enemy team's highlander was screened by his teammates and was making an all or nothing push against Mara.\n\n\"Fall back!\" she commanded, mana surging through her voice and the air to lend it that much more punch. Her fan snapped open and closed in a triple rhythm, carrying an equal amount of meaning to her order. Not a full retreat but a bait to break their ranks and counter attack.\n\n\"Kaede, you too!\" The aggressive catgirl blinked and then darted away from the pyromancer she'd been hassling, ending up slightly behind the enemy front line. That confused them even more as they struggled to decide if breaking Shannon's defensive formation was the play or to punish the now seemingly vulnerable Kaede. But before they could make up their mind, Kane and Mara suddenly planted their feet and turned, taking the chasing highlander by surprise as they re-engaged him.\n\n\"Now swing the hammer! Anvil formation!\"\n\nKaede seemed to glide right through the staggered enemy frontline formation and slammed into the back of the highlander. The man went tumbling from her axe strike and didn't get back up. Suddenly, the battlefield had reversed itself and the pressure had instantly shifted. The enemy confusedly reformed their battered front line and a fireball crashed into Kane's shield to no seeming effect.\n\nBut that breath of a moment had allowed her team to recover their footing and bearings. It was time to end it.\n\n\"Secret Art: Shock and Awe!\"\n\nEnergy swirled around Shannon as she snapped her fan shut and pointed it directly at the reeling enemy. \"Take them!\"\n\nIt was over seconds later and she barely heard the judge announce Team Shannon as the winners over the cheering crowd.","guide":"The strategist is a continuation of the tactician class and like it focuses on supporting their team.\n\nSound the retreat is limited in its use, but very useful if you do have to run away from an enemy you can't beat. Feigned retreat on the other hand is used for a temporary retreat, functioning like Order: Retreat but working on more than 1 ally. The free attack of opportunity is also nice and your allies can choose whether they want to make a light attack, or spend the 1 RP for a heavy one.\n\nAnvil tactics is another ability that lets an ally make an attack of opportunity. If they can spare the RP, getting a heavy attack with lock on can be pretty valuable. Even without it, the low cost on anvil tactics still makes it worthwhile to use as long as you can guarantee the attack.\n\nWall Formation is for when you need to stand your ground, giving all allies next to eachother a noticeable increase to guard and block. Do be wary that this type of positioning may make you more vulnerable to AoE attacks.\n\nFinally, your secret art: Shock & Awe is best used as soon as possible as long as your allies can use all the AP it gives to gain momentum.","keyAbility":"Sound the retreat","abilities":["Wall Formation","Feigned Retreat","Anvil Tactics","Secret Art: Shock & Awe"]},{"id":"summoner","name":"Summoner","tier":2,"role1":"Specialist","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Any class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning, Reason, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on any non-crafting and non-gathering skill. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"A summoning that contracts with Eidolons.\n\n(See Summoning Contract breakthroughs for which eidolons you can contract with.)","guide":"Soon.","keyAbility":"Summoning Basics","abilities":["Channel Eidolon","Summon Lesser Eidolon","Unsummon","Secret Art: Summon Eidolon"]},{"id":"swashbuckler","name":"Swashbuckler","tier":2,"role1":"Controller","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Fighter, Rogue, Ranger, Cultivator, Adventurer, Maid or Forager mastered. Proficient in Light Swords.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Stealth, Athletics, Roguecraft, Survival or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The deck rolled under her feet and rain lashed down in windblown sheets. Lightning flashed in the near distance, the roar of the thunder nearly drowned out by the crashing waves. Her long blue coat snapped in the wind as she brought her swords up in a parry, steel ringing against steel. She grinned, stepping back with a flourishing spin of her cutlasses.\n\n\"You've got skill, kid!\" she praised.\n\n\"It's over, Captain Rook! Your crew has abandoned you, you have nowhere to run!\" the kid shouted, a young Lieutenant. Half a dozen of his comrades were collapsed on the deck behind him. There were a handful still on their feet, muskets aimed but unwilling to fire into the melee. If their powder would even spark in this storm, they weren't protecting their frizzen pans at all from the rain. They were part of the Holy Westrian Navy, uniforms that were normally crisp and white with golden highlighting hanging heavy with water and blood stains, and had laid this ambush specifically to capture her. Well&ambush was giving them a little too much credit, she'd known this \u0018merchant ship' had been packed with Navy men before it left port. But who was she to say no to such a polite challenge?\n\n\"Well, if yer so keen to bring me in, c'mon then.\" She gestured with one of her blades and then rasped them against each other as she settled into an easy stance that seemed to ignore the heavy pitching of the deck.\n\nThe heavy blow of his longsword slid easily off her cutlass in a neat deflection and she retaliated with an embarrassing swat to the rear as she danced past him, sending him staggering. Then she lunged, her sword ringing against the base of his, knocking it from his hands and overboard into the ocean. Her second sword, she hooked behind his knee with the back of the blade, sending him sprawling. Before he could push himself up, she planted a boot on his chest and leveled her cutlass at his throat.\n\n\"Need to watch that footing, kid. Could get ya killed!\"\n\n\"W-what are you men waiting for?! Shoot her!\" The musketmen snapped their aim up and fired.\n\nWell, they clicked, at least. \"Gotta keep that powder dry!\" she coached with a laugh.\n\n\"Anyway, as fun as this was, I gotta get going. What's your name, anyway?\"\n\n\"Lieutenant Mortimer Augustus--\"\n\n\"That's a horrible name, Mort!\" Rook stepped back, her swords rasping back home into their scabbards. \"Better luck next time!\"\n\nBefore Lieutenant Mort could say anything else, Rook grabbed onto a rope that suddenly landed between them from above and she was pulled off her feet into the sky. Faintly, through the rain, a small airship could be seen as it pulled up and away. When Rook was firmly back on deck of her ship, she patted the men on the shoulder that hauled her up and gratefully accepted her Captain's Hat from her first officer.\n\n\"Alright lads, back home to Vivian! We got what we wanted today!\"","guide":"Class by Buntaoo.\n\nThe Swashbuckler being a focus based melee character, excels at striking at enemies weaknesses using Staggering Slice to first to lower their evasion then following it up with the Deckbreaker to force them to make a decision of either taking the Off-Step Debuff or the raw damage from the Swashbuckler.\n\nDust Kick is a Universal Defensive tool with a lot of flexibility where you can choose to control enemies to force them to a spot you want them to be or save your backline from being attacked by them.\n\nDuring Exposing Edge, All your abilities become stronger making you a more serious threat than before with every move now being noticeably stronger, especially Staggering Slice and Deckbreaker combo being more potent and likely to force a reaction out of your enemies.\n\nFAQ\n\nQ: When it says my debuffs go away at the end of my next turn, does that mean they disappear when my current turn ends?\nA: No, after your turn ends they remain on the target. It is only after your turn after that that the debuffs dissappear, unless you re-apply them.","keyAbility":"Take the advantage","abilities":["Staggering Slice","Deckbreaker","Dust Kick","Exposing Edge"]},{"id":"sword-paladin","name":"Sword Paladin","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Human.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on any non crafting or gathering skill. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Paladins are powerful warriors who receive their powers from their god. Sword paladins are fearless juggernauts from whom escape is nearly impossible.","guide":"The sword paladin is the more aggressive counterpart of the shield paladin.\n\nThey specialize in hunting down their enemies by limiting their escape options. Mark of Justice slows down an enemy to the same level as a basic human. Very useful against Fae, Cats and rogue-ish characters. It also opens an enemy up to other abilities.\n\nJustice Blade can only be used against an enemy marked by Mark of Justice. It trades 1 AP cost in 1 for mana, which is a fair trade.\n\nWhen an enemy is low enough, Divine Smite can finish them off automatically dealing max damage with full pierce. If the enemy is not low enough, this ability still gets used but without the extra benefits so be aware of that. The enemy can also still dodge it, but it's good for finishing grunt type enemies.","keyAbility":"Holy Weapon","abilities":["Mark of Justice","Justice Blade","Paragon of Virtue","Divine Smite"]},{"id":"sword-saint","name":"Sword Saint","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Iaido style mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Awareness or Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Intimidation, History, Insight, Art, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"A warrior with peerless skill in swordsmanship.","guide":"The Sword Saint has further mastered Iaido. Resheathe allows them to regain the Sheathed state during combat without relying on a kiri-tsuke killing blow. The AP cost is high though and it should only be used during a lull in combat.\n\nKiri-tsuke II is an upgrade from the normal kiri-tsuke that combos of Iai strike, saving you some AP.\n\nChiburi Noto II is also a straight upgrade from Chiburi Noto, adding full pierce on top of the previous benefit.\n\nFlash Cut is a mana intensive attack that does unavoidable heavy damage. It requires you to be in the sheathed state, which makes it only really an option in the beginning of the fight. Flash Cut into Iai strike into Kiri-tsuke II is a very dangerous combo.\n\nThe Secret Art: Tsubame Gaeshi has high potential damage, but also does some guaranteed damage. You are guaranteed at least 1 hit, most likely a second and a third if you're lucky or if the target is out of RP. You can use this even early in the fight, especially if you've already softened up an enemy through your other attacks with sure hit and lock on.","keyAbility":"Resheathe","abilities":["Kiri-tsuke II","Flash Cut","Chiburi Noto II","Secret Art: Tsubame Gaeshi"]},{"id":"tactician","name":"Tactician","tier":2,"role1":"Support","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Any class mastered, 5 skill points in the history skill.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason, Awareness or Cunning.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on History. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in this skill.","description":"Tacticians are capable battlefield commanders that augment their allies’ natural abilities through tactical advance and organization.","guide":"The tactician is a support class that has a lot of mobility options. Stratagem: Lightning not only gives all your allies extra initiative, it also lets them move once for free. This is very useful if your part consists of primarily melee fighters.\n\nOrder: Retreat is primarily meant to be a defensive tool, pulling an injured ally out of a bad situation. It can also be used offensively. You can move up towards the enemy and then Order: Retreat them closer to you and the enemy.\n\nTag Rotation is useful in chokepoints. Let your first ally make attacks, then tag rotate to let your second melee fighter make their attacks. It can also be used when a weaker ally is about to be attacked to swap positions with a tank.\n\nTake Cover! is used in long range shootoffs. Turning your low cover into high cover will give your allies an edge in ranged battles.\n\nAttack in Detail is used against boss type enemies. The primary benefit is the +1 damage all your allies get against the target. It's more useful if your allies use light attacks, due to more attacks gaining a benefit from the +1. It also is more useful the more allies you have. When you only have 2 allies with you, the benefit of this ability might not be high enough vs just firing an attack yourself.","keyAbility":"Scholar of Tactics","abilities":["Tag Rotation","Order: Retreat","Stratagem: Lightning","Attack in Detail"]},{"id":"tavern-brawler","name":"Tavern Brawler","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Controller","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Any class mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Perception, Insight, Survival, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Fighters who have learned the art of a drunken brawl.","guide":"Tavern Brawler is a weird striker that relies on improvised weapons for their abilities. They can easily grab one with Chair Grab. It can still only be used once per turn, so if you don't have another weapon be careful you don't break it too early. Here is where Martial Artist has an advantage over a Fighter→Tavern Brawler, they can always use unarmed attacks. Those without unarmed attacks may want to consider having daggers on them as back up, or using a longsword for their weapon.\n\nBottle Smash and Bottle Toss are both attacks that break the improvised weapon and apply daze. Bottle Toss has longer range, but it also costs a bit of mana. The drawback of breaking the weapon isn't too bad as long as you use it as the last action in your turn. Bottle Smash also has the prone keyword, letting it be used while you're on the floor. This is relevant because of the Tackle ability.\n\nTackle is a bit of a double-edged sword. It costs no AP, but also deals no damage. Knocking the enemy prone is powerful, but even if you land the attack you will also fall prone. The enemy can also dodge it to make only you fall prone. This is not all bad though. Standing up is only 1 AP, so if you land the knockdown you could spend 3 AP of attacks against the target against which they will struggle to react. If they choose to avoid your attack by spending an RP, you have now wasted one of their RP's for only 1 AP of your own, which is more efficient than a normal heavy attack. You can also use it at the end of your actions, knock yourself and the enemy prone the hit them with the bottle smash.\n\nImprovised Defense's effectiveness relies greatly on what is around you. Something like a table would be very effective cover, but you may not always have that luxury. Tavern brawler requires some level of creativity to get the most use out of.","keyAbility":"Improvised Weaponry","abilities":["Bottle Smash","Improvised Defense","Bottle Toss","Tackle"]},{"id":"temporal-trickster","name":"Temporal Trickster","tier":3,"role1":"Utility","role2":"Controller","difficulty":4,"requirements":"Time Thief mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Cunning or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on any non crafting or gathering skill. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"-","guide":"-","keyAbility":"Mending","abilities":["Position Rewind","Stasis","Delay Time","Secret Art: Double Accel"]},{"id":"thief","name":"Thief","tier":2,"role1":"Utility","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Be a rabbitfolk or have Rogue mastered and possess the Decipher Magic ability.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness or Cunning.","soul":"You gain +1 Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Appraise, Athletics, Stealth, Deception, Roguecraft, Perception, Insight, Negotiation, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Pickpockets and scallywags.","guide":"The thief is a class that steals things, whether it's small objects, magic or a grand robbery.\n\nTheir infiltrate ability lets them sneak into magically guarded places without raising any suspicion.\n\nWith Quick Getaway, you are able to escape from pursuers when you use it after Feint or Disengage. If used after feint, you can effectively more for 5 AP in 1 turn which lets you move faster than the enemy. Even against groups, they will never be able to catch up and attack in the same turn without movement abilities of their own.\n\nFast Hands can also help with escaping, allowing you to open or close doors without using AP on them. It can also just let you draw a weapon or consumable.\n\nSnatch is a situational ability that makes it impossible for enemies to use consumables against you when you are close to them. If you are able to close in on an enemy before they can draw their weapon, you can even steal that.\n\nSpellsteal is another situational ability that lets you steal a buff from the enemy. It removes the buff from the enemy, so even if you can't use it very well it may still be worth using.","keyAbility":"Infiltrate","abilities":["Fast Hands","Snatch","Quick Getaway","Spellsteal"]},{"id":"timberwright","name":"Timberwright","tier":2,"role1":"Artisan","role2":"Striker","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Carpenter mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness or Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Power, Focus or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Carpentry.","description":"Enid's Dogfolk ears drooped down as the Timberwright foreman scolded her. So zealous to learn and finish her tasks, she worked with great effort—but alone, to put the finishing touches on a wall frame that would be a part of a new facility for a famous adventuring guild. Overwhelmed with work Enid nearly fell over from exhaustion before her mentor told her to take a break.\n\n\"A big project like this, you could do it with just one person sure,\" the Timberwright folded his arms across his chest and nodded in thought. \"But you have to learn to work with others Eni. Mothergreen wasn't built in a day... and it wasn't built with one builder. We craftsmen have to stick together and help each other out... that's how we create things that are beloved by many. Things that will be remembered long before we pass.\"\n\nEnid yawned and then hit herself for the disrespect, \"Teacher, I just want to make sure that it gets done, so I have to do it myself right?\"\n\nHer mentor smiled, \"Perhaps this time you can, but there will be a time when you have to learn to work with others. You're always off on your own.\"\n\nMonths passed and the Lumberwright put Enid in charge of a big project—to go along with a team to build barracks for the workers of a new magical fuel mine. The Chimera girl, who was comfortable in her solitude was quite happy to keep to herself in the middle of the march column—when suddenly a scream rang out.\n\n\"Hobs... out here?!\" the fighter shouted.\n\nA miner clutched his pickaxe as he spun around, swinging his pickaxe at the hobgoblins wildly as they ducked and weaved through every strike delivering small cuts and blows with every dodge. The acolyte, in an attempt to assist tripped into the miner as they fell into a pile on the ground.\n\nThe Hobgoblin went in for a heavy blow on the two twisted upon the ground as the fighter stepped in to guard them. Enid clutched her axe, swallowed hard and stepped forward as her untrained nerves shook her to the core. The Hob did as Hobs do, spinning his blade wildly as he slathered the blade with its own tongue in a taunt.\n\nEnid nearly lost her grip with her axe, thoughts flashing across her mind—\"I don't know how to fight...I can't do this alone.\" She looked up at the Hob and then back to the Fighter when her mentors words echoed clearly in her mind, \"There will be a time where you have to learn to work with others.\" She hit herself lightly once more, glancing once more at the seasoned fighter beside her.\n\nThe Hobgoblin lunged, blade whistling through the air as iron met iron in rhythmic percussion. The Fighter's heel dug in, knowing that he couldn't evade or have his comrades injured by the beast. He leaned back and then delivered a light kick to push the Hobgoblin away. Much to his shock, a force pushed back on his foot.\n\nStanding behind the Hobgloblin, waiting for her chance to strike in unison, she pulled the blade of her axe back as it dripped with Hob blood. The creature whined as it fell to the ground, blood pooling underneath it. It was a perfectly coordinated attack.\n\nEnid smiled in relief as her mentor's words were realized, \"Let's stick together...\" she said quietly, more to herself than anyone else as the Fighter nodded in approval. The Chimera felt the wisdom of her Timberwright mentor that day, carried on the wind. \"That's how we build something that lasts.\"","guide":"-","keyAbility":"Timberwright's Core Crafting","abilities":["Stable Foundation","Strengthening the Bond","Expertise Study (Carpentry)","Secret Art: Beaver Timber Fang"]},{"id":"time-thief","name":"Time Thief","tier":2,"role1":"Utility","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Rogue mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Cunning or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on any non crafting or gathering skill. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Time Thieves manipulate time to pull off perfect heists.","guide":"The time thief is a utility class that manipulates their own time to gain advantages.\n\nWith Shatter Time, you can act multiple times in a turn. This can let you act after teammates when needed, act when an enemy has moved closer to you or enemies have positioned for an AoE or several other things. It doesn't let you use an ability multiple times in a round though.\n\nStart Dash is a free movement, but it can only be used as the first action on your turn. This movement does provoke attacks of opportunity and you can't disengage or feint before it, so you may want to evasive maneuver before your turn begins if you plan to use it while engaged in melee.\n\nSteal Time gives you a small boost to your initiative while lowering that of enemy. This may let your allies potentially act before the enemy does on subsequent turns.\n\nSecret Art: Rewind lets you do stupid things without being punished for it. You can potentially hit into enemy counters to see what happens, run past suspicious hallways that may be trapped, attempt dangerous jumps across a cliff. If the result is bad, you can simply rewind time and either try again or do something else entirely.","keyAbility":"Thefts of the past","abilities":["Start Dash","Steal Time","Shatter Time","Secret Art: Rewind"]},{"id":"transcendent-lightning-style","name":"Transcendent Lightning Style","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Cultivator or Martial Artist mastered, any tier 2 mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Perception, Intimidation, Survival or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Natsuki blinked in confusion at her surroundings, the wind from the mountains tugging at her robes and hair. Lightning danced around her limbs and she was tense, like a battle was upon her. Bells and gongs rang behind her from a village, all indicating some sort of attack. Which would explain why she was there, ready to defend them.\n\nBut she didn't remember anything that would have warranted her assuming the Stance of Heavenly Lightning. Had she been training? &No, that wasn't wise if she was there to defend the village. Like a fog slowly lifting, she remembered being dispatched from the temple to investigate missing villagers nearby and&even a completely wiped out hamlet.\n\nIn a flash, her mind cleared. A huge face loomed in front of her, lipless mouth spread in a permanent, horrific grin. Empty eye sockets bore down on her as it opened its mouth.\n\nAkuma, her mind identified. Too large to be a bakemono, too little devastation to be a kaiju. A kaibutsu, then. And a tricky one at that.\n\nShe traced the thin, tentacle-like neck back to the main body, a pulsing globule of flesh as large as a house. Other heads grinned at her from their own serpentine necks. They were quiet, no longer singing, as if they wanted to enjoy her terror as she was devoured. Like it had probably picked off villagers one by one, using its song to make everyone forget until it struck again.\n\nBut the akuma had made a grave mistake. Its weapon was song and sound. But her's&her's was what thunder chased and could never catch.\n\nThe air cracked and the akuma howled in agony as she came to a stop on the other side of it, lighting glittering across her skin and snapping at the wind.\n\n\"Lightning Release,\" she said, the mantra unnecessary but it felt appropriate. \"Living Lightning.\"\n\nAll she had to do was kill the akuma before it could sing again. Simple as that. Natsuki clenched her fists and thunder boomed again, desperately giving chase to her lightning.","guide":"The Transcendent Lightning Style is a martial arts based class focused on speed. Like most martial arts based classes, it expects you to lean heavily into that playstyle.\n\nThe Heavenly Lightning Stance is their specific stance and is essentially required to use their other two active abilities. Because it goes away when you use a non-melee attack, it's not suited for people that like to use ranged attacks. Its main use is to allow you to move freely across the battlefield, but if you're already engaged in a melee fight you can also use the free sidestep movement to move away safely.\n\nLightning Lariat is your opening attack move of choice, letting you move and attack in the same action. Stance into Lariat gets you in the fight at basically no mana cost, potentially with a trick attack and with extra damage if you moved far enough for your key ability to activate.\n\nLiving Lightning combo's well with Lightning Lariat but essentially requires you to be in your lightning stance to be usable. It requires you to move in a straight line, similar to horse movement. Because Lightning Lariat already forces you to move like that, you can use living lightning while use that. You can also move through the target you're hitting with the lariat to hit them with the living lightning as well.\n\nYour secret art: Lightning Release is best used immediately at the start of the fight unless you have a better secret art available. It gives you buffs that last for the entire encounter and even activates your lightning stance at the same time.\n\nAs a last note, this style naturally combo's well with the Sky Talon Style due to the lightning stance giving you the benefits of the wind stance as well.","keyAbility":"Rolling Thunder","abilities":["Heavenly Lightning Stance","Lightning Lariat","Living Lightning","Secret Art: Lightning Release"]},{"id":"transmuter","name":"Transmuter","tier":1,"role1":"Artisan","role2":"Utility","difficulty":2,"requirements":"None","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness. In addition, as an errand you can use Co-Craft to help in crafting once. Only 1 person can Co-Craft with a craft at a time. When you Co-Craft, you help another crafter allowing you to use a single Co-Craft ability in their crafting session. Your Co-Craft actions count towards the 1 limit of using an ability for the main crafter. (Both you and the main crafter cannot use the same co-craft ability in one crafting session). You must declare you are helping before any crafting actions are taken by the main crafter.","skills":"You gain 5 Transmuter points. Pick one of the crafting disciplines, such as blacksmithing or alchemy. Whenever you use your Transmuter abilities in a craft of that discipline, you may add your transmuter points as bonus to that ability (even if it's not a roll).","description":"In the dust of an artisan's workshop or in the open clearings of a logging company, the hum and chirps of transmutation can be heard. Transmutation is an art, a magic as ancient as Lyr. Long before the shadows of the great calamity, Transmuters were scholars who questioned the very nature of existence. This pursuit led to a mastery over both destruction and creation, spinning the threads of reality itself into a tapestry.\n\nTransmutation is the second branch of alchemy and created a revolution in society. It replaced primitive methods such as smelting and manual refinement—which previously had artisans sweating over blazing crucibles into the dark hours of the night. It isn't uncommon for master craftsmen to have a Transmuter in their employ or as a partner, processing material in the atelier or even helping with the crafting itself. In fact, nowadays there is rarely a town across Lyr without at least one person versed in the basics of this ancient art.\n\nTransmuters manipulate matter at its core, unraveling its threads and rebuilding them into entire new forms. They can shatter stone into dust, or create small figurines from blocks of wood. The control of Transmutation is only limited by skill and imagination. Transmutation is the second branch of Alchemy, which itself is one of the great pillars of Arcane Magic.\n\nYet with great power comes great peril. Those who understand Transmutation know that creation and destruction are two sides of the same coin. It requires a sound mind and body to walk the delicate balance, making Transmuters some of the most respected Artisans in any community they are in.","guide":"Transmuter is a class that helps crafting for other classes and provided utility in combat.\n\nTransmute weapon is a simple ability that lets you create a weapon for yourself or ally. While you probably don't want to rely entirely on this for your equipment as it costs mana and may not always work, it's good for providing an emergency backup or if there happens to be special material nearby.\n\nTransmute wall is a reactionary defense against a ranged attack. Because you'll be able to see the damage you're about to take in most cases, it will be easy to judge how much mana you should spend on this. Because it's a wall and not you blocking, this can help you defend against full pierce type of attacks.\n\nTransmute terrain is a versatile ability that lets you create walls, bridges, ledges and other terrain. You can spend a lot of mana on this at once, allowing for some creative use such as completely boxing in a character, pushing yourself 60ft into the air for a sniper position, pushing enemies off a cliff and much more.\n\nDeconstruct is an interlude ability that lets you recycle useless items into usable material. Best to use it when you have a large amount of things piled up.\n\nIn crafting, you have a few unique abilities as well as the ability to co-craft. This costs you nothing to do by default, so use it whenever you can. Two of your co-craft abilities do have a cost and you can also use them in your own crafts. Temperature Shock is useful early when you roll poorly to have a guaranteed number to your next roll. Once your bonus grows higher or if you need to gamble, Alchemic catch will be better as it uses the full bonus you have. If you're co crafting and don't want to spend money, you can just use bouncing ideas for a free small bonus. Finally ragequit is useful if you don't care about profit by itself and only want to make something big. You do lose a lot when using this, so avoid it unless you know what you're doing.","keyAbility":"Transmutation Basics","abilities":["Transmute Weapon","Transmute Wall","Deconstruction","Transmute Terrain"]},{"id":"trapper","name":"Trapper","tier":2,"role1":"Controller","role2":"Utility","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Ranger mastered","heart":"You gain +1 to Cunning or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Power or Agility. The food units received from your key ability is increased to 1d10 x 10 food units.","skills":"You gain 5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Stealth, Medicine, Perception, Survival, Animal Husbandry or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Carter's breath came in sharp gasps as he leapt over a fallen log, his boots scraping the moss off the top with how narrowly he cleared it. Behind him, frustrated yells followed him as his pursuers crashed through the thick brush and thorny bushes. He knew the forest around him better than his hometown and that gave him an advantage, but the catfolk chasing him were both faster and more nimble than he was. It was taking every trick he knew to stay ahead of the poachers.\n\nThe twang of a bowstring had him juking right and diving over a particularly nastily thorny berry bush, just barely avoiding the arrow that snapped past him. He landed and rolled, still careful of his own bow and supply of arrows, and he felt a smile pull at his lips. The forest opened up slightly into a small clearing with limited brush and only a couple fallen trees for cover. The old scorch marks on some of the trees told him that there had likely been a lightning strike that had briefly burned out the area some months ago. This was exactly where he expected to get \"caught\".\n\nHe carefully retreated to the center of the small clearing and collapsed back against one of the scorched logs. He was still catching his breath when the three catfolk pushed into the open area, eyes scanning around before locking on him. They raised their bows and the leader stepped forward a few paces.\n\n\"Finally! You know there was no way for you to outrun us. Now you're just gonna die tired,\" the poacher boasted. He raised his bow and knocked an arrow. \"Just stay still for a second, will you?\"\n\nCarter grinned. \"Sure, buddy.\" With the hand that was out of sight of the catfolk, he cut three small lines. There was the horrible snap and crunch of a bear trap snapping closed on a leg followed almost instantly by the surprised shriek of a catgirl suddenly finding herself tangled in a net and hanging twenty feet off the ground. The catfolk caught in the bear trap barely had much time to scream in pain himself before a log swung out of the trees and caught him straight in the chest, carrying him fully out of the clearing in a crash.\n\nThe poacher leader took a surprised step back and fell with a startled yelp, the support for the pit trap he'd walked over no longer in place. Carter hopped to his feet and jogged over to the hole, absently eyeing the hanging catgirl. She'd dropped her bow and had fumbled her knife in her struggles, so she was good and stuck. He peaked over into the hole with a smug grin, bow in hand and arrow ready.\n\n\"Why don't we have a nice conversation about why you don't poach in my forests, huh?\"","guide":"Trapper is a primarily controller class that relies on preparation time to spring unexpected traps on the enemy.\n\nYour main ability is Place Trap. You require at least 1 minute or 1 hour of prep time, but the good thing is that you don't have to choose which trap you're placing until you trigger it. The most important thing to be aware of is that you can only trigger these when an enemy walks into your range. Log Swing is guaranteed damage and a knockback, which can let an enemy potentially trigger multiple traps to approach you again. Snare is the weakest trap, but has the advantage of having multiple uses per trap. Pitfall is the most punishing trap, 20ft down can be deep enough that enemies may struggle to get out. Net is the most offensive trap, as it roots the enemy potentially making them vulnerable to attacks if they are out of AP to instantly free themselves.\n\nAmbush Trapper is essentially a free trap use, provided that you ambush the enemy which is something that you want to do as a trapper already anyway. Bear trap is the only trap you can use without preparation time, though it's not a hidden one. Still, in a choke point or if combod with displacement abilities it can be powerful.\n\nYour Secret Art: Guiding Shot can also be used to force an enemy into a bear trap in addition to its normal trap activating effect. It's best used on low block enemies that cannot afford to tank a sure hit attack.","keyAbility":"Trap Basics","abilities":["Bear Trap","Place Trap","Ambush Trapper","Secret Art: Guiding Shot"]},{"id":"trickster","name":"Trickster","tier":3,"role1":"Support","role2":"Utility","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Two classes mastered, of which 1 must be a tier 2 class.","heart":"You gain +1 Cunning.","soul":"You gain +1 Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Deception. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Tricksters are a support class that cause chaos on the battlefield. The world is a stage.","guide":"The trickster is a support class that provides weird and unique benefits to the team.\n\nAssign Decoy gives the unique ability to taunt an enemy by an ally that would normally have no access to it. It can be used to temporarily make an enemy switch targets or if in a party without a tank, can be used to set up a sort of tank rotation.\n\nSwap gives the Trickster high control over the battlefield. They can walk near the edge of a clif, then swap an enemy next to it. Forcefully group enemies to setup for a teammates AoE attack. Swap an ally out of danger and much more. Extremely versatile and due to its Rapid nature and low cost can easily be spammed.\n\nMisdirected Blow has some conditions for it to be good, but it can turn enemies against each other. Most effective on tricksters with high agility, as it can let you evade blows that will hit most other targets.\n\nThe Secret Art Grand Theater allows the trickster to set up a magnificent performance. They can force enemies to hit each other and give allies free actions. They just need to be careful, because even their allies are forced to attack and careless use may force them to attack an ally.\n\nTheir perfect mimicry has little combat potential, but it allows a trickster to truly infiltrate a place and sow chaos.","keyAbility":"Perfect Mimicry","abilities":["Assign Decoy","Swap","Misdirected Blow","Secret Art: The Grand Theater"]},{"id":"true-shinigami-eyes","name":"True Shinigami Eyes","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Utility","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Shinigami Eyes mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Power.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Stealth, Medicine, Perception, Insight or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Wielders of the shinigami eyes, rare as they are, have the ability to perceive the death of living things. For most of them, that is where it ends. However, there are those who over time grow an even deeper understanding of death. They can see the death not just of living things, but also of objects and even non-physical things such as magic. This enhanced perception has given those wielders the name of the ‘True Shinigami Eyes’.","guide":"Wielders of the True Shinigami Eyes bring some personal defense and utility to the table. Failing a save can be devastating, but Cut Away gives them an extremely high chance to succeed as most of them possess high Focus.\n\nThe high focus also helps them with Cut Magic, allowing them to potentially break barriers and other magic effects at little cost. Barriers are the most obvious thing, but even things like Glittershards are considered temporary magic effects.\n\nPoint of Death II is an upgrade of the original Point of Death ability. Its primary use is to finish off high toughness enemies, but the AP refund makes it a tempting choice against any weak foe.\n\nTheir key ability allows them to kill non-living things as well as they do living things, and lets them build up marks for their ultimate ability: 7 Points of Death.\n\nThis Climax Art grows in power the more they attack a single target. It takes several turns to build up and must be used against a weakened enemy, but it has high damage potential. Similar to their previous Secret Art, the damage is static so you know what to expect even if there’s a small risk of missing.","keyAbility":"Improved Death Perception","abilities":["Cut Away","Point of Death II","Cut Magic","Secret Art: 7 Points of Death"]},{"id":"vampire","name":"Vampire","tier":1,"role1":"Specialist","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Must have the Curse of Vampirism breakthrough.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on any non crafting or gathering skill. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Vampires are those who are cursed, using their cursed abilities to their advantage.","guide":"Vampires are a versatile class with a slight focus on unarmed combat.\n\nVampire Bite is the only way that vampires can regenerate mana and using it whenever possible is required to keep your mana high. The high AP cost makes it hard to use in a straight up battle. You can combine it with Vampiric Fascination to remove one enemy from the battle. The chosen target will move towards you and you can easily follow it up with your bite on the next turn, dealing guaranteed full pierce damage. Action economy wise, this is still not very efficient though. In harder fights, it may be more worthwhile to fight normally at the start and only start looking for enemies to drain near the end of a fight.\n\nCloak of Bats is a manaless teleport that can also be used offensively. The RP cost on it is higher than that of a basic defense, but the teleport lets you potentially avoid attacks that are undodgeable. Whether you're stuck in bad terrain, about to get hit by an AoE effect or you need to get behind cover, Cloak of Bats will get you out of almost any bad situation.\n\nBlood Frenzy is your last resort move. While it lasts you become very difficult to kill, especially if enemies are low on RP and can't avoid your attacks to prevent you from regaining health. It does however, lock you into a very specific set of actions. You can't regain mana through vampire bite or switch to a ranged weapon to hit an enemy that's far away. You also cannot turn it off manually, which may lead you to losing all your mana even when you no longer need the healing effect. This is especially devastating for a vampire, since mana regeneration is a problem for them.\n\nVampire Shapeshift is a cheap utility tool that can be useful for infiltration and sneaking. Shapeshifting into a bat is also an easy way to gain access to flight to reach high ground.\n\nThe last thing to keep in mind as a vampire is that your vampire bite is not just a combat ability. You are able to use it on willing targets without hurting them, though they still lose mana. You will have to convince them first though, someone charmed by Vampiric Fascination does not count as a willing person.","keyAbility":"Vampiric Strength","abilities":["Vampiric Fascination","Vampire Shapeshift","Cloak of Bats","Blood Frenzy"]},{"id":"vampire-lord","name":"Vampire Lord","tier":2,"role1":"Specialist","role2":"Striker","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Vampire mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on any non crafting or gathering skill. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Vampire Lords drift through the pages of history like living shadows—accursed souls chained to undeath by the very forces that empower them. In dimly lit taverns, alongside whispered tales of Dragons and other legendary horrors, travelers speak of eerie encounters and boast of glimpses caught at the corner of a moonlit eye. Whether these sightings are truth or fancy, one thing is certain: the name Vampire Lord stirs fear and fascination in equal measure.\n\nUnlike lesser Vampires who lose themselves to bloodlust or despair, Vampire Lords have embraced their curse, searching its depths to forge a power all their own. They understand their twisted existence at a level few can rival, developing uncanny resistances to the sun’s harsh sting and other infamous banes of their kind. Yet what truly sets them apart is their mastery over the delicate threads connecting the Arcane, Faith, and Astra—allowing them to skirt the borders of Higher Order Magic. Their Vampiric Domination arises from this warped interplay of energies, a distant, corrupted echo of the Mystic Eye once claimed by the fabled Aseria clan of Sorthen.\n\nThat unholy gift grants them the power to ensnare weaker minds, exerting a terrible control that echoes across dark corridors and silent chambers. Even so, few mortals have battled a Vampire Lord and returned with their lives, for these lords of night prefer to move in secrecy. Outwardly, they can seem disarmingly regal—yet beneath that lies a being forever dancing on the razor’s edge between life and the endless darkness. Should you cross paths with a Vampire Lord, know this—their secrets run deeper than any mortal can fathom, and their hunger, while tempered, still seeks knowledge and power in their cursed existence.","guide":"A lot of the vampire lord builds on what the vampire does.\n\nFeeding Frenzy gives you a free bite whenever you down someone while in Blood Frenzy, allowing you to regain 1 mana. If fighting a lot of grunts you can reliably kill, this can effectively half the upkeep cost of Blood Frenzy.\n\nVampiric Domination is a stronger version of the fascination. You can choose to have a permanent servant, or you can use it more situationally such as to dominate enemies to extract information from them, dominate people of import to have them aid you. They will know what you did afterwards, so it's recommended not to stay around when you're done with them.\n\nBloodbolt is a simple ranged option that can be lacking as a normal vampire. You can invest HP into it for extra damage, but this might not be worth doing in most cases unless you plan to Blood Frenzy shortly after.\n\nYour Secret Art: Bloody Ritual is a powerful AoE ability. The damage is guaranteed unless the tether is broken and if you can hit enough enemies with the ability, you can even refund the mana you spent on it. Due to the range on the ability and the slowing effect, it can be a powerful zoning tool even if enemies do manage to break it.","keyAbility":"Lord's Dominion","abilities":["Bloodbolt","Feeding Frenzy","Vampiric Domination","Secret Art: Bloody Ritual"]},{"id":"veilguard","name":"Veilguard","tier":3,"role1":"Healer","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Shieldwarden mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason.","soul":"You gain +1 to Power or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Magic, Religion, Medicine, Perception, Negotiation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"-","guide":"-","keyAbility":"Emergency Shields","abilities":["Shield Burst","Redistribute","Purifying Shields","Power Word: Guardian Shield"]},{"id":"venomancer","name":"Venomancer","tier":2,"role1":"Controller","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Alchemist, Culinarian, Cultivator, Farmer, Forager, Maid, Pierrot, Rogue, Ranger or Mycomancer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Cunning.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Stealth, Deception, Roguecraft, Medicine, Survival or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"\"I'm always cleaning up messes,\" Selle complained, gesturing toward the scattered papers, books, and broken chairs. A few drops of dense liquid dropped from the tip of one of her fingers and landed on a wrinkled piece of paper. The mana dense liquid sizzled on contact, quickly burning a hole through the thin material and continued to bubble as it slowly scorched a divot into the wooden floor.\n\n\"Go here, Selle. Remove the complication, Selle. They saw too much, Selle. Wi Vaniin's are supposed to make sure things stay quiet, Selle.\" She flicked her wrist and snapped her fingers. The man that had been trying to sneak his way out the door dropped to the ground in a clatter, gasping and clutching at his throat, the venom in his system resonating with her mana and seizing his muscles. She glanced at him to make sure he stopped twitching before turning back to her captive audience of one. The goblin struggled against his bonds, rocking the chair she had bound him to.\n\n\"Look, neither one of us want me to be here,\" she said, reaching out to steady him so he'd stop making that irritating clomping noise with the chair. \"But you got yourself some really sensitive information and I need you to tell me--\"\n\nA glint of something behind the terrified goblin caught her eye and she only realized she'd thrown him aside after she had shakily lifted a framed picture from his messy desk. Those eyes. The smile. The hat. The signature!\n\n\"--where did you get this?!\"\n\nThe goblin grunted something high pitched through his gag.\n\n\"This is a First Edition Signed Camielelieananu Portrait! Only fifty of these exist in the world! They were a unique promotional item handed out to the first buyers of her Fundamentals of Alchemy book!\"\n\nSelle clutched the portrait gently to her chest and turned with wide, frantic eyes to her captive. All thoughts of recovering the Wi Vanian research data for Endo completely forgotten.\n\n\"Did you meet her? Did she sign your book? DID SHE SHAKE YOUR HAND?!\"\n\nThe sounds of crashing and muffled screaming continued from the isolated workshop escalated as Selle began a renewed hunt for something precious. That book had to be here!","guide":"The Venomancer is a controller whose main goal is to be annoying with poison.\n\nToxic Blast inflicts a weak poison that doesn't do much damage, but takes relatively high amount of AP to remove. It's also on hit and doesn't provoke, so you're safe to use it in melee. Most enemies won't want to spend the time to remove it.\n\nIf they don't, you can hit them with Catalyze to weaker their defenses for your allies. It also opens them up for a crippling poison. The slow can be nice, but the main benefit of crippling poison is the ability to shut down abilities with a fixed distance such as Spirit Jump or Photon Line.\n\nPoison Spray is another way of inflicting Poison to open multiple enemies up for your abilities. If needed, you can also use it against single enemies due to Toxic Blast not being rapid and this class being reliant on having a poison active\n\nResistant Venom is a simple passive ability that makes it more annoying for others to get rid of your poison.","keyAbility":"Toxic Blast","abilities":["Poison Spray","Catalyze","Resistant Venom","Crippling Poison"]},{"id":"venomblade","name":"Venomblade","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Controller","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Alchemist, Culinarian, Cultivator, Farmer, Forager, Maid, Pierrot, Rogue, Ranger or Mycomancer mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Cunning.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Stealth, Deception, Roguecraft, Medicine, Survival or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Drip. Drip. Drip.\n\nThe normal and constant sounds of the swamp were silent, allowing the drops of viscous poison falling from her needles to be clearly audible. Ruo Shui tapped her chin as she stared at the gasping trio in front of her. Shiny needles protruded from gaps in their armor or through their clothing, the dense magic infused venom eating away at them from within. They were fighting it off but it was making their movements sluggish as they turned energies inward to purge it, making them increasingly easy targets. One of their number, their fourth, was already face down in the swampy water, unmoving, his cat tail drifting in the stagnant water like a moldy stick. A wannabe assassin that had tried to take her by surprise.\n\n\"This didn't need to happen,\" she said as she stepped easily through the knee deep water. \"You were warned to not trespass in Hei lands, you were warned to turn back. And now you've paid your price.\"\n\nShe stopped over the man in heavy armor as he definitely stood to his full height, the fresh venom she'd inflicted on him finally being overcome by his own magic.\n\n\"You killed our friend! You killed Iolo!\"\n\nRuo Shui stared at the man for a long moment. \"He literally tried to stab me in the back while we were talking. I feel like it's a little bit deserved, don't you?\"\n\nThe man clicked his tongue in irritation and shifted to look back at his other two companions. They were worse off than he was, exhausted and looking ready to collapse into the water.\n\n\"Fine,\" he said eventually through gritted teeth. \"Let us get our friend and we'll leave.\"\n\nHe took a step to do just that.\n\n\"Oh, I don't think so,\" she said. He froze, his guard coming up. \"You can leave, you and your pretty little lady friends. But your&Iolo, was it? Well, he belongs to the swamp now. And the swamp is Hei land&and you wouldn't be intending on stealing from us&would you?\"\n\nRuo Shui watched in satisfaction as the reduced party staggered away, retreating back toward&wherever it was they came from. Probably from the south and Sarjes. There was a new crop of explorers coming from there recently. Once they were fully out of sight and the sounds of the swamp began to return to normal, she turned to the body of Iolo. She honestly didn't care about him, he could rot in the swamp. But&those knives of his on the other hand. Those had been masterfully made and had delightful little mechanical devices attached to them. She wondered what other trinkets and items he might have on him. Any edge was an edge she'd secure for her people.\n\nTranslator's Note: \"Iolo\" is a catfolk traditional name and is pronounced \"Yolo\" in the common tongue.","guide":"The venomblade is a striker/controller class that slowly kills an enemy by being really annoying. Your damage can be avoided, but an enemy's action economy will be hampered a lot if they choose to do so.\n\nEnvenom weapon is a weapon buff similar to those of a spellblade, but it instead just add 1 poison dmg to every attack. Worse if you like doing heavies, but most of your attacks in this class will be lights.\n\nVenom Strike is your basic poison application. It's rapid, so you can spam it if needed though the mana cost on that will be quite costly if you do. The poison damage by itself isn't great, but that's why you have other abilites such as Deadly Venom.\n\nDeadly Venom is a mana less ability that adds a stack to your poison which increases the damage by a decent amount. Your main goal is to build to 3 stacks with this.\n\nWhen an enemy is at 3 stacks, you can hit them with Outbreak. Outbreak is just a light attack, but against an enemy with maximum poison stacks it adds 3d6 full pierce damage which is a decent amount. You can then combo that with Maximum Dose to guarantee 18 full pierce damage on the hit.","keyAbility":"Envenom Weapon","abilities":["Venom Strike","Deadly Venom","Maximum Dose","Outbreak"]},{"id":"warding-mage","name":"Warding Mage","tier":2,"role1":"Utility","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Mage mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Cunning, Reason or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Stealth, Magic, Perception or Insight or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Warding Mages focus on creating bounded fields that ward off intruders.","guide":"The warding mage is a utility class that relies on setting up defensive barriers. It is unsuited for many normal campaigns, due to the long casting time and only working when enemies come to you. In a campaign focused more around intrigue or where action takes place around a single place, they can provide peace of mind and creates a zone where enemies will struggle to fight in.\n\nMaintaining bounded fields reduces your maximum mana, but they last forever. Maintain the ones you need to and cancel fields once they have exhausted their use.\n\nAlarm Ward is the first field you get. It simply warns you (and others) when someone unwanted enters it. Many vaults, treasure rooms or other rooms containing important goodds or information will contain some form of an Alarm Ward.\n\nExplosive Ward is your second available field. It is usually placed on containers containing papers with sensitive information on it. If anybody tries to steal it, the papers will be destroyed even if the thief manages to get away.\n\nSapping Ward is your final ward and one that greatly reduces the combat potential of any enemies entering it. The weakened condition is already bad enough, but grunts become stunned as well. Because a stunned target has no AP or RP, they will never be able to escape the ward while it lasts, essentially permanently disabling them for the encounter.\n\nThrough hidden wards, you are able to hide your fields. With Disable Magic, you are able to disable other fields making Warding Mages good for infiltration as well.","keyAbility":"Disable Magic","abilities":["Alarm Ward","Hidden Wards","Explosive Ward","Sapping Ward"]},{"id":"wave-palm-style","name":"Wave Palm Style","tier":2,"role1":"Striker","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Cultivator or Martial Artist mastered. Must have at least 1 mystic eye slot open.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 Focus.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Athletics, Negotiation, Perception or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"The Wave Palm style does not strike with force, but disrupts the enemies internal lifeforce.","guide":"The Wave Palm style focuses on disrupting enemy mana usage.\n\nMana Sight lets you see the mana of all enemies. This will let you make better choices on who to attack.\n\nTwo Point Strike is a light attack that applies the Wave Palm effect, which increases the enemies mana costs. It follows into Four Point Strike, which has greatly reduced costs and appiles a stronger debuff if combo'd. Against many normal monsters, the detonation effect for when your stacks exceed their maximum mana will happen quickly due to their low mana pools. This can potentially shut down powerful abilites they might have.\n\nThe Mystic Eyes of Light Perception lets you see all HP and Mana, but more importantly it lets you see through cover and you automatically detect all hidden creatures. Very useful when you're under attack by rogues or other stealthy characters.\n\nDisrupt Ki is used against mages who are concentrating on spells to make them drop it.","keyAbility":"Mana Sight","abilities":["Two Point Strike","Mystic Eyes of Life Perception","Disrupt Ki","Four Point Strike"]},{"id":"wildheart","name":"Wildheart","tier":3,"role1":"Specialist","role2":"","difficulty":3,"requirements":"Animal summoner mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Fitness, Cunning, Reason, Awareness or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend on Animal Husbandry. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"A better animal summoner.","guide":"Wildheart is a continuation of the animal summoner that gets more powerful animals and more control over them. Expanded Menagerie lets you choose which animal you want to summon in exchange for 1 mana, which is well worth for not having to rely on RNG.\n\nYou gain two buffing tools for your pet as Wildheart. The first being X-Attack, which gives a +1 focus and power buff for a moderate AP cost. With this buff, pets become a more viable dpser and target for Bestial Command. Secret Art: Bestial Wrath pushes this even further (but doesn't stack), giving a +2/+2 and letting pets compete offensively with dps characters. It also makes them not die once, letting them potentially soak another hit if focused.\n\nQuick Revive is a situational ability that's there for if you mess up or your pet gets hit by an instakill attack. With it, you don't get locked out of your pet abilities for the entire fight if something like that happens.\n\nLeashing is a cheap teleport for your pet that you can use to pull it back to safety, or to help it advance without spendin its own AP.","keyAbility":"Expanded Menagerie","abilities":["X-Attack","Quick Revive","Leashing","Secret Art: Bestial Wrath"]},{"id":"windbringer","name":"Windbringer","tier":2,"role1":"Support","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Mage mastered or Wind mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason or Fitness.","soul":"You gain +1 to Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"A supportive wind user that speeds up allies and hampers enemies.","guide":"The windbringer is a wind based support that focuses on movement.\n\nThey start the battle by giving their allies Tailwind, which increases their initiative and boosts their movement speed. This is especially useful when you start far away from the enemy and have many melee focused fighters in the party.\n\nIf you need even more movement speed, you can activate Gale-Wind Aura. 20ft movement speed increase is a big boost and since your allies keep it after leaving the aura, they can cross great distances in a single turn.\n\nHeadwind instead hampers enemy. You need to be somewhat close to an enemy for it to take effect, but it's an otherwise unavoidable slow. Once you and your allies have engaged the front most enemy, Headwind can be used to deny their allies a chance to help.\n\nFly gives flying to yourself or an ally. It has a small mana cost, but the extra movement speed alone makes it worth using.","keyAbility":"Wind Master","abilities":["Gale-Wind Aura","Tailwind","Headwind","Fly"]},{"id":"zen-warrior","name":"Zen Warrior","tier":3,"role1":"Striker","role2":"Defender","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Monk mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 Fitness or Awareness.","soul":"You gain +1 Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points to spend in Athletics, Perception, Insight, Medicine, Intimidation or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"Zen Warriors are mobile monks with both offensive and defensive capabilities.","guide":"The Zen Warrior follows up from the monk and gives them some much needed mobility. Walking away from the Serene Water Stance will no longer instantly save you.\n\nKi Blast II gives you the option to use a Light or Precise attack. This is useful when already in Serene Water stance, since you can follow it up with Flying Kick.\n\nFlying Kick can be used immediately after a Ki Blast has hit and places you next to the target. Because it then reduces the AP cost of Strike of Still Water by 1, you can do a Precise Ki Blast→Flying Kick→Strike of Still Water combo.\n\nKi Burst is a damage increase that can be used after you've hit an enemy with an attack. Mostly used for adding small points of damage when an enemy barely survives.\n\nRedirected Force takes advantage of the high dodge you will have in serene water stance. You can turn heavy attacks that miss you into attacks the enemy must respond to, or may be completely unable to avoid even when reacting to it.\n\nSecret Art: True Serenity is basically a guaranteed dodge for an entire turn unless the enemy uses sure hit attacks. Due to the +17 bonus that applies even when not dodging, even lock-on attacks will find it near impossible to hit you. As a bonus, you also enter Serene Water Stance from it. Best used when you about to take a lot of attacks in a single turn.","keyAbility":"Rapid Blasts","abilities":["Flying Kick","Ki Burst","Redirected Force","Secret Art: True Serenity"]},{"id":"zephyr-warder","name":"Zephyr Warder","tier":2,"role1":"Support","role2":"","difficulty":2,"requirements":"Mage mastered or Wind mastered.","heart":"You gain +1 to Reason or Presence.","soul":"You gain +1 to Focus or Agility.","skills":"You gain +5 skill points in Medicine, Magic, Religion, History, Flight, Artifice or Common Knowledge. You can exchange any skill point for 2 expertise points, but must spend them in these skills.","description":"A supportive wind user that can protect against and help with ranged attacks.","guide":"The Zephyr Warder specializes in ranged combat, helping both allies hit targets and preventing enemy archers from hitting.\n\nWind Infusion can be cast on every ally over the course of a battle and gives them not only an evasion bonus against ranged attacks, but also damage resistance against wind attacks. Worth using immediately when facing those types of enemies.\n\nWind Shield completely shuts down an enemy ranged attack, granting your ally such a huge bonus along with removing the lock-on and sure hit that the attack is sure to miss.\n\nWind Wall has to be cast in advance, but it can cover a wide chokepoint and removes all keywords that lets them ignore Dodge or Block. The range decrease can also matter a lot, especially if enemies are only using light ranged weapons. The mana cost isn't too bad either.\n\nWind-Empowered Aim buffs all your (heroic) ranged allies, giving a decent bonus to their accuracy rolls. Worth using if you have a lot of ranged attackers in your party or if you get into a shootout. With this buffs and all the anti-ranged buffs you have, you're sure to win a shooting battle.","keyAbility":"Wind Master","abilities":["Wind Infusion","Wind Wall","Wind-Empowered Aim","Wind Shield"]}],"items":[{"id":"adjustable-lens-refractor-gun","name":"Adjustable Lens Refractor Gun","type":"Artifice","subType":"Weapon","cost":"Original Weapon + 3000","burden":"Original Weapon + 1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"1 shell per encounter","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"An artifice gun with cartridges that lets it fire blasts of arcane energy through a series of lenses rather than bullets. Attacks with this weapon deal Arcane damage. By spending 1 AP per lens, the user may adjust the strength of the gun at the cost of accuracy. Each lens adjusted for power lets the user treat their attacks with the weapon as if their power was 1 higher than it actually is, at the cost of their focus being treated as 1 lower than it actually is. Up to 3 lenses can be modified in this way. Exists in Musket and Sniper Rifle variants.\n\nMods:\n\nUses normal musket and sniper rifle mods.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493058c-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493058c-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"advanced-surgery-kit","name":"Advanced Surgery Kit","type":"Adventuring Essentials","subType":"Kit","cost":"1500 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"Surgery kits contain stitches, bandages and other items used for more serious wounds.\n\nRest Action: You perform minor surgery on an ally or yourself. Requires at least 5 points in Medicine (or a relevant expertise in Medicine) to use. Make a medicine check against DC 15. On success you can negate the effect of one injury suffered this campaign until the end of the campaign. An injury can only be negated once by this effect, and one person can only have one negated injury at a time. The injury must still be dealt with after the campaign ends.\n\nWith an advanced surgery kit, you can heal two injuries from a single person instead of just one. The DC to heal two injuries is DC30.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ef-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ef-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"adventurer-s-kit","name":"Adventurer's Kit","type":"Adventuring Essentials","subType":"Kit","cost":"100 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"-","craftingType":"","description":"Adventuring kits contain all of the basic tools for adventuring. Included in the kit: Backpack, Flint and steel, Rope, Notebook, Pen, Compass, Bedroll, Torches, Hand Mirror.\n\nEffect: You can use the items for their various purposes within reason. Can store up to 5 burden of Adventuring Essentials, a Northi Lantern or items included in this kit in a combat ready state for 0 burden and contains a torch/lantern holster for hands off torch/lantern use for light purposes. Cannot store kits or other burden reducing items in this combat ready state.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305bd-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305bd-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"aerial-staff--sparrow-model-","name":"Aerial Staff (Sparrow Model)","type":"Artifice","subType":"Airship","cost":"3500 Clim","burden":"3","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per hour","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"The Sparrow Model Aerial Staff design is the most simple entry level Aerial Staff. It has a base speed of 20 feet and does not include integrated shielding or any weapon systems. Often used for training, its fuel efficiency is fairly high.\n\nIts user can use it to fly. It has a speed of a 20ft.\n\nRequires 1 hand to operate while flying.\n\nModifications\n\n- A Modification, Jury-Rigged Shield. Adds a shield generator, granting the airship a 15 HP shield. This shield can be switched on and off, but can only be replenished by changing the fuel cell.\n- A Modification, Jury-Rigged Cannon. Adds a small star cannon that fires an arcane blast from the front that deals heavy attack damage for 2 AP with 120ft Range.\n- A Modification, Medivac Rig. Allows a downed ally to be hauled on the underbelly of the staff. But reduces the speed by 10ft while hauling.\n- B Modification, Upgraded Airship Engine. Increases the speed to 50ft but adds Line Movement: The airship may only move in a straight line when making a movement action.\n- B Modification, Sorthen Shield Generator. Requires Jury-Rigged Shield. Installs a Sorthen style Shield Generator increasing the shield value by 15 HP.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493056c-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493056c-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"aetherie-sensory-station","name":"Aetherie Sensory Station","type":"Artifice","subType":"Basic","cost":"100000","burden":"--","activationCost":"--","fuelUsage":"1 shell per day","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A large stationary artifice chair an Aetherie connects themselves to that drastically boosts Mind Connection range by 250 miles.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305bb-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305bb-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"alchemist-s-alembic","name":"Alchemist's Alembic","type":"Equipment","subType":"Tool","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Core crafting tool. Allows you to craft items as an alchemist.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305af-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305af-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"alchemy-materials","name":"Alchemy Materials","type":"Crafting","subType":"Materials","cost":"","burden":"","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"Alchemy Herbs:\n\nRarityFire Water Earth Wind Arcane\nCommon 60 Clim 50 Clim 55 Clim 55 Clim 65 Clim\nRare 300 Clim 250 Clim 275 Clim 275 Clim 325 Clim\nMystic 600 Clim 500 Clim 550 Clim 550 Clim 650 Clim\nSupreme 1200 Clim 1000 Clim 1100 Clim 1100 Clim 1300 Clim\nAlchemy Herb Mixing\n\nWhen crafting as an alchemist, you may add additional herbs and alchemy materials into the mix. By adding in an extra amount of alchemy units as well as the exact same herbs as the recipe needs, you get extra dice.\n\n- Small Herb Mix- Required extra's: 2x recipe's original cost.\n- Effect: +1 Crafting Dice\n\n- Medium Herb Mix- Required extra's: 4x recipe's original cost.\n- Effect: +2 Crafting Dice\n\n- Large Herb Mix- Required extra's: 8x recipe's original cost.\n- Effect: +3 Crafting Dice\n\n- Supreme Herb Mix- Required extra's: 14x recipe's original cost.\n- Effect: +4 Crafting Dice","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305cf-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305cf-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"alchemy-rig","name":"Alchemy Rig","type":"Adventuring Essentials","subType":"Storage","cost":"50 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"A carrier that allows easy access to Elixirs, Flasks, Potions, Poisons and Salves. You can only equip one alchemy rig at a time, whether it's the normal alchemy rig or the deluxe version.\n\nStores up to 2 burden worth of Elixirs, Flasks, Potions and Salves.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930571-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930571-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"alchemy-rig--deluxe-","name":"Alchemy Rig (Deluxe)","type":"Adventuring Essentials","subType":"Storage","cost":"300 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"A carrier that allows easy access to Elixirs, Flasks, Potions, Poisons and Salves. You can only equip one alchemy rig at a time, whether it's the normal alchemy rig or the deluxe version.\n\nStores up to 5 burden worth of Elixirs, Flasks, Potions and Salves.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ce-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ce-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"anti-air-weapon-sight","name":"Anti-Air Weapon Sight","type":"Artifice","subType":"Weapon","cost":"2000 Clim","burden":"+1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per use","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"An artifice designed to combat against aerial mages. Provides tracking assistance against the more predictable movement of air units. Attaches to ranged weapons. Increases the accuracy of ranged weapon attacks against flying targets by +4 until the start of your next turn.\n\nModifications:\n\n- A Modification, Holographic Optic. Increases the accuracy against flying targets by +1\n- B Modification, Wide Targeting. Decreases the accuracy bonus by -2 but now works on all targets.\n- B Modification, Wing Outlining. Increases the aerial knockdown of the first attack made after activating by 20ft.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493056a-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493056a-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"antidote-shot-potion","name":"Antidote Shot Potion","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Potion","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"Created with Goblin Medical Science, a universal antidote for all common poisons. Stored inside of a glass vial syringe that is injected into the body. When used, immediately removes a single common poison effect and grants immunity to that poison for the next hour.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 1400 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Mystic Earth\n- 1x Rare Water","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930555-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930555-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"armor--clothing-","name":"Armor (Clothing)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Armor","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"0","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Armorsmithing","description":"A high quality set of clothing. Does not provide any bonuses by itself, but if crafted by an armorsmith, can accept Flamellon mods.\n\nCannot be worn at the same time as regular armor.\n\nMods:\n\n- A mods- Mage Robes (20 points): You gain +1 maximum mana, but lose 1 guard and 2 block.\n\n- B mods- Cloud Robes (50 points): Your movement speed is increased by 5ft.\n- Battle Casting (80 points): The first spell you cast each turn does not provoke attacks of opportunity.\n\n- Frame mods- Reinforced Clothing (0 points): This clothing can benefit from material bonuses, but its burden is increased by 1.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305f0-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305f0-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"armor--heavy-","name":"Armor (Heavy)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Armor","cost":"2000 Clim","burden":"3","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Armorsmithing","description":"Increases your Guard by 3 and your Block by 12, but reduces your Initiative by 3 and your Evasion and Dodge by 6.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Beacon Armor (35 points): Unarmored allies (except armor plates) within 40ft of you gain +1 guard.\n\n- B mods:- Deflecting Armor (25 points): An accuracy roll against you that rolls a 1 always misses.\n- Weighted Greaves (50 points): You become immovable while on the ground.\n- Titan Armor (50 points): You are treated as having a size category 1 step higher (maximum Large).\n\n- Frame mods:- Berserker Armor II (10 points): This armor reduces your RP by 3, but does not reduce your evasion and dodge.\n- Fortress (20 points): Reduces the Initiative penalty by 1 and the Evasion/Dodge penalty by 2, but it also reduces the movement speed by 5ft.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a5-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a5-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"armor--light-","name":"Armor (Light)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Armor","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Armorsmithing","description":"Increases your Guard by 1 and your Block by 4, but reduces your Initiative by 1 and your Evasion and Dodge by 2.\n\nMods:\n\n- A mods- Agile Weave (35 points): No armor penalty, but no guard/block bonus. You gain +1 evasion (but no additional dodge). This also takes up your Frame mod slot.\n- Acrobat's Harness (10 points): You gain +10 bonus to athletics while wearing this armor.\n- Camo (10 points): Pick a color theme. You gain +5 to stealth when hiding in environments of that theme, but -5 when hiding elsewhere. A GM may approve new environments, defaults are: green camo (jungle, woodland, prone in grass), yellow camo (desert, savannas), white camo (snow, arctic), dark camo (night, caves, rocky terrain), blue camo (rivers or oceanic)\n- Porcupine Hide (10 points): Enemies grappling you take 1d6 full pierce damage. When escaping a grapple, you also deal 1d6 full pierce damage to the creature grappling you.\n\n- B mods- Sleek (25 points): If you spend RP dodging an attack of opportunity, you may dodge any other attacks of opportunity made in reaction to the same action at the first for free.\n- Padded (25 points): Increase guard vs light attacks by 1, doesn't affect heavy damage.\n- Mistweave (50 points): You no longer provoke attacks of opportunity, but all attacks against you gain Half Pierce.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a0-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a0-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"armor--medium-","name":"Armor (Medium)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Armor","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Armorsmithing","description":"Increases your Guard by 2 and your Block by 8, but reduces your Initiative by 2 and your Evasion and Dodge by 4.\n\nMods:\n\n- A mods:- Weak Point Protection (20 Points): Pinpoint attacks against you reduce 1 less guard.\n\n- B mods:- Chain Links (25 points): Increases the block gained from this armor by 4.\n- Flexible Armor (50 points): When you take the Dodge action, your next Block gains a +8 bonus. When you take the Block action, your next Dodge action gains a +4 bonus. Lasts until the start of your next turn. Can activate multiple times per turn, but does not stack.\n\n- Frame mods:- Berserker Armor (10 points): This armor reduces your RP by 2, but does not reduce your evasion and dodge.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a1-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a1-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"armor-plates","name":"Armor Plates","type":"Equipment","subType":"Armor","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"3","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Armorsmithing","description":"Can be attached to an armor to increase its guard, but make it bulkier.\n\nGives the armor they are attached to +1 Guard (and +2 block), but increases the Burden of it by 3.\n\nAttaching it or removing it from an armor takes 10 minutes.\n\nCan be used together with other armor modifications. Can be put on regular clothing, but always requires an armor proficiency to have an effect. While you can wear multiple armor plates, the effect does not stack.\n\nDespite being craftable by an armorsmith, the item cannot be modified during crafting.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b2-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b2-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"armorsmithing-materials","name":"Armorsmithing Materials","type":"Crafting","subType":"Materials","cost":"","burden":"","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"Armorsmithing Base Metal Materials\n\nThe base material for crafting Medium and Heavy armor with armorsmithing is Iron. Iron units must be converted into an ingot before they can be used.\n\n- Iron:- Clim Cost per ingot: 300 Clim\n- Unit cost per ingot: 500 Iron units\n- Effect: None\n- When using Iron to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot for shield or armor plates, 2 ingots for a medium armor or greatshield or 4 for a heavy armor.\n\nOutside of iron, there are a variety of special materials that an armorsmith can use while crafting. These are more expensive, but grant stat bonuses.\n\n- Tamahagane- Clim Cost per ingot: 1050 Clim\n- Unit cost per ingot: 2000 Tamahagane units.\n- Effect: +1 stat bonus\n- When using Tamahagane to craft an item, you must spend 1 of Tamahagane. If crafting a medium armor or great shield, you must add 1 ingot of Iron. If crafting a heavy armor, you must add 3 ingots of Iron.\n\n- Mithril- Clim Cost per ingot: 4050 Clim\n- Unit cost per ingot: 8000 Mithril units.\n- Effect: +1/+1 stat bonus\n- When using Mithril to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Mithril. If crafting a medium armor or great shield, you must add 1 ingot of Iron. If crafting a heavy armor, you must add 3 ingots of Iron.\n\n- Orichalcum- Clim Cost per ingot: 8050 Clim\n- Unit cost per ingot: 16000 Orihalcum units.\n- Effect: +2/+1 stat bonus\n- When using Orihalcum to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Orihalcum. If crafting a medium armor or great shield, you must add 1 ingot of Iron. If crafting a heavy armor, you must add 3 ingots of Iron.\n\n- Escudo- Clim Cost per ingot: 11550 Clim\n- Unit cost per ingot: 23000 Escudo units.\n- Effect: +2/+2 stat bonus\n- When using Escudo to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Escudo. If crafting a medium armor or great shield, you must add 1 ingot of Iron. If crafting a heavy armor, you must add 3 ingots of Iron.\n\nStat bonuses:\n\nArmor: Each stat bonus gives a +1 evasion and dodge Material bonus or a +1 guard and +2 block Material bonus. A mithril or primehide armor would thus give +1 evasion, dodge and guard as well as +2 Block.\nShield: Each stat bonus gives a +1 Gear bonus to Dodge or a +2 Gear bonus to Block.\n\nArmorsmithing Base Leather Materials\n\nThe base material for crafting clothing, light armor and cloaks is Animal Hides. Animal Hides must be converted into Tanned Animal Hide before they can be used.\n\nIMPORTANT: Clothing does not gain material bonuses when made out of something better unless they have the \"Reinforced Clothing\" A mod.\n\n- Animal Hide:- Clim Cost per tanned hide: 300 Clim\n- Unit cost per tanned hide: 500 Animal Hide units\n- Effect: None\n- When using animal hides to craft an item, you must spend 1 tanned animal hide for clothing, light armor, bags and cloaks.\n\nOutside of animal hides, there are a variety of special materials that an armorsmith can use while crafting. These are more expensive, but grant stat bonuses.\n\n- Direhide:- Clim Cost per tanned hide: 1050 Clim\n- Unit cost per tanned hide: 2000 Direhide units\n- Effect: +1 stat bonus\n- When using direhides to craft an item, you must spend 1 tanned direhide for clothing, light armor and cloaks.\n\n- Primehide:- Clim Cost per tanned hide: 4050 Clim\n- Unit cost per tanned hide: 8000 Primehide units\n- Effect: +1/+1 stat bonus\n- When using primehides to craft an item, you must spend 1 tanned primehides for clothing, light armor and cloaks.\n\n- Dragonscale:- Clim Cost per tanned hide: 8050 Clim\n- Unit cost per tanned hide: 16000 Dragonscale units\n- Effect: +2/+1 stat bonus\n- When using Dragonscales to craft an item, you must spend 1 tanned Dragonscale for clothing, light armor and cloaks.\n\n- Astrahide:- Clim Cost per tanned hide: 11550 Clim\n- Unit cost per tanned hide: 23000 Astrahide units\n- Effect: +2/+2 stat bonus\n- When using Astrahide to craft an item, you must spend 1 tanned Astrahide for clothing, light armor and cloaks.\n\nStat bonuses:\n\nArmor: Each stat bonus gives a +1 evasion and dodge Material bonus or a +1 guard and +2 block Material bonus. A mithril or primehide armor would thus give +1 evasion, dodge and guard as well as +2 Block.\n\nArmorsmithing Special Materials\n\n- Spidersilk (500 Clim / 15 Crafting Points):- Unit cost: 1000 Spidersilk units\n- A Spidersilk armor reduces the Initiative penalty by 1 and the Evasion/Dodge penalty by 2, but the wearer takes double damage from Fire damage. Light armor only.\n\n- Electrum (3050 Clim / 30 Crafting Points): - Unit cost per ingot: 6050 Electrum units.\n- Armors infused with Electrum gain a +1 Guard and +4 block bonus against attacks made by Divines, Summons and Otherworlders.\n\n- Silver (1050 Clim / 30 Crafting Points): - Unit cost per ingot: 2000 Silver units.\n- Silver infused armors remove a Fiend's regeneration. When a fiend hits you with a melee attack or a physical contact attack, they lose their regeneration until the start of their next turn.\n\n- Mycelite (1550 Clim / 20 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Mycelite units.\n- Mycelite infused armor incur 1 less burden to a minimum of 1.\n\n- Adamantite (2050 Clim / 20 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per ingot: 4000 Adamantite units\n- Adamantite armors cannot be destroyed or damaged by effect such as Sunder by non adamantite tools or weapons.\n\n- Luxaeterna (1550 Clim / 30 Crafting Points): - Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Luxaeterna units.\n- Armor infused with Luxaterna gives the wearer 5 damage reduction against Holy damage.\n\n- Corvuskite (1550 Clim / 30 Crafting Points): - Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Corvuskite units.\n- Armor infused with Corvuskite gives the wearer 5 damage reduction against Dark damage.\n\n- Arcanium (1550 Clim / 30 Crafting Points): - Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Arcanium units.\n- Armor infused with Arcanium gives the wearer 5 damage reduction against Arcane damage.\n\n- Vivinthal (1550 Clim / 30 Crafting Points): - Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Vivinthal units.\n- Armor infused with Vivinthal gives the wearer 5 damage reduction against Water damage.\n\n- Glacite (1550 Clim / 30 Crafting Points): - Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Glacite units.\n- Armor infused with Glacite gives the wearer 5 damage reduction against Frost damage.\n\n- Salachar (1550 Clim / 30 Crafting Points): - Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Salachar units.\n- Armor infused with Salachar gives the wearer 5 damage reduction against Fire damage.\n\n- Sylphsteel (1550 Clim / 30 Crafting Points): - Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Sylphsteel units.\n- Armor infused with Sylphsteel gives the wearer 5 damage reduction against Wind damage.\n\n- Fulgarite ( 1550 Clim / 30 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Fulgarite units.\n- Armor infused with Fulgarite gives the wearer 5 damage reduction against Lightning damage.\n\n- Ghimslag (1550 Clim / 30 Crafting Points): - Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Ghimslag units.\n- Armor infused with Ghimslag gives the wearer 5 damage reduction against Earth damage.\n\n- Crystal Core (3500 Clim / 35 Crafting Points)- Unit cost: 1 core\n- Armor infused with the core of a specific fiend. The wearer may spend 1 Mana and 0 RP to absorb the energy of an elemental (Arcane, Fire, Water, Wind, Earth or any of its subtypes) damage attack. Their next weapon attack gains bonus damage equal to the attacker's power and becomes the element of the triggering attack.\n\n- Nullite ( 2050 Clim / 20 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per ingot: 4000 Nullite units\n- Anti-Magic Layer: Against spells, you gain 2 guard, 2 evasion and a +2 bonus to saves. However you can no longer become the target of friendly spells (including your own).\n\n- Runesteel ( 1050 Clim / 10 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per ingot: 2000 Runesteel units\n- Select Magic Absorption: Friendly spells targeting you gain +20ft range.\n\n- Sunsteel ( 1550 Clim, 15 crafting points):- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Sunsteel units\n- Sun Protection: You are immune to any negative effects suffered from being in the sun.\n\n- Perfect Shell (2000 Clim)- Can be made into light armor or armor plates by a Master Armorer (counts as Mithril in terms of difficulty).\n- If used for light armor, the light armor cannot have another special material (may still have flamelon mods) and cannot reduce its armor penalty, but it receives +1 guard and +4 Block and may have one medium armor property. Counts as a base material for crafting as well.\n- If used for armor plates, the armor plates receive an additional 2 block for a +1 guard and +4 block total.\n\nArmorsmithing Cloak Materials\n\nCloaks may benefit from higher base materials being used. This is on a per cloak basis and is listed with the material.\n\n- No special material- A cloak made with no special material may gain a Gear bonus to its Dodge or Block.\n- When made with Direhide/Primehide/Dragonscale/Astrahide gives a +1/+2/+3/+4 Gear bonus to Dodge or a +2/+4/+6/+8 Gear bonus to Block.\n\n- Night Wolf Pelt (550 Clim / 5 Crafting Points)- Unit cost: 1000 units\n- A cloak of night wolf pelt gives the wielder +5 bonus to stealth checks during the night or in area's without light.\n- When made with Direhide/Primehide instead gives a +10/+15 bonus.\n\n- Fae Wolf Pelt (1050 Clim / 10 Crafting Points)- Unit Cost: 2000 Units\n- A cloak of faewolf pelt gives the wielder the ability to spend 4 AP to hide in plain sight. This hide lasts until you take any other action or speak.\n- When made with Primehide, reduce the AP cost to 3.\n\n- Astral Tiger Pelt (1050 Clim / 10 Crafting Points)- Unit Cost: 2000 Units\n- A cloak of astral tiger pelt gives the wielder the ability to teleport when attacked. After an attack against you misses (or you dodge it), you may spend 1 RP to teleport up to 20ft.\n\n- Wonderland Rabbit Hide (1550 Clim / 15 Crafting Points) (By CCeles)- Unit Cost: No units, just 1 hide.\n- When you take a movement action that costs RP, that movement is increased by 5ft. (Doesn't stack with Compact Ergonomics mod)\n- When made with Primehide, the movement is increased by 10ft instead.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305dd-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305dd-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"artifice-limb","name":"Artifice Limb","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"4000 Clim","burden":"0","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"1 shell per arc","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"An artifice item that replaces a lost limb or body part. Each of these must be custom made for a person. When attached, it allows the user to function as if the artifice limb was a normal limb.\n\nModifications:\n\nA mod: Grapple Launcher (Arm only): Allows the user to install a grappling hook artifice in the arm, functioning just like the grappling hook would. (Grappling hook must be supplied separately and takes an errand action from an artificer to install). A grappling hook installed in the arm takes burden like usual and still takes an AP to activate, but requires no AP to pull out.\n\nA mod: Weapon slot (Arm only): Allows the user to install a weapon into the arm, functioning just like the weapon would (takes an errand from artificer to install). The weapon costs burden like normal, but may be drawn or sheathed for 0 AP once per turn.\n\nA mod: Movement Burst (Leg only): You may spend 0 AP to gain +20ft movement until the start of your next turn. Afterwards, your movement speed is halved until you put in a new shell into your leg.\n\nA mod: Zoom In (Eye only): You may spend 1 AP to gain a +10 bonus to your perception until the start of your next turn.\n\nB mod: Thermal Fusion Sight (Eye only). Adds thermal vision up to 120ft. This cannot detect things hidden by magical means. The sight can not discern a difference in heat once something reaches freezing temperatures.\n\nB mod: Blast Knuckle (Arm or Leg only): After making a Heavy unarmed attack with the limb, you may spend 0 RP to make a Light attack against all enemies in a 15ft wide, 15ft long cone behind the target. After doing this, you must put in a new shell into the limb to use it again (your movement speed is halved if your leg is unusable).","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e5-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e5-lg.webp","imageAlignment":""},{"id":"artifice-water-purifier","name":"Artifice Water Purifier","type":"Artifice","subType":"Basic","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per arc","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A filter that purifies water to make it safe to drink. The device is easy to use and can filter up to 2 liters of water in 1 minute.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.12.6/69ea4f7b6be32fced492fc5a-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.12.6/69ea4f7b6be32fced492fc5a-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"artificer-materials","name":"Artificer Materials","type":"Crafting","subType":"Materials","cost":"","burden":"","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"The base material for crafting items with Artificing is Iron Artifice parts. You can either buy Iron Artifice parts or convert them from Iron by using the Artificer or Transmuter abilities.\n\nArtifice weapons follow special rules. If you see an artifice weapon with a crafting cost of 30, refer to the rules under the artifice weapon materials section.\n\nIron:\nEqual artifice parts to the base clim cost of the artifice is required to craft Iron Artifices.\n\nOutside of iron, there are a variety of special materials that an Artificer can use while crafting. These are more expensive, but grant additional crafting dice.\n\nYou need Artifice Parts of the matching type to craft and the amount you need is determined this way:\n\n(Special Material Modifier) x (Base Clim Cost) = Amount of Special Material Artifice Parts Needed\n\n- Iron Artifice Parts- Multiplier: 1x\n- Effect: None\n\n- Tamahagane Artifice Parts- Multiplier: 2x\n- Effect: +1 Crafting Dice\n\n- Mithril Artifice Parts- Multiplier: 4x\n- Effect: +2 Crafting Dice\n\n- Orichalcum Artifice Parts- Multiplier: 8x\n- Effect: +3 Crafting Dice\n\n- Escudo Artifice Parts- Multiplier 11x\n- Effect: +4 Crafting Dice\n\nArtificing Weapon Materials:\n\nThe base material for crafting weapons such as pistols or sniper rifles with artificing is Iron. Iron units must be converted into an ingot before they can be used.\n\n- Iron:- Clim Cost per ingot: 300 Clim\n- Unit cost per ingot: 500 Iron units\n- Effect: None\n- When using Iron to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot.\n\nOutside of iron, there are a variety of special materials that an artificer can use while crafting. These are more expensive, but grant stat bonuses.\n\nNOTE: When making an Artifice weapon that is an actual weapon and not an attachment, you must spend an additional iron artifice parts equal to the cost of the weapon - 500 rather than an extra ingot. This also applies to guns.\n\n- Tamahagane- Clim Cost per ingot: 1050 Clim\n- Unit cost per ingot: 2000 Tamahagane units.\n- Effect: +1 stat bonus\n- When using Tamahagane to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Tamahagane.\n\n- Mithril- Clim Cost per ingot: 4050 Clim\n- Unit cost per ingot: 8000 Mithril units.\n- Effect: +1/+1 stat bonus\n- When using Mithril to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Mithril.\n\n- Orichalcum- Clim Cost per ingot: 8050 Clim\n- Unit cost per ingot: 16000 Orihalcum units.\n- Effect: +2/+1 stat bonus\n- When using Orihalcum to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Orihalcum.\n\n- Escudo- Clim Cost per ingot: 11550 Clim\n- Unit cost per ingot: 23000 Escudo units.\n- Effect: +2/+2 stat bonus\n- When using Escudo to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Escudo.\n\nStat bonuses depend on if the crafted item is a tool or weapon.\n\nWeapon: The Material bonuses to go Focus and Power. With getting a +1 bonus or a +2/+1 bonus, the crafter may choose which of the two stats gets the extra bonus.\n\nArtificing special materials\n\n- Dark Iron (550 Clim / 15 Crafting Points) :- Unit cost per ingot: 1000 Dark Iron units.\n- Strikes with Dark Iron infused weapons cause the target to be unable to teleport until the end of their next turn.\n\n- Silver (1050 Clim / 30 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per ingot: 2000 Silver units.\n- Dealing damage with Silver infused weapons disables the Regeneration effect of Fiends until the start of your next turn.\n\n- Electrum (3050 Clim/ 30 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per ingot: 6000 Electrum units.\n- Strikes with Electrum infused weapons grant a +2 Electrum Power bonus against Divines, Summons or Otherworlders.\n\n- Mycelite (1550 Clim / 20 Crafting points)- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Mycelite units.\n- Mycelite infused weapons incur 1 less burden to a minimum of 1\n\n- Obsidian Steel (550 Clim)- Unit cost per ingot: 1000 Obsidian Steel units.\n- Obsidian Steel infused weapons cannot be the targets of magical effects.\n\n- Adamantite (2050 Clim / 20 Crafting points)- Unit cost per ingot: 4000 Adamantite units\n- Adamantite weapons cannot be destroyed by non adamantite tools or weapons.\n\n- Luxaeterna (1550 Clim / 15 Crafting points)- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Luxaeterna units.\n- Changes the physical damage type into Holy.\n\n- Corvuskite (1550 Clim / 15 Crafting points)- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Corvuskite units.\n- Changes the physical damage type into Dark.\n\n- Arcanium (1550 Clim / 15 Crafting points)- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Arcanium units.\n- Changes the physical damage type into Arcane.\n\n- Fulgarite ( 1550 Clim / 15 Crafting points )- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Fulgarite units\n- Changes the physical damage type into Lightning.\n\n- Vivinthal (1550 Clim / 15 Crafting points)- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Vivinthal units.\n- Changes the physical damage type into Water.\n\n- Salachar (1550 Clim / 15 Crafting points)- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Salachar units.\n- Changes the physical damage type into Fire.\n\n- Sylphsteel (1550 Clim / 15 Crafting points)- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Sylphsteel units\n- Changes the physical damage type into Wind.\n\n- Ghimslag (1550 Clim / 15 Crafting points)- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Ghimslag units.\n- Changes the physical damage type into Earth.\n\n- Nullite ( 2050 Clim / 30 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per ingot: 4000 Nullite units\n- All attacks made with this weapon gain the Shieldbreaker property.\n\n- Runesteel ( 1050 Clim / 10 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per ingot: 2000 Runesteel units\n- This weapon can channel spells as if it was a channeling weapon.\n\n- Sepsium ( 2050 Clim / 30 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per ingot: 4000 Sepsium units\n- When damaging a creature with this weapon, they cannot recover HP (except for regeneration type effects) until the start of your next turn.\n\n- Sunsteel ( 1550 Clim / 15 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Sunsteel units\n- Attacks with this weapon gain Full Pierce against creatures weak to light or sunlight.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305dc-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305dc-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"artificer-s-kit","name":"Artificer's Kit","type":"Adventuring Essentials","subType":"Kit","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"-","craftingType":"","description":"Artificer’s Patch kit with various tools for maintaining artifices.\n\nRest Action: You can either patch a broken, non-airship Artifice, allowing it to be usable until the end of the scenario if its repairable. The Artifice still counts as broken at the end of the scenario and cannot be patched again until fully repaired. Alternatively, you can instead choose to create an Artifice Shell, paying its cost in Magical Fuel to create.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c4-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c4-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"artificer-s-multitool","name":"Artificer's Multitool","type":"Equipment","subType":"Tool","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Core crafting tool. Allows you to craft items as an artificer.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305db-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305db-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"astra-guidance-beacon","name":"Astra Guidance Beacon","type":"Artifice","subType":"Basic","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per arc","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"While this artifice is in effect, the spirit core values of your allies within 300ft of you are treated as 500 higher than they actually are for the purposes of calculating astra corruption risks. Does not stack with similar resistance boosting effects and only works on allies with a Spirit Core lower than yours.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ee-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ee-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"axe--one-handed-","name":"Axe (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Wild Swing: When attacking a target, you still deal 4 (Light Attack) or 8 (Heavy/Precise Attack) damage if the attack misses. This is reduced by guard (to a minimum of 1). On damage effects do not trigger from this damage.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Reinforced Langet (10 points): This weapon cannot be disarmed.\n- Bearded Extension (20 points): Wild Swing now ignores guard, but the damage is reduced to 2 (light attack) or 4 (heavy attack).\n- Rotational Stability (35 points): If a target moves away from you when you attack with this weapon and your next attack this turn is a throwing attack using this weapon against that target, that attack gains lock on.\n\n- B mods:- Boomerang Wing (25 points): After using a throwing attack with this weapon, you can return the weapon to your hand for 0 RP.\n- Lancebreaker (80 points): You gain a +2 Lancebreaker Power bonus against enemies wielding polearms or lances.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493058e-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493058e-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"axe--two-handed-","name":"Axe (Two-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Wild Swing: When attacking a target, you still deal 4 (Light Attack) or 8 (Heavy/Precise Attack) damage if the attack misses. This is reduced by guard (to a minimum of 1). On damage effects do not trigger from this damage.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Reinforced Langet (10 points): This weapon cannot be disarmed.\n- Bearded Extension (20 points): Wild Swing now ignores guard, but the damage is reduced to 2 (light attack) or 4 (heavy attack).\n- Rotational Stability (35 points): If a target moves away from you when you attack with this weapon and your next attack this turn is a throwing attack using this weapon against that target, that attack gains lock on.\n\n- B mods:- Boomerang Wing (25 points): After using a throwing attack with this weapon, you can return the weapon to your hand for 0 RP.\n- Lancebreaker (80 points): You gain a +2 Lancebreaker Power bonus against enemies wielding polearms or lances.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930596-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930596-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"axolotl-elixir","name":"Axolotl Elixir","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Elixir","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP, 2 Mana","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"When drunk, you take true damage equal to your Toughness x 5. Until the end of the encounter, you regain HP equal to your Toughness at the start of your turn.\n\nIf the triggering damage lowers your HP to 0 or lower, the effect immediately ends. Your HP being dropped to 0 or lower from other effects does not cancel this elixir.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 870 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Rare Water\n- 1x Common Arcane","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930588-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930588-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"backpack","name":"Backpack","type":"Adventuring Essentials","subType":"Storage","cost":"50 Clim","burden":"","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"Mounted on your back or a pack animal.\n\nAllows you to store items in non-combat storage.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493056f-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493056f-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"bear-elixir","name":"Bear Elixir","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Elixir","cost":"400 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"An elixir that raises your stamina and reaction speed. When drunk, you take 11 true damage. You immediately gain 1 RP and your maximum RP increases by 1 until the end of the encounter.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 650 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Rare Earth","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493057a-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493057a-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"binoculars","name":"Binoculars","type":"Artifice","subType":"Basic","cost":"500","burden":"1","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"Binoculars let you zoom in on distant views, bringing faraway details up close and clear. You gain a +10 bonus on perception checks against things further than 60ft away.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b4-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b4-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"blacksmithing-materials","name":"Blacksmithing Materials","type":"Crafting","subType":"Materials","cost":"Varies","burden":"0","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"-","craftingType":"-","description":"Blacksmithing Base Materials\n\nThe base material for crafting items with blacksmithing is Iron. Iron units must be converted into an ingot before they can be used.\n\n- Iron:- Clim Cost per ingot: 300 Clim\n- Unit cost per ingot: 500 Iron units\n- Effect: None\n- When using Iron to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot for a one handed weapon or tool, or 2 for a longsword or two handed weapon (or two handed tool).\n\nOutside of iron, there are a variety of special materials that a blacksmith can use while crafting. These are more expensive, but grant stat bonuses\n\n- Tamahagane- Clim Cost per ingot: 1050 Clim\n- Unit cost per ingot: 2000 Tamahagane units.\n- Effect: +1 stat bonus\n- When using Tamahagane to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Tamahagane. If making a two handed weapon, you must add an additional ingot of Iron.\n\n- Mithril- Clim Cost per ingot: 4050 Clim\n- Unit cost per ingot: 8000 Mithril units.\n- Effect: +1/+1 stat bonus\n- When using Mithril to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Mithril. If making a two handed weapon, you must add an additional ingot of Iron.\n\n- Orichalcum- Clim Cost per ingot: 8050 Clim\n- Unit cost per ingot: 16000 Orihalcum units.\n- Effect: +2/+1 stat bonus\n- When using Orihalcum to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Orihalcum. If making a two handed weapon, you must add an additional ingot of Iron.\n\n- Escudo- Clim Cost per ingot: 11550 Clim\n- Unit cost per ingot: 23000 Escudo units.\n- Effect: +2/+2 stat bonus\n- When using Escudo to craft an item, you must spend 1 ingot of Escudo. If making a two handed weapon, you must add an additional ingot of Iron.\n\nStat bonuses depend on if the crafted item is a tool or weapon.\n\nWeapon: The Material bonuses to go Focus and Power. With getting a +1 bonus or a +2/+1 bonus, the crafter may choose which of the two stats gets the extra bonus.\n\nTool: For tools, there is a crafting bonus and a finish bonus. A crafting bonus gives you +1 (or +2) Material bonus to each crafting dice roll. The finish bonus gives you a +5 (or +10) Finish bonus once at the end of your craft.\n\nBlacksmithing Special Materials\n\nWhen these materials are added to a crafting tool, they give a +1 bonus to crafting checks when working with that material.\n\n- Dark Iron (550 Clim / 15 Crafting Points) :- Unit cost per ingot: 1000 Dark Iron units.\n- Strikes with Dark Iron infused weapons cause the target to be unable to teleport until the end of their next turn.\n\n- Silver (1050 Clim / 30 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per ingot: 2000 Silver units.\n- Dealing damage with Silver infused weapons disables the Regeneration effect of Fiends until the start of your next turn.\n\n- Electrum (3050 Clim/ 30 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per ingot: 6000 Electrum units.\n- Strikes with Electrum infused weapons grant a +2 Electrum Power bonus against Divines, Summons or Otherworlders.\n\n- Mycelite (1550 Clim / 20 Crafting points)- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Mycelite units.\n- Mycelite infused weapons incur 1 less burden to a minimum of 1\n\n- Obsidian Steel (550 Clim)- Unit cost per ingot: 1000 Obsidian Steel units.\n- Obsidian Steel infused weapons cannot be the targets of magical effects.\n\n- Adamantite (2050 Clim / 20 Crafting points)- Unit cost per ingot: 4000 Adamantite units\n- Adamantite weapons cannot be destroyed by non adamantite tools or weapons.\n\n- Luxaeterna (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points)- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Luxaeterna units.\n- Changes the physical damage type into Holy.\n\n- Corvuskite (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points)- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Corvuskite units.\n- Changes the physical damage type into Dark.\n\n- Arcanium (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points)- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Arcanium units.\n- Changes the physical damage type into Arcane.\n\n- Fulgarite ( 1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points )- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Fulgarite units\n- Changes the physical damage type into Lightning.\n\n- Vivinthal (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points)- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Vivinthal units.\n- Changes the physical damage type into Water.\n\n- Salachar (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points)- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Salachar units.\n- Changes the physical damage type into Fire.\n\n- Sylphsteel (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points)- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Sylphsteel units\n- Changes the physical damage type into Wind.\n\n- Ghimslag (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points)- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Ghimslag units.\n- Changes the physical damage type into Earth.\n\n- Nullite ( 2050 Clim / 30 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per ingot: 4000 Nullite units\n- All attacks made with this weapon gain the Shieldbreaker property.\n\n- Runesteel ( 1050 Clim / 10 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per ingot: 2000 Runesteel units\n- This weapon can channel spells as if it was a channeling weapon.\n\n- Sepsium ( 2050 Clim / 30 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per ingot: 4000 Sepsium units\n- When damaging a creature with this weapon, they cannot recover HP (except for regeneration type effects) until the start of your next turn.\n\n- Sunsteel ( 1550 Clim / 15 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per ingot: 3000 Sunsteel units\n- Attacks with this weapon gain Full Pierce against creatures weak to light or sunlight.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305cc-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305cc-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"blaster-weapon","name":"Blaster Weapon","type":"Artifice","subType":"Weapon","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"+1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per use","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"An artifice that fires a condensed blast of magical energy. Used to give a ranged option to melee weapons. Attachable to melee weapons. When activated, changes the weapon to a ranged mode that can fire elemental blasts to a target up to 80ft away like a ranged weapon could. The elemental type is determined at artifice creation. When the weapon is activated again, the weapon switches back to the melee mode and the shell is expended.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930569-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930569-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"blood-elixir","name":"Blood Elixir","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Elixir","cost":"750 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"A deep red potion that when drunk reduces your current and maximum HP by 15 until the end of your next rest.. You immediately gain 3 mana, up to your maximum mana.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 1350 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 3x Common Water\n- 1x Rare Fire","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493054a-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493054a-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"bludgeoning-weapon--one-handed-","name":"Bludgeoning Weapon (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Hollow Blow: When attacking and hitting a target, you deal additional damage if they Block. This damage is 2 on a Light/Precise attack or 4 on a Heavy attack.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Flexible Handle (10 points): When dealing damage to a target, the minimum damage you deal is always 2. (this does not trigger on damage effects if damage would be 0 otherwise).\n- Chain Flail (35 points): Cannot be defended against by 0 RP actions. Attacks made with this weapon do not count as consuming 0 RP actions.\n\n- B mods:- Weighted Poll Upsetting (25 points): When making 3 separate attacks against a target, the third attack you make with \"Weighted Poll Upsetting\" knocks the target back 10ft on damage.\n- Flanged Head (50 points): When you crit with this weapon, the damage is still maximized even against blocking targets.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493058f-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493058f-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"bludgeoning-weapon--two-handed-","name":"Bludgeoning Weapon (Two-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Hollow Blow: When attacking and hitting a target, you deal additional damage if they Block. This damage is 2 on a Light/Precise attack or 4 on a Heavy attack.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Flexible Handle (10 points): When dealing damage to a target, the minimum damage you deal is always 2. (this does not trigger on damage effects if damage would be 0 otherwise).\n- Chain Flail (35 points): Cannot be defended against by 0 RP actions. Attacks made with this weapon do not count as consuming 0 RP actions.\n\n- B mods:- Weighted Poll Upsetting (25 points): When making 3 separate attacks against a target, the third attack you make with \"Weighted Poll Upsetting\" knocks the target back 10ft on damage.\n- Flanged Head (50 points): When you crit with this weapon, the damage is still maximized even against blocking targets.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930595-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930595-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"boar","name":"Boar","type":"Mount","subType":"","cost":"1500 Clim","burden":"0","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"A boar trained to be used in combat.\n\nStats:\n\nHP: 45\n\nFocus: 2\n\nPower: 4\n\nAgility: 2\n\nToughness: 4\n\nSpeed: 30ft\n\nSize: Medium\n\nSpecial qualities:\n\nBoar Charge: When using the trample ability, you can trample enemies the same size as you (Medium). You also deal an additional Power damage with the attack.\n\nLine Movement: You may only move in a straight line when taking a movement action.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c5-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c5-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"botany-bag","name":"Botany Bag","type":"Equipment","subType":"Materials","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Armorsmithing","description":"You can carry an additional 2000 units of each Lumber material + Alchemy units.\n\n(May be stored for 0 burden while empty)\n\nMay be crafted using Direhide / Primehide / Dragonscale / Astrahide to hold an additional 1000 / 3000 / 6000 / 10000 units of each Lumber material + Alchemy units.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- -\n\n- B mods:- One item container (50 points): The additional units this bag can carry is doubled, but it only works for a single material type rather than all of them.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e4-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e4-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"bow--two-handed-","name":"Bow (Two-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Carpentry","description":"High Ground: If fired against a target who is at least 10ft lower than you are, you may treat the attack as coming from the sky and calculate any low cover as if the attack originated from above the target.\n\nRange: 240ft\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Recurve (20 points): Range increased by 60ft.\n\n- B mods:- Shortbow (25 points): Range reduced to 120ft but when making a basic light attack, you can make a second light attack for 0 AP once per turn. This counts as your dual wield attack.\n- Bodkin Arrows (25 points): Grants Hollow Blow: When attacking and hitting a target, you deal additional damage if they Block. This damage is 2 on a Light/Precise attack or 4 on a Heavy attack.\n- Broadhead Arrows (50 points): Deals +1 damage against light armor or unarmored targets.\n- Blunthead Arrows (80 points): First basic heavy attack per turn dazes targets on damage.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493059d-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493059d-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"breaching-flask","name":"Breaching Flask","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Flask","cost":"400 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"A flask made for breaching locked doors. When tossed against a door, window or similar medium sized entryway it blasts them open and anyone within 5ft behind the door is knocked prone. Works against doors with a roguecraft DC equal or less than 20. Creates a loud noise regardless of success. When attempting to use it against living creatures, they may choose to avoid it for 0 RP. Else, they are knocked back 30ft.\n\nMaterials: 600 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Rare Fire","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493057d-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493057d-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"bull-potion","name":"Bull Potion","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Potion","cost":"300 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"A potion that immediately gives the benefit of consuming food when drunk. You regain 2 mana, but this counts as your one food buff per day. This potion gives no benefit if you already received benefits from eating food today.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 350 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Rare Fire","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930580-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930580-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"buster-weapon","name":"Buster Weapon","type":"Artifice","subType":"Weapon","cost":"3000 Clim","burden":"+1","activationCost":"0 RP, Instant","fuelUsage":"1 shell per use","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"An artifice that adds an explosive blast to increase forward velocity. The most common type of weapon artifice used to help overwhelm an opponent. Attachable to melee weapons. Use when you are making an attack against an enemy. The attack gains +3 accuracy and +3 damage.\n\nArtificer Modifications:\n\n- A Modification, Optimized Explosion: Increases the accuracy bonus by +1\n- A Modification, Powerful Explosion: Increases the damage bonus by +1\n- B Modification, Angel-Type: Knocks the target back by 5ft on damage.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930568-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930568-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"calibretto-device","name":"Calibretto Device","type":"Artifice","subType":"Basic","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"1 per use","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A small handheld device that display the astra level of where you're currently standing.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305f3-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305f3-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"camping-kit","name":"Camping Kit","type":"Adventuring Essentials","subType":"Kit","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"-","craftingType":"","description":"Camping kits contain all of the basic tools for setting up camp. A tent, 5 bedrolls, tinder, flint and steel, camping mat.\n\nRest action: You can create a comfortable camp for your party, giving you the benefits of comfortable rest (2x toughness) even in poor conditions.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305be-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305be-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"carpenter-materials","name":"Carpenter Materials","type":"Crafting","subType":"Materials","cost":"","burden":"","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"Carpenter Base Materials\n\nThe base material for crafting items with carpenter is Pine. Pine units must be converted into a block before they can be used.\n\n- Pine:- Clim Cost per block: 300 Clim\n- Unit cost per block: 500 Pine units\n- Effect: None\n- When using Pine to craft an item, you must spend 1 block for a one handed weapon or cart, or 2 for a two handed weapon.\n\nOutside of Pine, there are a variety of special materials that a carpenter can use while crafting. These are more expensive, but grant stat bonuses.\n\n- Maple- Clim Cost per block: 1050 Clim\n- Unit cost per block: 2000 Maple units.\n- Effect: +1 stat bonus\n- When using Maple to craft an item, you must spend 1 block of Maple. If making a two handed weapon, you must add an additional block of Pine.\n\n- Ash- Clim Cost per block: 4050 Clim\n- Unit cost per block: 8000 Ash units.\n- Effect: +1/+1 stat bonus\n- When using Ash to craft an item, you must spend 1 block of Ash. If making a two handed weapon, you must add an additional block of Pine.\n\n- Yew- Clim Cost per block: 8050 Clim\n- Unit cost per block: 16000 Yew units.\n- Effect: +2/+1 stat bonus\n- When using Yew to craft an item, you must spend 1 block of Yew. If making a two handed weapon, you must add an additional block of Pine.\n\n- Yggdrasil- Clim Cost per block: 11550 Clim\n- Unit cost per block: 23000 Yggdrasil units.\n- Effect: +2/+2 stat bonus\n- When using Yggdrasil to craft an item, you must spend 1 block of Yggdrasil. If making a two handed weapon, you must add an additional block of Pine.\n\nStat bonuses:\n\nWeapon: The Material bonuses to go Focus and Power. With getting a +1 bonus or a +2/+1 bonus, the crafter may choose which of the two stats gets the extra bonus.\n\nCarpenter Special Materials\n\n- Yugusbane Block (550 Clim / 15 Crafting Points) :- Unit cost per block: 1000 Yugusbane units.\n- Strikes with Yugusbane cause the target to be unable to teleport until the end of their next turn.\n\n- Silver Oil (1050 Clim / 30 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per Oil: 2000 Silver units.\n- Dealing damage with Silver infused weapons disables the Regeneration effect of Fiends until the start of your next turn.\n\n- Electrum Oil (3050 Clim / 30 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per Oil: 6000 Electrum units.\n- Strikes with Electrum infused weapons grant a +2 Electrum Power bonus against Divines, Summons or Otherworlders.\n\n- Mycelite Block (1550 Clim / 20 Crafting points)- Unit cost per block: 3000 Mycelite units.\n- Mycelite weapons incur 1 less burden to a minimum of 1.\n\n- Ebony Wood Block (550 Clim)- Unit cost per block: 1000 Ebony Wood.\n- Ebony weapons cannot be the targets of magical effects.\n\n- Lignum Vitae (2050 Clim / 20 Crafting Points)- Unit cost per block: 4000 Lignum Vitae units\n- Lignum Vitae weapons cannot be destroyed by non Lignum Vitae tools or weapons.\n\n- Luxaeterna Oil (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points)- Unit cost per Oil: 3000 Luxaeterna units.\n- Changes the physical damage type into Holy.\n\n- Corvuskite Oil (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points)- Unit cost per Oil: 3050 Corvuskite units.\n- Changes the physical damage type into Dark.\n\n- Arcanium Oil (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points)- Unit cost per Oil: 3000 Arcanium units.\n- Changes the physical damage type into Arcane.\n\n- Vivinthal Oil (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points)- Unit cost per Oil: 3000 Vivinthal units.\n- Changes the physical damage type into Water.\n\n- Salachar Oil (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points)- Unit cost per Oil: 3000 Salachar units.\n- Changes the physical damage type into Fire.\n\n- Sylphsteel Oil (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points)- Unit cost per Oil: 3000 Sylphsteel units\n- Changes the physical damage type into Wind.\n\n- Fulgarite Oil ( 1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points)- Unit cost per Oil: 3000 Fulgarite Units\n- Changes the physical damage type into Lightning.\n\n- Ghimslag Oil (1550 Clim / 10 Crafting points)- Unit cost per Oil: 3000 Ghimslag units.\n- Changes the physical damage type into Earth.\n\n- Nullite Oil ( 2050 Clim / 30 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per oil: 4000 Nullite units\n- All attacks made with this weapon gain the Shieldbreaker property.\n\n- Runesteel Oil ( 1050 Clim / 10 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per oil: 2000 Runesteel units\n- This weapon can channel spells as if it was a channeling weapon.\n\n- Sepsium Oil ( 2050 Clim / 30 Crafting Points):- Unit cost per oil: 4000 Sepsium units\n- When damaging a creature with this weapon, they cannot recover HP (except for regeneration type effects) until the start of your next turn.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d2-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d2-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"carpenter-s-chisel","name":"Carpenter's Chisel","type":"Equipment","subType":"Tool","cost":"500","burden":"1","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Core crafting tool. Allows you to craft items as a carpenter.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d7-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d7-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"cart","name":"Cart","type":"Mount","subType":"","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"0","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Carpentry","description":"A simple cart used for storing items. May store an additional 2000 units worth of every material.\n\nMust be pulled by a large creature or reduce traveling speed by half.\n\n(Costs 1 Wood Block to craft.)\n\nMay be crafted using Maple / Ash / Yew / Yggdrasil wood to hold an additional 1000 / 3000 / 6000 / 10000 units of every material.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e7-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e7-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"cartographer-s-kit","name":"Cartographer's Kit","type":"Adventuring Essentials","subType":"Kit","cost":"300 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"Cartographer’s Kits contain a compass, gridded parchment, graphite pencils, a measuring rod, a protractor, and a travel logbook. Perfect for mapping unknown terrain and recording vital landmarks.\n\nEffect: You can use the cartographer's kit to make maps to trade to others and can accurately mark things on the map. You may also use it to perfectly copy other maps by making an Art (Cartography) check against DC15.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305cd-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305cd-lg.webp","imageAlignment":""},{"id":"chainsaw-artifice--two-handed-weapon-","name":"Chainsaw Artifice (Two-Handed Weapon)","type":"Artifice","subType":"Weapon","cost":"3000 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"1 per use","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"Let it rip: After making an attack with this weapon, subsequent attacks with this weapon deal +1 damage.\n\nYou may consume 1 shell to empower the artifice until the end of your turn. While empowered, the damage bonus of subsequent attacks stacks.\n\nMods:\n\n- A mods:- Multi Gear Chaindrive (20 points): On activate. Heavy attacks grant 2 stacks instead of 1.\n- Turbo Engine (10 points): If a heavy attack is the first attack used, it grants the damage stack immediately.\n\n- B mods:- B Modification, Redline Engine (80 points): The activation ability begins at +2 stacks, but the artifice cannot use the empower ability again after it ends until the end of the arc.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d4-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d4-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"cloak","name":"Cloak","type":"Equipment","subType":"Armor","cost":"500","burden":"0","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Armorsmithing","description":"A common cloak made from animal hides. Helps protects the wearer from cold weather, but offers no additional benefits.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305de-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305de-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"top"},{"id":"corrosive-flask","name":"Corrosive Flask","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Flask","cost":"350 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"An Alchemical mix that splashes acid onto a target, making armor brittle. May be thrown up to 40ft away. When thrown, the target of the flask takes 1 damage. On contact, their armor value is reduced by 3 (min 0) until they spend 2 AP to wipe the substance of.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 450 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Rare Fire","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930558-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930558-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"counter-magic-shackles","name":"Counter-Magic Shackles","type":"Artifice","subType":"Basic","cost":"4000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"2 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per day","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"Special Shackles that were created for restraining targets with high magic levels. They disrupt the shackled target’s magic circuits— making them unable to use any magic or mana abilities. Because of the nature of the magic circuit restriction, they can only be used on unconscious targets.\n\nModifications:\n\nB Modification, Zero Suppression. Lowers the target’s visible aura to 0 while wearing these, making them difficult to locate by magical means.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930567-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930567-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"crossbow--one-handed-","name":"Crossbow (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Carpentry","description":"Armor Pierce: Treats the enemy's Guard as if it was 1 lower if within 30ft of the target.\n\nRange: 60ft\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Wrist-mounted (35 points): One handed crossbow only, range lowered to 30ft. Is mounted on your wrist and is always considered drawn + can hold a weapon in that hand.\n- Windlass Arbalest (35 points): Two handed crossbow only. Basic attacks with this weapon gain full pierce within 30 ft. However must be reloaded for 2 AP or 1 RP before it can be used again.\n\n- B mods:- Extended Draw (50 points): Your armor piercing effect range is increased to 60ft. If combined with a wrist mounted crossbow, increases the range but not the armor piercing range to 60ft.\n- Repeater (80 points): When you make 3 attacks with this weapon in 1 turn, you may make an additional light attack.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493059e-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493059e-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"crossbow--two-handed-","name":"Crossbow (Two-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Carpentry","description":"Armor Pierce: Treats the enemy's Guard as if it was 2 lower if within 30ft of the target.\n\nRange: 120ft\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Wrist-mounted (35 points): One handed crossbow only, range lowered to 30ft. Is mounted on your wrist and is always considered drawn + can hold a weapon in that hand.\n- Windlass Arbalest (35 points): Two handed crossbow only. Basic attacks with this weapon gain full pierce within 30 ft. However after every attack (even without the benefit), it must be reloaded for 2 AP or 1 RP before it can be used again.\n\n- B mods:- Extended Draw (50 points): Your armor piercing effect range is increased to 60ft.\n- Repeater (80 points): When you make 3 attacks with this weapon in 1 turn, you may make an additional light attack.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493059f-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493059f-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"culinarian-ingredients","name":"Culinarian Ingredients","type":"Crafting","subType":"Materials","cost":"","burden":"","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"The base material for crafting food is Food Units. These units can be any kind of food/filler material for example:\n\n- 100u of Flour\n- 50u of Fish\n- 100u of Noodles\nOther than that there are special materials used for making different cooking stocks:\n\n- Box of Fresh Mushrooms (250c)\n- Box of Fresh Meat (250c)\n- Box of Fresh Fish (250c)\n- Box of Fresh Vegetables (250c)\n- Bundle of Spicy Peppers (250c)\n- Bundle of Fresh Cooking Herbs (250c)\nIn addition you can add special ingredients.\n\n- King Chungus Fungus (1250 Clim / 30 Crafting Points)- An extremely rare mushroom known for extreme deliciousness. Gives +1 Mana Regeneration to a Stock when eating food made with the stock.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e1-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e1-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"culinary-kit","name":"Culinary Kit","type":"Adventuring Essentials","subType":"Kit","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"-","craftingType":"","description":"Culinary Kits come with easily portable cooking knives, a pot and a pan and preserved food. Has a special compartment to draw the pan as a weapon in a pinch! The included pan isn't tough enough for a skilled chef, but good enough for a novice.\n\nRest Action: You cook a meal for your party at the cost of 40 units of food (equal to 20 Clim) per person, giving you the benefits of food (2 mana) for the rest.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c2-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c2-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"demonblood-potion","name":"Demonblood Potion","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Potion","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"Not actually made out of Demonblood, it refers to Demon tenacity. The potion is an intense stimulant that allows a character to fight through pain and injury. When drank, you ignore the penalties of one injury until the end of the encounter.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 250 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Rare Arcane\n- 1x Rare Fire","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930552-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930552-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"diamondize-potion","name":"Diamondize Potion","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Potion","cost":"3000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"Temporarily encases the user in hard crystal, rendering them nearly impervious to damage but incapacitating them in stasis. While in stasis, you cannot take any actions but all damage (including true damage) you take is reduced by 200. Lasts for 10 minutes and can be used while downed.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 4400 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Supreme Earth\n- 1x Mystic Arcane\n- 1x Mystic Water","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930554-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930554-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"displacement-potion","name":"Displacement Potion","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Potion","cost":"300 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"When drunk, you teleport 40ft in a random direction (roll 1d8 to determine this, 1 being north and 5 being south etc). If this would place you inside a wall or otherwise occupied place, the teleport fails and the potion is wasted.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 350 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Rare Wind","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930587-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930587-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"dueling-weapon--one-handed-","name":"Dueling Weapon (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Dueling: When attacking a single enemy during a turn at least 3 times with this weapon, your next Dodge or Block against that enemy costs 0 RP until the start of your next turn. This property cannot be used if you target any other enemy during your turn or if you spend AP making a Heavy attack against the target.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Spade Lunga (10 points): When moving at least 40ft towards an enemy, increases the range of your next attack made with this weapon by 5 ft.\n- Ornate Blade (35 points): Moving into the target’s threatened zone the first time in a turn counts as 1 attack for the requirement to activate Dueling.\n\n- B mods:- Paired Duelers (25 points): When wielding two dueling weapons with paired duelers, your offhand extra attack counts as one attack for your dueling bonus on your main hand weapon.\n- Passato Sotto (80 points): You may make 1 Heavy attack with this weapon and still gain the dueling effect.\n- Ferrobri Grip (80 points): Dueling weapon passive changes to Aggressive Dueling: When attacking a single enemy 3 times with this weapon in 1 turn, your next basic attack with this weapon this turn has its cost reduced by 1 AP. Once per round.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930599-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930599-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"elemental-immunity-elixir","name":"Elemental Immunity Elixir","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Elixir","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"An elixir that raises your resistance against a type of damage. When drunk, you take 11 true damage. You gain 10 damage reduction against a single type of damage, determined by the type of elixir. This lasts until the end of the encounter.\n\nThere exist elixirs for Arcane, Fire, Water, Frost, Lightning, Wind, Earth, Holy and Dark resistance.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 1250 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 3x Rare herb of matching element (Arcane for holy/dark, Wind for Lightning, Water for Frost)","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930578-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930578-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"elemental-mixture-flask","name":"Elemental Mixture Flask","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Flask","cost":"200 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"A flask that when thrown explodes in a 15x15ft area dealing damage based on the type of flask. May be thrown up to 40ft away. You may make a light attack against all caught in the explosion area. The damage type of this is determined by the type of flask. There exist flasks that deal Arcane, Fire, Water, Frost, Wind, Lightning, Earth, Holy and Dark damage.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 0 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Rare herb of the element (Arcane for holy/dark, Wind for Lightning, Water for Frost)","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930576-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930576-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"elemental-resistance-elixir","name":"Elemental Resistance Elixir","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Elixir","cost":"300 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"An elixir that raises your resistance against a type of damage. When drunk, you take 11 true damage. You gain 5 damage reduction against a single type of damage, determined by the type of elixir. This lasts until the end of the encounter.\n\nThere exist elixirs for Arcane, Fire, Water, Frost, Lightning, Wind, Earth, Holy and Dark resistance.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 350 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Rare herb of matching element (Arcane for holy/dark, Wind for Lightning, Water for Frost)","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930577-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930577-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"elemental-weapon-artifice","name":"Elemental Weapon Artifice","type":"Artifice","subType":"Weapon","cost":"1000","burden":"Cost of weapon + 1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per use","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"An artifice that sends energy through the weapon. The type is predetermined and can not be changed. The appearance and effect are based on the type. For example, a fire weapon might cover the weapon in flames and deal fire damage. When your attacks with this weapon deal damage, the type of damage they deal changes based on this weapon’s element. This effect lasts for 1 minute. Can only be applied to melee weapons.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930537-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930537-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"equipment-patching-kit","name":"Equipment Patching Kit","type":"Adventuring Essentials","subType":"Kit","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"-","craftingType":"","description":"Contains all the necessary materials to jury rig a fix on damaged weapons.\n\nRest Action: You can patch a broken piece of equipment, allowing it to be usable until the end of the scenario if it is repairable. The equipment still counts as broken at the end of the scenario and cannot be patched again until fully repaired.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c3-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c3-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"eye-lens","name":"Eye Lens","type":"Equipment","subType":"Accessory","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A lens that boosts the power of mystic eyes when crafted with good materials. Has little effect normally, except for looking stylish.\n\nIf crafted with Tamahagane, Mithril, Orihalcum or Escudo gives a bonus to Mystic Eye attacks as if it was a weapon.\n\nThis item is crafted similarly to an artifice weapon and gives the same sort of Material bonus, but cannot take alloys, mods or burden reducing effects.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ba-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ba-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"facilities","name":"Facilities","type":"Crafting","subType":"Materials","cost":"","burden":"","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"Blacksmithing Workshop\n\nLevel 1\n\n- Labor Required: 450 labor points\n- Iron Units: 10,800\n- Lumber Units: 7,200\n- Alchemy Units (flux, bonding agents): 3,600\n- Magical Fuel Units (forge core): 2,400\nLevel 2\n\n- Labor Required: 900 labor points\n- Iron Units: 21,600\n- Lumber Units: 14,400\n- Alchemy Units: 7,200\n- Magical Fuel Units: 4,800\nLevel 3\n\n- Labor Required: 1,350 labor points\n- Iron Units: 32,400\n- Lumber Units: 21,600\n- Alchemy Units: 10,800\n- Magical Fuel Units: 7,200\nAlchemy Atelier\n\nLevel 1\n\n- Labor Required: 450 labor points\n- Alchemy Units (distillers, reagents, containers): 12,000\n- Iron Units (racks, containment): 6,000\n- Magical Fuel Units (heating, boiling): 3,600\n- Lumber Units (workbenches, storage): 2,400\nLevel 2\n\n- Labor Required: 900 labor points\n- Alchemy Units: 24,000\n- Iron Units: 12,000\n- Magical Fuel Units: 7,200\n- Lumber Units: 4,800\nLevel 3\n\n- Labor Required: 1,350 labor points\n- Alchemy Units: 36,000\n- Iron Units: 18,000\n- Magical Fuel Units: 10,800\n- Lumber Units: 7,200\nCarpentry Workshop\n\nLevel 1\n\n- Labor Required: 450 labor points\n- Lumber Units (framework, shelving, benches): 15,600\n- Iron Units (tools, clamps, hinges): 4,800\n- Alchemy Units (wood preservatives, finishes): 2,400\n- Calligraphy Units (stencils, carving plans): 1,200\nLevel 2\n\n- Labor Required: 900 labor points\n- Lumber Units: 31,200\n- Iron Units: 9,600\n- Alchemy Units: 4,800\n- Calligraphy Units: 2,400\nLevel 3\n\n- Labor Required: 1,350 labor points\n- Lumber Units: 46,800\n- Iron Units: 14,400\n- Alchemy Units: 7,200\n- Calligraphy Units: 3,600\nProfessional Kitchen\n\nLevel 1\n\n- Labor Required: 450 labor points\n- Iron Units (appliances, counters): 9,600\n- Food Units (storage, prep components): 6,000\n- Lumber Units (tables, cabinetry): 4,800\n- Alchemy Units (preservation agents): 2,400\n- Magical Fuel Units (heat source): 1,200\nLevel 2\n\n- Labor Required: 900 labor points\n- Iron Units: 19,200\n- Food Units: 12,000\n- Lumber Units: 9,600\n- Alchemy Units: 4,800\n- Magical Fuel Units: 2,400\nLevel 3\n\n- Labor Required: 1,350 labor points\n- Iron Units: 28,800\n- Food Units: 18,000\n- Lumber Units: 14,400\n- Alchemy Units: 7,200\n- Magical Fuel Units: 3,600\nArtificer's Atelier\n\nLevel 1\n\n- Labor Required: 450 labor points\n- Magical Fuel Units (power conduits, channeling arrays): 9,600\n- Alchemy Units (enchantment mediums): 7,200\n- Iron Units (framework, clamps): 3,600\n- Calligraphy Units (rune matrices, glyphs): 2,400\n- Lumber Units (tables, cabinets): 1,200\nLevel 2\n\n- Labor Required: 900 labor points\n- Magical Fuel Units: 19,200\n- Alchemy Units: 14,400\n- Iron Units: 7,200\n- Calligraphy Units: 4,800\n- Lumber Units: 2,400\nLevel 3\n\n- Labor Required: 1,350 labor points\n- Magical Fuel Units: 28,800\n- Alchemy Units: 21,600\n- Iron Units: 10,800\n- Calligraphy Units: 7,200\n- Lumber Units: 3,600\nInfirmary\n\nLevel 1\n\n- Labor Required: 180 labor points\n- Lumber Units (structure, beds): 2,688\n- Alchemy Units (disinfectants, reagents): 1,920\n- Iron Units (tools, fixtures): 1,920\n- Medical Units (gauze, potions, ointments): 1,920\n- Junk Units (bandages, bedding): 1,152\nLevel 2\n\n- Labor Required: 180 labor points\n- Lumber Units: 2,688\n- Alchemy Units: 1,920\n- Iron Units: 1,920\n- Medical Units: 1,920\n- Junk Units: 1,152\nLevel 3\n\n- Labor Required: 360 labor points\n- Lumber Units: 5,376\n- Alchemy Units: 3,840\n- Iron Units: 3,840\n- Medical Units: 3,840\n- Junk Units: 2,304\nGreenhouse\n\nLevel 1\n\n- Labor Required: 150 labor points\n- Lumber Units (frames, planting beds, support beams): 3,200\n- Alchemy Units (growth treatments, pest control, soil infusion): 1,600\n- Food Units (compost, botanical starter stock): 1,200\n- Iron Units (hinges, glass framing, support rods): 800\n- Magical Fuel Units (temperature and light control orbs): 800\n- Calligraphy Units (plant labels, cultivation logs): 400\nLevel 2\n\n- Labor Required: 150 labor points\n- Lumber Units (frames, planting beds, support beams): 3,200\n- Alchemy Units (growth treatments, pest control, soil infusion): 1,600\n- Food Units (compost, botanical starter stock): 1,200\n- Iron Units (hinges, glass framing, support rods): 800\n- Magical Fuel Units (temperature and light control orbs): 800\n- Calligraphy Units (plant labels, cultivation logs): 400\nLevel 3\n\n- Labor Required: 150 labor points\n- Lumber Units (frames, planting beds, support beams): 3,200\n- Alchemy Units (growth treatments, pest control, soil infusion): 1,600\n- Food Units (compost, botanical starter stock): 1,200\n- Iron Units (hinges, glass framing, support rods): 800\n- Magical Fuel Units (temperature and light control orbs): 800\n- Calligraphy Units (plant labels, cultivation logs): 400\nDojo\n\nLevel 1\n\n- Labor Required: 150 labor points\n- Lumber Units (flooring, walls, weapon racks): 4,000\n- Iron Units (training gear, fittings): 2,000\n- Calligraphy Units (instructional scrolls, banners): 1,200\n- Alchemy Units (tonics, conditioning oils): 800\nLevel 2\n\n- Labor Required: 150 labor points\n- Lumber Units: 4,000\n- Iron Units: 2,000\n- Calligraphy Units: 1,200\n- Alchemy Units: 800\nLevel 3\n\n- Labor Required: 300 labor points\n- Lumber Units: 8,000\n- Iron Units: 4,000\n- Calligraphy Units: 2,400\n- Alchemy Units: 1,600\nShrine\n\nLevel 1\n\n- Labor Required: 570 labor points\n- Lumber Units (structure, altar frame): 12,160\n- Alchemy Units (oils, incense, blessing media): 9,120\n- Calligraphy Units (prayer plaques, scripture): 6,080\n- Magical Fuel Units (radiant light wells, wards): 3,040\nLevel 2\n\n- Labor Required: 570 labor points\n- Lumber Units: 12,160\n- Alchemy Units: 9,120\n- Calligraphy Units: 6,080\n- Magical Fuel Units: 3,040\nLevel 3\n\n- Labor Required: 1140 labor points\n- Lumber Units: 24,320\n- Alchemy Units: 18,240\n- Calligraphy Units: 12,160\n- Magical Fuel Units: 6,080\nSauna\n\nLevel 1\n\n- Labor Required: 570 labor points\n- Lumber Units (walls, benches, decking): 15,200\n- Alchemy Units (steam oils, restorative blends): 7,600\n- Magical Fuel Units (heat stones, vapor generators): 4,560\n- Iron Units (steam vents, pipework): 3,040\nLevel 2\n\n- Labor Required: 570 labor points\n- Lumber Units: 15,200\n- Alchemy Units: 7,600\n- Magical Fuel Units: 4,560\n- Iron Units: 3,040\nLevel 3\n\n- Labor Required: 1140 labor points\n- Lumber Units: 30,400\n- Alchemy Units: 15,200\n- Magical Fuel Units: 9,120\n- Iron Units: 6,080\nAppraiser's Workshop\n\nLevel 1\n\n- Labor Required: 120 labor points\n- Alchemy Units (analysis fluids, solvents): 2,560\n- Calligraphy Units (valuation records, ledgers): 1,600\n- Artifice Units (reference samples, comparative pieces): 1,280\n- Iron Units (weighing tools, clamps): 640\n- Lumber Units (display racks, benches): 320\nLevel 2\n\n- Labor Required: 360 labor points\n- Alchemy Units: 7,680\n- Calligraphy Units: 4,800\n- Artifice Units: 3,840\n- Iron Units: 1,920\n- Lumber Units: 960\nLevel 3\n\n- Labor Required: 600 labor points\n- Alchemy Units: 12,800\n- Calligraphy Units: 8,000\n- Artifice Units: 6,400\n- Iron Units: 3,200\n- Lumber Units: 1,600\nShop\n\nLevel 1\n\n- Labor Required: 150 labor points\n- Lumber Units (walls, counters, display cases): 2,800\n- Calligraphy Units (signage, ledgers): 2,400\n- Iron Units (shelving, locks): 1,600\n- Alchemy Units (storage stabilizers): 800\n- Food Units (sample packaging, merchant stock): 400\nLevel 2\n\n- Labor Required: 150 labor points\n- Lumber Units: 2,800\n- Calligraphy Units: 2,400\n- Iron Units: 1,600\n- Alchemy Units: 800\n- Food Units: 400\nLevel 3\n\n- Labor Required: 300 labor points\n- Lumber Units: 5,600\n- Calligraphy Units: 4,800\n- Iron Units: 3,200\n- Alchemy Units: 1,600\n- Food Units: 800\nStable\n\nLevel 1\n\n- Labor Required: 120 labor points\n- Lumber Units (stalls, framework, walls): 3,840\n- Iron Units (gates, hinges, locks): 1,280\n- Alchemy Units (wood treatment, pest repellent): 640\n- Food Units (storage bins, feed provisions): 640\nLevel 2\n\n- Labor Required: 120 labor points\n- Lumber Units: 3,840\n- Iron Units: 1,280\n- Alchemy Units: 640\n- Food Units: 640\nLevel 3\n\n- Labor Required: 120 labor points\n- Lumber Units: 3,840\n- Iron Units: 1,280\n- Alchemy Units: 640\n- Food Units: 640","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305da-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305da-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"falcon-elixir","name":"Falcon Elixir","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Elixir","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"When drunk, you take 11 true damage. You gain the ability to fly with a speed equal to your normal speed. The effect lasts for 10 rounds.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 1250 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Mystic Wind\n- 1x Rare Arcane","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493058a-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493058a-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"farming-materials","name":"Farming Materials","type":"Crafting","subType":"Materials","cost":"","burden":"","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"Seeds:\n\nThere are several basic seeds farmers can use:\n\n- Food Units:- Cost: 5 Clim\n- Difficulty: 5\n- Yields: 150 Food units\n- Growing time: 1\n\n- Alchemy Units:- Cost: 5 Clim\n- Difficulty: 5\n- Yields: 150 Alchemy units\n- Growing time: 1\n\n- Alchemy Herbs:- Cost: 10 Clim\n- Difficulty: 5\n- Yields: 1 common herb of the element of the seed\n- Growing time: 1\n\nCost is the value of the seed.\n\nDifficulty is how much crafting points it takes to gather the yield when harvesting.\n\nYield is what the seed gives once harvested.\n\nGrowing time is how long a seed takes to be harvested. A growing time of 1 means it can be harvested immediately once you have enough IP to use the Harvest ability. When a seed has a growing time longer than 1, it takes harvests equal to the growing time to receive the yield. When resolving a harvest with a seed with a growing time of more than 1 remaining, you still need to pay the difficulty to take care of the seed like normal.\n\nSpecial Seeds:\n\nThese function like normal seeds, but are not typically available in stores.\n\n- Moon-Phase Seeds:- Cost: 25 Clim\n- Difficulty 15\n- Yield: 1 rare herb of the element of the seed\n- Growing time 1\n- Special: If you let it grow for another season after the first, the yield changes to a Mystic Herb of the same element.\n\nFertilizer:\n\n- Average:- Cost: 250 Clim\n- Effect: +1 Crafting dice\n\n- Good- Cost: 500 Clim\n- Effect: +2 Crafting dice\n\n- Excellent:- Cost: 1000 Clim\n- Effect: +3 Crafting Dice\n\n- Supreme:- Cost: 2000 Clim\n- Effect: +4 Crafting Dice\n\nFertilizer can be applied during the harvesting part. You can only apply 1 fertilizer at the same time.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d1-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d1-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"fire-robe","name":"Fire Robe","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"3000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per arc","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A red robe with a design based of a Divine Arms. Keeps the wearer cool in even the hottest of weathers by repelling the heat.\n\nCan be activated to give the wearer 5 damage reduction against fire damage until the end of the encounter. When this effect ends, the shell inside the robe is immediately used up and needs to be replaced for the weather repelling effect to function.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930581-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930581-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"flame-oil-flask","name":"Flame Oil Flask","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Flask","cost":"150 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"An Alchemical mix that creates an area of flame. May be thrown up to 40ft away. Creates a 15x15ft area of fire that lasts until the start of your next turn. Any creature ending their turn in the area takes 20 full pierce fire damage.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 330 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Common Fire","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493055b-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493055b-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"flamellon","name":"Flamellon","type":"Crafting","subType":"Materials","cost":"","burden":"","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"A generic term for items attuned to a Flamelic Polarity.\n\nThese items are valued at the usual 2 units for 1 clim.\n\nFor example, you could have 500 corpse dust that has an Undead Flamelic Polarity. This 500 dust would be valued at 250 clim.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b5-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b5-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"flashbang-flask","name":"Flashbang Flask","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Flask","cost":"250 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"An Alchemical mix that explodes in a bright flash and loud noise when exposed to air. May be thrown up to 40ft away. All targets caught within a 25x25ft area become Dazed.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 420 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 3x Common Wind","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930556-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930556-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"frying-pan","name":"Frying Pan","type":"Equipment","subType":"Tool","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Core crafting tool. Allows you to craft items as a culinarian.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e0-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e0-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"fuel-cartridge-pack","name":"Fuel Cartridge Pack","type":"Adventuring Essentials","subType":"Storage","cost":"50 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"A bag that stores magical fuel shells. Each shell is shaped like a cartridge.\n\nStores up to 20 burden worth of Fuel Shells, reducing their burden to 0.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930570-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930570-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"gauntlets--one-handed-","name":"Gauntlets (One-handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"500","burden":"1","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Unarmed Combat: Attacks with this weapon count as unarmed attacks for the purposes of Unarmed Strike. If you are proficient in unarmed attacks, you are automatically proficient in this weapon. Otherwise, you are never proficient in this weapon.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Martial Mastery (35 points): You may have your attacks deal Elemental damage instead of physical based on your mastered classes. Bajiquan for Fire, Monk for Water, Sky Talon for Wind and Still Stone for Earth, Transcendant Lightning for Lightning, Five Harmonies for Holy, Black Oath for Dark.\n\n- B mods:- Wrist Claw (25 points): While wearing this item, you may still hold an item in that hand as if it was empty.\n- Katar (50 points): Grants Nimble. Nimble: After attacking an enemy with a light attack on your turn, you may move 5ft. This movement only provokes attacks of opportunity if that movement would put you out of melee range of the target.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ed-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ed-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"ghost-elixir","name":"Ghost Elixir","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Elixir","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"A translucent potion that when drunk gives you the phase through trait for 1 minute. This Lets you move through solid objects and creatures. When thrown at a creature with the phase through and/or incorporeal traits, they lose these traits for a minute. Can be thrown up to 40ft.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 300 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Rare Arcane\n- 1x Rare Wind","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493054b-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493054b-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"ghostblade","name":"Ghostblade","type":"Divine Arms","subType":"Main","cost":"","burden":"","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"Current Wielder: Unknown\n\nA weapon that mimics the movement and attacks of ghostly creatures.\n\nLevel 1:\nFor your first 20ft of movement during a turn, you become Ethereal. You do not provoke attacks of opportunity and may move through solid objects.\n\nLevel 2:\nOnce per arc, you may use Soul Pierce\n\nSoul Pierce\nCost: 2 AP\nKeywords: Sure Hit, Full Pierce\nRange: Melee Weapon Range\nRequirement: -\nDescription:\nYou may make a Precise attack against the target that deals maximum Heavy damage and lowers the target’s mana by 5. If the target has 0 or less mana after this, they take an additional maximum Heavy damage.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930573-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930573-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"giant-dragonfly","name":"Giant Dragonfly","type":"Mount","subType":"","cost":"1500 Clim","burden":"0","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"A dragonfly trained to be used in combat.\n\nStats:\n\nHP: 18\n\nFocus: 3\n\nPower: 2\n\nAgility: 6\n\nToughness: 1\n\nSpeed: 30ft\n\nSize: Small\n\nSpecial Qualities:\n\nTiny Flying Mount: Your mount can fly. While moving only on the ground, your speed is reduced to 5ft. You may use the cavalier’s ability Rider & Mount As One to re-direct attacks away from your mount even while flying. Any damage you take while using this will cause you to lose altitude as if your mount took damage.\n\nSpectral Trample: You may apply the trample effect to creatures of any size, but your attack does not gain Sure Hit, displace the enemy or knock them prone. If they dodge your attack, your trample movement is not canceled.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ca-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ca-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"giant-scissors--two-handed-","name":"Giant Scissors (Two-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Artisan Weapon","cost":"1250","burden":"2","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Giant Scissors are used by Foragers in their activities. With proficiency, they count as a 2h weapon that can be used as a foraging tool.\n\nShearing: You deal +1 damage against unarmored targets.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Elegant Executioner (35 points): Reduces Vivisect AP cost by 1.\n- Diamond Tip (35 points): Shearing now always deals +1 damage regardless of armor.\n\n- B mods:- Executioner's Blade (50 points): Heavy basic attacks strike an adjacent target in range with a light attack. Once per turn\n- Separation (80 points): You can separate the Giant Scissors into two pieces for 0 AP (Quick), allowing you to dual wield them. You can use Separation again to put them back together. The passive changes from Shearing to Shearing Flurry which instead grants +1 accuracy to unarmored targets.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d3-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d3-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"gourmet-cooking-stock","name":"Gourmet Cooking Stock","type":"Crafting","subType":"","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Culinary","description":"Can be added to meals to make gourmet meals. When cooking food during rest actions, you can create gourmet food which grants non-stacking buffs. Can only be used when cooking fresh food with a Culinary Kit or a Kitchen. Cooking stocks typically come in a pack of 10 and it uses one cooking stock per meal. If you are cooking a big meal for your party members, you need one stock per serving. When using the Culinary Kit action with a stock, you must have enough stock to cover all of the food being made, otherwise the effect does not work. For example, if you are cooking for 4 people, you need 160u of food and 4 cooking stocks to get the cooking stock effect. (Remember, you can only use your culinary kit once per rest).\n\nTo make a cooking stock you start with a base, which requires 500u of any mix of food.\n\n- Mushroom Stock (+Focus)\n- Meaty Stock (+Power)\n- Fish Stock (+Toughness)\n- Vegetable Stock (+Agility)\n- Spicy Stock (+Crafting)\n- Herbal Stock (+Gathering)\nCulinarians can make multi-flavored stocks as well, which can increase more than one attribute at once.\n\nWhen using a Gourmet stock, the meal counts as a gourmet meal and gives +1 mana.\n\nWhen crafting a stock, you make 10 at a time.\n\nUsing stock from scratch example:\n\n- Obtain 500u of Mushrooms.\n- Errand action to create a box of fresh mushrooms.\n- Craft Base Stock for 500u of any food.\n- Change base stock to mushroom stock by putting in the box of fresh mushrooms and using the Culinarian skill.\n- Use Stir Layered Flavors to add another ingredient. Adding a box of fresh meat to make a Meaty Mushroom stock.\n- Use Every Last Drop to increase stock yield by 2.\n- You obtain 10+2 Meaty Mushroom Stock which grants +1 Focus and +1 Power Food Bonus for 24 hours.\n- During a rest action, cooking for 5 people, you add 5 Meaty Mushroom Stock and 200u of food to make 5 Meaty Mushroom Dishes to feed your party and give them buffs.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e2-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e2-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"grapeshot-flask","name":"Grapeshot Flask","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Flask","cost":"100 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"An Alchemical mix that explodes when shattered, sending small metal balls in all directions. May be thrown up to 40ft away. All targets within a 15x15ft area take 5 full pierce physical damage.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 180 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Common Fire","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930557-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930557-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"grappling-hook-artifice","name":"Grappling Hook Artifice","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"2000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per use","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A handheld cylinder shaped artifice that fires out a pin with a 40ft rope attached to it. The pin attaches itself to any non-living surface it hits and it can support the weight of up to four people. The GM may require an accuracy check for distant or hard to hit surfaces.\n\nAfter the pin is attached, you may spend 0 AP to reel yourself in and move towards where the pin is attached to. Any allies within 5ft of you may grab onto you and be moved alongside you for 0 RP (Up to 3 allies total).\n\nModifications:\n\n- A Modification, Belt Attachment. The Grappling Hook Artifice is modified to be mounted onto the belt, allowing for operation while wielding items in both hands via a switch mounted on the arm.\n- A Modification, Drive By Model. The Grappling Hook Artifice loses the ability to move allies, but you can now make attacks at any point while being reeled as long as you have actions. While you are moving in this way, you do not provoke attacks of opportunity.\n- B Modification, Scorpion Tip. The range of the Grappling Hook Artifice is lowered to 20ft, but can be used to make a light attack that does exactly 1 damage with full pierce. On damage, the target can be pulled up to 20ft towards the user.\n- B Modification, Swing Engine. The grappling hook artifice can be used to swing from the point the pin is embedded instead of pulling straight towards it, in addition the rope length is increased by 20ft. The pin automatically detaches and reels in when you move to your destination for smooth traveling.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930539-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930539-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"greater-healing-potion","name":"Greater Healing Potion","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Potion","cost":"600 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP, 4 Mana","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"Healing liquid in a vial made from various herbs and reagents. Spurs the body’s natural healing by converting mana into regeneration. Much purer and more difficult to create, uses special materials. When drank, you heal for 30 HP.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 970 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Rare Water\n- 3x Common Earth","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930553-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930553-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"growth-potion","name":"Growth Potion","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Potion","cost":"1100 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"By Charre.\n\nA rare magical potion that speeds up the growth of animals when given to them, allowing them to reach maturity much more quickly. See animal raising in the rulebook for more details on its use.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 2000 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Mystic Arcane","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305f4-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305f4-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"healing-potion","name":"Healing Potion","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Potion","cost":"150 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP, 2 Mana","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"Healing liquid in a vial made from various herbs and reagents. Spurs the body’s natural healing by converting mana into regeneration. When drank, you heal 15 HP.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 450 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs: None required","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930538-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930538-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"heavy-blade--two-handed-","name":"Heavy Blade (Two-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Overpower: When you land a critical hit with a Heavy Blade, you deal an additional 1d4 damage if it was a light attack or an additional 1d12 damage if it was a heavy attack. This extra damage is not automatically maximized from rolling a critical hit, but you keep the extra damage even if the target blocked the critical hit.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Overwhelming Edge (20 points): You cannot be disarmed or parried.\n- Wide Blade (35 points): When you are wielding this in two hands and don’t make an attack with this weapon on your turn you can grant yourself or an adjacent ally low cover against ranged attacks for 0 RP until the start of your next turn. Can only use this once per turn.\n\n- B mods:- Quakemaker (25 points): Critical hits render the target prone regardless of if they hit or not.\n- Gutsy Blade (50 points): The crit threshold of this weapon is lowered by 5, but you no longer maximize damage dice or gain full pierce on a crit.\n- Executioner's Blade (50 points): Heavy basic attacks strike an adjacent target in range with a light attack. Once per turn\n- Unreasonable Mass (80 points): Heavy attacks gain 1 additional dice in damage (5d6->6d6) but suffer -1 accuracy on all attacks.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930594-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930594-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"hori","name":"Hori","type":"Equipment","subType":"Artisan Weapon","cost":"500","burden":"1","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Hori knives are used by Foragers in their activities. With proficiency, they count as small weapons that can be used as a foraging tool.\n\nHidden Weapon: You may draw this weapon for 0 AP. Each combat, after you draw the weapon if the next attack you make that round is using this weapon and is a basic Light or Heavy attack, it gains the Trick Attack keyword. After benefiting from this bonus, you cannot do so again the same combat even if drawing a different weapon with this ability.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Aerodynamic Design (10 points): Boomerang/Return effects cannot be used with this. For 1 RP you can throw the dagger, making a light ranged attack. On damage, the target is slowed until the end of its next turn.\n- Compact Ergonomics (20 points): When your other hand is free and you take a movement action that costs RP, that movement range is increased by 5ft.\n- Parrying Dagger (20 points): If you don’t use this weapon to make an attack during your turn, you gain a +4 bonus to your Block until the start of your next turn. You also gain a +4 bonus to your ‘damage’ roll when using the Parry ability.\n- Flat Pommel (35 points): When your other hand is free, you use your free hand to push the target into targets increasing melee heavy attack damage to 5d6.\n\n- B mods:- Poisoner Weapon (25 points): Applying poison to this weapon costs -1 AP (min 0).\n- Butterfly Knife (50 points): Your first light attack each turn with this weapon gains Trick Attack, but it can no longer make Heavy attacks.\n- Ring Pommel (50 points): If you make a heavy attack that the target defends against, you do not trigger attacks of opportunity from them until the start of your next turn.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d5-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d5-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"horse","name":"Horse","type":"Mount","subType":"","cost":"2000 Clim","burden":"0","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"A horse trained to be used for combat.\n\nStats:\n\nHP: 30\n\nFocus: 3\n\nPower: 3\n\nAgility: 3\n\nToughness: 3\n\nSpeed: 50ft\n\nSize: Large\n\nSpecial Qualities:\n\nLine Movement: You may only move in a straight line when making a movement action.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c6-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c6-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"ice-flask","name":"Ice Flask","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Flask","cost":"450 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"A flask that when thrown explodes in a 5ft radius around the target and applies frost to all target. The target and everyone within 5ft of it become Slowed until the start of your next turn. May be thrown up to 40ft away.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 300 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Rare Water\n- 1x Rare Wind","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930574-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930574-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"immunity-elixir","name":"Immunity Elixir","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Elixir","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"An elixir that raises your resistance against negative effects. When drunk, you take 11 true damage. The next 3 negative effects that you would be affected by are negated. Negative effects caused by Secret Art or Climax Art level effects are not negated through this. This lasts until the end of the encounter.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 1400 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Mystic Earth\n- 1x Rare Water","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930579-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930579-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"isona-poison","name":"Isona Poison","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Poison","cost":"700 clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"Contact Poison. Can be applied to a weapon. Lasts for 2 minute (12 rounds).\n\nWhen an attack with this poison damages a fiend type enemy, the target is considered silvered until the start of your next turn.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 1430 Alchemy Materials\nSpecial Materials:\n\n- 100u of silver\n- Common Fire Herb\n- Common Water Herb\n- Common Earth Herb\n- Common Wind Herb\n- Common Arcane Herb","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305f1-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305f1-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"katana--one-handed-","name":"Katana (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Keen: You score a critical hit on a 19 or 20.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Mastercrafted Saya (20 points): The first single target attack made with this weapon per combat also draws the weapon simultaneously. This first attack has its crit threshold lowered by 1.\n- Sori Curve (20 points): When you roll a 1 on an accuracy roll, you can reroll the attack. Your target(s) can make an opportunity attack, even with a ranged weapon. This opportunity attack does not provoke other opportunity attacks.\n- Beneri Special (35 points): Grants a +1/+1 Bonus, doesn’t stack with material bonuses. Weapon shatters, becoming irreparably broken on a 1 roll for an accuracy roll.\n\n- B mods:- Equilibrium Forging (25 points): You do not roll damage on this weapon, but deal slightly higher than average damage. Instead it deals 6 damage on light attacks or 15 damage (1h) or 19 damage (2h). Critical strikes apply maximum damage as normal.\n- Hamon Line (50 points): Grants Keen II lowers the crit threshold by 2 (replaces Keen).\n- Swallow's Edge (80 points): The crit threshold decreases by 1 for each attack made this turn with a Swallow’s Edge weapon. This bonus resets if you land a critical hit. If both your mainhand and offhand weapon have this mod, the effect aplies to both weapons at the same time.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930592-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930592-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"katana--two-handed-","name":"Katana (Two-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Keen: You score a critical hit on a 19 or 20.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Mastercrafted Saya (20 points): The first single target attack made with this weapon per combat also draws the weapon simultaneously. This first attack has its crit threshold lowered by 1.\n- Sori Curve (20 points): When you roll a 1 on an accuracy roll, you can reroll the attack. Your target(s) can make an opportunity attack, even with a ranged weapon. This opportunity attack does not provoke other opportunity attacks.\n- Beneri Special (35 points): Grants a +1/+1 Bonus, doesn’t stack with material bonuses. Weapon shatters, becoming irreparably broken on a 1 roll for an accuracy roll.\n\n- B mods:- Equilibrium Forging (25 points): You do not roll damage on this weapon, but deal slightly higher than average damage. Instead it deals 6 damage on light attacks or 15 damage (1h) or 19 damage (2h). Critical strikes apply maximum damage as normal.\n- Hamon Line (50 points): Grants Keen II lowers the crit threshold by 2 (replaces Keen).\n- Swallow's Edge (80 points): The crit threshold decreases by 1 for each attack made this turn with a Swallow’s Edge weapon. This bonus resets if you land a critical hit. If both your mainhand and offhand weapon have this mod, the effect aplies to both weapons at the same time.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930598-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930598-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"lance--one-handed-","name":"Lance (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Specialized Weapon","cost":"750 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"-","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Charger Weapon: Can only be used while mounted. Counts as a polearm weapon and has all the same properties of one. Your first attack made with this weapon type after moving at least 20ft deal maximum damage instead of rolling.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Crown Tip (10 points): The first basic attack per turn made immediately after moving 50ft or more, dismounts mounted targets on damage.\n- Demi-Lance (20 points): Can be used while dismounted as a normal spear, but loses its movement max damage bonus unless mounted.\n\n- B mods:- Justice Lance (50 points): Your movement speed is capped at 25ft while this is in your burden. This weapon has an additional 5ft range and a 15ft threaten range.\n- Shield Lance (80 points): When spending at least 3 AP to move in one turn, your next basic defense before the start of your next turn costs 1 less RP.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305bc-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305bc-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"lesser-diamondize-potion","name":"Lesser Diamondize Potion","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Potion","cost":"1500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"3 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"Temporarily encases the user in hard crystal, rendering them nearly impervious to damage but incapacitating them in stasis. While in stasis, you cannot take any actions but all damage (including true damage) you take is reduced by 200. Lasts until the start of your next turn.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 2100 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Mystic Earth\n- 1x Mystic Arcane","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493057f-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493057f-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"light-sword--one-handed-","name":"Light Sword (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Nimble: After attacking an enemy with a light attack on your turn, you may move 5ft. This movement only provokes attacks of opportunity if that movement would put you out of melee range of the target.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Single Edge (20 points): Nimble instead becomes Nimble Rotation. After attacking you can no longer move away from the enemy, but you can sidestep to anywhere adjacent to the enemy taking the most direct path possible when making a melee attack. This cannot be used if the target is reduced to 0 HP from the attack.\n- Heroic Emblem (20 points): Grants a +1 power or +1 focus bonus, but cannot gain the benefits from base material bonuses. This bonus is actually 100% from hype.\n- Fullering Groves (35 points): Gives Nimble II. After attacking an enemy with a light attack on your turn, you may move 10ft. This movement only provokes attacks of opportunity if that movement would put you out of melee range of the target.\n\n- B mods:- Extended Quillons (25 points): Grants +1 to guard when out of RP.\n- Weighted Edge (25 points): You may use Nimble (and Nimble II or Nimble Rotation etc if you have those instead) even after making a Heavy or Precise attack.\n- Gladius Edge (50 points): When you are struck by a critical hit and you do not defend against it, you can make a 0 RP opportunity attack before the triggering attack. You can spend 1 RP to instead make it a heavy attack.\n- Axebreaker (80 points): You gain a +2 Axebreaker Power bonus against enemies wielding axes.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493058d-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493058d-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"lightning-rod","name":"Lightning Rod","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"3000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"2 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per use","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A short metal rod that can be expanded with the push of a button. When placed into the ground and activated, it creates a 25x25ft zone with it in the center. Everyone in the zone gains 5 damage reduction against Lightning damage. Lasts until the end of the encounter.\n\nModifications:\n\n- A Modification, Telescopic Pole. Increases the range to 30ft x 30ft.\n- A Modification, Silver Tip Enhancement. Increases the damage reduction by 1.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930584-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930584-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"lizard-elixir","name":"Lizard Elixir","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Elixir","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP, 3 Mana","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"When drunk with a severed limb held to the right part of the body, the limb will begin to re-attach. Has to be drunk within 5 minutes of the loss. After drinking, you become stunned for a minute until the process finishes.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 1400 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Mystic Water\n- 1x Rare Earth","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930589-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930589-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"locking-seal","name":"Locking Seal","type":"Talisman","subType":"","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"4 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"A piece of paper inscribed with a single Kiraran character of ‘Lock’. When placed on a door, chest or similar object it prevents any person from opening it. The person who placed it can safely remove it, but for everyone else it counts as a tier 1 bounded field. Destroying the seal itself through physical force is impossible by normal means, but if the object it's placed on is sufficiently damaged, then the seal is broken.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493053f-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493053f-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"long-distance-communications-array","name":"Long Distance Communications Array","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"200000 Clim","burden":"5","activationCost":"4 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per hour","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A series of boxes, microphones and earplugs that is used for long range communications. It can connect to other devices by inputting a code unique to the artifice its connecting to. Any sound spoken into the microphone is broadcasted to all other artifices connected to it. It has unlimited range.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930545-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930545-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"longsword--one-handed-two-handed-","name":"Longsword (One-Handed/Two-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"750 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"-","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Versatile: At the start of your turn, before you make any attacks you may choose to treat this as either a One-Handed weapon or a Two-Handed weapon. When using a longsword as a One-Handed weapon and no other weapon or shield, you may treat the longsword as a shield as well. When using it as a Two-Handed Weapon, you deal an additional 1d4 damage on a critical hit. This extra damage is not automatically maximized from rolling a critical hit, but you keep the extra damage even if the target blocked the critical hit.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Catch Pommel (10 points): When using the Longsword with one hand, once per turn you can extend the range of your attack by 5ft.\n- War Sword (20 points): Your first basic attack made with this weapon after moving at least 20ft maximizes one damage dice of your choice instead of rolling.\n- Bastard Sword (35 points): You gain a +1 Armorbreaker Power bonus against targets in Heavy armor or higher.\n\n- B mods:- Extended Quillons (25 points): Grants +1 to guard when out of RP.\n- Heavy Crossguard (25 points): You retain the Block bonus even while using the weapon with two hands, the block value increases by +4 when wielding with one hand and no other weapon or shield in your other hand.\n- Lange Messer (50 points): Grants +1 to guard but increases burden by +1.\n- Axebreaker (80 points): You gain a +2 Axebreaker Power bonus against targets wielding axes.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930593-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930593-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"mage-s-blood","name":"Mage's Blood","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Poison","cost":"600 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"Contact poison. Can be applied to a weapon. Lasts for 1 hit or 1 minute (6 rounds).\n\nWhen an attack with this poison damages an enemy, they are inflicted with a Circuit Crash debuff. The next time they use mana before the end of the encounter, they take 4d6+8 damage.\n\nDiscovered by Beetle Swallower.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 1800 Alchemy Materials\nSpecial Materials:\n\n- 3x vial of Heartwood Poison Water.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e8-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e8-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"mana-vision-goggles","name":"Mana Vision Goggles","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"8000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"1 shell per hour","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A pair of goggles that link themselves to the wielder’s eyes. Once put on, they are always active. They allow the wielder to see the fluctuations of mana, letting them see the presence of any magic or mana based abilities including traps or barriers. They can also automatically see the presence of any creature that has mana that is not behind total cover. However, they become unable to see living creatures without mana in them.\n\nDue to the nature of these goggles, they must be carefully removed. Removing them takes a minute. Attempting to do it faster will blind the person wielding them for a minute instead.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493054c-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493054c-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"marlone-jelly-poison","name":"Marlone Jelly Poison","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Poison","cost":"400","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"Contact Poison. Can be applied to a weapon. Lasts for 1 hits or 1 minute (6 rounds).\n\nWhen an attack with this poison damages a grunt type enemy, the target is stunned until the end of this next turn. An enemy can only be affected by this poison once per combat.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 700 Alchemy Materials\nSpecial Materials:\n\n- 1x Rare Water Herb","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b6-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b6-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"medical-kit","name":"Medical Kit","type":"Adventuring Essentials","subType":"Kit","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"Medical Kits contain basic bandages, salves, alcohol, scissors and a knife. Perfect for patching up light wounds.\n\nRest action: You heal yourself or an ally for their Toughness+5. A character can only be affected once per rest by Medical Kit.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c0-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c0-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"medium-shell","name":"Medium Shell","type":"Artifice","subType":"Fuel","cost":"200 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"A medium cylinder of magical fuel that is used to power artifices. Most weapon-type artifices automatically eject the shell when they are emptied… along with a burst of steam to prevent overheating.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930564-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930564-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"memory-bubble","name":"Memory Bubble","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"2000/4000/10000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"1 shell per use (including recording)","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A spherical object that can record memories. A person can record up to 1, 2 or 5 minutes of memory into the object depending on the type. After a memory is recorded onto this artifice, no further memories can be recorded even if the time is not fully spent.\n\nAfter a memory is recorded, other people can view the memory. When using this object, they view the memory from the point of view of the recorder.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930551-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930551-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"military-ration","name":"Military Ration","type":"Adventuring Essentials","subType":"Basic","cost":"40 Clim","burden":"","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"A ready to eat meal. Grants the effects of food for rest without having to cook or prepare anything. Can be consumed during a rest to gain the effects of food (2 mana).\n\nTypically consists of of dried meats, dried fruits and blocks of compressed grains with honey. Sometimes includes vials of sauce. Typically pressed together and then rolled in linen cloth, but higher end ones can come in wooden boxes.\n\nIf eaten during an encounter, it's a Setup action that takes 8 AP to complete.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493056e-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493056e-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"mimic-potion","name":"Mimic Potion","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Potion","cost":"200 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"When drunk, your appearance shifts to that of an average sized chest. Lasts up to a minute or until a character attempts to interact with you.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 360 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Common Arcane\n- 1x Common Earth","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930586-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930586-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"mining-bag","name":"Mining Bag","type":"Equipment","subType":"Materials","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Armorsmithing","description":"You can carry an additional 2000 units of each mining material.\n\n(May be stored for 0 burden while empty)\n\nMay be crafted using Direhide / Primehide / Dragonscale / Astrahide to hold an additional 1000 / 3000 / 6000 / 10000 units of each mining material.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- -\n\n- B mods:- One item container (50 points): The additional units this bag can carry is doubled, but it only works for a single material type rather than all of them.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e3-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e3-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"minor-item","name":"Minor Item","type":"Adventuring Essentials","subType":"Basic","cost":"25 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"Generic listing for minor items not listed separately. May contain any item within reason (GM's discretion), but should only contain adventuring or daily life utility stuff.\n\nFor example: Shovel, Rope, Ink, Bedroll, Sack, Piton etc","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305bf-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305bf-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"mule","name":"Mule","type":"Mount","subType":"","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"0","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"A mule used for pulling carts and storing items. Can't be used as mount in combat (Abilities like Trample will not work if mounted on a mule).\n\nMay store an additional 1000 units worth of every material.\n\nStats:\n\nHP: 20\n\nFocus: 3\n\nPower: 3\n\nAgility: 3\n\nToughness: 3\n\nSpeed: 20ft\n\nSize: Large","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e6-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e6-lg.webp","imageAlignment":""},{"id":"musket--two-handed-","name":"Musket (Two-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"Superior Armor Pierce: Treats the enemy’s Guard as if it was 1 lower.\n\nRange: 120ft\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Range Finder (20 points): You add a range finder to the weapon. This does not increase its range, but does allow you to look through the lens for a +10 perception bonus against things further than 60ft away. In addition, you can tell how far objects are from you when doing this.\n- Bayonet (35 points): You may make melee attacks with this weapon that deal Physical(Piercing) damage without provoking attacks of opportunity. These attacks don't do 2h melee damage.\n\n- B mods:- Long Barrel (25 points): Your weapon gains 240ft range, but you don’t armor pierce when shooting at targets further than 120ft away.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a2-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a2-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"netting-flask","name":"Netting Flask","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Flask","cost":"1200 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"A flask that when thrown explodes in a 5ft radius around the target and conjures up magnetic nets. The target and everyone within 5ft of it become Rooted until the start of your next turn or until they use 2 AP to remove the net. May be thrown up to 40ft away\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 1950 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Mystic Wind\n- 1x Rare Earth","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.12.6/69ea4f7b6be32fced492fc79-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.12.6/69ea4f7b6be32fced492fc79-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"night-vision-goggles","name":"Night Vision Goggles","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"2000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per day","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"Special goggles that grant the user night vision up to 120ft in addition to keeping the eyes protected from weather and impacts. Easy to operate with the flick of a switch.\n\nModifications:\n\n- B Modification, Thermal Fusion Sight. Adds thermal vision up to 120ft. This cannot detect things hidden by magical means. The sight can not discern a difference in heat once something reaches freezing temperatures.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930566-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930566-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"northi-lantern","name":"Northi Lantern","type":"Artifice","subType":"Basic","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per arc","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A contained magical light within a casing. The light can be easily turned on and off with the flick of a switch and provides clear and stable white light that emits up to 30 feet away.\n\nModifications:\n\n- A Modification, Directional Light. Makes the light directionally forward instead of all around.\n- B Modification, Lumen Sphere. Increases the light emission to 60ft.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930561-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930561-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"parrot-elixir","name":"Parrot Elixir","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Elixir","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"When drunk, your appearance shifts to that of a random, average looking person of the same gender and race. This lasts for 24 hours. If drunk again before the time is up, the duration is extended by 24 hours.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 560 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Rare Wind\n- 3x Common Arcane","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930585-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930585-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"pegasus","name":"Pegasus","type":"Mount","subType":"","cost":"5000 Clim","burden":"0","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"A pegasus trained to be used in combat.\n\nStats:\n\nHP: 45\n\nFocus: 4\n\nPower: 4\n\nAgility: 5\n\nToughness: 4\n\nSpeed: 60ft\n\nSize: Large\n\nSpecial qualities:\n\nFlying Mount: Your mount can fly. While flying you may only move in a straight line when making a movement action. While moving only on the ground, your speed is reduced to 20ft but this restriction does not apply.\n\nIn flight vulnerability: When your mount takes damage while flying, its height is lowered by 20ft. If this would reduce its height to the ground level, it becomes rooted and cannot fly again until the end of your next turn. If the attack that reduced your HP came from a flying creature other than yourself, you do not lose altitude.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c8-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c8-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"personal-camouflage-field","name":"Personal Camouflage Field","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"3000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per minute","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A circular device that barely fits in one hand. When activated, the user’s appearance shifts the match the surroundings. The user is able to hide without cover with a +10 bonus to stealth checks from any creature that was unaware of its presence before. In combat or against creatures looking for the wearer, the cloak will only give a +5 bonus to stealth checks.\n\nUpon making an attack, the effect of this artifice is disabled until the start of your next turn.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493053b-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493053b-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"photon-shield","name":"Photon Shield","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"3000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per encounter","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A bracelet that projects a shield of light onto the user's arm. Activates a projected shield of light onto your arm, which acts as a shield but does not use your hand to wield it allowing you to carry a weapon in it. Does not stack with other shields and while activated, it is treated as a shield for things with that as requirement.\n\nModifications:\n\n- A Modification, Photon Dome. Changes the Photon Shield effect to instead project a dome 5ft around you that grants the shield effect to allies against ranged attacks only. Does not stack with other equipped shields. Does not stack with other \"Photon\" modifications. May still choose to activate the original effect of Photon Shield.\n- A Modification, Photon Wall. Changes the Photon Shield effect to instead to create a stationary wall of light in front of you. This wall disappears when you move. The wall is a 1 way high cover with 15 HP and only allows ranged attacks to pass through it from your side. When you move, the wall is immediately destroyed. Once the wall is destroyed, the shell is expended and ejects from the artifice. Does not stack with other \"Photon\" modifications. May still choose to activate the original effect of Photon Shield.\n- B Modification, Wall Boost Circuit. Requires Photon Wall modification. Increases the health of Photon wall to 20 HP.\n- B Modification, Photon Greatshield. Increases the burden by 2 but changes the Photon Shield effect to that of a Greatshield and decreases your agility as such while activated. You can deactivate the photon greatshield for 0 RP, but doing so ejects the shell and ends the effect.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493056b-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493056b-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"pickaxe--one-handed-","name":"Pickaxe (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Artisan Weapon","cost":"750 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Pickaxes are used by Miners in their activities. With proficiency, they are treated as a One-Handed axe that can be used as a miner's tool.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Reinforced Langet (10 points): This weapon cannot be disarmed.\n- Bearded Extension (20 points): Wild Swing now ignores guard, but the damage is reduced to 2 (light attack) or 4 (heavy attack).\n- Rotational Stability (35 points): If a target moves away from you when you attack with this weapon and your next attack this turn is a throwing attack using this weapon against that target, that attack gains lock on.\n\n- B mods:- Boomerang Wing (25 points): After using a throwing attack with this weapon, you can return the weapon to your hand for 0 RP.\n- Lancebreaker (80 points): You gain a +2 Lancebreaker Power bonus against enemies wielding polearms or lances.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d9-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d9-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"pickaxe--two-handed-","name":"Pickaxe (Two-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Artisan Weapon","cost":"1250 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Pickaxes are used by Miners in their activities. With proficiency, they are treated as a Two-Handed axe that can be used as a miner's tool.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Reinforced Langet (10 points): This weapon cannot be disarmed.\n- Bearded Extension (20 points): Wild Swing now ignores guard, but the damage is reduced to 2 (light attack) or 4 (heavy attack).\n- Rotational Stability (35 points): If a target moves away from you when you attack with this weapon and your next attack this turn is a throwing attack using this weapon against that target, that attack gains lock on.\n\n- B mods:- Boomerang Wing (25 points): After using a throwing attack with this weapon, you can return the weapon to your hand for 0 RP.\n- Lancebreaker (80 points): You gain a +2 Lancebreaker Power bonus against enemies wielding polearms or lances.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d6-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d6-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"pistol--one-handed-","name":"Pistol (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Specialized Weapon","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"Two-Handed Grip: You may sheath or draw this weapon for 0 AP once per turn. When you use two hands to make attacks with this weapon, you get a +1 (Light or Heavy attack) or +2 (Precise attack) bonus to your accuracy roll.\n\nRange: 60ft\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Blast Diverter (10 points): Once per turn, attacks from this weapon cause the target to only be able to make heavy attacks of opportunity against you until the end of your turn.\n- Double Action (35 points): Accuracy is reduced by 3, but attacks with this weapon reduce the target’s ranged accuracy by 1 (stacking) until the start of your next turn regardless of if they hit or not. Doesn’t affect boss enemies.\n\n- B mods:- Match Barrel (50 points): The range of this weapon is increased by 60ft.\n- Beavertail Grip (50 points): When making a light attack at a target you can move 10ft in a straight line towards them.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305aa-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305aa-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"polaris-pair","name":"Polaris Pair","type":"Astra Relic","subType":"Weapon","cost":"-","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"A pair of blue shortswords that are always calling out to each other.\n\nWhile the wielder has one of the weapons in their hand, they may summon the other weapon at no cost, regardless of distance. Both swords are treated as Light Swords.\n\nIf the dual wield offhand attack made with this weapon is made against a target that was previously attacked by the main hand attack, the attack gains Lock-on.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b1-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b1-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"polearm--one-handed-","name":"Polearm (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Polearm: You gain +5ft range on your weapon attacks and your threatened range becomes 5-10ft.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Heavy Broadhead (10 points): Increases thrown power by 2 but boomerang/returning effects no longer work.\n- Shepherd's Lanza (20 points): Fall damage is reduced by 60ft while wielding.\n- Halberd (35 points): This weapon also gains the axe passive (Wild Swing).\n\n- B mods:- Winged Lugs (25 points): Increase guard by 1 and Block by 2 and reduce evasion by 1 while wielding.\n- Fullpike (25 points): Polearm weapon passive changes to +10ft and your threatened range becomes 5-15 ft. Having this item in your burden reduces your max RP by 1.\n- Yari Point Taper (50 points): After making a basic heavy attack, strike another target immediately behind the first with a light attack.\n- Swordbreaker (80 points): You gain a +2 Swordbreaker Power bonus against targets wielding light blades and heavy blades.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930590-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930590-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"polearm--two-handed-","name":"Polearm (Two-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Polearm: You gain +5ft range on your weapon attacks and your threatened range becomes 5-10ft.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Heavy Broadhead (10 points): Increases thrown power by 2 but boomerang/returning effects no longer work.\n- Shepherd's Lanza (20 points): Fall damage is reduced by 60ft while wielding.\n- Halberd (35 points): This weapon also gains the axe passive (Wild Swing).\n\n- B mods:- Winged Lugs (25 points): Increase guard by 1 and Block by 2 and reduce evasion by 1 while wielding.\n- Fullpike (25 points): Polearm weapon passive changes to +10ft and your threatened range becomes 5-15 ft. Having this item in your burden reduces your max RP by 1.\n- Yari Point Taper (50 points): After making a basic heavy attack, strike another target immediately behind the first with a light attack.\n- Swordbreaker (80 points): You gain a +2 Swordbreaker Power bonus against targets wielding light blades and heavy blades.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930597-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930597-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"portable-vacuum","name":"Portable Vacuum","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"2500 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per minute","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A large box with a powerful vacuum on top. When activated, it sucks in any mist or gas within 20ft of its location, removing its effects. This affects magical mists or gasses too, but cannot affect those created by Secret Art or Climax Art.\n\nModifications:\n\n- A Modification, Powerful Fan. Increases the range by 10ft.\n- A Modification, Engine Tuning. Increases the range by 10ft.\n- B Modification, Airflow Optimization. Increases the range by 10ft.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930542-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930542-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"portable-wall","name":"Portable Wall","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Flask","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"A handful of rock-like objects that when thrown generate a magical wall between each of the rocks. If there is a living creature between the rocks, the wall will not appear. The wall is 10ft high, 5ft long, lasts for 2 turns and has 100 HP. After a single use, this item becomes unusable. Can be thrown up to 40ft away.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 600 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Mystic Earth\n- 1x Mystic Arcane","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493053d-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493053d-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"power-gauntlets","name":"Power Gauntlets","type":"Artifice","subType":"Weapon","cost":"1500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per hour","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A large and heavy pair of gloves. Once the wearer inserts their hand into them, they will secure themselves properly around their hands. When activated, the wearer’s unarmed attacks do normal weapon damage instead of their normal unarmed damage. If the wearer already has a feature that lets them do this, the gauntlets instead give them +1 Power to unarmed attacks. While wearing these gauntlets, even if they are inactive, the wearer suffers a -10 penalty to all checks that require finesse movements with their hands.\n\nWearing these gauntlets also prevents the user from properly holding and using other items and weapons with them. Both hands are taken up by these gauntlets.\n\nMods:\n\n- A mods:- Fine Size (10 points): Removes the -10 penalty for finesse movements while wearing the gauntlets.\n- Vault Breaker (20 points): Your attacks deal double damage against objects.\n\n- B mods:- Finesse Grip (25 points): You may hold and use items or weapons like normal while wearing these gauntlets.\n- Heavy punches (50 points): Unarmed attacks made with this weapon deal 5d6 damage instead of 4d6.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930546-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930546-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"private-communications-device","name":"Private Communications Device","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"1500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per hour","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A small box that comes with two earplugs. It can connect to other devices within a mile by inputting a code unique to the box its connecting to. When a person speaks into the box, their voice can be heard through the earplugs as normal volume, regardless of how loud the person speaks. Only a person wearing at least 1 earplugs can hear sounds coming through it.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930544-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930544-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"projected-recorder-orb","name":"Projected Recorder Orb","type":"Artifice","subType":"Basic","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"Special","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A special crystal ball that records sounds and images. It can be used to playback what it has recorded with illusionary magic. The shell is built-in and the device records up to 1 minute in a 10ft radius around the orb. When used again it will project an illusion of the recording around itself. The illusion appears slightly distorted and is clearly an illusion. The orb can only record once, but may playback for up to a year.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930565-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930565-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"rabbit-elixir","name":"Rabbit Elixir","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Elixir","cost":"200 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"An elixir that increases metabolism when used, increasing speed. When drank, you take 11 true damage. Until the end of the encounter your speed increases by 10 ft.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 490 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Common Wind","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493055c-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493055c-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"reaper-elixir","name":"Reaper Elixir","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Elixir","cost":"200 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"An elixir that causes a surge of energy within the body. When drank, you take 11 true damage. You gain +1 Power. Lasts until the end of combat.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 350 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Common Fire\n- 1x Common Arcane","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493055e-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493055e-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"refractor-gun","name":"Refractor Gun","type":"Artifice","subType":"Weapon","cost":"Original Weapon + 1000","burden":"Original Weapon + 1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"1 shell per encounter","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"An artifice gun with cartridges that lets it fire blasts of arcane energy through a series of lenses rather than bullets. Attacks with this weapon deal Arcane damage. Exists in Musket, Pistol, Shotgun and Sniper Rifle variants.\n\nMods:\n\nUses normal pistol, shotgun, musket and sniper rifle mods.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493058b-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493058b-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"research-kit","name":"Research Kit","type":"Adventuring Essentials","subType":"Kit","cost":"100 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"-","craftingType":"","description":"Has enough bottles/vials/containers to store research samples for one expedition.\n\nThe kit is consumed at the end of the expedition if used.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305cb-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305cb-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"return-stone","name":"Return Stone","type":"Artifice","subType":"Basic","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"3 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A small crystal that is attuned to normal reality. Can be used as an emergency escape from dungeons. When activated, the person who activated it is immediately teleported out of the dungeon. May be used on downed allies instead of oneselves.\n\nModifications:\n\n- A Modification, Shortened Activator. Reduces the activation cost by 1 AP.\n- B Modification, Ranged Circuit. Increases the range by 20ft when used on a downed ally.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930541-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930541-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"saboteur-thread-daggers--one-handed-","name":"Saboteur Thread Daggers (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Specialized Weapon","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Wired Weapon: You may draw or sheath this weapon for 0 AP once per turn. You may throw this weapon up to 30ft as if it was a throwing weapon. You may recall the weapon after throwing it for 0 AP.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Compact Ergonomics (20 points): When your other hand is free and you take a movement action that costs RP, that movement range is increased by 5ft.\n- Parrying Dagger (20 points): If you don’t use this weapon to make an attack during your turn, you gain a +4 Shield bonus to your Block until the start of your next turn. You also gain a +4 bonus to your ‘damage’ roll when using the Parry ability.\n- Flat Pommel (35 points): When your other hand is free, you use your free hand to push the target into targets increasing melee heavy attack damage to 5d6.\n\n- B mods:- Poisoner Weapon (25 points): Applying poison to this weapon costs -1 AP (min 0).\n- Butterfly Knife (50 points): Your first light attack each turn with this weapon gains Trick Attack, but it can no longer make Heavy attacks.\n- Ring Pommel (50 points): If you make a heavy attack that the target defends against, you do not trigger attacks of opportunity from them until the start of your next turn.\n- Rappel (80 points): After you deal damage with a thrown attack with this weapon, you may move up to 30ft towards the target. Can only be done once per turn.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ae-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ae-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"scythe--two-handed-","name":"Scythe (Two-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Artisan Weapon","cost":"1250 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Sweeping Arc: Once per round, when you make a Heavy attack against a target, you may make a Light attack against a different enemy within your range.\n\nMods:\n\n- A mods:- Spinning Dance (20 points): You may move 5ft after making your Heavy attack, but before making your Sweeping Arc attack.\n- Long Haft (35 points): You gain +5ft range on your weapon attacks and your threatened range becomes 10ft.\n\n- B mods:- Rapid Spins (50 points): Your Sweeping Arc can now be used two times per round.\n- Focused Spin (50 points): Your Sweeping Arc now instead targets the same creature as the target of your Heavy attack.\n- Full Spin (80 points): Your sweeping arc can now target all creatures within 5ft of you.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d0-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d0-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"set-of-missiles--one-handed-","name":"Set of Missiles (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Stealthy Throwing: You draw one instance of this weapon at the start of making an attack (the rest remain on your equipment). Making an attack while stealthed with this weapon does not break your stealth.\n\nRange: 30ft\n\nMods:\n\n- A mods:- Featherflight (35 points): Range is increased to 60ft, but the remain stealthed mechanic only applies when attacking within 30ft.\n\n- B mods:- Poison Container (25 points): Poison can be pre-applied to the container and then sealed. Once the lid is opened and a missile is drawn, it is considered to be applied and begins to use up its application limit and duration.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493059c-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493059c-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"shark-elixir","name":"Shark Elixir","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Elixir","cost":"150 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"An elixir that makes temporary physical changes to allow you to breathe underwater. When drank you take 11 true damage. You can breathe underwater and swim easily underwater up to your speed for up to 1 day.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 350 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Common Water","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493055d-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493055d-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"shepherd-s-sling--one-handed-","name":"Shepherd's Sling (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"200 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Carpentry","description":"A sling that throws carved stones at high speed as a projectile.\n\nRange: 60ft\n\nGiant Killer: Cannot be dual wielded with another sling. You can overcharge your basic heavy attack for 1 AP to deal 9 extra damage.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Soon\n\n- B mods:- Anti-Goliath (50 points): You gain a +1 Size Power bonus on attacks against creatures that are Large or bigger.\n- Explosive Rock (80 points): When making the Overcharge attack, you may deal the extra damage to all creatures within 5ft of the original target. In addition, this extra damage becomes a Light damage roll for all creatures except the original target instead of the flat 9 damage.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b9-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b9-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"shield","name":"Shield","type":"Equipment","subType":"","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Armorsmithing","description":"Gives a +4 Shield bonus to your Block.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Spiked Shield (20 points): You may treat your shield as a One-Handed weapon. You can use it to make an attack and still gain the shield bonus.\n- Mirror Shield (35 points): When you are the target of a Mystic Eye ability, you may spend 1 RP to negate the effect and reflect it back to the user.\n\n- B mods:- Throwing Shield (50 points): You may throw this shield at an enemy within 30ft to make a ranged attack against it. Afterwards, the shield returns to your hand.\n- Shield Formation (80 points): While next to another ally with a shield or greatshield, you gain +1 Guard. (Only actual shields apply)","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a6-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a6-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"shield--great-","name":"Shield (Great)","type":"Equipment","subType":"","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Armorsmithing","description":"Gives a +1 Shield bonus to your guard, but a -1 penalty to your Initiative and a -2 penalty to your Evasion and Dodge. When taking the Block action, this Shield bonus is increased to 8.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Spiked Shield (20 points): You may treat your shield as a One-Handed weapon. You can use it to make an attack and still gain the shield bonus.\n- Mirror Shield (35 points): When you are the target of a Mystic Eye ability, you may spend 1 RP to negate the effect and reflect it back to the user.\n\n- B mods:- Tower Shield (50 points): The burden of this shield is increased by 1, but it now counts as Low cover for you against ranged attacks.\n- Shield Formation (80 points): While next to another ally with a shield or greatshield, you gain +1 Guard. (Only actual shields apply)","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a7-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a7-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"shielding-potion","name":"Shielding Potion","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Potion","cost":"200 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"A potion that briefly forms a protective barrier around you when drunk. You gain 15 temporary hit points that last until the start of your next turn.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 270 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 3x Common Earth","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493057c-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493057c-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"shock-stick","name":"Shock Stick","type":"Artifice","subType":"Weapon","cost":"1500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per encounter","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A long stick that can easily be used by anyone proficient in any melee weapon. Considered an improvised weapon until it is activated, after which it is considered a light weapon that does normal Lightning damage. Upon reducing an enemy to 0 or lower HP, the target becomes stunned instead of killed. This stun lasts until the end of the encounter and an extra minute after that.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493053c-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493053c-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"short-range-communications-device","name":"Short Range Communications Device","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per day","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"Two small boxes that are connected to each other. When a button is pressed and both are active, all audio from one of the boxes is transmitted to the other one. It has a maximum range of 1 mile.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930543-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930543-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"shotgun--one-handed-","name":"Shotgun (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Specialized Weapon","cost":"750 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"Point Blank: Can be fired while in melee range of an enemy without provoking an attack of opportunity.\n\nRange: 15ft\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Dragon's Breath (10 points): The first basic attack you make with this weapon in a turn inflicts burning 5 regardless of it hits or not. (If used with Open Choke mod, this can affect that attack).\n- Proof Load (20 points): When you make a heavy attack with this weapon, you may knock yourself back 5ft.\n- Point Blank (20 points): You may make AoO’s as if this was a melee weapon with a 5ft threaten range.\n\n- B mods:- Slugs (50 points): Your range is doubled.\n- Open Choke (80 points): The first basic light attack you make with this weapon in a turn makes a Light attack against all enemies in a 45 degree cone up to range.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.12.6/69ea4f7b6be32fced492fccb-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.12.6/69ea4f7b6be32fced492fccb-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"shotgun--two-handed-","name":"Shotgun (Two-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Specialized Weapon","cost":"1500 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"Point Blank: Can be fired while in melee range of an enemy without provoking an attack of opportunity.\n\nRange: 30ft\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Dragon's Breath (10 points): The first attack you make with this weapon in a turn inflicts burning 5 regardless of it hits or not.\n- Proof Load (20 points): When you make a heavy attack with this weapon, you may knock yourself back 5ft.\n- Point Blank (20 points): You may make AoO’s as if this was a melee weapon with a 5ft threaten range.\n\n- B mods:- Slugs (50 points): Your range is doubled.\n- Double Barrel (50 points): Two-handed only. The first single target heavy attack you make with this weapon per round also light attacks the same target afterwards. This counts as your dual wield attack.\n- Open Choke (80 points): The first light attack you make with this weapon in a turn makes a Light attack against all enemies in a 45 degree cone up to range.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.12.6/69ea4f7b6be32fced492fccb-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.12.6/69ea4f7b6be32fced492fccb-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"sickle","name":"Sickle","type":"Equipment","subType":"Artisan Weapon","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Sickle's are used by Farmers in their activities. With proficiency, they are treated as a One-Handed axe that can be used as a farmer's tool.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Reinforced Langet (10 points): This weapon cannot be disarmed.\n- Bearded Extension (20 points): Wild Swing now ignores guard, but the damage is reduced to 2 (light attack) or 4 (heavy attack).\n- Rotational Stability (35 points): If a target moves away from you when you attack with this weapon and your next attack this turn is a throwing attack using this weapon against that target, that attack gains lock on.\n\n- B mods:- Boomerang Wing (25 points): After using a throwing attack with this weapon, you can return the weapon to your hand for 0 RP.\n- Lancebreaker (80 points): You gain a +2 Lancebreaker Power bonus against enemies wielding polearms or lances.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d8-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305d8-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"silencer","name":"Silencer","type":"Artifice","subType":"Weapon","cost":"1500 Clim","burden":"0","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A tool for guns that reduces the sound they make. Can be applied to weapons of the Musket, Pistol, Shotgun and Sniper Rifle weapon groups. When applied, these weapons no longer make a very loud noise when fired.\n\nWhen a gun is fired without a silencer, the loud noise will alert all enemies within 120ft of the shooter.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.12.6/69ea4f7b6be32fced492fc5a-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.12.6/69ea4f7b6be32fced492fc5a-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"small-shell","name":"Small Shell","type":"Artifice","subType":"Fuel","cost":"50 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"A small cylinder of magical fuel that is used to power artifices. Most weapon-type artifices automatically eject the shell when they are emptied… along with a burst of steam to prevent overheating.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930563-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930563-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"small-weapons--one-handed-","name":"Small Weapons (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Hidden Weapon: You may draw this weapon for 0 AP. Each combat, after you draw the weapon if the next attack you make that round is using this weapon and is a basic Light or Heavy attack, it gains the Trick Attack keyword. After benefiting from this bonus, you cannot do so again the same combat even if drawing a different weapon with this ability.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Aerodynamic Design (10 points): Boomerang/Return effects cannot be used with this. For 1 RP you can throw the dagger, making a light ranged attack. On damage, the target is slowed until the end of its next turn.\n- Spring-loaded (20 points): You do not need to draw and wield this weapon to use it, it is worn in your equipment. However, you can only attack once per round with it. If your first attack with it in a fight is a basic attack, it activates Hidden Weapon as if you drew it right before attacking, though this still does not allow you to benefit from Hidden Weapon multiple times per combat. This weapon can no longer be used to make thrown weapon attacks and cannot be drawn normally. Designed by Nya.\n- Compact Ergonomics (20 points): When your other hand is free and you take a movement action that costs RP, that movement range is increased by 5ft.\n- Parrying Dagger (20 points): If you don’t use this weapon to make an attack during your turn, you gain a +4 Shield bonus to your Block until the start of your next turn. You also gain a +4 bonus to your ‘damage’ roll when using the Parry ability.\n- Flat Pommel (35 points): When your other hand is free, you use your free hand to push the blade into targets increasing melee heavy attack damage to 5d6.\n\n- B mods:- Poisoner Weapon (25 points): Applying poison to this weapon costs -1 AP (min 0).\n- Butterfly Knife (50 points): Your first light attack each turn with this weapon gains Trick Attack, but it can no longer make Heavy attacks.\n- Ring Pommel (50 points): If you make a heavy attack that the target defends against, you do not trigger attacks of opportunity from them until the start of your next turn.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930591-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930591-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"smith-s-hammer--one-handed-","name":"Smith's Hammer (One-handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Artisan Weapon","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Core crafting tool. Allows you to craft items as a Blacksmith or Armorsmith.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Flexible Handle (10 points): When dealing damage to a target, the minimum damage you deal is always 2. (this does not trigger on damage effects if damage would be 0 otherwise).\n- Chain Flail (35 points): Cannot be defended against by 0 RP actions. Attacks made with this weapon do not count as consuming 0 RP actions.\n\n- B mods:- Weighted Poll Upsetting (25 points): When making 3 separate attacks against a target, the third attack you make with \"Weighted Poll Upsetting\" knocks the target back 10ft on damage.\n- Flanged Head (50 points): When you crit with this weapon, the damage is still maximized even against blocking targets.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b0-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b0-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"smith-s-hammer--two-handed-","name":"Smith's Hammer (Two-handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Artisan Weapon","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Core crafting tool. Allows you to craft items as a Blacksmith or Armorsmith.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Flexible Handle (10 points): When dealing damage to a target, the minimum damage you deal is always 2. (this does not trigger on damage effects if damage would be 0 otherwise).\n- Chain Flail (35 points): Cannot be defended against by 0 RP actions. Attacks made with this weapon do not count as consuming 0 RP actions.\n\n- B mods:- Weighted Poll Upsetting (25 points): When making 3 separate attacks against a target, the third attack you make with \"Weighted Poll Upsetting\" knocks the target back 10ft on damage.\n- Flanged Head (50 points): When you crit with this weapon, the damage is still maximized even against blocking targets.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305df-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305df-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"smoke-flask","name":"Smoke Flask","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Flask","cost":"250 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"An Alchemical mix that creates a cloud of smoke temporarily. May be thrown up to 20ft away. Creates a smokecloud in a 15x15ft area that blocks line of sight. This effect functions similarly to ‘Glittershards’ and ends at the start of your next turn.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 200 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Rare Wind","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493055a-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493055a-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"sniper-rifle--two-handed-","name":"Sniper Rifle (Two-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Specialized Weapon","cost":"2000 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"Snipe: Looking through a sniper scope gives you a +10 bonus to Perception when looking at things further than 60ft away.\n\nRange: 720ft\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Semi-Automatic (20 points): The first time you miss with a basic Heavy attack in a round you can follow up with a light attack against the same target. This counts as your dual wield attack.\n- Hollow Point Boat Tail Rounds (35 points): You gain a +1 bonus to your accuracy when making a basic Heavy or precise attack.\n- Armor Piercing Rounds (35 points): The first attack you make each round with this weapon treats the enemy guard as if it were 4 lower.\n\n- B mods:- Bipod (50 points): All attacks with this weapon gain the Prone keyword. While prone, you are considered to have low cover against ranged attacks.\n- Snipe (80 points): If you did not move this turn or the previous turn you gain a +1d4 bonus to your accuracy roll on attacks made with a Sniper Rifle. If you already have the Sniper's Snipe ability, the effect is 4 instead of rolling when used with this weapon.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ac-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ac-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"snow-cloak","name":"Snow Cloak","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"3000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per arc","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A white cloak designed as the counterpart to the Fire Robe. Keeps the wearer warm in even the coldest of weathers.\n\nCan be activated to give the wearer 5 damage reduction against frost damage until the end of the encounter. When this effect ends, the shell inside the cloak is immediately used up and needs to be replaced for the weather repelling effect to function.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930582-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930582-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"soul-lamp","name":"Soul Lamp","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"1500 Clim","burden":"0","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"1 shell at attunement","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A lamp that can be attuned to the soul of a single person. While that person is alive, the lamp emits a light glow. Should the person die, the lamp’s light fades and the lamp then shatters into pieces.\n\nModifications:\n\n- A Modification, Vivre Flame. The person who is attuned to the lamp must be present upon its creation, and a bit of their blood or magic must be inserted into the lamp. The soul lamp’s flame’s strength now corresponds to the health of the target, being a bright flame when the target is at 100% HP and becoming a Dim flicker when they are downed.\n- B Modification, Damage Sensor. Requires Vivre Flame modification. When the target takes damage, the flame flickers a different color.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930550-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930550-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"souleater-elixir","name":"Souleater Elixir","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Elixir","cost":"600 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"An elixir that heightens spirit circuits in the eyes, making the user able to view invisible creatures. When drank you take 11 true damage. You gain the ability to see invisible (not hidden) creatures and gain a +10 bonus to Perception checks to detect creatures until the end of the encounter.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 1100 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Rare Fire\n- 1x Common Water","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930560-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930560-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"space-time-anchor","name":"Space Time Anchor","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"5000 Clim","burden":"3","activationCost":"2 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per minute","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A large box that when activated projects an area in a 40ft radius around it. Any creature inside cannot use any teleportation abilities. Any creature outside of the area trying to teleport inside is placed at the nearest edge of the area.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.12.6/69ea4f7b6be32fced492fc67-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.12.6/69ea4f7b6be32fced492fc67-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"speed-potion","name":"Speed Potion","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Potion","cost":"200 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"A potion that briefly increases your movement speed when drunk. Your movement speed is increased by 20ft until the end of your turn.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 270 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 3x Common Wind","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930560-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930560-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"spider-shoes","name":"Spider Shoes","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"2000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per minute","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A pair of shoes that can be adjusted to fit the wearer. Upon use, the wearer is able to walk across any angled surface as if it was normal solid ground","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.12.6/69ea4f7b6be32fced492fc5a-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.12.6/69ea4f7b6be32fced492fc5a-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"staff--one-handed-","name":"Staff (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Channeling Weapon","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Carpentry","description":"On damage with an attack made with this weapon, you may spend 1 Mana to push the target back 5ft.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Elemental Staff (35 points): You may alter the damage type from an attack made with this weapon for 0 AP. The damage type must be an element type you have mastered (usually unlocked through classes) or one that’s built into the weapon.\n- Powerful Push (35 points): The knockback distance is increased to 10ft.\n\n- B mods:- Efficiency (50 points): The first basic attack you make each turn may trigger the knockback effect without spending mana.\n- Unstoppable Force (80 points): The knockback effect is now on hit rather than on damage.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a9-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a9-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"staff--two-handed-","name":"Staff (Two-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Channeling Weapon","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Carpentry","description":"On damage with an attack made with this weapon, you may spend 1 Mana to push the target back 5ft.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Elemental Staff (35 points): You may alter the damage type from an attack made with this weapon for 0 AP. The damage type must be an element type you have mastered (usually unlocked through classes) or one that’s built into the weapon\n- Powerful Push (35 points): The knockback distance is increased to 10ft.\n\n- B mods:- Efficiency (50 points): The first basic attack you make each turn may trigger the knockback effect without spending mana.\n- Unstoppable Force (80 points): The knockback effect is now on hit rather than on damage.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a8-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a8-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"sticky-glue-flask","name":"Sticky Glue Flask","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Flask","cost":"350 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"An Alchemical mix that coats the target in Sticky Glue, restricting mobility. May be thrown up to 40ft away. When thrown, the target of the flask takes 1 damage. If they took damage, their evasion is reduced by 3 until they spend 2 AP to wipe the substance off.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 500 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Rare Earth","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.12.6/69ea4f7b6be32fced492fc79-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.12.6/69ea4f7b6be32fced492fc79-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"stone-serpent-s-kiss","name":"Stone Serpent's Kiss","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Poison","cost":"1000c","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"By Boshi\n\nContact poison(Venom). Can be applied to a cutting or thrusting weapon- or to an arrow, bolt, or bullet. Lasts for 1 hit or 1 minute (6 rounds).\n\nWhen an attack with this poison damages an enemy, they are inflicted with a form of Paralysis. A paralyzed Heroic or Boss target is Rooted and Unbalanced until recovering from this poison, which lasts for 1 minute (6 rounds). A paralyzed grunt is completely incapacitated (0AP, 0RP) until they recover from this poison, which lasts for 1 hour (360 rounds).\n\nA Heroic or Boss unit afflicted may spend 2 AP or make a Save at the end of their turn for free against Potency 13 to end the effect early on each of their turns.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 900 Alchemy Materials\nSpecial Materials:\n\n- 1 Rare Wind Herb\n- 1 Rare Arcane Herb\n- 1 Mystic Earth Herb","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305eb-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305eb-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"stun-gun","name":"Stun Gun","type":"Artifice","subType":"Weapon","cost":"2000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"1 shell per encounter","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A Light gun that can be used by anyone proficient in Muskets, Pistols, Shotguns or Sniper Rifles. It has a range of 60ft and does normal Lightning damage. Upon reducing an enemy to 0 or lower HP, the target becomes stunned instead of killed. This stun lasts until the end of the encounter and an extra minute after that.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493054e-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493054e-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"suppression-potion","name":"Suppression Potion","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Potion","cost":"600 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"A potion that temporarily suppresses the effects of a poison, disease or other natural affliction. The effect lasts for 24 hours. Magical poisons, diseases, curses etc are not affected by this.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 600 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Rare Water\n- 1x Rare Earth","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930549-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930549-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"surgery-kit","name":"Surgery Kit","type":"Adventuring Essentials","subType":"Kit","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"-","craftingType":"","description":"Surgery kits contain stitches, bandages and other items used for more serious wounds.\n\nRest Action: You perform minor surgery on an ally or yourself. Requires at least 5 points in Medicine (or a relevant expertise in Medicine) to use. Make a medicine check against DC 15. On success you can negate the effect of one injury suffered this campaign until the end of the campaign. An injury can only be negated once by this effect, and one person can only have one negated injury at a time. The injury must still be dealt with after the campaign ends.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c1-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c1-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"thrown--one-handed-","name":"Thrown (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Switch Hit: This weapon can be used as a melee weapon without penalty.\n\nRange: 30ft\n\nMods:\n\n- A mods:- Boomerang (35 points): After making a thrown attack with this weapon, the weapon returns to your hand.\n- Spinning Axe (35 Points): This weapon also gains the axe passive (Wild Swing). You keep this effect even when throwing the weapon.\n\n- B mods:- Throwing Hammer (50 points): Attacks with this weapon gain the Artillery keyword within 30ft.\n- Ricocheting (50 points): Once per round when this weapon deals damage with a Heavy attack, you may make a Light attack against a different target within 20ft.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493059a-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493059a-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"thrown--two-handed-","name":"Thrown (Two-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Switch Hit: This weapon can be used as a melee weapon without penalty.\n\nRange: 60ft\n\nMods:\n\n- A mods:- Boomerang (35 points): After making a thrown attack with this weapon, the weapon returns to your hand.\n- Spinning Axe (35 Points): This weapon also gains the axe passive (Wild Swing). You keep this effect even when throwing the weapon.\n\n- B mods:- Throwing Hammer (50 points): Attacks with this weapon gain the Artillery keyword within 30ft.\n- Ricocheting (50 points): Once per round when this weapon deals damage with a Heavy attack, you may make a Light attack against a different target within 20ft.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493059b-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493059b-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"timeworn-katana","name":"Timeworn Katana","type":"Astra Relic","subType":"Main","cost":"-","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"Current Wielder: Unknown\n\nA rusty katana with a dull blade.\n\nAny attack made with this weapon does not deal damage immediately, but any damage it deals is stored (after the hit resolves). When the wielder sheathes this weapon, it deals true damage based on the damage stored. The damage each target takes is based on the damage that was stored against them.\n\nHits and damage remain stored this way for up to the end of an encounter or for up to a minute, whichever is longer.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930572-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930572-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"torch","name":"Torch","type":"Adventuring Essentials","subType":"Basic","cost":"10 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"2 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"A simple piece of wood with a pre-oiled tied cloth on one end. Provides ample light and is quite easy to light on fire. Comes with an attached striker that can be lit on most rock and metal surfaces. When ‘activated’, creates a light that emits light within 30 feet. Can also be used as an improvised weapon that deals fire damage. Lasts up to two hours.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493056d-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493056d-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"transforming-weapon","name":"Transforming Weapon","type":"Artifice","subType":"Weapon","cost":"Cost of the individual weapons + 1000 Clim","burden":"Burden cost of the individual weapons + 1","activationCost":"0 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per switch","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A transforming weapon is two weapons in one. The wielder can press a button to consume a shell and transform the weapon into its other version. The two types of weapons that are accessible are predetermined and cannot be changed later, but there’s no restriction on the type of weapon that can initially be chosen. Up to 5 shells fit into a weapon.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930540-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930540-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"tunnel-elixir","name":"Tunnel Elixir","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Elixir","cost":"200 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"An elixir that causes intense focus on the task at hand. When drank you take 11 true damage. You gain +1 Focus. Lasts until the end of combat.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 380 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 2x Common Earth","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493055f-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493055f-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"twinblade--two-handed-","name":"Twinblade (Two-handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Weapon","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Blacksmithing","description":"Twin Strike: You can make dual wield attacks as if you were wielding two weapons.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Haladie Blade (20 points): Attacks with this weapon have -1 Power, but you can make 2 offhand attacks per turn instead of one.\n\n- B mods:- Shadow-Type Saber (80 points): When engaged in melee and you take a block or dodge action and then you are attacked by another melee attack by a different enemy, you may use block or dodge against that attack for 0 RP. Applies once per turn","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ea-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ea-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"universal-armor-mods","name":"Universal Armor Mods","type":"Crafting","subType":"Mods","cost":"","burden":"","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"Base Mods:\n\nThese are mods that can be put on any armor (not shield), regardless of type. The crafting cost to add these is listed after the name.\n\nA mods:\n\n- Ceremonial Armor (10 points): You gain +10 bonus to negotiation and intimidation checks, but automatically fail any stealth checks.\n- Cast Off Design (10 points): After using the Block action, you may spend 0 RP to cast off the armor immediately unequipping it. The armor becomes Broken until repaired.\n- Hidden Armor (10 points): This armor looks like normal clothing to other creatures (which may make you look more vulnerable than you are).\n- Ki Concealment (20 points): Requires Manaweave Frame mod. While wearing this armor you gain presence concealment. Spending any mana immediately removes presence concealment. After losing presence concealment, you can’t regain it until you rest for the day.\nB mods:\n\n- Mana Barrier (25 points): Requires Manaweave Frame mod. While putting on this armor, your mana and max mana is set to 0. For each mana you lose thanks to this effect, you gain 7 temporary HP. When you would regain mana or HP from resting, this temporary HP regenerates (up to a max of what you started with at the start of the arc)\n- Sensory Suit (50 points): This armor boosts the range of Mind Connection and Scry by 10x. Also reduces the mana cost of Psychometry by 1.\nFrame mods:\n\n- Barrier (20 points): This armor provides no passive guard bonus, but reduces the Initiative penalty by 2 and the Evasion/Dodge penalty by 4. When taking the Block action, you still receive the normal bonus the armor would provide.\n- Protective Coating (20 points): Reduces the Initiative penalty by 1 and the Evasion/Dodge penalty by 2, but only gives the passive guard increase. When taking the Block action, it does not gain an increased guard (though any other bonuses to your Block such as your Toughness still apply).\n- Manaweave (20 points): Reduces the Initiative penalty by 1 and the Evasion/Dodge penalty by 2. but reduces the wearer's current and maximum mana by 3 when equipped. Cannot be equipped if it would reduce the mana below 0.\nFlamellon Mods:\n\nFlamellon mods are special mods that can be put on armors. To put one of these mods on an item you must have sufficient items with the matching Flamelic Polarity.\n\nAdding a layering of the required element automatically fulfills gives polarity equal to the units in the ingot. For example, adding a Salachar ingot as layering also gives you 3000 Salachar polarity.\n\n- Arcanium- Quick Channel Layer (B mod, 40 points, 2000 Arcanium Polarity): Your maximum mana is increased by 1 while wearing this armor.\n\n- Salachar- Fire Armor (Frame mod, 20 points, 600 Salachar Polarity): Reduces the Initiative penalty by 1 and the Evasion/Dodge penalty by 2, but you take double damage from Water damage.\n- Refractory Plates (A mod, 20 points, 600 Salachar Polarity): You become immune to Burning and natural heat effects.\n- Sunfire Infusion (B mod, 80 points, 4000 Salachar Polarity): All creatures ending their turn next to you take Light Fire damage.\n\n- Sylphsteel- Turbulent Air Layer (Frame mod, 20 points, 600 Sylphsteel Polarity): Reduces the Initiative penalty by 1 and the Evasion/Dodge penalty by 2, but the bonuses of this armor only apply against ranged attacks.\n- Wind's Blessing (B mod, 25 points, 1250 Sylphsteel Polarity): After you Dodge, you gain +10ft of movement speed until the end of your next turn.\n- Cloud Pillow (B mod, 25 points 1250 Sylphsteel Polarity): When you would take falling or pushback damage, you treat the distance you would fall as 30ft lower.\n- Aerolevitation Effect (B mod, 80 points, 4000 Sylphsteel Polarity): You may Hover.\n\n- Fulgarite- Lightning Armor (Frame mod, 20 points, 600 Fulgarite Polarity): Reduces the Initiative penalty by 1 and the Evasion/Dodge penalty by 2, but you take double damage from Earth damage.\n- Static Armor (B mod, 25 points, 1250 Fulgarite Polarity): Anyone ending their turn next to you is afflicted with Static 12 that triggers at the end of their next turn.\n- Franklin Badge (B mod, 50 points, 2500 Fulgarite Polarity): Any attack dealing Lightning damage that targets an ally within 30ft of you and doesn’t include you as a target suffers a -5 penalty to Accuracy.\n- Lightning Reprisal (B mod, 80 points, 4000 Fulgarite Polarity): The first time each round you take damage from a Heavy attack in melee, you may make a Light attack against the attacker.\n\n- Corvuskite- Shadow Buoyancy (Frame mod, 20 points, 600 Corvuskite Polarity): Reduces the Initiative penalty by 1 and the Evasion/Dodge penalty by 2 during the night.\n- Light Absorbing Layer (A mod, 10 points, 300 Corvuskite Polarity): You gain +5 stealth during the night (doesn’t stack with cloak).\n\n- Vivinthal- Condensation Layer (Frame mod, 20 points, 600 Vivinthal Polarity): Reduces the Initiative penalty by 1 and the Evasion/Dodge penalty by 2, but you take double damage from Lightning damage and you are considered permanently soaked.\n- Bubble Flow Armor (B mod, 25 points, 1250 Vivinthal Polarity): You gain a swim speed of 20ft and can hold your breath for twice as long.\n- Galilean Latticing (B mod, 25 points, 1250 Vivinthal Polarity): You may walk on water as if it was normal ground.\n- Fog Plates (B mod, 80 points, 4000 Vivinthal Polarity): You gain a +4 bonus to your Dodge.\n\n- Glacite- Ice Armor (Frame Mod, 20 points, 600 Glacite Polarity): Reduces the Initiative penalty by 1 and the Evasion/Dodge penalty by 2, but you take double damage from Fire damage.\n- Permafrost Mantle (B mod, 50 points, 2500 Glacite Polarity): Enemies within 5ft of you are slowed. This slow is applied during a movement if they walk within 5ft of you. Lasts until they are no longer within 5ft of you, but it applies for the entire movement if leaving the range.\n\n- Ghimslag:- Seismographic Reflex Layer (B mod, 50 points, 2500 Ghimslag Polarity): You gain 20ft of Tremorsense.\n- Rock Plates (B mod, 80 points, 4000 Ghimslag Polarity): You gain a +8 bonus to your Block.\n\n- Luxaeterna:- Luxflow Coating (A mod 20 points, 600 Luxaeterna Polarity): You radiate a bright light that illuminates up to 60ft away.\n- Triboluminescent Plates (B mod 80 points, 4000 Lux Aeterna Polarity): Undead creatures that deal damage to you take Light Holy damage in return.\n\n- Aetherplumes (feathers/wings with high magic concentration. Tengu/Harpy/Fae etc):- Tengu Armor (A mod 35 points, 1000 Aetherplume Polarity): Your movement speed increases by 5ft while hovering or flying.\n- Aerodynamic Glider (A mod 35 points, 1000 Aetherplume Polarity): You may spend 1 RP to glide (as per the aeromancer ability)\n\n- Phoenix Materials (Phoenix Core):- Trauma Heat (B mod 80 points, 4000 Phoenix Polarity): Once per round, when you drop to 0 or lower HP while above 0 HP, you may immediately revive at 1 HP. You still gain an injury.\n\n- Gravity Materials (Gravity Orb):- Repulsive Sheeting (A mod 35 points, 1000 Gravity Polarity): When you push or pull a target, you may push or pull them for an additional 5ft.\n- Anti-Terror Field (B mod 50 points, 2500 Gravity Polarity): You gain a +4 bonus to your evasion against ranged attacks, but you cannot make any ranged attacks yourself (they automatically miss).\n\n- Plant (Ygdrassil Seed):- Dryad Bark (A mod 35 points, 1000 Plant Polarity): You can move through natural difficult terrain without losing movement.\n- Resinosis (B mod 50 points, 2500 Plant Polarity): When you take the Block action against an enemy attack, you heal for 3 HP.\n\n- Silver:- Ionic Field (B mod 25 points, 1250 Silver Polarity): Your astra corruption resistance is increased by 1.\n\n- Insectoid (Fae Cicada Shell):- Hive Mind (A mod 35, 1000 Insectoid Polarity): You gain a +1 to initiative for every allied creature (including yourself) wearing an armor with this mod (max +3).\n- Bee Armor (B mod 50 points, 2000 Insectoid Polarity): The first time each combat you take damage from an attack, the attacker becomes Dazed as bees attack it.\n- Living Armor (B mod 80, 4000 Insectoid Polarity): The first time each combat you take damage from a melee attack, you release a swarm of insects in a 5ft radius around you. The swarm remains in the same spot and any creature other than you ending its turn inside of it takes 6 full pierce damage.\n\n- Undead (Soulstone):- Reanimated Bone (B mod 25 points. 1250 Undead Polarity): When you are downed, attacks against you do not gain Full Pierce as your armor actively protects you.\n- Hands of Ptah (B mod 25 points, 1250 Undead Polarity): While you are downed, a necromantic hand activates on your armor, performing emergency medical aid, you regain 2 HP per turn.\n- False Bone Layer (B mod 80 points, 4000 Undead Polarity): Critical hits against you do not gain Full Pierce (but still do max damage)\n\n- Spidersilk:- Slippery (B mod 25 points, 1250 Spidersilk Polarity): You automatically escape from the first grapple effect against you each encounter.\n- Sticky (B mod 50 points, 2500 Spidersilk Polarity): You gain Spider Climb while wearing this armor (as per spiderfolk racial)\n\n- Poison Materials (Toxic Core)- Poison Inlay (B mod 25 points, 1250 Poison Polarity): You may apply a poison to this armor as a Rest action. When you are hit by a melee attack, the poison explodes outwards and automatically triggers on the attacker as if you had dealt damage to them.\n- Poison Resistance (B mod 50 points, 2500 Poison Polarity): You gain 5 DR against Poison damage.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b7-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b7-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"universal-crafting-mods","name":"Universal Crafting Mods","type":"Crafting","subType":"Mods","cost":"","burden":"","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"A mods:\n\n- Cross Peen Hammer (30 points): When crafting two of the same one-handed weapon with the same mods and materials, you may use double materials and only use one crafting attempt to make a pair of weapons.\n- Westrian Style Tool (10 points): You no longer roll dice and instead take 5 for every d10 crafting roll.\n- Sylvan Style Tool (20 points): While crafting points are 30 or less, you gain a +1 bonus to your crafting rolls.\n- Kiraran Style Tool (30 points): You may reroll any one dice when crafting.\nB mods:\n\n- Expertise (80 points): You gain a +1 bonus to crafting checks with a specific armor group, weapon group (or tools) or any other valid expertise.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b3-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b3-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"universal-translator","name":"Universal Translator","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"1500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per day","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A small black box. When a creature speaks into it while activated, everyone who hears the creature’s voice can automatically understand what they are saying, regardless of the language they are speaking in. It cannot translate for creatures that lack a proper language such as animals.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.12.6/69ea4f7b6be32fced492fc5a-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.12.6/69ea4f7b6be32fced492fc5a-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"universal-weapon-mods","name":"Universal Weapon Mods","type":"Crafting","subType":"Mods","cost":"","burden":"","activationCost":"","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"Base Mods:\n\nThese are mods that can be put on any weapon, regardless of type. The crafting cost to add these is listed after the name.\n\nWhile gathering is a universal mod, you still cannot gather unless the weapon is a tool that can be used for gathering.\n\nA mods:\n\n- Ninja Weapon (10 points): This weapon is treated as a weapon that can be used for Ninjutsu.\n- Quickdraw (10 points): You may draw this weapon for 0 AP.\n- Gathering (35 points): This weapon gives a +1 bonus to gathering rolls its used in.\n- Perfect Balance (20 points): When using the weapon in dual wielding, you can perform a dual wield attack with your other weapon, even when making a heavy or precise attack with this weapon.\n- Surprise Weapon (35 points): The weapon is designed to look like a mundane object. Each Combat, after you draw the weapon, if the next attack you make that round is using this weapon and is a basic light or heavy attack it gains the Trick Attack keyword. After benefitting from this bonus, you cannot do so again the same combat even if drawing a different weapon with with Surprise Weapon or Hidden Weapon.\n- Versatile (10 points): Can be added to a 1h weapon from a group that also has an option to be a 2h weapon (ie Axe, but not small weapons). Increases the burden of the weapon by 1, but the weapon can be used as either a one-handed or two-handed weapon. Must declare which version you are using at the start of your turn, before you making any attacks with this weapon.\nB mods:\n\n- Perfect Edge (25 points): An accuracy roll of 20 gains Sure Hit. If you roll a 20 and choose to have this apply, any Full Pierce is removed from the attack.\n- Momentum (25 points): After downing or killing an enemy, you may Sidestep up to your speed towards another enemy as part of that action.\n- Gathering II (80 points): This weapon gives a +1 bonus to gathering rolls its used in. Stacks with Gathering mod.\nAlloy Mods:\n\nAlloy mods can also be put on any weapon, but require the weapon to include a specific type of alloy. If the weapon does not include this alloy, the mod cannot be used.\n\n- Arcanium- Barrier Weaving (A mod, 20 points): When you apply a Shield to an ally or yourself, your shield is treated as if the stat it scales off is 1 higher. (If it doesn’t scale off a stat, there is no effect)\n\n- Salachar- Burning Weapon (B mod, 50 points): The first basic attack made with this weapon each turn inflicts Burning 18 to the target on damage until the start of your next turn.\n\n- Ghimslag:- Slowing Weapon (B mod, 50 points): The first basic attack made with this weapon each turn slows the target on damage until the start of your next turn.\n\n- Fulgorite:- Thundering Weapon (B mod, 25 points): The first basic attack made with this weapon each turn inflicts Static 18 to the target on damage.\n- Conductor (B mod, 50 points): When this weapon deals Lightning damage against a soaked target, it gains Half Pierce.\n\n- Luxaeterna:- Shining Weapon (A mod, 10 points): Your weapon emits a bright light in a 60ft radius. Can be enabled or disabled for 1 AP.\n- Healer Weapon (A mod, 20 points): When you heal an ally or yourself, you heal as if your power (or focus, agility or toughness if the heal scales off those) was 1 higher.\n- Undead Slayer (B mod, 50 points): When this weapon deals holy damage, it always deals Full Pierce damage against undead unless the undead resists Holy damage.\n- Shielding Healer (B mod, 50 points): When you cast a healing spell that costs mana, the target(s) of your spell gain Temporary HP equal to your Toughness until the start of your next turn.\n\n- Sylphsteel:- Pushing Weapon (B mod, 25 points): The first basic attack made with this weapon each turn pushes the target back 10ft on damage.\n\n- Corvuskite:- Stealth Weapon (B mod, 25 points): The first attack of an encounter does not break stealth if made with this weapon.\n- Darkness Weapon (B mod, 80 points): If the first basic attack on a turn made with this weapon deals damage, you may immediately hide from the target (but not other enemies) even if you’re not in cover.\n\n- Glacite- Slowing Weapon (B mod, 50 points): The first basic attack made with this weapon each turn slows the target on damage until the start of your next turn.\n\nFlamellon Mods:\n\nFlamellon mods are special mods that can be put on weapons. To put one of these mods on an item you must have sufficient items with the matching Flamelic Polarity.\n\n- Aetherplumes (feathers/wings with high magic concentration. Tengu/Harpy/Fae etc):- Aerial Supremacy (A mod, 30 points, 1500 Aetherplume polarity): You gain +1 accuracy against flying creatures.\n- Aerial Takedown (B mod, 50 points, 2500 Aetherplume polarity): If you damage a flying creature and it would lose altitude from taking damage, the altitude they lose is doubled.\n\n- Insectoid (Fae Cicada Shell):- Dazing Strike (B mod, 80 points, 6000 Insect Polarity): If your first basic attack of a round deals damage, the target becomes Dazed.\n- Distracting Strike (B mod, 80 points, 4000 Insect Polarity): If your first basic attack of a round deals damage, the target loses any concentration effect they have.\n\n- Plant Materials (Yggdrassil Seed):- Vine Grab (B mod, 80 points, 4000 Plant Polarity): If your first basic attack of a round deals damage to an enemy that's slowed, that target becomes rooted until the start of your next turn.\n\n- Poison Materials (Toxic Core):- Poison Weapon (A mod, 10 points, 2000 Poison Polarity): You deal Poison damage with this weapon.\n- Venom Drip (A mod, 30 points, 1500 Poison Polarity): You deal 1 Full Pierce Earth(Poison) damage on hit. (This extra damage does not trigger effects that normally trigger on damage).\n- Poisoned Sheath (B mod, 25 points, 1250 Poison Polarity): You may apply a poison to your sheath. When you draw the weapon, the poison is automatically applied to the weapon.\n\n- Gravity Materials (Gravity Orb): - Gravity Disruption (B mod, 80 points, 4000 Gravity Polarity): When you deal damage to a target with this weapon, the target suffers a -4 penalty to all ranged attacks until the start of your next turn. Can only be added to a melee weapon and does not apply when the target you were attacking with the weapon was more than 10ft away from you.\n\n- Spidersilk:- Sticky Weapon (B mod, 50 points, 2000 Spidersilk Polarity): Once per turn when you make a basic attack against an enemy you may choose to have your weapon stick to them on hit. While you are stuck to them, you move along with them if the target chooses to move unless they spend 2 AP to remove the weapon from you. While stuck to the target, the weapon cannot be used to make attacks. Can only be added to a melee weapon.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ec-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305ec-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"wand--one-handed-","name":"Wand (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Channeling Weapon","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Carpentry","description":"Magic Blast: You may alter the damage type fired by an attack made with this weapon for 0 AP. The damage type must be an element type you have mastered (usually unlocked through classes) or one that’s built into the weapon. Each weapon has at least one element built in.\n\nRange: 60ft\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Ornamental (10 points): You may use this weapon as one minor item such as an instrument or parasol.\n- Echo Blast (20 points): When you make a basic Heavy attack, you may split the damage against two different targets in range. Make only 1 accuracy check against both.\n- Warding Wand (35 points): You may spend 1 AP to gain 5 temporary HP until the start of your next turn.\n\n- B mods:- Dedicated Focus (50 points): Gain +1 bonus to accuracy rolls, but can only fire elemental attacks of 1 element. Spells cast through this wand only gain that bonus if they deal that element of damage.\n- Mana Core (80 points): When you deal max damage with an attack made with this weapon or with a spell cast through this weapon against an enemy in an encounter, your next spell this turn costs 1 less mana (min 0)","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a3-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a3-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"wand--two-handed-","name":"Wand (Two-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Channeling Weapon","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"2","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Carpentry","description":"Magic Blast: You may alter the damage type fired by an attack made with this weapon for 0 AP. The damage type must be an element type you have mastered (usually unlocked through classes) or one that’s built into the weapon. Each weapon has at least one element built in.\n\nRange: 120ft\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Ornamental (10 points): You may use this weapon as one minor item such as an instrument or parasol.\n- Echo Blast (20 points): When you make a basic Heavy attack, you may split the damage against two different targets in range. Make only 1 accuracy check against both.\n- Warding Wand (35 points): You may spend 1 AP to gain 5 temporary HP until the start of your next turn.\n\n- B mods:- Mana Surge (25 points): Once per turn after you cast a spell, you may make a Light attack for 0 AP. Two-Handed wand only. This counts as your dual wield attack.\n- Dedicated Focus (50 points): Gain +1 bonus to accuracy rolls, but can only fire elemental attacks of 1 element. Spells cast through this wand only gain that bonus if they deal that element of damage.\n- Mana Core (80 points): When you deal max damage with an attack made with this weapon or with a spell cast through this weapon against an enemy in an encounter, your next spell this turn costs 1 less mana (min 0)","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a4-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305a4-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"weak-spider-poison","name":"Weak Spider Poison","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Poison","cost":"150 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"Contact Poison. Can be applied to a weapon. Lasts for 2 hits or 1 minute (6 rounds).\n\nWhen an attack with this poison damages an enemy, they become Dazed. If an enemy is already dazed, they instead take 8 full pierce Poison damage. An enemy can only be affected by this poison (daze and damage effect both apply) twice per round.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 300 Alchemy Materials\nSpecial Materials:\n\n- 150 units of Spidersilk","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e9-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305e9-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"weak-wyvern-poison","name":"Weak Wyvern Poison","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Poison","cost":"150 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"Contact Poison. Can be applied to a weapon. Lasts for 1 hits or 1 minute (6 rounds).\n\nWhen an attack with this poison damages an enemy, they become poisoned. The next time they move the full distance they can in an action they take, they take 3d6 full pierce Poison damage.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 230 Alchemy Materials\nSpecial Materials:\n\n- 2 Common Earth Herbs","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305f2-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305f2-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"web-flask","name":"Web Flask","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Flask","cost":"500 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"A flask that when thrown coats a 20x20 feet area in sticky webs until the start of your next turn. Anyone walking through it becomes Slowed and any creature ending its turn inside of it becomes Rooted until the start of their next turn. May be thrown up to 40ft away.\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 400 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Rare Wind\n- 1x Rare Earth","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930548-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930548-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"whip--one-handed-","name":"Whip (One-Handed)","type":"Equipment","subType":"Specialized Weapon","cost":"750 clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Carpentry","description":"Whip Crack: You gain +5ft range on your weapon attacks. Weapon attacks made at max range (default of 10) gain +1 damage. Your threatened range is still 5ft.\n\nMods\n\n- A mods:- Barbed Wire (10 points): Upon landing a critical hit with this weapon, apply Bleeding to the target.\n- Fluttering Ribbon (35 points): At the start of your turn, you may change your threatened range to 5-10ft until the start of your next turn.\n\n- B mods:- Binding Flow (50 points): When dealing damage with a Heavy attack, you may choose to not do damage to instead reduce a creature’s movement speed to 0 until the start of your next turn or until you move. Does not work against bosses or creatures bigger than you.\n- Hooked Coil (80 points): When dealing damage with an attack of opportunity against an enemy leaving your range, you may pull them back 5ft. Only triggers once per turn.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b8-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305b8-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"wind-bubble","name":"Wind Bubble","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"1000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP or 1 RP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per use","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A simple device that can be attached to the body or held in the hand. When activated, it creates a bubble of wind around the wielder that slows down falling speed to 40ft per round. If the wearer reaches the ground while in this bubble, they take no fall damage.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930583-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced4930583-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"winged-backpack","name":"Winged Backpack","type":"Artifice","subType":"Assist","cost":"2000 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"1 shell per use","craftingType":"Artificing","description":"A backpack that looks ordinary at a first glance. It can store the same amount of items as a normal backpack. When activated, a pair of mechanical wings fold out. While the wings are out, you slow down your falling speed to 15ft per round and you are able to move horizontally as if normally moving. If you hit the ground while they are active, you do not take any falling damage. Lasts for 5 minues or until you hit the ground.\n\nModifications\n\n- B Modification, Hover Mode: When activated, the wearer can fly at half speed up to a maximum of 40ft high. If activated when higher than 40ft high, you glide down until you reach the 40ft heigth limit. Functions similarly to the Flight ability in regards to taking damage while flying.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493054f-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493054f-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"wolf","name":"Wolf","type":"Mount","subType":"","cost":"3000 Clim","burden":"0","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"A wolf trained to be used in combat.\n\nStats:\n\nHP: 20\n\nFocus: 4\n\nPower: 4\n\nAgility: 3\n\nToughness: 3\n\nSpeed: 25ft\n\nSize: Large\n\nSpecial qualities:\n\nTopple Prey: You may spend 2 AP to command your mount to make a Light attack against the target. On damage, the target is knocked prone. This attack uses your mount’s stats instead of your own and it gains a +2 to hit for every ally (apart from you) within 5ft of the target.","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c7-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c7-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"wolverine-elixir","name":"Wolverine Elixir","type":"Alchemy","subType":"Elixir","cost":"1250 Clim","burden":"1","activationCost":"1 AP","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"Alchemy","description":"An elixir that prevents non-lethal injuries. When drunk, you take 11 true damage. Until the end of the encounter, you do not suffer any injuries, except for a Mortal Wound (you can still lose HP and still become downed when reaching 0 HP).\n\nCrafting:\nMaterials: 2050 Alchemy Materials\nHerbs:\n\n- 1x Mystic Earth\n- 1x Rare Fire","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493057e-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced493057e-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"},{"id":"wyvern","name":"Wyvern","type":"Mount","subType":"","cost":"10000 Clim","burden":"0","activationCost":"-","fuelUsage":"","craftingType":"","description":"A wyvern trained to be ridden by people.\n\nStats:\n\nHP: 75\n\nFocus: 4\n\nPower: 6\n\nAgility: 3\n\nToughness: 6\n\nSpeed: 40ft\n\nSize: Large\n\nSpecial qualities:\n\nFlying Mount: Your mount can fly. While flying you may only move in a straight line when making a movement action. While moving only on the ground, your speed is reduced to 20ft but this restriction does not apply.\n\nIn flight vulnerability: When your mount takes damage while flying, its height is lowered by 20ft. If this would reduce its height to the ground level, it becomes rooted and cannot fly again until the end of your next turn.\n\nBreath Weapon: You may spend 1 AP to make your mount use a breath weapon (damage type dependent on the wyrm type), making a Light attack against all enemies in a 30ft cone. This attack uses your mount’s stats instead of your own","imageSmUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c9-sm.webp","imageLgUrl":"assets/item-images/0.13.0/6a06299f6be32fced49305c9-lg.webp","imageAlignment":"middle"}],"breakthroughs":[{"id":"8-eyes--spiderfolk-","name":"8 Eyes (Spiderfolk)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be a spiderfolk.","description":"You may have up to 8 Mystic Eyes instead of the regular 2."},{"id":"angelblooded--human---restricted-","name":"Angelblooded (Human) (Restricted)","cost":"0","requirements":"Must be a human and only a human. Requires GM Approval","description":"You have the blood of angels in you. You may purchase the Angelblooded class."},{"id":"arachne--spiderfolk-","name":"Arachne (Spiderfolk)","cost":"0","requirements":"Must be a spiderfolk. Can only be taken at character creation.","description":"You lose your extra arms racial ability. In exchange, you become Large size and your max burden is increased by 2. When attempting to move through 5ft wide spaces, it is considered difficult terrain for you and many humanoid buildings will struggle to accommodate you. You also suffer a -10 penalty to swimming checks, but you may climb through your spider climb ability at your normal speed instead of half speed.\n\nIn addition, you count as mounted for the purposes of abilities that require you to be mounted. This does not let you be a mount to other creatures."},{"id":"become-fire--salamander-","name":"Become Fire (Salamander)","cost":"200","requirements":"Must be a Salamander.","description":"The RP cost of Consume Fire is reduced to 0."},{"id":"become-ice--yuki-onna-","name":"Become Ice (Yuki-Onna)","cost":"200","requirements":"Must be a Yuki-Onna.","description":"The RP cost of Absorb Ice is reduced to 0 the first time you use it per round. Cost is reset back to 0 when it becomes your turn"},{"id":"become-lightning--raijin-","name":"Become Lightning (Raijin)","cost":"200","requirements":"Must be a Raijin Youkai.","description":"The RP cost of Consume Lightning is reduced to 0 the first time you use it per round. Cost is reset back to 0 when it becomes your turn. Any Power bonus you gain from using Consume Lightning does not stack."},{"id":"blend-in--slimefolk-","name":"Blend In (Slimefolk)","cost":"200","requirements":"Must be a Slimefolk.","description":"You disguise your appearance using magic to be that of another race (and gain a +30 bonus to hide this magical effect from things such as sense magic). This skill does not allow you to change your appearance at will, but instead lets you appear as you would as a different race. You choose this race when this breakthrough is picked up and cannot change it.\n\nIn addition, the first time you use Slime Body while disguised in this way, it costs 0 RP instead of 1 RP but reveals your actual race. This effect does not work if the attacker knows that you are a Slimefolk."},{"id":"blend-in-ii--slimefolk-","name":"Blend In II (Slimefolk)","cost":"25","requirements":"Must have Blend In.","description":"You may disguise as a different race in addition to your chosen race during Blend In. You may take this breakthrough multiple times, selecting a new race to disguise as each time."},{"id":"blessed-by-kari--human-","name":"Blessed by Kari (Human)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be a Human.","description":"After using Divine Providence you may use it a second time before resting, but the cost increases to 1 RP. This second use must pick a different option then your first one."},{"id":"bully","name":"Bully","cost":"50","requirements":"-","description":"You gain a +5 bonus to intimidation skill checks against targets with less Fitness than you."},{"id":"celestial-dragon--ryujin-","name":"Celestial Dragon (Ryujin)","cost":"300","requirements":"Must be a Ryujin. Can only be taken at character creation.","description":"Your elemental mastery from your Ryujin's Mastery may be Holy or Dark as well. In addition, you can use Flight."},{"id":"combat-doggy--cu-sith-","name":"Combat Doggy (Cu Sith)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be a Cu Sith.","description":"You may use abilities like normal while in Dog Form and may use One-Handed weapon. Any abilities that require a specific armor or other specific physical requirements still cannot be used.\n\nYour Dog Form no longer breaks upon taking damage."},{"id":"combat-kitty--cait-sith-","name":"Combat Kitty (Cait Sith)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be a Cait Sith.","description":"You may use abilities like normal while in cat form and may use One-Handed weapon. Any abilities that require a specific armor or other specific physical requirements still cannot be used.\n\nYour cat form no longer breaks on damage."},{"id":"curse-of-vampirism","name":"Curse of Vampirism","cost":"300","requirements":"Must be taken at character creation or after being killed by a vampire's bite.","description":"You rise as a vampire, an immortal creature that feeds on the blood of living creatures and immediately gain the Vampire racial style class and its key ability. Your race changes to ‘Vampire’, but you keep the benefits of your previous race.\n\nAs a vampire, you no longer age and your physical appearance changes slightly. Your skin becomes more pale and you grow a pair of fangs. You still need to eat, drink and breathe as normal.\n\nA vampire’s spirit core is cracked, making it difficult for it to regenerate mana naturally and requiring it to obtain it from other creatures. You no longer regenerate mana from eating (including potions), resting and can no longer use the Draw Mana encounter conclusion action. You still recover full mana at the start of a new arc.\n\nYou are weak to sunlight. Every round you spend in sunlight without proper protection you take 10 true damage and your maximum HP is lowered by 10. Your maximum HP remains lowered until you finish a rest. You may carry a parasol or similar object in one hand to protect yourself from the sun and can do so even in combat.\n\nIn addition to these drawbacks, you no longer receive Wounds unless the damage that reduced your HP to 0 was fire, holy or true damage. You also gain 60ft Darkvision. Darkvision lets you see in total darkness, even if there's no source of light."},{"id":"deep-connection","name":"Deep Connection","cost":"50","requirements":"Cavalier mastered.","description":"You may command your mount to move and attack even if you're not mounted on it. This still using AP, Mana etc like normal as if you were mounted."},{"id":"deus-ex-machina","name":"Deus Ex Machina","cost":"600","requirements":"-","description":"The first time you would die from a mortal wound at Encounter Conclusion, the mortal wound is removed and you instead receive a normal injury. The benefit of this breakthrough is then lost and you may not choose this breakthrough again after."},{"id":"divine-luck-i","name":"Divine Luck I","cost":"300","requirements":"-","description":"Once per rest, you may roll an additional dice when making a check and take the higher result."},{"id":"divine-luck-ii","name":"Divine Luck II","cost":"600","requirements":"Must have purchased Divine Luck I.","description":"Once per arc, you may choose to automatically succeed on a check (if success is possible)."},{"id":"drag-along--lamia-","name":"Drag along (Lamia)","cost":"200","requirements":"Must be a Lamia.","description":"When you have a target under the effect of \"Just a hug\", you can still move at half of your normal movement speed while under the Just a hug root effect and you still count as rooted for all other purposes.\n\nWhen moving, you can drag along the target of Just a hug, but they still count as rooted at your new location.\n\nIn addition, your grapple power increases by +1."},{"id":"dual-personality","name":"Dual Personality","cost":"300","requirements":"-","description":"Whether through magical or non-magical means, you have more than a single personality or entity within you through either physical or magical means. When under the influence of a Charm, Illusion or other mind-influencing effect you may spend 1 AP to switch personalities/entities and act as normal.\n\nYou may only do this once per encounter."},{"id":"early-ascension","name":"Early Ascension","cost":"300","requirements":"Must be taken at character creation.","description":"You are treated as having 1 class mastered for the purposes of selecting a tier 2 class that has \"Any class mastered\" or similar requirement. This does not apply to any class that requires a specific class to be mastered and it doesn't automatically qualify you for other requirements such as weapon proficiencies."},{"id":"elemental-affinity","name":"Elemental Affinity","cost":"150","requirements":"-","description":"You gain Elemental Mastery in an element of your choice.\n\nYou may pick this breakthrough more than once, choosing a different element each time."},{"id":"elemental-breath--ryujin-","name":"Elemental Breath (Ryujin)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be a Ryujin.","description":"You may let your Dragon Breath do the damage of any element that you have mastered."},{"id":"elixir-addict","name":"Elixir Addict","cost":"0","requirements":"Must have used at least 3 elixirs.","description":"You have become used to the effects of drinking elixirs, too used in fact. At the end of your turn in combat, if you do not have an Elixir active you take 6 true damage. The HP cost of drinking all elixirs is reduced by 11.\n\nThis breakthrough may be removed during an interlude phase by spending 1 IP."},{"id":"expert-summoner","name":"Expert Summoner","cost":"0","requirements":"At least 1 of Summoner, Animal Summoner or Necromancer maxed. 3000+ Spirit Core","description":"When you summon during the first or second round of an encounter, you may transfer main stat points from yourself into your summon.\n\nThe maximum stat points you can imbue for all your summons combined is equal to your total main stat points (Focus, Power, Agility, Toughness) - 18. You can not lower a stat below 3 with this. When you lose stat points due to this, your related values such as mana, HP and RP have their max reduced. When lowering your agility or toughness, you also lose RP or HP equal to the respective stat lost. If your Mana is higher than your max Mana after imbuing, it is reduced to the new max.\n\nThis transfer stays until end of encounter or until the summon you invested in dies (or is otherwise removed from combat). Your max of your stats is returned to normal, but any HP or Mana lost due to this is not refunded.\n\nYou may imbue a Heroic summon with any amount of stats from this pool. These points don't need to be a direct transfer (for example, you can lower your Agility by 2 to buff your summons Power). They increase your summons values such as HP/RP etc by the regular amount these stats give.\n\nFor grunt summons, you may imbue them with half of this max. They are still capped at max 1 RP."},{"id":"fae-flash-acrobat--fae-","name":"Fae Flash Acrobat (Fae)","cost":"50","requirements":"Must be a Fae.","description":"While using Fae Flash, you may teleport a partial distance and materialize there to redirect your teleport. In a single Fae Step, you may teleport multiple times, reappearing each time you stop, to teleport from that new position. You are still limited by your maximum teleport distance and cannot take any other actions between each teleport."},{"id":"faerie-flash-master--fae-","name":"Faerie Flash Master (Fae)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be a Fae.","description":"When using your Faerie Flash ability, you may spend X additional mana to increase your teleport distance by X times your movement speed."},{"id":"faerie-chimera-hybrid--race-","name":"Faerie-Chimera Hybrid (Race)","cost":"200","requirements":"Must be chosen at character creation. Must choose Faerie or Chimera race.","description":"An extremely rare condition in which a Chimera parent and a Faerie parent produces a child with Chimera traits. The odds are said to be less than 1%.\n\nIf your main race is Chimera, you may choose a Fae subrace instead of a Chimera one. If your main race is Fae, you may choose a Chimera subrace instead of a Fae one.\n\nYou do not get any of the base traits from the other race and keep the ones from your chosen main race. However, you do get the language from the other race (or a dialect of choosing a chimera subrace)\n\nIf you pick High Fae as your subrace, you gain Fae Flash instead of Fae Flash II."},{"id":"fast-metabolism","name":"Fast Metabolism","cost":"150","requirements":"-","description":"Once per arc you may eat food and gain the benefits even if you already had gotten the benefits from eating food that day."},{"id":"fast-movement--centaur-","name":"Fast Movement (Centaur)","cost":"200","requirements":"Must be Centaur or Arachne Spiderfolk","description":"Your base movement speed increases by 5ft."},{"id":"fearless","name":"Fearless","cost":"200","requirements":"-","description":"Whenever you are afflicted by a Fear type condition, you may spend 1 RP or 0 AP to remove it."},{"id":"fight-and-flight--chimera-","name":"Fight and Flight (Chimera)","cost":"200","requirements":"Must be a Chimera.","description":"When using Fight or Flight, you no longer receive the drawback."},{"id":"flesheater--jiangshi-","name":"Flesheater (Jiangshi)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be a Jiangshi.","description":"When using Consume Enemy, you may consider that your food for the day and regain mana equal to a normal ration. You cannot gain this benefit if you already regained mana from food that day and using this benefit prevents you from regaining mana from food until you’ve rested."},{"id":"flying-counter--kitsune-","name":"Flying Counter (Kitsune)","cost":"200","requirements":"Must be a Kitsune.","description":"When using Fading Counter, you may move up to your movement speed instead of 5ft. This movement has Flight and still does not provoke attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"four-paw-sprint--catfolk-","name":"Four Paw Sprint (Catfolk)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be a Catfolk.","description":"When spending at least 3 AP of movement, your base movement speed is increased to 40ft instead of 25."},{"id":"greatshield-training","name":"Greatshield Training","cost":"100","requirements":"You must be proficient with shields.","description":"You gain proficiency with Greatshields."},{"id":"heavy-armor-training","name":"Heavy Armor Training","cost":"100","requirements":"You must be proficient with Light and Medium armor.","description":"You gain proficiency with Heavy Armor."},{"id":"hide-behind-ally--pixie-","name":"Hide Behind Ally (Pixie)","cost":"300","requirements":"Must be a Pixie.","description":"When occupying the same space as a conscious ally that's at least a size bigger than you, you may choose to become untargetable to single target attacks. The ally must be willing to take the hits for you, though they may react to these attacks as normal. While occupying the same space as a conscious ally, any effect that triggers upon not being targeted by an enemy (such as Challenge) will not be triggered. Does not work against Attacks of Opportunity."},{"id":"human-chimera-hybrid--race-","name":"Human-Chimera Hybrid (Race)","cost":"200","requirements":"Must be chosen at character creation. Must choose Human race.","description":"While most unions of Human and Chimera parents result in the offspring being fully of Human or fully of Chimera, there are rare instances in which the Chimera traits are still present in a human offspring.\n\nChoose one Chimera Subrace and gain all of its features. You do not gain any of the Chimera base traits and instead have the Human ones, including Divine Providence. You do not get the 100 extra exp that humans normally get or human adaptability."},{"id":"improved-demonic-divine-release--demon-","name":"Improved Demonic Divine Release (Demon)","cost":"300","requirements":"Must be a Demon","description":"When activating your divine release you may choose to reduce your max HP by 22. When you do, you do not pay any additional HP cost to activate it and the HP Upkeep is reduced to 0 while above 0 HP.\n\nWhen you fall below 0 HP, you pay the increased Upkeep cost as normal."},{"id":"in-sync--youkai-","name":"In Sync (Youkai)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be a Youkai.","description":"After you use Spiritual Sync, you may cancel the effect for 0 RP at any time. If you do, you regain mana like it is described in the ability or 8 HP for each temporary mana you still had remaining.\n\nIn addition, the maximum mana or HP you can spend on Spiritual Sync is doubled."},{"id":"kit-expert","name":"Kit Expert","cost":"200","requirements":"-","description":"You may reduce the Burden cost of a single kit in your inventory by 2."},{"id":"language-training","name":"Language Training","cost":"100","requirements":"-","description":"You learn a language of your choice. Rare, dead or similar languages may be unavailable (GM’s discretion).\n\nYou may take this breakthrough multiple times, picking a different language each time."},{"id":"large-specimen--nio--bullfolk-or-bearfolk-","name":"Large Specimen (Nio, Bullfolk or Bearfolk)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be a Nio, Bullfolk or Bearfolk.","description":"Your size becomes Large."},{"id":"light-armor-training","name":"Light Armor Training","cost":"25","requirements":"-","description":"You gain proficiency with Light Armor and shields."},{"id":"light-sleeper","name":"Light Sleeper","cost":"75","requirements":"-","description":"When asleep, you may roll Perception rolls as if you were awake to be aware of danger approaching."},{"id":"mark-of-conflict","name":"Mark of Conflict","cost":"0","requirements":"Must be an Unknown Paladin that follows Eisen. Must have the Mark of Justice ability.","description":"The effect of your Mark of Justice changes to the following:\n\n\"You mark a single enemy, inflicting the Mark of Conflict on them. If an enemy moves away from you and not towards another ally, they take Full Pierce physical damage equal to your Power for each 20ft of movement they spent moving away from you.\"\n\nThe range and AP cost remain the same."},{"id":"medium-armor-training","name":"Medium Armor Training","cost":"50","requirements":"You must be proficient with Light Armor","description":"You gain proficiency with Medium Armor."},{"id":"mental-torture--unseelie-","name":"Mental Torture (Unseelie)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be an Unseelie.","description":"When you roll a natural 20 on your accuracy roll, you may apply the effects of Torture Techniques even if the enemy Dodges or Blocks it."},{"id":"mixed-house--demon-","name":"Mixed House (Demon)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be a Demon.","description":"You choose another house to gain the benefit of."},{"id":"mystic-eyes-of-faerie-light--fae-","name":"Mystic Eyes of Faerie Light (Fae)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be a Fae.","description":"Your Fae eyes have developed into the Eyes of Faerie Light. You may purchase the Faerie Light Eyes class.\n\nIn addition, you can make a Perception check at +10 bonus to determine if something is an illusion. You are not immune to these illusions however."},{"id":"natural-immunity--ratfolk-","name":"Natural Immunity (Ratfolk)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be Ratfolk","description":"When you successfully resist the effect of a disease or poison (or are immune to the effect), you may choose to become afflicted anyway. You suffer no effects from a disease or poison you choose to accept this way. This poison or disease lasts the normal duration or until the end of the encounter, whichever is shorter."},{"id":"on-the-draw","name":"On the draw","cost":"100","requirements":"-","description":"You gain +1 to your initiative."},{"id":"organized-inventory","name":"Organized Inventory","cost":"100","requirements":"-","description":"Increases your in-combat burden capacity by 1."},{"id":"organized-inventory-ii","name":"Organized Inventory II","cost":"200","requirements":"Must have the Organized Inventory breakthrough","description":"Your in-combat Burden capacity is increased by 1."},{"id":"organized-inventory-iii","name":"Organized Inventory III","cost":"300","requirements":"Must have the Organized Inventory II breakthrough","description":"Your in-combat Burden capacity is increased by 1."},{"id":"overrun--centaur-","name":"Overrun (Centaur)","cost":"200","requirements":"Must be a Centaur.","description":"When using the Charge or Spear Charge ability your movement speed is increased by 5ft and if your attack made through the Charge ability does damage, it knocks the target prone."},{"id":"panda-martial-arts--red-panda-","name":"Panda Martial Arts (Red Panda)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be Red Panda","description":"You can be in Panda stance at the same time as another stance without either stance ending.\n\nOther rules for stance breaking (such as entering 2 non-panda stances) still apply."},{"id":"photosynthesis--dryad-","name":"Photosynthesis (Dryad)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be Dryad.","description":"By spending at least an hour in the direct sunlight, you may gain the benefits of having eaten food and you do not need to eat or drink for the next 24 hours."},{"id":"power-saving-mode--ancient-marionette-","name":"Power Saving Mode (Ancient Marionette)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be an Ancient Marionette","description":"If you are at maximum mana during your meal, you only need to consume half the normal amount to be well fed."},{"id":"powerful-ki--oni-","name":"Powerful Ki (Oni)","cost":"200","requirements":"Must be an Oni.","description":"When using Gravitational Ki, the range increases by 30ft. The push and pull distance increases by up to 10ft. In addition, you may spend 1 AP instead of 1 RP on it."},{"id":"primary-stat-training","name":"Primary Stat Training","cost":"400","requirements":"-","description":"You gain a +1 bonus to Focus, Power, Agility or Toughness.\n\nThis breakthrough can be selected multiple times. The effects stack. Each time you take this breakthrough the cost increases by 100, up to a maximum of 700."},{"id":"racial-flight","name":"Racial Flight","cost":"300","requirements":"Must be Phoenix, Mothfolk, Lizardfolk or Willowisp race.","description":"You may use Flight."},{"id":"rapid-flash--high-fae-","name":"Rapid Flash (High Fae)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be a High Fae.","description":"Your Fae Flash gains the Rapid keyword."},{"id":"rich-parents","name":"Rich Parents","cost":"300","requirements":"Must be taken at character creation.","description":"You start the game with an additional 3000 Clim of funds."},{"id":"secondary-stat-training","name":"Secondary Stat Training","cost":"200","requirements":"-","description":"You gain a +1 bonus to Fitness, Cunning, Reason, Awareness or Presence.\n\nThis breakthrough can be selected multiple times. The effects stack."},{"id":"skill-training","name":"Skill Training","cost":"25","requirements":"-","description":"You gain a single skill point or two expertise points to spend on a skill. Crafting skills cannot be selected with this training.\n\nYou may select this breakthrough multiple times. Its effects can stack."},{"id":"skilled-flier","name":"Skilled Flier","cost":"100","requirements":"Must have Flight racial ability or Racial Flight breakthrough","description":"When you are about to lose Height from taking damage due to your Flight ability, you may instead spend 3 Mana to negate losing height from the flight mechanic until the start of your next turn.\n\nAbilities that make you lose height not part of the Flight ability (such as downburst) may still knock you out of the air."},{"id":"slime-summoner","name":"Slime Summoner","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be a mastered Animal Summoner.","description":"When using the Summon Animal ability, you may instead choose to summon slimes. You roll randomly from the following slimes: Slime, Fire Slime, Earth Slime, Water Slime, Wind Slime or Mana Slime.\n\nEven if you have the Wildheart class, you still cannot choose which slime you summon except you may choose to summon the regular Slime."},{"id":"slow-starter","name":"Slow Starter","cost":"300","requirements":"Must be taken at character creation.","description":"You receive 200 less EXP at character creation to spend on classes and abilities. Every time you get EXP after character creation, you get twice as much. This lasts until you’ve received a total of 500 (1000 when doubled) exp."},{"id":"small-doggy--cu-sith-","name":"Small Doggy (Cu Sith)","cost":"0","requirements":"Must be a Cu Sith.","description":"When you enter your Dog Form, you become a small dog instead. Instead of the usual bonuses and penalties, you instead lose 4 guard and 8 Block but gain a +2 Size bonus to Evasion and Dodge."},{"id":"small-specimen--cowfolk-","name":"Small Specimen (Cowfolk)","cost":"25","requirements":"Cowfolk only. Must be taken at character creation.","description":"Your size is Small instead of Medium."},{"id":"speciality-weapon-training","name":"Speciality Weapon Training","cost":"100","requirements":"-","description":"You gain proficiency with a Speciality Weapon group.\n\nThis breakthrough can be selected multiple times. You must select a different weapon group each time you select it."},{"id":"summon-contract--fortuna--lady-luck","name":"Summon Contract: Fortuna, Lady Luck","cost":"0","requirements":"Must be a summoner and have visited the eidolon.","description":"Appearance: Fortuna appears as a beautiful lady wearing clothing of the highest quality. Her clothes change each time she appears, but she always carries with her a parasol designed like a roulette wheel.\nDesires: Fortuna desires to see gambling. To have people bet their all on impossible odds.\nPact Cost: You can never naturally roll 20 again. Every 20 you roll is reduced to 19.\nAttunement Cost: None\nRe-Summon Cost: Roll a natural 20 (before the pact cost reduces it) on an attack or skill check with consequences for failure (GM’s decision).\n\nWhen you contract Fortuna, you are able to attune to it. While attuned, you gain access to the Draw Luck ability through your Channel Eidolon ability. You summon the Jack of Hearts for your Lesser Eidolon and Fortuna for your Eidolon (The stats for these are listed under monsters)."},{"id":"summon-contract--ixilune--the-swarm","name":"Summon Contract: Ixilune, The Swarm","cost":"0","requirements":"Must be a summoner and have visited the eidolon.","description":"Appearance: Hot bug lady.\nDesires: Ixilune desires to consume everything.\nPact Cost: You need to eat 1.5x as much food to be fed.\nAttunement Cost: None\nRe-Summon Cost: Must eat the flesh of a creature of the same (main) race.\n\nWhen you contract Ixilune, you are able to attune to it. While attuned, you gain access the Distracting Swarm ability through your Channel Eidolon ability. You summon the Devouring Swarm for your Lesser Eidolon and Ixilune for your Eidolon. (The stats for these are listed under monsters.)"},{"id":"summon-contract--pipoltr--the-gardener","name":"Summon Contract: Pipoltr, The Gardener","cost":"0","requirements":"Must be a summoner and have visited the eidolon.","description":"- Appearance: Pipoltr appears as a giant scarab beetle whose carapace glints with a metallic sheen like burnished bronze and emerald green. His presence is both otherworldly and ancient, curved antennae sprout from his head that can detect the health of plants. His compound eyes shine like brilliant gems.\n- Desires: Pipoltr’s desire is the health of nature.\n- Pact Cost: 1 Maximum Mana.\n- Attunement Cost: None\n- Re-Summon Eidolon: Character must perform 1 day of gardening work before resummoning Pipoltr.\nWhen you contract Pipoltr, you are able to attune to it. While attuned, you gain access the Vine Wall Cover ability through your Channel Eidolon ability. You summon the Rhinoceros Beetle for your Lesser Eidolon and Pipoltr for your Eidolon. (The stats for these are listed under monsters.)"},{"id":"superior-escapist--rabbitfolk-","name":"Superior Escapist (Rabbitfolk)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be a Rabbitfolk.","description":"You may use your Escape Artist when Rooted to remove it in addition to grapples."},{"id":"tengu-defensive-aura--tengu-","name":"Tengu Defensive Aura (Tengu)","cost":"100","requirements":"Must be a Tengu.","description":"Your resistance to astra corruption is increased by 1 (Your SC is treated as 500 higher when determining if you suffer from astra corruption). In addition, you do not suffer any negative effects when the astra level is raised artificially. (such as from Exousiai's)."},{"id":"the-unknown-paladin","name":"The Unknown Paladin","cost":"200","requirements":"-","description":"Despite not being human, you fulfill the human requirement to become a Paladin. In addition, your Smite skill's damage type changes to one that represents your chosen Divine. The paladin holy weapon key ability also changes its damage type to the one that represents your chosen Divine (all physical in the case of Eisen)."},{"id":"third-eye","name":"Third Eye","cost":"200","requirements":"-","description":"You may have up to 3 Mystic Eyes instead of the regular 2."},{"id":"touched-by-death","name":"Touched by Death","cost":"200","requirements":"Must be taken at character creation or after your HP has dropped below 0 in an encounter.","description":"Near-death experiences sometimes leave people more sensitive to death itself, manifesting in what is called the Shinigami’s Eyes. You may purchase the Shinigami Eyes class.\n\nIn addition, you may spend 1 AP to see the HP percentage and weak spots (if any) of all creatures for 1 turn."},{"id":"universal-training","name":"Universal Training","cost":"700","requirements":"-","description":"You gain +1 to any primary stat, +1 to any secondary stat and 5 skill points. You may put these skill points into any normal skill, except crafting and gathering skills.\n\nThis breakthrough may be taken multiple times. The effects stack."},{"id":"weapon-training","name":"Weapon Training","cost":"25","requirements":"-","description":"You gain proficiency with a weapon group. You may not select Speciality Weapons with this.\n\nThis breakthrough can be selected multiple times. You must select a different weapon group each time you select it."},{"id":"wide-circuits-i","name":"Wide Circuits I","cost":"150","requirements":"-","description":"Your maximum mana increases by 1."},{"id":"wide-circuits-ii","name":"Wide Circuits II","cost":"175","requirements":"Must have the Wide Circuits breakthrough.","description":"Your maximum Mana is increased by 1."},{"id":"wide-circuits-iii","name":"Wide Circuits III","cost":"200","requirements":"Must have the Wide Circuits II breakthrough.","description":"Your maximum Mana is increased by 1."},{"id":"wide-circuits-iv","name":"Wide Circuits IV","cost":"250","requirements":"Must have the Wide Circuits III breakthrough","description":"Your maximum Mana is increased by 1.\n\nYou may take this breakthrough multiple times. The effects stack."}],"abilities":[{"id":"abjurer-s-blast","name":"Abjurer's Blast","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"10ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Rapid","Spell"],"description":"You make a Light (1 AP), Heavy (2 AP) or Precise (2 AP) attack against the target that deals Arcane damage. This spell does not provoke attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"absorb-ice","name":"Absorb Ice","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You're about to take Frost Damage.","keywords":["Rapid"],"description":"You gain Absorb Ice, which gives you Damage Reduction 100 Frost against the triggering damage. After the damage resolves, if the caster is not you, someone allied to you or from an effect made by you or an ally, you gain Temporary HP until the end of the encounter equal to the amount of damage this ability reduces."},{"id":"accelerando","name":"Accelerando","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Encounter Start"],"description":"Grant yourself or an ally +4 initiative."},{"id":"accelerating-strike","name":"Accelerating Strike","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You make a Heavy Attack against the target. Afterwards, you gain Accelerating Strike, which increases your Initiative by up to 2."},{"id":"adaptive-defense","name":"Adaptive Defense","costLabel":"1 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Rapid"],"description":"You take the Block Action. You then gain 4 Adaptive Defense (Type) which grants you Damage Reduction 4 against that damage type until the end of your next turn. You can only have one instance of Adaptive Defense at a time."},{"id":"advanced-artificing","name":"Advanced Artificing","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Skeleton Welding\nCost: 40 crafting points\nDescription:\nYou expertly create the artifice hookup, reducing the artifice weight burden by a further 1 to a total minimum of 0.5.\n\nArtifice Modification B\nCost: 40 crafting points\nDescription:\nYou add a B-Type modification to an artifice. See the individual artifice to see if modifications are available.\n\nArtifice Modification A2\nCost: 40 crafting points\nDescription:\nYou add a second A-Type modification to an artifice. See the individual artifice to see if modifications are available.\n\nWeapon Modification B\nCost: X Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou add an B-Type modification to the weapon. See the Universal Weapon or Crafting mods page as well as the individual weapon page for details. Each modification has its own cost."},{"id":"aerial-crashdown","name":"Aerial Crashdown","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"You are mounted on a flying mount and the target is at least 20ft below you.","keywords":["-"],"description":"You and your mount crash down on the target. You move towards the target and your mount makes a Heavy attack against it. On damage, the target is knocked prone."},{"id":"aerial-loop","name":"Aerial Loop","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self or Mount","requirement":"You are mounted on a flying mount and you or your mount are the target of a ranged attack","keywords":["-"],"description":"You and your mount take the Dodge action and gain a +5 bonus to evasion against the attack."},{"id":"aftershock","name":"Aftershock","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"You missed an attack with a Two-Handed Melee Weapon.","keywords":["Rage"],"description":"You attack with such force that you create aftershocks when you miss your attack, dealing True Damage to all enemies within 5ft of the missed target. This True Damage equals twice the AP spent on the attack. If your attack targets multiple enemies, this only applies if you miss all enemies."},{"id":"aimed-shot","name":"Aimed Shot","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Lock On"],"description":"You make a Heavy Attack against the target."},{"id":"alarm-ward","name":"Alarm Ward","costLabel":"1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Touch","requirement":"-","keywords":["Bounded Field","Spell"],"description":"A ward that can be placed on a normal-sized room or can be combined to ward off a house or larger area. Each ward can cover a 40ft radius. For each Alarm Ward placed in the same area as another Alarm Ward, this radius increases by 40ft (For example, 120ft with 3 Alarm Wards). If someone other than you passes through the ward, the ward triggers creating a loud ringing noise that persists until the ward is disabled. Casting this takes 10 minutes of uninterrupted casting. Once triggered, the field remains active for 5 more minutes before vanishing. At the time of casting, you may choose people that can pass through the barrier without triggering it. If not triggered, Alarm Ward lasts until you remove it. For each Alarm Ward you maintain, your maximum mana is reduced by 1. This is considered a tier 1 ward."},{"id":"alchemeister-core-crafting","name":"Alchemeister Core Crafting","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Masterful Dilution\nCost: 40 Crafting Points\nDescription:\nBy diluting the contents to the perfect required amounts, you gain an additional Elixir, Potion, Flask, Potion or Salve upon crafting success. Stacks with Efficient Dilution.\n\nDistillation\nCost: 40 Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou extract the highest quality healing materials from herbs, granting Healing +8 to a Potion with a heal or shielding effect.\n\nExplosive Lining\nCost: 10 Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou carefully add an alchemical compound to a pressurized Flask. If the Flask has an area of effect, increases the area by another 5ft (example a 10ft radius becomes 15ft radius).\n\nPurify Elixir\nCost: 40 Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou reduce the toxicity of an Elixir that has been detoxified while still maintaining its effect, reducing the damage from taking an Elixir by an additional 5."},{"id":"alchemical-detonation","name":"Alchemical Detonation","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Rapid"],"description":"You touch a wall, door or container in front of you, which shatters from deconstructive force, becoming destroyed. Can destroy up to a 5ftx5ft segment of wall. Only affects objects made out of common building materials (wood, clay, stone, iron etc), however it affects all walls made out of player abilities. The GM determines if the object is detonateable. You can then take a movement action to move 5ft into the space where the wall was."},{"id":"alchemist-core-crafting","name":"Alchemist Core Crafting","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Efficient Dilution\nCost: 10 Crafting Points\nDescription:\nBy diluting the contents to the perfect required amounts, you gain an additional Elixir, Potion, Flask, Poison or Salve upon crafting success.\n\nStone Grinding\nCost: 10 Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou extract the highest quality healing materials from herbs, granting Healing +5 to a Potion with a heal or shielding effect.\n\nPressurization\nCost: 10 Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou pressurize a Flask carefully. If the Flask has an area of effect, increases the area by 5ft (example a 10ft radius becomes 15ft radius).\n\nVolatile Flask\nCost: 10 Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou overload the active ingredients on a Flask, giving it a +5 damage to its damaging effects.\n\nDetoxify Elixir\nCost: 10 Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou reduce the toxicity of an Elixir while still maintaining its effect, reducing the damage from taking an Elixir by 3.\n\nCreate Oil Coating\nCost: Errand\nDescription:\nYou create an Oil Coating from Carpenter materials. See Items: Carpenter Materials"},{"id":"allow-me-to-clean-that-","name":"Allow me to clean that~","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Rapid"],"description":"You instantly remove a negative effect from the terrain (such as Oil Slick, Sheet Ice, Web etc). Permanent effects such as fissure or effects with HP like a wall cannot be removed with this. A maximum of 15x15ft can be removed in 1 use and you may move to any spot of the cleaned terrain afterwards.\n\nIn addition, you may target an ally with this to remove 1 negative physical effect from them instead."},{"id":"ambush-trapper","name":"Ambush Trapper","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be stealthed or have surprised the enemy.","keywords":["Encounter Start"],"description":"You may use Place Trap’s 0 RP effect once this encounter, even if you didn’t spend the time to set it up. The GM may rule that the pitfall and net options are unavailable based on the situation.\n\nThese activations still cost a Trap when used (but not if you don't use them)."},{"id":"amoxicillin","name":"Amoxicillin","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"You can identify the disease.","keywords":["Concentration","Healing","Spell"],"description":"You choose up to 10 willing units in range. After spending 1 minute in concentration, you create a cloud of spores that heals a disease that you can identify."},{"id":"amphibious","name":"Amphibious","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You can swim up to your speed and can hold your breath underwater for up to an hour."},{"id":"anathema","name":"Anathema","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Curse","Spell"],"description":"You choose one target unit and they must save against your Potency or be afflicted by Anathema. Anathema increases the next source of damage that the target receives by your Heavy Attack damage."},{"id":"angel-s-embrace","name":"Angel's Embrace","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"15ft","requirement":"A creature other than you is attacked.","keywords":["Shield","Spell","Aid"],"description":"You grant the target ally Angel’s Embrace, which grants a Shield against the triggering attack that blocks damage equal to 5 + (2 x Toughness). This Spell does not provoke attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"antennae","name":"Antennae","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You are able to detect creatures by sensing the vibrations in the air. You gain a +10 expertise bonus to Perception (Vibration Sense) which works up to 40ft from you, but only detects creatures."},{"id":"anti-magic-shield","name":"Anti-Magic Shield","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"Ally is the target of a damage dealing Spell.","keywords":["Aid","Arcane","Shield","Spell"],"description":"You grant the target ally 1 RP that must be spend on a basic Dodge or Block action against the triggering attack as well as Anti-Magic Shield for the triggering attack. Anti-Magic Shield reduces the damage the target ally takes by your Focus."},{"id":"anti-shield","name":"Anti-Shield","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Arcane","Spell"],"description":"You weave a web of magic around the target. The target cannot be the target of any abilities with the Shield keyword until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"anvil-tactics","name":"Anvil Tactics","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"80ft","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"A single ally in range may move up to their speed. If they end up in melee range of an enemy and there is an ally on the direct opposite side of that enemy, they may make an Attack of Opportunity. This attack gains Lock On."},{"id":"aqua-drill","name":"Aqua Drill","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 RP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"You are touching an amount of water equal to a normal sized bucket of water.","keywords":["Safe"],"description":"You infuse water with your mana firing a spiraling blast of high pressure water, making a heavy attack that deals Water damage against a target within range. You can use either the RP or AP cost for the ability. The water is used as a projectile and spills anywhere within 5ft of the target at your choice.\n\nIf you use an RP for this ability, the mana cost increases by 1."},{"id":"aquatic-fae","name":"Aquatic Fae","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"While swimming, your base movement speed becomes 30, in addition you gain Elemental Mastery: Water.\n\nYour Aqua Drill costs 0 mana when used as RP ability while in natural water."},{"id":"arcane-barrier","name":"Arcane Barrier","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You're about to take damage.","keywords":["Shield","Spell"],"description":"You create a Magical Barrier that absorbs damage until it breaks. The barrier has HP equal to 15 + your Focus. The barrier has a Guard of 0 and any damage it takes is subtracted from the barrier’s HP. When the barrier breaks, any remaining damage is subtracted from your HP. The barrier otherwise lasts until the start of your next turn or until you take any action other than the Block action.\n\nThis spell does not provoke attacks of opportunity and does not protect against true damage."},{"id":"arcane-barrier-ii","name":"Arcane Barrier II","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You're about to take damage.","keywords":["Shield","Spell"],"description":"You create a Magical Barrier that absorbs damage until it breaks.\n\nThe barrier has HP equal to 15 + your Focus. The barrier has a Guard of 0 + your guard and any damage it takes is subtracted from the barrier’s HP. When the barrier breaks, any remaining damage is subtracted from your HP. The barrier otherwise lasts until the start of your next turn or until you take any action other than the Block action. If using the Block action while the barrier is active, the guard of the barrier also increases.\n\nThis spell does not provoke attacks of opportunity and does not protect against true damage."},{"id":"arcane-blast","name":"Arcane Blast","costLabel":"1 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Circuit"],"description":"You make a Heavy attack that deals Arcane damage against the target."},{"id":"arcane-buster","name":"Arcane Buster","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Arcane","Spell","Shieldbreaker"],"description":"You fire a blast of energy, making a Heavy Attack that deals Arcane Damage. This attack has the Shieldbreaker property."},{"id":"arcane-explosion","name":"Arcane Explosion","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Arcane","Rapid","Spell","Blanketing"],"description":"You make a Light Attack that deals Arcane damage against all enemies within 10ft of yourself. This Spell does not provoke attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"arcane-power","name":"Arcane Power","costLabel":"0 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Arcane"],"description":"You gain Arcane Power, which adds 3 damage to the damage of all your Arcane Damage rolls until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"arcane-pull","name":"Arcane Pull","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"Target is challenged by you and attacking someone that isn't you.","keywords":["Spell"],"description":"You pull the target to an empty square next to you. This movement does not provoke attacks of opportunity. Your next Block or Dodge action against the target before the start of your next turn costs 0 RP. This Spell does not provoke attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"arcane-rapidfire","name":"Arcane Rapidfire","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Arcane","Circuit"],"description":"You make 4 light attacks that deal Arcane damage against the target."},{"id":"armor-up","name":"Armor Up","costLabel":"1 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be wearing armor and/or a shield.","keywords":["Shield"],"description":"You gain temporary HP equal to the Block value of your armor and shield, up to a maximum of 40 temporary HP."},{"id":"armored-blow","name":"Armored Blow","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"May only be used after moving at least 20ft in the previous action. Must be mounted.","keywords":[],"description":"You make a Heavy attack against the target. Your next Block against that target costs 0 RP and gains a +10 bonus."},{"id":"armorsmith-basics","name":"Armorsmith Basics","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Armorsmith's Modification A\nCost: X Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou add an A-Type modification to the armor. See the Universal Armor page as well as the individual armor pages for details. Each modification has its own cost.\n\nArmorsmith's Modification Frame\nCost: X Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou add an Frame-Type modification to the armor. See the Universal Armor page as well as the individual armor pages for details. Each modification has its own cost.\n\nAdaptive Layering\nCost: X crafting points\nDescription:\nYou mix a special material into the armor or shield. Each material has its own crafting point cost.\n\nCloak Layering\nCost: X crafting points\nDescription:\nYou use a special material for the creation of the cloak. Each material has its own crafting point cost. Only cloak special materials can be used and mixing in a special material increases the burden cost of the cloak by 1.\n\nCreate Ingot\nCost: Errand\nDescription:\nYou create an ingot from armorsmithing base materials or from armorsmithing special materials. See Item: Armorsmithing Materials.\n\nTan Leather\nCost: Errand\nDescription:\nYou create a tanned hide from armorsmithing base leather materials. See item: Armorsmithing materials."},{"id":"armorsmithing-expert","name":"Armorsmithing Expert","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Armorsmith's Modification B\nCost: X Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou add an B-Type modification to the weapon or tool. See the Universal Armor page as well as the individual armor pages for details. Each modification has its own cost."},{"id":"artery-cut","name":"Artery Cut","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"One-Handed weapon only, can be used after a light attack hits and is not reacted against.","keywords":[],"description":"You change the arc of your weapon and go for a vital spot, turning the hit into a critical hit."},{"id":"artificer-basics","name":"Artificer Basics","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Advanced Melding\nCost: 10 crafting points\nDescription:\nYou expertly create the artifice hookup, reducing the artifice weight burden by 1 to a minimum of 0.5.\n\nDouble Barrel\nCost: 10 crafting points\nDescription:\nCan hold up to 2 shells. You still reload 1 shell at a time.\n\nArtifice Modification A\nCost: 10 crafting points\nDescription:\nYou add an A-Type modification to an artifice. See the individual artifice to see if modifications are available.\n\nWeapon Modification A\nCost: X Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou add an A-Type modification to the weapon. See the Universal Weapon or Crafting mods page as well as the individual weapon page for details. Each modification has its own cost.\n\nAttach/Detach Artifice\nCost: Errand\nDescription:\nYou spend some time connecting the artifice to a weapon with an open artifice slot. If you remove an artifice from a weapon, you can attach it to a different weapon with the same Errand action.\n\nCraft Fuel Shells\nCost: Errand\nDescription:\nYou craft up to 5 small shells. You can instead craft a medium shell instead of 2 small shells. Small shells require 50 magical fuel, medium shells require 200 magical fuel.\n\nCraft Artifice Parts\nCost: Errand\nDescription:\nYou create up to 3000u of artifice parts of the same type of blacksmithing material used to make them at a 1:1 rate. (3000u of Iron Creates 3000u of Iron Artifice Parts.) See Items: Blacksmithing Materials, Artificer Materials. When converting items of a higher tier, you can convert up to 6000 of tamahagane, 9000 of mithril, 12000 of Orihalcum or 15000 of escudo.\n\nFirearm Alloy\nCost: X Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou mix a special material into the firearm or artifice weapon. Each material has its own crafting point cost.\n\nCreate Ingot\nCost: Errand\nDescription:\nYou create an ingot from blacksmithing base materials or from blacksmithing special materials. See Item: Blacksmithing Materials."},{"id":"assign-decoy","name":"Assign Decoy","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Challenge","Quick"],"description":"Choose one willing ally within range and one enemy within range. The enemy is Challenged by the chosen ally until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"astral-projection","name":"Astral Projection","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["-"],"description":"After a 10 minute channel you arrive at the space between worlds, allowing you to interact with Eidolons that wish to meet with you."},{"id":"at-your-side","name":"At your side","costLabel":"0 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Teleport"],"description":"You teleport next to your VIP."},{"id":"attack-in-detail","name":"Attack in Detail","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You target one enemy unit. All allied units (including yourself) gain a +1 Damage Bonus when that enemy unit is the target of an attack until the start of your next turn. In addition, all allied units gain +5 Movement Speed when moving towards that enemy unit."},{"id":"attacks-from-the-past","name":"Attacks from the Past","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Rage"],"description":"After making a melee weapon attack, you may repeat the attack from one of your past self tokens. You may target the same enemy as your original attack. Cannot repeat Secret Arts or other attacks with a once per combat/arc etc type limitation.\n\nCan only repeat attacks with a base cost of 2 AP or lower and any mana cost must be paid as normal."},{"id":"attune-eidolon","name":"Attune Eidolon","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You have an Eidolon you are contracted to.","keywords":["Encounter Start"],"description":"You attune to a specific Eidolon, paying the attunement cost (if applicable) and then activating its Passive (if applicable). You gain its Channel Eidolon, Summon Lesser Eidolon and Secret Art: Summon Eidolon abilities provided that you have advanced enough in this class to get them.\n\nYou may use this as an Encounter Start ability without paying an AP cost."},{"id":"aura-of-protection","name":"Aura of Protection","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Aura"],"description":"You create a 30ft radius Aura of Protection around yourself. While this aura is active, when an ally within 30ft of you takes the Block action you may spend 1 Mana to replace their Block Value with your own. In addition, any abilities with the Aid keyword have their range increased by 20ft while inside the Aura."},{"id":"aura-of-resistance","name":"Aura of Resistance","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Aura"],"description":"You create a 30ft radius Aura of Resistance around yourself until the end of the encounter.\n\nWhile this aura is active, when an ally other than yourself fails a save you may spend 1 Mana to increase their save value by your Toughness."},{"id":"aurora-blade-style-secret-art--permafrost-guilotine","name":"Aurora Blade Style Secret Art: Permafrost Guilotine","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Can only be used after you move to a target using Rimestep. Light swords, longsword, katana or dueling weapon only.","keywords":["Secret Art","Stance","Frost"],"description":"You make a light attack against the target or spend 1 extra AP to make a heavy or precise attack that deals Frost damage. On damage, the target is rooted until the end of your next turn.\n\nThen, enter Permafrost Guillotine stance. While in this stance you can use Aurora Blade Style Secret Art: Permafrost Guillotine again. The stance lasts until the end of combat or until you enter different stance."},{"id":"aurora-blade-style--aurora-slash","name":"Aurora Blade Style: Aurora Slash","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"80ft","requirement":"Light swords, longsword, katana or dueling weapon only.","keywords":["Slow","Frost"],"description":"You fire slashes in a straight line creating a curtain of light which strikes the first target hit with a light attack that deals frost damage. On hit the target is slowed until the end of your next turn.\n\nThe light from the slash continues for the full range, creating a 300ft high wall that blocks vision on both sides. This wall of multicolored light last until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"aurora-blade-style--rimestep","name":"Aurora Blade Style: Rimestep","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"When a target is slowed by an attack with the frost keyword, you may sidestep up to your speed towards the target. If you have enough movement you can end your movement anywhere next to the target. Overcharge: You may spend 1 Mana to instead make it three times your speed."},{"id":"aurora-blade-style--winter-s-edge","name":"Aurora Blade Style: Winter's Edge","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Light swords, longsword, katana or dueling weapon only.","keywords":["Slow","Frost"],"description":"You imbue your blade with frost energy and make a precise attack that deals Frost damage. On hit, the target is slowed until the end of your next turn."},{"id":"ave-mar-a","name":"Ave María","costLabel":"3 AP","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You attack with a swift double slash in the blink of an eye, making a Heavy Attack that deals Light damage + Heavy Holy damage."},{"id":"backlash","name":"Backlash","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"","keywords":["Full Pierce","Lockstep"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target. You take true damage equal to half the damage dealt."},{"id":"banana-peel","name":"Banana Peel","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"20ft","requirement":"An enemy is moving within range.","keywords":[],"description":"You toss a banana peel in front of the target and they must make a Save or fall prone. If they fall prone, you may immediately use Pie Toss against them for 0 RP."},{"id":"battle-cast","name":"Battle Cast","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Circuit"],"description":"The next Spell you cast before the end of your turn does not provoke an attack of opportunity from being casted in Melee Range of an opponent."},{"id":"bear-maul","name":"Bear Maul","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Unarmed Strike"],"description":"You swing your paw at the target and make a Heavy attack against it that deals maximum damage. If the target dodges, this attack automatically misses.\n\nYou are considered proficient in unarmed attacks for this attack, even if you normally wouldn’t be."},{"id":"bear-shock","name":"Bear Shock","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You gain a +20 bonus to Deception checks when disguising yourself as something other than a bearfolk."},{"id":"bear-trap","name":"Bear Trap","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Root","Full Pierce","Stealth"],"description":"You place down a bear trap in an empty square within range. If an enemy enters that square, they trigger the trap taking Light full pierce damage and becoming rooted until they spend 2 AP to remove the effect.\n\nAgainst beasts, this does Heavy damage instead of Light damage.\n\nThis ability consumes a Trap."},{"id":"bestial-command","name":"Bestial Command","costLabel":"0 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"Can only target your summoned animal.","keywords":["-"],"description":"The summon may take basic actions as if it had 2 AP to spend.\n\nIn addition, if your summon is under the effects of Independent Action, it gains Bestial Command until the end of the encounter, it dies or you cancel it for 0 AP. While Bestial Command lasts, its maximum AP and AP recovery are increased by 2 while your AP recovery is lowered by 2."},{"id":"biohacking","name":"Biohacking","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"At the start of an arc, you can transmute a gene from a Chimera Subrace into your DNA as long as you have a sample (a vial of blood).\n\nTransmuting the gene does not consume the item. Add a single Chimera gene to your gene inventory.\n\nYou can perform this action again for an IP or EP. Biohacking can store genes equal to your gene limit."},{"id":"blackbird","name":"Blackbird","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Small Shell","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"1 Small Shell","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You deploy a Blackbird, a small artifice drone that outputs a grainy image to a device on your wrist. The blackbird has a maximum range of 3000ft and can observe major movements and structures such as doors and enemies. The drone cannot display fine movements or detail such as words in a book without being up close, but can see large signs. The blackbird is the size of a walnut and is relatively quiet, and can only be heard by those with normal human hearing within 10 ft.\n\nThe fuel shell lasts for one flight, up to 15 minutes. If your Blackbird is lost or damaged, you must create a new one as an errand action before you can use this again."},{"id":"blacksmith-core-crafting","name":"Blacksmith Core Crafting","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Blacksmith’s Modification A\nCost: X Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou add an A-Type modification to the weapon or tool. See the Universal Weapon or Crafting mods page as well as the individual weapon page for details. Each modification has its own cost.\n\nWeapon Alloy\nCost: X Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou mix a special material into the smithing weapon. Each material has its own crafting point cost.\n\nCreate Ingot\nCost: Errand\nDescription:\nYou create an ingot from blacksmithing base materials or from blacksmithing special materials. See Item: Blacksmithing Materials."},{"id":"blast-away","name":"Blast Away","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You fire a point blank shot at an enemy unit. The enemy must save against your Potency or be knocked back 5ft and take Light Damage. This ability does not provoke attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"blast-wave","name":"Blast Wave","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Fire","Spell","Blanketing"],"description":"You may make a Light attack that deals Fire damage against every character within 10ft of you. On damage, they are pushed back 10ft. This spell does not provoke attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"blinding-dust","name":"Blinding Dust","costLabel":"1 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"You are the target of an attack.","keywords":["Sidestep","Blinded"],"description":"You flap your wings and blow dust in the eyes of the attacker, making them Blinded 6 until the end of their attack. If their attack against you misses, you may Sidestep 5ft."},{"id":"blocking-move","name":"Blocking Move","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You made an opportunity attack against a target moving away from you. Must be mounted.","keywords":[],"description":"You move in front of the target and their movement action immediately ends. Until the end of their turn, they are Challenged by you and your next Block action against them costs 0 RP. If they willingly move from you through any method (including teleports) you may make a Heavy attack against them with Sure Hit.\n\nYour movement may ignore Line Movement restrictions for this ability."},{"id":"blood-drain","name":"Blood Drain","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"Target must be a living creature. Target cannot be an ally.","keywords":["Healing","Safe"],"description":"You make a Light Attack that deals Dark damage against the target. On damage, you recover HP equal to your Toughness + 3."},{"id":"blood-frenzy","name":"Blood Frenzy","costLabel":"0 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You go into a blood frenzy, mindlessly attacking enemies near you.\n\nWhile the blood frenzy lasts, you must attack the nearest enemy target with a basic unarmed attack. If two targets are equally close, you may choose which one you attack. If no enemies are within range, you must use your movement to move closer to the closest visible enemy until you can attack them.\n\nWhile under the effect of blood frenzy, you heal for half the damage you deal with your unarmed attacks.\n\nYou cannot use Vampire Bite while under the effect of Blood Frenzy.\n\nThis effect lasts until all visible enemies are dead or until your mana runs out. At the start of your turn, you lose 2 mana."},{"id":"blood-shield","name":"Blood Shield","costLabel":"1 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"Target is the target of an attack.","keywords":["Aid","Healing","Shield"],"description":"You grant the target 1 RP that must be spent on the Block action against the triggering attack. They gain a +5 bonus to their Guard for this Block action. After the attack, the target regains HP equal to half the damage blocked (Blocked meaning the damage reduced through block, not necessarily your total block value)."},{"id":"bloodbolt","name":"Bloodbolt","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Overcharge"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target.\n\nOvercharge: You may spend X HP to increase the damage the attack deals by X. X may not exceed your Toughness."},{"id":"blue-tide","name":"Blue Tide","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Domain","Spell"],"description":"You create a 15ft radius zone of 1ft of water in a circle around yourself. This zone of water remains stationary at its original position, even after you move.\n\nThis zone lasts until the end of the encounter and automatically replenishes itself when Aqua Drill is used inside of it. You may have multiple of these zones active at once."},{"id":"bolting","name":"Bolting","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"360ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Lightning","Rapid","Spell"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack that deals Lightning Damage with a bolt from the sky. On damage, inflict Static X where X equals your Focus x 3. As the attack from the sky, any cover is calculated from above the target rather than from your path to the target."},{"id":"bone-armor","name":"Bone Armor","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"Corpse within range.","keywords":[],"description":"You target and destroy a corpse within range to give yourself Bone Armor, which gives you a +2 bonus to your guard. Bone Armor lasts until the end of the encounter or until you take 2 or more damage from an attack."},{"id":"bottle-smash","name":"Bottle Smash","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"Improvised weapon only.","keywords":["Daze","Prone"],"description":"You may make a Light Attack against the target. On damage, the target becomes Dazed. After this attack, your improvised weapon breaks."},{"id":"bottle-toss","name":"Bottle Toss","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"20ft","requirement":"Improvised weapon only.","keywords":["Daze"],"description":"You may make a Light Attack against the target. On damage, the target becomes Dazed. After this attack, your improvised weapon breaks."},{"id":"boundless-wind-stance","name":"Boundless Wind Stance","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Stance"],"description":"You enter the Wind Stance, an unarmed style focusing around aerial combat. While in this stance, you may Hover and Fly up to your speed. If you already have a natural Flying speed or the Flight racial ability, your flying speed is increased by 10ft.\n\nThis stance lasts until you enter a different stance or make an attack with anything other than a melee attack or an ability with the Unarmed Strike keyword."},{"id":"break-away","name":"Break Away","costLabel":"1 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be mounted.","keywords":["-"],"description":"You disengage and may move up to half your speed away from the nearest enemy."},{"id":"break-free","name":"Break Free","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Not in Rage Stance.","keywords":["Rage"],"description":"You may use this ability when you would be affected by a Stun, Root, Fear or a similar effect that would prevent you from acting that's inflicted by an enemy. You may immediately enter Rage Stance without spending any AP or RP. You gain immunity to this effect for the duration of the Rage."},{"id":"brilliance","name":"Brilliance","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"80ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Illumination","Light"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target dealing Holy(Light) damage. On damage, inflict Illumination X, where X equals your Focus / 2 (rounded down) until the end of your next turn."},{"id":"bring-out-your-dead","name":"Bring out your dead","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"10ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Encounter Start"],"description":"You summon 3 zombies, as if you used Raise Undead 3 times. Restrictions on max zombie limit still apply.\n\nDoes not require corpses."},{"id":"bullet-magnet","name":"Bullet Magnet","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"20ft","requirement":"Must be using a greatshield.","keywords":[],"description":"Until the start of your next turn, any single target Ranged Weapon Attack made against an ally in range is made against you instead."},{"id":"bunshin-tai-no-jutsu","name":"Bunshin Tai no Jutsu","costLabel":"1 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Ninjutsu","Stealth"],"description":"You create a body double of yourself that has the same stats you do at the time of creation. You and the body double share the same HP, Mana, AP and RP. Any buffs applied to your clone also applies to you (but not vice versa). When taking an action, you may choose to let the user be yourself or the body double. However, the body double may only use basic abilities and abilities with the Ninjutsu keyword and cannot create more body doubles of itself.\n\nWhen you take the movement action or use a non-teleport movement ability, your clone may move for the same amount of distance as you moved.\n\nYou may spend 0 AP or 1 RP to dismiss the body double. A clone can never travel more than 300ft from your actual body, but while it lasts you may spend 2 AP to swap locations with it.\n\nA clone lasts until you rest."},{"id":"call-of-the-grave","name":"Call of the Grave","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Challenge"],"description":"You make a Heavy Attack against the target that deals Dark damage. On hit, if the target is large or smaller, you pull them to you. They are Challenged until the start of your next turn. This ability does not provoke an attack of opportunity."},{"id":"can-t-escape-death","name":"Can't Escape Death","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"A target Challenged by you leaves your melee range.","keywords":["Sidestep"],"description":"You may use this after an enemy leaves your melee range. After the target finishes moving, you may sidestep up to your speed towards them. For 1 RP, you may move double your speed instead."},{"id":"canter","name":"Canter","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be mounted and can be used immediately after making a weapon attack.","keywords":["Sidestep"],"description":"You may Sidestep 10ft."},{"id":"carpenter-basics","name":"Carpenter Basics","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Carpenter's Modification A\nCost: X Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou add an A-Type modification to the weapon or tool. See the Universal Weapon page as well as the individual weapon page for details. Each modification has its own cost.\n\nJoining and Assembling\nCost: X Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou mix a special material into the carpentry project. Each material has its own crafting point cost.\n\nCreate Oil Coating\nCost: Errand\nDescription:\nYou create an Oil Coating from Carpenter materials. See Items: Carpenter Materials.\n\nCreate Wood Block\nCost: Errand\nDescription:\nYou create a Wood Block from Carpenter materials. See Items: Carpenter Materials.\n\nInfuse Wand\nCost: 5 Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou add a drop of Oil Coating into a wand, changing the built in damage type to the element of the oil. Only works with oils that change the damage type. Does not consume the oil."},{"id":"castling","name":"Castling","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Teleport"],"description":"You swap positions with a Rook puppet piece you control."},{"id":"cat-form","name":"Cat Form","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":["Transformation"],"description":"You transform into cat form, reducing your Guard to 0 but increasing your Evasion by +3 and Dodge by +6. Your size is tiny and you are able to occupy the same square as an ally. While in Cat form the only attack you can make is Light Melee Attack. If you take damage in Cat Form, you immediately return to your normal form. You can dispel this form for 0 AP or 1 RP."},{"id":"catalyze","name":"Catalyze","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"Target is afflicted with your Toxic.","keywords":["Poison","Circuit"],"description":"The target must succeed at a Save. On failure, you inflict Stagger II or Sunder II until the end of your next turn."},{"id":"cavalry-charge","name":"Cavalry Charge","costLabel":"-1 AP","apCost":"-1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be mounted.","keywords":["-"],"description":"You may spend up to 4 AP on this ability and move as though you had spent that AP on movement. You automatically gain the Trample effect as like the Trample ability once you have moved 20ft.\n\nFor every 10ft moved, the attack you make as part of the Trample effect gains +1 bonus damage, up to a maximum of +10."},{"id":"cavalry-heal","name":"Cavalry Heal","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Touch","requirement":"-","keywords":["Spell","Healing"],"description":"You heal the target for 11 + (Power x 2). If the target is mounted, their mount gets healed for the same amount."},{"id":"cave-raider","name":"Cave Raider","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Circuit"],"description":"Until the start of your next turn, you gain the ability to climb your speed. In addition if you have rope, you can tie it to a secure object and you can rappel down a cliffside up to 50ft at the cost of 5ft of movement."},{"id":"chain-lightning","name":"Chain Lightning","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Lightning","Spell"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target dealing Lightning Damage and inflicting Static X where X equals your Focus x 3. On damage, you may repeat this attack against another target within 30ft of the target without paying additional costs. This attack may repeat multiple times like this.\n\nYou cannot target the same creature more than once per use of this ability."},{"id":"chair_grab","name":"Chair Grab","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Quick"],"description":"You grab a nearby unattended object and are able to use it as an improvised weapon."},{"id":"channel-eidolon","name":"Channel Eidolon","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":["-"],"description":"You use the ability granted by your attuned Eidolon. All costs and effects are determined by your attunement."},{"id":"channel-eidolon--distracting-swarm","name":"Channel Eidolon: Distracting Swarm","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"Ixilune attunement.","keywords":[],"description":"You summon a distracting swarm around a target. The target immediately loses any Concentration effects and suffers -5 penalty to Perception checks unless they spend 1 RP to sidestep out of the effect. If they did not move, they also cannot use any abilities with the Concentration keyword until they move.\n\nYou can only have 1 Distracting Swarm active at the same time."},{"id":"channel-eidolon--draw-luck","name":"Channel Eidolon: Draw Luck","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["-"],"description":"You draw on your luck, manipulating the circumstances around you to the best possible state. If you are the target of an attack, that attack becomes a 1. If you made a roll, that roll becomes a 20 (despite the pact cost).\n\nMay also be used in situations that don’t have you making a roll, such as flipping a coin, but the act that you’re influencing cannot take more than 5 seconds to complete.\n\nAfter using this ability, you become temporarily afflicted with bad luck. The GM decides what exactly happens and what triggers it, but it could turn your roll into a 1, make an enemy roll a 20 against you or something related to the environment. After a bad luck action happens, the bad luck is removed.\n\nYou cannot use this ability again until after the bad luck has been removed."},{"id":"channel-eidolon--vine-wall-cover","name":"Channel Eidolon: Vine Wall Cover","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"Pipoltr attunement.","keywords":["Spell"],"description":"Thick vines sprout from the ground or natural wall as you create a 5x5 wall of vines that is 10ft high. The wall of vines counts as full cover (unless you peek from it) and has HP equal to your Toughness x6. The vines are sturdy enough to stand on.\n\nLasts for up to 5 minutes and you can only have 5 instances of Vine Wall Cover at one time."},{"id":"charge","name":"Charge","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You may spend 2 or 4 AP on this ability and move as though you had spent that AP on movement. After you finish moving, you may spend half of the AP you used on this ability on Light or Heavy Melee Attacks."},{"id":"charm","name":"Charm","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Mystic Eye","Charm","Mind Affecting"],"description":"The target must make a Save or be charmed by you until the end of the encounter."},{"id":"check","name":"Check","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You move a puppet piece in such a way (following Move Piece rules) that it can attack an enemy if it moves again. It cannot attack with this movement.\n\nAt the start of your next turn, you may move that piece as if you used Move Piece without spending AP/Mana or it counting as an ability use."},{"id":"chemical-explosive","name":"Chemical Explosive","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Sure Hit"],"description":"You place a Chemical Explosive package that detonates after one minute. The explosion has a 15 ft radius and deals Double Heavy damage. The package makes an obvious noise after it has been planted that can be heard within the radius. The explosive charge deals 5x damage against inanimate objects. You can create a Chemical Explosive during an interlude phase for free, but can only carry one at a time. The check to disable a Chemical Explosive is equal to 20 + 2 x Power of the creator."},{"id":"chiburi-noto","name":"Chiburi Noto","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self (Weapon)","requirement":"Must have used an ability with the Iaijutsu keyword with the chosen weapon this encounter.","keywords":["Encounter Conclusion"],"description":"You clean the blood off your katana and sheath the blade. If your next Iai strike with this weapon during this arc is a hit, its Roll Damage is maximized."},{"id":"chiburi-noto-ii","name":"Chiburi Noto II","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self (Weapon)","requirement":"Must have used an ability with the Iaijutsu keyword with the chosen weapon this encounter.","keywords":["Encounter Conclusion"],"description":"You clean the blood off your katana and sheath the blade. If your next Iai strike with this weapon during this arc is a hit, its Roll Damage is maximized and it gains Full Pierce."},{"id":"chilling-cold","name":"Chilling Cold","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You can emit a cooling wind within 30ft that counters the effects of most hot weather. You can enable or disable this every 1 second. In addition you gain Elemental Mastery: Frost."},{"id":"circle-swing","name":"Circle Swing","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You make a Light Attack against the target. On damage, you may move the target to anywhere in your weapon range (Max 10ft) , then push it 5ft. The target must remain at the same height it was before this ability was used. Your next Spell or Channeling Weapon attack this turn costs 1 less AP (Min 0)."},{"id":"circuit-reset","name":"Circuit Reset","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You reset your circuits, allowing you to once again benefit from the Circuit effect."},{"id":"clearcasting","name":"Clearcasting","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Encounter Start"],"description":"The next Spell you cast this encounter has its mana cost reduced by 2. This cannot reduce the mana cost below 0."},{"id":"cleave","name":"Cleave","costLabel":"3 AP","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Two-Handed weapons only.","keywords":["Blanketing"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against two different targets in range."},{"id":"cloak-of-bats","name":"Cloak of Bats","costLabel":"2 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"2","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Teleport"],"description":"You vanish into a swarm of bats and reappear somewhere else within range. If this was used in reaction to an attack, that attack automatically misses you."},{"id":"cloud-piercing-claw","name":"Cloud Piercing Claw","costLabel":"1 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"","keywords":["Unarmed Strike","Sidestep","Combo"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target. On damage, they are knocked airborne 20ft until the end of your turn (if this attack is made outside of your turn, they drop immediately). They are NOT knocked prone from this, but do take fall damage like normal.\n\nYou may Sidestep up to 25ft into the air after making this attack, regardless of if you did damage with it.\n\nCombo: If used after entering Boundless Wind Stance, the mana cost of this ability is reduced by 1."},{"id":"cloudstep","name":"Cloudstep","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be the first movement action in your turn.","keywords":["Sidestep"],"description":"You may Sidestep up to half your speed. This movement ignores difficult terrain."},{"id":"combat-chemistry","name":"Combat Chemistry","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Can only be used once per encounter.\n\nUsing your knowledge of alchemy, you jury-rig a special item that has the effect of an an elixir, poison, flask or potion with a cost of 300c or lower.\n\nYou can only make the base version of the item with no mods. The item doesn't take up burden, but must be used before the start of your next turn or it is lost. This item can only be used by you."},{"id":"comet","name":"Comet","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"240ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Celestial"],"description":"You make a Light (1 AP) or Heavy (2 AP) attack against the target that deals Arcane damage."},{"id":"command-undead","name":"Command Undead","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You may have one of your Necromancer summons act as if they had spent 1 AP."},{"id":"compression","name":"Compression","costLabel":"1 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Gravity"],"description":"You make a Heavy attack against the target that deals Physical (Crushing) damage.\n\nIf the target is Large Size or bigger, the mana cost of this is reduced by 1."},{"id":"concealed-shot","name":"Concealed Shot","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Only usable after attacking with a Sniper Rifle while stealthed.","keywords":[],"description":"You immediately make a new stealth check and remain hidden if enemies fail their perception check."},{"id":"conduit","name":"Conduit","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":["-"],"description":"When Mind Connection is active, you can channel some abilities through others with Mind Connection. You cannot use conduit with abilities that require a physical object to be present, such as a Mystic Eye power or a specific weapon or abilities that require you to interact with a physical object, such as Snatch. Abilities that require your physical body to make an attack, such as Double Punch also don't work.\n\nYou still must pay the costs to use the abilities, and your Mind Connection source becomes the origin point of the spell for purposes of range. Abilities with a range of Self cannot be used through Conduit.\n\nAny ability used through Conduit that isn't an Aetherie ability costs +1 AP (or RP) to use."},{"id":"consistent-shot","name":"Consistent Shot","costLabel":"3 AP","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You may make a Precise Attack against the target. This attack deals Heavy Damage instead.\n\nThis attack does not gain Pinpoint."},{"id":"consume-enemy","name":"Consume Enemy","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"One dead enemy","requirement":"-","keywords":["Encounter Conclusion"],"description":"You eat the body of a deceased enemy, healing you for your Toughness x 2, regaining 1 mana and preventing a single injury."},{"id":"consume-fire","name":"Consume Fire","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You're about to take Fire Damage.","keywords":["Fire"],"description":"You gain Consume Fire, which gives you Damage Reduction 100 Fire against the triggering damage. If the attacker is not yourself or from an effect caused by you, you can then spend 2 Mana to heal for the original damage amount, up to 100 HP."},{"id":"consume-lightning","name":"Consume Lightning","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You are about to take Lightning damage","keywords":["Rapid"],"description":"You gain Consume Lightning, which gives you Damage Reduction 100 Lightning for the triggering damage. If you reduce damage in any way from this ability and the cause of this damage is not you or from an effect caused by you, you gain Lightning Boost. Lightning Boost grants a damage bonus on your next Lightning Elemental Attack equal to the attacker’s power. This damage bonus is doubled on heavy attacks."},{"id":"corona-burst","name":"Corona Burst","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"240ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Celestial"],"description":"You make a Heavy attack against the target that deals Fire damage. For every 20ft of distance the target is away from you, this deals +1 damage. (Up to a maximum of +12)"},{"id":"corpse-domination","name":"Corpse Domination","costLabel":"3 AP, 4 Mana","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"4","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"Target must be a dead humanoid.","keywords":["Summon"],"description":"You raise the target under your command. A target raised in this way is treated as a non-heroic unit that takes its own actions, however it will try to act in a way that is most helpful to you in the fight. The raised target keeps all of its stats and abilities it had in life, though it only starts with half its maximum health (before any reductions) and whatever mana it had left over when it died. This summon lasts until the end of the encounter or until its HP reaches 0, upon which it immediately dies again and cannot be raised again in any way."},{"id":"corpse-explosion","name":"Corpse Explosion","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"15x15ft area circled on your zombie","requirement":"Must have an active zombie from Raise Undead.","keywords":["Scatter"],"description":"You detonate 1 of your zombies, making a Light Attack that deals Dark damage against all creatures in range but killing the zombie. You may detonate additional zombies when using this ability to increase the damage this deals by 2 for each additional zombie."},{"id":"corpse-puppetry","name":"Corpse Puppetry","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"Target must be dead.","keywords":[],"description":"You may control a corpse less than a week old within 30ft of you to perform simple actions, such as moving or talking.\n\nA corpse used this way has no combat stats and cannot attack."},{"id":"counter-stance","name":"Counter Stance","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Counter","Stance","Unarmed Strike"],"description":"You enter a stance in which you freely counterattack against enemies that attack you. After an attack against you has resolved, you may make a Melee Attack of Opportunity against that target. While in this stance, you cannot use the Dodge or Block reactions.\n\nYou may spend 0 AP or 1 RP to cancel this stance. It otherwise lasts until you enter another stance."},{"id":"counter-potion","name":"Counter-Potion","costLabel":"-1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"-1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You may immediately use a Potion, Elixir, Salve, Poison or Flask that is held in your hand. X is equal to the AP cost of the action."},{"id":"countershot","name":"Countershot","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"You or an ally are targeted by a ranged weapon attack.","keywords":[],"description":"You may make a Precise Attack against the incoming attack. If your accuracy check matches or beats the enemy’s accuracy check, you shoot down the incoming arrow and the attack is negated."},{"id":"counterspell","name":"Counterspell","costLabel":"1 or 2 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1 or 2","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"An enemy casts a spell within range","keywords":["Arcane","Counter","Spell"],"description":"You pay RP equal to half the AP spent on the triggering Spell (rounded up) or equal to the RP spent on the triggering spell and Counter it, canceling its effect without refunding the AP. If the AP cost is higher than your RP, you cannot Counterspell it.\n\nIf used against a non-Grunt target, you must pay 1 mana for each point of Focus that the target has more than you (minimum 0).\n\nThis Spell does not provoke attacks of opportunity, but cannot be used to Counter Spells that have an AP and RP cost of 0."},{"id":"craft-artificer-s-glove","name":"Craft Artificer's Glove","costLabel":"1 IP","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"1 IP","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You create a personalized Artificer’s Glove that only you have proficiency with. Choose a glove type with properties of your choosing at the time of creation. You can modify this glove for an errand action to change the property, but you can only have one property at a time and only one Artificer’s glove at a time.\n\nGamma Glove (Hacker): Artifice Jamming. For 1 RP you can Jam a small shell artifice within 120ft causing it to malfunction and be unusable until the user spends 1 AP to clear the jam.\n\nSigma Glove (Combat Artificer): Heat Sink. 0 RP, 1 mana. Your glove emits frost energy that saps heat from an artifice, allowing it to bypass the once per turn limit a single time. Overcharge: 1 RP, the mana cost becomes 0.\n\nDelta Glove (Specialist): The glove is specialized for an expertise skill granting you +10 in that skill. For instance, it might fire an arcane blast to propel you, granting you +10 to jumping. May not choose artisan or gathering skils."},{"id":"craft-pemmican","name":"Craft Pemmican","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":["Errand"],"description":"Errand. You turn up to 1000u of food into 25 Pemmican Bars (40u of food per bar), which are incredibly shelf stable and easy to eat. They perform about the same as Military Rations but they are wrapped by special leaves that deter pests—useful and consistent adventure food.\n\nYou may also use this as an IP action to convert up to 2000u of food into 50 Pemmican bars."},{"id":"crashing-foam-wave","name":"Crashing Foam Wave","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 RP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30 ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Active"],"description":"Creates a wave of water originating from a point of water within range. Shoves an adjacent target of size large or smaller 10ft away from the point of origin. If the target is on top of the water, you can choose to shove the target in any direction. You can use either AP or RP for the cost of this ability."},{"id":"create-talisman","name":"Create Talisman","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"-","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You may create a talisman or scroll by spending an interlude point. Choose an Spell that you know or choose a specialized talisman, such as a Sealing Talisman. You inscribe that Spell onto a piece of paper. A talisman of a Spell allows you to use the Spell at a different time. When you use it, it is consumed. A Spell talisman costs as much AP and mana to use as the original Spell does.\n\nYou may craft up to 5 talismans per interlude point. A secret art talisman takes up 3 of these slots. When crafting, you may make no more than 2 of the same spell. A crafted talisman costs 1 burden to carry with you. A Secret Art talisman costs 2 burden and can only be used through the Secret Talisman ability.\n\nCrafting a talisman costs 100 calligraphy units per AP and Mana of the spell. A spell with no AP or Mana costs 50 units. If the spell has an RP cost and no AP cost, it costs 200u per RP. If the spell has a casting time longer than 4 AP (ie 10 minutes), then treat the spell as having a cost of 4 AP.\n\nSome spells, such as Summon Lesser Eidolon and Summon Eidolon may be unavailable."},{"id":"crescent-sweep","name":"Crescent Sweep","costLabel":"3 AP","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Polearm only","keywords":["Blanketing"],"description":"You make a Light Attack against all enemies in range. On damage, a target falls Prone."},{"id":"crimson-enmity","name":"Crimson Enmity","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"When your HP is at or below 50% of your max HP, you gain Crimson Enmity. When you would heal an ally or yourself with an ability from this class (Bloodbinder), you heal for 1.5x that amount."},{"id":"crippling-attack","name":"Crippling Attack","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Slow"],"description":"You make a Light Attack against the target. On damage the target is Slowed until the end of their next turn."},{"id":"crippling-poison","name":"Crippling Poison","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"Target suffering from your Toxic takes a movement action.","keywords":["Poison"],"description":"You slow the target for their movement.\n\nOvercharge: You may spend 1 additional mana to make it affect a movement not reliant on movement speed, something that moves a fixed distance. The distance moved with that is halved. If that movement had an attack attached that now cannot be made, the ability is NOT refunded."},{"id":"crucified-by-radiance","name":"Crucified by Radiance","costLabel":"3 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Light","Illumination","Scatter"],"description":"You make a light attack that deals Holy(Light) to any targets in a 5ft wide line. At any point of the line you can draw a second 55ft long perpendicular line centered on that point of the initial line. You make another Light attack against all caught on this second line and on damage you inflict Illumination X where X is your Focus / 2 (Rounded Down) until the end of your next turn.\n\nIf a target gets hit by both lines, the second line deals Heavy damage and inflicts your full Focus in Illumination instead."},{"id":"crusader-s-advance","name":"Crusader's Advance","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"Target has your Mark of Justice on them.","keywords":["Teleport"],"description":"You teleport to an empty square next to an enemy you marked with the Mark of Justice."},{"id":"culinary-basics","name":"Culinary Basics","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Mushroom Stock\nCost: 15 Crafting Points\nDescription:\nTurns a Gourmet Base Stock into a Mushroom Stock (does not stack with other stocks), which when added to a cooked meal gives a +1 Focus Food Bonus that lasts for 24 hours. Requires 1 Box of Fresh Mushrooms.\n\nMeaty Stock\nCost: 15 Crafting Points\nDescription:\nTurns a Gourmet Base Stock into a Meaty Stock (does not stack with other stocks), which when added to a cooked meal gives a +1 Power Food Bonus that lasts for 24 hours. Requires 1 Box of Fresh Meat.\n\nFish Stock\nCost: 15 Crafting Points\nDescription:\nTurns a Gourmet Base Stock into a Fish Stock (does not stack with other stocks), which when added to a cooked meal gives a +1 Toughness Food Bonus that lasts for 24 hours. Requires 1 Box of Fresh Fish.\n\nVegetable Stock\nCost: 15 Crafting Points\nDescription:\nTurns a Gourmet Base Stock into a Vegetable Stock (does not stack with other stocks), which when added to a cooked meal gives a +1 Agility Food Bonus that lasts for 24 hours. Requires 1 Box of Fresh Vegetables.\n\nSpicy Stock\nCost: 30 Crafting Points\nDescription:\nTurns a Gourmet Base Stock into a Spicy Stock (does not stack with other stocks), which when added to a cooked meal gives a +1 Crafting Food Bonus that lasts for 24 hours. Requires 1 bundle of Spicy Peppers.\n\nHerbal Stock\nCost: 30 Crafting Points\nDescription:\nTurns a Gourmet Base Stock into a Herbal Stock (does not stack with other stocks), which when added to a cooked meal gives a +1 Gathering Food Bonus that lasts for 24 hours. Requires 1 bundle of Fresh Cooking Herbs. When gathering from a node with a bonus from this stock, you keep the benefit for that entire node unless you go a day without harvesting from that node.\n\nStir Layered Flavors\nCost: 30 Crafting Points\nDescription:\nAllows you to add another flavor, allowing you to add a second different flavor. Choose from Mushroom, Meaty, Fish, Vegetable, Spicy or Herbal—then add the corresponding ingredient. For example: A Mushroom stock + Meaty stock becomes a Mushroom-Meaty stock that grants +1 Power / +1 Focus Food Bonus.\n\nUse Every Last Drop\nCost: 15 Crafting Points\nDescription:\nIncreases the stock yield by 2.\n\nSecret Ingredient\nCost: X Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou mix a special material into the stock. Each material has its own crafting point cost.\n\nCreate Box or Bundle of Food\nCost: Errand.\nDescription:\nYou create a perfect mix of ingredients that would be worthy of a stock with 500u of matching material. Example: 500u of Meat can make 1 Box of Fresh Meat. You can make 5 boxes of any kind for one errand action."},{"id":"cure-touch","name":"Cure Touch","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Touch","requirement":"-","keywords":["Healing","Spell"],"description":"You heal the target for 11 + Power x 2"},{"id":"cure-touch-ii","name":"Cure Touch II","costLabel":"2 AP, 5 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"5","otherCosts":"","range":"Touch","requirement":"","keywords":["Healing","Spell"],"description":"You Heal the target for 22 + (4 x Power)"},{"id":"cure-water","name":"Cure Water","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 RP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"15 ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Healing","Spell"],"description":"You cast this ability on water within range, healing a target within 30ft for 11 + Power x 2. You can use either AP or RP for the cost of this ability."},{"id":"cursed-evil-eye","name":"Cursed Evil Eye","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Mystic Eye","Upkeep","Blanketing"],"description":"You open your Cursed Mystic Eye that curses everything in sight.\n\nAll targets in a 90 degree cone up to range must make a save against your Potency or take Light Dark(Curse) damage.\n\nUpkeep: 1 AP. When you pay the upkeep cost, you may repeat this attack."},{"id":"cut-away","name":"Cut Away","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You are the target of an ability that forces you to make a save.","keywords":[],"description":"Instead of rolling a save normally, you may make a Precise Attack against the Potency of the ability instead. If your accuracy roll beats the Potency, you are treated as having passed the save."},{"id":"cut-magic","name":"Cut Magic","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"","keywords":["Overcharge"],"description":"You make a Heavy Attack against a temporary magic effect. If your accuracy roll is equal or higher than the Potency of the effect, the effect is removed.\n\nOvercharge: You may spend 1 additional AP to turn the Heavy attack into a Precise attack instead."},{"id":"cyclone","name":"Cyclone","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Spell","Wind"],"description":"All targets in a 15x15 ft area must make a save against your Potency or be knocked airborne for 10ft, falling Prone once they land."},{"id":"dark-barrier","name":"Dark Barrier","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Dark","Full Pierce","Shield"],"description":"You and up to 4 other willing allies within range take Light Dark damage. Afterwards they gain temporary HP until end of encounter equal to double the damage taken.\n\nYou may choose to ignore Dark resistance or damage reduction on your allies for this ability."},{"id":"dark-bolt","name":"Dark Bolt","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Dark","Half Pierce","Full Pierce"],"description":"You fire a bolt of darkness at a target, making a Light Attack that deals Dark Damage. You may take true damage equal to your Power + 3 to give this ability Full Pierce."},{"id":"dark-healing","name":"Dark Healing","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Dark","Full Pierce","Healing"],"description":"You take Light (1 AP) or Heavy damage (2 AP), then heal a target within range an amount equal to damage taken.\n\nYou may choose to ignore Dark resistance or damage reduction on yourself for this damage."},{"id":"darkness","name":"Darkness","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Concentration","Spell","Stealth","Blinded"],"description":"You conjure a 15x15ft area of pure darkness within range. The darkness blocks line of sight. Targets inside of or within 5ft of the Darkness can only see up to 5ft into or out of Darkness. In addition, any targets within the Darkness that do not have Darkvision or a similar ability that lets them see in darkness are considered Blinded 2 (nightvision does not apply).\n\nThis lasts for up to 10 minutes and you may end this effect for 0 AP.\n\nThe mana cost of this ability is reduced by 2 during the night."},{"id":"darkvision","name":"Darkvision","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Touch","requirement":"","keywords":["Stealth"],"description":"You touch an ally and share your Darkvision with them until the end of the encounter, letting them see up 60ft in the darkness."},{"id":"darkvision--passive-","name":"Darkvision (passive)","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You gain 60ft darkvision, allowing you to see perfectly in the dark even without a source of light."},{"id":"deadly-venom","name":"Deadly Venom","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Weapon Range","requirement":"Must be made with a melee weapon or with a throwing weapon or set of missiles.","keywords":["Poison","Toxic"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target. On damage, you worsen the target’s Toxic, letting it stack and adding +1 stack to it. Stacks a maximum of 3 times.\n\nA Toxic with more than 1 stack deals damage at the end of the target’s turn rather than the start."},{"id":"death-mark","name":"Death Mark","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"Enemy is surprised.","keywords":["Encounter Start"],"description":"You mentally mark a target for death by applying Death Mark, opening them up to your Assassin abilities. When you reduce a character marked by Death Mark to 0 HP or lower, you may move up to your Speed and take the Hide action for 0 RP. This movement does not provoke attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"death-perception","name":"Death Perception","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"","keywords":["Mystic Eye"],"description":"You can assess the approximate HP percentage of all living units within range until the end of combat. (The DM should enable health bars for the unit). Only affects unit in your line of sight when you use this ability, if more enemies join the fight later they are not affected until you use this ability again."},{"id":"decipher-magic","name":"Decipher Magic","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"","keywords":["Hacking"],"description":"You may start a skill challenge against a magic effect you can see in an attempt to understand it.\n\nYou are able to disable tier 1 bounded fields with this ability."},{"id":"deckbreaker","name":"Deckbreaker","costLabel":"1 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"One-Handed weapons only.","keywords":["Offstep","Lock On"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target. On damage, you inflict Offstep on the target for the next attack against it.\n\nIf the target is inflicted with Stagger, the mana cost of this is reduced by 1.\n\nIf you're under the effects of Exposing Edge, this attack gains Lock On."},{"id":"deconstruction","name":"Deconstruction","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":["Errand"],"description":"By spending an Interlude Point, you deconstruct a basic item into materials. You gain 500 matching crafting material per ingot or block used in the item. If the item does not use ingots, you instead get 1 matching crafting material per clim value of the item.\n\nRegardless of the material used in the item, you will only gain the base price amount even if using upgraded materials and all alloys and upgrades are lost. You can deconstruct up to 5 basic items for 1 interlude point.\n\nAlternatively instead of 1 basic item, you can transmute up to 1000u of random junk into up to 250u of usable basic (ie: Iron, Pine etc) Blacksmithing Materials, Armorsmithing Materials, Carpentry Materials, Calligraphy Material, Magical Fuel Materials or Medical Materials units at a 4:1 ratio.\n\nYou can also use Deconstruction as an Errand Action, but the deconstruction limit is reduced to 1 basic item instead of 5 basic items."},{"id":"decree","name":"Decree","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Mystic Eye","Mind Affecting"],"description":"You command the target to Approach or Flee.\n\nThe target must make a Save or be forced to obey your chosen command, immediately moving up to their speed towards you (if you chose approach) or away from you (if you chose flee)."},{"id":"defensive-flexibility","name":"Defensive Flexibility","costLabel":"0 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be the target of an attack and must have reacted to the previous attack against you with the Dodge or Block action.","keywords":["Circuit"],"description":"You react to the triggering attack with the opposite reaction you used to meet the requirement of this ability. (IE if you used Dodge as your last reaction, you use the Block reaction for this).\n\nThe first time each encounter your RP goes below half your maximum RP, you regain the Circuit benefit on this."},{"id":"delay-time","name":"Delay Time","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Stealth"],"description":"You choose one or more negative effects on the target that would trigger at the start or end of their turn. They trigger on the turn after the turn they would normally trigger instead.\n\nYou may only delay an effect once, but you are able to delay Stasis even though the target is normally immune to all abilities.\n\nStart of turn effects still trigger at the start of the turn and end of turn effects still trigger at the end of the turn."},{"id":"delayed-hit","name":"Delayed Hit","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You make a Heavy Attack against the target, but don’t deal damage. On hit, even if it was guarded, the target takes Heavy Damage at the start of your next turn. (This delayed damage is calculated of the target’s Guard at the time it’s applied, not when the attack hit)"},{"id":"demonblood-regeneration","name":"Demonblood Regeneration","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You heal faster than those of other races. You gain the following benefits:\n\n- When using Grit, you heal for 6 HP instead.\n- When using Second Wind, you heal for an additional 3 HP."},{"id":"dense-frame","name":"Dense Frame","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"When you would be pushed back by an effect, you are shoved for 5ft less."},{"id":"dense-mana","name":"Dense Mana","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You augment your next ability, increasing the Potency of your next ability by 2."},{"id":"density-break","name":"Density Break","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Gravity","Full Pierce"],"description":"You make a Precise attack that deals damage equal to the target’s Toughness."},{"id":"despair-of-isolation","name":"Despair of Isolation","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Mist of the Vale must be active.","keywords":["Song","Mind Affecting","Sound"],"description":"Everyone within your Mist of the Vale becomes Slowed until the end of their next turn. They must also make a Save or become Dazed until the end of their next turn. On failure, they also cannot target allies with friendly effects while in the mist until the end of their next turn.\n\nYou may spend 1 Mana to exclude allies from this attack."},{"id":"destroy","name":"Destroy","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Mystic Eye","Circuit"],"description":"The target must make a Save or take Heavy Dark(Curse) damage."},{"id":"destroy-ground","name":"Destroy Ground","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You destroy natural earth with magical speed, creating up to a 10ft x 10ft x 10ft hole in most natural earth. Those caught in the effect may spend 1 RP to Sidestep 5ft out of the effect. All caught in the effect fall down 10ft into the hole and take falling damage as normal.\n\nThe spell requires natural ground to be below the touching surface to function. It may work on the bottom floor of a house, but will fail if used higher up or in some dungeons"},{"id":"destroying-angel","name":"Destroying Angel","costLabel":"4 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Poison","Spell","Healing"],"description":"You make a Precise Attack against an enemy unit within range, dealing Poison Damage. On damage, if the enemy is a Grunt, they are immediately reduced to negative their Max HP and die. On Killing Blow, the current host of Spore Symbiote is healed for 5 + Power x 2."},{"id":"detailed-finish","name":"Detailed Finish","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"This is your last crafting dice. Costs 1 Crafting Dice.","keywords":[],"description":"Make a crafting check. Upgrade the dice to 2d8."},{"id":"deus-vult","name":"Deus Vult","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"A target of your Holy Order.","keywords":[],"description":"Can use with active Holy Orders. Your next basic attack or Ave Maria against your Holy Order gains the Lock On and Shieldbreaker keywords against your Holy Order."},{"id":"devastating-strike","name":"Devastating Strike","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Target must have 0 RP remaining.","keywords":["Full Pierce","Sure Hit"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target."},{"id":"devastating-strike-ii","name":"Devastating Strike II","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"The target has no RP.","keywords":["Sure Hit","Full Pierce"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target. The dice are maximized instead of rolling."},{"id":"devastating-strike-iii","name":"Devastating Strike III","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Target must have 0 RP remaining and must be marked by Death Mark. One-handed weapons only.","keywords":["Full Pierce","Sure Hit"],"description":"You make a Light (1 AP) or Heavy (2 AP) attack against the target."},{"id":"devil-s-blow","name":"Devil's Blow","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"","keywords":["Full Pierce"],"description":"You make a Heavy attack against the target. This attack does NOT have Full Pierce.\n\nIf you roll a 1 on the accuracy check, you take full pierce damage of same the type as the attack equal to the damage roll of the attack. You also regain the mana spent on this."},{"id":"devil-s-curse","name":"Devil's Curse","costLabel":"0 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"An enemy accuracy check against you rolls a 1.","keywords":["-"],"description":"The attacker takes damage equal to the damage roll of the triggering attack. They cannot Dodge or Block this damage.\n\nDoes not work against Secret Arts, Climax Arts or similar level abilities."},{"id":"dharani--blooming-conciousness","name":"Dharani: Blooming Conciousness","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"20ft","requirement":"Must be in Luminous Form Stance and have 5 stacks of Harmony.","keywords":["Secret Art","Healing"],"description":"You release all gathered harmony as petals of radiant light that spiral outward from your body.\n\nYou consume all Harmony stacks and 1 mana per stack to heal all allies within range for (6 + Your focus) / 2 for each stack consumed.\n\nIf you do not have enough mana for all stacks, this ability instead consumes stacks equal to the mana you can spend."},{"id":"dimensional-armory-expansion","name":"Dimensional Armory Expansion","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Your burden limit for your Dimensional Armory is increased by 4. Ahead of time, you designate one armor, one cloak and one weapon/shield or two weapons or one two-handed weapon that are inside of your Dimensional Armory as a \"dimensional set\", this process takes 15 minutes of concentration. You can only have one dimensional set at a time."},{"id":"dirge-of-despair","name":"Dirge of Despair","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Sound","Song","Upkeep","Mind Affecting"],"description":"All enemies within range must make a save against your Potency or become affected by this Song. While affected, you may subtract 1d4 from a single roll they make until the start of your next turn. You may choose to add this after seeing the roll.\n\nUpkeep: At the start of your next turn and every turn thereafter, you may spend 1 AP to continue this performance. Enemies that successfully made their save, do not have to save again against this continued performance, but those who were affected continue to be affected."},{"id":"disarming-attack","name":"Disarming Attack","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Disarm"],"description":"You may make a Light Attack against the target. On damage, you Disarm the target until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"disarming-shot","name":"Disarming Shot","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Disarm"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target. If the attack beat the passive evasion of the target (before Dodge bonuses), you Disarm the target until the start of your next turn. The target may spend 1 RP to avoid the disarm effect. This is in addition to any RP the target may spend to avoid the attack itself."},{"id":"discern-immunities","name":"Discern Immunities","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"","keywords":["Quick"],"description":"You look at a single target and glean what its resistances are until the end of the encounter. When you are about to use an ability with a negative effect that would be passively negated by the target, you become aware of this and may cancel your action.\n\nDoes not apply if the target has an active ability that can remove it, such as a paladin’s Paragon of Virtue for example."},{"id":"discipline","name":"Discipline","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You have at least 5 skill points in the called for skill. Use when you need to roll a skill check.","keywords":[],"description":"Instead of rolling, you can choose instead to accept 10 as the dice value for a skill check."},{"id":"dispel-magic","name":"Dispel Magic","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Arcane","Dispel","Spell"],"description":"You dispel a temporary magic effect from an area or target. All non-permanent effects within range that are created by an ability with the Spell or Enchantment keyword are affected. Spells that do not have a time limit listed or create a permanent effect such as a Geomancer's fissure are not affected. Bounded Fields and Secret Arts cannot be removed with Dispel Magic."},{"id":"disrupt-ki","name":"Disrupt Ki","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Unarmed Strike","Mystic Eye"],"description":"You may make a Light Attack against the target. On damage, if they have any Concentration ability active, that ability immediately ends as if they had chosen to drop it."},{"id":"divine-barrage","name":"Divine Barrage","costLabel":"2 AP, -1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"-1","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target and instruct others to follow your lead.\n\nX allies other than you within 30ft of you may also make a Light attack against the same target."},{"id":"divine-guard","name":"Divine Guard","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be transformed by Divine Release and targeted by an attack.","keywords":[],"description":"You may immediately use the Block action to guard against the triggering attack with a +5 bonus to Guard."},{"id":"divine-might","name":"Divine Might","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Must be transformed by Divine Release.","keywords":[],"description":"You make a Light Attack against the target."},{"id":"divine-providence","name":"Divine Providence","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Rage"],"description":"When you use this ability you choose one of the following effects:\n\nDivine Protection: You are protected from harm through divine protection, gaining 100 damage reduction against the next source of damage you take.\n\nFortune: When used for this effect, this ability becomes Instant. You may reroll your last d20 and take the new result.\n\nHealth: You heal someone (or yourself) within touching distance for 15 hp.\n\nLight: You summon a bright light at your position that shines a bright light up to 30ft around you. You may detonate this light by spending 0 AP to Daze all enemies within its range.\n\nOnce you use this ability, you may not use it again until after a rest."},{"id":"divine-release","name":"Divine Release","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Transformation","Rage"],"description":"Demons can feed on their own lifeforce to release a brilliant display of divine powers. Horns can elongate, fangs might grow, eyes glow and even wings can sprout as the Demon realizes their Divine Roots.\n\nUpkeep: 11 HP\n\nYou transform into your new form and take 11 true damage. You may end this form at any time by spending 0 RP. While the form lasts you gain the following benefits:\n\nFallen Guard: When you take the Block basic action, you gain an additional +5 to guard.\nFallen Alacrity: You gain +5 movement speed and the ability to fly.\nFallen Might: You gain +1 AP at the start of your turn.\nFallen Conviction: When you are reduced to 0 HP, you do not enter the downed state. You still receive the wounded status. While at or below 0 HP, the upkeep for this ability is increased to 16. If you end this ability while at or below 0 HP, you are immediately placed into the downed state. If your HP become equal to or lower than your negative maximum HP, you are immediately incapacitated and this ability ends.\n\nOnce you use this ability, you cannot do so again until you finish an interlude rest phase."},{"id":"divine-smite","name":"Divine Smite","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Target has your Mark of Justice on them.","keywords":["Full Pierce"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack that deals Holy Damage against the target. If your target’s HP is lower than the max damage your attack would deal, this attack gains Full Pierce and does maximum damage instead of rolling.\n\nThis calculation only involves your base damage (Base weapon damage + the power). Any other effects added to the damage such as Heavy Blade's bonus damage, Anathema on target etc do not affect the calculation and aren't maximized."},{"id":"divine-smite-ii","name":"Divine Smite II","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack that deals Holy Damage against the target. On damage, you may give yourself or an ally within 30ft temporary HP equal your 5+Power until the end of the encounter."},{"id":"divine-storm","name":"Divine Storm","costLabel":"3 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Target has your Mark of Justice on them.","keywords":["Scatter"],"description":"You make a Heavy attack with your weapon against the target of your Mark of Justice.\n\nYou then make a Light attack against all other enemies within 5ft and push them back 10ft, regardless of whether the attack hit or not. This light attack is not made with your weapon and always does the damage type of your god (as determined by your Holy weapon key ability)."},{"id":"divining-petalfall","name":"Divining Petalfall","costLabel":"1 Strike Dice","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"1 Strike Dice","range":"","requirement":"Must be in a gathering session.","keywords":[],"description":"Make a gathering check with a +5 bonus. If the final dice value is even, add it to Node Points. If it’s odd, add it to Lucky Points."},{"id":"doctor-jekyll","name":"Doctor Jekyll","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Encounter Start"],"description":"You draw and either drink a Potion or Elixir, or throw one to a willing ally within 30ft who immediately drinks it."},{"id":"dog-form","name":"Dog Form","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Transformation"],"description":"You transform into your Dog Form, becoming a medium size dog. You lose 2 guard and 4 block, but gain a +1 Size bonus to Evasion and Dodge.\n\nWhile in Dog Form, you can only make melee unarmed attacks and you are considered proficient in these attacks.\n\nIf you take damage in Dog Form, you immediately return to your normal form. You can dispel this form for 0 AP or 1 RP."},{"id":"doom","name":"Doom","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Mystic Eye"],"description":"The target must make a Save. On failure, they take additional light damage the next time they take damage that isn't true damage."},{"id":"double-elements","name":"Double Elements","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Quick"],"description":"Your next Elemental Strike or Elemental Sweep ability used this turn may add in the effect of another element. This element must be one you have mastered and different from the effect that's already dealt by the attack."},{"id":"double-palm-strike","name":"Double Palm Strike","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Bajiquan","Unarmed Strike"],"description":"You attack the target for Light Damage. On damage, the target is moved up to 15ft away from you (At least 5 feet)."},{"id":"double-punch","name":"Double Punch","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Must not have made a dual wield attack this turn.","keywords":["Unarmed Strike"],"description":"You may make two Light Attacks against the same target.\n\nYou may not make a dual wield attack until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"double-slam","name":"Double Slam","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Two-Handed weapons only","keywords":["Unbalanced"],"description":"You may make up to 2 Light attacks against the target, paying 1 AP and 1 Mana for each. On damage of either hit, the target becomes Unbalanced. If the target is already unbalanced, they are knocked prone.\n\nIf you are wielding only 1 Two-Handed weapon, you are limited to 1 attack."},{"id":"downburst","name":"Downburst","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"720ft","requirement":"Target must be Flying.","keywords":["Lock On","Spell","Wind"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack that deals Wind damage against the target. On damage, the target immediately plummets to the ground and takes falling damage. This falling damage cannot be negated through the use of abilities that would normally negate falling damage."},{"id":"downburst-ii","name":"Downburst II","costLabel":"2 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"2","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"720ft","requirement":"Target is knocked airborne or is Flying.","keywords":["Lock On","Spell","Wind"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack that deals Wind damage against the target. On damage, the target immediately plummets to the ground and takes falling damage. This falling damage cannot be negated through the use of abilities that would normally negate falling damage."},{"id":"draconic-presence","name":"Draconic Presence","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You gain a +10 bonus to Negotiation and Intimidation checks against Grunts and against Heroics that have a lower Spirit Core than you."},{"id":"dragon-breaks-the-ranks","name":"Dragon Breaks The Ranks","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"80ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Fire","Spell","Sidestep"],"description":"You gain Flight and surround yourself in fire, then Sidestep to a point in a direct line. You destroy low cover you pass through, though the GM may rule that some cover is too sturdy to be destroyed. In either case, you continue until you reach the target and may make a single melee Heavy Attack against an enemy in range with your weapon. Any other characters in your path may spend 1 RP to move 5ft out of your charge or take Light Fire Damage.\n\nIf you have an element mastered, you may change the Fire damage of this ability to the element you have mastered.\n\nThis spell does not provoke attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"dragon-s-breath","name":"Dragon's Breath","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Water","Lightning","Fire","Arcane","Wind","Frost","Scatter","Safe"],"description":"You exhale a devastating breath attack, making a ranged Light attack against all targets in a 30ft long 60 degree cone. This attack deals the same type of damage as your element chosen in Ryujin's Mastery."},{"id":"dragonfire-dive","name":"Dragonfire Dive","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"Polearm only.","keywords":["Fire","Jump","Blanketing"],"description":"You jump to the target, not provoking any attacks of opportunity, and attacking the target plus all other creatures within 5ft of the target for Heavy Fire Damage."},{"id":"dramatic-death","name":"Dramatic Death","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You've taken damage and that damage is done resolving.","keywords":[],"description":"You fall prone and may immediately use the Play Dead action. You may use your Art(Mime) for this roll instead of Deception.\n\nAt the start of your turn, you may stop playing dead and immediately stand up from prone for 0 AP."},{"id":"draw_elements","name":"Draw Elements","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"-","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You may choose an element. Until the start of your next turn, you are considered to have mastered that element."},{"id":"draw-elements-ii","name":"Draw Elements II","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Quick"],"description":"You may choose an element. Until the start of your next turn, you are considered to have mastered that element."},{"id":"draw-in","name":"Draw-In","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Polearm only.","keywords":["Combo"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target. On damage, they are pulled up to 5ft towards you.\n\nCombo: If used after Lunge, the range of this attack and the pullback distance are doubled. This consumes the Lunge effect."},{"id":"driftwind-evasion","name":"Driftwind Evasion","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You take the Dodge action against the attack and gain a Windflow bonus to your Dodge equal to your Windflow stacks.\n\nAfterwards, you lose all Windflow stacks."},{"id":"drink_to_battle","name":"Drink to Battle","costLabel":"2 AP or Encounter Start action","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"2 AP or Encounter Start action","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Encounter Start"],"description":"You drink some Alcohol in preparation for a battle, granting you 1 stack of Tipsy."},{"id":"dualcast","name":"Dualcast","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be used immediately after successfully using an ability with the spell keyword.","keywords":["Arcane"],"description":"You immediately repeat the last used ability with the same target. Any cost must be paid as normal."},{"id":"duelist-blow","name":"Duelist Blow","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You make a Heavy Attack against the target. Your next Block or Dodge reaction against that target costs 0 RP. This benefit disappears when you use an RP ability against a target other than the target of this ability."},{"id":"dullahan-s-mount","name":"Dullahan's Mount","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["-"],"description":"You conjure up a black horse that becomes part of you. You immediately mount when using this ability and upon dismounting, the horse vanishes. While mounted, your movement speed is increased by 30ft and you are considered a large creature, but you may only move in a straight line. When attempting to move through 5ft wide spaces, it is considered difficult terrain for you. You also suffer a -10 penalty to most finesse athletics checks as well as climbing and swimming checks while mounted.\n\nAny attack against the horse is considered an attack against you instead. As the horse is considered part of you, any displacement or teleport abilities move the horse alongside with you. You may dismount by spending 0 AP."},{"id":"duplicate","name":"Duplicate","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"An enemy in range casts a Spell","keywords":["Spell","Arcane"],"description":"You attempt to analyze the spell and duplicate it. After the triggering spell resolves, immediately cast a copy of it. You must select a valid target for this copy, pay any additional mana cost originally on the spell as well as pay any costs that are not AP or RP. Failure to do so will make the duplicated spell fizzle, dissipating the magic harmlessly into the air.\n\nUpon successfully copying the spell, it resolves with the same damage and effects as the original spell, though using your stats to resolve them.\n\nThe cost is 1 RP for a 0-2 AP spell or 2 RP for a 3-4 AP spell. Spells with a higher cost cannot be duplicated.\n\nSecret Arts and Esoteric Arts also cannot be duplicated and upon attempting to do so, this ability is canceled and any cost refunded. Unique spells by heroic or boss enemies may also be impossible to duplicate (GM's discretion)."},{"id":"dust-kick","name":"Dust Kick","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"Must be within 5ft of the ground. An ally or you are being attacked by an enemy in range.","keywords":["Blinded"],"description":"You kick the ground in front of you, causing a veil of dust to appear. The target becomes Blinded 3 until the attack resolves. If the triggering attack misses, you kick the target and may push it 5ft into any horizontal direction.\n\nIf under the effects of Exposing Edge, you apply Blinded 5 instead."},{"id":"eagle-hunt","name":"Eagle Hunt","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"-","requirement":"-","keywords":["Combo","Jump"],"description":"You leap up to 30ft into the air and then horizontally up to twice your Speed, this movement does not provoke attacks of opportunity. You may use Silentium at any point during the movement, gaining the Combo bonus."},{"id":"earth-armor","name":"Earth Armor","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Enchantment","Aid","Earth"],"description":"You touch a willing ally’s armor and enchant it with earthen power. Until the end of the encounter, it grants a +1 guard and +4 block bonus."},{"id":"earth-infusion","name":"Earth Infusion","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Type","Earth"],"description":"You surround a willing target in mud and rocks, changing their typing to Earth II.\n\nAs an Earth II type, they take half damage from Lightning and Earth damage or attacks with the Lightning or Earth keyword unless that attack deals true damage. They take 50% more damage from Wind damage or attacks with the Wind keyword."},{"id":"earth-shield","name":"Earth Shield","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"An ally within range is the target of a melee attack and/or physical attack.","keywords":["Spell","Aid","Shield","Earth"],"description":"You grant the target 1 RP they must spend on the Block action against the triggering attack. They gain a bonus to their Block for this action equal to your focus x 2."},{"id":"earthen-divide","name":"Earthen Divide","costLabel":"3 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Earth"],"description":"You create a wall up to 20ft high, 5ft wide and 20ft long in a straight line. Each Segment of the wall has HP equal to 20 + Focus.\n\nOvercharge: You may spend X mana to increase the length by 20 x Xft."},{"id":"earthen-guardian","name":"Earthen Guardian","costLabel":"1 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"In Steadfast Earth Stance, ally within range is the target of an attack.","keywords":["Sidestep","Jump"],"description":"You jump and sidestep towards the attacked ally and the triggering attack resolves against you instead. You automatically take the Block action against this attack."},{"id":"eclipse-breaker","name":"Eclipse Breaker","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Setup","Scatter"],"description":"You make a Heavy attack against all targets in a 15x15ft line.\n\nYou must choose the line direction when starting the ability."},{"id":"efficient-strike","name":"Efficient Strike","costLabel":"1 Strike Dice","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"1 Strike Dice","range":"","requirement":"Must in a gathering session.","keywords":[],"description":"Make a gathering check. If this maxes node points, all overflow is converted into lucky points."},{"id":"elbow-uppercut","name":"Elbow Uppercut","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Bajiquan","Combo","Unarmed Strike"],"description":"You attack the target for Heavy Damage. Combo: If used after an ability with the Unarmed Strike keyword, this ability gains Full Pierce."},{"id":"elemental-bolt","name":"Elemental Bolt","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Burning","Soaked","Static","Slow","Sunder","Illumination","Blinded"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target. The damage type is chosen at the type of casting and must be that of an element you have mastered.\n\nOn damage, inflict an effect based on the damage type of this attack:\n\nArcane: The target loses 1 Mana\nFire: The target becomes Burning X, where X is your Focus x 3.\nWater: The target becomes Soaked X, where X is your Focus, until they take lightning damage.\nLightning: The target becomes Static X, where X equals your Focus x 3.\nFrost: The target becomes Slowed until the start of your next turn.\nEarth: The target becomes afflicted with Sunder X, where X equals your Focus, for the next damage they take.\nWind: You push the target 10ft.\nHoly: The target becomes inflicted with Illumination X, where X is your focus / 2.\nDark: The target becomes inflicted with Blinded X, where X is your focus, for their next attack."},{"id":"elemental-burst","name":"Elemental Burst","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"Can be used after dealing elemental damage that does not contain the Full Pierce or Sure Hit keywords.","keywords":["Spell"],"description":"You cause your attack to burst into the target causing them to take additional damage of that element equal to 2d4 + Focus."},{"id":"elemental-convergence","name":"Elemental Convergence","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Encounter Start"],"description":"You may choose 1 element from Arcane, Fire, Water, Frost, Wind, Lightning or Earth. Until the end of the encounter, you are considered to have mastered that element.\n\nYou may swap this element once per turn for 1 Mana."},{"id":"elemental-mastery--dark","name":"Elemental Mastery: Dark","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You gain Elemental Mastery: Dark"},{"id":"elemental-mastery--fire","name":"Elemental Mastery: Fire","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You gain Elemental Mastery: Fire"},{"id":"elemental-mastery--frost","name":"Elemental Mastery: Frost","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You gain Elemental Mastery: Frost"},{"id":"elemental-mastery--holy","name":"Elemental Mastery: Holy","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You gain Elemental Mastery: Holy"},{"id":"elemental-mastery--lightning","name":"Elemental Mastery: Lightning","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You gain Elemental Mastery: Lightning."},{"id":"elemental-strike","name":"Elemental Strike","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Burning","Soaked","Static","Slow","Blinded"],"description":"You make a Light Attack against the target. On damage, your attack applies an additional effect based on one of your attack's damage type. (If you are able to have multiple damage types on the attack such as through Holy weapon, you may pick any of the effects).\n\nArcane: The target loses 1 mana.\nFire: The target becomes Burning X, where X equals your Power x 3.\nWater: The target becomes Soaked X, where X equals your power/2 (rounded down), until they take Lightning damage.\nLightning: The target is afflicted with Static X, where X equals your Power x 3\nEarth/Frost: The target becomes Slowed until the start of your next turn.\nWind: You may push the target back 10ft.\nHoly: You gain temporary hit points equal to your Power + 5.\nDark: The target becomes Blinded 5 until after their next attack."},{"id":"elemental-sweep","name":"Elemental Sweep","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"","keywords":["Burning","Soaked","Static","Slow","Blinded","Blanketing"],"description":"You may make a Light Attack against all enemies within range. On damage, your attack applies an additional effect based on one of your attack's damage type. (If you are able to have multiple damage types on the attack such as through Holy weapon, you may pick any of the effects).\n\nArcane: The target loses 1 mana.\nFire: The target becomes Burning X, where X equals your Power x 3.\nWater: The target becomes Soaked X, where X equals your power/2 (rounded down), until they take Lightning damage.\nLightning: The target is afflicted with Static X, where X equals your Power x 3.\nEarth/Frost: The target becomes Slowed until the start of your next turn.\nWind: You may push the target back 10ft.\nHoly: You gain temporary hit points equal to your Power+5.\nDark: The target becomes Blinded 5 until after their next attack."},{"id":"emergency-maneuvers","name":"Emergency Maneuvers","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"When you fail a check when operating an airship, you may use this to reroll the check. You must accept the new result and cannot reroll it again."},{"id":"emergency-recall","name":"Emergency Recall","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"Your summon from Summon Animal is the target of an attack.","keywords":[],"description":"You give your summon 100 Damage Reduction against the attack. Afterwards, if it is still alive, it is immediately unsummoned."},{"id":"emergency-shield","name":"Emergency Shield","costLabel":"1 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Shield","Spell"],"description":"The target gains temporary HP equal to 7 + Power."},{"id":"empower-mana-shield","name":"Empower Mana Shield","costLabel":"1 AP, -1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"-1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You spend X mana to add X*8 to the value of your mana shield until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"empty-body","name":"Empty Body","costLabel":"0 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You failed a saving throw.","keywords":[],"description":"You may reroll the failed saving throw and must accept the new result."},{"id":"en-dama","name":"En-dama","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Hiding","Stealth"],"description":"You throw a smoke bomb on the ground within range that blocks line of sight in a 5ft radius (15x15 area total) of where it was thrown. Targets inside or within 5ft of the smoke can only see up to 5ft into or out of the smoke.\n\nIf you’re inside of it at the point it's thrown, you may immediately take the Hide action.\n\nThe smoke lasts until the start of your next turn. When it ends, if you are inside your smoke, you may immediately move up to your speed and you are considered hidden up until you finish that movement. If you end your movement in cover, you keep being Hidden from people you have cover from."},{"id":"enduring-warmth","name":"Enduring Warmth","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You can emit comforting heat within 30feet that counters the effects of most cold weather. You can activate or deactivate this heat every 1 second."},{"id":"energy-drain","name":"Energy Drain","costLabel":"0 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Dark"],"description":"You deal Light true damage to a willing ally other than yourself. You gain Haste, which gives you 2 AP for the rest of this turn. A target can only be affected by haste once per turn."},{"id":"envenom-weapon","name":"Envenom Weapon","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Enchantment","Stealth"],"description":"You enchant your weapon with a minor venom, making your attacks deal 1 additional full pierce Poison damage when you hit an enemy."},{"id":"escape_artist","name":"Escape Artist","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 RP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You are grappled.","keywords":[],"description":"You immediately escape the grapple by twisting and kicking. May be used by spending either AP or RP."},{"id":"eternal-mirane-cage","name":"Eternal Mirane Cage","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"Use when an ally attack would kill a target and target is not an ally.","keywords":["Frost","Spell"],"description":"Instead of killing the target, they are reduced to negative their Max HP +1. The target is encased in Magical Ice for 10 years, rooted on the location and cannot be moved. The Ice never melts despite temperature and can only be dispelled by Higher Order Magic (such as a Divine Arms), or by you. The Spell effect ends if you die. You can extend the duration of the Frost by 10 years for every 2 mana spent."},{"id":"eternal-vigil","name":"Eternal Vigil","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"While in statue mode and sleeping, you make perception checks as if you were awake."},{"id":"evasive-maneuver","name":"Evasive Maneuver","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Sidestep","Stealth"],"description":"You Sidestep 5ft in any direction.\n\nWhen used on your turn, you may spend 1 mana and 0 AP on this ability instead."},{"id":"evil-eye-of-death","name":"Evil Eye of Death","costLabel":"4 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"Target must be a grunt.","keywords":["Mystic Eye","Upkeep"],"description":"You open your Mystic Eye, focus it on a single target and they instantly die.\n\nUpkeep: 3 AP. When you pay the upkeep cost, you may repeat this attack against a new target."},{"id":"evil-eye-of-fear","name":"Evil Eye of Fear","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Mystic Eye","Upkeep","Fear","Mind Affecting"],"description":"You open your Mystic Eye and inflict fear on everything in sight.\n\nAll targets in a 90 degree cone up to range must make a save against your potency or become Shaken until the start of your next turn.\n\nUpkeep: 1 AP. When you pay the upkeep cost, you may repeat this attack."},{"id":"evil-eye-of-lethargy","name":"Evil Eye of Lethargy","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Mystic Eye","Upkeep","Slow"],"description":"You open your Mystic Eye and inflict lethargy on everything in sight.\n\nAll targets in a 90 degree cone up to range become Slowed until the start of your next turn, unless they spent 1 RP to resist the effect.\n\nUpkeep: 1 AP. When you pay the upkeep cost, you may repeat this attack."},{"id":"excavation-crash","name":"Excavation Crash","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"","keywords":["-"],"description":"Choose one adjacent location 5ft from the target. The target may immediately use a move action for 0 RP to move there if they wish, you cannot make an attack of opportunity during Excavation Crash. If the target does not move to the location, make a heavy attack against them."},{"id":"execute-heretic","name":"Execute Heretic","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Target must be downed.","keywords":["Sure Hit","Full Pierce"],"description":"You deal damage to the target equal to their max HP."},{"id":"expert-farmer","name":"Expert Farmer","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Greater Infuse Qi\nKeywords: Rapid\nDescription:\nYou infuse one of the planted herbs with Qi, upgrading it from rare to mystic and adding 20 to its difficulty.\n\nBountiful Harvest II\nKeywords: Rapid\nDescription:\nYou bless one of the planted seeds that grants Food units or Alchemy materials. It grants 4 times that amount and you add 10 to its difficulty. Does not stack."},{"id":"expertise-study--armorsmithing-","name":"Expertise Study (Armorsmithing)","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You gain 5 Expertise Points in 2 different armorsmithing crafts. You also gain wielding proficiency in Heavy Armor or Greatshields.\n\nIn addition, you always gain the expertise bonus when crafting an armor for yourself. An armor crafted this way cannot be worn by other creatures and is effectively valued at 0 clim."},{"id":"expertise-study--artificing-","name":"Expertise Study (Artificing)","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You gain 5 expertise points in 3 different Artificing crafts. You also gain one basic weapon proficiency or one specialized weapon proficiency of your choice."},{"id":"expertise-study--blacksmithing-","name":"Expertise Study (Blacksmithing)","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You gain 5 Expertise Points in 3 different blacksmithing crafts. You also gain wielding proficiency in one smithing melee weapon of your choice. You may select specialized weapons with this."},{"id":"expertise-study--carpentry-","name":"Expertise Study (Carpentry)","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You gain 5 Expertise Points in 3 different carpentry crafts. You also gain wielding proficiency in one carpentry weapon of your choice or artifice chainsaws."},{"id":"explosive-advance","name":"Explosive Advance","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Encounter Start"],"description":"You immediately activate Horse Step Acceleration and it becomes active for the entire first round of combat. Immediately make up to 1 AP of movement actions."},{"id":"explosive-ward","name":"Explosive Ward","costLabel":"2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Touch","requirement":"-","keywords":["Bounded Field","Fire","Spell","Scatter"],"description":"A ward that can be placed on a door or medium-sized container of some sort. If other than you knowingly tries to open the door or container in any way (whether normal opening, attacking it etc), the ward triggers creating a loud noise and dealing Heavy Fire Damage to all creatures in a 10ft radius around the container. All items inside the container (if any) also take this damage. Once triggered, the bounded field vanishes. Casting this takes 10 minutes of uninterrupted casting. You may at the time of casting choose a number of people equal to your Focus that can also open the container or door without triggering the ward. If not triggered, Explosive Ward lasts until you remove it. For each Explosive Ward you maintain your maximum mana is reduced by 2. This is considered a tier 2 ward."},{"id":"exposing-edge","name":"Exposing Edge","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Stance","Upkeep"],"description":"You sharpen your blades, enhancing the effects of your debuffs.\n\nUpkeep: You may spend 1 AP or 1 mana to continue the effect."},{"id":"exposing-stab","name":"Exposing Stab","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target. On damage, you may use your Devastating Strike against the target until the end of your turn as if the target had 0 RP."},{"id":"extending-spear","name":"Extending Spear","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"Polearm only.","keywords":["Scatter","Crushing"],"description":"You may make a Light Attack against all targets in a line up to the range."},{"id":"extra-arms","name":"Extra Arms","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Quick"],"description":"Your next interact with object costs 1 less AP."},{"id":"fading-counter","name":"Fading Counter","costLabel":"2 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"2","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Counter","Illusion"],"description":"When the enemy attacks you in melee, they instead attack an illusionary clone, missing you. You may then immediately attack the enemy with a basic Light Melee Attack. You may then move up to 5ft in any direction and this movement does not provoke attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"faerie-eyes--calling","name":"Faerie Eyes: Calling","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Charm","Illusion"],"description":"You activate your Faerie Eyes, charming a target to move their Speed towards you. If your Focus is higher than the target’s the target moves up to its speed towards you. The target immediately stops their movement if they are going to take damage from further movement. Against Grunts, this attack always hits regardless of Focus, costs 0 mana, and the target will continue to move even if it will take damage."},{"id":"faerie-flash","name":"Faerie Flash","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"-","requirement":"-","keywords":["Teleport","Rage"],"description":"You Teleport up to twice your Speed to an unoccupied space that you can see. Can only be used once per encounter."},{"id":"faerie-flash-ii","name":"Faerie Flash II","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"-","requirement":"-","keywords":["Teleport"],"description":"You Teleport up to twice your Speed to an unoccupied space that you can see."},{"id":"faerie-light-eyes---empty","name":"Faerie Light Eyes: Empty","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"Enemy has used the target ability","keywords":["Concentration","Mind Affecting","Illusion"],"description":"You lock eyes with an enemy, casting an illusion onto the target’s mind. Name an ability that the target had previously used in the current encounter. The target forgets the target ability, being unable to use it completely while the Illusion is in effect. This ability cannot target Secret Arts, Climax Arts or Esoteric Arts. Only one target may be under the effect of this illusion at a time. If the target is non-heroic and under the effect of Faerie Light Eyes: Hold Person, instead the target immediately is rendered insane permanently. An insane target takes no further combat actions.\n\nIf used on a grunt under the effects of Hold Person, they do not need to meet the normal requirements for this ability.\n\nDoes not work against Boss type enemies. Some abilities such as those granted by items, passives or racial abilities (such as flight) also cannot be removed by this ability (GM's discretion)."},{"id":"faerie-light-eyes--golden-illusion","name":"Faerie Light Eyes: Golden Illusion","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"A target is affected by Faerie Light Eyes: Empty.","keywords":["Illusion","Mind Affecting"],"description":"You copy the target’s ability that was forgotten and add it to your abilities until the end of the encounter. You must still fulfill all requirements to use this skill. This ability is generated from illusions and gains the keyword, Illusion. You can only have one Golden Illusion ability at a time.\n\nIf the target stops being affected by Empty, you lose your Golden Illusion ability."},{"id":"faerie-light-eyes--hold-person","name":"Faerie Light Eyes: Hold Person","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"Target must be a grunt and have eyes.","keywords":["Illusion","Mind Affecting","Stun"],"description":"You gaze into the target’s eyes and stun them for 1 turn, reducing their AP and RP to 0. While stunned, the target can also not take any actions."},{"id":"faerie-light-eyes--time-dilation","name":"Faerie Light Eyes: Time Dilation","costLabel":"1 RP, -1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"-1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You are the target of a single-target attack.","keywords":[],"description":"Flooding your eyes with magic, you cast a self Illusion causes time slow down. You use the Dodge action with a Dodge bonus equal to 2X."},{"id":"faithful-shield","name":"Faithful Shield","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Overcharge"],"description":"You may use Shelter once at 0 RP cost if the target is your Soulmate. This effect lasts until the start of your next turn.\n\nOvercharge: You may spend 4 AP on this ability to instead gain 2 free uses of Shelter.\n\nThese free uses ignore the normal limitation of using an ability only once per turn."},{"id":"fan-of-knives","name":"Fan of Knives","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"20ft","requirement":"Throwing Weapon, Set of Missiles or Thrown attack only.","keywords":["Scatter"],"description":"You may make a Light Attack against all enemies in range. This is considered a Ranged Weapon Attack that does not provoke attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"farming-basics","name":"Farming Basics","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Spiritual Ground\nCost: 1 Interlude Point\nDescription:\nYou infuse the land with your spiritual energy, creating up to 10 plots of land suitable for farming. These plots of lands can grow food and herbs at an accelerated rate and allow the planting of tier 1 rare herbs.\n\nAll plots of land must be filled with seeds before they begin growing.\n\nAfter creating a spiritual ground, you may immediately use Sow Seeds in it for 0 IP.\n\nYou can only have 1 spiritual ground at the same time.\n\nSow Seeds\nCost: 1 Interlude Point\nDescription:\nYou may plant seeds in plots of land. You may plant 1 set of seeds in each plot of land you can work.\n\nHarvest\nCost: 1 Interlude Point\nDescription:\nYou harvest the planted seeds or take care of the plants not ready to be harvested yet. Do a crafting session. Your crafting score is the total value of seeds you can harvest or take care of.\n\nIf your crafting score is not high enough to harvest or take care of all seeds you planted, you must give up on some of the seeds. Starting from the seed with the highest difficulty, you drop seeds until your total crafting score matches or exceeds the total difficulty of the seeds.\n\nInfuse Qi\nKeywords: Rapid\nDescription:\nYou infuse one of the planted herbs with Qi, upgrading it from common to rare and adding 10 to its difficulty.\n\nBountiful Harvest\nKeywords: Rapid\nDescription:\nYou bless one of the planted seeds that grants Food units or Alchemy materials. It grants double that amount and you add 5 to its difficulty. Does not stack."},{"id":"fast-dimensional-equip","name":"Fast Dimensional Equip","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You have a Dimension Armory active.","keywords":["-"],"description":"You summon an item from your dimensional armory into your hand. You can also send a held weapon (not wielded or carried by another creature) under your full control to your Dimensional Armory and swap it with another from your Dimensional Armory.\n\nYou may use 1 RP to activate this ability. If you do, the Mana cost is reduced by 1."},{"id":"fast-hands","name":"Fast Hands","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"-","requirement":"-","keywords":["Quick","Stealth"],"description":"You reduce the AP cost of your next Interact with object action this turn by 1."},{"id":"fast_runner","name":"Fast Runner","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Your base movement speed is 25ft instead of 20ft."},{"id":"feeding-frenzy","name":"Feeding Frenzy","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be under the effects of Blood Frenzy.","keywords":[],"description":"You may use this after reducing an enemy’s hit points to 0 or less.\n\nYou may immediately use your Vampire Bite ability for 0 RP against the enemy you downed."},{"id":"feign-death","name":"Feign Death","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"The first time you enter the Downed state in an encounter, you may use Play Dead as a reaction for 0 RP. In addition, you gain a +10 bonus to playing dead."},{"id":"feigned-retreat","name":"Feigned Retreat","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Sidestep"],"description":"All allies in a 15x15ft square within range may Sidestep up to their speed towards you.\n\nIf they successfully left an enemy’s melee range and are not in an enemy’s melee range after moving, then the first time an enemy enters their melee range before the start of their next turn, they may make an Attack of Opportunity against that enemy."},{"id":"feint","name":"Feint","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"15ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Stealth"],"description":"You target an enemy. If the target is a Grunt or you have higher Agility than the target, then they cannot make an attack of opportunity against you until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"feinting-stab","name":"Feinting Stab","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"At least two enemies within range.","keywords":[],"description":"You make a Heavy attack against the target. If they react to it in any way, you may cancel your attack on them and instead make it against a different enemy in range. Any RP spent by the first target is not refunded."},{"id":"felling-strike","name":"Felling Strike","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Axe, Chainsaw and Giant Scissors Only","keywords":["-"],"description":"Make a heavy attack against a target enemy that is no larger than large size category. On damage, sidestep to any unoccupied space next to the target, of the same elevation as the target, and knockback the target 10ft."},{"id":"fiery-rebirth","name":"Fiery Rebirth","costLabel":"0 RP, 5 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"5","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You’ve suffered a mortal wound.","keywords":["Downed","Blanketing"],"description":"You regain HP until you are at 1 HP, stand up from prone and deal Light full pierce fire damage to all enemies within 5ft of you.\n\nAfter using this ability, the mortal wound condition is removed from you and you cannot use Fiery Rebirth again for the rest of the arc."},{"id":"fight-or-flight","name":"Fight or Flight","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Rage"],"description":"Fight: You immediately gain 2 AP that can be used on basic abilities, but lose 1 RP.\n\nFlight: You immediately gain 1 RP, but recover 2 less AP on your next turn.\n\nYou regain the use of this ability after the Encounter Conclusion phase."},{"id":"fireball","name":"Fireball","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Fire","Spell","Scatter"],"description":"You hurl a Fireball at a 15x15ft area, making a Light Attack that deals Fire Damage against all units in the area."},{"id":"fireball-barrage","name":"Fireball Barrage","costLabel":"3 AP","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Fire","Spell","Scatter"],"description":"You hurl three Fireballs at three separate 15x15ft areas, making a Light Attack that deals Fire Damage against all units in each area. Each unit can only be attacked once per use of this ability, even if hit by multiple fireballs."},{"id":"fireball-ii","name":"Fireball II","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Fire","Overcharge","Spell","Scatter"],"description":"You hurl a Fireball at a 15x15ft area, making a Light Attack that deals Fire Damage against all units in the area. On damage, they become Burning X where X equals your Power x 3 Overcharge: You may spend extra mana to increase the size of the area. Every mana spent increases the size by 5ft."},{"id":"first-response","name":"First Response","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"If you have a Medical Kit, you may use your encounter conclusion to give the Second Wind encounter conclusion effect to someone else. You heal for an additional 1d6+3 (from your Demonblood Regeneration) when doing this."},{"id":"fissure","name":"Fissure","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"Special","keywords":["Spell","Earth"],"description":"You slam the ground and create a 15ft wide fissure up to the target point. Those at the edges of the spell’s range may spend 1 RP to Sidestep 5ft out of the effect. All caught in the effect fall down 20ft into the fissure and take falling damage as normal.\n\nThe spell requires natural ground to be below the touching surface to function. It may work on the bottom floor of a house, but will fail if used higher up or in some dungeons."},{"id":"flame-infusion","name":"Flame Infusion","costLabel":"1 AP, 0 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"0","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Fire","Spell","Type"],"description":"You surround a willing target in searing flames, changing their typing to Fire II. As a Fire II type, they take half damage from Fire and Frost Damage or attacks with the Fire or Frost keywords unless that attack deals true damage. They take 50% more damage from Water Damage or attacks with the Water keyword. While the ward lasts, they also gain immunity to Burning. The ward lasts until the end of the encounter or until their type is overwritten by a more powerful type."},{"id":"flame-shield","name":"Flame Shield","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"An ally took damage from a melee attack.","keywords":["Fire","Full Pierce","Shield","Spell","Aid","Sure Hit"],"description":"The attacker immediately takes Light Fire Damage."},{"id":"flame-wall","name":"Flame Wall","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Concentration","Fire","Spell"],"description":"You create a wall of Fire that is 30ft long, 5ft wide and 30ft high. This wall must be a straight line. Anyone passing through the wall or starting their turn in it takes Heavy Fire Damage. The wall lasts for 10 minutes or until canceled. Those in the wall when it is casted, may spend 1 RP to sidestep out of the wall. A person can only take this damage once per round."},{"id":"flame-weapon","name":"Flame Weapon","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Touch","requirement":"-","keywords":["Enchantment"],"description":"You touch one willing ally’s or your own weapon and enchant it with Fire. Until the end of the encounter, the weapon deals Fire Damage and grants a +1 Power Enchantment."},{"id":"flash-bomb","name":"Flash Bomb","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"20ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Daze"],"description":"You throw a Flash Bomb at a point within range that explodes in an 25x25 area centered on that point. All targets within the area must save against Potency or become Dazed."},{"id":"flash-cut","name":"Flash Cut","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Katana only, must be in Iai state.","keywords":["Iaijutsu","Sure Hit"],"description":"You draw your katana and attack with such Speed it becomes impossible to perceive, making a Heavy Attack against the target, after which you resheathe the weapon. This ability does not break the Iai state."},{"id":"flash-star-style-secret-art--twin-nova-pursuit","name":"Flash Star Style Secret Art: Twin Nova Pursuit","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"50ft","requirement":"Light sword, Longsword, Katana, dueling weapon only.","keywords":["Teleport","Secret Art"],"description":"You teleport to the target and then knock them 25ft in any horizontal direction. You then teleport in a straight line to them again and make a Heavy attack. If the attack is responded to with any RP action, knock them straight back 25ft again, teleport in a straight line to them and make another Heavy attack."},{"id":"flash-star-style--photon-line","name":"Flash Star Style: Photon Line","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"25ft","requirement":"Can move 25ft in a straight line. Light sword, longsword, katana, dueling weapon only.","keywords":["Sidestep","Pass","Blanketing"],"description":"You sidestep exactly 25ft in a straight line in any direction and can move over gaps of terrain as long as you end on solid ground. You make a Light attack against all targets that are in your path. If only one target is in your path, make a Heavy attack instead.\n\nIf you were flying at least 10ft above the ground when using this ability, you do not need to end on solid ground."},{"id":"flash-star-style--starlight-crescent-reversal","name":"Flash Star Style: Starlight Crescent Reversal","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"You are targeted by a heavy attack. Light sword, Longsword, Katana, dueling weapon only.","keywords":["Counter"],"description":"You take advantage of the slow windup of the enemy’s attack, countering with a Light attack of your own. You may still Dodge or Block the triggering attack after this counter."},{"id":"flash-star-style--thunderbolt-slash","name":"Flash Star Style: Thunderbolt Slash","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Light sword, Longsword, Katana, dueling weapon only.","keywords":["Combo"],"description":"You slash the target in a thunderbolt pattern, making a 3-hit attack. Make 3 separate Light attacks against the target.\n\nCombo: If used immediately after Flash Star Style: Photon Line, mana cost reduced by 1."},{"id":"flight","name":"Flight","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["-"],"description":"You gain controlled Flight up to your speed. If you take damage while flying higher than 5ft above the ground, your altitude drops by 20ft. If this would reduce your altitude to the point where you touch the ground, you become rooted and cannot fly again until the end of your next turn. If the attack that reduced your HP came from a flying creature other than yourself, you do not lose altitude.\n\nWhen you end your turn within 5ft of the ground, Flight ends."},{"id":"flower-squirt","name":"Flower Squirt","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You press your flower and make a Light attack against the target that deals Water damage. On damage they are Soaked for X, where X equals your Focus until the next time they take Lightning damage."},{"id":"flowing-kick","name":"Flowing Kick","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Combo","Unarmed Strike"],"description":"You make a Heavy Attack against the target. Combo: If used after an unarmed attack misses, reduce the AP cost of this by 1."},{"id":"flowing-wind-strike","name":"Flowing Wind Strike","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Must have moved at least 10ft before using this.","keywords":["Sidestep"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target that deals additional damage equal to double your Windflow stacks. Afterwards, you lose all Windflow stacks.\n\nAfterwards, you may Sidestep 5ft though this movement does not give a Windflow stack."},{"id":"flushing-shot","name":"Flushing Shot","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"Target must be in Low or High cover.","keywords":["Sure Hit"],"description":"You make a Heavy attack against the target. The target may choose to sidestep out of cover from your attack to automatically avoid the attack. Otherwise, the attack gains Sure Hit."},{"id":"fly","name":"Fly","costLabel":"1 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Touch","requirement":"-","keywords":["Spell","Concentration"],"description":"You or the creature you touch gains Fly, which gives them controlled Flight, Hover and their movement speed is doubled while flying until the end of the encounter. If they take damage while flying higher than 5ft above the ground, their altitude drops by 20ft. If this would reduce their altitude to the point where they touch the ground, they become rooted and cannot fly again until the end of their next turn. If the attack that reduced your HP came from an flying creature other than yourself, you do not lose altitude."},{"id":"flyby-attack","name":"Flyby Attack","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be mounted on a flying mount.","keywords":["Sidestep"],"description":"You sidestep up to your speed. At any point during this movement, you may spend 1 AP to make a Light attack with a weapon or spend 2 AP to make a Heavy attack with a weapon. After this attack, you may change the direction in which you spend the rest of your movement."},{"id":"flying-kick","name":"Flying Kick","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"Must have hit a target with Ki Blast in the previous action.","keywords":["Combo","Unarmed Strike"],"description":"You may Sidestep next to the target within range and make a Light Attack against it. You gain Flight for this movement. Combo: Your Strike of Still Water has its AP cost reduced by 1."},{"id":"focused-detonation","name":"Focused Detonation","costLabel":"1 Strike Dice","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"1 Strike Dice","range":"","requirement":"Must in a gathering session.","keywords":[],"description":"Make a gathering check against either Node or Lucky points. If this strike would max out it out, you may instead leave it at 1 away from completion and you gain +1 Strike Dice"},{"id":"focused-power","name":"Focused Power","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be in Inexorable Shadow Stance.","keywords":[],"description":"When you’re about to take the extra damage from Inexorable Shadow Stance, you may choose to maximize the damage instead of rolling. Affects both the self damage and the damage you deal with it."},{"id":"forager-s-eye","name":"Forager's Eye","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"Can see or hear the target category.","keywords":[],"description":"Initiate a sight and sound based search for hidden plants, fungi, creatures or living enemy units in a 30x30 area within range. You become automatically aware of the targeted species of plants, fungi or creatures or you can choose to be aware of all hostile enemy units. You must have line of sight to the target in order to spot them. After revealing the target your Lifebeat Sense gains (if used immediately after):\n\nCombo: If used after Forager's Eye, the AP and mana cost of this is reduced by 1 and the target's location is known to you and your allies until the end of your next turn. This removes Hiding from them."},{"id":"forest-walker","name":"Forest Walker","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You ignore difficult terrain created by vines, foliage and similar natural phenomena."},{"id":"foretell","name":"Foretell","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Divination"],"description":"You receive a vision of the near future. Roll a d20 and store that number. When you or your allies are going to roll that dice type, you can instead replace it with your dice roll, you then lose your Foretell dice. You can only have one Foretell dice at a time, casting Foretell again overwrites the previous dice. Foretel dice last until the end of your next turn.\n\nAfter rolling, you may spend 1 mana to reroll the dice once. After doing this, you can't do so again for this use of the ability."},{"id":"forged-knowledge","name":"Forged Knowledge","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Attack must be made with a weapon you crafted.","keywords":[],"description":"Using your knowledge of weapons, you infuse the strongest point of your weapon with mana and then strike at the perfect angle dealing maximum weapon damage. Maximize one damage dice for the attack."},{"id":"forged-knowledge-ii","name":"Forged Knowledge II","costLabel":"0 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"You or an ally attacked with a weapon you crafted.","keywords":[],"description":"Your bond with the weapon allows you to infuse it with mana at a crucial point. Use when determining attack damage, maximize all weapon dice for that attack."},{"id":"forgemaster-core-crafting","name":"Forgemaster Core Crafting","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Blacksmith’s Modification B\nCost: X Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou add an B-Type modification to the weapon or tool. See the Universal Weapon or Crafting mods page as well as the individual weapon page for details. Each modification has its own cost."},{"id":"forked-lightning","name":"Forked Lightning","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Lightning","Spell"],"description":"You make a Light Attack against two different targets who can be no further than 20ft apart, dealing Lightning Damage and on damage, inflict Static X where X equals your Focus x 2."},{"id":"forward-momentum","name":"Forward Momentum","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Quick"],"description":"Until the start of your next turn, on damage of every melee attack you make, you may push the target back 5ft. You must then move 5ft towards that target (if possible to do safely) without provoking attacks of opportunity. This only works with attacks that target a single enemy."},{"id":"four-field-system","name":"Four Field System","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"Must be in a crafting session and costs 1 crafting dice.","keywords":[],"description":"Make a crafting check. Afterwards, whenever you use an ability for crafting that you haven’t used before in this crafting session, it gains a +2 bonus to the crafting points it gives."},{"id":"four-point-strike","name":"Four Point Strike","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Combo","Unarmed Strike","Mystic Eye"],"description":"You may make a Light Attack against the target. On damage, you apply Wave Palm II.\n\nCombo: If used after Two Point Strike or against a target afflicted with Wave Palm I, the mana cost is reduced by 2 and the AP cost by 1. If the target is afflicted with Wave Palm I, you apply Wave Palm III instead of Wave Palm II.\n\nWave Palm increases the mana cost of the afflicted target’s next action that uses mana by an amount equal to the amount of stacks applied. If the triggering attack makes the number of total stacks exceed the target's current mana, they lose mana equal to the amount of total stacks and take true damage equal to triple this amount. Wave Palm does not stack with itself, use only the higher value.\n\nIf the target has no mana, they immediately take true damage as if their stacks exceeded their current mana.\n\nWhen the Wave Palm effect triggers, either by increasing the mana cost or by dealing the true damage, the Wave Palm effect is removed."},{"id":"freerunner","name":"Freerunner","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You do not incur difficult terrain penalties in Forest, Cities or Ruins."},{"id":"frost-coffin","name":"Frost Coffin","costLabel":"3 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Frost","Spell"],"description":"You cast a Spell that flash freezes a target Grunt, killing them instantly and creates a two Glacial Wall cube stack at their location. These cubes have HP equal to 15 + Focus. These structures can function as cover. Ice wall segments take double damage from Fire Attacks."},{"id":"frost-driver","name":"Frost Driver","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"80ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Frost","Root","Slow","Spell","Combo"],"description":"You send ice spikes along the ground towards a single target, making a Heavy attack that deals Frost Damage. This cannot hit a target higher than 5ft above the ground. On hit, the target is Slowed until the end of their next turn. If the target is already Slowed, they instead become Rooted, making them unable to move until the end of their next turn.\n\nCombo: When used after Icicle Nail or White Thunder hits, reduce the mana cost to 0."},{"id":"full-dimensional-equip","name":"Full Dimensional Equip","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You have a Dimensional Armory active.","keywords":["-"],"description":"You swap your armor, cloak and weapons currently wielded with a dimensional set. The weapon and armor you had equipped as you used to this ability become a Dimensional Set, allowing you to switch back to it."},{"id":"full-power-swing","name":"Full Power Swing","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Two-handed weapons only.","keywords":[],"description":"You may make a Heavy attack that does double heavy damage."},{"id":"g--shift","name":"G. Shift","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Encounter Start"],"description":"You take 11 true damage, then choose to either lose 1 RP or reduce your AP by 1 for your first turn.\n\nYou temporarily mutate your body, granting an effect similar to one of the following Alchemy Elixirs: Rabbit, Reaper, Shark, Tunnel, Bull, Bear. This effect does not stack with their corresponding Elixir Effect. This effect cannot be dispelled and lasts until the end of the encounter."},{"id":"gale-wind-aura","name":"Gale-Wind Aura","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Aura","Upkeep"],"description":"You project a Gale-Wind Aura around yourself that increases the movement speed of allies (excluding yourself) within 60ft of you by 20ft. An ally that starts their movement in the Aura, keeps the Speed increase for that move even if they leave the aura. Upkeep: You must spend 1 AP at the start of each turn or the aura fades."},{"id":"gene-activation","name":"Gene Activation","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must have the required Gene in your gene inventory.","keywords":["Transformation"],"description":"You transmute yourself, consuming a gene. You transform, granting yourself a single chimera racial ability that corresponds with the gene.\n\nYou are transformed until the end of your next turn. Doing this consumes the gene from your DNA. You can deactivate the transformation for 0 RP.\n\nYou cannot obtain and use abilities that require an IP or EP to use through this ability."},{"id":"genjutsu-kai","name":"Genjutsu Kai","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"Target is under the effects of an Illusion.","keywords":["Ninjutsu","Stealth"],"description":"You focus your internal energies and dispel any Illusions affecting you or an ally within 5ft of you."},{"id":"glacial-bastion","name":"Glacial Bastion","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Frost","Spell"],"description":"You encase yourself in a Glacial Wall that fills your space until the start of your next turn, making you untargetable for attacks during the duration. This Glacial Wall has HP equal to 20 + Focus, any remaining damage is transferred to you (mitigated by your armor). While encased, you can cast White Thunder on your encased Ice for 1 RP which removes Glacial Bastion. Other than White Thunder, you cannot take any other actions while under the effect of Glacial Bastion.\n\nThis Spell does not provoke attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"glacial-wall","name":"Glacial Wall","costLabel":"2 AP, -1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"-1","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Frost","Spell"],"description":"You create 4 * X connected ice structures that are 5ft x 5ft cubes that last for up to 24 hours. These cubes have HP equal to 20 + Focus. These structures can function as low cover. Ice Wall segments take double damage from Fire Attacks."},{"id":"gleaming-cut","name":"Gleaming Cut","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Light","Rapid","Illumination"],"description":"You attack with blades of pure light making a light attack against the target, dealing Holy(Light) damage. On damage, inflict Illumination X where X equals your Focus / 2 (Rounded Down) until the end of your next turn."},{"id":"glide","name":"Glide","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Spell"],"description":"You slow down your falling speed to 15ft per round and you are able to move horizontally as if normally moving. If you hit the ground while Glide is active, you do not take any falling damage and this effect ends."},{"id":"glittershards","name":"Glittershards","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft range, 5ft radius","requirement":"","keywords":["Concentration","Spell"],"description":"Numerous sparkling arcane crystals swarm the area and block line of sight. Targets inside of or within 5ft of the Glittershards can only see up to 5ft into or out of Glittershards. Glittershards lasts for up to 10 minutes and you can only have 1 Glittershards active at a time. You can end this effect for 0 AP on your turn."},{"id":"gloom-infusion","name":"Gloom Infusion","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Dark","Type"],"description":"You surround a willing target in gloom and shadow, changing their typing to Dark II. As a Dark II type, they take half damage from Dark Damage or attacks with the Dark keywords, unless the attack deals true damage. They take 50% more damage from Holy Damage or attacks with the Holy keyword. While the ward lasts, they also gain 60 feet Darkvision and a +4 bonus to saves against mind affecting effects.\n\nThe ward lasts until the end of the encounter or until their type is overwritten by a more powerful type."},{"id":"gnome-claws","name":"Gnome Claws","costLabel":"1 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You burrow into natural earth ground, granting Burrow, making you move underground at your normal speed. While you are not attacking, you gain a +10/+20 bonus to your dodge except against other burrowed creatures. Using any action except movement or basic defenses cancels Gnome Claws. Canceling Gnome Claws with a melee attack grants a +2 Accuracy Bonus to the attack."},{"id":"god's_blessing","name":"God's Blessing","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"-","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"The AP cost of True Divine Release I is lowered by 4 and the mana cost upkeep is lowered to 0."},{"id":"good-fortune","name":"Good Fortune","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You always seem to find money in inexplicable ways.\n\nAt the end of an Interlude phase, you gain 500 Clim per Interlude Point spent during the phase."},{"id":"goring-charge","name":"Goring Charge","costLabel":"-1 AP","apCost":"-1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You lower your head and charge in a direction with your horns. You move X times your speed in a straight line. If you move at least 15 feet, you make a Heavy attack against the first target in your path. They may sidestep this attack for 1 RP.\n\nIf a target sidesteps your attack, you continue charging for your maximum distance or until you hit an object. If you charge into another creature, you make a Heavy attack against them as well and the process continues. You do not provoke attacks of opportunity from creatures that sidestepped your attack for this movement.\n\nIf the object you charge into is destroyable, the GM may also ask you to make a Heavy attack against it.\n\nThese attacks are considered unarmed attacks that you are proficient in, even if you normally wouldn't be. It does not benefit from any sort of gauntlet bonuses."},{"id":"graceful-landing","name":"Graceful Landing","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You gain Graceful Landing until the start of your next turn, treating all fall distance as 50ft lower."},{"id":"graceful-service","name":"Graceful Service","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You assist a target character, giving them 1 additional encounter conclusion action.\n\nThis uses up your own encounter conclusion action."},{"id":"grand-theft-horse","name":"Grand Theft Horse","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"Target must be mounted.","keywords":[],"description":"The target must make a save against your Potency or be immediately dismounted and knocked prone next to their mount. You may then spend 0 RP to immediately mount it.\n\nDoes not work against creatures that are considered a mount by themselves such as Dullahans or Centaurs."},{"id":"gravitational_ki","name":"Gravitational Ki","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"10ft","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You target one unit and either push them away from you 5ft or pull them towards you 5ft. Cannot move a creature or object that’s bigger than 5ft and automatically fails against enemy heroic creatures."},{"id":"gravitational-push","name":"Gravitational Push","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Active","Gravity"],"description":"You push the target 20ft or pull it 20ft towards you."},{"id":"gravity-crush","name":"Gravity Crush","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Gravity","Rapid"],"description":"You make a Light (1 AP), Heavy (2 AP) or Precise (2 AP) attack against the target that deals Physical (Crushing) damage."},{"id":"greater-imbue-weapon","name":"Greater Imbue Weapon","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Enchantment"],"description":"You may enchant your weapon as though you had used Imbue Weapon, but it also gains a +1 Power bonus in addition to the normal benefits. If you are not holding the enchanted weapon at the start of your turn, your weapon loses this benefit."},{"id":"grindstone-echo","name":"Grindstone Echo","costLabel":"1 Crafting Dice","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"1 Crafting Dice","range":"","requirement":"Must be in a crafting session.","keywords":[],"description":"You make a crafting check. You may choose the dice result from a previous check this crafting session and use that as your roll value."},{"id":"grudge","name":"Grudge","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"An enemy hits you with an attack.","keywords":["Safe"],"description":"You curse the attacker and make a Light attack that deals Dark(Curse) damage against them."},{"id":"guard-dog","name":"Guard Dog","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"An ally within range is the target of an attack.","keywords":[],"description":"You redirect the attack towards you instead of your ally and may take the Block action against it for 0 RP.\n\nYou may use this even if you’re also a target of the attack and both attacks will resolve against you. Your Block action works against both of these attacks."},{"id":"guided-aim","name":"Guided Aim","costLabel":"0 AP, -1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"-1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You gain a bonus to your next accuracy roll equal to the mana spent on this ability. If the attack is a Precise Attack, the bonus gained is doubled."},{"id":"half-restore","name":"Half Restore","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"Can only target your summoned animal.","keywords":["Healing"],"description":"You heal your summoned animal for 11 + Power x 2 HP. It also removes 1 negative effect from it. If the amount healed exceeds the target’s maximum HP, any extra HP is converted into temporary HP."},{"id":"hammer-and-nail","name":"Hammer and Nail","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"An ally dealt damage to a target that didn't take a defense action.","keywords":["Sure Hit","Full Pierce","Rage"],"description":"Make a light attack against the target with Sure Hit and Full Pierce."},{"id":"hardening-fist","name":"Hardening Fist","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"","keywords":["Unarmed Strike","Combo"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target. Afterwards, you gain Hardening Fist, which gives +2 guard and +8 Block, but lose 4 evasion (including dodge) until the start of your next turn.\n\nCombo: If used after Steadfast Earth Stance, the mana cost is reduced by 1."},{"id":"harvest-moon","name":"Harvest Moon","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Slow","Healing","Killing Blow","Concentration","Upkeep"],"description":"You call down a harvest moon over the area that shines in a 60ft radius around yourself.\n\nAll allies in range may spend 2 Mana at the start of their turn to heal for 15 HP.\n\nAll enemies starting their turn in its range must make a Save against your potency or become slowed.\n\nYou may end this ability early by choosing to make a 0 AP heavy attack against an enemy slowed by this ability. This attack must be made with a Scythe. On killing blow of that attack, you recover 1 mana.\n\nUpkeep: You must spend 1 mana at the start of your turn to continue this effect."},{"id":"haste","name":"Haste","costLabel":"1 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Circuit"],"description":"Grants the target Haste, granting them 2 AP for the rest of this turn. A target can only be affected by haste once per turn."},{"id":"haunting-bark","name":"Haunting Bark","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"Must be in Dog Form.","keywords":["Mind Affecting","Fear","Shaken","Full Pierce","Sound"],"description":"You bark at an enemy forcing them to make a Save or become shaken until the end of their next turn. The third time in a combat you use this against the same target, they also take Light Full Pierce Lightning damage in addition to the shaken effect if they fail their save."},{"id":"headless","name":"Headless","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Critical hits rolled against you do not gain Full Pierce and do not automatically deal maximum damage."},{"id":"headwind","name":"Headwind","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Aura","Upkeep","Slow"],"description":"You project an aura around you that hinders the movements of enemies.\n\nAll enemies that start their movement within 30ft of you become slowed. If an enemy takes a Move basic action outside of your zone and spends more than 1 AP, they are still slowed after calculating each individual AP spent on the move.\n\nUpkeep: 1 AP"},{"id":"hearthlight","name":"Hearthlight","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You can glow, emitting a comforting light within 30 feet. You can activate or deactivate this light every 1 second."},{"id":"heavenfall-descent","name":"Heavenfall Descent","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be airborne and between 20ft and 120ft above the ground.","keywords":["Unarmed Strike","Blanketing","Rage"],"description":"You crash to the ground without taking falling damage and make a Light attack against all enemies within 5ft of you.\n\nMay target a point on the floor as long as it’s within 20ft of you horizontally."},{"id":"heavenly-lightning-stance","name":"Heavenly Lightning Stance","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Stance"],"description":"You enter the Heavenly Lightning Stance, a stance that lets you move with the unpredictability of the heavens. For your first movement of your turn, you may pass through enemies and your movement becomes a Sidestep.\n\nIf you have mastered Sky Talon Style, entering this stance also counts as your Wind Stance.\n\nThis stance lasts until you enter a different stance or make an attack with anything other than a melee attack or an ability with the Unarmed Strike keyword."},{"id":"heavy-trample","name":"Heavy Trample","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"When using Trample, you may use your Toughness for the damage roll instead of your mount’s power."},{"id":"helix-siphon","name":"Helix Siphon","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range or Touch","requirement":"Melee attack deals damage against a known Chimera.","keywords":[],"description":"When you make a melee attack against an enemy that is a Chimera, you copy some of their DNA, granting you a gene for any ability of their race.\n\nThis gene is temporary and only lasts until the end of combat. Alternatively, you can touch an ally Chimera or downed enemy and copy a single gene."},{"id":"hibernate","name":"Hibernate","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"When you take the rest IP action, the temporary HP gained is doubled. When you rest during the night as a rest action, you recover an additional toughness HP."},{"id":"hidden-wards","name":"Hidden Wards","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"-","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You may choose to hide your Bounded Fields when casting them by making a Stealth check. The casted ward uses the result of your Stealth check. Hidden Bounded Fields cannot be seen with Sense Magic without a successful perception or insight check."},{"id":"hide-in-bush","name":"Hide in bush","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be in natural terrain.","keywords":["-"],"description":"You take the Hide action and are considered to be in cover for the purposes of remaining stealthed. This lasts until you take any action or speak."},{"id":"hide-in-shadows","name":"Hide in Shadows","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"Must be day.","keywords":["Teleport","Full Pierce","Stealth"],"description":"You jump into a target’s shadow. If you were hidden before using this ability, you remain hidden inside the shadow. Else, the target or any other enemy may attack the shadow as if they were attacking you. If you take damage, you are forced out. While you’re inside the shadow, you travel with the target when it moves, including if it teleports, but cannot take actions other than exiting it.\n\nYou may exit the shadow willingly for 0 RP. When you exit it, if you were hidden, your next basic attack that turn against the target whose shadow you were hiding in gains Full Pierce."},{"id":"highly-sensitive-to-magic","name":"Highly Sensitive to Magic","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You may enter the Aetherie class without meeting its requirements and the cost for doing so is reduced by 100 exp."},{"id":"hit---run","name":"Hit & Run","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Weapon Range","requirement":"Must be mounted.","keywords":["-"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target. Afterwards, you may move up to your speed."},{"id":"hold-the-line","name":"Hold the line","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"Your next Block action costs 0 RP. Until the start of your next turn, unless you use the Dodge action, you become Immovable."},{"id":"holy-declaration","name":"Holy Declaration","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Challenge"],"description":"You take the Block action against the attack. Afterwards, you challenge all enemies within 5ft of you until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"holy-light","name":"Holy Light","costLabel":"1 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Healing","Spell"],"description":"You Heal the target for 8 + Power"},{"id":"holy-orders","name":"Holy Orders","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Sidestep"],"description":"You target an enemy unit within range, causing the target to become your Holy Order until the start of your next turn.\n\nWhile active, only your Holy Order may be chosen as the target for any offensive ability, or must be included as a target to use an offensive action.\n\nIf you make an attack of opportunity against your Holy Order, or if they move away from you while in your melee range, you can Sidestep up to twice your Speed towards them for 0 RP after their movement finishes.\n\nCan only be used on your turn before you use an offensive action."},{"id":"holy-shield","name":"Holy Shield","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be using a shield.","keywords":["Overcharge"],"description":"Your gain Holy Shield, which gives your next Block action gains a +2 guard bonus (not doubled again). If you reduce the damage you take with your next Block action to 0, you gain 3 temporary HP.\n\nOvercharge: You may spend up to 3 additional AP on this ability. Each extra AP spent increases the Guard bonus and temporary HP gained by 3."},{"id":"honk-","name":"HONK!","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Quick"],"description":"You place a clown nose on the target and honk it. The target must succeed at a Save or become challenged by you until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"hopping_zombie","name":"Hopping Zombie","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You gain +20 to any checks that involve jumping."},{"id":"horse-body","name":"Horse Body","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You may carry an ally on your back without lowering your movement speed and your Burden is increased by 2. However, you are considered a large creature. When attempting to move through 5ft wide spaces, it is considered difficult terrain for you and many humanoid buildings will struggle to accommodate you. You also suffer a -10 penalty on most finesse athletics checks, as well as a -10 penalty on climbing and swimming checks.\n\nPicking up an ally takes 1 AP and they cannot take AP actions while on your back. You or they may spend 1 AP to dismount and act like normal."},{"id":"horse-step-acceleration","name":"Horse Step Acceleration","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Opener"],"description":"You gain Horse Step Acceleration until the start of your next turn, which increases movement speed by 30. All of your movement is now Line Movement (You may only move in a straight line when making a movement action)."},{"id":"horse-whistle","name":"Horse Whistle","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"Must NOT be mounted.","keywords":["Sidestep"],"description":"Your mount (the last mount you were riding on this arc) may sidestep up to its speed towards you and it gains Trample (as per the ability, if you have it) for this movement. If this movement moves your mount onto your square, you may mount it for 0 RP. If you were prone and mount your mount, you are no longer prone."},{"id":"hover","name":"Hover","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You can passively hover up to 5ft above the ground. While hovering, you are not an eligible target for abilities that require a target to be flying or airborne unless you'd meet those conditions normally."},{"id":"hug-tight","name":"Hug tight","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"10ft","requirement":"Enemy Unit Affected By \"Just A Hug\".","keywords":["Full Pierce","Sure Hit","Rapid"],"description":"You deal Light Damage to the target."},{"id":"human-adaptability","name":"Human Adaptability","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":["Errand"],"description":"As an errand action, you may refund an ability and choose to learn another ability. You cannot pick an ability that makes you ineligible for any of your prerequisites. Your new ability must cost the same as your unlearned one, or you must pay additional normal EXP to make up for the cost difference. If you choose to unlearn a class and learn a new one with this ability, you must spend IP for that new class as normal. Any previous IP spent on learning the class you unlearn is NOT refunded.\n\nIf you choose to refund primary stats, secondary stats or skill points and then level up the class again, you must put those points back in the same things you originally put them in.\n\nDoes not work on breakthroughs."},{"id":"hunting-wolf","name":"Hunting Wolf","costLabel":"-1 AP","apCost":"-1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"The target enemy is below half HP.","keywords":[],"description":"You may move towards the target as if you had spent X AP on movement. Your movement speed is doubled for this movement."},{"id":"hyphal-force","name":"Hyphal Force","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"The host of your Spore Symbiote is making a melee attack.","keywords":["Earth","Spell"],"description":"Your spore symbiote surges the host’s muscles with temporary power. When the host of Spore Symbiote is making a melee attack, increase the damage by your Light Attack Damage. The extra damage dealt is Earth Damage.\n\nThis spell does not provoke attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"iai-strike","name":"Iai Strike","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Katana only. Must be in the Iai state.","keywords":["Iaijutsu","Lock On"],"description":"You draw your weapon and attack with lightning speed, making a Heavy Attack. You lose the Sheathed state afterwards."},{"id":"icicle-nail","name":"Icicle Nail","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Frost","Slow","Spell"],"description":"You fire a shard of ice at a target unit, making a Light Attack that deals Frost Damage. On hit, the target is Slowed until the end of their next turn."},{"id":"ignite","name":"Ignite","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Fire","Overcharge","Spell"],"description":"You may use this as a reaction after you deal Fire Damage to an enemy to set them on fire, causing them to become Burning X, where X equals your Power x 3. Overcharge: You may target additional enemies with this ability if you hit them with the same ability or attack. You may pay 1 mana per target beyond the first to also affect them with this ability."},{"id":"illuminating-flash","name":"Illuminating Flash","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft.","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Light","Blinded","Illumination"],"description":"You select a point within range. All targets in a 15x15 area centered on the point must make a save against your Potency or be inflicted with Illumination X where X your Focus / 2 (Rounded Down) until the end of your next turn. They also become Blinded 5 for their next attack."},{"id":"imaginary-consumables","name":"Imaginary Consumables","costLabel":"1 AP, -1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"-1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Illusion"],"description":"You ‘draw’ an imaginary basic consumable alchemy item or minor item that can cost no more than 100c per mana spent on this ability and no more than 500c total.\n\nThis consumable works like regular consumables would, but only you can use it, normal people can’t see it and it doesn’t work with abilities that require you to use real consumables like counter-potion.\n\nAny items created with this ability only last until the end of the encounter, or for 5 minutes outside of one."},{"id":"imaginary-weapon","name":"Imaginary Weapon","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Quick","Illusion"],"description":"You ‘draw’ an imaginary weapon or shield in which you are proficient.\n\nThis weapon works exactly like a normal weapon would, but only you can wield it and normal people can't see it."},{"id":"imbue_weapon","name":"Imbue Weapon","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Enchantment"],"description":"You enchant your melee weapon with an element you mastered. Your weapon now deals the chosen element’s damage instead of its normal damage.\n\nIf you are not holding the enchanted weapon at the start of your turn, your weapon loses this benefit."},{"id":"improvised-defense","name":"Improvised Defense","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You become the target of an attack.","keywords":[],"description":"You grab a nearby item and use it as cover against the triggering attack while taking the Dodge or Block action. The type of item used determines whether it is light, heavy or full cover."},{"id":"in-the-zone","name":"In The Zone","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"Must be in a crafting session. Costs 1 Crafting Dice","keywords":[],"description":"You add a crafting check to the item. This craft gains a +X bonus where X is equal to the amount of crafting dice spent this session."},{"id":"incendiary-ray","name":"Incendiary Ray","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Fire","Spell","Scatter"],"description":"You may make a Light Attack that deals Fire damage against all targets in a 10ft wide line up to the range. On damage, inflict Burning X where X is your Power x 3."},{"id":"increased-reach","name":"Increased Reach","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"The range of the next Spell you cast is doubled. Only works on Spells that have a range listed in ft."},{"id":"independent-action","name":"Independent Action","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"Can only target your summoned animal.","keywords":["-"],"description":"Your animal summoned through the Summon Animal ability gains the ability to act independently. It acts at initiative 0, though you may still control its action. A summon with Independent Action starts with 2 AP and 1 RP and may use those as normal. If they have an ability that costs mana, then you still have to pay that mana cost.\n\nWhile it is under the effects of Independent Action, you cannot command your summon through the use of your own AP.\n\nA summon targeted by this ability takes up 2 slots towards the summon limit. If this would put you past your limit, you cannot use this ability."},{"id":"inexorable-shadow-stance","name":"Inexorable Shadow Stance","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Stance"],"description":"You enter a stance that enhances your attacks at the cost of your own life. Whenever you hit an enemy with an unarmed attack, you may deal Light or Heavy true damage to yourself to increase the damage of the attack by the same amount. This may be done after reactions to the attack have been declared, though an enemy may still choose to react to it again or differently afterwards.\n\nIf used with an attack that hits more than 1 target, this extra damage only applies to one of the damage rolls.\n\nThis stance lasts until you enter a different stance."},{"id":"infernal-bastion","name":"Infernal Bastion","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You are targeted by a melee attack.","keywords":["Burning"],"description":"You surround yourself with flames and take the Block action against the attack. If you reduce damage of this attack to 0, inflict Burning X on the target where X is your focus x 3."},{"id":"inspired-finish","name":"Inspired Finish","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"This is your last crafting dice. Costs 1 Crafting Dice.","keywords":[],"description":"Make a crafting check. The dice is upgraded to 3d10 and you still add your crafting bonus to this. The crafting immediately ends after using this ability and you may not spend Crafting Points to add artisan bonuses, alloys or similar things."},{"id":"inspiring-song","name":"Inspiring Song","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Song","Sound","Upkeep"],"description":"All allies within range (including yourself) may add 1d4 to a single roll they make until the start of your next turn. They may choose to add this after seeing the roll.\n\nUpkeep: At the start of your next turn and every turn thereafter, you may spend 1 AP to continue this performance, granting all allies within range the benefit once again."},{"id":"instinct","name":"Instinct","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"The first time per encounter that you are attacked by a Stealth attack, that attack does not gain the Trick Attack benefit. If you become the target of an attack while you're surprised, you may still react to it and any special properties of an attack that require you to be unaware of the attack (such as Killshot) do not apply to it.\n\nIn addition, when you are about to take an action that leads to grave harm or death (example: The enemy has an instant death ability), you can receive a premonition from the DM."},{"id":"intercept","name":"Intercept","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Your movement speed.","requirement":"Must be mounted and an ally is the target of an attack.","keywords":["-"],"description":"You move towards an ally, Sidestepping them 5ft in a direction of their choice and occupying their square. The triggering attack is made against you and you automatically take the Block action against it.\n\nMounted move rules apply to your movement for this action."},{"id":"into-the-fray","name":"Into the Fray","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Rage"],"description":"You may move up to twice your movement speed. You must end this movement in range to make a melee attack against an enemy. Can only be used on your turn."},{"id":"invisible-wall","name":"Invisible Wall","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Illusion"],"description":"You create an invisible 5ft wide and high wall within range. It gives Low Cover, but it counts as High Cover against the first ranged attacks the wall gives cover from."},{"id":"judgement-shot","name":"Judgement Shot","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target.\n\nAfterwards, an ally other than you within 30ft of you may make a Light attack against the target. They may spend 1 RP to make this a Heavy or Precise attack instead."},{"id":"jump","name":"Jump","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"-","requirement":"-","keywords":["Jump","Sidestep"],"description":"You leap up to 30ft into the air and then Sidestep up to twice your Speed. You may use Skydive at any point during this movement."},{"id":"jump-back","name":"Jump Back","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"Previous action had the jump keyword.","keywords":["Jump","Quick"],"description":"You Jump Back to your previous location. This movement does not provoke any attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"just-a-hug","name":"Just a hug","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Grapple"],"description":"You coil and grapple a non-heroic enemy that is not larger than you, rooting both of you and rendering the target incapable of any attacks. You automatically guard against any attacks made towards the target as if using Block. You can also use this on a willing ally target.\n\nThe target may spend 1 Ap or 1 RP to attempt to escape, granting them escape power equal to their power. Further escape attempts continue to add escape power. When the escape power is equal to 8, then the target successfully escapes. You may end this effect at any time for 0 RP."},{"id":"justice-blade","name":"Justice Blade","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Target has your Mark of Justice on them.","keywords":[],"description":"You make a Heavy Attack against the target."},{"id":"kage-bunshin--kyomei","name":"Kage Bunshin: Kyomei","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"You must have a Bunshin clone active and within range.","keywords":["Ninjutsu","Stealth"],"description":"Your clone assists in the preparation of your next Ninjutsu, reducing the AP cost of it by 1."},{"id":"kage-shuriken-no-jutsu","name":"Kage Shuriken no Jutsu","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Weapon Range","requirement":"Set of Missiles, Throwing Weapon or Thrown attack with small weapon only.","keywords":["Ninjutsu"],"description":"You attack by throwing two weapons at the target, one hidden in the shadow of the other. Both of these are considered Light Attacks. If you fail your Accuracy roll on the first one, the second gains Sure Hit."},{"id":"kawarimi-no-jutsu","name":"Kawarimi no Jutsu","costLabel":"2 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"2","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Targeted by an attack.","keywords":["Ninjutsu","Hiding","Stealth"],"description":"The triggering attack automatically misses and you may Hide for 0 AP/RP, then move up to your Speed without provoking attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"ki-blast","name":"Ki Blast","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Arcane","Rapid"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target. This attack deals Arcane damage."},{"id":"ki-blast-ii","name":"Ki Blast II","costLabel":"1 or 2 AP","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"1 or 2 AP","range":"120ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Arcane","Rapid"],"description":"You may make a Light (1 AP), Precise (2 AP) or Heavy (2 AP) Attack against the target. This attack deals Arcane Damage."},{"id":"ki-burst","name":"Ki Burst","costLabel":"0 RP, -1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"-1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Can be used after damaging a single opponent with an Unarmed Strike attack.","keywords":[],"description":"Your attack deals an extra X damage.\n\nIf used with a basic attack or double punch, deal 2X extra damage instead up to a maximum of +10 damage. Only affects 1 damage roll even if an attack makes multiple attacks."},{"id":"ki-circulation","name":"Ki Circulation","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You cycle the Ki inside your body and purge it from negative energy. You remove Bleeding, Shaken, Unbalanced or any Poison effect from yourself."},{"id":"ki-recovery","name":"Ki Recovery","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Encounter Conclusion"],"description":"You spend your Encounter Conclusion action to regain 2 mana."},{"id":"ki-sense","name":"Ki Sense","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Stealth"],"description":"You send out your Ki and become aware of any creatures without presence concealment within 40ft of you, giving you a rough idea of their location. This does not remove Hiding from them, but their attacks against you do not gain Trick Attack or any other stealth or surprise bonuses until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"kibaku-fuda-shuriken","name":"Kibaku Fuda Shuriken","costLabel":"3 AP","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"Set of Missiles, Throwing Weapon or Thrown attack with small weapon only.","keywords":["Ninjutsu","Blanketing"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack by throwing a weapon with an explosive tag attached at a target. Regardless of whether it hits, the target and others within 5ft of the target must then make a save against Potency or take Light Fire Damage."},{"id":"killshot","name":"Killshot","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"Sniper Rifles only","keywords":["Trick Attack"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target that deals double Heavy Damage instead.\n\nIf fired in the first round of combat while all enemies are unaware of you, the target has to spend an additional RP to react to your attack. This stacks with the Trick Attack keyword, but is ineffective against abilities that negate surprise or stealth attacks such as Instinct."},{"id":"kiri-tsuke","name":"Kiri-tsuke","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Katana only","keywords":["Killing Blow"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target. On Killing Blow, you regain the Iai state."},{"id":"kiri-tsuke-ii","name":"Kiri-tsuke II","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Katana only.","keywords":["Combo","Killing Blow"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target. On Killing Blow, you regain the Iai state. Combo: If used after Iai Strike, the AP cost is reduced by 1."},{"id":"kneel","name":"Kneel","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Mystic Eye","Mind Affecting"],"description":"The target must make a Save or fall prone."},{"id":"knockback-shot","name":"Knockback Shot","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range (Up to 60ft)","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target. On damage, the target is pushed back 20ft."},{"id":"knockdown-swing","name":"Knockdown Swing","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Two-Handed weapons only.","keywords":[],"description":"You may make a Light Attack against the target. On damage, the target is knocked Prone."},{"id":"knockout-punch","name":"Knockout Punch","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Unarmed Strike"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target. On damage if the enemy is a Grunt, they immediately drop to 0 HP and fall unconscious."},{"id":"kugeki-zan","name":"Kugeki-zan","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"Target must have 0 RP remaining.","keywords":["Ninjutsu","Sure Hit","Full Pierce"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target."},{"id":"last-rites","name":"Last Rites","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You deal +1 damage to undead creatures. This is increased to a +2 bonus on Heavy attacks."},{"id":"last-stand","name":"Last Stand","costLabel":"2 RP, -1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"2","manaCost":"-1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Stance"],"description":"Until the start of your next turn, you may use the Block action for 0 RP and you gain additional Guard equal to the mana spent on this ability. Once you use this ability, you cannot use it again in this encounter."},{"id":"lay-on-hands","name":"Lay on Hands","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Touch","requirement":"-","keywords":["Healing","Overcharge"],"description":"You Heal the target for 4 + Power. Overcharge: You may spend an additional mana to remove a negative effect from the target. Injuries and Mortal Wounds cannot be removed with this."},{"id":"leashing","name":"Leashing","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"Can only target your summoned animal.","keywords":["Teleport"],"description":"You teleport your summoned animal to an empty square within 5ft of you."},{"id":"leg-sweep","name":"Leg Sweep","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Unarmed Strike"],"description":"You may make a Light Attack against the target. On damage, the target falls Prone."},{"id":"lengthened-incantation","name":"Lengthened Incantation","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Arcane"],"description":"You lengthen the time it takes to cast your next Spell to empower it. You may add up to 2 AP to the cost of your next spell with the Spell gaining additional Light Damage on it. If you cannot pay this AP cost this turn, the Spell also gains the Setup keyword.\n\nIf the Spell has multiple attack rolls or different damage rolls, this bonus only applies to one of them.\n\nHowever, if the spell is a Scattering AoE spell then the bonus damage applies to all targets of that spell. If that Scattering spell hits a target more than once it only applies to one damage roll. If the spell lasts for multiple turns, it only applies to the initial casting."},{"id":"lifebeat-sense","name":"Lifebeat Sense","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Expose","Analyze"],"description":"You can assess the approximate HP percentage of the target until the end of combat. (The DM should enable health bars for the unit, or you can ask for an approximate percentage). In addition, the target is afflicted by Expose 1, reducing the target’s crit threshold by 1. (20 to crit becomes 19.) Expose is removed once the target is critically hit (regardless of if they defend or not)"},{"id":"lifesense","name":"Lifesense","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Unlimited","requirement":"","keywords":["-"],"description":"You know the direction your Soulmate is in and if you’re within 300 feet of them, you know their exact location.\n\nYou also know their current HP, Mana and RP."},{"id":"light-work","name":"Light Work","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"Costs 1 Crafting Dice.","keywords":[],"description":"Only usable as the first crafting action. All material costs are doubled and all produced items are doubled. You may only use basic crafting actions for the rest of the craft. Make a crafting attempt."},{"id":"light-s-care","name":"Light's Care","costLabel":"1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Touch","requirement":"-","keywords":["Encounter Conclusion","Healing"],"description":"At the end of combat you may use 1 Encounter Conclusion action to heal a single target for 11 + Power x 2 and grant them First Aid. First Aid: The target can expend an Encounter Conclusion Action to prevent one injury to themself."},{"id":"lightning-lariat","name":"Lightning Lariat","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Unarmed Strike","Overcharge","Combo","Trick Attack"],"description":"You gather lightning energy and move up to twice your speed in a direct line and make a Heavy attack against a target. If you moved more than 60ft before making the attack, your attack gains the Trick Attack keyword.\n\nOvercharge: You may spend X mana to move an additional 2 x X times your speed.\n\nCombo: If used after Heavenly Lightning Stance or Secret Art: Lightning Release, the mana cost is reduced by 1."},{"id":"lightning-rod","name":"Lightning Rod","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Attack Deals Lightning Damage,","keywords":["Rapid"],"description":"You gain Damage Reduction 100 Lightning for the triggering attack. If you reduce damage in any way from this ability and the attacker isn't you, you gain a Power Bonus on your next Lightning Elemental Attack equal to the attacker’s Power."},{"id":"lightning-weapon","name":"Lightning Weapon","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"When attacking with a weapon, you may choose to have the weapon deal Lightning Damage instead of its normal damage type. You must declare you chosen damage type before making the accuracy roll."},{"id":"line-of-death","name":"Line of Death","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Slashing weapons only.","keywords":["Half Pierce","Overcharge"],"description":"You may make a Light Attack against the target. Overcharge: You may spend 1 additional mana and AP to make another Light Attack against the same target."},{"id":"living-lightning","name":"Living Lightning","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Not mounted and must move entirely in a straight line.","keywords":["Sure Hit","Full Pierce","Blanketing"],"description":"You turn into a spark of lightning as you move. For this movement action, you deal Light Lightning damage to all creatures you pass through."},{"id":"localized-collapse","name":"Localized Collapse","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Gravity","Full Pierce"],"description":"You target a 15x15ft square. All in the area take damage equal to your Focus / 2. If a creature occupies multiple squares in your target square, they take damage for each square they occupy.\n\nA creature caught in it may spend 1 RP to avoid the effect."},{"id":"long-toss","name":"Long Toss","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"Throwing Weapon, Set of Missiles or Thrown attack only.","keywords":[],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target. This attack has triple the range it would normally have."},{"id":"loyalty","name":"Loyalty","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"When standing within 5ft of a heroic ally, your Guard is increased by 1 and your Block is increased by 2."},{"id":"lucid_sleep","name":"Lucid Sleep","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"High Fae remain aware of their surroundings while they sleep and do not suffer from Surprised from being asleep."},{"id":"luminous-form-stance","name":"Luminous Form Stance","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Stance","Stacking"],"description":"You enter the Luminous Form Stance and create the Threads of Light. These manifest spiritual cloth, spectral arms or something similar that enhances your reach.\n\nWhile in this stance, you gain an additional 10ft range on your unarmed attacks and your threatened range becomes 5-15ft. Whenever you deal damage to an enemy with an unarmed strike ability (not basic attacks), you gain 1 stack of Harmony up to a maximum of 5. You cannot gain more than 1 Harmony per use of ability.\n\nWhen you leave this stance all stacks are lost.\n\nThis stance lasts until you enter a different stance or you willingly move, with the exception of movement abilities with the unarmed strike keyword. Abilities from allies that allow you to move, such as Gravitional Ki, count as willing movement."},{"id":"lunge","name":"Lunge","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"The attack range of your next basic Light, Heavy or Precise Attack with a melee weapon is doubled."},{"id":"mage-armor","name":"Mage Armor","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Arcane","Encounter Start","Spell"],"description":"You gain magical Light Armor, Medium Armor or Heavy Armor until the end of the encounter. This function just as normal armor of that type would, giving the same benefits and penalties. Does not stack with other armor, apply the effects of the Mage Armor This magical armor does not require proficiency of any sort and does not cost any Burden to wear and carry.\n\nYou may apply the effects of Barrier, Fortress, Manaweave, Protective Coating or Spidersilk to this armor (It must still meet the requirements, you cannot put fortress on a light armor for example). This can only be done when you first apply it, not if you later change your armor during combat.\n\nIf Mage Armor is active, you may spend 2 AP to change its type or to remove it."},{"id":"magic-blast","name":"Magic Blast","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Rapid"],"description":"You make a Light (1 AP), Heavy (2 AP) or Precise (2 AP) attack against the target that deals Arcane damage.\n\nIf you have an element mastered, you may change the damage of this spell to that element."},{"id":"magic-blast-ii","name":"Magic Blast II","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Rapid"],"description":"You make a Light (1 AP), Heavy (2 AP) or Precise (2 AP) attack against the target that deals Arcane damage.\n\nIf you have an element mastered, you may change the damage of this spell to that element."},{"id":"magic-missile","name":"Magic Missile","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Arcane","Lock On","Spell","Rapid"],"description":"You fire a highly accurate blast of arcane energy at the target, making a Precise Attack that deals Arcane damage against the target\n\nThis attack does not gain Pinpoint."},{"id":"magic-missile-ii","name":"Magic Missile II","costLabel":"1 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Arcane","Lock On","Rapid","Spell","Circuit"],"description":"You fire a highly accurate blast of arcane energy at the target, making a Precise Attack that deals Arcane damage against the target"},{"id":"malevolent-phantasm","name":"Malevolent Phantasm","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"An ally (including yourself) took damage on your turn.","keywords":["Spell","Dark"],"description":"You siphon the energy lost from your allies and make a Heavy Attack against the target that deals Dark Damage."},{"id":"mana-burst","name":"Mana Burst","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You augment your next attack, increasing accuracy by 3 and dealing 3 bonus damage on hit.\n\nYou may use AP for this attack instead."},{"id":"mana_eater","name":"Mana Eater","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You cannot consume biological food and instead consume equal monetary value of Magical Fuel for sustenance. You do not need to breathe."},{"id":"mana-razor","name":"Mana Razor","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Overcharge","Quick"],"description":"Until the end of your turn you gain Mana Razor granting your basic melee attacks an additional 30ft range. Augmenting melee attacks with this ability makes them into ranged attacks. If using a Two-Handed melee weapon with Mana Razor, gain an additional 45ft range instead.\n\nOvercharge: You may spend 1 mana to have this also affect basic ranged attacks and to remove the Quick keyword from it."},{"id":"mana-shield","name":"Mana Shield","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Encounter Start"],"description":"You use your Encounter Start action to give yourself Mana Shield, which gives you Temporary HP equal to your Toughness + 3 or Focus + 3 (whichever is higher).\n\nWearing armor reduces this to 2/3rd, 1/3rd or 0 if wearing Light, Medium or Heavy Armor respectively. While Mana Shield is active, you do not provoke attacks of opportunity from casting Spells from enemies that are Challenged by you.\n\nUntil the end of the encounter, at the start of your turn you may spend 1 mana to restore your Mana Shield to its maximum value. (With similarly reduced values for wearing armor)\n\nIf you did not use this as an encounter start, you may also spend 1 AP and 1 Mana to activate this."},{"id":"mana-sight","name":"Mana Sight","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"-","keywords":["Quick"],"description":"You can assess the approximate mana percentage of a unit until the end of combat. (The DM should enable mana bar for the unit)."},{"id":"mantra--flowing-perception","name":"Mantra: Flowing Perception","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"Must be in Luminous Form Stance.","keywords":["Unarmed Strike","Sidestep"],"description":"You extend your Threads of Light and make an unarmed light attack against a target within range. On damage, you may pull yourself towards the target and sidestep to the nearest square within 5ft of them.\n\nYou may also use this on ally. If you do, this always hits and deals no damage. It still gives you a stack of Harmony."},{"id":"mantra--pure-intentions","name":"Mantra: Pure Intentions","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"15ft","requirement":"Must have at least 1 stack of Harmony.","keywords":["Healing"],"description":"You wrap your Threads of Light around the chosen ally and channel your Harmony into them.\n\nYou may spend up to 5 stacks of Harmony and 1 mana per stack you consume to heal an ally within range for 3+Focus for each stack."},{"id":"mark-of-justice","name":"Mark of Justice","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You mark a single enemy, inflicting Mark of Justice on them. A marked enemy’s movement speed is reduced to 20ft. Abilities that allow for movement cannot move the target for more than 20ft per use. Secret Arts and Esoteric Arts are not affected by this. You can only have a single enemy marked by this at the same time. It lasts until the end of the encounter. Does not work on vehicles.\n\nA marked target may spend 1 mana per AP/RP of the action (with a minimum of 1 mana even for 0 AP abilities) to temporarily ignore the restricting effect for a movement action."},{"id":"mashup","name":"Mashup","costLabel":"0 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must have at least 1 song with Idol keyword active.","keywords":[],"description":"You may activate another song with the Idol keyword. This song’s AP cost is reduced by 2 and this song may go past your regular maximum song limits."},{"id":"master-of-the-empty-sky","name":"Master of the Empty Sky","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"When flying, you gain a +2 Cover bonus to your Evasion and Dodge against ranged attacks."},{"id":"maximum-dose","name":"Maximum Dose","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"Target takes damage from your Toxic","keywords":["Poison","Toxic"],"description":"You maximize the damage they take from your Toxic."},{"id":"measured-collapse","name":"Measured Collapse","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"","keywords":["Full Pierce"],"description":"You make a Heavy attack against the target. This attack is always considered to have rolled a 2 for accuracy instead of rolling the d20.\n\nAgainst creatures that are large size, gain a +2 bonus. If they are huge size, gain a +4 bonus."},{"id":"memory-of-the-grove","name":"Memory of the Grove","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"Usable after making a gathering a check.","keywords":[],"description":"After making a gathering check, you may choose to reroll the die. If you do, store the original die result. You may replace a future gathering die result (before bonus) with the stored value."},{"id":"mighty-leap","name":"Mighty Leap","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"Two-Handed melee weapons only.","keywords":["Unbalanced"],"description":"You jump to a target within range and may make a Light attack against them. All enemies within 5ft of the target must make a save or become Unbalanced."},{"id":"mind-connection","name":"Mind Connection","costLabel":"4 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Touch","requirement":"","keywords":["-"],"description":"You physically touch up to five willing people, granting them Mind Connection—creating a mind link through you. While linked, each creature can speak through telepathy to all other creatures linked to the same caster. Mind Connection has unlimited duration but also reduces your maximum mana by 1, this effect lasts until you cancel Mind Connection. Mind Connection has a maximum range of 500 ft—breaking this range doesn’t cancel the spell but interrupts the signal until within range again.\n\nWhile Mind Connection lasts, you may spend 1 AP to transfer view through the eyes of one of the people connected with the mind link."},{"id":"mind-s-eye","name":"Mind's Eye","costLabel":"0 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You may ask the GM for the rough best course of action during an encounter based on the information you have. The GM should answer truthfully, but does not need to go in depth. (For example: Retreat, kill the grunts, focus the boss, use magic attacks etc)."},{"id":"mining-expertise","name":"Mining Expertise","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You may unlock the miner class for 0 EXP. You must still spend the IP on it."},{"id":"miracle--sanctuary","name":"Miracle: Sanctuary","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft radius centered on self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Concentration","Miracle","Spell","Upkeep"],"description":"You create an immobile sphere of protection in a 5ft radius that prevents all entry into and out of it. The Shield has health points equal to 20 + Toughness x 8. Attacks and Magical Effects cannot be casted out of or into the Sanctuary, which functions as line-of-sight blocking for the purposes of abilities. Sanctuary lasts until the start of your next turn unless you pay Upkeep (1 Mana). The Spell also ends when the Shield’s health points are reduced to zero. This spell does not provoke attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"misdirected-blow","name":"Misdirected Blow","costLabel":"1 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You are the target of an attack and have a different enemy within 5ft of you.","keywords":[],"description":"You may take the Dodge action. If the attack is successfully avoided, the attack is then made against an enemy within 5ft of you and using the same accuracy roll. This enemy must be different from the one making the attack. The new target may react to this attack as normal.\n\nDoes not work against Secret Art or Esoteric Art level attacks."},{"id":"mist-of-the-vale","name":"Mist of the Vale","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be played on a flute.","keywords":["Song","Upkeep"],"description":"A mist rolls out from around you, trapping those caught in it in a misty vale in which travelers are doomed to die. All in the mist must make a save against your Potency when they try to escape it. If they fail their save when they attempt to move out, you may finish the remaining movement for them as long as they end within your mist. This movement does not provoke attacks of opportunity.\n\nThe mist also blocks Line of Sight. Targets inside of or within 5ft of the mist can only see up to 5ft into or out of mist.\n\nThe mist is a 15ft radius around yourself, but if flying it does not go below you. You may choose to exclude allies from the trapping effect. If you do, the upkeep mana cost and initial mana cost is increased by 1.\n\nUpkeep: 1 AP"},{"id":"molten-domain","name":"Molten Domain","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Domain","Burning"],"description":"Until the start of your next turn, the ground 5ft around you becomes like burning ground.\n\nAny enemy willingly leaving or moving through this area other than entering it becomes Burning X, where X is your Focus x 3.\n\nThe domain burns away other friendly damage aura effects while in effect. Effects that would normally trigger upon ending the turn in it (such as Poison Spore) don't trigger if someone ends their turn in the Molten Domain."},{"id":"momentum","name":"Momentum","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Must be mounted.","keywords":["-"],"description":"You make a Heavy attack against the target. For every 10ft moved during your last action this turn, this attack gains +1 damage up to a maximum of +10 damage. Abilities with the Teleport keyword do not apply for this."},{"id":"mordschlag","name":"Mordschlag","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Longsword, Heavy Blades and Bludgeoning weapons only.","keywords":["Block Crush"],"description":"You attack the target with the pommel or crossguard making a Heavy Attack against the target."},{"id":"mountain-slayer","name":"Mountain Slayer","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Target can be affected by Shieldbreaker.","keywords":["Shieldbreaker"],"description":"You make a Light attack against a target."},{"id":"mounted-casting","name":"Mounted Casting","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be mounted and taking a movement action.","keywords":["-"],"description":"You may cast a Spell with an AP cost of 2 or less."},{"id":"move-piece","name":"Move Piece","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Killing Blow","Sidestep"],"description":"You move a puppet piece you can see that's under your control. The way it moves depends on the type of piece. When a piece moves, it's a Sidestep.\n\nPawn: Moves up to 2 squares orthogonally or 1 square diagonally in a straight line.\n\nKnight: Moves 1 square orthogonally, then 1 square diagonal in the same direction it moved in orthogonally (like a knight in chess). Can pass through allies and enemies.\n\nBishop: Moves up to 8 squares diagonally in a straight line.\n\nRook: Moves up to 8 squares orthogonally in a straight line.\n\nQueen: Moves up to 8 squares orthogonally or diagonally in a straight line.\n\nExcept for the Knight, chess pieces cannot move through allies and stop their movement when they hit an object or creature. If this happens, it makes a Heavy attack against that target with your stats. A knight that makes an attack and does not kill the target remains in its original spot.\n\nOn damage, a piece is promoted into a higher rank (Pawn -> Bishop/Knight -> Rook -> Queen). A queen cannot promote.\n\nOn Killing Blow, a piece occupies the square of the thing it attacked."},{"id":"movement-burst","name":"Movement Burst","costLabel":"1 AP, -1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"-1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Stealth"],"description":"You may move up to your Speed + up to 15ft per mana spent on this ability. Any unspent movement is lost afterwards.\n\nIf you spend more than 1 Mana on this ability, it loses the Stealth keyword."},{"id":"mud-wall","name":"Mud Wall","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Earth"],"description":"You create a wall 4ft high, 1ft thick and up to 20ft long that serves as low cover. Anybody attempting to get over the wall treats it as difficult terrain. Walls must be placed on solid ground and cannot be stacked on top of eachother.\n\nEach 5ft of wall has 60 HP and dissolves if it reaches 0. It otherwise lasts until the end of the encounter.\n\nYou may spend 1 RP instead of 2 AP on this ability instead."},{"id":"mudra--first-sensation","name":"Mudra: First Sensation","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Must be in Luminous Form Stance","keywords":["Unarmed Strike","Combo"],"description":"You deliver the first motion, a graceful strike that awakens awareness in both you and your foe and you make a Light attack against the target. On hit, you gain a Harmony stack (In addition to the one you might get if this deals damage.)\n\nCombo: When used after entering Luminous Form Stance, the mana cost is reduced by 1."},{"id":"multishot","name":"Multishot","costLabel":"3 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Overcharge"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against two different targets. Overcharge: You may spend X extra mana to attack 2 + X targets instead."},{"id":"mystic-eyes-of-life-perception","name":"Mystic Eyes of Life Perception","costLabel":"0 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Mystic Eye"],"description":"You temporarily empower your eyes. While active, you gain 360 degree vision and automatically detect all enemies within a 30ft radius of you that are not behind at least 1ft of full cover. In addition, you can see the approximate HP and Mana percentage of all enemies in this range. This lasts for 5 minutes or until you turn it off."},{"id":"nature-s-grasp","name":"Nature's Grasp","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Root","Earth"],"description":"You shoot out a vine that wraps around the target and make a Light Attack against the target that only deals 1 Earth damage. On damage, the target becomes Rooted until the start of your next turn or until they spend 2 AP to remove the root with a slashing or fire based attack.\n\nAgainst Grunts, this attack costs 0 Mana and gains Sure Hit."},{"id":"nightvision","name":"Nightvision","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"As long as there is a source of weak light (even a weak moon) you do not suffer penalties to your vision due to darkness up to 120ft."},{"id":"ninja-run","name":"Ninja Run","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Ninjutsu","Quick","Stealth"],"description":"For your next movement action, you may treat the surface you’re walking on as horizontal ground, allowing you to walk over water or up walls."},{"id":"no-getting-past-","name":"No getting past!","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Only usable when you would be able to make an attack of opportunity.","keywords":["Sure Hit"],"description":"You may make a Light (0 RP) or Heavy (1 RP) attack against the target. On damage, the target becomes Slowed until the end of their turn. If the target is already Slowed, they become Rooted. This ability is treated as an attack of opportunity."},{"id":"oil-slick","name":"Oil Slick","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You throw a bottle of oil on the ground within range, creating a 15x15 area of slippery oil. If the target contacts the oil at any point of movement (even the start or end) and they moved more than 5ft in a single movement action, they immediately fall prone. The slick lasts until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"one-beat--one-heart","name":"One Beat, One Heart","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Song","Sound","Idol","Upkeep"],"description":"All allies within range gain a +1 Song bonus to their accuracy. This bonus is doubled on Precise attacks.\n\nUpkeep: 1 AP"},{"id":"order--retreat","name":"Order: Retreat","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You order one willing allied unit to retreat, moving up to their Speed. All movement must be made towards you, and does not provoke attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"ougi--taju-bunshin-no-jutsu","name":"Ougi: Taju Bunshin no Jutsu","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art","Ninjutsu","Illusion","Upkeep"],"description":"You create 3 illusionary copies of yourself within 10ft of yourself or your Bunshin clone. These copies can take actions similar to your Bunshin Tai no Jutsu, but each of them may also act with its own 2 AP from the start of your next turn.\n\nEach clone has 1 HP and upon taking any damage, they vanish. You may use RP for these clones as normal.\n\nUpkeep: 2 AP"},{"id":"outbreak","name":"Outbreak","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Weapon Range","requirement":"Must be made with a melee weapon or with a throwing weapon or set of missiles.","keywords":["Poison","Toxic"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target. On damage, inflicts the enemy with Toxic, making them take 1d6 full pierce Poison damage at the start of their turn until they spend 2 AP to remove the poison effect.\n\nIf the target is already suffering from Toxic, instead immediately trigger the damage effect from it."},{"id":"overclock","name":"Overclock","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"Must be in a crafting session.","keywords":[],"description":"You may add 1d10 crafting points to the item. The item starts in the Broken condition. Cannot be used for Alchemy crafting."},{"id":"overpower","name":"Overpower","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Two-Handed weapons only.","keywords":["Combo"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target. For every point of Power you have over the target, you deal 1 additional damage. If the enemy is Prone, each point of Power you have over the target adds 2 additional damage instead.\n\nCombo: If used after Knockdown Swing, the AP cost is reduced by 1."},{"id":"overtime-again-","name":"Overtime again?","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"When you take the Heal Injury, Appraise or Mentor IP actions, you may do the same action again for an EP.\n\nIn addition, if you take the Rest interlude action you may give the benefit to a different character instead. This does not stack with any Rest bonuses they may have already."},{"id":"own-mount","name":"Own Mount","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You count as mounted for the purposes of abilities that require you to be mounted. This does not let you be a mount to other creatures."},{"id":"pack-tactics","name":"Pack Tactics","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"","keywords":["Quick"],"description":"Select a target within range. Until the end of your turn, while the target has one of your allies within 5ft of it, you gain Pack Tactics, which gives a +2 bonus on accuracy checks for melee attacks against that target."},{"id":"panda-roll","name":"Panda Roll","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You prepare to roll from an incoming attack. Your next Dodge action before the start of your next turn costs 0 RP. If you successfully avoid an attack with this Dodge action, you may Sidestep 5ft."},{"id":"panda-stance","name":"Panda Stance","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 RP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Stance"],"description":"You enter a stance in which you use your tail for extra balance. When you would be knocked back or prone, you may end this stance to negate the effect. This stance then ends.\n\nOtherwise, the stance lasts until you enter a different stance.\n\nYou may use AP or RP for this ability."},{"id":"paragon-of-virtue","name":"Paragon of Virtue","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You may remove a single negative non-physical effect from yourself (ie, fears, charms but not things such as bleed). If you are afflicted with more than 1 negative effect that is a valid target, you may choose which one you remove."},{"id":"parry","name":"Parry","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"-","requirement":"Target of a melee attack, wielding a One-Handed melee weapon.","keywords":[],"description":"Roll your Heavy Weapon Damage, but add your Focus instead of Power to the roll and treat that as your Block against the attack targeting you. If Parry reduces the damage to 0, you regain 1 RP (cannot go higher than your max RP). On hit effects and maces do not gain their effect if you reduce the damage to 0.\n\nWhen using Parry against an attack, that attack cannot land a critical hit against you."},{"id":"past-self","name":"Past Self","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Opener","Quick"],"description":"You place a past self token at your current position that lasts until the end of the encounter. Your past self tokens are used for other abilities and cannot be attacked normally.\n\nWhen you make a weapon attack, you may have the attack come from a past self token. After a past self token attacks, it becomes targetable by attacks and effects for 1 round as if you were in that position though you cannot be hit more than once by the same attack because of this.\n\nYour past selves cannot be moved, willingly or forcefully."},{"id":"pathfinder","name":"Pathfinder","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Stealth"],"description":"You may move up to your speed and you ignore difficult terrain penalties for this movement. Until the start of your next turn, all terrain within 20ft of you is not considered difficult terrain for your allies."},{"id":"penetrating-shot","name":"Penetrating Shot","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"Sniper Rifles only.","keywords":[],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target. This attack penetrates through thin layers of cover such as wood planks (GM’s decision), negating the bonus it would give."},{"id":"pepper-spray","name":"Pepper Spray","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Blinded"],"description":"You reach into your pocket and pull out a handful of ground chili pepper that you throw in front of you in a 15ft cube. Inflicts all targets with Pepper Spray, causing Blinded 4 and the inability to smell. The target or an ally of the target within 5ft can spend 1 AP to wipe it off. Otherwise the effect ends at the end of the target’s next turn.\n\nYou may spend 1 RP and 1 additional mana instead of paying the AP cost."},{"id":"perfect-seasoning","name":"Perfect Seasoning","costLabel":"1 Crafting Dice","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"1 Crafting Dice","range":"","requirement":"Must be in a crafting session. Must have added a special ingredient (box of food, alloy materials) in your last action.","keywords":["Rapid"],"description":"Make a crafting check with a +3 Bonus."},{"id":"perfect-shot","name":"Perfect Shot","costLabel":"6 AP","apCost":"6","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Full Pierce","Prone","Setup","Sure Hit"],"description":"You line up the perfect shot, striking an enemy for double Heavy Damage with Sure Hit and Full Pierce.\n\nAutomatically fails if the target has cover when this ability finishes."},{"id":"perish","name":"Perish","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Mystic Eye","Rapid"],"description":"You make a Light (1 AP), Heavy (2 AP) or Precise (2 AP) attack against the target that deals Dark(Curse)."},{"id":"persistent-spell","name":"Persistent Spell","costLabel":"0 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"If the next Spell you cast applies a buff or debuff, the duration of this buff or debuff is extended by 1 turn. If the Spell allows for a save, the target may make another save after the original effect is over to resist the duration extension."},{"id":"phantoms-of-the-mist","name":"Phantoms of the Mist","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Mist of the Vale must be active.","keywords":["Song","Scatter"],"description":"You conjure several phantoms in the mist and make a Light attack against all creatures within your Mist of the Vale.\n\nYou may spend 1 Mana to exclude allies from this attack."},{"id":"phoenix-tears","name":"Phoenix Tears","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Touch","requirement":"-","keywords":["Encounter Conclusion"],"description":"At the end of combat you may use 1 Encounter Conclusion action to heal a single target other than yourself for Power and prevent one injury on them."},{"id":"pie-toss","name":"Pie Toss","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Sure Hit","Full Pierce","Rapid","Encounter Start","Encounter Conclusion","Downed","Safe"],"description":"You deal 2 damage to the target. This damage can not be increased and does not trigger extra damage effects on the target.\n\nCan be used while downed, as an attack of opportunity, Encounter Start and Encounter Conclusion."},{"id":"piercing-stab","name":"Piercing Stab","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"A target in melee weapon range and a target directly behind the first target in melee weapon range.","requirement":"Polearm only.","keywords":["Blanketing"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target and the target directly behind it."},{"id":"pillar-of-earth","name":"Pillar of Earth","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Earth"],"description":"You create a 5x5, 20ft high pillar below someone. The target may spend 1 RP to step out of the way.\n\nEach block of the pillar has HP equal to 20+Focus and the entire pillar collapses if one block is removed from it."},{"id":"pinning-shot","name":"Pinning Shot","costLabel":"1 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range (Up to 60ft)","requirement":"Bow or Crossbow only.","keywords":["Root"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target with your weapon. On damage, if there is a wall or similar object directly behind the target, they become pinned against it. A pinned target is considered Rooted until they spend 2 AP to remove the arrow pinning them."},{"id":"pistol-whip","name":"Pistol Whip","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Must be holding a pistol.","keywords":["Unarmed Strike"],"description":"You make a Light Attack with a pistol in your hand. On damage, the target becomes Unbalanced.\n\nThis attack benefits from alloys and material bonuses on your pistol (but not from any on your unarmed strike)."},{"id":"pixie_flight","name":"Pixie Flight","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Upkeep"],"description":"You gain controlled Flight and Hover up to your speed. This ability ends at the start of your next turn unless you pay Upkeep 3 Mana, if you choose to not pay upkeep, you cannot use Pixie Flight until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"place-trap","name":"Place Trap","costLabel":"Special","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"Special","range":"","requirement":"Sufficient time (see description)","keywords":["Root","Stealth"],"description":"You choose to spend either 1 minute or 1 hour to place an undetermined trap in an area. You may only have 2 traps placed at a time in this way.\n\nWhen an enemy comes within 20ft of you, you may spend 0 RP to determine the effects of a trap and trigger it. If you spent 1 minute, you may choose a Simple Trap. If you spent 1 hour, you may choose either a Simple Trap or a Complex Trap.\n\nLog Swing (Simple): The target takes Light bludgeoning damage and is knocked back 20ft.\n\nSnare (Simple): You place up to 3 snare traps, each within 20ft of each other. When triggered, the target’s movement is interrupted and they fall prone.\n\nNet (Complex): The target is caught in a net and raised up into the air. It remains rooted there until the net is destroyed by dealing 15 damage, after which the target falls prone on the ground below it.\n\nPitfall (Complex): The target falls down a 5x5, 20ft deep pit and takes falling damage as normal.\n\nA used trap cannot be reused. Setting a trap consumes a Trapper's Trap."},{"id":"plaguebringer","name":"Plaguebringer","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"When you damage an enemy with a melee attack while infected with a disease or suffering from poison, you inflict that disease or poison on the enemy. They can make a save against it as normal, if the original disease or poison allowed for it."},{"id":"please-hold-still-","name":"Please Hold Still~","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Illumination"],"description":"You apply Illumination X to the target where X is your Focus. You cannot benefit from this Illumination yourself, but also cannot consume it."},{"id":"plow-the-fields","name":"Plow the fields","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"15ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Blanketing"],"description":"You strike the ground with magical power and make a Light attack against all enemies in a 15ft wide line up to range. The terrain within this range becomes difficult terrain until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"plume-treading-art","name":"Plume-Treading Art","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":["Stacking"],"description":"After you use Cloudstep, you treat air as regular walkable terrain until the end of your turn. At the end of your turn, if still standing on air and not Flying, you float back down to the ground without taking fall damage.\n\nIn addition, after each AP spent on the Move action or an ability that lets you move, you gain 1 Windflow up to a maximum of 6. Each stack of Windflow gives a +5 Windflow bonus to your movement speed. These stacks last until the end of the encounter or until you end your turn without having moved.\n\nCloudstep also always gives you 1 stack, up to your normal cap."},{"id":"point-blank-shot","name":"Point Blank Shot","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"Pistol only.","keywords":["Sure Hit"],"description":"You make a Heavy Attack against the target."},{"id":"point-of-death","name":"Point of Death","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Target is below half HP of their original max HP (Before True Death reductions).","keywords":["Full Pierce"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target. This attack deals maximum damage instead of rolling for the damage."},{"id":"point-of-death-ii","name":"Point of Death II","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Target is below half HP of their original max HP (Before True Death reductions).","keywords":["Full Pierce"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target. This attack deals maximum damage instead of rolling for the damage.\n\nOn killing blow, refund the mana and AP cost spent on this ability."},{"id":"poison-spore","name":"Poison Spore","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 RP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self or The Host of Poison Spore. 15ft x 15ft Area with the target at the center.","requirement":"-","keywords":["Concentration","Poison","Full Pierce"],"description":"You may spend either 2 AP or 1 RP to use this ability.\n\nYou create an Area of Poison Spores around you or the Host of Spore Symbiote. Units who end their turn in the Poison Spore take Full Pierce Poison damage equal to your Power + 2. You and the host of Spore Symbiote are immune to your own Poison Spore. Poison Spore lasts until the end of the encounter but you can only have one instance of Poison Spore active at a time.\n\nThe spore stays centered around the original target, even if the target of this ability moves. If the original target of this ability was the symbiote target and you swap the symbiote target, the location of the poison spore moves with it."},{"id":"poison-spray","name":"Poison Spray","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Poison","Safe","Toxic"],"description":"You make a Light attack against all targets in a 60ft wide, 30ft long cone. On damage, you inflict the enemy with Toxic, making them take 1d6 full pierce Poison damage at the start of their turn until they spend 2 AP to remove the poison effect."},{"id":"position-rewind","name":"Position Rewind","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"2000ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Stealth"],"description":"You teleport to where you were at the start of your last turn. (Use a token to mark the position)"},{"id":"power-jump","name":"Power Jump","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Jump","Circuit"],"description":"You jump up to 60ft vertically straight up into the air. You can additionally move 5ft horizontally afterwards. Unless flying, you automatically land straight down from your position at the end of your turn or for 0 AP, this falling movement does not provoke attacks of opportunity and you don’t take fall damage from it. If you land inside an occupied square, you are shunted 5ft into an empty square (your original one if possible).\n\nYou cannot make any non-teleport movement actions while in the air unless you’re flying, but can still take other actions (such as attacking) while airborne."},{"id":"power-rock-strike","name":"Power Rock Strike","costLabel":"1 Strike Dice","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"1 Strike Dice","range":"","requirement":"Must in a gathering session.","keywords":[],"description":"Make a gathering check at only half of your gathering bonus (rounded down) add the rolled amount to both node and lucky points."},{"id":"power-strike","name":"Power Strike","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Crushing"],"description":"You make a Light (1 AP), Heavy (2 AP) or Precise (2 AP) attack against the enemy."},{"id":"power-word--barrier","name":"Power Word: Barrier","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 RP, 4 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"4","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Shield","Spell"],"description":"Up to 5 target allies within range (including yourself) gain temporary HP until the end of the encounter equal to 10 + Power.\n\nYou may pay either the AP or RP cost for this ability, you don't need to pay both."},{"id":"power-word--guardian-shield","name":"Power Word: Guardian Shield","costLabel":"2 AP, 4 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"4","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Shield"],"description":"The target gains temporary HP until the end of the encounter equal to 11 + 2 x Power. While this temporary HP lasts, on damage effects do not trigger on them unless the damage dealt does damage to their actual HP.\n\nIf this source of temporary HP is overwritten by a stronger source, this effect is lost."},{"id":"power-word--reinforce","name":"Power Word: Reinforce","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"An ally is the target of an attack.","keywords":["Aid"],"description":"The target gains temporary HP equal to 2 x their current temporary HP.\n\nAfter the attack is done resolving, the target's temporary HP is set to the value it was before this ability was used unless the target's current temporary HP is lower than that."},{"id":"power-word--shield","name":"Power Word: Shield","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Shield","Spell"],"description":"The target gains temporary HP until the end of the encounter equal to 11 + (2 x Power)."},{"id":"precise-thrust","name":"Precise Thrust","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Full Pierce"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target.\n\nThis attack does not disable the dueling weapon ability."},{"id":"predict","name":"Predict","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You are the target of an attack.","keywords":[],"description":"You may take the Dodge action and remove the Lock On effect from the triggering attack."},{"id":"prediction","name":"Prediction","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"An ally is the target of an attack.","keywords":["Aid","Divination"],"description":"You remove the keyword Sure Hit and Lock On from the triggering attack and the target gains a +2 Dodge Bonus for their next Dodge action."},{"id":"prehensile-tail","name":"Prehensile Tail","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You may carry objects with your tail, allowing you to interact with objects as normal even when you have both hands full. The action you are performing must not require physical strength and you cannot wield weapons with your tail."},{"id":"prepared-talisman","name":"Prepared Talisman","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"Special","keywords":[],"description":"You may place a Talisman on a surface or on a target within range. This costs the same amount of AP and Mana as it would normally cost and placing it on an unwilling target requires an accuracy roll that the target may dodge as normal. A target may spend AP equal to the AP cost of the talisman (before reductions) to remove the talisman from themselves.\n\nAfter placing it, until the end of the encounter or for the next 5 minutes, you may spend 0 RP to instantly trigger the effect of the talisman. You cannot trigger it anymore once a talisman has been removed or is in the process of being removed and a removed talisman loses its power entirely. A talisman placed on a creature gains Sure Hit against the creature it's on when triggered.\n\nYou can only have 1 talisman prepared in this way at the same time and Sealing Talisman cannot be prepared like this. A placed talisman cannot have an AP cost of greater than 4 (or 10 seconds for casting times)."},{"id":"preparedness","name":"Preparedness","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"-","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"Up to 3 talismans, scrolls or similar objects you carry do not count towards your burden."},{"id":"presence-concealment","name":"Presence Concealment","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Presence Concealment","Stealth"],"description":"By suppressing your mana output you conceal your presence, gaining Presence Concealment. You cannot use any abilites that cost mana or any abilities with the aura keyword while in Presence Concealment. You can end this effect for 0 RP but the inability to use abilities that cost mana or abilities with the aura keyword persists until the end of your next turn."},{"id":"presence-of-mind","name":"Presence of Mind","costLabel":"0 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You reduce the AP cost of your next Spell this turn by 2 AP."},{"id":"prone-cover","name":"Prone Cover","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Cannot be used while Flying.","keywords":["Stance"],"description":"You become Prone. While Prone from this ability, you gain the benefits of low cover against ranged attacks. In addition, all Ranged Weapon Attacks gain the Prone keyword."},{"id":"provide-milk","name":"Provide Milk","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You may spend an EP to produce 400u worth of milk."},{"id":"provoke","name":"Provoke","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Challenge"],"description":"You Challenge an enemy until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"provoke-ii","name":"Provoke II","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Challenge"],"description":"You Challenge the enemy until the end of the encounter. You may only have 1 target Challenged at the same time through this ability."},{"id":"psychometry","name":"Psychometry","costLabel":"4 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Touch","requirement":"","keywords":["Aura"],"description":"By touching the door to a room you gain information as to the physical layout of the room and objects within it as if you were able to see inside of the room. By reading the Auras of all creatures within the room, you can also get a general idea of any creatures within, which you see as blobs of light—brighter for more powerful auras. You can also use this effect on containers as well to get a general idea of the layout within containers like backpacks, and chests. This ability can be used at unlimited range as long as a creature under the effect of Mind Connection touches the door or container."},{"id":"pull-the-weeds","name":"Pull the weeds","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"Must be in a crafting session. Only applies to a farming crafting session.","keywords":[],"description":"You destroy one of your planted seeds to give yourself +5 crafting points for this session."},{"id":"purification-circle","name":"Purification Circle","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell"],"description":"You remove all stacks of single debuff from all allies in a 20ft radius circle from target point."},{"id":"purify","name":"Purify","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell"],"description":"You cleanse a target, removing all stacks of a negative effect of your choice that you are able to identify."},{"id":"purifying-shields","name":"Purifying Shields","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You remove all stacks of a debuff from every ally within range that has temporary HP."},{"id":"quick-artifice-reload","name":"Quick Artifice Reload","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Stealth"],"description":"You quickly reload one shell into an artifice in range using one of your shells."},{"id":"quick-assist","name":"Quick Assist","costLabel":"1 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"20ft","requirement":"Your soulmate is the target of an attack.","keywords":["Teleport"],"description":"You teleport next to your soulmate and force the triggering attack to resolve against you, gaining the benefit of the Block action against it.\n\nAfterwards, if your Soulmate is in range of the attacker, they may make an Attack of Opportunity against it.\n\nIf you were already next to your Soulmate before you used this ability, the mana cost is reduced by 1."},{"id":"quick-getaway","name":"Quick Getaway","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"-","requirement":"-","keywords":["Combo","Stealth"],"description":"You may move as if you had spent 2 AP on the movement action. Combo: If used after Feint or the Disengage action, the AP cost of this is reduced by 2."},{"id":"quick-revive","name":"Quick Revive","costLabel":"0 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["-"],"description":"You immediately resummon the summon from your Summon Animal that was killed in this current encounter. If multiple of your summons have died, you summon the one that died most recently."},{"id":"quickdraw","name":"Quickdraw","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"Pistol only.","keywords":["Encounter Start"],"description":"You may draw a pistol and make a Light Attack with the drawn pistol against the target. The target may not react to this shot."},{"id":"quickdraw-alchemy","name":"Quickdraw Alchemy","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Stealth"],"description":"You draw an Alchemy item from your combat inventory."},{"id":"radiant-halo","name":"Radiant Halo","costLabel":"2 AP, 6 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"6","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Healing","Spell"],"description":"You Heal all allied targets in a 15ft radius from the target point for 11 + (2 x Power).\n\nYou may use 1 RP instead of 2 AP for this ability. When using RP on this ability, you may use it even when it is not your turn."},{"id":"rage-stance","name":"Rage Stance","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Stance"],"description":"You enter a Stance in which you prioritize offense over defense. The Stance lasts until the encounter ends, you get Downed or up to an hour. While the Stance lasts, gain 2 additional AP that can only be used on melee attacks each turn (including the turn you use this), but cannot use actions that use RP other than attack of opportunity unless they have the Rage keyword. You also cannot use abilities with the Spell keyword, unless they also have the Rage keyword. You are treated as having 0 RP for abilities with that as a requirement. While in your Rage Stance, you gain a +1 bonus to Guard and a +5 bonus to all Fitness checks."},{"id":"raise-undead","name":"Raise Undead","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"Target must be a dead humanoid.","keywords":["Summon"],"description":"You raise the target corpse as a basic undead, such as a zombie. This zombie is treated as a non-heroic unit that you can command directly. You can have multiple zombies under your command, up to your Necromancer level + 1. However, the zombies act as a group under the same token rather than having an individual token. The group acts on your Initiative.\n\nEach zombie has a single point of HP and immediately dies, but you only lose 1 zombie per attack the group takes, including AoE attacks that do not deal Holy Damage. AoE attacks that deal Holy damage remove a number of zombies equal to the damage taken. The zombie group has a focus and power of 3 + 1 for every 3 zombies, rounded down. They have an Agility of 2 and Toughness equal to 4. They have access to all basic actions, but otherwise have no special abilities. As a non-heroic entity, they only have access to a single RP. Because they are undead, they are immune to all mind-affecting effects.\n\nA raised undead lasts until the end of the arc or until killed, after which the corpse cannot be raised again in any way."},{"id":"raise-undead-ii","name":"Raise Undead II","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"Target must be a dead humanoid.","keywords":["Overcharge","Summon"],"description":"You raise the target corpse as a basic undead, such as a zombie. This zombie is treated as a non-heroic unit that you can command directly. You can have multiple zombies under your command, up to your Necromancer level + 1. However, the zombies act as a group under the same token rather than having an individual token. The group acts on your Initiative.\n\nEach zombie has a single point of HP and immediately dies, but you only lose 1 zombie per attack the group takes, including AoE attacks that do not deal Holy Damage. AoE attacks that deal Holy damage remove a number of zombies equal to the damage taken. The zombie group has a focus and power of 3 + 1 for every 3 zombies, rounded down. They have an Agility of 2 and Toughness equal to 4. They have access to all basic actions, but otherwise have no special abilities. As a non-heroic entity, they only have access to a single RP. Because they are undead, they are immune to all mind-affecting effects.\n\nA raised undead lasts until the end of the arc or until killed, after which the corpse cannot be raised again in any way.\n\nOvercharge: You may spend 1 Mana to raise a non-humanoid corpse."},{"id":"rapid-correction","name":"Rapid Correction","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You miss with a ranged weapon Light attack.","keywords":[],"description":"You turn your Light attack into a Precise attack."},{"id":"rappelling-dagger","name":"Rappelling Dagger","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"Throwing Weapon or Thrown attack only.","keywords":[],"description":"You may make a Light Attack against the target. On damage, you may move to the closest available spot within 5ft of the target. This movement does not provoke attacks of opportunity. Can be used against non-living objects and the on damage part always applies when used in that way."},{"id":"receive-oracle","name":"Receive Oracle","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Divination"],"description":"You seek divine knowledge on a topic and can ask up to three yes or no questions. You then receive a vision on the answers from an unknown entity. The GM chooses the information you receive. You regain the use of Receive Oracle after a rest."},{"id":"reckless-strike","name":"Reckless Strike","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 RP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Rage"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target."},{"id":"redirected_force","name":"Redirected Force","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Must be in Serene Water stance and after a melee attack against you missed.","keywords":["Counter"],"description":"You redirect the incoming attack back onto the attacker, using the same attack roll. The attacker may react to this attack as normal.\n\nCan not be used against the same attack used to enter the Serene Water stance."},{"id":"redistribute","name":"Redistribute","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"80ft","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You may transfer temporary HP from a single willing ally within range to any number of other allies within range. The total amount of temporary HP must be the same after the transfer.\n\nMay only redistribute temporary HP you applied through the use of a Shieldwarden or Veilguard ability. Does not affect temporary HP added through Reinforce."},{"id":"refreshing-stream","name":"Refreshing Stream","costLabel":"1 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"15 ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell"],"description":"You cast this ability on water within range, recovering fatigue and granting a target within 15ft of that point 1 RP. The target cannot go over their max RP from this."},{"id":"regrowing-limbs","name":"Regrowing Limbs","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"Costs 1 Interlude Point","keywords":[],"description":"You regrow a lost limb, restoring it to full use."},{"id":"reinforce-armor","name":"Reinforce Armor","costLabel":"0 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be wearing armor or a shield you crafted.","keywords":[],"description":"Until the start of your next turn, the guard and block value gained from an armor and shield you crafted and are wearing is doubled.\n\nDoes not affect armor plates."},{"id":"repair-armor","name":"Repair Armor","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":["Interlude","Errand"],"description":"Errand. You repair a broken armor."},{"id":"repair-artifice","name":"Repair Artifice","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":["Interlude","Errand"],"description":"Errand. You repair a broken artifice."},{"id":"repair-weapon","name":"Repair Weapon","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":["Interlude","Errand"],"description":"Errand. You repair a broken smithing weapon."},{"id":"repair-wood-weapon","name":"Repair Wood Weapon","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":["Interlude","Errand"],"description":"Errand. You repair a broken carpentry weapon."},{"id":"rescue","name":"Rescue","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Spell","Teleport"],"description":"You Teleport a willing ally within range to an empty square next to you. If the target is mounted, you may also teleport their mount together with the target."},{"id":"rescue---drop","name":"Rescue & Drop","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"Must be mounted.","keywords":["-"],"description":"You pick up a willing ally and put them on your mount. They travel with you on the back of your mount until either you or they spend 0 AP or 1 RP to place them back on the ground. An ally that is being rescued can not take any other actions until they are dropped.\n\nOnly 1 ally can be rescued at a time."},{"id":"resheathe","name":"Resheathe","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Not in Iai state.","keywords":[],"description":"You regain the Iai state. In addition, your next Iai strike this encounter gains Full Pierce."},{"id":"resist-poison","name":"Resist Poison","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You're about to take Poison damage or become afflicted with a Poison.","keywords":["Rapid"],"description":"You gain Resist Poison, which gives you Damage Reduction 100 against the triggering damage. You also resist the application of the poison, negating its effect."},{"id":"resistant-venom","name":"Resistant Venom","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":["Persist"],"description":"Your Poison effects gain Persist 1."},{"id":"revealing-light","name":"Revealing Light","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You clap your hands and send out a pulse of solar light in a 40ft radius around you. All creatures within that range are immediately revealed, canceling any stealth, invisibility or similar technique to hide themselves. They glow brightly until the start of your next turn, giving them a -20 penalty to stealth checks."},{"id":"reverse-polarity","name":"Reverse Polarity","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"Must be in a crafting session.","keywords":[],"description":"You invert the roll result. (1 becomes 10, 2 becomes 9 etc)"},{"id":"ricochet","name":"Ricochet","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"Pistol only.","keywords":[],"description":"You may make a Light (1 AP) or Heavy (2 AP) Attack against the target. The target does not benefit from Light Cover against this attack."},{"id":"rider---mount-as-one","name":"Rider & Mount As One","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["-"],"description":"While you are mounted and not flying you and your mount are considered the same entity for the purposes of what can target you. This means that while you are mounted, your mount cannot be targeted by anything (including allied effects) unless the effect specifically says it does. Any debuff or buff on you also affects your mount's movement and speed as if it was placed on the mount."},{"id":"riposte","name":"Riposte","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"May only be used after you use the Parry fencer ability and you regained the RP.","keywords":["Counter"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target that you used your Parry ability against."},{"id":"riposte-ii","name":"Riposte II","costLabel":"0 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"May only be used after you use the Parry fencer ability and you regained the RP.","keywords":["Counter"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target that you used your Parry ability against."},{"id":"rock-fang","name":"Rock Fang","costLabel":"3 AP","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Pickaxe only","keywords":["Sunder"],"description":"Make a heavy attack against the target. On damage the target is affected by Armor Sunder 2, reducing their guard by 2 until the start of your next turn. This attack also immediately benefits from the Sunder effect."},{"id":"ruminant-metabolism","name":"Ruminant Metabolism","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You can go a day without eating before starvation applies."},{"id":"running-shot","name":"Running Shot","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"Must be mounted and taking a movement action.","keywords":["-"],"description":"You make a Heavy attack against the target."},{"id":"rushing-knee-drop","name":"Rushing Knee Drop","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 RP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"15ft","requirement":"An enemy is prone in range.","keywords":["Sure Hit","Unarmed Strike","Jump"],"description":"You may spend either 1 AP or 1 RP to leap up to 15 ft and crush a prone enemy within 5ft with a knee attack, dealing Light Damage. This movement does not provoke attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"ryujin-s-mastery","name":"Ryujin's Mastery","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You gain one of Elemental Mastery of your choice from the following options: Fire, Water, Ice, Wind, Lightning, or Earth."},{"id":"sable-grace","name":"Sable Grace","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"You become the target of an attack. Can only be used during the night.","keywords":["Stealth"],"description":"You take the Dodge action against the triggering attack. You remove Lock-On from this attack and treat your Dodge as 99 against it."},{"id":"sacrament","name":"Sacrament","costLabel":"2 AP, 0 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"0","otherCosts":"","range":"Touch","requirement":"-","keywords":["Enchantment"],"description":"You touch one willing ally’s or your own weapon and bless it. Until the end of the encounter, the weapon deals Holy Damage and grants a +1 Power Enchantment."},{"id":"sanctity-aura","name":"Sanctity Aura","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Aura"],"description":"You project an aura 30ft around you that blesses your allies.\n\nWhen an ally makes an attack as part of one of your Gun Paladin abilities, they may choose to make the damage type of that attack the same as your Holy Weapon damage type."},{"id":"sapping-ward","name":"Sapping Ward","costLabel":"2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Touch","requirement":"-","keywords":["Bounded Field","Spell"],"description":"A ward that can be placed on a normal-sized room or can be combined to ward off a house or larger area. Each ward can cover a 20ft radius and for each Sapping Ward placed in the same area as another Sapping Ward, this radius increases by 20ft (For example, 60ft with 3 Sapping Wards) If someone other than you enters the area, they must make a save against your Potency or become Weakened. Non-heroic units that enter the area must make a save or become Stunned instead. These conditions last while they remain inside the field and for an additional 2 rounds after exiting it. Casting this takes 10 minutes of uninterrupted casting. Once triggered, the field remains active for 5 more minutes before vanishing. You may at the time of casting choose a number of people equal to your Focus that can enter the area without triggering the ward. If not triggered, Sapping Ward lasts until you remove it. While it remains, your maximum mana is reduced by 2 for each instance of Sapping Ward you have active. This is considered a tier 2 ward."},{"id":"saprophytic-bolt","name":"Saprophytic Bolt","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Healing","Spell","Earth"],"description":"You may make a Light Attack against the target, dealing Earth damage. On damage, the current host of Spore Symbiote is Healed for your Power + 3."},{"id":"scarecrow-s-gaze","name":"Scarecrow's Gaze","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Fear","Mind Affecting","Circuit"],"description":"You summon the appearance of whatever someone fears the most. Every enemy within range must make a Save against your potency. On failure, they may not walk closer to you until the start of your next turn unless they have no valid targets to attack without doing so."},{"id":"scent","name":"Scent","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You gain a +5 Expertise bonus to Perception (Smell)."},{"id":"scent-of-blood","name":"Scent of Blood","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Quick"],"description":"You sniff the air and become aware of all targets within range that have below half of their maximum HP. This does not reveal their HP percentage."},{"id":"schadenfreude","name":"Schadenfreude","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You are targeted by an attack.","keywords":["Dark"],"description":"You redirect an attack to another ally in range of the triggering attack. If they don't react to this, your next Malevolent Phantasm ignores the requirement and costs no mana."},{"id":"scorching-reprisal","name":"Scorching Reprisal","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"An enemy provokes an attack of opportunity.","keywords":[],"description":"You make a Heavy attack of opportunity against the target. Your next basic attack of opportunity against that target costs 0 RP."},{"id":"scout-s-retreat","name":"Scout's Retreat","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"No known allies within 300ft of you","keywords":["Stealth"],"description":"You disengage and may move up to two times your speed away from enemies towards the closest escape point."},{"id":"scouting-ahead","name":"Scouting Ahead","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"-","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"When traveling stealthily across the map, you can choose to move slightly ahead of the party when moving. If you do, you treat your roll as the lowest roll of the party."},{"id":"scry","name":"Scry","costLabel":"4 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"5000ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Divination","Spell","Concentration"],"description":"You designate a point that you can see within range, creating a magical ward at that point. If you focus you can shift your perception to that ward and see and hear everything within line of the sight of that ward in a 30ft radius. The ward can persist as long as you want over any distance, but you can only have one instance of Scry active at a time.\n\nThe ward is invisible and inaudible, but can be detected through magical means."},{"id":"scurry-away","name":"Scurry Away","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"After using the Disengage or Feint action, your movement speed increases by 10ft until the end of your turn."},{"id":"seal-cloak","name":"Seal Cloak","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Transformation"],"description":"You manifest and don a seal cloak that has been with you since you were born, transforming you into your Seal Form. While in seal form you gain a swim speed of 80 feet but you can only take basic actions while in Seal Form and you are proficient in melee attacking without weapons in seal form. While in Seal Form, you can hold your breath underwater for up to 2 hours and your land speed is reduced to 5. You can remove the cloak for 0 AP."},{"id":"sealing-talisman","name":"Sealing Talisman","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"The target has 0 RP. Must have a Sealing Talisman in hand.","keywords":["Stun"],"description":"You attach a Sealing Talisman to the target. Non-heroics become Stunned immediately, while heroic targets must spend 2 AP to remove it from themselves. If they do not remove it by the end of their turn, they become Stunned. While the talisman remains attached, the target is stunned. Anyone within touching distance of the talisman may spend 2 AP to remove the talisman, immediately removing the stun effect. If the talisman is not removed, it lasts until the end of encounter or until the target takes damage. A person can only be affected by 1 Sealing Talisman at a time."},{"id":"second-tremor","name":"Second Tremor","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"An enemy stands up from prone or takes falling damage without falling prone.","keywords":["Earth"],"description":"The enemy falls prone and takes Light damage."},{"id":"secret-art---revitalize","name":"Secret Art: Revitalize","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"Ally is downed.","keywords":["Healing","Overcharge","Secret Art","Spell"],"description":"You pray for a Downed ally. The ally’s HP becomes 0 and then heals for your Power x 3. They may stand up from prone after this healing.\n\nOvercharge: You may pay X extra mana to make the target heal + 7 HP for every additional point of mana spent.\n\nThis ability does not work on Mortally Wounded allies."},{"id":"secret-art--7-points-of-death","name":"Secret Art: 7 Points of Death","costLabel":"3 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Target is below half HP and has at least 1 Mark of Death.","keywords":["Full Pierce","Secret Art"],"description":"You make a number of Precise Attacks up to the amount of Marks of Death on the target. Each attack deals damage equal to your Focus + Power instead of rolling for damage."},{"id":"secret-art--absolute-compression","name":"Secret Art: Absolute Compression","costLabel":"4 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Gravity","Full Pierce","Trick Attack"],"description":"You make an attack against the target that deals Double Heavy Physical(Crushing) damage."},{"id":"secret-art--all-of-creation","name":"Secret Art: All of Creation","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art"],"description":"Change the damage type of the target attack into any damage type except True."},{"id":"secret-art--ambush-shot","name":"Secret Art: Ambush Shot","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"Enemy must be unaware of your presence. Can only be used on the first turn of an encounter and must be your first attack.","keywords":["Secret Art","Sure Hit","Full Pierce"],"description":"You make a Heavy attack that does maximum damage instead of rolling. This attack does not break your stealth."},{"id":"secret-art--anima-synthesis-form","name":"Secret Art: Anima Synthesis Form","costLabel":"0 RP, 3 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must have the required gene in your gene inventory.","keywords":["Secret Art","Transformation"],"description":"You consume a gene and transform, granting yourself all abilities of the chimera subrace of that corresponding gene.\n\nThis lasts until the end of the encounter.\n\nIn addition, learning this skill grants you +1 to your gene inventory for the Biohacking skill. Despite being transformed, you can still use Gene Activation to add additional abilities.\n\nYou cannot obtain and use abilities that require an IP or EP to use through this ability."},{"id":"secret-art--assassinate","name":"Secret Art: Assassinate","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Target must be marked by Death Mark. One-handed weapons only.","keywords":["Full Pierce","Secret Art","Sure Hit"],"description":"You attack the target for Heavy Damage.\n\nIf you surprised the enemy, are currently stealthed and have not been spotted by an enemy this entire encounter, this attack deals double heavy damage. You may move next to an enemy and still qualify as being stealthed and not spotted, provided you use this ability immediately after that movement ends."},{"id":"secret-art--beaver-timber-fang","name":"Secret Art: Beaver Timber Fang","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"","keywords":["Sure Hit","Secret Art"],"description":"Make a normal heavy attack against the target. Afterwards make a light attack against the target with Sure Hit that immediately renders the target prone, even if the damage is reduced to 0."},{"id":"secret-art--bestial-wrath","name":"Secret Art: Bestial Wrath","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"Can only target your summoned animal.","keywords":["Secret Art"],"description":"Your summon gains Bestial Wrath and AP equal to its maximum AP they may immediately use. Bestial Wrath gives +2 Focus and +2 Power and prevents the summon from dropping below 1 HP. This effect lasts for 3 rounds or until the summon is reduced to 1 HP."},{"id":"secret-art--black-hole","name":"Secret Art: Black Hole","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Gravity","Secret Art"],"description":"You create a Black Hole at a target location within range. When you cast this and when you pay upkeep, all enemies within 120ft of the black hole must make a save or get pulled 20ft towards it.\n\nAll enemies within 120ft of the black hole that are moving away from it are considered slowed for that movement.\n\nUpkeep: 1 Mana. Instead of paying upkeep, you may detonate the Black Hole making a Heavy attack against all enemies within 15ft of the black hole."},{"id":"secret-art--bladestorm","name":"Secret Art: Bladestorm","costLabel":"2 AP, 4 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"4","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Two-handed weapons only. Slashing weapons only.","keywords":["Secret Art","Stance","Upkeep","Scatter"],"description":"You enter a stance in which you continuously spin your weapon around your body. When activating this ability, you may make a Heavy attack against all enemies within your melee weapon range. While the stance lasts you may make a Heavy attack against all enemies within your melee weapon range at the start of your turn.\n\nYou can move while in this stance. If you move close enough to an enemy for them to be within your melee weapon range, you may make a Heavy attack against them.\n\nYou can only attack a creature once per round through this ability, regardless of how many times you move closer to them.\n\nUpkeep: 2 Mana, 1 AP"},{"id":"secret-art--bloody-ritual","name":"Secret Art: Bloody Ritual","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art","Slow","Blanketing","Sure Hit"],"description":"You create a blood tether to all enemies within range, causing them to be Slowed. The tether lasts until the start of your next turn or until they move out of the range of this ability.\n\nAt the start of your next turn, the tethers explode, dealing Heavy damage to all tethered enemies as it sucks the life energy from them. For every enemy dealt damage with this ability, you recover 1 Mana or 5 HP (your choice). If an enemy dies while under the effect of the tether but before it explodes, you also gain this regeneration effect."},{"id":"secret-art--chase-the-horizon","name":"Secret Art: Chase the Horizon","costLabel":"0 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be mounted.","keywords":["Secret Art"],"description":"You focus on a single enemy and maintain a constant position from them. Whenever the target moves, you may move the same amount as they did (up to your movement speed) away from them for 0 RP. This movement does not provoke attacks of opportunity from the target, but does provoke from other enemies.\n\n Every time this happens, you may make a Light attack against the target with a ranged weapon. If the target spends multiple AP on a single movement action, you may make an amount of Light attacks equal to the AP they spent.\n\nLasts until the start of your next turn or until you can no longer see the target."},{"id":"secret-art--checkmate","name":"Secret Art: Checkmate","costLabel":"4 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art"],"description":"You may move all your pieces as if you used Move Piece on them."},{"id":"secret-art--divine-judgement","name":"Secret Art: Divine Judgement","costLabel":"2 AP, 4 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"4","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Target has your Mark of Justice on them.","keywords":["Secret Art","Sure Hit","Full Pierce"],"description":"You make a Heavy attack that deals Holy damage against the target. If your target’s HP is lower than the max damage your attack would deal, this attack gains Full Pierce and does maximum damage instead of rolling.\n\nThis calculation only involves your base damage (Base weapon damage + the power). Any other effects added to the damage such as Heavy Blade's bonus damage, Anathema on target etc do not affect the calculation and aren't maximized.\n\nAn enemy reduced to 0 HP or lower with this ability is immediately killed."},{"id":"secret-art--divine-shield","name":"Secret Art: Divine Shield","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art"],"description":"Until the start of your next turn, you gain Damage Reduction 1000 against all damage types, but you only deal half damage.\n\nYou gain 2 AP.\n\nMust be used as the first action in your turn."},{"id":"secret-art--double-accel","name":"Secret Art: Double Accel","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art","Stealth"],"description":"You gain 4 AP. Your AP recovery is lowered by 3 until the end of your next turn."},{"id":"secret-art--dragonslaying-jump","name":"Secret Art: Dragonslaying Jump","costLabel":"4 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"Target must be airborne, polearm only.","keywords":["Full Pierce","Jump","Overcharge","Secret Art","Sure Hit"],"description":"You Jump up to the target, not provoking any attacks of opportunity, and make a Heavy Attack against it. On damage, the target plummets to the ground taking falling damage as normal. Overcharge: You may spend additional AP on this ability to increase the range by 60ft for every extra AP spent. If this increases the AP cost to more than what you currently have, it gains the Setup keyword."},{"id":"secret-art--dynamic-duo","name":"Secret Art: Dynamic Duo","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"","keywords":["Challenge","Secret Art"],"description":"You challenge all enemies in range until the start of your next turn. Any time you would be allowed to make an Attack of Opportunity, your Soulmate may make it instead. They may Sidestep up to their speed before making each Attack of Opportunity."},{"id":"secret-art--earthquake","name":"Secret Art: Earthquake","costLabel":"4 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"160ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Spell","Earth","Secret Art","Scatter"],"description":"You make a Light attack that deals Earth damage against all enemies in range that are touching the ground. On damage, they fall prone.\n\nYou also make a Light attack that deals Earth damage against all magically created walls and similar inanimate objects created by magic. You deal 10x damage against those targets."},{"id":"secret-art--efficient-spirit-control","name":"Secret Art: Efficient Spirit Control","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art"],"description":"You reduce the cost of your next non-healing keyword action by 2 mana. This cannot reduce the mana cost below 0.\n\nAlso resets your Circuits, allowing abilities with the Circuit keyword to be used for their reduced mana cost once more."},{"id":"secret-art--endless-waltz","name":"Secret Art: Endless Waltz","costLabel":"4 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Killing Blow","Secret Art"],"description":"You make two Light Attacks against the same target. On damage of this attack, you may repeat this attack for 0 AP.\n\nKilling Blow: You may move up to twice your speed without provoking attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"secret-art--entropic-magic-pulse","name":"Secret Art: Entropic Magic Pulse","costLabel":"1 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"200ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art","Dispel"],"description":"You send out a wave of energy that disrupts spirit circuits that cancels all temporary magic effects in range. All non-permanent effects within range that are created by an ability with the Spell or Enchantment keyword are affected. Spells that do not have a time limit listed or create a permanent effect such as a Geomancer's fissure are not affected.\n\nBounded Fields and Secret Arts cannot be removed by this ability.\n\nIn addition, artifices cannot be used by anyone except you until the end of your next turn."},{"id":"secret-art--everything--everywhere--all-at-once","name":"Secret Art: Everything, Everywhere, All At Once","costLabel":"3 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Secret Art"],"description":"You make a Heavy Attack against the enemy.\n\nYou may then repeat this attack from each of your past selves and may target the same enemy multiple times."},{"id":"secret-art--fan-the-hammer","name":"Secret Art: Fan the hammer","costLabel":"4 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"20ft","requirement":"Pistol only","keywords":["Secret Art"],"description":"You may make 4 Heavy Attacks against the target. Afterwards, the weapon used for this ability cannot be used again until the end of the encounter.\n\nIf an enemy reacts to this ability with a Dodge or Block type reaction, that reaction is valid for all 4 attacks."},{"id":"secret-art--forbid","name":"Secret Art: Forbid","costLabel":"0 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Mystic Eye","Secret Art","Mind Affecting"],"description":"You choose a target and pick between basic actions or abilities.\n\nUntil the start of your next turn, any time the target does the chosen action, they take Full Pierce damage equal to your Focus per AP spent on it."},{"id":"secret-art--gae-bolg","name":"Secret Art: Gae Bolg","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Polearm only.","keywords":["Secret Art","Sure Hit"],"description":"Make a Heavy attack against the target. Unless your accuracy roll is a 1, your roll is treated as if you rolled a 20 and it gains Sure Hit.\n\nIt is treated as a critical hit even though it's Sure Hit, unless the target blocks."},{"id":"secret-art--galaxy-stop","name":"Secret Art: Galaxy Stop","costLabel":"3 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"2000ft Radius","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art","Spell"],"description":"You create a space-time anomaly that freezes time itself in a local area for a short while, affecting all but the strong-willed. All non-heroic units in range cannot take any actions until the end of their next turn."},{"id":"secret-art--gate-of-fate","name":"Secret Art: Gate of Fate","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"An ally rolls a 1.","keywords":["Divination","Secret Art","Aid"],"description":"You subvert fate and a bad end, twisting reality into its most fortunate outcome. When a target ally rolls a 1, you can instead change it to a 20."},{"id":"secret-art--guiding-shot","name":"Secret Art: Guiding Shot","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art","Sure Hit"],"description":"You may make a Heavy attack against the target. The target may spend 1 RP to avoid the attack. If they do, you may Sidestep them up to 20ft in a direction of your choice and then trigger a Place Trap effect, provided you have at least one set up.\n\nThis trap effect does not count towards your per encounter limitation. You may not Sidestep an enemy into a hazard (such as off a cliff or into fire) apart from your trap, unless the target has nowhere else to go.\n\nAlternatively, you may choose to move an enemy into a Bear Trap you set up within the 20ft movement instead of a Place Trap effect. You can only choose one of these two options, not both."},{"id":"secret-art--jade-skin","name":"Secret Art: Jade Skin","costLabel":"0 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You are attacked by a Melee attack.","keywords":["Secret Art","Disarm"],"description":"You take the Block action against the triggering attack. If you reduce the damage to 0, the attacker becomes Disarmed until the start of their next turn."},{"id":"secret-art--life-bet","name":"Secret Art: Life Bet","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art"],"description":"You reduce your HP to 1 and make a Heavy attack against the target. You gain a bonus to the damage roll of this attack equal to the amount of HP you lost through this ability.\n\nIf this attack fails to meet the base evasion of the target, the HP you lost is refunded. It still counts as your one secret art use of the fight regardless."},{"id":"secret-art--life-sacrifice","name":"Secret Art: Life Sacrifice","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Healing","Secret Art","Aid"],"description":"You lose HP until your HP reaches 1. Target ally within range recovers that much HP. Any HP that exceeds the target’s max HP becomes temporary HP.\n\nThis HP loss cannot be mitigated in any way and ignores temporary HP. This does not trigger effects that would trigger upon taking damage."},{"id":"secret-art--lifesaver","name":"Secret Art: Lifesaver","costLabel":"4 AP, 5 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"5","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art","Shield","Spell"],"description":"The target gains temporary HP until the end of the encounter equal to their missing HP."},{"id":"secret-art--lightning-field","name":"Secret Art: Lightning Field","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Lightning","Secret Art","Spell","Upkeep"],"description":"You conjure a statically charged field around you, applying Static X where X equals your Focus x 3 to all enemies within 30ft of you. Enemies already afflicted by Static immediately take damage equal to 3 + half the static value. While within your Lightning Field, the Static on enemies is not removed at the end of their turn.\n\nThis field lasts until the end of your next turn.\n\nUpkeep: You may pay 1 Mana at the start of your turn to repeat the initial effect and extend the duration of the field by 1 turn."},{"id":"secret-art--lightning-release","name":"Secret Art: Lightning Release","costLabel":"0 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art","Transformation"],"description":"You infuse yourself with Lightning and gain Lightning Release until the end of the encounter, allowing you to deal Lightning damage with your unarmed attacks and immediately enter the Heavenly Lightning Stance. While this lasts, you also gain the following benefits:\n\n- Your movement speed is doubled.\n- You can make an additional attack when you use Double Punch.\n- When making an unarmed attack, your critical threshold is lowered by 1 (19-20 base). Whenever you hit with a critical hit with an unarmed attack, the attack arcs to a different enemy within 20ft of the original target. This attack uses the same attack roll and damage, but cannot arc again.\nIf you ever leave the Lightning Stance, you lose the benefit of this."},{"id":"secret-art--meteor","name":"Secret Art: Meteor","costLabel":"2 AP, 4 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"4","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Fire","Overcharge","Spell","Sure Hit","Secret Art","Blanketing"],"description":"You mark a 30x30ft area and begin summoning a meteor to strike it at the start of your next turn. Those in the area when it lands take Heavy Fire Damage. You cannot use the Prepare action on this ability. Overcharge: You may spend extra AP on this ability to increase the damage and size of it. For every extra 2 AP spent on it, the size increases by 5ft and the damage increases by your Power. If the Overcharge increases the AP cost to above 4, this ability gains the Setup keyword. You mark the area of this ability when you have finished spending all AP on it and not before. The maximum AP you can spend on this ability is 16 AP."},{"id":"secret-art--moving-castle","name":"Secret Art: Moving Castle","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Secret Art","Aura","Upkeep"],"description":"You project a defensive aura up to 15ft around you, granting all allies (excluding yourself) the Bulwark buff. While under the effects of Bulwark, allies take 3 less damage.\n\nWhile projecting this aura, you may spend 0 RP to sidestep up to your movement. After you do so, you may not do so again until the start of your next turn.\n\nUpkeep: You must spend 1 mana at the start of your turn to continue this effect."},{"id":"secret-art--mushroomize","name":"Secret Art: Mushroomize","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"Must be used on your Spore Symbiote target that is in the Downed state.","keywords":["Healing","Spell","Upkeep","Concentration"],"description":"You fill your target with mycelium from your spore symbiote, allowing them to act fully despite being Downed. Removing Spore Symbiote from the target cancels this effect. This effect ends at the start of your next turn unless you spend 1 mana to continue the effect. When paying upkeep, if the target is below 0 HP, heal the target for your power + 3.\n\nThis effect ends if the target’s HP is reduced to negative their maximum HP amount.\n\nYou can use 1 RP instead of 2 AP to use this ability."},{"id":"secret-art--mythical-awakening","name":"Secret Art: Mythical Awakening","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be mounted on a mount mentioned in the description.","keywords":["Secret Art"],"description":"You channel your power into your mount, allowing it to unleash a devastating attack based on what type of mount it is.\n\nPegasus: Bellerophon: You Sidestep towards a target within 60ft and make a Heavy attack against it. This attack has Lock-on and costs 1 RP and 2 Mana\n\nWyvern: Reginliev: You make a Heavy attack against all enemies in a 5ft wide line up to a point within 60ft. You also make a Heavy attack against all enemies within 10ft of the selected point, though enemies can also take an attack from this ability once. This attack costs 2 AP and 2 Mana.\n\nDragonfly: Darting Mirage: You move at incredible speed and create several illusionary afterimages in your wake. Until the start of your next turn, every attack against you or your mount that is not a critical hit or does not have the Sure Hit keyword automatically misses. This is an Illusion effect. This ability costs 0 AP and 4 Mana.\n\nAll these attacks are made with your mount’s stats instead of your own."},{"id":"secret-art--nightcaller","name":"Secret Art: Nightcaller","costLabel":"0 AP, 4 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"4","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art","Stealth"],"description":"Until the end of the encounter, it is considered night for all your abilities and items that are affected by it."},{"id":"secret_art:_overcharge","name":"Secret Art: Overcharge","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Secret Art"],"description":"Reduces the mana cost of your next Spell cast this turn by 3. You cannot gain mana from this."},{"id":"secret-art--override","name":"Secret Art: Override","costLabel":"3 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be mounted.","keywords":["Secret Art","Sure Hit","Pass","Blanketing"],"description":"You make a Heavy attack against all enemies in a line and move through them. You keep moving through enemies until you reach an empty spot you can stand in. If there is no valid end position due to an ally occupying the spot or terrain (such as a wall) being in the way, you cannot use this ability."},{"id":"secret-art--perfect-repetition","name":"Secret Art: Perfect Repetition","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Secret Art"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target. On damage, on the next turn, you may repeat this attack against the same target using the same accuracy check as the initial attack. You may continue to repeat this attack on subsequent turns until you spend a turn not using this move or if the attack fails to deal damage."},{"id":"secret-art--pyroblast","name":"Secret Art: Pyroblast","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Fire","Secret Art","Spell"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target that deals double Heavy Fire Damage. This attack gains Lock On against a target that has the Burning condition that you inflicted on it."},{"id":"secret-art--razor-hurricane","name":"Secret Art: Razor Hurricane","costLabel":"4 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Concentration","Full Pierce","Secret Art","Spell","Wind","Scatter"],"description":"You create a rapid spinning hurricane with a 15x15 size and 50ft in height in the target location. All creatures caught in the hurricane immediately take Wind Light Damage and are pushed out of the Hurricane. Every creature that enters the hurricane immediately takes Wind Light Damage and must succeed at a save against your Potency or be pushed back 20ft. Leaving the hurricane does no damage and requires no save. Upkeep: You must spend 1 Mana and 2 AP at the start of each turn or the spell ends. When you pay this Upkeep, you may move the hurricane up to 20ft. Any creature that comes into contact with the hurricane during this move takes damage and must make a save as if they had entered it."},{"id":"secret-art--rewind","name":"Secret Art: Rewind","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Can only be used on your turn.","keywords":["Secret Art"],"description":"You rewind time to before your last action. All results based on your last action are reversed- All HP, Mana, AP and RP are returned to how they were. The ability you used in that action is no longer considered used, but this ability is."},{"id":"secret-art--ride-of-the-valkyrie","name":"Secret Art: Ride of the Valkyrie","costLabel":"4 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be mounted.","keywords":["Secret Art","Sidestep","Healing","Pass"],"description":"You Sidestep up to your speed and can move through enemies for this movement. You and every ally you pass through are healed for 11 + (Power x 2).\n\nThis movement must always be in a straight line, regardless of your mount type."},{"id":"secret-art--seventeen-dissection","name":"Secret Art: Seventeen Dissection","costLabel":"3 AP","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Slashing weapons only.","keywords":["Full Pierce","Secret Art","Sure Hit"],"description":"You deal 17 true damage to the target. If this damage lowers the target’s HP to 0 or lower, they immediately die.\nIf the target of this attack is a non-heroic unit, they instantly die regardless of their remaining HP."},{"id":"secret-art--shatter","name":"Secret Art: Shatter","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Attack must be made with a Blacksmith's Hammer.","keywords":["Secret Art","Sure Hit"],"description":"You make a Heavy Attack against the target using a Blacksmith’s Hammer. If the target chooses to Block the attack, they gain 100 damage reduction against it. If they do, choose one equipped non-divine arms weapon in their hand that has equal or less crafted enhancements than your hammer and destroy that item, giving it the Broken condition."},{"id":"secret-art--shield-wall","name":"Secret Art: Shield Wall","costLabel":"1 RP, 6 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"6","otherCosts":"","range":"20ft","requirement":"Usable when you are the target of an ability that affects an area, using a shield.","keywords":["Secret Art"],"description":"You and your allies in range gain Shield Wall, which reduces the damage they take from the triggering attack by 75."},{"id":"secret-art--shock---awe","name":"Secret Art: Shock & Awe","costLabel":"4 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art"],"description":"You and up to 3 other allies within range gain 3 AP they must spend immediately. On their next turn, they regain 1 less AP.\n\nThese AP may not be spent on Setup abilities and normal once per turn ability limitations apply."},{"id":"secret-art--skeletal-champion","name":"Secret Art: Skeletal Champion","costLabel":"4 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Summon","Secret Art","Upkeep","Overcharge"],"description":"You drain the surrounding area of energy and form a skeletal champion until the end of the encounter. (Stats can be found in the Monster page)\n\nThis champion takes 2 of your summon limit. Any zombies you had active when you summoned this are instead converted into temporary HP for the champion at a rate of 5 HP per zombie.\n\nThe champion acts after you on the initiative, but cannot take AP actions on the turn it is summoned.\n\nUpkeep: 2 AP\n\nOvercharge: You may spend 5 mana to give your summon the ability to act on the turn it is summoned."},{"id":"secret-art--spectrum-blade","name":"Secret Art: Spectrum Blade","costLabel":"1 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Enchantment","Secret Art"],"description":"Until the end of the encounter, you enchant your weapon with every single element. When using Elemental Strike or Elemental Sweep, you may choose which effect you want regardless of the damage type your attack deals. When you deal damage, you apply the damage type that would deal the most damage.\n\nIn addition, your weapon gains a +1 Power bonus until the end of the encounter. If it already had a +1 Power bonus through an enchantment, this bonus is instead increased to +2.\n\nIf you are not holding the enchanted weapon at the start of your turn, your weapon loses this benefit."},{"id":"secret-art--spirit-stigma","name":"Secret Art: Spirit Stigma","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art","Spell","Dark"],"description":"You stigmatize the targets spirit, they are inflicted with Spirit Stigma until the start of your next turn. A target with Spirit Stigma counts as a willing ally for your Eremancer abilities and damaging them fulfills the Malevolent Phantasm requirement."},{"id":"secret-art--summon-eidolon","name":"Secret Art: Summon Eidolon","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Summon","Spell","Upkeep","Secret Art","Overcharge"],"description":"Your contracted Eidolon hears your call and sends a proxy of themselves to fight for you. The Eidolon called and the costs are dependent on your attunement. Lasts up to 5 minutes. You must pay the upkeep cost under the Eidolon’s Summon Skill or the Eidolon vanishes.\n\nUnless the summon has a skill that says otherwise, a summon acts after you on initiative, but cannot act the round it is summoned, except for RP actions.\n\nOvercharge: You may spend 5 mana to give your summon the ability to act on the turn it is summoned."},{"id":"secret-art--surge-of-elements","name":"Secret Art: Surge of Elements","costLabel":"4 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Secret Art","Overcharge"],"description":"You channel all masteries of the elements and fire a barrage of elemental bolts at the target.\n\nYou make 7 light attacks, doing Arcane, Fire, Water, Frost, Wind, Lightning and Earth damage respectively.\n\nOvercharge: You may spend one more mana to make additional Light attacks, one that does Holy damage and one that does Dark damage."},{"id":"secret-art--the-grand-theater","name":"Secret Art: The Grand Theater","costLabel":"4 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art"],"description":"All allies within range may sidestep up to their movement speed.\n\nYou may Sidestep all enemies within range up to their movement speed.\n\nAfter all targets have moved, everyone that was originally in range of this ability immediately gains 2 AP they must spend on attacks against other creatures if possible."},{"id":"secret-art--titan-blade","name":"Secret Art: Titan Blade","costLabel":"2 AP, 4 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"4","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"Two-Handed melee weapons only.","keywords":["Sure Hit","Full Pierce","Secret Art","Scatter"],"description":"You greatly increase the size and weight of your weapons, then slam them down in a direction. You make a melee Heavy attack against all enemies in a 15ft wide line up to the range. On damage, a target is knocked prone.\n\nAfter the initial hit, a shockwave follows. You make another Heavy attack against any enemy still in the original line’s range. This second attack has the Sure Hit and Full Pierce qualities against a prone target."},{"id":"secret-art--transmute-proto-armatae","name":"Secret Art: Transmute Proto Armatae","costLabel":"2 AP, 4 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"4","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art"],"description":"You touch the ground, transmuting a Proto Armatae of your own design. The Proto Armatae lifts you up and immediately encases you into its cockpit. The Proto Armatae is 15ft tall and is a large creature that occupies a 15ftx15ft space. All creatures and moveable objects surrounding the Proto Armatae are pushed back away from its zone of control in a burst of steam. The Armatae also gains a temporary shield with 20 HP that disappears at the start of your next turn.\n\nYou must use your own actions to cause the Proto Armatae to move and attack. You can eject from a transmutation hatch on the top at the center of the Proto Armatae for 1 AP, in which the Proto Armatae stops functioning. When you re-enter you must close the hatch for 1 AP before the Proto Armatae functions again.\n\nThe Proto Armatae has health equal to 15 + 5x Focus and it uses your AP and RP for actions. You can channel your Transmuter abilities through the Proto Armatae, and Transmute Weapon can create a giant sized weapon for the Armatae to use.\n\nYou may also spend 1 RP to use this ability instead of the AP cost.\n\nOnly usable once. You regain the use of this ability when you gain an Interlude Point.\n\nProto Armatae\n\nHP: –\n\nEvasion: 9/19\n\nGuard: 4/14\n\nMini Transmutation Cannon (Right Arm)\n\nCost: 0 AP\n\nRange: 40ft\n\nDescription: Fires a mini transmutation cannon of deconstructive energy making a light attack against a target. Doesn’t provoke attacks of opportunity.\n\nHumanoid Gripper (Left Arm)\n\nDescription: Humanoid Gripper can make all basic attacks. It is proficient in any transmuted weapon it holds. Its regular melee attacks deal light weapon damage and any transmuted weapon it wields gains the benefit of that weapon category."},{"id":"secret-art--true-serenity","name":"Secret Art: True Serenity","costLabel":"1 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Secret Art","Stance"],"description":"You enter the Serene Water stance and gain an additional +17 bonus to your Evasion until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"secret-art--tsubame-gaeshi","name":"Secret Art: Tsubame Gaeshi","costLabel":"4 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Katana only.","keywords":["Lock On","Secret Art","Sure Hit"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target 3 times. On the first miss, the next attacks gain Lock On. On the second miss, the next attack gains Sure Hit. These only apply to attacks made during Tsubame Gaeshi."},{"id":"secret-art--ultimate-spell","name":"Secret Art: Ultimate Spell","costLabel":"0 AP, 4 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"4","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"The next Spell you cast this turn with an AP cost lower than 5 deals true damage."},{"id":"secret-art--unholy-strength","name":"Secret Art: Unholy Strength","costLabel":"2 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art","Upkeep"],"description":"You Gain Unholy Strength which grants +2 Power and Focus. While Unholy Strength is active your attacks/abilities that use your melee weapon to deal physical damage inflict Dark Damage instead and your Bone Armor will not break from damage.\n\nUpkeep: 1 Mana."},{"id":"secret-art--unstoppable-onslaught","name":"Secret Art: Unstoppable Onslaught","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be mounted.","keywords":["Secret Art","Sure Hit","Mind Affecting","Fear","Challenge","Shaken"],"description":"You may move up to your speed in a line. All enemies you pass through and all enemies within 15ft of your ending position take Light damage, become Challenged and Shaken until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"secret-art--vanishing-thousand-steps","name":"Secret Art: Vanishing Thousand Steps","costLabel":"0 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art","Sidestep"],"description":"You may sidestep to a target within range and make a Heavy attack against them.\n\nThen, until the end of the turn, you may Sidestep to any enemy you can see as part of a melee attack you are about to make. You gain Windflow stacks as if you spent AP on the movement equal to the AP spent on the attack."},{"id":"secret-art--void","name":"Secret Art: Void","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Mystic Eye","Secret Art"],"description":"You target one buff or passive effect you can identify from a grunt or heroic target within range. It is immediately removed and cannot be re-applied for the rest of the encounter."},{"id":"secret-art--walking-church","name":"Secret Art: Walking Church","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art"],"description":"Blesses the target, granting them the status of a church. Until the end of your next turn, the target gains Damage Reduction 1000 against all damage types."},{"id":"secret-art--whirling-death","name":"Secret Art: Whirling Death","costLabel":"0 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Secret Art","Stance","Scatter"],"description":"You enter the Whirling Death stance, spinning wildly and shooting at enemies within range. While in this Stance you may spend 2 AP to make a basic Light Attack with a pistol against all enemies within 20ft.\n\nWhen you kill an enemy or make them enter the downed state from with this attack, you may repeat the attack.\n\nThe Stance lasts until you enter a different Stance or until you make an attack that is not tied to this ability."},{"id":"secret-art--whiteout","name":"Secret Art: Whiteout","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"2500ft radius on self","requirement":"","keywords":["Encounter Start","Frost","Spell","Upkeep","Concentration","Secret Art"],"description":"You create a sudden snowstorm that obscures sight, creating difficult battle conditions.\n\nAttack accuracy for all affected units is reduced by your Focus and sight range is reduced to 60ft. A creature can only target something within their sight range.\n\nYou and creatures with Frost Immunity are not affected by this ability.\n\nYou may activate this ability as an Encounter Start action during the Encounter Start phase of an encounter. If you do, you do not pay the RP or initial mana cost.\n\nUpkeep: You must pay 2 mana at the start of your turn or the effect ends at the end of that turn."},{"id":"secret-art--within-this-ink--the-perfect-answer","name":"Secret Art: Within This Ink, The Perfect Answer","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Special","requirement":"","keywords":["Flashback","Secret Art"],"description":"You draw and immediately use a special talisman.\n\nThis talisman may have any spell in the base game on it (meaning it’s on the website), though it cannot be a secret or esoteric art. Any costs for this spell must be paid as normal. You must pay the required calligraphy units as if you made the spell yourself. If you can’t pay the required amount, you go into ‘debt’. While in debt, you cannot create any more talisman or use this ability.\n\nTo clear the debt, you must pay the required amount of calligraphy units at any point.\n\nAfter you use this ability, you cannot do so again until the end of the arc."},{"id":"secret-talisman","name":"Secret Talisman","costLabel":"Special","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"Special","range":"Special","requirement":"Special","keywords":["Special"],"description":"You use a talisman you possess that contains a Secret Art. This functions like using a normal talisman. You may only use this once per encounter. Does not count towards your Secret Art usage for this encounter."},{"id":"seismic-shove","name":"Seismic Shove","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"80ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Earth"],"description":"You make a Light attack that deals Earth damage against the target. On damage, you may push the target 5ft in any direction."},{"id":"selective-casting","name":"Selective Casting","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Circuit"],"description":"For the next Spell you cast, you may choose to have it not affect a number of targets equal to your Focus.\n\nOnly affects spells with an instantaneous effect (excluding setup things). Lingering spell effects such as Glittershards cannot be used with Selective Casting."},{"id":"send-to-armory","name":"Send To Armory","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Touch","requirement":"You have a Dimensional Armory active.","keywords":["Spell"],"description":"You touch an item not held or carried by another creature and immediately teleport it to your Dimensional Armory into an unoccupied space (if there is room). If there is no space the spell fails. Some magic items can be rejected by the dimensional armory. Living creatures cannot be teleported into the Dimensional Armory.\n\nOvercharge: You spend 1 minute instead of 2 AP, reducing the mana cost by 1."},{"id":"sense_magic","name":"Sense Magic","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft radius centered on self","requirement":"None","keywords":["Sensory","Spell"],"description":"You can detect active magical effects that aren’t hidden within range.\n\nHidden magical effects may require a Perception or Insight check."},{"id":"separate-wheat-from-chaff","name":"Separate wheat from chaff","costLabel":"3 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"10ft","requirement":"Scythe only","keywords":["Killing Blow","Fear","Mind Affecting","Scatter"],"description":"You make a Light attack against all enemies in range. On damage, you push the target back 5ft. If you landed a Killing Blow, all that took damage become Shaken as well."},{"id":"serene-water-stance","name":"Serene Water Stance","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"An attack against you misses.","keywords":["Stance"],"description":"You enter the Serene Water Stance. While in this Stance, you gain a +3 bonus to your evasion and you may move 5ft everytime an accuracy check against you misses. This movement does not provoke attacks of opportunity. This Stance lasts until you enter a different Stance, you use the Block action or until you move, with the exceptions of this ability and movement abilities with the Unarmed Strike keyword. Making an attack does not cancel this Stance."},{"id":"shade-form","name":"Shade Form","costLabel":"1 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Shadow","Stealth"],"description":"You become like a shade becoming near weightless and gaining the ability to pass through spaces occupied by other creatures. You can also slip through small cracks in walls or doors, as long as they are at least 1inch wide and tall. Upkeep: You must pay 2 mana at the start of each turn or this ability ends. During the night, the mana cost and Upkeep of this is reduced by 2."},{"id":"shadow-cloak","name":"Shadow Cloak","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Shadow","Stealth"],"description":"You cloak yourself in Shadows, giving you a +5 bonus on Stealth checks for 1 hour or until end of encounter. It also allows you to hide even when not behind cover or concealment. During the night, the mana cost of this is reduced by 2."},{"id":"shadow-counter","name":"Shadow Counter","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Must be in Inexorable Shadow Stance.","keywords":["Setup","Unarmed Strike"],"description":"You prepare a powerful heavy attack against a single enemy. This attack deals extra damage based on half your missing health.\n\nIf that enemy provokes an AoO while you are charging this ability, you may immediately use this ability as if you finished charging it."},{"id":"shadow-step","name":"Shadow Step","costLabel":"1 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Shadow","Teleport","Stealth"],"description":"You may Teleport up to twice your movement speed. During the night, the mana cost of this is reduced by 2."},{"id":"share-armor","name":"Share Armor","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"Must be wearing armor.","keywords":["Aid"],"description":"Your ally may treat their guard and block as if they were wearing your armor until the end of the current creature’s turn. If multiple creatures of the same type move on the same initiative, it lasts through all of their turns.\n\nAny temporary increases to the guard/block of this armor (such as through reinforce armor) is not transferred over."},{"id":"shared-defense","name":"Shared Defense","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"Must be dismounted.","keywords":["-"],"description":"Your mount (the last mount you were riding on this arc) may use your defenses instead of its own while within range. In addition, you may spend RP for it while dismounted if your mount is in range."},{"id":"shatter","name":"Shatter","costLabel":"3 AP","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Sound","Scatter"],"description":"Every enemy within range must make a save against your Potency or take Light Damage. Any unattended objects made of glass or a similar vulnerable material also shatter."},{"id":"shatter-time","name":"Shatter Time","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Encounter Start"],"description":"For this encounter you may act during different parts of a round. When you end your turn with AP remaining, you may choose to act immediately after another creature ends their turn. You do not regain AP or RP and these extra actions are not considered turns. You may take these extra actions multiple times during a round, provided you have AP remaining.\n\nYou cannot use Setup abilities during this extra actions."},{"id":"sheet-ice","name":"Sheet Ice","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Frost","Spell","Upkeep"],"description":"You freeze the ground in a 20x20 area, creating difficult terrain that lasts until the end of your next turn. You may use 1 mana per instance of this spell to continue the effect until the end of your next turn."},{"id":"shelter","name":"Shelter","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"Your VIP is the target of an attack.","keywords":[],"description":"The attack targeting your VIP instead targets you. You may use this even if you’re also a target of the attack and both attacks will resolve against you. You also gain the benefits of the Block action against the triggering attack."},{"id":"shield-burst","name":"Shield Burst","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"Target must have temporary HP applied by you.","keywords":["Spell"],"description":"You heal the target for an amount equal to half the temporary HP they have, then all temporary HP on them is removed. All enemies within 5ft of the target must make a save against your Potency or be pushed back 10ft.\n\nYou may use 1 AP instead of 1 RP for this ability."},{"id":"shield-the-fallen","name":"Shield the Fallen","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"Downed ally takes damage from an attack.","keywords":["Aid"],"description":"You give the ally temporary HP equal to the damage they would take from the attack."},{"id":"shieldcrusher","name":"Shieldcrusher","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Two-handed weapons only.","keywords":["Broken"],"description":"You make a Heavy attack against the target. If they Block against this attack and are wielding a shield or greatshield, that shield becomes Broken."},{"id":"shooting-form","name":"Shooting Form","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"-","requirement":"-","keywords":["Rapid"],"description":"You transform a melee weapon you’re holding into a Wand Channeling Weapon or return a transformed weapon back to normal. While transformed, the weapon keeps any relevant enchants and functions exactly like how a wand would. You are considered proficient in this wand, even if you normally wouldn’t be and can fire Arcane Elemental shots with it, even if you normally wouldn’t be able to.\n\nLasts until the end of the encounter, for 5 minutes or until the weapon leaves your possession."},{"id":"silentium","name":"Silentium","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Weapon Range","requirement":"One-handed Thrown Weapon or Sets of missiles Only.","keywords":["Combo","Holy"],"description":"You infuse a light thrown weapon with Sacred Power and Light Attack the target for Light Holy Damage. On damage the weapon disrupts the target’s magic circuits, breaking concentration and preventing the target from using abilities with the Spell keyword. The lodged weapon can be removed for 1 RP or 2 AP, removing the disruption. Combo: If used after Eagle’s Hunt, reduce the AP cost to 0 from 2."},{"id":"single-minded-fury","name":"Single-Minded Fury","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"In Rage Stance, ability is not already active.","keywords":["Quick"],"description":"You choose a single enemy as the target of your Single-Minded Fury. Your movement speed is doubled when moving towards your target plus you gain immunity to Slowed and difficult terrain. You also gain immunity to any mind-affecting effect that would prevent you from chasing or attacking your target. You gain a 1d4 bonus to accuracy rolls against that target, but suffer a 2d4 penalty to accuracy rolls against any other target. This effect lasts until the end of the encounter or until the target falls to 0 HP or lower."},{"id":"singularity-collapse","name":"Singularity Collapse","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Gravity"],"description":"You target a 25x25 square and all creatures within that square must make a save or be pulled 10ft towards the center."},{"id":"siphon-material","name":"Siphon Material","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":["Interlude","Errand"],"description":"Errand. You siphon the alloyed material from an item if possible, removing the effects that the original item would’ve had. If you cannot remove the effect then the skill fails.\n\nYou remove the alloy and regain its original form, while also maintaining the form of the item minus the effect. The special material is retrieved in raw units."},{"id":"siren-song","name":"Siren Song","costLabel":"3 AP","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Song","Sound"],"description":"All enemies in range must make a save against your Potency. If they fail, they may only spend AP on their next turn to move closer to you using the most direct path possible and cannot make attacks before that. To move closer, they may take actions that would help in getting closer such as standing up from prone or using fae flash.\n\nIf this path leads them through an obviously harmful hazard such as off a cliff, they are no longer affected by this ability. Otherwise, this ability lasts until they are within 5ft of you or until they take damage. While playing this Song, you can take no other actions. Taking any other action cancels the Song, immediately freeing all enemies from its effects. A creature can only be affected by this ability once per encounter."},{"id":"skillfull-blow","name":"Skillfull Blow","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Lock On"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target."},{"id":"skydive","name":"Skydive","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Special","requirement":"Must be airborne, polearm only.","keywords":["Jump"],"description":"You target an enemy below you, no more than 5ft away from you horizontally. You then immediately dive down to that target, making a Heavy Attack against them. You deal an additional point of damage for every 10ft you fell before making the attack, up to 10 extra damage."},{"id":"slam","name":"Slam","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You attack a single target for Light Damage. On damage, the target is moved 5ft away from you if they are a Grunt or if your Power is higher than theirs, in addition the target must be no more than one size larger than you.\n\nYou may spend 1 Mana to ignore the Power requirement."},{"id":"slide---shoot","name":"Slide & Shoot","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"Pistol only.","keywords":["Pass","Sidestep","Combo"],"description":"You slide forward up to 20ft towards your target. This movement does not provoke attacks of opportunity and you may pass through enemy space while moving. At the same time, you may make a Light Attack with your pistol against the target at any point during this movement.\n\nYour next ability gains Combo: If this attack is an unarmed attack, its AP cost is reduced by 1."},{"id":"slime-body","name":"Slime Body","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You gain Slime Body, which gives Damage Reduction 100 against physical damage against the next attack."},{"id":"slow","name":"Slow","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Slow"],"description":"The target is slowed until the start of your next turn unless the target pays 1 RP to resist this effect."},{"id":"smash-through-the-pain","name":"Smash through the pain","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Rage"],"description":"You gain Smash through the pain, which reduces the damage taken by the next attack by an amount equal to 3 + Power"},{"id":"snack-time-everyone--","name":"Snack Time Everyone!~","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"At least 1 hand free","keywords":["Upkeep"],"description":"You present a tray of refreshing Health and Mana snacks to your allies. All allies within 5ft of you may spend 0 RP to eat a snack.\n\nHealth: The ally may spend 2 Mana to heal for 15 HP.\n\nMana: The ally recovers 1 Mana. This counts as a character’s one food for the day and a character cannot benefit from this ability if they already had food. Does not count as a meal for the purposes of fending of starvation.\n\nYou keep the tray of snacks up for 1 turn and a character walking within 5ft of you while it’s up may also spend the 0 RP to eat a snack.\n\nAllies may also spend 0 AP to eat another snack. They can do this once per turn.\n\nUpkeep: 1 Mana, you keep the tray up for an additional turn."},{"id":"snap-shot","name":"Snap Shot","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target with a ranged weapon or a thrown weapon. You do not add your Focus to the accuracy roll."},{"id":"snap-shot-ii","name":"Snap Shot II","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You may make a Light Attack against the target. You do not add your focus to this roll."},{"id":"snatch","name":"Snatch","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"At least 1 hand free.","keywords":["Stealth"],"description":"You may use this when a target in range uses the interact with object action. If you can hold the object the target is interacting with in one hand, you steal it from them.\n\nAny AP they may have spent on their action is not refunded to them."},{"id":"sneak-attack","name":"Sneak Attack","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Trick Attack"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target."},{"id":"solar-radiance","name":"Solar Radiance","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You shine brightly like the sun in a 60ft radius around you. You cannot turn this off, but you can lower the range to just 5ft. This light counts as sunlight, though any negative effects a creature suffers from it are halved. It also counts as bright light for creatures weak to light."},{"id":"soul-absorption","name":"Soul Absorption","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"20ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Dark","Full Pierce","Sure Hit"],"description":"You make a Light Attack against a willing target that deals Light Dark damage. Your next Dark type Spell or Attack other than Soul Absorption gains extra damage equal to damage taken by the target. (Does not stack)"},{"id":"soul-strike","name":"Soul Strike","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"You land a killing blow.","keywords":["Killing Blow","Overcharge"],"description":"After landing a killing blow, you can use Soul Strike once on that target. If they are still at 0 HP or less, you raise an orb of divine energy out of the target, killing them instantly. You then use that orb against a second target, making a light attack that deals dark damage. It is possible to use Soul Strike while in Cat Form. Overcharge: You may spend 1 extra AP to instead deal heavy damage."},{"id":"soulreap","name":"Soulreap","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Killing Blow"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target. On Killing Blow, you instantly kill the target and immediately cast Raise Undead on the target for 0 AP."},{"id":"sound-the-retreat","name":"Sound the retreat","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Sidestep"],"description":"You sidestep 4 times your speed, moving as far away from visible enemies as possible. After that, your allies may sidestep up to twice their speed towards you."},{"id":"speak_with_dead","name":"Speak with dead","costLabel":"1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"-","requirement":"Special","keywords":[],"description":"You attempt to communicate with the soul of a person who has died recently. This requires you to perform a ritual that takes an hour, that must be performed next to the corpse or where the person died. You must be aware of the identity of the person you’re trying to contact. Finally, you must have a tool such as an ouija board that allows the spirit to communicate with you.\n\nEven if the ritual succeeds, the spirit is not forced to answer your questions if hostile to you or it might answer in cryptic ways."},{"id":"spear-charge","name":"Spear Charge","costLabel":"-1 AP","apCost":"-1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Polearm only.","keywords":["-"],"description":"You may spend 2 or 4 AP on this ability and move as though you had spent that AP on movement. After you finish moving, you may spend half of the AP you used on this ability on a single Light or Heavy attack.\n\nFor every 10ft moved, this attack gains +1 damage up to a maximum of +10.\n\nIf you spent 4 AP on this ability, you may also choose to use Wild Thrusts instead of making a Light or Heavy attack. These attacks only gain the damage bonus listed above for the initial attacks (and not the constant attacks of opportunity) and Wild Thrusts mana cost is reduced to 0 if used in this way."},{"id":"spellblade-s-preparation","name":"Spellblade's Preparation","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Enchantment","Encounter Start"],"description":"You unsheathe your weapon and enchant your weapon with an element you've mastered. Your weapon now deals the chosen element’s damage instead of its normal damage.\n\nIf you are not holding the enchanted weapon at the start of your turn, your weapon loses this benefit.\n\nThe weapon gains a +1 Power bonus to attacks until the end of the encounter."},{"id":"spellsteal","name":"Spellsteal","costLabel":"2 AP, -1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"-1","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You attempt to steal an effect from the target, removing it from the target and applying it to yourself for the same duration, provided you meet the requirements (if any). You must pay mana equal to the effects original mana cost. Effects granted through stances, transformations and permanent effects cannot be stolen. After stealing an effect, you can’t use this again until the stolen effect has ended. The stolen effect also cannot be re-applied on the target until it has faded from you. You must have seen the effect be applied or otherwise identified an effect before you can steal it."},{"id":"spellstrike","name":"Spellstrike","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You choose an ability with the Spell keyword that you can use. You make a melee attack against a target in range for the same AP and mana as the Spell.\n\nYour attack functions like the chosen Spell does, but does not provoke an Attack of Opportunity and is not treated as casting a Spell (meaning it can be used while Raging and Anti-Spell effects don't work). If the chosen spell was an AoE effect, the target point would be the target you strike with the spell. The requirements for applying any effects remain the same.\n\nThe spell you chose cannot be used again in the same round like normal, and if used with Secret Arts it counts as your Secret Art use for that encounter.\n\nOnly works with Spells that are attacks."},{"id":"spider-climb","name":"Spider Climb","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You do not suffer any penalties from moving across webs, either natural or created through magic or items. You may climb up walls without using any tools or making any checks at half your normal movement speed and can remain attached to the wall.\n\nIf you take any action other than moving or climbing, you become vulnerable to be knocked off the wall you're climbing until the start of your next turn. When you take damage, you slide down 20ft. If you are hanging on a ceiling or similar surface, you instead fall down from it falling prone and taking fall damage as normal."},{"id":"spike-field","name":"Spike Field","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Earth","Upkeep"],"description":"You create a 20x20ft field of spikes. Any creature moving more than 5ft per movement action across it takes full pierce damage equal to your Focus for each 5ft they move across the field.\n\nIf the movement through it was forced movement, you only take the damage once.\n\nLasts until the start of your next turn.\n\nUpkeep: 1 mana, extends the duration of the spike field by 1 turn."},{"id":"spiked-armor","name":"Spiked Armor","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be wearing armor and/or a shield.","keywords":["Counter"],"description":"Until the start of your next turn, the spikes on your armor and shield reflect damage when you are attacked. When an enemy hits you with a melee attack, they take 4 full pierce damage."},{"id":"spirit-circuit-crash","name":"Spirit Circuit Crash","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"45ft","requirement":"","keywords":["-"],"description":"You send a wave of magic energy onto the target, afflicting them with Spirit Circuit Crash— jamming their Spirit Circuits. The target cannot use Secret Arts or any abilities that require mana until the end of their next turn. The target may choose to take damage equal to your heavy attack damage to cancel this effect.\n\nYou can cast this through a creature affected by Mind Connection."},{"id":"spirit-jump","name":"Spirit Jump","costLabel":"0 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be mounted.","keywords":["-"],"description":"You and your mount jump up to 60ft vertically straight up into the air. You can additionally move 5ft horizontally afterwards. Unless your mount can fly, you automatically land straight down from your position at the end of your turn or for 0 AP, this falling movement does not provoke attacks of opportunity and you do not take fall damage from it. You cannot make any non-teleport movement actions while in the air, but can still take other actions (such as attacking) while airborne.\n\nYou may trade height to move horizontally as part of the initial jump, moving 5ft horizontally as part of the jump in exchange for 5ft of height. You may move up to 40ft extra horizontally with this.\n\nInstead of spending mana, you may instead spend a minute preparing this ability before activating it. When you do, this ability costs 0 mana."},{"id":"spirited-bravado","name":"Spirited Bravado","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"When you are under the effect of Tipsy, you gain a Spirited Bravado which grants +1 Power."},{"id":"spiritual-reading","name":"Spiritual Reading","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Analyze"],"description":"You are able to check the aura of a creature or object within range.\n\nIf you check a creature, you can see whether a creature is non-heroic, weaker than you, around the same as you, stronger than you or much stronger than you. The GM may also give you their Spirit Core value if it has one. You also are aware if someone is concealing their spirit core level, but can’t get an accurate reading of their strength if they are. In addition, you are able to see their mana % until the end of the encounter.\n\nIf you check an item, you can determine whether it’s magical in nature. If it is, you may immediately make a Magic check against it to determine its effect as if you were using Decipher Magic with a +5 bonus."},{"id":"spiritual-sync","name":"Spiritual Sync","costLabel":"0 AP, -1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"-1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Rage"],"description":"If you paid mana for this ability, you gain Temporary HP equal to 8X. Any Temporary HP from this ability remaining after the encounter conclusion phase is turned back into mana at a ratio of 8 Temporary HP to 1 mana.\n\nYou may instead pay HP for this ability. If you do, you gain 1 Temporary Mana for every 8 HP you spend. You cannot spend more HP than you currently have. Any Temporary mana is lost at the encounter conclusion phase.\n\nYou may spend a maximum of 3 mana or 24 HP on this ability.\n\nOnce you use this ability, you may not use it again until after an encounter conclusion phase."},{"id":"spore-burst","name":"Spore Burst","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Earth","Spell"],"description":"You create an explosion of spores in front of you. Make a Heavy Attack against the target that deals Poison damage. Afterwards, knock back the target 5ft and knock yourself back 5ft. This Spell does not trigger attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"spore_symbiote","name":"Spore Symbiote","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Quick"],"description":"You send a Spore Symbiote to an ally or yourself. The Spore Symbiote lasts until the end of combat, or you move it to another target (You can only have one Spore Symbiote active at a time). If the host of Spore Symbiote moves more than 240 feet away from you, the Spore Symbiote ends."},{"id":"squadsight","name":"Squadsight","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"300ft","requirement":"","keywords":["-"],"description":"An ally that can see or hear you within range may use your Perception score until the start of your next turn. They may also see from your position rather than their own and they may calculate their ranged weapon range (but not LoS) from your position instead of their own. This new range may not exceed twice their normal range."},{"id":"stab---throw","name":"Stab & Throw","costLabel":"3 AP","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Special","requirement":"Throwing Weapon, Set of Missiles or Thrown attack only.","keywords":[],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against a target in melee range. You may then use the same weapon to Heavy Attack a different target within your ranged weapon range or thrown attack range. This second attack does not provoke attacks of opportunity from the target of your first attack."},{"id":"stable-foundation","name":"Stable Foundation","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"Must be the first crafting dice in a crafting session. Costs 1 Crafting Dice","keywords":[],"description":"Make a crafting check, afterwards all future crafting dice for this session cannot roll below a 3."},{"id":"staggering-slice","name":"Staggering Slice","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"One-Handed weapons only.","keywords":["Stagger"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target. On damage, you inflict Stagger 1 until the end of your next turn..\n\nIf you're under the effects of Exposing Edge, you inflict Stagger 2 on damage instead."},{"id":"stalks-of-comparison","name":"Stalks of Comparison","costLabel":"1 Strike Dice","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"1 Strike Dice","range":"","requirement":"Costs 1 Strike Dice","keywords":[],"description":"Make a gathering check and apply it to either Node Points or Lucky Points. If the result of this check (before bonuses) is higher than your previous roll this session, gain a bonus to the result equal to your Foraging skill (max +10)."},{"id":"stardust-reverie","name":"Stardust Reverie","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Celestial","Upkeep"],"description":"Declare a distance up to the range of this spell. You create a celestial dome at that range from you that harm those that pass through it.\n\nUntil the start of your next turn, whenever a creature willingly enters that distance from you, you may make a Light attack against them that deals Arcane damage. You may choose to spend an RP before making this attack to make it a Heavy attack. A character that Sidesteps or Teleports through your stars does not provoke this attack.\n\nUpkeep: 1 mana. When you pay the upkeep cost, you may change the distance of the stars."},{"id":"starfall","name":"Starfall","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"360ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Celestial"],"description":"You target a 25x25 square within range. On the start of your next turn, 4 stars fall down in the area.\n\nAt the start of your next turn, you make 4 light attacks that deal Arcane damage, evenly divided amongst enemies in the area. If there are less enemies than stars, you may hit an enemy more than once (though you must still attempt to hit each enemy an equal amount of times if possible)."},{"id":"starlance","name":"Starlance","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Celestial","Pinpoint"],"description":"You make a Precise attack against the target that deals Arcane damage."},{"id":"start-dash","name":"Start Dash","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be the first action in your turn.","keywords":["Quick","Opener"],"description":"You move up to your speed."},{"id":"stasis","name":"Stasis","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You put a Grunt level character or any willing ally into Stasis until the start of your next turn. While in Stasis, they cannot be affected by any ability, attack or anything similar but they also cannot take any actions."},{"id":"static-discharge","name":"Static Discharge","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"The target must be afflicted with Static you applied.","keywords":["Lightning","Spell"],"description":"A single target in range must make a save or the Static stacks on them immediately discharge, triggering the Static effect as though it was the end of the target’s turn.\n\nWhether the target succeeds at or fails the save, they lose all Static charges."},{"id":"static-overload","name":"Static Overload","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"The target must be afflicted with Static you applied.","keywords":["Daze","Lightning","Spell"],"description":"A single target in range must make a save or immediately take Lightning damage equal to their Static and become inflicted with Daze."},{"id":"statue-form","name":"Statue Form","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Transformation"],"description":"You turn yourself into a statue, petrifying yourself and the items on you. While in this mode, you gain a +5 bonus to your guard but cannot take any actions except Block. You may leave this mode by spending 0 AP.\n\nYou may rest as normal while in this form. While staying in this form, you do not need to eat.\n\nYou gain a +10 bonus to your Deception for convincing others that you are just a statue."},{"id":"status-assessment","name":"Status Assessment","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"-","keywords":["Analyze","Quick","Stealth"],"description":"You can assess the approximate HP percentage of a unit until the end of combat. (The DM should enable health bars for the unit). You can also determine which parts of a creature can be targeted and destroyed, if any."},{"id":"status-assessment-ii","name":"Status Assessment II","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"-","keywords":["Analyze","Quick","Stealth"],"description":"You can assess the approximate HP percentage of a unit until the end of combat. (The DM should enable health bars for the unit). You can also assess any damage type weaknesses and strengths that the enemy has at the current time. You can also determine which parts of a creature can be targeted and destroyed, if any."},{"id":"status-assessment-iii","name":"Status Assessment III","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"-","keywords":["Analyze","Stealth"],"description":"You can assess the approximate HP and RP percentage of a unit until the end of combat. (The DM should enable health bars for the unit). You can also assess any damage type weaknesses and strengths that the enemy has at the current time. You can also determine which parts of a creature can be targeted and destroyed, if any."},{"id":"stay-here-with-me-","name":"Stay Here With Me!","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Song","Sound","Idol","Healing","Upkeep"],"description":"All allies within range heal for 8 HP.\n\nUpkeep: 1 AP, 2 Mana. When you pay upkeep, you heal all allies for 8 HP again."},{"id":"steadfast-earth-stance","name":"Steadfast Earth Stance","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Not wearing any armor (including armor plates)","keywords":["Stance"],"description":"You enter a stance that grants you the toughness of the earth. You gain a +2 bonus to your guard and a +6 bonus to your Block.\n\nThis stance lasts until you enter a different stance."},{"id":"steady-craft-ii","name":"Steady Craft II","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"1 Crafting Dice.","keywords":[],"description":"You add a crafting check to the item. The crafting dice is automatically a 7."},{"id":"steady-ground","name":"Steady Ground","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"The target must be touching the ground.","keywords":["Aid"],"description":"The target gains Immovable until the start of their next turn.\n\nYou may also use this for 2 AP instead."},{"id":"steady-stance","name":"Steady Stance","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Stance","Immovable"],"description":"You enter a Stance in which you become Immovable unless the enemy has more Power than you. If they do, you may pay an additional mana to retain the effect against them for that turn if they would prone you or knock you back.\n\nThis stance lasts until you enter a different stance."},{"id":"steal-heart","name":"Steal Heart","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Charm","Mind Affecting","Stealth"],"description":"The target must make a save or become Charmed until the end of the encounter.\n\nIf you use this on a Grunt level enemy and you charm them, you may choose their actions when it's their turn in addition to Charm’s normal effect.\n\nYou may only have 1 target charmed at the same time."},{"id":"steal-time","name":"Steal Time","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You may make a Light Attack against the target. On damage, you inflict Time Stolen, which lowers their Initiative by 1 and you gain Stolen Time, which increases yours by 1. This effect can stack both on you and on enemies."},{"id":"steel-aura","name":"Steel Aura","costLabel":"0 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Aura","Rage","Circuit"],"description":"You gain Steel Aura, granting you 3 additional guard, but you can no longer use any RP actions besides Block and actions with the Rage keyword. You can end this effect at any time for 0 RP. This effect ends at the start of your next turn."},{"id":"stolen-power","name":"Stolen Power","costLabel":"-1 AP","apCost":"-1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell"],"description":"Make a Light (1 AP), Precise (2 AP) or Heavy (2 AP) attack that deals Arcane damage against the target. You use their Power for the damage calculation.\n\nThis spell does not provoke attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"stolen-skill","name":"Stolen Skill","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Stealth"],"description":"You may name one skill (such as perception, athletics) and force the target enemy to make a save against your Potency. On failure, you steal their skill points spent into the skill until the end of the encounter or for 1 minute. You gain their skill points they have in that skill to your skill while they lose all of theirs.\n\nOnly affects skill points spent, not any other bonuses from abilities or stats.\n\nCan not be used on artisan and gathering skills.\n\nYou may only have 1 instance of Stolen Skill active at the same time, but you may choose to drop your current stolen one for 0 AP."},{"id":"stoneskin","name":"Stoneskin","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You gain Stoneskin, which grants +1 guard and +4 block, but also -2 evasion and dodge."},{"id":"store-time","name":"Store Time","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You gain Store Time, granting you 1 extra AP at the start of your next turn."},{"id":"store/consume_item","name":"Store/Consume Item","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You store a consumable item within your body, this item still counts towards weight limits. Without needing to equip the item, you can consume an item to gain its effects."},{"id":"strata-cut","name":"Strata Cut","costLabel":"1 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"","keywords":["Combo","Half Pierce"],"description":"You make a Precise attack against the target.\n\nCombo: If used after Tectonic Overhead, the mana cost is reduced by 1."},{"id":"stratagem--lightning","name":"Stratagem: Lightning","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"All allies in sight, including yourself.","requirement":"-","keywords":["Encounter Start"],"description":"All allied units (including yourself) gain +1 to Initiative and may immediately move up to their Speed."},{"id":"strengthening-the-bond","name":"Strengthening the Bond","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 RP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"A willing ally is within 10ft range.","keywords":[],"description":"You swap places with a willing ally. This movement does not trigger any attacks of opportunity. You cannot use this ability if it causes an ally unit to occupy an invalid space. Before or after the swap you can take a 5ft step, but the swap must occur.\n\nYou may spend either 0 AP or 1 RP to use this ability."},{"id":"strike-of-still-water","name":"Strike of Still Water","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Must be in Serene Water Stance.","keywords":["Full Pierce","Sure Hit","Unarmed Strike"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target."},{"id":"study-target","name":"Study Target","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"-","keywords":["Lock On","Full Pierce","Sure Hit","Overcharge","Stealth"],"description":"Your next basic attack against the target gains the Lock On keyword OR you apply Death Mark to the target.\n\nOvercharge: You may spend 2 additional AP to instead make the next basic attack gain the Sure hit and Full Pierce keywords."},{"id":"stygian-screen","name":"Stygian Screen","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Spell","Dark","Concentration"],"description":"You create a wall of darkness that is 20ft long, 5ft wide and 10ft high. This wall must be a straight line. This wall blocks line of sight. Targets inside of the wall can only see 5ft away"},{"id":"suckerpunch","name":"Suckerpunch","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Encounter Start","Sure Hit","Unarmed Strike"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target. On damage, the target becomes Unbalanced."},{"id":"summon-animal","name":"Summon Animal","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Summon"],"description":"You summon a randomly chosen animal to a location you can see within range. The summon does not act by itself, but you may spend AP to make it act. The AP cost for these actions is the same as they would be for you taking the basic actions. (Example, you can spend 2 AP to make the summon do a Heavy attack).\n\nThe summon also gains access to the abilities the summoned creature normally has. The costs for these have to be paid by you, same as they would be for basic actions. Any attacks it makes are made with its own stats. When an animal summoned through this ability dies, you cannot use this ability again until the end of the encounter. You can undo the summoning manually for 0 AP.\n\nThe pool of creatures that can be summoned is the following: Wolf, Boar, Giant Spider."},{"id":"summon-lesser-eidolon","name":"Summon Lesser Eidolon","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Summon","Spell","Upkeep"],"description":"Your contracted Eidolon hears your call and sends their minions to fight for you. The summon called and costs are dependent on your attunement. Lasts up to 5 minutes. You must pay the upkeep cost under the Summon’s Summon Skill or the Summon vanishes.\n\nUnless the summon has a skill that says otherwise, a summon acts after you on initiative, but cannot act the round it is summoned except for RP actions."},{"id":"summon-piece","name":"Summon Piece","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You summon a Pawn puppet under your control. It (and other puppets from this class) have HP equal to 20 + Focus, no evasion and no guard. These puppets are not living targets and are generally treated as structures rather than creatures.\n\nOvercharge: You may spend extra mana to summon the following puppets instead:\n\n1 Mana: Knight or Bishop\n\n2 Mana: Rook\n\n3 Mana: Queen"},{"id":"swallow-acrobatics","name":"Swallow Acrobatics","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Can be used after you make a melee attack while flying.","keywords":["-"],"description":"Your next movement before the end of your turn does not provoke attacks of opportunity."},{"id":"swap","name":"Swap","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 RP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"20ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Rapid","Teleport"],"description":"You Swap positions with a chosen willing ally or any non-heroic enemy.\n\nYou may use either AP or RP for this ability. You don't need to pay the cost of both."},{"id":"sweeping-stance","name":"Sweeping Stance","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Two-handed weapons only.","keywords":["Stance"],"description":"You enter a stance in which you spin your weapon around in a circular motion and lash out against any enemy that approaches. When an enemy enters your weapon’s range you may make an Attack of Opportunity against them. An enemy moving while already being in your attack range does not provoke. Your weapon's range for these attacks of opportunities is increased by 5ft (This does not affect your normal threaten range).\n\nThe stance lasts until you make an attack that isn’t an Attack of Opportunity."},{"id":"sweet-dreams","name":"Sweet Dreams","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"As a rest action, you may choose an ally other than yourself to heal for 5 + Toughness after their rest has finished.\n\nDoesn't stack with Medical Kit."},{"id":"swift-wind-palm","name":"Swift Wind Palm","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"You and the target must be airborne","keywords":["Unarmed Strike","Sidestep","Lock On"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target. On damage, the target is knocked down 30ft or until they hit the floor (on top of any other height loss from being hit while flying) and you may Sidestep next to them afterwards.\n\nA target knocked down on to the ground with this ability is knocked prone and takes falling damage as normal. They do not take the normal extra damage as result of being knocked into the floor."},{"id":"sword-riding-art","name":"Sword Riding Art","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must have a Light Sword or two-handed melee weapon in your hand.","keywords":[],"description":"You jump onto a light sword, versatile melee weapon, greatshield, bayonet musket or two-handed melee weapon you’re carrying and use it to move around. While riding on top of the sword, you gain Flight. You can fly this way for up to 5 minutes.\n\nIf you take damage while flying higher than 5ft above the ground, your altitude drops by 20ft. If this would reduce your altitude to the point where you touch the ground, you may hop off your weapon and put it back into your hand if possible for 0 RP. After this happens, your Sword Riding ends. If the attack that reduced your HP came from a flying creature other than yourself, you do not lose altitude but instead become unbalanced.\n\nIf you are knocked back by an effect, you must make a save against the attacker's potency. Else, you are blown off your sword."},{"id":"tackle","name":"Tackle","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You attempt to tackle the target and may make a Heavy Attack against them. This attack deals no damage. On hit and if the target did not use the Block action against this ability, you and the target fall Prone. If the target successfully dodges this ability, you fall Prone."},{"id":"tag_rotation","name":"Tag Rotation","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 RP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Two ally units, or yourself and an ally unit that are adjacent to each other that you can see.","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"The target willing allies, or yourself and a target willing ally switch places. This movement does not trigger any attacks of opportunity. You cannot use this if it causes an ally unit to occupy an invalid space. You may use either AP or RP for this ability."},{"id":"tailwind","name":"Tailwind","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Encounter Start"],"description":"You and all allies within 40ft gain Tailwind, which provides a +1 bonus to initiative and doubles movement speed in the first round of combat."},{"id":"take-cover-","name":"Take Cover!","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Light cover in sight","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"All Low Cover in a 20x20 area becomes High Cover for your allies (including yourself). This effect lasts until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"take-it-easy","name":"Take it easy","costLabel":"1 Strike Dice","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"1 Strike Dice","range":"","requirement":"Must in a gathering session.","keywords":[],"description":"Do not make a gathering check. Instead, immediately collect 25% of the Outcrop’s base material as a bonus (doesn’t affect material totals), but no Node or Lucky progress is made."},{"id":"talisman-recursion","name":"Talisman Recursion","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"After using a Talisman, you may immediately spend the cost of that talisman (before reductions) to repeat the effect without consuming another talisman. If the talisman had a target, you must choose the same target.\n\nDoes not work with Secret Talismans."},{"id":"tap-cracker","name":"Tap Cracker","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"45ft","requirement":"Object is in a room affected by Psychometry","keywords":["Overcharge"],"description":"You open a door or interact with an object remotely. You can cast this through a creature affected by Mind Connection.\n\nOvercharge: You can pay 1 mana to magically unlock most doors and objects (DM can decide if an object is too complicated, and still make you roll a Skill Check)."},{"id":"tectonic-overhead","name":"Tectonic Overhead","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"","keywords":["Half Pierce"],"description":"You make a slow, powerful overhead swing and make a Heavy attack against the target. Their evasion (but not dodge) is doubled for this attack."},{"id":"tempestuous-fire-stance","name":"Tempestuous Fire Stance","costLabel":"0 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Stance"],"description":"You enter the Tempestuous Fire Stance. While in this Stance, before you make an attack with the Unarmed Strike keyword, you may choose to move 5ft per AP spent on the move. This movement does not provoke attacks of opportunity. This Stance lasts until you enter a different stance or until you move, with the exceptions of this ability and movement abilities with the Unarmed Strike keyword. Making an attack does not cancel this stance."},{"id":"temporary_protection","name":"Temporary Protection","costLabel":"0 AP, 3 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"3","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"Until the end of the encounter, the target ally you selected is also treated as your VIP."},{"id":"tengu-aura-weapon","name":"Tengu Aura Weapon","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":["Aura"],"description":"Your infuse your weapons with fiend killing aura, making them equivalent to Silver weapons for the purposes of harming fiends. Attacking a fiend with a silver weapon disables their regeneration."},{"id":"tengu-mask","name":"Tengu Mask","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Presence Concealment"],"description":"You manifest and don a Tengu Mask of your desired design, granting Presence Concealment. You cannot use any mana abilities or Aura abilities while in Presence Concealment. You can end this effect for 1 AP or 1 RP, to either remove your mask or to wear it on your head in a way that doesn't cover your face."},{"id":"terracing","name":"Terracing","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["-"],"description":"You raise the ground around you in a 25x25ft square centered on yourself. The ground is raised upwards by 10ft. Can only be used on natural ground and cannot be used on ground that’s already been raised.\n\nOvercharge: You may spend 1 AP and 1 Mana to raise it upwards by another 10ft."},{"id":"tetsuzanko","name":"Tetsuzanko","costLabel":"3 AP","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Bajiquan","Combo","Unarmed Strike"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target. This attack deals additional Light Damage added to the Heavy Damage. Combo: If used after an ability that moved the target, you may push the target for an equal distance again."},{"id":"thanergetic-bloom","name":"Thanergetic Bloom","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Opener","Summon"],"description":"You summon a temporary Zombie as if you used Raise Undead. It disappears at the end of the encounter (or immediately if used outside of an encounter)."},{"id":"thermal-quench","name":"Thermal Quench","costLabel":"1 Crafting Dice","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"1 Crafting Dice","range":"","requirement":"Must be in a crafting session.","keywords":[],"description":"You make a crafting check. For each time you rolled a 5 or higher this craft, this check gains a +1 bonus."},{"id":"thermal-vision","name":"Thermal Vision","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You can perfectly see and detect heat sources up to 120ft away, including stealthed creatures. This cannot detect things hidden by magical means. You can no longer discern a difference in heat once something reaches freezing temperatures."},{"id":"thick-skull","name":"Thick Skull","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"When you would get Dazed, you may make a Save against the effect even if it would normally not allow for one. If you already had to make a save to avoid it, then you don’t get another."},{"id":"this-is-our-moment-","name":"This is our moment!","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Song","Sound","Idol","Upkeep"],"description":"All allies within range gain a +1 Song bonus to their damage rolls. This bonus is doubled on Heavy attacks.\n\nUpkeep: 1 AP"},{"id":"threatening-aura","name":"Threatening Aura","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Challenge"],"description":"Until the start of your next turn, all enemies in your melee range are considered Challenged by you."},{"id":"throw-potion","name":"Throw Potion","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You throw a Potion in your hands at a willing ally unit within range. The unit may pay the mana cost (if any) to receive the effect of the Potion."},{"id":"thunderstorm","name":"Thunderstorm","costLabel":"3 AP","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Lightning","Spell","Scatter"],"description":"You may make a Light Attack that deals Lightning damage against all target enemies in range. As the attack comes from the sky, any cover is calculated from above the target rather than from your path to the target."},{"id":"timberwright-s-core-crafting","name":"Timberwright's Core Crafting","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Carpenter's Modification B\nCost: X Crafting Points\nDescription:\nYou add an B-Type modification to the weapon or tool. See the Universal Weapon page as well as the individual weapon page for details. Each modification has its own cost."},{"id":"tiny-pixie","name":"Tiny Pixie","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Your size is tiny and you are able to occupy the same square as an ally or enemy. Your Toughness is reduced by 2 and your Agility is increased by 2.\n\nWhen walking (and not hovering or flying), your movement speed is reduced to 5ft."},{"id":"tireless_undead","name":"Tireless Undead","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Jiangshi do not know pain or fatigue, making them terrifying warriors. You are always counted as rested despite the most inhospitable conditions. You also do not need to sleep."},{"id":"torture-techniques","name":"Torture Techniques","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"You landed a crit on the enemy (and it wasn't blocked or dodged).","keywords":["Slow","Unbalanced","Bleeding"],"description":"You twist the knife and inflict a debilitating wound on the enemy. You inflict one of the following conditions: Slowed, Unbalanced or Bleeding. These last until the end of the target’s next turn."},{"id":"toxic-blast","name":"Toxic Blast","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Safe","Poison","Toxic"],"description":"You fire a stream of poison and make a Light attack against the target. On hit, this deals no damage but inflicts the enemy with Toxic, making them take 1d6 full pierce Poison damage at the start of their turn until they spend 2 AP to remove the poison effect."},{"id":"track","name":"Track","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You find any tracks that aren’t hidden. Once you find tracks, you can follow them at normal speed without having to make checks."},{"id":"trail-mix","name":"Trail Mix","costLabel":"Rest Action","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"Rest Action","range":"","requirement":"20u of Food Per Serving","keywords":[],"description":"For a camp action you create up to 5 servings of a trail meal. It costs 20u of food per serving and only gives 1 mana (0 for Mirane), but it keeps starvation away. Does not require a culinary kit, and does not count as cooking for the purposes of culinary actions such as using stocks."},{"id":"trailblazer","name":"Trailblazer","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be mounted and meet the requirements of your Light Cavalry key ability.","keywords":["-"],"description":"You move up to your speed. Any allies within 30ft of where you started moving may spend 1 RP to move up to twice their speed towards you. They ignore the effects of natural difficult terrain for this movement."},{"id":"trample","name":"Trample","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Must be mounted.","keywords":["Sure Hit"],"description":"You may activate this after moving at least 20ft in a movement action to gain Trample until you stop moving. Abilities with the Teleport keyword do not apply for this, but declaring multiple AP to move at the same time counts as 1 action. While under the effects of trample, you don't provoke attacks of opportunity by moving and you can move into enemies that are at least one size smaller than your mount. An enemy may spend 1 RP to move out of the way to an empty spot within 5ft of them.\n\nIf they don’t move out of the way, you make a Sure Hit Light attack against them with your mount, using your mount’s stats. On damage, you knock them prone into the square you came from and keep moving, occupying the square they were in. Otherwise your movement action ends.\n\nEach enemy can only be affected by trample once per activation of the ability, regardless of whether they are attacked or move out of it."},{"id":"transfusion","name":"Transfusion","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Healing","Aid"],"description":"You lose HP up to your Toughness x 2. Target ally within range heals for the same amount of HP you lost.\n\nThis HP loss cannot be mitigated in any way and ignores temporary HP. This does not trigger effects that would trigger upon taking damage."},{"id":"transmutation-basics","name":"Transmutation Basics","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Alchemic Catch\nDescription:\nCo-Craft. Use a hasty transmutation to attempt to fix a crafting error. You may reroll a crafting dice after already determining the result. You must keep the second number. Cannot be used for the last crafting dice.\n\nTemperature Shock\nDescription:\nCo-Craft. Can be used immediately after the result of a roll is determined. The previous action has no effect and instead gain a +10 to your next crafting action.\n\nRage Quit\nCost: 1 Crafting Dice\nDescription:\nCo-Craft. Only usable once per crafting IP. Destroy the uncrafted item and all materials invested into the craft. You may immediately start another crafting session. If you use this as a Co-Craft it requires 1 crafting dice from the main crafter.\n\nBouncing Ideas\nDescription:\nCo-Craft. You assist with crafting adding 1d4 crafting points to the current craft.\n\nCreate Ingot\nCost: Errand\nDescription:\nYou create an ingot from blacksmithing base materials or from blacksmithing special materials. See Item: Blacksmithing Materials.\n\nCreate Oil Coating\nCost: Errand\nDescription:\nYou create an Oil Coating from Carpenter materials. See Items: Carpenter Materials\n\nCreate Wood Block\nCost: Errand\nDescription:\nYou create a Wood Block from Carpenter materials. See Items: Carpenter Materials\n\nCraft Fuel Shells\nCost: Errand\nDescription:\nYou craft up to 5 small shells. You can instead craft a medium shell instead of 2 small shells. Small shells require 50 magical fuel, medium shells require 200 magical fuel.\n\nCreate Artifice Parts\nCost: Errand\nDescription:\nYou create up to 3000u of artifice parts of the same type of blacksmithing material used to make them at a 1:1 rate. (3000u of Iron Creates 3000u of Iron Artifice Parts.) See Items: Blacksmithing Materials, Artificer Materials. When converting items of a higher tier, you can convert up to 6000 of tamahagane, 9000 of mithril, 12000 of Orihalcum or 15000 of escudo.\n\nTan Leather\nCost: Errand\nDescription:\nYou create a tanned hide from armorsmithing base leather materials. See item: Armorsmthing materials.\n\nCreate Box or Bundle of Food\nCost: Errand.\nDescription:\nYou create a perfect mix of ingredients that would be worthy of a stock with 500u of matching material. Example: 500u of Meat can make 1 Box of Fresh Meat. You can make 5 boxes of any kind for one errand action."},{"id":"transmute-effective-implement","name":"Transmute Effective Implement","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Overcharge"],"description":"From the surrounding material you construct an \"Effective Implement\", granting you a +5 to the skill of your choice. You must explain how this implement will be effective towards the check using the relevant skill (example: creating a springboard to jump higher with athletics) and the GM determines the validity or this ability has no effect. Does not work with crafting or gathering skills. This implement lasts until you have attempted the specific check it was created for.\n\nYou may also spend 1 RP instead of 1 AP for this ability.\n\nOvercharge: You can spend 1 additional mana to increase the skill bonus to +10."},{"id":"transmute-terrain","name":"Transmute Terrain","costLabel":"2 AP, -1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"-1","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":["-"],"description":"Creates a connected transmuted terrain that grows from the point of origin. For every mana spent, you can create up to 4 5ft squares of terrain that must be connected. Choose solid ground normal terrain or difficult terrain. Removes effects on the terrain such as ice, fire. The terrain can push objects and creatures in the direction its being created. If the transmute terrain deals damage to a creature, the spell stops after and the 5ft segment that contacted them is destroyed. Each segment of wall has HP equal to 20+Focus\n\nHeroics caught in the terrain may spend 1 RP to step out of it. Once they do, they can't be shoved within this use of transmute terrain even if you attempt to hit them with it again."},{"id":"transmute-wall","name":"Transmute Wall","costLabel":"1 RP, -1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"-1","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"You or an ally in range is the target of a ranged attack.","keywords":[],"description":"You quickly transmute multiple walls to defend against an incoming ranged attack. Each wall you summon reduces the damage of the incoming attack by 2* Focus, you can summon as many walls as you like against the incoming attack for 1 mana per wall. After the attack resolves, every wall you made vanishes regardless of remaining HP."},{"id":"transmute-weapon","name":"Transmute Weapon","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"There is suitable material available. (GM decides)","keywords":["-"],"description":"Using the available materials around you, you transmute any basic weapon or shield into your hand or next to an ally, your ally can grab the weapon at the time of its creation for 0 RP, as well as sheathe their weapons. The weapon lasts until the end of the encounter and is destroyed.\n\nYou can transmute weapons out of special material if there is enough of it in the area, or if you have one (such as an ingot) but the material is destroyed afterwards. The DM determines if this is possible in the specific case."},{"id":"transmuter-tricks","name":"Transmuter Tricks","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Stabilize Matter\nDescription:\nCo-Craft. Use a transmutation that stabilizes the material, making it easier to work with. The next crafting d10 cannot roll lower than a 6.\n\nA Small Bit of Creation\nCost: One herb with a rarity higher than common.\nDescription:\nYou deconstruct and reconstruct the structure of an harvested alchemy herb. By lowering its energy level you attune an herb to another element. Choose one herb and lower its rarity by one step and then change its element into the element of your choice."},{"id":"traveler-s-end","name":"Traveler's End","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Mist of the Vale must be active for at least 1 turn.","keywords":["Song","Upkeep","Sound","Blanketing"],"description":"You play the final tunes of the melody that signals the traveler’s ending.\n\nWhile Traveler’s End remains active, the Potency of your Mist of the Vale and Despair of Isolation is increased by 3. Your Mist of the Vale can no longer be removed and any effect that would remove it instead dispels Traveler’s End.\n\nAt any point after activating this song, you may spend 1 RP and 5 Mana to make a Sure Hit Heavy attack against all enemies within your Mist of the Vale. On killing blow, you regain 1 mana you spend on the attack (up to 5). Afterwards, the Mist of the Vale ends and cannot be reused in this encounter.\n\nTraveler’s End otherwise lasts until the end of the encounter or until the Mist of the Vale is gone.\n\nUpkeep: 1 Mana"},{"id":"tremorsense","name":"Tremorsense","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Overcharge"],"description":"You become aware of the presence and exact location of any creature within range that is touching the ground until the end of your turn.\n\nOvercharge: You may spend extra mana to increase the range by an additional 40ft per mana spent."},{"id":"trial-by-fire","name":"Trial By Fire","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"","keywords":["Challenge"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target. On damage, they are challenged by you until the start of your next turn.\n\n If this does not deal damage, they cannot be challenged by you until the start of your next turn."},{"id":"true_death","name":"True Death","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"-","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"Damage from melee weapon attacks made by you also reduces the target’s max HP by the same amount. This lasts until the end of the encounter."},{"id":"true-divine-release","name":"True Divine Release","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Not already transformed","keywords":["Transformation","Upkeep"],"description":"You unleash your latent angelic powers and transform into a semi-divine being for up to an hour. While transformed, you gain controlled flight and +5 movement speed. Upkeep: 2 mana After using this ability, you cannot do so again until the interlude rest phase."},{"id":"twin-verdict","name":"Twin Verdict","costLabel":"3 AP, 1 RP","apCost":"3","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You make two Heavy attacks against the target."},{"id":"twinkle-step","name":"Twinkle Step","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Song","Sound","Idol","Upkeep"],"description":"All allies within range gain a +1 Song bonus to their Evasion and Dodge.\n\nUpkeep: 1 AP"},{"id":"two-point-strike","name":"Two Point Strike","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Unarmed Strike","Mystic Eye"],"description":"You may make a Light Attack against the target. On damage, you apply Wave Palm I.\n\nWave Palm increases the mana cost of the afflicted target’s next action that uses mana by an amount equal to the amount of stacks applied. If the triggering attack makes the number of total stacks exceed the target's current mana, they lose mana equal to the amount of total stacks and take true damage equal to triple this amount. Wave Palm does not stack with itself, use only the higher value.\n\nIf the target has no mana, they immediately take true damage as if their stacks exceeded their current mana.\n\nWhen the Wave Palm effect triggers, either by increasing the mana cost or by dealing the true damage, the Wave Palm effect is removed."},{"id":"two-sword-crush","name":"Two Sword Crush","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Can be used after hitting an attack with a Two-Handed melee weapon. Must be dual wielding.","keywords":["Rage"],"description":"You may add your Light damage to the attack."},{"id":"uke-nagashi","name":"Uke Nagashi","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Katana only, target of a melee attack and must be in the Iai state.","keywords":["Counter","Iaijutsu"],"description":"Roll Heavy Damage and treat that as your Block against the attack that’s targeting you. If you reduce the damage to 0, the attacker becomes Unbalanced. On hit effects and maces do not gain their effect if you reduce the damage to 0. After the attack is resolved, you may immediately make an Iai Strike against the attacker for 0 RP. This Iai Strike gains the Sure Hit keyword against an Unbalanced target."},{"id":"unconventional-weapon","name":"Unconventional Weapon","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Quick"],"description":"You may treat the weapon you’re currently wielding as a weapon of a different group for the next attack in addition to its normal group. In addition to receiving the base weapon properties of both weapon groups, this allows it to meet the requirements of abilities that require a certain group, and allows you to change its damage type to the chosen weapon’s damage type. The GM may rule that some abilities still cannot be performed with your equipped weapon."},{"id":"undying-justice","name":"Undying Justice","costLabel":"0 RP, 2 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You take damage. Your HP is higher than 1.","keywords":[],"description":"If the damage would reduce your HP to 0 or lower, it instead lowers your HP to 1."},{"id":"unerring_aim","name":"Unerring Aim","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"When you aim at an object not being worn or wielded within your ranged weapon range, you always hit your target."},{"id":"unholy-pact","name":"Unholy Pact","costLabel":"1 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"Bone Armor is active on you.","keywords":["Healing"],"description":"You remove your Bone Armor to heal yourself for Power x 2 and gain a +2 Power bonus on your next attack."},{"id":"unmake","name":"Unmake","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Mystic Eye"],"description":"You target one magically created wall or unattended object within range. You instantly destroy a 5x5 square of it or the object entirely."},{"id":"unrelenting-assault","name":"Unrelenting Assault","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"An enemy moves out of your range.","keywords":["Rage"],"description":"You may use this ability when an enemy willingly moves out of your melee weapon range to make a Heavy attack against them. You can use this even if they took the disengage action or a similar action that would not make them provoke attacks of opportunity. If the target uses a teleport type move, then you cannot use this ability, unless they Teleport into your weapon range.\n\nThis is treated as an opportunity attack."},{"id":"unsummon","name":"Unsummon","costLabel":"3 AP","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You have an active Eidolon or Lesser Eidolon.","keywords":["Encounter Conclusion"],"description":"Unsummon your Eidolon or Lesser Eidolon. Recover mana equal to half of the mana cost of the summon cost.\n\nYou may use this as an Encounter Conclusion action."},{"id":"vampire-bite","name":"Vampire Bite","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Unarmed Strike"],"description":"You may make a Light Attack against the target. On damage, you drain 1 mana from the target, recovering 1 mana yourself. If the target has no mana remaining, you instead deal an additional Light damage.\n\nThis unarmed strike must be made with your fangs, but may be made even with both hands full.\n\nDamage done by this ability also reduces the target’s max HP until the target finishes a rest.\n\nA target reduced to 0 HP by this ability is killed and if the target was a heroic unit, it has a chance (GM’s decision) to turn into a vampire subservient to you.\n\nIf the target has any mana remaining and is a willing target, you may choose to not deal damage with this attack."},{"id":"vampire-shapeshift","name":"Vampire Shapeshift","costLabel":"0 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":["Concentration"],"description":"You are able to change your form to that of a rat or bat.\n\nWhile in this form, your size changes to that of the chosen animal and you are treated as a normal animal of that type. You cannot make any attacks or use any abilities while in this form.\n\nYou may exit this form at any time for 0 RP."},{"id":"vampiric-domination","name":"Vampiric Domination","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"20ft","requirement":"Target must be under the effects of Vampiric Fascination","keywords":[],"description":"You mentally dominate the target. The target immediately considers you their master and they will serve you like a loyal servant. You may command them and they will obey most commands. Any command that is obviously suicidal or completely goes against their nature (for example: telling a servant to jump off a cliff or to kill their own child) will end the domination prematurely. This effect lasts until dispelled, they die or until you use Vampiric Domination on another target.\n\nAfter the effect ends, the target will remember everything it was forced to do while it was your servant and it cannot be affected by Vampiric Domination again for a year."},{"id":"vampiric-fascination","name":"Vampiric Fascination","costLabel":"4 AP","apCost":"4","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"Target must be able to see or hear you, Target must be non-heroic.","keywords":["Mind Affecting"],"description":"You charm a non-heroic creature within range. While charmed, the target must spend its AP during its turns on moving towards you in the most direct path possible while avoiding any dangers it is aware of. If it is already next to you, it instead takes no actions.\n\nAt the start of your next turn, you may spend 4 AP to continue the charm. If so, the charm continues until you stop paying the AP cost or until the target takes damage from an attack other than a Vampire Bite.\n\nWhile you have a target under the influence of Vampiric Fascination, your Vampire Bite costs 0 AP and has Sure Hit plus Full Pierce against that target the first time you use it each turn."},{"id":"vanish","name":"Vanish","costLabel":"1 RP, 1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Shadow","Hiding","Stealth"],"description":"You may immediately take the Hide action.\n\nDuring the night, the mana cost of this is reduced by 1."},{"id":"vengeance","name":"Vengeance","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Weapon Range","requirement":"Your VIP was attacked last turn and you re-directed an attack from them to you or your VIP is downed.","keywords":["Lock On","Block Crush"],"description":"You may make a Heavy Attack against the target. If your VIP is at 0 HP or lower, this attack gains Lock On and Guard Crush."},{"id":"venom-strike","name":"Venom Strike","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Weapon Range","requirement":"Must be made with a melee weapon, with a throwing weapon or set of missiles.","keywords":["Poison","Rapid","Toxic"],"description":"You make a Light attack against the target. On damage, inflicts the enemy with Toxic, making them take 1d6 full pierce Poison damage at the start of their turn until they spend 2 AP to remove the poison effect."},{"id":"verdant-instinct","name":"Verdant Instinct","costLabel":"1 Strike Dice","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"1 Strike Dice","range":"","requirement":"Must be in a gathering session.","keywords":[],"description":"Make a gathering check. After rolling, roll two more dice that will be used as your next 2 strike dice values. You may reorder them or replace one with a 5."},{"id":"victory_or_death","name":"Victory or Death","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"In rage stance.","keywords":[],"description":"All melee weapon attacks that you make this turn deal maximum damage on hit. All weapon attacks made against you until the start of your next turn also deal maximum damage on hit.\n\nOnce used, this cannot be used again until the end of the encounter."},{"id":"vip-protection","name":"VIP Protection","costLabel":"0 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"5ft","requirement":"Your VIP is within 5ft of you and is the target of an attack that does not target you as well.","keywords":["Rapid"],"description":"You change the target of the attack to you instead of your VIP.\n\nThis attack automatically hits you and you may not use the Dodge and Block or similar reactions against it.\n\nThe re-directed attack is treated as having most the requirements met as if it was still targeting the original target, including effects that are conditional such as Full Pierce on a downed target, and you are considered to be in the original target's spot for the purposes of range of the attack you're re-directing.\n\nGM's may rule some conditional effects are based on you rather than the original target, such as attacks with effects based on race.\n\nDoes not work against Attacks of Opportunity."},{"id":"vital-drain","name":"Vital Drain","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"20ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Earth","Full Pierce","Healing","Spell"],"description":"You make a Precise Attack against the target creature that deals Earth damage equal to their Toughness with Full Pierce. On damage the current host of Spore Symbiote is healed for the damage dealt.\n\nVital Drain can be casted from the location of the host of your Spore Symbiote."},{"id":"vital-drive","name":"Vital Drive","costLabel":"0 AP, -1 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"-1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Healing"],"description":"You regain HP equal to 5 times the mana spent."},{"id":"vital-drive-ii","name":"Vital Drive II","costLabel":"0 RP, -1 Mana","apCost":"","rpCost":"0","manaCost":"-1","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"You took damage from an attack.","keywords":["Healing"],"description":"You regain HP equal to five times the mana spent. Vital Drive II cannot heal more than the damage you took from the triggering attack."},{"id":"vivisect","name":"Vivisect","costLabel":"3 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"3","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Giant Scissors or Chainsaw only. Target is affected by Expose and is a grunt.","keywords":["-"],"description":"You cut the target in half with your scissors or chainsaw, killing them instantly."},{"id":"volley","name":"Volley","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Scatter"],"description":"You make a Light attack against all targets in a 25x25ft area."},{"id":"wall-formation","name":"Wall Formation","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"Until the start of your next turn, every ally within range gains Wall Formation. If they are adjacent to another ally gains a +1 bonus to their guard and a +4 bonus to their block value."},{"id":"warm_together","name":"Warm Together","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"When you have “Just A Hug” active. You and the target gain resistance to cold from environmental effects."},{"id":"warning_shot","name":"Warning Shot","costLabel":"0 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"Ranged Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":[],"description":"You fire a warning shot against a target in your range. Your next basic attack or Ricochet ability with a pistol against that target gains the Trick Attack keyword."},{"id":"weapon-maintenance","name":"Weapon Maintenance","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"1 Ally’s Smithed Weapon, or your own smithed weapon.","keywords":["Encounter Start","Flashback","Stealth"],"description":"You recall having previously assisted an ally in maintaining their weapon, causing it to be in top shape for battle. This weapon gains a +1 Power Material Bonus or +1 Focus Material Bonus. If you smithed the weapon it gains both. This Artisan bonus is considered the same bonus as from a weapon's material like Tamahagane and does not stack with it.\n\nIf the weapon you choose gets no bonus from this ability, it's critical range instead improves by 1. (A normal weapon now crits on a 19 and 20, a katana on a 18, 19 and 20)."},{"id":"weighing-the-heart","name":"Weighing the Heart","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You get a +5 Expertise bonus to insight checks when looking to discern if someone is lying to you."},{"id":"weight-of-the-mountain","name":"Weight of the Mountain","costLabel":"0 AP","apCost":"0","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"You prepare to strike with enhanced power.\n\nYour next attack with a two-handed melee weapon this turn loses the keywords: Lock On and Sure Hit. In addition, you do not gain accuracy from your Focus on the enhanced attack. The attack also cannot benefit from Offstep and similar effects that guarantee the attack hits.\n\nInstead, the attack deals extra damage equal to the accuracy lost from not gaining Focus due to Weight of the Mountain. If the attack is a heavy or precise attack, it deals extra damage equal to double the accuracy lost instead.\n\nIf the attack made with this effect already did not benefit from focus, this ability has no effect."},{"id":"weight-of-the-world","name":"Weight of the World","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"40ft","requirement":"Target enemy is flying or jumping.","keywords":["Gravity"],"description":"You increase the target’s gravity, reducing their elevation by 40ft. This may interrupt movement and if you reduce their elevation down to 0, you slam them into the ground dealing fall damage for the distance they failed to move and knocking them prone."},{"id":"white-thunder","name":"White Thunder","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"80ft","requirement":"","keywords":["Frost","Slow","Spell","Scatter"],"description":"You target a Glacial Wall in range and fire a bolt of Frost energy that requires line of sight. On impact, the wall is destroyed and explodes into blades of ice, attacking all enemies within 5ft of the destroyed wall with a Precise attack that deals Frost damage. On damage, the target is Slowed until the end of their next turn."},{"id":"wild-thrusts","name":"Wild Thrusts","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Polearm only.","keywords":["Scatter"],"description":"You rapidly thrust your weapon in front of you, making a Light attack against all enemies in a 15ft wide, 10ft long box in front of you. Until the start of your next turn, you may make Attacks of Opportunity against any enemy walking through that box. You cannot make any other Attacks of Opportunity while this effect lasts.\n\nYou may cancel this effect for 0 RP."},{"id":"wind-blast","name":"Wind Blast","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Spell","Wind"],"description":"You may make a Light Attack that deals Wind against the target. On damage, you push the target back 20ft. Targets knocked into other characters or an object take damage as if they fell a distance equal to distance they failed to move."},{"id":"wind-blast-ii","name":"Wind Blast II","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"120ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Spell","Wind"],"description":"You may make a Light (1 AP), Precise (2 AP) or Heavy Attack (2 AP) that deals Wind damage against the target. On damage, you push the target back 20ft."},{"id":"wind-buffet","name":"Wind Buffet","costLabel":"2 AP, 2 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"2","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft cone","requirement":"-","keywords":["Spell","Wind"],"description":"You blow wind in a 30ft, 60ft degree cone in your chosen direction. All caught in the cone must make a save against your Potency or be blown back to the end of the cone and knocked Prone. Enemies with a size smaller than you suffer a 1d4 penalty to this roll, while enemies bigger than you get a 1d4 bonus instead. Targets knocked into other characters or an object take damage as if they fell a distance equal to distance they failed to move."},{"id":"wind-infusion","name":"Wind Infusion","costLabel":"1 AP, 0 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"0","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Spell","Type","Wind"],"description":"You surround the willing target in protective winds, changing their typing to Wind II. As a Wind II type, they take regular damage from all other elements, but only half damage from Wind or Earth damage or from attacks with the Wind or Earth keyword unless that attack deals true damage. They take 50% more damage from Frost damage or attacks with the Frost keyword. While the ward lasts, they gain a +2 bonus to their Evasion against ranged weapon attacks. The ward lasts until the end of the encounter or until their type is overwritten by a more powerful type."},{"id":"wind-scatter","name":"Wind Scatter","costLabel":"1 AP","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Spell","Wind"],"description":"You select a point within range. All targets in a 15x15 area must make a save against Potency or be pushed back 15ft away from the point you selected.\n\nTargets knocked into other characters or an object take damage as if they fell a distance equal to distance they failed to move."},{"id":"wind-shield","name":"Wind Shield","costLabel":"1 RP","apCost":"","rpCost":"1","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"30ft","requirement":"Ally is targeted by a ranged attack.","keywords":["Aid","Shield","Spell"],"description":"You grant the target 1 RP that must be spent on the basic Dodge or Block action against the triggering attack as well as Wind Shield. Wind Shield grants a bonus to Dodge equal to your Focus against the triggering attack. The triggering attack can also no longer benefit from Lock On or Sure Hit"},{"id":"wind-wall","name":"Wind Wall","costLabel":"2 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Concentration","Spell","Wind"],"description":"You create a wall of wind that is 30ft long, 5ft wide and 10ft high that slows down all ranged weapon attacks passing through it, treating them as having only half the normal range. This wall must be a straight line. These attacks also lose the Lock On, Sure Hit, Half Pierce, Guard Crush and Full Pierce keywords. In addition, the targets of those attacks are treated as having +2 Evasion and +1 Guard. Any Spells that are considered attacks (those that require an accuracy roll against a person that isn’t using the Block reaction) that pass through the wall also suffer this penalty."},{"id":"wind-empowered-aim","name":"Wind-Empowered Aim","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Self","requirement":"-","keywords":["Aura","Upkeep"],"description":"You project Wind-Empowered Aim aura around yourself that empowers the ranged attacks of your allies. When a heroic ally within 20ft of you (including yourself) makes a ranged attack, they may add 1d4 to the accuracy roll. Upkeep: You must spend 1 AP at the start of each turn or the Aura fades."},{"id":"wind-up-punch","name":"Wind-up Punch","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"-","keywords":["Overcharge","Unarmed Strike"],"description":"You may make a Heavy attack against the target. Overcharge: You may spend additional AP when using this ability to deal an additional Light Damage per AP used. Add all of this damage together before applying damage reduction from Guard or abilities."},{"id":"wire-sweep","name":"Wire Sweep","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"20ft","requirement":"Saboteur Threaded Dagger only.","keywords":[],"description":"You whip your wire to ensnare the target. If they fail their save against your Potency+2 they are rendered Prone and take Light Damage."},{"id":"wither-the-stalk","name":"Wither the Stalk","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"Melee Weapon Range","requirement":"Scythe only","keywords":["-"],"description":"You strike an enemy with an attack that saps their strength. You make a Light attack against the target. On damage, the target cannot add their Power for damage to their next attack.\n\nDoes not work against Boss enemies."},{"id":"x-attack","name":"X-Attack","costLabel":"2 AP","apCost":"2","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"Sight","requirement":"Can only target your summoned animal.","keywords":["-"],"description":"You give your summon a +1 Focus and +1 Power buff."},{"id":"zap","name":"Zap","costLabel":"1 AP, 1 Mana","apCost":"1","rpCost":"","manaCost":"1","otherCosts":"","range":"60ft","requirement":"-","keywords":["Lightning","Lock On","Spell"],"description":"You may make a Light attack against the target, dealing Lightning damage. On damage, inflict Static X where X equals your Focus X 3."},{"id":"zhen-jiao","name":"Zhen Jiao","costLabel":"","apCost":"","rpCost":"","manaCost":"","otherCosts":"","range":"","requirement":"","keywords":[],"description":"When you move toward an enemy as part of a Martial Artist or Bajiquan ability due to Fire Stance or an inherent move effect of the ability (such as Rushing Knee Drop), your attack deals three extra points of damage for every 5ft moved. If your attack hits more than once or more than one target, you only apply this damage once."}]};
